INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1001, 'After the death of Moses the servant of the Lord, it came to pass that the Lord spoke to Joshua the son of Nun, Moses&rsquo; assistant, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1002, 'Moses My servant is dead. Now therefore, arise, go over this Jordan, you and all this people, to the land which I am giving to them &ndash; the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1003, 'Every place that the sole of your foot will tread upon I have given you, as I said to Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1004, 'From the wilderness and this Lebanon as far as the great river, the River Euphrates, all the land of the Hittites, and to the Great Sea toward the going down of the sun, shall be your territory. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1005, 'No man shall be able to stand before you all the days of your life; as I was with Moses, so I will be with you. I will not leave you nor forsake you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1006, 'Be strong and of good courage, for to this people you shall divide as an inheritance the land which I swore to their fathers to give them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1007, 'Only be strong and very courageous, that you may observe to do according to all the law which Moses My servant commanded you; do not turn from it to the right hand or to the left, that you may prosper wherever you go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1008, 'This Book of the Law shall not depart from your mouth, but you shall meditate in it day and night, that you may observe to do according to all that is written in it. For then you will make your way prosperous, and then you will have good success. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1009, 'Have I not commanded you? Be strong and of good courage; do not be afraid, nor be dismayed, for the Lord your God is with you wherever you go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1010, 'Then Joshua commanded the officers of the people, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1011, 'Pass through the camp and command the people, saying, &lsquo;Prepare provisions for yourselves, for within three days you will cross over this Jordan, to go in to possess the land which the Lord your God is giving you to possess.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1012, 'And to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh Joshua spoke, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1013, 'Remember the word which Moses the servant of the Lord commanded you, saying, &lsquo;The Lord your God is giving you rest and is giving you this land.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1014, 'Your wives, your little ones, and your livestock shall remain in the land which Moses gave you on this side of the Jordan. But you shall pass before your brethren armed, all your mighty men of valor, and help them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1015, 'until the Lord has given your brethren rest, as He gave you, and they also have taken possession of the land which the Lord your God is giving them. Then you shall return to the land of your possession and enjoy it, which Moses the Lord&rsquo;s servant gave you on this side of the Jordan toward the sunrise. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1016, 'So they answered Joshua, saying, &ldquo;All that you command us we will do, and wherever you send us we will go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1017, 'Just as we heeded Moses in all things, so we will heed you. Only the Lord your God be with you, as He was with Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 1018, 'Whoever rebels against your command and does not heed your words, in all that you command him, shall be put to death. Only be strong and of good courage.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2001, 'Now Joshua the son of Nun sent out two men from Acacia Grove* to spy secretly, saying, &ldquo;Go, view the land, especially Jericho.&rdquo; So they went, and came to the house of a harlot named Rahab, and lodged there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2002, 'And it was told the king of Jericho, saying, &ldquo;Behold, men have come here tonight from the children of Israel to search out the country.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2003, 'So the king of Jericho sent to Rahab, saying, &ldquo;Bring out the men who have come to you, who have entered your house, for they have come to search out all the country.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2004, 'Then the woman took the two men and hid them. So she said, &ldquo;Yes, the men came to me, but I did not know where they were from. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2005, 'And it happened as the gate was being shut, when it was dark, that the men went out. Where the men went I do not know; pursue them quickly, for you may overtake them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2006, '(But she had brought them up to the roof and hidden them with the stalks of flax, which she had laid in order on the roof.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2007, 'Then the men pursued them by the road to the Jordan, to the fords. And as soon as those who pursued them had gone out, they shut the gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2008, 'Now before they lay down, she came up to them on the roof, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2009, 'and said to the men: &ldquo;I know that the Lord has given you the land, that the terror of you has fallen on us, and that all the inhabitants of the land are fainthearted because of you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2010, 'For we have heard how the Lord dried up the water of the Red Sea for you when you came out of Egypt, and what you did to the two kings of the Amorites who were on the other side of the Jordan, Sihon and Og, whom you utterly destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2011, 'And as soon as we heard these things, our hearts melted; neither did there remain any more courage in anyone because of you, for the Lord your God, He is God in heaven above and on earth beneath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2012, 'Now therefore, I beg you, swear to me by the Lord, since I have shown you kindness, that you also will show kindness to my father&rsquo;s house, and give me a true token, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2013, 'and spare my father, my mother, my brothers, my sisters, and all that they have, and deliver our lives from death.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2014, 'So the men answered her, &ldquo;Our lives for yours, if none of you tell this business of ours. And it shall be, when the Lord has given us the land, that we will deal kindly and truly with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2015, 'Then she let them down by a rope through the window, for her house was on the city wall; she dwelt on the wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2016, 'And she said to them, &ldquo;Get to the mountain, lest the pursuers meet you. Hide there three days, until the pursuers have returned. Afterward you may go your way.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2017, 'So the men said to her: &ldquo;We will be blameless of this oath of yours which you have made us swear, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2018, 'unless, when we come into the land, you bind this line of scarlet cord in the window through which you let us down, and unless you bring your father, your mother, your brothers, and all your father&rsquo;s household to your own home. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2019, 'So it shall be that whoever goes outside the doors of your house into the street, his blood shall be on his own head, and we will be guiltless. And whoever is with you in the house, his blood shall be on our head if a hand is laid on him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2020, 'And if you tell this business of ours, then we will be free from your oath which you made us swear.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2021, 'Then she said, &ldquo;According to your words, so be it.&rdquo; And she sent them away, and they departed. And she bound the scarlet cord in the window. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2022, 'They departed and went to the mountain, and stayed there three days until the pursuers returned. The pursuers sought them all along the way, but did not find them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2023, 'So the two men returned, descended from the mountain, and crossed over; and they came to Joshua the son of Nun, and told him all that had befallen them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 2024, 'And they said to Joshua, &ldquo;Truly the Lord has delivered all the land into our hands, for indeed all the inhabitants of the country are fainthearted because of us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3001, 'Then Joshua rose early in the morning; and they set out from Acacia Grove* and came to the Jordan, he and all the children of Israel, and lodged there before they crossed over. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3002, 'So it was, after three days, that the officers went through the camp; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3003, 'and they commanded the people, saying, &ldquo;When you see the ark of the covenant of the Lord your God, and the priests, the Levites, bearing it, then you shall set out from your place and go after it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3004, 'Yet there shall be a space between you and it, about two thousand cubits by measure. Do not come near it, that you may know the way by which you must go, for you have not passed this way before.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3005, 'And Joshua said to the people, &ldquo;Sanctify yourselves, for tomorrow the Lord will do wonders among you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3006, 'Then Joshua spoke to the priests, saying, &ldquo;Take up the ark of the covenant and cross over before the people.&rdquo; So they took up the ark of the covenant and went before the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3007, 'And the* Lord said to Joshua, &ldquo;This day I will begin to exalt you in the sight of all Israel, that they may know that, as I was with Moses, so I will be with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3008, 'You shall command the priests who bear the ark of the covenant, saying, &lsquo;When you have come to the edge of the water of the Jordan, you shall stand in the Jordan.&rsquo;&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3009, 'So Joshua said to the children of Israel, &ldquo;Come here, and hear the words of the Lord your God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3010, 'And Joshua said, &ldquo;By this you shall know that the living God is among you, and that He will without fail drive out from before you the Canaanites and the Hittites and the Hivites and the Perizzites and the Girgashites and the Amorites and the Jebusites: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3011, 'Behold, the ark of the covenant of the Lord of all the earth is crossing over before you into the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3012, 'Now therefore, take for yourselves twelve men from the tribes of Israel, one man from every tribe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3013, 'And it shall come to pass, as soon as the soles of the feet of the priests who bear the ark of the Lord, the Lord of all the earth, shall rest in the waters of the Jordan, that the waters of the Jordan shall be cut off, the waters that come down from upstream, and they shall stand as a heap.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3014, 'So it was, when the people set out from their camp to cross over the Jordan, with the priests bearing the ark of the covenant before the people, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3015, 'and* as those who bore the ark came to the Jordan, and the feet of the priests who bore the ark dipped in the edge of the water (for the Jordan overflows all its banks during the whole time of harvest), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3016, 'that the waters which came down from upstream stood still, and rose in a heap very far away at Adam, the city that is beside Zaretan. So the waters that went down into the Sea of the Arabah, the Salt Sea, failed, and were cut off; and the people crossed over opposite Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 3017, 'Then the priests who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord stood firm on dry ground in the midst of the Jordan; and all Israel crossed over on dry ground, until all the people had crossed completely over the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4001, 'And it came to pass, when all the people had completely crossed over the Jordan, that the Lord spoke to Joshua, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4002, 'Take for yourselves twelve men from the people, one man from every tribe, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4003, 'and command them, saying, &lsquo;Take for yourselves twelve stones from here, out of the midst of the Jordan, from the place where the priests&rsquo; feet stood firm. You shall carry them over with you and leave them in the lodging place where you lodge tonight.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4004, 'Then Joshua called the twelve men whom he had appointed from the children of Israel, one man from every tribe; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4005, 'and Joshua said to them: &ldquo;Cross over before the ark of the Lord your God into the midst of the Jordan, and each one of you take up a stone on his shoulder, according to the number of the tribes of the children of Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4006, 'that this may be a sign among you when your children ask in time to come, saying, &lsquo;What do these stones mean to you?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4007, 'Then you shall answer them that the waters of the Jordan were cut off before the ark of the covenant of the Lord; when it crossed over the Jordan, the waters of the Jordan were cut off. And these stones shall be for a memorial to the children of Israel forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4008, 'And the children of Israel did so, just as Joshua commanded, and took up twelve stones from the midst of the Jordan, as the Lord had spoken to Joshua, according to the number of the tribes of the children of Israel, and carried them over with them to the place where they lodged, and laid them down there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4009, 'Then Joshua set up twelve stones in the midst of the Jordan, in the place where the feet of the priests who bore the ark of the covenant stood; and they are there to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4010, 'So the priests who bore the ark stood in the midst of the Jordan until everything was finished that the Lord had commanded Joshua to speak to the people, according to all that Moses had commanded Joshua; and the people hurried and crossed over. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4011, 'Then it came to pass, when all the people had completely crossed over, that the ark of the Lord and the priests crossed over in the presence of the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4012, 'And the men of Reuben, the men of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh crossed over armed before the children of Israel, as Moses had spoken to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4013, 'About forty thousand prepared for war crossed over before the Lord for battle, to the plains of Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4014, 'On that day the Lord exalted Joshua in the sight of all Israel; and they feared him, as they had feared Moses, all the days of his life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4015, 'Then the Lord spoke to Joshua, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4016, 'Command the priests who bear the ark of the Testimony to come up from the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4017, 'Joshua therefore commanded the priests, saying, &ldquo;Come up from the Jordan.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4018, 'And it came to pass, when the priests who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord had come from the midst of the Jordan, and the soles of the priests&rsquo; feet touched the dry land, that the waters of the Jordan returned to their place and overflowed all its banks as before. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4019, 'Now the people came up from the Jordan on the tenth day of the first month, and they camped in Gilgal on the east border of Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4020, 'And those twelve stones which they took out of the Jordan, Joshua set up in Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4021, 'Then he spoke to the children of Israel, saying: &ldquo;When your children ask their fathers in time to come, saying, &lsquo;What are these stones?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4022, 'then you shall let your children know, saying, &lsquo;Israel crossed over this Jordan on dry land&rsquo;; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4023, 'for the Lord your God dried up the waters of the Jordan before you until you had crossed over, as the Lord your God did to the Red Sea, which He dried up before us until we had crossed over, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 4024, 'that all the peoples of the earth may know the hand of the Lord, that it is mighty, that you may fear the Lord your God forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5001, 'So it was, when all the kings of the Amorites who were on the west side of the Jordan, and all the kings of the Canaanites who were by the sea, heard that the Lord had dried up the waters of the Jordan from before the children of Israel until we* had crossed over, that their heart melted; and there was no spirit in them any longer because of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5002, 'At that time the Lord said to Joshua, &ldquo;Make flint knives for yourself, and circumcise the sons of Israel again the second time.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5003, 'So Joshua made flint knives for himself, and circumcised the sons of Israel at the hill of the foreskins.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5004, 'And this is the reason why Joshua circumcised them: All the people who came out of Egypt who were males, all the men of war, had died in the wilderness on the way, after they had come out of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5005, 'For all the people who came out had been circumcised, but all the people born in the wilderness, on the way as they came out of Egypt, had not been circumcised. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5006, 'For the children of Israel walked forty years in the wilderness, till all the people who were men of war, who came out of Egypt, were consumed, because they did not obey the voice of the Lord &ndash; to whom the Lord swore that He would not show them the land which the Lord had sworn to their fathers that He would give us, &ldquo;a land flowing with milk and honey.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5007, 'Then Joshua circumcised their sons whom He raised up in their place; for they were uncircumcised, because they had not been circumcised on the way. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5008, 'So it was, when they had finished circumcising all the people, that they stayed in their places in the camp till they were healed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5009, 'Then the Lord said to Joshua, &ldquo;This day I have rolled away the reproach of Egypt from you.&rdquo; Therefore the name of the place is called Gilgal to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5010, 'Now the* children of Israel camped in Gilgal, and kept the Passover on the fourteenth day of the month at twilight on the plains of Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5011, 'And they ate of the produce of the land on the day after the Passover, unleavened bread and parched grain, on the very same day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5012, 'Then the manna ceased on the day after they had eaten the produce of the land; and the children of Israel no longer had manna, but they ate the food of the land of Canaan that year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5013, 'And it came to pass, when Joshua was by Jericho, that he lifted his eyes and looked, and behold, a Man stood opposite him with His sword drawn in His hand. And Joshua went to Him and said to Him, &ldquo;Are You for us or for our adversaries?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5014, 'So He said, &ldquo;No, but as Commander of the army of the Lord I have now come.&rdquo; And Joshua fell on his face to the earth and worshiped, and said to Him, &ldquo;What does my Lord say to His servant?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 5015, 'Then the Commander of the Lord&rsquo;s army said to Joshua, &ldquo;Take your sandal off your foot, for the place where you stand is holy.&rdquo;| And Joshua did so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6001, 'Now Jericho was securely shut up because of the children of Israel; none went out, and none came in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6002, 'And the Lord said to Joshua: &ldquo;See! I have given Jericho into your hand, its king, and the mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6003, 'You shall march around the city, all you men of war; you shall go all around the city once. This you shall do six days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6004, 'And seven priests shall bear seven trumpets of rams&rsquo; horns before the ark. But the seventh day you shall march around the city seven times, and the priests shall blow the trumpets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6005, 'It shall come to pass, when they make a long blast with the ram&rsquo;s horn, and when you hear the sound of the trumpet, that all the people shall shout with a great shout; then the wall of the city will fall down flat. And the people shall go up every man straight before him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6006, 'Then Joshua the son of Nun called the priests and said to them, &ldquo;Take up the ark of the covenant, and let seven priests bear seven trumpets of rams&rsquo; horns before the ark of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6007, 'And he said to the people, &ldquo;Proceed, and march around the city, and let him who is armed advance before the ark of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6008, 'So it was, when Joshua had spoken to the people, that the seven priests bearing the seven trumpets of rams&rsquo; horns before the Lord advanced and blew the trumpets, and the ark of the covenant of the Lord followed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6009, 'The armed men went before the priests who blew the trumpets, and the rear guard came after the ark, while the priests continued blowing the trumpets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6010, 'Now Joshua had commanded the people, saying, &ldquo;You shall not shout or make any noise with your voice, nor shall a word proceed out of your mouth, until the day I say to you, &lsquo;Shout!&rsquo; Then you shall shout.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6011, 'So he had the ark of the Lord circle the city, going around it once. Then they came into the camp and lodged in the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6012, 'And Joshua rose early in the morning, and the priests took up the ark of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6013, 'Then seven priests bearing seven trumpets of rams&rsquo; horns before the ark of the Lord went on continually and blew with the trumpets. And the armed men went before them. But the rear guard came after the ark of the Lord, while the priests continued blowing the trumpets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6014, 'And the second day they marched around the city once and returned to the camp. So they did six days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6015, 'But it came to pass on the seventh day that they rose early, about the dawning of the day, and marched around the city seven times in the same manner. On that day only they marched around the city seven times. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6016, 'And the seventh time it happened, when the priests blew the trumpets, that Joshua said to the people: &ldquo;Shout, for the Lord has given you the city! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6017, 'Now the city shall be doomed by the Lord to destruction, it and all who are in it. Only Rahab the harlot shall live, she and all who are with her in the house, because she hid the messengers that we sent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6018, 'And you, by all means abstain from the accursed things, lest you become accursed when you take of the accursed things, and make the camp of Israel a curse, and trouble it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6019, 'But all the silver and gold, and vessels of bronze and iron, are consecrated to the Lord; they shall come into the treasury of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6020, 'So the people shouted when the priests blew the trumpets. And it happened when the people heard the sound of the trumpet, and the people shouted with a great shout, that the wall fell down flat. Then the people went up into the city, every man straight before him, and they took the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6021, 'And they utterly destroyed all that was in the city, both man and woman, young and old, ox and sheep and donkey, with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6022, 'But Joshua had said to the two men who had spied out the country, &ldquo;Go into the harlot&rsquo;s house, and from there bring out the woman and all that she has, as you swore to her.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6023, 'And the young men who had been spies went in and brought out Rahab, her father, her mother, her brothers, and all that she had. So they brought out all her relatives and left them outside the camp of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6024, 'But they burned the city and all that was in it with fire. Only the silver and gold, and the vessels of bronze and iron, they put into the treasury of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6025, 'And Joshua spared Rahab the harlot, her father&rsquo;s household, and all that she had. So she dwells in Israel to this day, because she hid the messengers whom Joshua sent to spy out Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6026, 'Then Joshua charged them at that time, saying, &ldquo;Cursed be the man before the Lord who rises up and builds this city Jericho; he shall lay its foundation with his firstborn, and with his youngest he shall set up its gates.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 6027, 'So the Lord was with Joshua, and his fame spread throughout all the country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7001, 'But the children of Israel committed a trespass regarding the accursed things, for Achan the son of Carmi, the son of Zabdi,* the son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, took of the accursed things; so the anger of the Lord burned against the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7002, 'Now Joshua sent men from Jericho to Ai, which is beside Beth Aven, on the east side of Bethel, and spoke to them, saying, &ldquo;Go up and spy out the country.&rdquo; So the men went up and spied out Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7003, 'And they returned to Joshua and said to him, &ldquo;Do not let all the people go up, but let about two or three thousand men go up and attack Ai. Do not weary all the people there, for the people of Ai are few.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7004, 'So about three thousand men went up there from the people, but they fled before the men of Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7005, 'And the men of Ai struck down about thirty-six men, for they chased them from before the gate as far as Shebarim, and struck them down on the descent; therefore the hearts of the people melted and became like water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7006, 'Then Joshua tore his clothes, and fell to the earth on his face before the ark of the Lord until evening, he and the elders of Israel; and they put dust on their heads. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7007, 'And Joshua said, &ldquo;Alas, Lord God, why have You brought this people over the Jordan at all &ndash; to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites, to destroy us? Oh, that we had been content, and dwelt on the other side of the Jordan! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7008, 'O Lord, what shall I say when Israel turns its back before its enemies? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7009, 'For the Canaanites and all the inhabitants of the land will hear it, and surround us, and cut off our name from the earth. Then what will You do for Your great name?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7010, 'So the Lord said to Joshua: &ldquo;Get up! Why do you lie thus on your face? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7011, 'Israel has sinned, and they have also transgressed My covenant which I commanded them. For they have even taken some of the accursed things, and have both stolen and deceived; and they have also put it among their own stuff. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7012, 'Therefore the children of Israel could not stand before their enemies, but turned their backs before their enemies, because they have become doomed to destruction. Neither will I be with you anymore, unless you destroy the accursed from among you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7013, 'Get up, sanctify the people, and say, &lsquo;Sanctify yourselves for tomorrow, because thus says the Lord God of Israel: &ldquo;There is an accursed thing in your midst, O Israel; you cannot stand before your enemies until you take away the accursed thing from among you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7014, 'In the morning therefore you shall be brought according to your tribes. And it shall be that the tribe which the Lord takes shall come according to families; and the family which the Lord takes shall come by households; and the household which the Lord takes shall come man by man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7015, 'Then it shall be that he who is taken with the accursed thing shall be burned with fire, he and all that he has, because he has transgressed the covenant of the Lord, and because he has done a disgraceful thing in Israel.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7016, 'So Joshua rose early in the morning and brought Israel by their tribes, and the tribe of Judah was taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7017, 'He brought the clan of Judah, and he took the family of the Zarhites; and he brought the family of the Zarhites man by man, and Zabdi was taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7018, 'Then he brought his household man by man, and Achan the son of Carmi, the son of Zabdi, the son of Zerah, of the tribe of Judah, was taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7019, 'Now Joshua said to Achan, &ldquo;My son, I beg you, give glory to the Lord God of Israel, and make confession to Him, and tell me now what you have done; do not hide it from me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7020, 'And Achan answered Joshua and said, &ldquo;Indeed I have sinned against the Lord God of Israel, and this is what I have done: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7021, 'When I saw among the spoils a beautiful Babylonian garment, two hundred shekels of silver, and a wedge of gold weighing fifty shekels, I coveted them and took them. And there they are, hidden in the earth in the midst of my tent, with the silver under it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7022, 'So Joshua sent messengers, and they ran to the tent; and there it was, hidden in his tent, with the silver under it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7023, 'And they took them from the midst of the tent, brought them to Joshua and to all the children of Israel, and laid them out before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7024, 'Then Joshua, and all Israel with him, took Achan the son of Zerah, the silver, the garment, the wedge of gold, his sons, his daughters, his oxen, his donkeys, his sheep, his tent, and all that he had, and they brought them to the Valley of Achor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7025, 'And Joshua said, &ldquo;Why have you troubled us? The Lord will trouble you this day.&rdquo; So all Israel stoned him with stones; and they burned them with fire after they had stoned them with stones. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 7026, 'Then they raised over him a great heap of stones, still there to this day. So the Lord turned from the fierceness of His anger. Therefore the name of that place has been called the Valley of Achor to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8001, 'Now the Lord said to Joshua: &ldquo;Do not be afraid, nor be dismayed; take all the people of war with you, and arise, go up to Ai. See, I have given into your hand the king of Ai, his people, his city, and his land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8002, 'And you shall do to Ai and its king as you did to Jericho and its king. Only its spoil and its cattle you shall take as booty for yourselves. Lay an ambush for the city behind it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8003, 'So Joshua arose, and all the people of war, to go up against Ai; and Joshua chose thirty thousand mighty men of valor and sent them away by night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8004, 'And he commanded them, saying: &ldquo;Behold, you shall lie in ambush against the city, behind the city. Do not go very far from the city, but all of you be ready. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8005, 'Then I and all the people who are with me will approach the city; and it will come about, when they come out against us as at the first, that we shall flee before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8006, 'For they will come out after us till we have drawn them from the city, for they will say, &lsquo;They are fleeing before us as at the first.&rsquo; Therefore we will flee before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8007, 'Then you shall rise from the ambush and seize the city, for the Lord your God will deliver it into your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8008, 'And it will be, when you have taken the city, that you shall set the city on fire. According to the commandment of the Lord you shall do. See, I have commanded you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8009, 'Joshua therefore sent them out; and they went to lie in ambush, and stayed between Bethel and Ai, on the west side of Ai; but Joshua lodged that night among the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8010, 'Then Joshua rose up early in the morning and mustered the people, and went up, he and the elders of Israel, before the people to Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8011, 'And all the people of war who were with him went up and drew near; and they came before the city and camped on the north side of Ai. Now a valley lay between them and Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8012, 'So he took about five thousand men and set them in ambush between Bethel and Ai, on the west side of the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8013, 'And when they had set the people, all the army that was on the north of the city, and its rear guard on the west of the city, Joshua went that night into the midst of the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8014, 'Now it happened, when the king of Ai saw it, that the men of the city hurried and rose early and went out against Israel to battle, he and all his people, at an appointed place before the plain. But he did not know that there was an ambush against him behind the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8015, 'And Joshua and all Israel made as if they were beaten before them, and fled by the way of the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8016, 'So all the people who were in Ai were called together to pursue them. And they pursued Joshua and were drawn away from the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8017, 'There was not a man left in Ai or Bethel who did not go out after Israel. So they left the city open and pursued Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8018, 'Then the Lord said to Joshua, &ldquo;Stretch out the spear that is in your hand toward Ai, for I will give it into your hand.&rdquo; And Joshua stretched out the spear that was in his hand toward the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8019, 'So those in ambush arose quickly out of their place; they ran as soon as he had stretched out his hand, and they entered the city and took it, and hurried to set the city on fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8020, 'And when the men of Ai looked behind them, they saw, and behold, the smoke of the city ascended to heaven. So they had no power to flee this way or that way, and the people who had fled to the wilderness turned back on the pursuers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8021, 'Now when Joshua and all Israel saw that the ambush had taken the city and that the smoke of the city ascended, they turned back and struck down the men of Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8022, 'Then the others came out of the city against them; so they were caught in the midst of Israel, some on this side and some on that side. And they struck them down, so that they let none of them remain or escape. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8023, 'But the king of Ai they took alive, and brought him to Joshua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8024, 'And it came to pass when Israel had made an end of slaying all the inhabitants of Ai in the field, in the wilderness where they pursued them, and when they all had fallen by the edge of the sword until they were consumed, that all the Israelites returned to Ai and struck it with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8025, 'So it was that all who fell that day, both men and women, were twelve thousand &ndash; all the people of Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8026, 'For Joshua did not draw back his hand, with which he stretched out the spear, until he had utterly destroyed all the inhabitants of Ai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8027, 'Only the livestock and the spoil of that city Israel took as booty for themselves, according to the word of the Lord which He had commanded Joshua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8028, 'So Joshua burned Ai and made it a heap forever, a desolation to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8029, 'And the king of Ai he hanged on a tree until evening. And as soon as the sun was down, Joshua commanded that they should take his corpse down from the tree, cast it at the entrance of the gate of the city, and raise over it a great heap of stones that remains to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8030, 'Now Joshua built an altar to the Lord God of Israel in Mount Ebal, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8031, 'as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded the children of Israel, as it is written in the Book of the Law of Moses: &ldquo;an altar of whole stones over which no man has wielded an iron tool.&rdquo; And they offered on it burnt offerings to the Lord, and sacrificed peace offerings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8032, 'And there, in the presence of the children of Israel, he wrote on the stones a copy of the law of Moses, which he had written. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8033, 'Then all Israel, with their elders and officers and judges, stood on either side of the ark before the priests, the Levites, who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord, the stranger as well as he who was born among them. Half of them were in front of Mount Gerizim and half of them in front of Mount Ebal, as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded before, that they should bless the people of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8034, 'And afterward he read all the words of the law, the blessings and the cursings, according to all that is written in the Book of the Law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 8035, 'There was not a word of all that Moses had commanded which Joshua did not read before all the assembly of Israel, with the women, the little ones, and the strangers who were living among them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9001, 'And it came to pass when all the kings who were on this side of the Jordan, in the hills and in the lowland and in all the coasts of the Great Sea toward Lebanon &ndash; the Hittite, the Amorite, the Canaanite, the Perizzite, the Hivite, and the Jebusite &ndash; heard about it, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9002, 'that they gathered together to fight with Joshua and Israel with one accord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9003, 'But when the inhabitants of Gibeon heard what Joshua had done to Jericho and Ai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9004, 'they worked craftily, and went and pretended to be ambassadors. And they took old sacks on their donkeys, old wineskins torn and mended, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9005, 'old and patched sandals on their feet, and old garments on themselves; and all the bread of their provision was dry and moldy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9006, 'And they went to Joshua, to the camp at Gilgal, and said to him and to the men of Israel, &ldquo;We have come from a far country; now therefore, make a covenant with us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9007, 'Then the men of Israel said to the Hivites, &ldquo;Perhaps you dwell among us; so how can we make a covenant with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9008, 'But they said to Joshua, &ldquo;We are your servants.&rdquo; And Joshua said to them, &ldquo;Who are you, and where do you come from?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9009, 'So they said to him: &ldquo;From a very far country your servants have come, because of the name of the Lord your God; for we have heard of His fame, and all that He did in Egypt, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9010, 'and all that He did to the two kings of the Amorites who were beyond the Jordan &ndash; to Sihon king of Heshbon, and Og king of Bashan, who was at Ashtaroth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9011, 'Therefore our elders and all the inhabitants of our country spoke to us, saying, &lsquo;Take provisions with you for the journey, and go to meet them, and say to them, &ldquo;We are your servants; now therefore, make a covenant with us.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9012, 'This bread of ours we took hot for our provision from our houses on the day we departed to come to you. But now look, it is dry and moldy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9013, 'And these wineskins which we filled were new, and see, they are torn; and these our garments and our sandals have become old because of the very long journey.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9014, 'Then the men of Israel took some of their provisions; but they did not ask counsel of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9015, 'So Joshua made peace with them, and made a covenant with them to let them live; and the rulers of the congregation swore to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9016, 'And it happened at the end of three days, after they had made a covenant with them, that they heard that they were their neighbors who dwelt near them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9017, 'Then the children of Israel journeyed and came to their cities on the third day. Now their cities were Gibeon, Chephirah, Beeroth, and Kirjath Jearim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9018, 'But the children of Israel did not attack them, because the rulers of the congregation had sworn to them by the Lord God of Israel. And all the congregation complained against the rulers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9019, 'Then all the rulers said to all the congregation, &ldquo;We have sworn to them by the Lord God of Israel; now therefore, we may not touch them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9020, 'This we will do to them: We will let them live, lest wrath be upon us because of the oath which we swore to them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9021, 'And the rulers said to them, &ldquo;Let them live, but let them be woodcutters and water carriers for all the congregation, as the rulers had promised them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9022, 'Then Joshua called for them, and he spoke to them, saying, &ldquo;Why have you deceived us, saying, &lsquo;We are very far from you,&rsquo; when you dwell near us? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9023, 'Now therefore, you are cursed, and none of you shall be freed from being slaves &ndash; woodcutters and water carriers for the house of my God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9024, 'So they answered Joshua and said, &ldquo;Because your servants were clearly told that the Lord your God commanded His servant Moses to give you all the land, and to destroy all the inhabitants of the land from before you; therefore we were very much afraid for our lives because of you, and have done this thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9025, 'And now, here we are, in your hands; do with us as it seems good and right to do to us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9026, 'So he did to them, and delivered them out of the hand of the children of Israel, so that they did not kill them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 9027, 'And that day Joshua made them woodcutters and water carriers for the congregation and for the altar of the Lord, in the place which He would choose, even to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10001, 'Now it came to pass when Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem heard how Joshua had taken Ai and had utterly destroyed it &ndash; as he had done to Jericho and its king, so he had done to Ai and its king &ndash; and how the inhabitants of Gibeon had made peace with Israel and were among them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10002, 'that they feared greatly, because Gibeon was a great city, like one of the royal cities, and because it was greater than Ai, and all its men were mighty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10003, 'Therefore Adoni-Zedek king of Jerusalem sent to Hoham king of Hebron, Piram king of Jarmuth, Japhia king of Lachish, and Debir king of Eglon, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10004, 'Come up to me and help me, that we may attack Gibeon, for it has made peace with Joshua and with the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10005, 'Therefore the five kings of the Amorites, the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon, gathered together and went up, they and all their armies, and camped before Gibeon and made war against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10006, 'And the men of Gibeon sent to Joshua at the camp at Gilgal, saying, &ldquo;Do not forsake your servants; come up to us quickly, save us and help us, for all the kings of the Amorites who dwell in the mountains have gathered together against us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10007, 'So Joshua ascended from Gilgal, he and all the people of war with him, and all the mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10008, 'And the Lord said to Joshua, &ldquo;Do not fear them, for I have delivered them into your hand; not a man of them shall stand before you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10009, 'Joshua therefore came upon them suddenly, having marched all night from Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10010, 'So the Lord routed them before Israel, killed them with a great slaughter at Gibeon, chased them along the road that goes to Beth Horon, and struck them down as far as Azekah and Makkedah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10011, 'And it happened, as they fled before Israel and were on the descent of Beth Horon, that the Lord cast down large hailstones from heaven on them as far as Azekah, and they died. There were more who died from the hailstones than the children of Israel killed with the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10012, 'Then Joshua spoke to the Lord in the day when the Lord delivered up the Amorites before the children of Israel, and he said in the sight of Israel: &ldquo;Sun, stand still over Gibeon; And Moon, in the Valley of Aijalon.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10013, 'So the sun stood still, And the moon stopped, Till the people had revenge Upon their enemies. Is this not written in the Book of Jasher? So the sun stood still in the midst of heaven, and did not hasten to go down for about a whole day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10014, 'And there has been no day like that, before it or after it, that the Lord heeded the voice of a man; for the Lord fought for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10015, 'Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10016, 'But these five kings had fled and hidden themselves in a cave at Makkedah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10017, 'And it was told Joshua, saying, &ldquo;The five kings have been found hidden in the cave at Makkedah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10018, 'So Joshua said, &ldquo;Roll large stones against the mouth of the cave, and set men by it to guard them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10019, 'And do not stay there yourselves, but pursue your enemies, and attack their rear guard. Do not allow them to enter their cities, for the Lord your God has delivered them into your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10020, 'Then it happened, while Joshua and the children of Israel made an end of slaying them with a very great slaughter, till they had finished, that those who escaped entered fortified cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10021, 'And all the people returned to the camp, to Joshua at Makkedah, in peace. No one moved his tongue against any of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10022, 'Then Joshua said, &ldquo;Open the mouth of the cave, and bring out those five kings to me from the cave.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10023, 'And they did so, and brought out those five kings to him from the cave: the king of Jerusalem, the king of Hebron, the king of Jarmuth, the king of Lachish, and the king of Eglon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10024, 'So it was, when they brought out those kings to Joshua, that Joshua called for all the men of Israel, and said to the captains of the men of war who went with him, &ldquo;Come near, put your feet on the necks of these kings.&rdquo; And they drew near and put their feet on their necks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10025, 'Then Joshua said to them, &ldquo;Do not be afraid, nor be dismayed; be strong and of good courage, for thus the Lord will do to all your enemies against whom you fight.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10026, 'And afterward Joshua struck them and killed them, and hanged them on five trees; and they were hanging on the trees until evening. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10027, 'So it was at the time of the going down of the sun that Joshua commanded, and they took them down from the trees, cast them into the cave where they had been hidden, and laid large stones against the cave&rsquo;s mouth, which remain until this very day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10028, 'On that day Joshua took Makkedah, and struck it and its king with the edge of the sword. He utterly destroyed them* &ndash; all the people who were in it. He let none remain. He also did to the king of Makkedah as he had done to the king of Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10029, 'Then Joshua passed from Makkedah, and all Israel with him, to Libnah; and they fought against Libnah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10030, 'And the Lord also delivered it and its king into the hand of Israel; he struck it and all the people who were in it with the edge of the sword. He let none remain in it, but did to its king as he had done to the king of Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10031, 'Then Joshua passed from Libnah, and all Israel with him, to Lachish; and they encamped against it and fought against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10032, 'And the Lord delivered Lachish into the hand of Israel, who took it on the second day, and struck it and all the people who were in it with the edge of the sword, according to all that he had done to Libnah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10033, 'Then Horam king of Gezer came up to help Lachish; and Joshua struck him and his people, until he left him none remaining. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10034, 'From Lachish Joshua passed to Eglon, and all Israel with him; and they encamped against it and fought against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10035, 'They took it on that day and struck it with the edge of the sword; all the people who were in it he utterly destroyed that day, according to all that he had done to Lachish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10036, 'So Joshua went up from Eglon, and all Israel with him, to Hebron; and they fought against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10037, 'And they took it and struck it with the edge of the sword &ndash; its king, all its cities, and all the people who were in it; he left none remaining, according to all that he had done to Eglon, but utterly destroyed it and all the people who were in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10038, 'Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to Debir; and they fought against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10039, 'And he took it and its king and all its cities; they struck them with the edge of the sword and utterly destroyed all the people who were in it. He left none remaining; as he had done to Hebron, so he did to Debir and its king, as he had done also to Libnah and its king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10040, 'So Joshua conquered all the land: the mountain country and the South and the lowland and the wilderness slopes, and all their kings; he left none remaining, but utterly destroyed all that breathed, as the Lord God of Israel had commanded. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10041, 'And Joshua conquered them from Kadesh Barnea as far as Gaza, and all the country of Goshen, even as far as Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10042, 'All these kings and their land Joshua took at one time, because the Lord God of Israel fought for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 10043, 'Then Joshua returned, and all Israel with him, to the camp at Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11001, 'And it came to pass, when Jabin king of Hazor heard these things, that he sent to Jobab king of Madon, to the king of Shimron, to the king of Achshaph, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11002, 'and to the kings who were from the north, in the mountains, in the plain south of Chinneroth, in the lowland, and in the heights of Dor on the west, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11003, 'to the Canaanites in the east and in the west, the Amorite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Jebusite in the mountains, and the Hivite below Hermon in the land of Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11004, 'So they went out, they and all their armies with them, as many people as the sand that is on the seashore in multitude, with very many horses and chariots. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11005, 'And when all these kings had met together, they came and camped together at the waters of Merom to fight against Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11006, 'But the Lord said to Joshua, &ldquo;Do not be afraid because of them, for tomorrow about this time I will deliver all of them slain before Israel. You shall hamstring their horses and burn their chariots with fire.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11007, 'So Joshua and all the people of war with him came against them suddenly by the waters of Merom, and they attacked them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11008, 'And the Lord delivered them into the hand of Israel, who defeated them and chased them to Greater Sidon, to the Brook Misrephoth, and to the Valley of Mizpah eastward; they attacked them until they left none of them remaining. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11009, 'So Joshua did to them as the Lord had told him: he hamstrung their horses and burned their chariots with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11010, 'Joshua turned back at that time and took Hazor, and struck its king with the sword; for Hazor was formerly the head of all those kingdoms. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11011, 'And they struck all the people who were in it with the edge of the sword, utterly destroying them. There was none left breathing. Then he burned Hazor with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11012, 'So all the cities of those kings, and all their kings, Joshua took and struck with the edge of the sword. He utterly destroyed them, as Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11013, 'But as for the cities that stood on their mounds, Israel burned none of them, except Hazor only, which Joshua burned. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11014, 'And all the spoil of these cities and the livestock, the children of Israel took as booty for themselves; but they struck every man with the edge of the sword until they had destroyed them, and they left none breathing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11015, 'As the Lord had commanded Moses his servant, so Moses commanded Joshua, and so Joshua did. He left nothing undone of all that the Lord had commanded Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11016, 'Thus Joshua took all this land: the mountain country, all the South, all the land of Goshen, the lowland, and the Jordan plain* &ndash; the mountains of Israel and its lowlands, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11017, 'from Mount Halak and the ascent to Seir, even as far as Baal Gad in the Valley of Lebanon below Mount Hermon. He captured all their kings, and struck them down and killed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11018, 'Joshua made war a long time with all those kings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11019, 'There was not a city that made peace with the children of Israel, except the Hivites, the inhabitants of Gibeon. All the others they took in battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11020, 'For it was of the Lord to harden their hearts, that they should come against Israel in battle, that He might utterly destroy them, and that they might receive no mercy, but that He might destroy them, as the Lord had commanded Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11021, 'And at that time Joshua came and cut off the Anakim from the mountains: from Hebron, from Debir, from Anab, from all the mountains of Judah, and from all the mountains of Israel; Joshua utterly destroyed them with their cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11022, 'None of the Anakim were left in the land of the children of Israel; they remained only in Gaza, in Gath, and in Ashdod. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 11023, 'So Joshua took the whole land, according to all that the Lord had said to Moses; and Joshua gave it as an inheritance to Israel according to their divisions by their tribes. Then the land rested from war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12001, 'These are the kings of the land whom the children of Israel defeated, and whose land they possessed on the other side of the Jordan toward the rising of the sun, from the River Arnon to Mount Hermon, and all the eastern Jordan plain: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12002, 'One king was Sihon king of the Amorites, who dwelt in Heshbon and ruled half of Gilead, from Aroer, which is on the bank of the River Arnon, from the middle of that river, even as far as the River Jabbok, which is the border of the Ammonites, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12003, 'and the eastern Jordan plain from the Sea of Chinneroth as far as the Sea of the Arabah (the Salt Sea), the road to Beth Jeshimoth, and southward below the slopes of Pisgah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12004, 'The other king was Og king of Bashan and his territory, who was of the remnant of the giants, who dwelt at Ashtaroth and at Edrei, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12005, 'and reigned over Mount Hermon, over Salcah, over all Bashan, as far as the border of the Geshurites and the Maachathites, and over half of Gilead to the border of Sihon king of Heshbon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12006, 'These Moses the servant of the Lord and the children of Israel had conquered; and Moses the servant of the Lord had given it as a possession to the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12007, 'And these are the kings of the country which Joshua and the children of Israel conquered on this side of the Jordan, on the west, from Baal Gad in the Valley of Lebanon as far as Mount Halak and the ascent to Seir, which Joshua gave to the tribes of Israel as a possession according to their divisions, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12008, 'in the mountain country, in the lowlands, in the Jordan plain, in the slopes, in the wilderness, and in the South &ndash; the Hittites, the Amorites, the Canaanites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12009, 'the king of Jericho, one; the king of Ai, which is beside Bethel, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12010, 'the king of Jerusalem, one; the king of Hebron, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12011, 'the king of Jarmuth, one; the king of Lachish, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12012, 'the king of Eglon, one; the king of Gezer, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12013, 'the king of Debir, one; the king of Geder, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12014, 'the king of Hormah, one; the king of Arad, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12015, 'the king of Libnah, one; the king of Adullam, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12016, 'the king of Makkedah, one; the king of Bethel, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12017, 'the king of Tappuah, one; the king of Hepher, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12018, 'the king of Aphek, one; the king of Lasharon, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12019, 'the king of Madon, one; the king of Hazor, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12020, 'the king of Shimron Meron, one; the king of Achshaph, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12021, 'the king of Taanach, one; the king of Megiddo, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12022, 'the king of Kedesh, one; the king of Jokneam in Carmel, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12023, 'the king of Dor in the heights of Dor, one; the king of the people of Gilgal, one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 12024, 'the king of Tirzah, one &ndash; all the kings, thirty-one. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13001, 'Now Joshua was old, advanced in years. And the Lord said to him: &ldquo;You are old, advanced in years, and there remains very much land yet to be possessed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13002, 'This is the land that yet remains: all the territory of the Philistines and all that of the Geshurites, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13003, 'from Sihor, which is east of Egypt, as far as the border of Ekron northward (which is counted as Canaanite); the five lords of the Philistines &ndash; the Gazites, the Ashdodites, the Ashkelonites, the Gittites, and the Ekronites; also the Avites; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13004, 'from the south, all the land of the Canaanites, and Mearah that belongs to the Sidonians as far as Aphek, to the border of the Amorites; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13005, 'the land of the Gebalites, and all Lebanon, toward the sunrise, from Baal Gad below Mount Hermon as far as the entrance to Hamath; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13006, 'all the inhabitants of the mountains from Lebanon as far as the Brook Misrephoth, and all the Sidonians &ndash; them I will drive out from before the children of Israel; only divide it by lot to Israel as an inheritance, as I have commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13007, 'Now therefore, divide this land as an inheritance to the nine tribes and half the tribe of Manasseh.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13008, 'With the other half tribe the Reubenites and the Gadites received their inheritance, which Moses had given them, beyond the Jordan eastward, as Moses the servant of the Lord had given them: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13009, 'from Aroer which is on the bank of the River Arnon, and the town that is in the midst of the ravine, and all the plain of Medeba as far as Dibon; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13010, 'all the cities of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, as far as the border of the children of Ammon; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13011, 'Gilead, and the border of the Geshurites and Maachathites, all Mount Hermon, and all Bashan as far as Salcah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13012, 'all the kingdom of Og in Bashan, who reigned in Ashtaroth and Edrei, who remained of the remnant of the giants; for Moses had defeated and cast out these. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13013, 'Nevertheless the children of Israel did not drive out the Geshurites or the Maachathites, but the Geshurites and the Maachathites dwell among the Israelites until this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13014, 'Only to the tribe of Levi he had given no inheritance; the sacrifices of the Lord God of Israel made by fire are their inheritance, as He said to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13015, 'And Moses had given to the tribe of the children of Reuben an inheritance according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13016, 'Their territory was from Aroer, which is on the bank of the River Arnon, and the city that is in the midst of the ravine, and all the plain by Medeba; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13017, 'Heshbon and all its cities that are in the plain: Dibon, Bamoth Baal, Beth Baal Meon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13018, 'Jahaza, Kedemoth, Mephaath, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13019, 'Kirjathaim, Sibmah, Zereth Shahar on the mountain of the valley, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13020, 'Beth Peor, the slopes of Pisgah, and Beth Jeshimoth &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13021, 'all the cities of the plain and all the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites, who reigned in Heshbon, whom Moses had struck with the princes of Midian: Evi, Rekem, Zur, Hur, and Reba, who were princes of Sihon dwelling in the country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13022, 'The children of Israel also killed with the sword Balaam the son of Beor, the soothsayer, among those who were killed by them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13023, 'And the border of the children of Reuben was the bank of the Jordan. This was the inheritance of the children of Reuben according to their families, the cities and their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13024, 'Moses also had given an inheritance to the tribe of Gad, to the children of Gad according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13025, 'Their territory was Jazer, and all the cities of Gilead, and half the land of the Ammonites as far as Aroer, which is before Rabbah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13026, 'and from Heshbon to Ramath Mizpah and Betonim, and from Mahanaim to the border of Debir, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13027, 'and in the valley Beth Haram, Beth Nimrah, Succoth, and Zaphon, the rest of the kingdom of Sihon king of Heshbon, with the Jordan as its border, as far as the edge of the Sea of Chinnereth, on the other side of the Jordan eastward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13028, 'This is the inheritance of the children of Gad according to their families, the cities and their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13029, 'Moses also had given an inheritance to half the tribe of Manasseh; it was for half the tribe of the children of Manasseh according to their families: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13030, 'Their territory was from Mahanaim, all Bashan, all the kingdom of Og king of Bashan, and all the towns of Jair which are in Bashan, sixty cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13031, 'half of Gilead, and Ashtaroth and Edrei, cities of the kingdom of Og in Bashan, were for the children of Machir the son of Manasseh, for half of the children of Machir according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13032, 'These are the areas which Moses had distributed as an inheritance in the plains of Moab on the other side of the Jordan, by Jericho eastward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 13033, 'But to the tribe of Levi Moses had given no inheritance; the Lord God of Israel was their inheritance, as He had said to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14001, 'These are the areas which the children of Israel inherited in the land of Canaan, which Eleazar the priest, Joshua the son of Nun, and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel distributed as an inheritance to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14002, 'Their inheritance was by lot, as the Lord had commanded by the hand of Moses, for the nine tribes and the half-tribe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14003, 'For Moses had given the inheritance of the two tribes and the half-tribe on the other side of the Jordan; but to the Levites he had given no inheritance among them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14004, 'For the children of Joseph were two tribes: Manasseh and Ephraim. And they gave no part to the Levites in the land, except cities to dwell in, with their common-lands for their livestock and their property. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14005, 'As the Lord had commanded Moses, so the children of Israel did; and they divided the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14006, 'Then the children of Judah came to Joshua in Gilgal. And Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite said to him: &ldquo;You know the word which the Lord said to Moses the man of God concerning you and me in Kadesh Barnea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14007, 'I was forty years old when Moses the servant of the Lord sent me from Kadesh Barnea to spy out the land, and I brought back word to him as it was in my heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14008, 'Nevertheless my brethren who went up with me made the heart of the people melt, but I wholly followed the Lord my God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14009, 'So Moses swore on that day, saying, &lsquo;Surely the land where your foot has trodden shall be your inheritance and your children&rsquo;s forever, because you have wholly followed the Lord my God.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14010, 'And now, behold, the Lord has kept me alive, as He said, these forty-five years, ever since the Lord spoke this word to Moses while Israel wandered in the wilderness; and now, here I am this day, eighty-five years old. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14011, 'As yet I am as strong this day as on the day that Moses sent me; just as my strength was then, so now is my strength for war, both for going out and for coming in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14012, 'Now therefore, give me this mountain of which the Lord spoke in that day; for you heard in that day how the Anakim were there, and that the cities were great and fortified. It may be that the Lord will be with me, and I shall be able to drive them out as the Lord said.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14013, 'And Joshua blessed him, and gave Hebron to Caleb the son of Jephunneh as an inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14014, 'Hebron therefore became the inheritance of Caleb the son of Jephunneh the Kenizzite to this day, because he wholly followed the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 14015, 'And the name of Hebron formerly was Kirjath Arba (Arba was the greatest man among the Anakim). Then the land had rest from war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15001, 'So this was the lot of the tribe of the children of Judah according to their families: The border of Edom at the Wilderness of Zin southward was the extreme southern boundary. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15002, 'And their southern border began at the shore of the Salt Sea, from the bay that faces southward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15003, 'Then it went out to the southern side of the Ascent of Akrabbim, passed along to Zin, ascended on the south side of Kadesh Barnea, passed along to Hezron, went up to Adar, and went around to Karkaa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15004, 'From there it passed toward Azmon and went out to the Brook of Egypt; and the border ended at the sea. This shall be your southern border. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15005, 'The east border was the Salt Sea as far as the mouth of the Jordan. And the border on the northern quarter began at the bay of the sea at the mouth of the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15006, 'The border went up to Beth Hoglah and passed north of Beth Arabah; and the border went up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15007, 'Then the border went up toward Debir from the Valley of Achor, and it turned northward toward Gilgal, which is before the Ascent of Adummim, which is on the south side of the valley. The border continued toward the waters of En Shemesh and ended at En Rogel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15008, 'And the border went up by the Valley of the Son of Hinnom to the southern slope of the Jebusite city (which is Jerusalem). The border went up to the top of the mountain that lies before the Valley of Hinnom westward, which is at the end of the Valley of Rephaim northward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15009, 'Then the border went around from the top of the hill to the fountain of the water of Nephtoah, and extended to the cities of Mount Ephron. And the border went around to Baalah (which is Kirjath Jearim). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15010, 'Then the border turned westward from Baalah to Mount Seir, passed along to the side of Mount Jearim on the north (which is Chesalon), went down to Beth Shemesh, and passed on to Timnah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15011, 'And the border went out to the side of Ekron northward. Then the border went around to Shicron, passed along to Mount Baalah, and extended to Jabneel; and the border ended at the sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15012, 'The west border was the coastline of the Great Sea. This is the boundary of the children of Judah all around according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15013, 'Now to Caleb the son of Jephunneh he gave a share among the children of Judah, according to the commandment of the Lord to Joshua, namely, Kirjath Arba, which is Hebron (Arba was the father of Anak). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15014, 'Caleb drove out the three sons of Anak from there: Sheshai, Ahiman, and Talmai, the children of Anak. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15015, 'Then he went up from there to the inhabitants of Debir (formerly the name of Debir was Kirjath Sepher). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15016, 'And Caleb said, &ldquo;He who attacks Kirjath Sepher and takes it, to him I will give Achsah my daughter as wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15017, 'So Othniel the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it; and he gave him Achsah his daughter as wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15018, 'Now it was so, when she came to him, that she persuaded him to ask her father for a field. So she dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said to her, &ldquo;What do you wish?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15019, 'She answered, &ldquo;Give me a blessing; since you have given me land in the South, give me also springs of water.&rdquo; So he gave her the upper springs and the lower springs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15020, 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Judah according to their families: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15021, 'The cities at the limits of the tribe of the children of Judah, toward the border of Edom in the South, were Kabzeel, Eder, Jagur, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15022, 'Kinah, Dimonah, Adadah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15023, 'Kedesh, Hazor, Ithnan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15024, 'Ziph, Telem, Bealoth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15025, 'Hazor, Hadattah, Kerioth, Hezron (which is Hazor), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15026, 'Amam, Shema, Moladah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15027, 'Hazar Gaddah, Heshmon, Beth Pelet, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15028, 'Hazar Shual, Beersheba, Bizjothjah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15029, 'Baalah, Ijim, Ezem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15030, 'Eltolad, Chesil, Hormah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15031, 'Ziklag, Madmannah, Sansannah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15032, 'Lebaoth, Shilhim, Ain, and Rimmon: all the cities are twenty-nine, with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15033, 'In the lowland: Eshtaol, Zorah, Ashnah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15034, 'Zanoah, En Gannim, Tappuah, Enam, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15035, 'Jarmuth, Adullam, Socoh, Azekah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15036, 'Sharaim, Adithaim, Gederah, and Gederothaim: fourteen cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15037, 'Zenan, Hadashah, Migdal Gad, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15038, 'Dilean, Mizpah, Joktheel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15039, 'Lachish, Bozkath, Eglon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15040, 'Cabbon, Lahmas, Kithlish, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15041, 'Gederoth, Beth Dagon, Naamah, and Makkedah: sixteen cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15042, 'Libnah, Ether, Ashan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15043, 'Jiphtah, Ashnah, Nezib, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15044, 'Keilah, Achzib, and Mareshah: nine cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15045, 'Ekron, with its towns and villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15046, 'from Ekron to the sea, all that lay near Ashdod, with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15047, 'Ashdod with its towns and villages, Gaza with its towns and villages &ndash; as far as the Brook of Egypt and the Great Sea with its coastline. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15048, 'And in the mountain country: Shamir, Jattir, Sochoh, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15049, 'Dannah, Kirjath Sannah (which is Debir), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15050, 'Anab, Eshtemoh, Anim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15051, 'Goshen, Holon, and Giloh: eleven cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15052, 'Arab, Dumah, Eshean, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15053, 'Janum, Beth Tappuah, Aphekah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15054, 'Humtah, Kirjath Arba (which is Hebron), and Zior: nine cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15055, 'Maon, Carmel, Ziph, Juttah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15056, 'Jezreel, Jokdeam, Zanoah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15057, 'Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah: ten cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15058, 'Halhul, Beth Zur, Gedor, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15059, 'Maarath, Beth Anoth, and Eltekon: six cities with their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15060, 'Kirjath Baal (which is Kirjath Jearim) and Rabbah: two cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15061, 'In the wilderness: Beth Arabah, Middin, Secacah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15062, 'Nibshan, the City of Salt, and En Gedi: six cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 15063, 'As for the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the children of Judah could not drive them out; but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Judah at Jerusalem to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16001, 'The lot fell to the children of Joseph from the Jordan, by Jericho, to the waters of Jericho on the east, to the wilderness that goes up from Jericho through the mountains to Bethel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16002, 'then went out from Bethel to Luz, passed along to the border of the Archites at Ataroth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16003, 'and went down westward to the boundary of the Japhletites, as far as the boundary of Lower Beth Horon to Gezer; and it ended at the sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16004, 'So the children of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, took their inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16005, 'The border of the children of Ephraim, according to their families, was thus: The border of their inheritance on the east side was Ataroth Addar as far as Upper Beth Horon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16006, 'And the border went out toward the sea on the north side of Michmethath; then the border went around eastward to Taanath Shiloh, and passed by it on the east of Janohah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16007, 'Then it went down from Janohah to Ataroth and Naarah, reached to Jericho, and came out at the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16008, 'The border went out from Tappuah westward to the Brook Kanah, and it ended at the sea. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Ephraim according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16009, 'The separate cities for the children of Ephraim were among the inheritance of the children of Manasseh, all the cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 16010, 'And they did not drive out the Canaanites who dwelt in Gezer; but the Canaanites dwell among the Ephraimites to this day and have become forced laborers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17001, 'There was also a lot for the tribe of Manasseh, for he was the firstborn of Joseph: namely for Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead, because he was a man of war; therefore he was given Gilead and Bashan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17002, 'And there was a lot for the rest of the children of Manasseh according to their families: for the children of Abiezer, the children of Helek, the children of Asriel, the children of Shechem, the children of Hepher, and the children of Shemida; these were the male children of Manasseh the son of Joseph according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17003, 'But Zelophehad the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, had no sons, but only daughters. And these are the names of his daughters: Mahlah, Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17004, 'And they came near before Eleazar the priest, before Joshua the son of Nun, and before the rulers, saying, &ldquo;The Lord commanded Moses to give us an inheritance among our brothers.&rdquo; Therefore, according to the commandment of the Lord, he gave them an inheritance among their father&rsquo;s brothers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17005, 'Ten shares fell to Manasseh, besides the land of Gilead and Bashan, which were on the other side of the Jordan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17006, 'because the daughters of Manasseh received an inheritance among his sons; and the rest of Manasseh&rsquo;s sons had the land of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17007, 'And the territory of Manasseh was from Asher to Michmethath, that lies east of Shechem; and the border went along south to the inhabitants of En Tappuah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17008, 'Manasseh had the land of Tappuah, but Tappuah on the border of Manasseh belonged to the children of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17009, 'And the border descended to the Brook Kanah, southward to the brook. These cities of Ephraim are among the cities of Manasseh. The border of Manasseh was on the north side of the brook; and it ended at the sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17010, 'Southward it was Ephraim&rsquo;s, northward it was Manasseh&rsquo;s, and the sea was its border. Manasseh&rsquo;s territory was adjoining Asher on the north and Issachar on the east. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17011, 'And in Issachar and in Asher, Manasseh had Beth Shean and its towns, Ibleam and its towns, the inhabitants of Dor and its towns, the inhabitants of En Dor and its towns, the inhabitants of Taanach and its towns, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and its towns &ndash; three hilly regions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17012, 'Yet the children of Manasseh could not drive out the inhabitants of those cities, but the Canaanites were determined to dwell in that land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17013, 'And it happened, when the children of Israel grew strong, that they put the Canaanites to forced labor, but did not utterly drive them out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17014, 'Then the children of Joseph spoke to Joshua, saying, &ldquo;Why have you given us only one lot and one share to inherit, since we are a great people, inasmuch as the Lord has blessed us until now?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17015, 'So Joshua answered them, &ldquo;If you are a great people, then go up to the forest country and clear a place for yourself there in the land of the Perizzites and the giants, since the mountains of Ephraim are too confined for you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17016, 'But the children of Joseph said, &ldquo;The mountain country is not enough for us; and all the Canaanites who dwell in the land of the valley have chariots of iron, both those who are of Beth Shean and its towns and those who are of the Valley of Jezreel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17017, 'And Joshua spoke to the house of Joseph &ndash; to Ephraim and Manasseh &ndash; saying, &ldquo;You are a great people and have great power; you shall not have only one lot, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 17018, 'but the mountain country shall be yours. Although it is wooded, you shall cut it down, and its farthest extent shall be yours; for you shall drive out the Canaanites, though they have iron chariots and are strong.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18001, 'Now the whole congregation of the children of Israel assembled together at Shiloh, and set up the tabernacle of meeting there. And the land was subdued before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18002, 'But there remained among the children of Israel seven tribes which had not yet received their inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18003, 'Then Joshua said to the children of Israel: &ldquo;How long will you neglect to go and possess the land which the Lord God of your fathers has given you? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18004, 'Pick out from among you three men for each tribe, and I will send them; they shall rise and go through the land, survey it according to their inheritance, and come back to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18005, 'And they shall divide it into seven parts. Judah shall remain in their territory on the south, and the house of Joseph shall remain in their territory on the north. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18006, 'You shall therefore survey the land in seven parts and bring the survey here to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the Lord our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18007, 'But the Levites have no part among you, for the priesthood of the Lord is their inheritance. And Gad, Reuben, and half the tribe of Manasseh have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan on the east, which Moses the servant of the Lord gave them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18008, 'Then the men arose to go away; and Joshua charged those who went to survey the land, saying, &ldquo;Go, walk through the land, survey it, and come back to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the Lord in Shiloh.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18009, 'So the men went, passed through the land, and wrote the survey in a book in seven parts by cities; and they came to Joshua at the camp in Shiloh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18010, 'Then Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the Lord, and there Joshua divided the land to the children of Israel according to their divisions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18011, 'Now the lot of the tribe of the children of Benjamin came up according to their families, and the territory of their lot came out between the children of Judah and the children of Joseph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18012, 'Their border on the north side began at the Jordan, and the border went up to the side of Jericho on the north, and went up through the mountains westward; it ended at the Wilderness of Beth Aven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18013, 'The border went over from there toward Luz, to the side of Luz (which is Bethel) southward; and the border descended to Ataroth Addar, near the hill that lies on the south side of Lower Beth Horon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18014, 'Then the border extended around the west side to the south, from the hill that lies before Beth Horon southward; and it ended at Kirjath Baal (which is Kirjath Jearim), a city of the children of Judah. This was the west side. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18015, 'The south side began at the end of Kirjath Jearim, and the border extended on the west and went out to the spring of the waters of Nephtoah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18016, 'Then the border came down to the end of the mountain that lies before the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, which is in the Valley of the Rephaim on the north, descended to the Valley of Hinnom, to the side of the Jebusite city on the south, and descended to En Rogel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18017, 'And it went around from the north, went out to En Shemesh, and extended toward Geliloth, which is before the Ascent of Adummim, and descended to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18018, 'Then it passed along toward the north side of Arabah, and went down to Arabah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18019, 'And the border passed along to the north side of Beth Hoglah; then the border ended at the north bay at the Salt Sea, at the south end of the Jordan. This was the southern boundary. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18020, 'The Jordan was its border on the east side. This was the inheritance of the children of Benjamin, according to its boundaries all around, according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 18021, 'Now the cities of the tribe of the children of Benjamin, according to their families, were Jericho, Beth Hoglah, Emek Keziz, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19001, 'The second lot came out for Simeon, for the tribe of the children of Simeon according to their families. And their inheritance was within the inheritance of the children of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19002, 'They had in their inheritance Beersheba (Sheba), Moladah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19003, 'Hazar Shual, Balah, Ezem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19004, 'Eltolad, Bethul, Hormah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19005, 'Ziklag, Beth Marcaboth, Hazar Susah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19006, 'Beth Lebaoth, and Sharuhen: thirteen cities and their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19007, 'Ain, Rimmon, Ether, and Ashan: four cities and their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19008, 'and all the villages that were all around these cities as far as Baalath Beer, Ramah of the South. This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Simeon according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19009, 'The inheritance of the children of Simeon was included in the share of the children of Judah, for the share of the children of Judah was too much for them. Therefore the children of Simeon had their inheritance within the inheritance of that people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19010, 'The third lot came out for the children of Zebulun according to their families, and the border of their inheritance was as far as Sarid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19011, 'Their border went toward the west and to Maralah, went to Dabbasheth, and extended along the brook that is east of Jokneam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19012, 'Then from Sarid it went eastward toward the sunrise along the border of Chisloth Tabor, and went out toward Daberath, bypassing Japhia. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19013, 'And from there it passed along on the east of Gath Hepher, toward Eth Kazin, and extended to Rimmon, which borders on Neah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19014, 'Then the border went around it on the north side of Hannathon, and it ended in the Valley of Jiphthah El. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19015, 'Included were Kattath, Nahallal, Shimron, Idalah, and Bethlehem: twelve cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19016, 'This was the inheritance of the children of Zebulun according to their families, these cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19017, 'The fourth lot came out to Issachar, for the children of Issachar according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19018, 'And their territory went to Jezreel, and included Chesulloth, Shunem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19019, 'Haphraim, Shion, Anaharath, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19020, 'Rabbith, Kishion, Abez, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19021, 'Remeth, En Gannim, En Haddah, and Beth Pazzez. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19022, 'And the border reached to Tabor, Shahazimah, and Beth Shemesh; their border ended at the Jordan: sixteen cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19023, 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Issachar according to their families, the cities and their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19024, 'The fifth lot came out for the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19025, 'And their territory included Helkath, Hali, Beten, Achshaph, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19026, 'Alammelech, Amad, and Mishal; it reached to Mount Carmel westward, along the Brook Shihor Libnath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19027, 'It turned toward the sunrise to Beth Dagon; and it reached to Zebulun and to the Valley of Jiphthah El, then northward beyond Beth Emek and Neiel, bypassing Cabul which was on the left, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19028, 'including Ebron, Rehob, Hammon, and Kanah, as far as Greater Sidon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19029, 'And the border turned to Ramah and to the fortified city of Tyre; then the border turned to Hosah, and ended at the sea by the region of Achzib. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19030, 'Also Ummah, Aphek, and Rehob were included: twenty-two cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19031, 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families, these cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19032, 'The sixth lot came out to the children of Naphtali, for the children of Naphtali according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19033, 'And their border began at Heleph, enclosing the territory from the terebinth tree in Zaanannim, Adami Nekeb, and Jabneel, as far as Lakkum; it ended at the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19034, 'From Heleph the border extended westward to Aznoth Tabor, and went out from there toward Hukkok; it adjoined Zebulun on the south side and Asher on the west side, and ended at Judah by the Jordan toward the sunrise. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19035, 'And the fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, Hammath, Rakkath, Chinnereth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19036, 'Adamah, Ramah, Hazor, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19037, 'Kedesh, Edrei, En Hazor, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19038, 'Iron, Migdal El, Horem, Beth Anath, and Beth Shemesh: nineteen cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19039, 'This was the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Naphtali according to their families, the cities and their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19040, 'The seventh lot came out for the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19041, 'And the territory of their inheritance was Zorah, Eshtaol, Ir Shemesh, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19042, 'Shaalabbin, Aijalon, Jethlah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19043, 'Elon, Timnah, Ekron, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19044, 'Eltekeh, Gibbethon, Baalath, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19045, 'Jehud, Bene Berak, Gath Rimmon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19046, 'Me Jarkon, and Rakkon, with the region near Joppa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19047, 'And the border of the children of Dan went beyond these, because the children of Dan went up to fight against Leshem and took it; and they struck it with the edge of the sword, took possession of it, and dwelt in it. They called Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19048, 'This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families, these cities with their villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19049, 'When they had made an end of dividing the land as an inheritance according to their borders, the children of Israel gave an inheritance among them to Joshua the son of Nun. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19050, 'According to the word of the Lord they gave him the city which he asked for, Timnath Serah in the mountains of Ephraim; and he built the city and dwelt in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 19051, 'These were the inheritances which Eleazar the priest, Joshua the son of Nun, and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel divided as an inheritance by lot in Shiloh before the Lord, at the door of the tabernacle of meeting. So they made an end of dividing the country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20001, 'The Lord also spoke to Joshua, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20002, 'Speak to the children of Israel, saying: &lsquo;Appoint for yourselves cities of refuge, of which I spoke to you through Moses, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20003, 'that the slayer who kills a person accidentally or unintentionally may flee there; and they shall be your refuge from the avenger of blood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20004, 'And when he flees to one of those cities, and stands at the entrance of the gate of the city, and declares his case in the hearing of the elders of that city, they shall take him into the city as one of them, and give him a place, that he may dwell among them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20005, 'Then if the avenger of blood pursues him, they shall not deliver the slayer into his hand, because he struck his neighbor unintentionally, but did not hate him beforehand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20006, 'And he shall dwell in that city until he stands before the congregation for judgment, and until the death of the one who is high priest in those days. Then the slayer may return and come to his own city and his own house, to the city from which he fled.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20007, 'So they appointed Kedesh in Galilee, in the mountains of Naphtali, Shechem in the mountains of Ephraim, and Kirjath Arba (which is Hebron) in the mountains of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20008, 'And on the other side of the Jordan, by Jericho eastward, they assigned Bezer in the wilderness on the plain, from the tribe of Reuben, Ramoth in Gilead, from the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan, from the tribe of Manasseh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 20009, 'These were the cities appointed for all the children of Israel and for the stranger who dwelt among them, that whoever killed a person accidentally might flee there, and not die by the hand of the avenger of blood until he stood before the congregation. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21001, 'Then the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the Levites came near to Eleazar the priest, to Joshua the son of Nun, and to the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the tribes of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21002, 'And they spoke to them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, saying, &ldquo;The Lord commanded through Moses to give us cities to dwell in, with their common-lands for our livestock.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21003, 'So the children of Israel gave to the Levites from their inheritance, at the commandment of the Lord, these cities and their common-lands: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21004, 'Now the lot came out for the families of the Kohathites. And the children of Aaron the priest, who were of the Levites, had thirteen cities by lot from the tribe of Judah, from the tribe of Simeon, and from the tribe of Benjamin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21005, 'The rest of the children of Kohath had ten cities by lot from the families of the tribe of Ephraim, from the tribe of Dan, and from the half-tribe of Manasseh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21006, 'And the children of Gershon had thirteen cities by lot from the families of the tribe of Issachar, from the tribe of Asher, from the tribe of Naphtali, and from the half-tribe of Manasseh in Bashan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21007, 'The children of Merari according to their families had twelve cities from the tribe of Reuben, from the tribe of Gad, and from the tribe of Zebulun. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21008, 'And the children of Israel gave these cities with their common-lands by lot to the Levites, as the Lord had commanded by the hand of Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21009, 'So they gave from the tribe of the children of Judah and from the tribe of the children of Simeon these cities which are designated by name, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21010, 'which were for the children of Aaron, one of the families of the Kohathites, who were of the children of Levi; for the lot was theirs first. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21011, 'And they gave them Kirjath Arba (Arba was the father of Anak), which is Hebron, in the mountains of Judah, with the common-land surrounding it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21012, 'But the fields of the city and its villages they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh as his possession. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21013, 'Thus to the children of Aaron the priest they gave Hebron with its common-land (a city of refuge for the slayer), Libnah with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21014, 'Jattir with its common-land, Eshtemoa with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21015, 'Holon with its common-land, Debir with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21016, 'Ain with its common-land, Juttah with its common-land, and Beth Shemesh with its common-land: nine cities from those two tribes; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21017, 'and from the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon with its common-land, Geba with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21018, 'Anathoth with its common-land, and Almon with its common-land: four cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21019, 'All the cities of the children of Aaron, the priests, were thirteen cities with their common-lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21020, 'And the families of the children of Kohath, the Levites, the rest of the children of Kohath, even they had the cities of their lot from the tribe of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21021, 'For they gave them Shechem with its common-land in the mountains of Ephraim (a city of refuge for the slayer), Gezer with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21022, 'Kibzaim with its common-land, and Beth Horon with its common-land: four cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21023, 'and from the tribe of Dan, Eltekeh with its common-land, Gibbethon with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21024, 'Aijalon with its common-land, and Gath Rimmon with its common-land: four cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21025, 'and from the half-tribe of Manasseh, Tanach with its common-land and Gath Rimmon with its common-land: two cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21026, 'All the ten cities with their common-lands were for the rest of the families of the children of Kohath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21027, 'Also to the children of Gershon, of the families of the Levites, from the other half-tribe of Manasseh, they gave Golan in Bashan with its common-land (a city of refuge for the slayer), and Be Eshterah with its common-land: two cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21028, 'and from the tribe of Issachar, Kishion with its common-land, Daberath with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21029, 'Jarmuth with its common-land, and En Gannim with its common-land: four cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21030, 'and from the tribe of Asher, Mishal with its common-land, Abdon with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21031, 'Helkath with its common-land, and Rehob with its common-land: four cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21032, 'and from the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with its common-land (a city of refuge for the slayer), Hammoth Dor with its common-land, and Kartan with its common-land: three cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21033, 'All the cities of the Gershonites according to their families were thirteen cities with their common-lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21034, 'And to the families of the children of Merari, the rest of the Levites, from the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with its common-land, Kartah with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21035, 'Dimnah with its common-land, and Nahalal with its common-land: four cities; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21036, 'and from the tribe of Reuben, Bezer with its common-land, Jahaz with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21037, 'Kedemoth with its common-land, and Mephaath with its common-land: four cities;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21038, 'and from the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with its common-land (a city of refuge for the slayer), Mahanaim with its common-land, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21039, 'Heshbon with its common-land, and Jazer with its common-land: four cities in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21040, 'So all the cities for the children of Merari according to their families, the rest of the families of the Levites, were by their lot twelve cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21041, 'All the cities of the Levites within the possession of the children of Israel were forty-eight cities with their common-lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21042, 'Every one of these cities had its common-land surrounding it; thus were all these cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21043, 'So the Lord gave to Israel all the land of which He had sworn to give to their fathers, and they took possession of it and dwelt in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21044, 'The Lord gave them rest all around, according to all that He had sworn to their fathers. And not a man of all their enemies stood against them; the Lord delivered all their enemies into their hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 21045, 'Not a word failed of any good thing which the Lord had spoken to the house of Israel. All came to pass. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22001, 'Then Joshua called the Reubenites, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22002, 'and said to them: &ldquo;You have kept all that Moses the servant of the Lord commanded you, and have obeyed my voice in all that I commanded you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22003, 'You have not left your brethren these many days, up to this day, but have kept the charge of the commandment of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22004, 'And now the Lord your God has given rest to your brethren, as He promised them; now therefore, return and go to your tents and to the land of your possession, which Moses the servant of the Lord gave you on the other side of the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22005, 'But take careful heed to do the commandment and the law which Moses the servant of the Lord commanded you, to love the Lord your God, to walk in all His ways, to keep His commandments, to hold fast to Him, and to serve Him with all your heart and with all your soul.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22006, 'So Joshua blessed them and sent them away, and they went to their tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22007, 'Now to half the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given a possession in Bashan, but to the other half of it Joshua gave a possession among their brethren on this side of the Jordan, westward. And indeed, when Joshua sent them away to their tents, he blessed them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22008, 'and spoke to them, saying, &ldquo;Return with much riches to your tents, with very much livestock, with silver, with gold, with bronze, with iron, and with very much clothing. Divide the spoil of your enemies with your brethren.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22009, 'So the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh returned, and departed from the children of Israel at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan, to go to the country of Gilead, to the land of their possession, which they had obtained according to the word of the Lord by the hand of Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22010, 'And when they came to the region of the Jordan which is in the land of Canaan, the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh built an altar there by the Jordan &ndash; a great, impressive altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22011, 'Now the children of Israel heard someone say, &ldquo;Behold, the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh have built an altar on the frontier of the land of Canaan, in the region of the Jordan &ndash; on the children of Israel&rsquo;s side.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22012, 'And when the children of Israel heard of it, the whole congregation of the children of Israel gathered together at Shiloh to go to war against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22013, 'Then the children of Israel sent Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest to the children of Reuben, to the children of Gad, and to half the tribe of Manasseh, into the land of Gilead, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22014, 'and with him ten rulers, one ruler each from the chief house of every tribe of Israel; and each one was the head of the house of his father among the divisions of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22015, 'Then they came to the children of Reuben, to the children of Gad, and to half the tribe of Manasseh, to the land of Gilead, and they spoke with them, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22016, 'Thus says the whole congregation of the Lord: &lsquo;What treachery is this that you have committed against the God of Israel, to turn away this day from following the Lord, in that you have built for yourselves an altar, that you might rebel this day against the Lord? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22017, 'Is the iniquity of Peor not enough for us, from which we are not cleansed until this day, although there was a plague in the congregation of the Lord, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22018, 'but that you must turn away this day from following the Lord? And it shall be, if you rebel today against the Lord, that tomorrow He will be angry with the whole congregation of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22019, 'Nevertheless, if the land of your possession is unclean, then cross over to the land of the possession of the Lord, where the Lord&rsquo;s tabernacle stands, and take possession among us; but do not rebel against the Lord, nor rebel against us, by building yourselves an altar besides the altar of the Lord our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22020, 'Did not Achan the son of Zerah commit a trespass in the accursed thing, and wrath fell on all the congregation of Israel? And that man did not perish alone in his iniquity.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22021, 'Then the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and half the tribe of Manasseh answered and said to the heads of the divisions of Israel:');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22022, 'The Lord God of gods, the Lord God of gods, He knows, and let Israel itself know &ndash; if it is in rebellion, or if in treachery against the Lord, do not save us this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22023, 'If we have built ourselves an altar to turn from following the Lord, or if to offer on it burnt offerings or grain offerings, or if to offer peace offerings on it, let the Lord Himself require an account. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22024, 'But in fact we have done it for fear, for a reason, saying, &lsquo;In time to come your descendants may speak to our descendants, saying, What have you to do with the Lord God of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22025, 'For the Lord has made the Jordan a border between you and us, you children of Reuben and children of Gad. You have no part in the Lord.&rdquo; So your descendants would make our descendants cease fearing the Lord.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22026, 'Therefore we said, &lsquo;Let us now prepare to build ourselves an altar, not for burnt offering nor for sacrifice, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22027, 'but that it may be a witness between you and us and our generations after us, that we may perform the service of the Lord before Him with our burnt offerings, with our sacrifices, and with our peace offerings; that your descendants may not say to our descendants in time to come, &ldquo;You have no part in the Lord.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22028, 'Therefore we said that it will be, when they say this to us or to our generations in time to come, that we may say, &lsquo;Here is the replica of the altar of the Lord which our fathers made, though not for burnt offerings nor for sacrifices; but it is a witness between you and us.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22029, 'Far be it from us that we should rebel against the Lord, and turn from following the Lord this day, to build an altar for burnt offerings, for grain offerings, or for sacrifices, besides the altar of the Lord our God which is before His tabernacle.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22030, 'Now when Phinehas the priest and the rulers of the congregation, the heads of the divisions of Israel who were with him, heard the words that the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and the children of Manasseh spoke, it pleased them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22031, 'Then Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest said to the children of Reuben, the children of Gad, and the children of Manasseh, &ldquo;This day we perceive that the Lord is among us, because you have not committed this treachery against the Lord. Now you have delivered the children of Israel out of the hand of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22032, 'And Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, and the rulers, returned from the children of Reuben and the children of Gad, from the land of Gilead to the land of Canaan, to the children of Israel, and brought back word to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22033, 'So the thing pleased the children of Israel, and the children of Israel blessed God; they spoke no more of going against them in battle, to destroy the land where the children of Reuben and Gad dwelt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 22034, 'The children of Reuben and the children of Gad called the altar, Witness, &ldquo;For it is a witness between us that the Lord is God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23001, 'Now it came to pass, a long time after the Lord had given rest to Israel from all their enemies round about, that Joshua was old, advanced in age. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23002, 'And Joshua called for all Israel, for their elders, for their heads, for their judges, and for their officers, and said to them: &ldquo;I am old, advanced in age. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23003, 'You have seen all that the Lord your God has done to all these nations because of you, for the Lord your God is He who has fought for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23004, 'See, I have divided to you by lot these nations that remain, to be an inheritance for your tribes, from the Jordan, with all the nations that I have cut off, as far as the Great Sea westward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23005, 'And the Lord your God will expel them from before you and drive them out of your sight. So you shall possess their land, as the Lord your God promised you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23006, 'Therefore be very courageous to keep and to do all that is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, lest you turn aside from it to the right hand or to the left, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23007, 'and lest you go among these nations, these who remain among you. You shall not make mention of the name of their gods, nor cause anyone to swear by them; you shall not serve them nor bow down to them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23008, 'but you shall hold fast to the Lord your God, as you have done to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23009, 'For the Lord has driven out from before you great and strong nations; but as for you, no one has been able to stand against you to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23010, 'One man of you shall chase a thousand, for the Lord your God is He who fights for you, as He promised you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23011, 'Therefore take careful heed to yourselves, that you love the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23012, 'Or else, if indeed you do go back, and cling to the remnant of these nations &ndash; these that remain among you &ndash; and make marriages with them, and go in to them and they to you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23013, 'know for certain that the Lord your God will no longer drive out these nations from before you. But they shall be snares and traps to you, and scourges on your sides and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from this good land which the Lord your God has given you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23014, 'Behold, this day I am going the way of all the earth. And you know in all your hearts and in all your souls that not one thing has failed of all the good things which the Lord your God spoke concerning you. All have come to pass for you; not one word of them has failed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23015, 'Therefore it shall come to pass, that as all the good things have come upon you which the Lord your God promised you, so the Lord will bring upon you all harmful things, until He has destroyed you from this good land which the Lord your God has given you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 23016, 'When you have transgressed the covenant of the Lord your God, which He commanded you, and have gone and served other gods, and bowed down to them, then the anger of the Lord will burn against you, and you shall perish quickly from the good land which He has given you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24001, 'Then Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem and called for the elders of Israel, for their heads, for their judges, and for their officers; and they presented themselves before God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24002, 'And Joshua said to all the people, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;Your fathers, including Terah, the father of Abraham and the father of Nahor, dwelt on the other side of the River in old times; and they served other gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24003, 'Then I took your father Abraham from the other side of the River, led him throughout all the land of Canaan, and multiplied his descendants and gave him Isaac. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24004, '&rsquo;To Isaac I gave Jacob and Esau. To Esau I gave the mountains of Seir to possess, but Jacob and his children went down to Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24005, '&rsquo;Also I sent Moses and Aaron, and I plagued Egypt, according to what I did among them. Afterward I brought you out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24006, '&rsquo;Then I brought your fathers out of Egypt, and you came to the sea; and the Egyptians pursued your fathers with chariots and horsemen to the Red Sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24007, '&rsquo;So they cried out to the Lord; and He put darkness between you and the Egyptians, brought the sea upon them, and covered them. And your eyes saw what I did in Egypt. Then you dwelt in the wilderness a long time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24008, '&rsquo;And I brought you into the land of the Amorites, who dwelt on the other side of the Jordan, and they fought with you. But I gave them into your hand, that you might possess their land, and I destroyed them from before you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24009, '&rsquo;Then Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab, arose to make war against Israel, and sent and called Balaam the son of Beor to curse you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24010, '&rsquo;But I would not listen to Balaam; therefore he continued to bless you. So I delivered you out of his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24011, '&rsquo;Then you went over the Jordan and came to Jericho. And the men of Jericho fought against you &ndash; also the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Girgashites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites. But I delivered them into your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24012, '&rsquo;I sent the hornet before you which drove them out from before you, also the two kings of the Amorites, but not with your sword or with your bow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24013, '&rsquo;I have given you a land for which you did not labor, and cities which you did not build, and you dwell in them; you eat of the vineyards and olive groves which you did not plant.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24014, 'Now therefore, fear the Lord, serve Him in sincerity and in truth, and put away the gods which your fathers served on the other side of the River and in Egypt. Serve the Lord! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24015, 'And if it seems evil to you to serve the Lord, choose for yourselves this day whom you will serve, whether the gods which your fathers served that were on the other side of the River, or the gods of the Amorites, in whose land you dwell. But as for me and my house, we will serve the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24016, 'So the people answered and said: &ldquo;Far be it from us that we should forsake the Lord to serve other gods; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24017, 'for the Lord our God is He who brought us and our fathers up out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage, who did those great signs in our sight, and preserved us in all the way that we went and among all the people through whom we passed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24018, 'And the Lord drove out from before us all the people, including the Amorites who dwelt in the land. We also will serve the Lord, for He is our God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24019, 'But Joshua said to the people, &ldquo;You cannot serve the Lord, for He is a holy God. He is a jealous God; He will not forgive your transgressions nor your sins. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24020, 'If you forsake the Lord and serve foreign gods, then He will turn and do you harm and consume you, after He has done you good.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24021, 'And the people said to Joshua, &ldquo;No, but we will serve the Lord!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24022, 'So Joshua said to the people, &ldquo;You are witnesses against yourselves that you have chosen the Lord for yourselves, to serve Him.&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;We are witnesses!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24023, 'Now therefore, he said, put away the foreign gods which are among you, and incline your heart to the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24024, 'And the people said to Joshua, &ldquo;The Lord our God we will serve, and His voice we will obey!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24025, 'So Joshua made a covenant with the people that day, and made for them a statute and an ordinance in Shechem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24026, 'Then Joshua wrote these words in the Book of the Law of God. And he took a large stone, and set it up there under the oak that was by the sanctuary of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24027, 'And Joshua said to all the people, &ldquo;Behold, this stone shall be a witness to us, for it has heard all the words of the Lord which He spoke to us. It shall therefore be a witness to you, lest you deny your God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24028, 'So Joshua let the people depart, each to his own inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24029, 'Now it came to pass after these things that Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the Lord, died, being one hundred and ten years old. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24030, 'And they buried him within the border of his inheritance at Timnath Serah, which is in the mountains of Ephraim, on the north side of Mount Gaash. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24031, 'Israel served the Lord all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had known all the works of the Lord which He had done for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24032, 'The bones of Joseph, which the children of Israel had brought up out of Egypt, they buried at Shechem, in the plot of ground which Jacob had bought from the sons of Hamor the father of Shechem for one hundred pieces of silver, and which had become an inheritance of the children of Joseph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Josh', 24033, 'And Eleazar the son of Aaron died. They buried him in a hill belonging to Phinehas his son, which was given to him in the mountains of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1001, 'Now after the death of Joshua it came to pass that the children of Israel asked the Lord, saying, &ldquo;Who shall be first to go up for us against the Canaanites to fight against them?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1002, 'And the Lord said, &ldquo;Judah shall go up. Indeed I have delivered the land into his hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1003, 'So Judah said to Simeon his brother, &ldquo;Come up with me to my allotted territory, that we may fight against the Canaanites; and I will likewise go with you to your allotted territory.&rdquo; And Simeon went with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1004, 'Then Judah went up, and the Lord delivered the Canaanites and the Perizzites into their hand; and they killed ten thousand men at Bezek. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1005, 'And they found Adoni-Bezek in Bezek, and fought against him; and they defeated the Canaanites and the Perizzites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1006, 'Then Adoni-Bezek fled, and they pursued him and caught him and cut off his thumbs and big toes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1007, 'And Adoni-Bezek said, &ldquo;Seventy kings with their thumbs and big toes cut off used to gather scraps under my table; as I have done, so God has repaid me.&rdquo; Then they brought him to Jerusalem, and there he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1008, 'Now the children of Judah fought against Jerusalem and took it; they struck it with the edge of the sword and set the city on fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1009, 'And afterward the children of Judah went down to fight against the Canaanites who dwelt in the mountains, in the South, and in the lowland. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1010, 'Then Judah went against the Canaanites who dwelt in Hebron. (Now the name of Hebron was formerly Kirjath Arba.) And they killed Sheshai, Ahiman, and Talmai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1011, 'From there they went against the inhabitants of Debir. (The name of Debir was formerly Kirjath Sepher.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1012, 'Then Caleb said, &ldquo;Whoever attacks Kirjath Sepher and takes it, to him I will give my daughter Achsah as wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1013, 'And Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb&rsquo;s younger brother, took it; so he gave him his daughter Achsah as wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1014, 'Now it happened, when she came to him, that she urged him to ask her father for a field. And she dismounted from her donkey, and Caleb said to her, &ldquo;What do you wish?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1015, 'So she said to him, &ldquo;Give me a blessing; since you have given me land in the South, give me also springs of water.&rdquo; And Caleb gave her the upper springs and the lower springs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1016, 'Now the children of the Kenite, Moses&rsquo; father-in-law, went up from the City of Palms with the children of Judah into the Wilderness of Judah, which lies in the South near Arad; and they went and dwelt among the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1017, 'And Judah went with his brother Simeon, and they attacked the Canaanites who inhabited Zephath, and utterly destroyed it. So the name of the city was called Hormah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1018, 'Also Judah took Gaza with its territory, Ashkelon with its territory, and Ekron with its territory. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1019, 'So the Lord was with Judah. And they drove out the mountaineers, but they could not drive out the inhabitants of the lowland, because they had chariots of iron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1020, 'And they gave Hebron to Caleb, as Moses had said. Then he expelled from there the three sons of Anak. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1021, 'But the children of Benjamin did not drive out the Jebusites who inhabited Jerusalem; so the Jebusites dwell with the children of Benjamin in Jerusalem to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1022, 'And the house of Joseph also went up against Bethel, and the Lord was with them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1023, 'So the house of Joseph sent men to spy out Bethel. (The name of the city was formerly Luz.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1024, 'And when the spies saw a man coming out of the city, they said to him, &ldquo;Please show us the entrance to the city, and we will show you mercy.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1025, 'So he showed them the entrance to the city, and they struck the city with the edge of the sword; but they let the man and all his family go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1026, 'And the man went to the land of the Hittites, built a city, and called its name Luz, which is its name to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1027, 'However, Manasseh did not drive out the inhabitants of Beth Shean and its villages, or Taanach and its villages, or the inhabitants of Dor and its villages, or the inhabitants of Ibleam and its villages, or the inhabitants of Megiddo and its villages; for the Canaanites were determined to dwell in that land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1028, 'And it came to pass, when Israel was strong, that they put the Canaanites under tribute, but did not completely drive them out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1029, 'Nor did Ephraim drive out the Canaanites who dwelt in Gezer; so the Canaanites dwelt in Gezer among them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1030, 'Nor did Zebulun drive out the inhabitants of Kitron or the inhabitants of Nahalol; so the Canaanites dwelt among them, and were put under tribute. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1031, 'Nor did Asher drive out the inhabitants of Acco or the inhabitants of Sidon, or of Ahlab, Achzib, Helbah, Aphik, or Rehob. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1032, 'So the Asherites dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land; for they did not drive them out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1033, 'Nor did Naphtali drive out the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh or the inhabitants of Beth Anath; but they dwelt among the Canaanites, the inhabitants of the land. Nevertheless the inhabitants of Beth Shemesh and Beth Anath were put under tribute to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1034, 'And the Amorites forced the children of Dan into the mountains, for they would not allow them to come down to the valley; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1035, 'and the Amorites were determined to dwell in Mount Heres, in Aijalon, and in Shaalbim; yet when the strength of the house of Joseph became greater, they were put under tribute. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 1036, 'Now the boundary of the Amorites was from the Ascent of Akrabbim, from Sela, and upward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2001, 'Then the Angel of the Lord came up from Gilgal to Bochim, and said: &ldquo;I led you up from Egypt and brought you to the land of which I swore to your fathers; and I said, &lsquo;I will never break My covenant with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2002, 'And you shall make no covenant with the inhabitants of this land; you shall tear down their altars.&rsquo; But you have not obeyed My voice. Why have you done this? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2003, 'Therefore I also said, &lsquo;I will not drive them out before you; but they shall be thorns in your side, and their gods shall be a snare to you.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2004, 'So it was, when the Angel of the Lord spoke these words to all the children of Israel, that the people lifted up their voices and wept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2005, 'Then they called the name of that place Bochim; and they sacrificed there to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2006, 'And when Joshua had dismissed the people, the children of Israel went each to his own inheritance to possess the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2007, 'So the people served the Lord all the days of Joshua, and all the days of the elders who outlived Joshua, who had seen all the great works of the Lord which He had done for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2008, 'Now Joshua the son of Nun, the servant of the Lord, died when he was one hundred and ten years old. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2009, 'And they buried him within the border of his inheritance at Timnath Heres, in the mountains of Ephraim, on the north side of Mount Gaash. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2010, 'When all that generation had been gathered to their fathers, another generation arose after them who did not know the Lord nor the work which He had done for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2011, 'Then the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord, and served the Baals; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2012, 'and they forsook the Lord God of their fathers, who had brought them out of the land of Egypt; and they followed other gods from among the gods of the people who were all around them, and they bowed down to them; and they provoked the Lord to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2013, 'They forsook the Lord and served Baal and the Ashtoreths.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2014, 'And the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel. So He delivered them into the hands of plunderers who despoiled them; and He sold them into the hands of their enemies all around, so that they could no longer stand before their enemies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2015, 'Wherever they went out, the hand of the Lord was against them for calamity, as the Lord had said, and as the Lord had sworn to them. And they were greatly distressed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2016, 'Nevertheless, the Lord raised up judges who delivered them out of the hand of those who plundered them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2017, 'Yet they would not listen to their judges, but they played the harlot with other gods, and bowed down to them. They turned quickly from the way in which their fathers walked, in obeying the commandments of the Lord; they did not do so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2018, 'And when the Lord raised up judges for them, the Lord was with the judge and delivered them out of the hand of their enemies all the days of the judge; for the Lord was moved to pity by their groaning because of those who oppressed them and harassed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2019, 'And it came to pass, when the judge was dead, that they reverted and behaved more corruptly than their fathers, by following other gods, to serve them and bow down to them. They did not cease from their own doings nor from their stubborn way. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2020, 'Then the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel; and He said, &ldquo;Because this nation has transgressed My covenant which I commanded their fathers, and has not heeded My voice, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2021, 'I also will no longer drive out before them any of the nations which Joshua left when he died, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2022, 'so that through them I may test Israel, whether they will keep the ways of the Lord, to walk in them as their fathers kept them, or not.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 2023, 'Therefore the Lord left those nations, without driving them out immediately; nor did He deliver them into the hand of Joshua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3001, 'Now these are the nations which the Lord left, that He might test Israel by them, that is, all who had not known any of the wars in Canaan ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3002, '(this was only so that the generations of the children of Israel might be taught to know war, at least those who had not formerly known it), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3003, 'namely, five lords of the Philistines, all the Canaanites, the Sidonians, and the Hivites who dwelt in Mount Lebanon, from Mount Baal Hermon to the entrance of Hamath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3004, 'And they were left, that He might test Israel by them, to know whether they would obey the commandments of the Lord, which He had commanded their fathers by the hand of Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3005, 'Thus the children of Israel dwelt among the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Amorites, the Perizzites, the Hivites, and the Jebusites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3006, 'And they took their daughters to be their wives, and gave their daughters to their sons; and they served their gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3007, 'So the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord. They forgot the Lord their God, and served the Baals and Asherahs.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3008, 'Therefore the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel, and He sold them into the hand of Cushan-Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia; and the children of Israel served Cushan-Rishathaim eight years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3009, 'When the children of Israel cried out to the Lord, the Lord raised up a deliverer for the children of Israel, who delivered them: Othniel the son of Kenaz, Caleb&rsquo;s younger brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3010, 'The Spirit of the Lord came upon him, and he judged Israel. He went out to war, and the Lord delivered Cushan-Rishathaim king of Mesopotamia into his hand; and his hand prevailed over Cushan-Rishathaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3011, 'So the land had rest for forty years. Then Othniel the son of Kenaz died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3012, 'And the children of Israel again did evil in the sight of the Lord. So the Lord strengthened Eglon king of Moab against Israel, because they had done evil in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3013, 'Then he gathered to himself the people of Ammon and Amalek, went and defeated Israel, and took possession of the City of Palms. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3014, 'So the children of Israel served Eglon king of Moab eighteen years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3015, 'But when the children of Israel cried out to the Lord, the Lord raised up a deliverer for them: Ehud the son of Gera, the Benjamite, a left-handed man. By him the children of Israel sent tribute to Eglon king of Moab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3016, 'Now Ehud made himself a dagger (it was double-edged and a cubit in length) and fastened it under his clothes on his right thigh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3017, 'So he brought the tribute to Eglon king of Moab. (Now Eglon was a very fat man.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3018, 'And when he had finished presenting the tribute, he sent away the people who had carried the tribute. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3019, 'But he himself turned back from the stone images that were at Gilgal, and said, &ldquo;I have a secret message for you, O king.&rdquo; He said, &ldquo;Keep silence!&rdquo; And all who attended him went out from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3020, 'And Ehud came to him (now he was sitting upstairs in his cool private chamber). Then Ehud said, &ldquo;I have a message from God for you.&rdquo; So he arose from his seat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3021, 'Then Ehud reached with his left hand, took the dagger from his right thigh, and thrust it into his belly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3022, 'Even the hilt went in after the blade, and the fat closed over the blade, for he did not draw the dagger out of his belly; and his entrails came out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3023, 'Then Ehud went out through the porch and shut the doors of the upper room behind him and locked them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3024, 'When he had gone out, Eglon&rsquo;s servants came to look, and to their surprise, the doors of the upper room were locked. So they said, &ldquo;He is probably attending to his needs in the cool chamber.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3025, 'So they waited till they were embarrassed, and still he had not opened the doors of the upper room. Therefore they took the key and opened them. And there was their master, fallen dead on the floor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3026, 'But Ehud had escaped while they delayed, and passed beyond the stone images and escaped to Seirah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3027, 'And it happened, when he arrived, that he blew the trumpet in the mountains of Ephraim, and the children of Israel went down with him from the mountains; and he led them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3028, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;Follow me, for the Lord has delivered your enemies the Moabites into your hand.&rdquo; So they went down after him, seized the fords of the Jordan leading to Moab, and did not allow anyone to cross over. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3029, 'And at that time they killed about ten thousand men of Moab, all stout men of valor; not a man escaped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3030, 'So Moab was subdued that day under the hand of Israel. And the land had rest for eighty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 3031, 'After him was Shamgar the son of Anath, who killed six hundred men of the Philistines with an ox goad; and he also delivered Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4001, 'When Ehud was dead, the children of Israel again did evil in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4002, 'So the Lord sold them into the hand of Jabin king of Canaan, who reigned in Hazor. The commander of his army was Sisera, who dwelt in Harosheth Hagoyim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4003, 'And the children of Israel cried out to the Lord; for Jabin had nine hundred chariots of iron, and for twenty years he harshly oppressed the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4004, 'Now Deborah, a prophetess, the wife of Lapidoth, was judging Israel at that time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4005, 'And she would sit under the palm tree of Deborah between Ramah and Bethel in the mountains of Ephraim. And the children of Israel came up to her for judgment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4006, 'Then she sent and called for Barak the son of Abinoam from Kedesh in Naphtali, and said to him, &ldquo;Has not the Lord God of Israel commanded, &lsquo;Go and deploy troops at Mount Tabor; take with you ten thousand men of the sons of Naphtali and of the sons of Zebulun; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4007, 'and against you I will deploy Sisera, the commander of Jabin&rsquo;s army, with his chariots and his multitude at the River Kishon; and I will deliver him into your hand&rsquo;?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4008, 'And Barak said to her, &ldquo;If you will go with me, then I will go; but if you will not go with me, I will not go!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4009, 'So she said, &ldquo;I will surely go with you; nevertheless there will be no glory for you in the journey you are taking, for the Lord will sell Sisera into the hand of a woman.&rdquo; Then Deborah arose and went with Barak to Kedesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4010, 'And Barak called Zebulun and Naphtali to Kedesh; he went up with ten thousand men under his command, and Deborah went up with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4011, 'Now Heber the Kenite, of the children of Hobab the father-in-law of Moses, had separated himself from the Kenites and pitched his tent near the terebinth tree at Zaanaim, which is beside Kedesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4012, 'And they reported to Sisera that Barak the son of Abinoam had gone up to Mount Tabor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4013, 'So Sisera gathered together all his chariots, nine hundred chariots of iron, and all the people who were with him, from Harosheth Hagoyim to the River Kishon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4014, 'Then Deborah said to Barak, &ldquo;Up! For this is the day in which the Lord has delivered Sisera into your hand. Has not the Lord gone out before you?&rdquo; So Barak went down from Mount Tabor with ten thousand men following him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4015, 'And the Lord routed Sisera and all his chariots and all his army with the edge of the sword before Barak; and Sisera alighted from his chariot and fled away on foot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4016, 'But Barak pursued the chariots and the army as far as Harosheth Hagoyim, and all the army of Sisera fell by the edge of the sword; not a man was left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4017, 'However, Sisera had fled away on foot to the tent of Jael, the wife of Heber the Kenite; for there was peace between Jabin king of Hazor and the house of Heber the Kenite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4018, 'And Jael went out to meet Sisera, and said to him, &ldquo;Turn aside, my lord, turn aside to me; do not fear.&rdquo; And when he had turned aside with her into the tent, she covered him with a blanket. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4019, 'Then he said to her, &ldquo;Please give me a little water to drink, for I am thirsty.&rdquo; So she opened a jug of milk, gave him a drink, and covered him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4020, 'And he said to her, &ldquo;Stand at the door of the tent, and if any man comes and inquires of you, and says, &lsquo;Is there any man here?&rsquo; you shall say, &lsquo;No.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4021, 'Then Jael, Heber&rsquo;s wife, took a tent peg and took a hammer in her hand, and went softly to him and drove the peg into his temple, and it went down into the ground; for he was fast asleep and weary. So he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4022, 'And then, as Barak pursued Sisera, Jael came out to meet him, and said to him, &ldquo;Come, I will show you the man whom you seek.&rdquo; And when he went into her tent, there lay Sisera, dead with the peg in his temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4023, 'So on that day God subdued Jabin king of Canaan in the presence of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 4024, 'And the hand of the children of Israel grew stronger and stronger against Jabin king of Canaan, until they had destroyed Jabin king of Canaan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5001, 'Then Deborah and Barak the son of Abinoam sang on that day, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5002, 'When leaders lead in Israel, When the people willingly offer themselves, Bless the Lord! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5003, 'Hear, O kings! Give ear, O princes! I, even I, will sing to the Lord; I will sing praise to the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5004, 'Lord, when You went out from Seir, When You marched from the field of Edom, The earth trembled and the heavens poured, The clouds also poured water; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5005, 'The mountains gushed before the Lord, This Sinai, before the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5006, 'In the days of Shamgar, son of Anath, In the days of Jael, The highways were deserted, And the travelers walked along the byways. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5007, 'Village life ceased, it ceased in Israel, Until I, Deborah, arose, Arose a mother in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5008, 'They chose new gods; Then there was war in the gates; Not a shield or spear was seen among forty thousand in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5009, 'My heart is with the rulers of Israel Who offered themselves willingly with the people. Bless the Lord! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5010, 'Speak, you who ride on white donkeys, Who sit in judges&rsquo; attire, And who walk along the road. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5011, 'Far from the noise of the archers, among the watering places, There they shall recount the righteous acts of the Lord, The righteous acts for His villagers in Israel; Then the people of the Lord shall go down to the gates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5012, 'Awake, awake, Deborah! Awake, awake, sing a song! Arise, Barak, and lead your captives away, O son of Abinoam! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5013, 'Then the survivors came down, the people against the nobles; The Lord came down for me against the mighty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5014, 'From Ephraim were those whose roots were in Amalek. After you, Benjamin, with your peoples, From Machir rulers came down, And from Zebulun those who bear the recruiter&rsquo;s staff. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5015, 'And the princes of Issachar were with Deborah; As Issachar, so was Barak Sent into the valley under his command; Among the divisions of Reuben There were great resolves of heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5016, 'Why did you sit among the sheepfolds, To hear the pipings for the flocks? The divisions of Reuben have great searchings of heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5017, 'Gilead stayed beyond the Jordan, And why did Dan remain on ships? Asher continued at the seashore, And stayed by his inlets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5018, 'Zebulun is a people who jeopardized their lives to the point of death, Naphtali also, on the heights of the battlefield. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5019, 'The kings came and fought, Then the kings of Canaan fought In Taanach, by the waters of Megiddo; They took no spoils of silver. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5020, 'They fought from the heavens; The stars from their courses fought against Sisera. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5021, 'The torrent of Kishon swept them away, That ancient torrent, the torrent of Kishon. O my soul, march on in strength! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5022, 'Then the horses&rsquo; hooves pounded, The galloping, galloping of his steeds. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5023, 'Curse Meroz,&rsquo; said the angel of the Lord, &lsquo;Curse its inhabitants bitterly, Because they did not come to the help of the Lord, To the help of the Lord against the mighty.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5024, 'Most blessed among women is Jael, The wife of Heber the Kenite; Blessed is she among women in tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5025, 'He asked for water, she gave milk; She brought out cream in a lordly bowl. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5026, 'She stretched her hand to the tent peg, Her right hand to the workmen&rsquo;s hammer; She pounded Sisera, she pierced his head, She split and struck through his temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5027, 'At her feet he sank, he fell, he lay still; At her feet he sank, he fell; Where he sank, there he fell dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5028, 'The mother of Sisera looked through the window, And cried out through the lattice, &lsquo;Why is his chariot so long in coming? Why tarries the clatter of his chariots?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5029, 'Her wisest ladies answered her, Yes, she answered herself, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5030, '&rsquo;Are they not finding and dividing the spoil: To every man a girl or two; For Sisera, plunder of dyed garments, Plunder of garments embroidered and dyed, Two pieces of dyed embroidery for the neck of the looter?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 5031, 'Thus let all Your enemies perish, O Lord! But let those who love Him be like the sun When it comes out in full strength. So the land had rest for forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6001, 'Then the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord. So the Lord delivered them into the hand of Midian for seven years, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6002, 'and* the hand of Midian prevailed against Israel. Because of the Midianites, the children of Israel made for themselves the dens, the caves, and the strongholds which are in the mountains. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6003, 'So it was, whenever Israel had sown, Midianites would come up; also Amalekites and the people of the East would come up against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6004, 'Then they would encamp against them and destroy the produce of the earth as far as Gaza, and leave no sustenance for Israel, neither sheep nor ox nor donkey. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6005, 'For they would come up with their livestock and their tents, coming in as numerous as locusts; both they and their camels were without number; and they would enter the land to destroy it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6006, 'So Israel was greatly impoverished because of the Midianites, and the children of Israel cried out to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6007, 'And it came to pass, when* the children of Israel cried out to the Lord because of the Midianites, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6008, 'that the Lord sent a prophet to the children of Israel, who said to them, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;I brought you up from Egypt and brought you out of the house of bondage; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6009, 'and I delivered you out of the hand of the Egyptians and out of the hand of all who oppressed you, and drove them out before you and gave you their land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6010, 'Also I said to you, &ldquo;I am the Lord your God; do not fear the gods of the Amorites, in whose land you dwell.&rdquo; But you have not obeyed My voice.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6011, 'Now the Angel of the Lord came and sat under the terebinth tree which was in Ophrah, which belonged to Joash the Abiezrite, while his son Gideon threshed wheat in the winepress, in order to hide it from the Midianites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6012, 'And the Angel of the Lord appeared to him, and said to him, &ldquo;The Lord is with you, you mighty man of valor!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6013, 'Gideon said to Him, &ldquo;O my lord, if the Lord is with us, why then has all this happened to us? And where are all His miracles which our fathers told us about, saying, &lsquo;Did not the Lord bring us up from Egypt?&rsquo; But now the Lord has forsaken us and delivered us into the hands of the Midianites.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6014, 'Then the Lord turned to him and said, &ldquo;Go in this might of yours, and you shall save Israel from the hand of the Midianites. Have I not sent you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6015, 'So he said to Him, &ldquo;O my Lord, how can I save Israel? Indeed my clan is the weakest in Manasseh, and I am the least in my father&rsquo;s house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6016, 'And the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Surely I will be with you, and you shall defeat the Midianites as one man.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6017, 'Then he said to Him, &ldquo;If now I have found favor in Your sight, then show me a sign that it is You who talk with me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6018, 'Do not depart from here, I pray, until I come to You and bring out my offering and set it before You.&rdquo; And He said, &ldquo;I will wait until you come back.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6019, 'So Gideon went in and prepared a young goat, and unleavened bread from an ephah of flour. The meat he put in a basket, and he put the broth in a pot; and he brought them out to Him under the terebinth tree and presented them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6020, 'The Angel of God said to him, &ldquo;Take the meat and the unleavened bread and lay them on this rock, and pour out the broth.&rdquo; And he did so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6021, 'Then the Angel of the Lord put out the end of the staff that was in His hand, and touched the meat and the unleavened bread; and fire rose out of the rock and consumed the meat and the unleavened bread. And the Angel of the Lord departed out of his sight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6022, 'Now Gideon perceived that He was the Angel of the Lord. So Gideon said, &ldquo;Alas, O Lord God! For I have seen the Angel of the Lord face to face.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6023, 'Then the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Peace be with you; do not fear, you shall not die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6024, 'So Gideon built an altar there to the Lord, and called it The-Lord-Is-Peace. To this day it is still in Ophrah of the Abiezrites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6025, 'Now it came to pass the same night that the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Take your father&rsquo;s young bull, the second bull of seven years old, and tear down the altar of Baal that your father has, and cut down the wooden image that is beside it; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6026, 'and build an altar to the Lord your God on top of this rock in the proper arrangement, and take the second bull and offer a burnt sacrifice with the wood of the image which you shall cut down.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6027, 'So Gideon took ten men from among his servants and did as the Lord had said to him. But because he feared his father&rsquo;s household and the men of the city too much to do it by day, he did it by night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6028, 'And when the men of the city arose early in the morning, there was the altar of Baal, torn down; and the wooden image that was beside it was cut down, and the second bull was being offered on the altar which had been built. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6029, 'So they said to one another, &ldquo;Who has done this thing?&rdquo; And when they had inquired and asked, they said, &ldquo;Gideon the son of Joash has done this thing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6030, 'Then the men of the city said to Joash, &ldquo;Bring out your son, that he may die, because he has torn down the altar of Baal, and because he has cut down the wooden image that was beside it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6031, 'But Joash said to all who stood against him, &ldquo;Would you plead for Baal? Would you save him? Let the one who would plead for him be put to death by morning! If he is a god, let him plead for himself, because his altar has been torn down!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6032, 'Therefore on that day he called him Jerubbaal, saying, &ldquo;Let Baal plead against him, because he has torn down his altar.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6033, 'Then all the Midianites and Amalekites, the people of the East, gathered together; and they crossed over and encamped in the Valley of Jezreel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6034, 'But the Spirit of the Lord came upon Gideon; then he blew the trumpet, and the Abiezrites gathered behind him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6035, 'And he sent messengers throughout all Manasseh, who also gathered behind him. He also sent messengers to Asher, Zebulun, and Naphtali; and they came up to meet them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6036, 'So *Gideon said to God, &ldquo;If You will save Israel by my hand as You have said &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6037, 'look, I shall put a fleece of wool on the threshing floor; if there is dew on the fleece only, and it is dry on all the ground, then I shall know that You will save Israel by my hand, as You have said.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6038, 'And it was so. When he rose early the next morning and squeezed the fleece together, he wrung the dew out of the fleece, a bowlful of water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6039, 'Then Gideon said to God, &ldquo;Do not be angry with me, but let me speak just once more: Let me test, I pray, just once more with the fleece; let it now be dry only on the fleece, but on all the ground let there be dew.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 6040, 'And God did so that night. It was dry on the fleece only, but there was dew on all the ground.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7001, 'Then Jerubbaal (that is, Gideon) and all the people who were with him rose early and encamped beside the well of Harod, so that the camp of the Midianites was on the north side of them by the hill of Moreh in the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7002, 'And the Lord said to Gideon, &ldquo;The people who are with you are too many for Me to give the Midianites into their hands, lest Israel claim glory for itself against Me, saying, &lsquo;My own hand has saved me.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7003, 'Now therefore, proclaim in the hearing of the people, saying, &lsquo;Whoever is fearful and afraid, let him turn and depart at once from Mount Gilead.&rsquo; &ldquo; And twenty-two thousand of the people returned, and ten thousand remained. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7004, 'But the Lord said to Gideon, &ldquo;The people are still too many; bring them down to the water, and I will test them for you there. Then it will be, that of whom I say to you, &lsquo;This one shall go with you,&rsquo; the same shall go with you; and of whomever I say to you, &lsquo;This one shall not go with you,&rsquo; the same shall not go.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7005, 'So he brought the people down to the water. And the Lord said to Gideon, &ldquo;Everyone who laps from the water with his tongue, as a dog laps, you shall set apart by himself; likewise everyone who gets down on his knees to drink.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7006, 'And the number of those who lapped, putting their hand to their mouth, was three hundred men; but all the rest of the people got down on their knees to drink water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7007, 'Then the Lord said to Gideon, &ldquo;By the three hundred men who lapped I will save you, and deliver the Midianites into your hand. Let all the other people go, every man to his place.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7008, 'So the people took provisions and their trumpets in their hands. And he sent away all the rest of Israel, every man to his tent, and retained those three hundred men. Now the camp of Midian was below him in the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7009, 'It happened on the same night that the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Arise, go down against the camp, for I have delivered it into your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7010, 'But if you are afraid to go down, go down to the camp with Purah your servant, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7011, 'and you shall hear what they say; and afterward your hands shall be strengthened to go down against the camp.&rdquo; Then he went down with Purah his servant to the outpost of the armed men who were in the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7012, 'Now the Midianites and Amalekites, all the people of the East, were lying in the valley as numerous as locusts; and their camels were without number, as the sand by the seashore in multitude. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7013, 'And when Gideon had come, there was a man telling a dream to his companion. He said, &ldquo;I have had a dream: To my surprise, a loaf of barley bread tumbled into the camp of Midian; it came to a tent and struck it so that it fell and overturned, and the tent collapsed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7014, 'Then his companion answered and said, &ldquo;This is nothing else but the sword of Gideon the son of Joash, a man of Israel! Into his hand God has delivered Midian and the whole camp.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7015, 'And so it was, when Gideon heard the telling of the dream and its interpretation, that he worshiped. He returned to the camp of Israel, and said, &ldquo;Arise, for the Lord has delivered the camp of Midian into your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7016, 'Then he divided the three hundred men into three companies, and he put a trumpet into every man&rsquo;s hand, with empty pitchers, and torches inside the pitchers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7017, 'And he said to them, &ldquo;Look at me and do likewise; watch, and when I come to the edge of the camp you shall do as I do: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7018, 'When I blow the trumpet, I and all who are with me, then you also blow the trumpets on every side of the whole camp, and say, &lsquo;The sword of the Lord and of Gideon!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7019, 'So Gideon and the hundred men who were with him came to the outpost of the camp at the beginning of the middle watch, just as they had posted the watch; and they blew the trumpets and broke the pitchers that were in their hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7020, 'Then the three companies blew the trumpets and broke the pitchers &ndash; they held the torches in their left hands and the trumpets in their right hands for blowing &ndash; and they cried, &ldquo;The sword of the Lord and of Gideon!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7021, 'And every man stood in his place all around the camp; and the whole army ran and cried out and fled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7022, 'When the three hundred blew the trumpets, the Lord set every man&rsquo;s sword against his companion throughout the whole camp; and the army fled to Beth Acacia, toward Zererah, as far as the border of Abel Meholah, by Tabbath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7023, 'And the men of Israel gathered together from Naphtali, Asher, and all Manasseh, and pursued the Midianites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7024, 'Then Gideon sent messengers throughout all the mountains of Ephraim, saying, &ldquo;Come down against the Midianites, and seize from them the watering places as far as Beth Barah and the Jordan.&rdquo; Then all the men of Ephraim gathered together and seized the watering places as far as Beth Barah and the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 7025, 'And they captured two princes of the Midianites, Oreb and Zeeb. They killed Oreb at the rock of Oreb, and Zeeb they killed at the winepress of Zeeb. They pursued Midian and brought the heads of Oreb and Zeeb to Gideon on the other side of the Jordan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8001, 'Now the men of Ephraim said to him, &ldquo;Why have you done this to us by not calling us when you went to fight with the Midianites?&rdquo; And they reprimanded him sharply. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8002, 'So he said to them, &ldquo;What have I done now in comparison with you? Is not the gleaning of the grapes of Ephraim better than the vintage of Abiezer? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8003, 'God has delivered into your hands the princes of Midian, Oreb and Zeeb. And what was I able to do in comparison with you?&rdquo; Then their anger toward him subsided when he said that. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8004, 'When Gideon came to the Jordan, he and the three hundred men who were with him crossed over, exhausted but still in pursuit. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8005, 'Then he said to the men of Succoth, &ldquo;Please give loaves of bread to the people who follow me, for they are exhausted, and I am pursuing Zebah and Zalmunna, kings of Midian.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8006, 'And the leaders of Succoth said, &ldquo;Are the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna now in your hand, that we should give bread to your army?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8007, 'So Gideon said, &ldquo;For this cause, when the Lord has delivered Zebah and Zalmunna into my hand, then I will tear your flesh with the thorns of the wilderness and with briers!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8008, 'Then he went up from there to Penuel and spoke to them in the same way. And the men of Penuel answered him as the men of Succoth had answered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8009, 'So he also spoke to the men of Penuel, saying, &ldquo;When I come back in peace, I will tear down this tower!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8010, 'Now Zebah and Zalmunna were at Karkor, and their armies with them, about fifteen thousand, all who were left of all the army of the people of the East; for one hundred and twenty thousand men who drew the sword had fallen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8011, 'Then Gideon went up by the road of those who dwell in tents on the east of Nobah and Jogbehah; and he attacked the army while the camp felt secure. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8012, 'When Zebah and Zalmunna fled, he pursued them; and he took the two kings of Midian, Zebah and Zalmunna, and routed the whole army. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8013, 'Then Gideon the son of Joash returned from battle, from the Ascent of Heres. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8014, 'And he caught a young man of the men of Succoth and interrogated him; and he wrote down for him the leaders of Succoth and its elders, seventy-seven men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8015, 'Then he came to the men of Succoth and said, &ldquo;Here are Zebah and Zalmunna, about whom you ridiculed me, saying, &lsquo;Are the hands of Zebah and Zalmunna now in your hand, that we should give bread to your weary men?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8016, 'And he took the elders of the city, and thorns of the wilderness and briers, and with them he taught the men of Succoth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8017, 'Then he tore down the tower of Penuel and killed the men of the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8018, 'And he said to Zebah and Zalmunna, &ldquo;What kind of men were they whom you killed at Tabor?&rdquo; So they answered, &ldquo;As you are, so were they; each one resembled the son of a king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8019, 'Then he said, &ldquo;They were my brothers, the sons of my mother. As the Lord lives, if you had let them live, I would not kill you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8020, 'And he said to Jether his firstborn, &ldquo;Rise, kill them!&rdquo; But the youth would not draw his sword; for he was afraid, because he was still a youth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8021, 'So Zebah and Zalmunna said, &ldquo;Rise yourself, and kill us; for as a man is, so is his strength.&rdquo; So Gideon arose and killed Zebah and Zalmunna, and took the crescent ornaments that were on their camels&rsquo; necks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8022, 'Then the men of Israel said to Gideon, &ldquo;Rule over us, both you and your son, and your grandson also; for you have delivered us from the hand of Midian.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8023, 'But Gideon said to them, &ldquo;I will not rule over you, nor shall my son rule over you; the Lord shall rule over you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8024, 'Then Gideon said to them, &ldquo;I would like to make a request of you, that each of you would give me the earrings from his plunder.&rdquo; For they had gold earrings, because they were Ishmaelites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8025, 'So they answered, &ldquo;We will gladly give them.&rdquo; And they spread out a garment, and each man threw into it the earrings from his plunder. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8026, 'Now the weight of the gold earrings that he requested was one thousand seven hundred shekels of gold, besides the crescent ornaments, pendants, and purple robes which were on the kings of Midian, and besides the chains that were around their camels&rsquo; necks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8027, 'Then Gideon made it into an ephod and set it up in his city, Ophrah. And all Israel played the harlot with it there. It became a snare to Gideon and to his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8028, 'Thus Midian was subdued before the children of Israel, so that they lifted their heads no more. And the country was quiet for forty years in the days of Gideon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8029, 'Then Jerubbaal the son of Joash went and dwelt in his own house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8030, 'Gideon had seventy sons who were his own offspring, for he had many wives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8031, 'And his concubine who was in Shechem also bore him a son, whose name he called Abimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8032, 'Now Gideon the son of Joash died at a good old age, and was buried in the tomb of Joash his father, in Ophrah of the Abiezrites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8033, 'So it was, as soon as Gideon was dead, that the children of Israel again played the harlot with the Baals, and made Baal-Berith their god. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8034, 'Thus the children of Israel did not remember the Lord their God, who had delivered them from the hands of all their enemies on every side; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 8035, 'nor did they show kindness to the house of Jerubbaal (Gideon) in accordance with the good he had done for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9001, 'Then Abimelech the son of Jerubbaal went to Shechem, to his mother&rsquo;s brothers, and spoke with them and with all the family of the house of his mother&rsquo;s father, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9002, 'Please speak in the hearing of all the men of Shechem: &lsquo;Which is better for you, that all seventy of the sons of Jerubbaal reign over you, or that one reign over you?&rsquo; Remember that I am your own flesh and bone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9003, 'And his mother&rsquo;s brothers spoke all these words concerning him in the hearing of all the men of Shechem; and their heart was inclined to follow Abimelech, for they said, &ldquo;He is our brother.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9004, 'So they gave him seventy shekels of silver from the temple of Baal-Berith, with which Abimelech hired worthless and reckless men; and they followed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9005, 'Then he went to his father&rsquo;s house at Ophrah and killed his brothers, the seventy sons of Jerubbaal, on one stone. But Jotham the youngest son of Jerubbaal was left, because he hid himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9006, 'And all the men of Shechem gathered together, all of Beth Millo, and they went and made Abimelech king beside the terebinth tree at the pillar that was in Shechem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9007, 'Now when they told Jotham, he went and stood on top of Mount Gerizim, and lifted his voice and cried out. And he said to them: &ldquo;Listen to me, you men of Shechem, That God may listen to you! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9008, 'The trees once went forth to anoint a king over them. And they said to the olive tree, &lsquo;Reign over us!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9009, 'But the olive tree said to them, &lsquo;Should I cease giving my oil, With which they honor God and men, And go to sway over trees?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9010, 'Then the trees said to the fig tree, &lsquo;You come and reign over us!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9011, 'But the fig tree said to them, &lsquo;Should I cease my sweetness and my good fruit, And go to sway over trees?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9012, 'Then the trees said to the vine, &lsquo;You come and reign over us!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9013, 'But the vine said to them, &lsquo;Should I cease my new wine, Which cheers both God and men, And go to sway over trees?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9014, 'Then all the trees said to the bramble, &lsquo;You come and reign over us!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9015, 'And the bramble said to the trees, &lsquo;If in truth you anoint me as king over you, Then come and take shelter in my shade; But if not, let fire come out of the bramble And devour the cedars of Lebanon!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9016, 'Now therefore, if you have acted in truth and sincerity in making Abimelech king, and if you have dealt well with Jerubbaal and his house, and have done to him as he deserves &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9017, 'for my father fought for you, risked his life, and delivered you out of the hand of Midian; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9018, 'but you have risen up against my father&rsquo;s house this day, and killed his seventy sons on one stone, and made Abimelech, the son of his female servant, king over the men of Shechem, because he is your brother &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9019, 'if then you have acted in truth and sincerity with Jerubbaal and with his house this day, then rejoice in Abimelech, and let him also rejoice in you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9020, 'But if not, let fire come from Abimelech and devour the men of Shechem and Beth Millo; and let fire come from the men of Shechem and from Beth Millo and devour Abimelech! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9021, 'And Jotham ran away and fled; and he went to Beer and dwelt there, for fear of Abimelech his brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9022, 'After Abimelech had reigned over Israel three years, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9023, 'God sent a spirit of ill will between Abimelech and the men of Shechem; and the men of Shechem dealt treacherously with Abimelech, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9024, 'that the crime done to the seventy sons of Jerubbaal might be settled and their blood be laid on Abimelech their brother, who killed them, and on the men of Shechem, who aided him in the killing of his brothers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9025, 'And the men of Shechem set men in ambush against him on the tops of the mountains, and they robbed all who passed by them along that way; and it was told Abimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9026, 'Now Gaal the son of Ebed came with his brothers and went over to Shechem; and the men of Shechem put their confidence in him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9027, 'So they went out into the fields, and gathered grapes from their vineyards and trod them, and made merry. And they went into the house of their god, and ate and drank, and cursed Abimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9028, 'Then Gaal the son of Ebed said, &ldquo;Who is Abimelech, and who is Shechem, that we should serve him? Is he not the son of Jerubbaal, and is not Zebul his officer? Serve the men of Hamor the father of Shechem; but why should we serve him? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9029, 'If only this people were under my authority! Then I would remove Abimelech.&rdquo; So he said to Abimelech, &ldquo;Increase your army and come out!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9030, 'When Zebul, the ruler of the city, heard the words of Gaal the son of Ebed, his anger was aroused. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9031, 'And he sent messengers to Abimelech secretly, saying, &ldquo;Take note! Gaal the son of Ebed and his brothers have come to Shechem; and here they are, fortifying the city against you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9032, 'Now therefore, get up by night, you and the people who are with you, and lie in wait in the field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9033, 'And it shall be, as soon as the sun is up in the morning, that you shall rise early and rush upon the city; and when he and the people who are with him come out against you, you may then do to them as you find opportunity.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9034, 'So Abimelech and all the people who were with him rose by night, and lay in wait against Shechem in four companies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9035, 'When Gaal the son of Ebed went out and stood in the entrance to the city gate, Abimelech and the people who were with him rose from lying in wait. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9036, 'And when Gaal saw the people, he said to Zebul, &ldquo;Look, people are coming down from the tops of the mountains!&rdquo; But Zebul said to him, &ldquo;You see the shadows of the mountains as if they were men.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9037, 'So Gaal spoke again and said, &ldquo;See, people are coming down from the center of the land, and another company is coming from the Diviners&rsquo; Terebinth Tree.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9038, 'Then Zebul said to him, &ldquo;Where indeed is your mouth now, with which you said, &lsquo;Who is Abimelech, that we should serve him?&rsquo; Are not these the people whom you despised? Go out, if you will, and fight with them now.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9039, 'So Gaal went out, leading the men of Shechem, and fought with Abimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9040, 'And Abimelech chased him, and he fled from him; and many fell wounded, to the very entrance of the gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9041, 'Then Abimelech dwelt at Arumah, and Zebul drove out Gaal and his brothers, so that they would not dwell in Shechem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9042, 'And it came about on the next day that the people went out into the field, and they told Abimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9043, 'So he took his people, divided them into three companies, and lay in wait in the field. And he looked, and there were the people, coming out of the city; and he rose against them and attacked them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9044, 'Then Abimelech and the company that was with him rushed forward and stood at the entrance of the gate of the city; and the other two companies rushed upon all who were in the fields and killed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9045, 'So Abimelech fought against the city all that day; he took the city and killed the people who were in it; and he demolished the city and sowed it with salt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9046, 'Now when all the men of the tower of Shechem had heard that, they entered the stronghold of the temple of the god Berith. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9047, 'And it was told Abimelech that all the men of the tower of Shechem were gathered together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9048, 'Then Abimelech went up to Mount Zalmon, he and all the people who were with him. And Abimelech took an ax in his hand and cut down a bough from the trees, and took it and laid it on his shoulder; then he said to the people who were with him, &ldquo;What you have seen me do, make haste and do as I have done.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9049, 'So each of the people likewise cut down his own bough and followed Abimelech, put them against the stronghold, and set the stronghold on fire above them, so that all the people of the tower of Shechem died, about a thousand men and women. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9050, 'Then Abimelech went to Thebez, and he encamped against Thebez and took it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9051, 'But there was a strong tower in the city, and all the men and women &ndash; all the people of the city &ndash; fled there and shut themselves in; then they went up to the top of the tower. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9052, 'So Abimelech came as far as the tower and fought against it; and he drew near the door of the tower to burn it with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9053, 'But a certain woman dropped an upper millstone on Abimelech&rsquo;s head and crushed his skull. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9054, 'Then he called quickly to the young man, his armorbearer, and said to him, &ldquo;Draw your sword and kill me, lest men say of me, &lsquo;A woman killed him.&rsquo; &ldquo; So his young man thrust him through, and he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9055, 'And when the men of Israel saw that Abimelech was dead, they departed, every man to his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9056, 'Thus God repaid the wickedness of Abimelech, which he had done to his father by killing his seventy brothers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 9057, 'And all the evil of the men of Shechem God returned on their own heads, and on them came the curse of Jotham the son of Jerubbaal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10001, 'After Abimelech there arose to save Israel Tola the son of Puah, the son of Dodo, a man of Issachar; and he dwelt in Shamir in the mountains of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10002, 'He judged Israel twenty-three years; and he died and was buried in Shamir. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10003, 'After him arose Jair, a Gileadite; and he judged Israel twenty-two years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10004, 'Now he had thirty sons who rode on thirty donkeys; they also had thirty towns, which are called &ldquo;Havoth Jair&rdquo; to this day, which are in the land of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10005, 'And Jair died and was buried in Camon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10006, 'Then the children of Israel again did evil in the sight of the Lord, and served the Baals and the Ashtoreths, the gods of Syria, the gods of Sidon, the gods of Moab, the gods of the people of Ammon, and the gods of the Philistines; and they forsook the Lord and did not serve Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10007, 'So the anger of the Lord was hot against Israel; and He sold them into the hands of the Philistines and into the hands of the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10008, 'From that year they harassed and oppressed the children of Israel for eighteen years &ndash; all the children of Israel who were on the other side of the Jordan in the land of the Amorites, in Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10009, 'Moreover the people of Ammon crossed over the Jordan to fight against Judah also, against Benjamin, and against the house of Ephraim, so that Israel was severely distressed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10010, 'And the children of Israel cried out to the Lord, saying, &ldquo;We have sinned against You, because we have both forsaken our God and served the Baals!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10011, 'So the Lord said to the children of Israel, &ldquo;Did I not deliver you from the Egyptians and from the Amorites and from the people of Ammon and from the Philistines? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10012, 'Also the Sidonians and Amalekites and Maonites oppressed you; and you cried out to Me, and I delivered you from their hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10013, 'Yet you have forsaken Me and served other gods. Therefore I will deliver you no more. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10014, 'Go and cry out to the gods which you have chosen; let them deliver you in your time of distress.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10015, 'And the children of Israel said to the Lord, &ldquo;We have sinned! Do to us whatever seems best to You; only deliver us this day, we pray.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10016, 'So they put away the foreign gods from among them and served the Lord. And His soul could no longer endure the misery of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10017, 'Then the people of Ammon gathered together and encamped in Gilead. And the children of Israel assembled together and encamped in Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 10018, 'And the people, the leaders of Gilead, said to one another, &ldquo;Who is the man who will begin the fight against the people of Ammon? He shall be head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11001, 'Now Jephthah the Gileadite was a mighty man of valor, but he was the son of a harlot; and Gilead begot Jephthah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11002, 'Gilead&rsquo;s wife bore sons; and when his wife&rsquo;s sons grew up, they drove Jephthah out, and said to him, &ldquo;You shall have no inheritance in our father&rsquo;s house, for you are the son of another woman.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11003, 'Then Jephthah fled from his brothers and dwelt in the land of Tob; and worthless men banded together with Jephthah and went out raiding with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11004, 'It came to pass after a time that the people of Ammon made war against Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11005, 'And so it was, when the people of Ammon made war against Israel, that the elders of Gilead went to get Jephthah from the land of Tob. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11006, 'Then they said to Jephthah, &ldquo;Come and be our commander, that we may fight against the people of Ammon.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11007, 'So Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, &ldquo;Did you not hate me, and expel me from my father&rsquo;s house? Why have you come to me now when you are in distress?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11008, 'And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, &ldquo;That is why we have turned again to you now, that you may go with us and fight against the people of Ammon, and be our head over all the inhabitants of Gilead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11009, 'So Jephthah said to the elders of Gilead, &ldquo;If you take me back home to fight against the people of Ammon, and the Lord delivers them to me, shall I be your head?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11010, 'And the elders of Gilead said to Jephthah, &ldquo;The Lord will be a witness between us, if we do not do according to your words.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11011, 'Then Jephthah went with the elders of Gilead, and the people made him head and commander over them; and Jephthah spoke all his words before the Lord in Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11012, 'Now Jephthah sent messengers to the king of the people of Ammon, saying, &ldquo;What do you have against me, that you have come to fight against me in my land?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11013, 'And the king of the people of Ammon answered the messengers of Jephthah, &ldquo;Because Israel took away my land when they came up out of Egypt, from the Arnon as far as the Jabbok, and to the Jordan. Now therefore, restore those lands peaceably.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11014, 'So Jephthah again sent messengers to the king of the people of Ammon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11015, 'and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says Jephthah: &lsquo;Israel did not take away the land of Moab, nor the land of the people of Ammon; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11016, 'for when Israel came up from Egypt, they walked through the wilderness as far as the Red Sea and came to Kadesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11017, 'Then Israel sent messengers to the king of Edom, saying, &ldquo;Please let me pass through your land.&rdquo; But the king of Edom would not heed. And in like manner they sent to the king of Moab, but he would not consent. So Israel remained in Kadesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11018, 'And they went along through the wilderness and bypassed the land of Edom and the land of Moab, came to the east side of the land of Moab, and encamped on the other side of the Arnon. But they did not enter the border of Moab, for the Arnon was the border of Moab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11019, 'Then Israel sent messengers to Sihon king of the Amorites, king of Heshbon; and Israel said to him, &ldquo;Please let us pass through your land into our place.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11020, 'But Sihon did not trust Israel to pass through his territory. So Sihon gathered all his people together, encamped in Jahaz, and fought against Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11021, 'And the Lord God of Israel delivered Sihon and all his people into the hand of Israel, and they defeated them. Thus Israel gained possession of all the land of the Amorites, who inhabited that country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11022, 'They took possession of all the territory of the Amorites, from the Arnon to the Jabbok and from the wilderness to the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11023, 'And now the Lord God of Israel has dispossessed the Amorites from before His people Israel; should you then possess it? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11024, 'Will you not possess whatever Chemosh your god gives you to possess? So whatever the Lord our God takes possession of before us, we will possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11025, 'And now, are you any better than Balak the son of Zippor, king of Moab? Did he ever strive against Israel? Did he ever fight against them? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11026, 'While Israel dwelt in Heshbon and its villages, in Aroer and its villages, and in all the cities along the banks of the Arnon, for three hundred years, why did you not recover them within that time? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11027, 'Therefore I have not sinned against you, but you wronged me by fighting against me. May the Lord, the Judge, render judgment this day between the children of Israel and the people of Ammon.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11028, 'However, the king of the people of Ammon did not heed the words which Jephthah sent him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11029, 'Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon Jephthah, and he passed through Gilead and Manasseh, and passed through Mizpah of Gilead; and from Mizpah of Gilead he advanced toward the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11030, 'And Jephthah made a vow to the Lord, and said, &ldquo;If You will indeed deliver the people of Ammon into my hands, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11031, 'then it will be that whatever comes out of the doors of my house to meet me, when I return in peace from the people of Ammon, shall surely be the Lord&rsquo;s, and I will offer it up as a burnt offering.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11032, 'So Jephthah advanced toward the people of Ammon to fight against them, and the Lord delivered them into his hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11033, 'And he defeated them from Aroer as far as Minnith &ndash; twenty cities &ndash; and to Abel Keramim, with a very great slaughter. Thus the people of Ammon were subdued before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11034, 'When Jephthah came to his house at Mizpah, there was his daughter, coming out to meet him with timbrels and dancing; and she was his only child. Besides her he had neither son nor daughter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11035, 'And it came to pass, when he saw her, that he tore his clothes, and said, &ldquo;Alas, my daughter! You have brought me very low! You are among those who trouble me! For I have given my word to the Lord, and I cannot go back on it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11036, 'So she said to him, &ldquo;My father, if you have given your word to the Lord, do to me according to what has gone out of your mouth, because the Lord has avenged you of your enemies, the people of Ammon.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11037, 'Then she said to her father, &ldquo;Let this thing be done for me: let me alone for two months, that I may go and wander on the mountains and bewail my virginity, my friends and I.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11038, 'So he said, &ldquo;Go.&rdquo; And he sent her away for two months; and she went with her friends, and bewailed her virginity on the mountains. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11039, 'And it was so at the end of two months that she returned to her father, and he carried out his vow with her which he had vowed. She knew no man. And it became a custom in Israel ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 11040, 'that the daughters of Israel went four days each year to lament the daughter of Jephthah the Gileadite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12001, 'Then the men of Ephraim gathered together, crossed over toward Zaphon, and said to Jephthah, &ldquo;Why did you cross over to fight against the people of Ammon, and did not call us to go with you? We will burn your house down on you with fire!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12002, 'And Jephthah said to them, &ldquo;My people and I were in a great struggle with the people of Ammon; and when I called you, you did not deliver me out of their hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12003, 'So when I saw that you would not deliver me, I took my life in my hands and crossed over against the people of Ammon; and the Lord delivered them into my hand. Why then have you come up to me this day to fight against me?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12004, 'Now Jephthah gathered together all the men of Gilead and fought against Ephraim. And the men of Gilead defeated Ephraim, because they said, &ldquo;You Gileadites are fugitives of Ephraim among the Ephraimites and among the Manassites.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12005, 'The Gileadites seized the fords of the Jordan before the Ephraimites arrived. And when any Ephraimite who escaped said, &ldquo;Let me cross over,&rdquo; the men of Gilead would say to him, &ldquo;Are you an Ephraimite?&rdquo; If he said, &ldquo;No,&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12006, 'then they would say to him, &ldquo;Then say, &lsquo;Shibboleth&rsquo;!&rdquo; And he would say, &ldquo;Sibboleth,&rdquo; for he could not pronounce it right. Then they would take him and kill him at the fords of the Jordan. There fell at that time forty-two thousand Ephraimites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12007, 'And Jephthah judged Israel six years. Then Jephthah the Gileadite died and was buried in among the cities of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12008, 'After him, Ibzan of Bethlehem judged Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12009, 'He had thirty sons. And he gave away thirty daughters in marriage, and brought in thirty daughters from elsewhere for his sons. He judged Israel seven years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12010, 'Then Ibzan died and was buried at Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12011, 'After him, Elon the Zebulunite judged Israel. He judged Israel ten years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12012, 'And Elon the Zebulunite died and was buried at Aijalon in the country of Zebulun. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12013, 'After him, Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite judged Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12014, 'He had forty sons and thirty grandsons, who rode on seventy young donkeys. He judged Israel eight years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 12015, 'Then Abdon the son of Hillel the Pirathonite died and was buried in Pirathon in the land of Ephraim, in the mountains of the Amalekites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13001, 'Again the children of Israel did evil in the sight of the Lord, and the Lord delivered them into the hand of the Philistines for forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13002, 'Now there was a certain man from Zorah, of the family of the Danites, whose name was Manoah; and his wife was barren and had no children. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13003, 'And the Angel of the Lord appeared to the woman and said to her, &ldquo;Indeed now, you are barren and have borne no children, but you shall conceive and bear a son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13004, 'Now therefore, please be careful not to drink wine or similar drink, and not to eat anything unclean. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13005, 'For behold, you shall conceive and bear a son. And no razor shall come upon his head, for the child shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb; and he shall begin to deliver Israel out of the hand of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13006, 'So the woman came and told her husband, saying, &ldquo;A Man of God came to me, and His countenance was like the countenance of the Angel of God, very awesome; but I did not ask Him where He was from, and He did not tell me His name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13007, 'And He said to me, &lsquo;Behold, you shall conceive and bear a son. Now drink no wine or similar drink, nor eat anything unclean, for the child shall be a Nazirite to God from the womb to the day of his death.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13008, 'Then Manoah prayed to the Lord, and said, &ldquo;O my Lord, please let the Man of God whom You sent come to us again and teach us what we shall do for the child who will be born.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13009, 'And God listened to the voice of Manoah, and the Angel of God came to the woman again as she was sitting in the field; but Manoah her husband was not with her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13010, 'Then the woman ran in haste and told her husband, and said to him, &ldquo;Look, the Man who came to me the other day has just now appeared to me!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13011, 'So Manoah arose and followed his wife. When he came to the Man, he said to Him, &ldquo;Are You the Man who spoke to this woman?&rdquo; And He said, &ldquo;I am.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13012, 'Manoah said, &ldquo;Now let Your words come to pass! What will be the boy&rsquo;s rule of life, and his work?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13013, 'So the Angel of the Lord said to Manoah, &ldquo;Of all that I said to the woman let her be careful. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13014, 'She may not eat anything that comes from the vine, nor may she drink wine or similar drink, nor eat anything unclean. All that I commanded her let her observe.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13015, 'Then Manoah said to the Angel of the Lord, &ldquo;Please let us detain You, and we will prepare a young goat for You.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13016, 'And the Angel of the Lord said to Manoah, &ldquo;Though you detain Me, I will not eat your food. But if you offer a burnt offering, you must offer it to the Lord.&rdquo; (For Manoah did not know He was the Angel of the Lord.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13017, 'Then Manoah said to the Angel of the Lord, &ldquo;What is Your name, that when Your words come to pass we may honor You?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13018, 'And the Angel of the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Why do you ask My name, seeing it is wonderful?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13019, 'So Manoah took the young goat with the grain offering, and offered it upon the rock to the Lord. And He did a wondrous thing while Manoah and his wife looked on &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13020, 'it happened as the flame went up toward heaven from the altar &ndash; the Angel of the Lord ascended in the flame of the altar! When Manoah and his wife saw this, they fell on their faces to the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13021, 'When the Angel of the Lord appeared no more to Manoah and his wife, then Manoah knew that He was the Angel of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13022, 'And Manoah said to his wife, &ldquo;We shall surely die, because we have seen God!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13023, 'But his wife said to him, &ldquo;If the Lord had desired to kill us, He would not have accepted a burnt offering and a grain offering from our hands, nor would He have shown us all these things, nor would He have told us such things as these at this time.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13024, 'So the woman bore a son and called his name Samson; and the child grew, and the Lord blessed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 13025, 'And the Spirit of the Lord began to move upon him at Mahaneh Dan between Zorah and Eshtaol. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14001, 'Now Samson went down to Timnah, and saw a woman in Timnah of the daughters of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14002, 'So he went up and told his father and mother, saying, &ldquo;I have seen a woman in Timnah of the daughters of the Philistines; now therefore, get her for me as a wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14003, 'Then his father and mother said to him, &ldquo;Is there no woman among the daughters of your brethren, or among all my people, that you must go and get a wife from the uncircumcised Philistines?&rdquo; And Samson said to his father, &ldquo;Get her for me, for she pleases me well.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14004, 'But his father and mother did not know that it was of the Lord &ndash; that He was seeking an occasion to move against the Philistines. For at that time the Philistines had dominion over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14005, 'So Samson went down to Timnah with his father and mother, and came to the vineyards of Timnah.Now to his surprise, a young lion came roaring against him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14006, 'And the Spirit of the Lord came mightily upon him, and he tore the lion apart as one would have torn apart a young goat, though he had nothing in his hand. But he did not tell his father or his mother what he had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14007, 'Then he went down and talked with the woman; and she pleased Samson well. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14008, 'After some time, when he returned to get her, he turned aside to see the carcass of the lion. And behold, a swarm of bees and honey were in the carcass of the lion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14009, 'He took some of it in his hands and went along, eating. When he came to his father and mother, he gave some to them, and they also ate. But he did not tell them that he had taken the honey out of the carcass of the lion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14010, 'So his father went down to the woman. And Samson gave a feast there, for young men used to do so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14011, 'And it happened, when they saw him, that they brought thirty companions to be with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14012, 'Then Samson said to them, &ldquo;Let me pose a riddle to you. If you can correctly solve and explain it to me within the seven days of the feast, then I will give you thirty linen garments and thirty changes of clothing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14013, 'But if you cannot explain it to me, then you shall give me thirty linen garments and thirty changes of clothing.&rdquo; And they said to him, &ldquo;Pose your riddle, that we may hear it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14014, 'So he said to them: &ldquo;Out of the eater came something to eat, And out of the strong came something sweet.&rdquo; Now for three days they could not explain the riddle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14015, 'But it came to pass on the seventh day that they said to Samson&rsquo;s wife, &ldquo;Entice your husband, that he may explain the riddle to us, or else we will burn you and your father&rsquo;s house with fire. Have you invited us in order to take what is ours? Is that not so?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14016, 'Then Samson&rsquo;s wife wept on him, and said, &ldquo;You only hate me! You do not love me! You have posed a riddle to the sons of my people, but you have not explained it to me.&rdquo; And he said to her, &ldquo;Look, I have not explained it to my father or my mother; so should I explain it to you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14017, 'Now she had wept on him the seven days while their feast lasted. And it happened on the seventh day that he told her, because she pressed him so much. Then she explained the riddle to the sons of her people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14018, 'So the men of the city said to him on the seventh day before the sun went down: &ldquo;What is sweeter than honey? And what is stronger than a lion?&rdquo; And he said to them: &ldquo;If you had not plowed with my heifer, You would not have solved my riddle!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14019, 'Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon him mightily, and he went down to Ashkelon and killed thirty of their men, took their apparel, and gave the changes of clothing to those who had explained the riddle. So his anger was aroused, and he went back up to his father&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 14020, 'And Samson&rsquo;s wife was given to his companion, who had been his best man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15001, 'After a while, in the time of wheat harvest, it happened that Samson visited his wife with a young goat. And he said, &ldquo;Let me go in to my wife, into her room.&rdquo; But her father would not permit him to go in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15002, 'Her father said, &ldquo;I really thought that you thoroughly hated her; therefore I gave her to your companion. Is not her younger sister better than she? Please, take her instead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15003, 'And Samson said to them, &ldquo;This time I shall be blameless regarding the Philistines if I harm them!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15004, 'Then Samson went and caught three hundred foxes; and he took torches, turned the foxes tail to tail, and put a torch between each pair of tails. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15005, 'When he had set the torches on fire, he let the foxes go into the standing grain of the Philistines, and burned up both the shocks and the standing grain, as well as the vineyards and olive groves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15006, 'Then the Philistines said, &ldquo;Who has done this?&rdquo; And they answered, &ldquo;Samson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he has taken his wife and given her to his companion.&rdquo; So the Philistines came up and burned her and her father with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15007, 'Samson said to them, &ldquo;Since you would do a thing like this, I will surely take revenge on you, and after that I will cease.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15008, 'So he attacked them hip and thigh with a great slaughter; then he went down and dwelt in the cleft of the rock of Etam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15009, 'Now the Philistines went up, encamped in Judah, and deployed themselves against Lehi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15010, 'And the men of Judah said, &ldquo;Why have you come up against us?&rdquo; So they answered, &ldquo;We have come up to arrest Samson, to do to him as he has done to us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15011, 'Then three thousand men of Judah went down to the cleft of the rock of Etam, and said to Samson, &ldquo;Do you not know that the Philistines rule over us? What is this you have done to us?&rdquo; And he said to them, &ldquo;As they did to me, so I have done to them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15012, 'But they said to him, &ldquo;We have come down to arrest you, that we may deliver you into the hand of the Philistines.&rdquo; Then Samson said to them, &ldquo;Swear to me that you will not kill me yourselves.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15013, 'So they spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;No, but we will tie you securely and deliver you into their hand; but we will surely not kill you.&rdquo; And they bound him with two new ropes and brought him up from the rock. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15014, 'When he came to Lehi, the Philistines came shouting against him. Then the Spirit of the Lord came mightily upon him; and the ropes that were on his arms became like flax that is burned with fire, and his bonds broke loose from his hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15015, 'He found a fresh jawbone of a donkey, reached out his hand and took it, and killed a thousand men with it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15016, 'Then Samson said: &ldquo;With the jawbone of a donkey, Heaps upon heaps, With the jawbone of a donkey I have slain a thousand men!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15017, 'And so it was, when he had finished speaking, that he threw the jawbone from his hand, and called that place Ramath Lehi.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15018, 'Then he became very thirsty; so he cried out to the Lord and said, &ldquo;You have given this great deliverance by the hand of Your servant; and now shall I die of thirst and fall into the hand of the uncircumcised?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15019, 'So God split the hollow place that is in Lehi, and water came out, and he drank; and his spirit returned, and he revived. Therefore he called its name En Hakkore, which is in Lehi to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 15020, 'And he judged Israel twenty years in the days of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16001, 'Now Samson went to Gaza and saw a harlot there, and went in to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16002, 'When the Gazites were told, &ldquo;Samson has come here!&rdquo; they surrounded the place and lay in wait for him all night at the gate of the city. They were quiet all night, saying, &ldquo;In the morning, when it is daylight, we will kill him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16003, 'And Samson lay low till midnight; then he arose at midnight, took hold of the doors of the gate of the city and the two gateposts, pulled them up, bar and all, put them on his shoulders, and carried them to the top of the hill that faces Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16004, 'Afterward it happened that he loved a woman in the Valley of Sorek, whose name was Delilah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16005, 'And the lords of the Philistines came up to her and said to her, &ldquo;Entice him, and find out where his great strength lies, and by what means we may overpower him, that we may bind him to afflict him; and every one of us will give you eleven hundred pieces of silver.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16006, 'So Delilah said to Samson, &ldquo;Please tell me where your great strength lies, and with what you may be bound to afflict you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16007, 'And Samson said to her, &ldquo;If they bind me with seven fresh bowstrings, not yet dried, then I shall become weak, and be like any other man.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16008, 'So the lords of the Philistines brought up to her seven fresh bowstrings, not yet dried, and she bound him with them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16009, 'Now men were lying in wait, staying with her in the room. And she said to him, &ldquo;The Philistines are upon you, Samson!&rdquo; But he broke the bowstrings as a strand of yarn breaks when it touches fire. So the secret of his strength was not known. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16010, 'Then Delilah said to Samson, &ldquo;Look, you have mocked me and told me lies. Now, please tell me what you may be bound with.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16011, 'So he said to her, &ldquo;If they bind me securely with new ropes that have never been used, then I shall become weak, and be like any other man.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16012, 'Therefore Delilah took new ropes and bound him with them, and said to him, &ldquo;The Philistines are upon you, Samson!&rdquo; And men were lying in wait, staying in the room. But he broke them off his arms like a thread. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16013, 'Delilah said to Samson, &ldquo;Until now you have mocked me and told me lies. Tell me what you may be bound with.&rdquo; And he said to her, &ldquo;If you weave the seven locks of my head into the web of the loom&rdquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16014, 'So she wove it tightly with the batten of the loom, and said to him, &ldquo;The Philistines are upon you, Samson!&rdquo; But he awoke from his sleep, and pulled out the batten and the web from the loom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16015, 'Then she said to him, &ldquo;How can you say, &lsquo;I love you,&rsquo; when your heart is not with me? You have mocked me these three times, and have not told me where your great strength lies.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16016, 'And it came to pass, when she pestered him daily with her words and pressed him, so that his soul was vexed to death, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16017, 'that he told her all his heart, and said to her, &ldquo;No razor has ever come upon my head, for I have been a Nazirite to God from my mother&rsquo;s womb. If I am shaven, then my strength will leave me, and I shall become weak, and be like any other man.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16018, 'When Delilah saw that he had told her all his heart, she sent and called for the lords of the Philistines, saying, &ldquo;Come up once more, for he has told me all his heart.&rdquo; So the lords of the Philistines came up to her and brought the money in their hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16019, 'Then she lulled him to sleep on her knees, and called for a man and had him shave off the seven locks of his head. Then she began to torment him, and his strength left him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16020, 'And she said, &ldquo;The Philistines are upon you, Samson!&rdquo; So he awoke from his sleep, and said, &ldquo;I will go out as before, at other times, and shake myself free!&rdquo; But he did not know that the Lord had departed from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16021, 'Then the Philistines took him and put out his eyes, and brought him down to Gaza. They bound him with bronze fetters, and he became a grinder in the prison. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16022, 'However, the hair of his head began to grow again after it had been shaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16023, 'Now the lords of the Philistines gathered together to offer a great sacrifice to Dagon their god, and to rejoice. And they said: &ldquo;Our god has delivered into our hands Samson our enemy!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16024, 'When the people saw him, they praised their god; for they said: &ldquo;Our god has delivered into our hands our enemy, The destroyer of our land, And the one who multiplied our dead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16025, 'So it happened, when their hearts were merry, that they said, &ldquo;Call for Samson, that he may perform for us.&rdquo; So they called for Samson from the prison, and he performed for them. And they stationed him between the pillars. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16026, 'Then Samson said to the lad who held him by the hand, &ldquo;Let me feel the pillars which support the temple, so that I can lean on them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16027, 'Now the temple was full of men and women. All the lords of the Philistines were there &ndash; about three thousand men and women on the roof watching while Samson performed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16028, 'Then Samson called to the Lord, saying, &ldquo;O Lord God, remember me, I pray! Strengthen me, I pray, just this once, O God, that I may with one blow take vengeance on the Philistines for my two eyes!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16029, 'And Samson took hold of the two middle pillars which supported the temple, and he braced himself against them, one on his right and the other on his left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16030, 'Then Samson said, &ldquo;Let me die with the Philistines!&rdquo; And he pushed with all his might, and the temple fell on the lords and all the people who were in it. So the dead that he killed at his death were more than he had killed in his life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 16031, 'And his brothers and all his father&rsquo;s household came down and took him, and brought him up and buried him between Zorah and Eshtaol in the tomb of his father Manoah. He had judged Israel twenty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17001, 'Now there was a man from the mountains of Ephraim, whose name was Micah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17002, 'And he said to his mother, &ldquo;The eleven hundred shekels of silver that were taken from you, and on which you put a curse, even saying it in my ears &ndash; here is the silver with me; I took it.&rdquo; And his mother said, &ldquo;May you be blessed by the Lord, my son!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17003, 'So when he had returned the eleven hundred shekels of silver to his mother, his mother said, &ldquo;I had wholly dedicated the silver from my hand to the Lord for my son, to make a carved image and a molded image; now therefore, I will return it to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17004, 'Thus he returned the silver to his mother. Then his mother took two hundred shekels of silver and gave them to the silversmith, and he made it into a carved image and a molded image; and they were in the house of Micah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17005, 'The man Micah had a shrine, and made an ephod and household idols; and he consecrated one of his sons, who became his priest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17006, 'In those days there was no king in Israel; everyone did what was right in his own eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17007, 'Now there was a young man from Bethlehem in Judah, of the family of Judah; he was a Levite, and was staying there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17008, 'The man departed from the city of Bethlehem in Judah to stay wherever he could find a place. Then he came to the mountains of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, as he journeyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17009, 'And Micah said to him, &ldquo;Where do you come from?&rdquo; So he said to him, &ldquo;I am a Levite from Bethlehem in Judah, and I am on my way to find a place to stay.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17010, 'Micah said to him, &ldquo;Dwell with me, and be a father and a priest to me, and I will give you ten shekels of silver per year, a suit of clothes, and your sustenance.&rdquo; So the Levite went in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17011, 'Then the Levite was content to dwell with the man; and the young man became like one of his sons to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17012, 'So Micah consecrated the Levite, and the young man became his priest, and lived in the house of Micah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 17013, 'Then Micah said, &ldquo;Now I know that the Lord will be good to me, since I have a Levite as priest!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18001, 'In those days there was no king in Israel. And in those days the tribe of the Danites was seeking an inheritance for itself to dwell in; for until that day their inheritance among the tribes of Israel had not fallen to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18002, 'So the children of Dan sent five men of their family from their territory, men of valor from Zorah and Eshtaol, to spy out the land and search it. They said to them, &ldquo;Go, search the land.&rdquo; So they went to the mountains of Ephraim, to the house of Micah, and lodged there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18003, 'While they were at the house of Micah, they recognized the voice of the young Levite. They turned aside and said to him, &ldquo;Who brought you here? What are you doing in this place? What do you have here?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18004, 'He said to them, &ldquo;Thus and so Micah did for me. He has hired me, and I have become his priest.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18005, 'So they said to him, &ldquo;Please inquire of God, that we may know whether the journey on which we go will be prosperous.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18006, 'And the priest said to them, &ldquo;Go in peace. The presence of the Lord be with you on your way.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18007, 'So the five men departed and went to Laish. They saw the people who were there, how they dwelt safely, in the manner of the Sidonians, quiet and secure. There were no rulers in the land who might put them to shame for anything. They were far from the Sidonians, and they had no ties with anyone.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18008, 'Then the spies came back to their brethren at Zorah and Eshtaol, and their brethren said to them, &ldquo;What is your report?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18009, 'So they said, &ldquo;Arise, let us go up against them. For we have seen the land, and indeed it is very good. Would you do nothing? Do not hesitate to go, and enter to possess the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18010, 'When you go, you will come to a secure people and a large land. For God has given it into your hands, a place where there is no lack of anything that is on the earth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18011, 'And six hundred men of the family of the Danites went from there, from Zorah and Eshtaol, armed with weapons of war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18012, 'Then they went up and encamped in Kirjath Jearim in Judah. (Therefore they call that place Mahaneh Dan to this day. There it is, west of Kirjath Jearim.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18013, 'And they passed from there to the mountains of Ephraim, and came to the house of Micah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18014, 'Then the five men who had gone to spy out the country of Laish answered and said to their brethren, &ldquo;Do you know that there are in these houses an ephod, household idols, a carved image, and a molded image? Now therefore, consider what you should do.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18015, 'So they turned aside there, and came to the house of the young Levite man &ndash; to the house of Micah &ndash; and greeted him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18016, 'The six hundred men armed with their weapons of war, who were of the children of Dan, stood by the entrance of the gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18017, 'Then the five men who had gone to spy out the land went up. Entering there, they took the carved image, the ephod, the household idols, and the molded image. The priest stood at the entrance of the gate with the six hundred men who were armed with weapons of war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18018, 'When these went into Micah&rsquo;s house and took the carved image, the ephod, the household idols, and the molded image, the priest said to them, &ldquo;What are you doing?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18019, 'And they said to him, &ldquo;Be quiet, put your hand over your mouth, and come with us; be a father and a priest to us. Is it better for you to be a priest to the household of one man, or that you be a priest to a tribe and a family in Israel?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18020, 'So the priest&rsquo;s heart was glad; and he took the ephod, the household idols, and the carved image, and took his place among the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18021, 'Then they turned and departed, and put the little ones, the livestock, and the goods in front of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18022, 'When they were a good way from the house of Micah, the men who were in the houses near Micah&rsquo;s house gathered together and overtook the children of Dan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18023, 'And they called out to the children of Dan. So they turned around and said to Micah, &ldquo;What ails you, that you have gathered such a company?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18024, 'So he said, &ldquo;You have taken away my gods which I made, and the priest, and you have gone away. Now what more do I have? How can you say to me, &lsquo;What ails you?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18025, 'And the children of Dan said to him, &ldquo;Do not let your voice be heard among us, lest angry men fall upon you, and you lose your life, with the lives of your household!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18026, 'Then the children of Dan went their way. And when Micah saw that they were too strong for him, he turned and went back to his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18027, 'So they took the things Micah had made, and the priest who had belonged to him, and went to Laish, to a people quiet and secure; and they struck them with the edge of the sword and burned the city with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18028, 'There was no deliverer, because it was far from Sidon, and they had no ties with anyone. It was in the valley that belongs to Beth Rehob. So they rebuilt the city and dwelt there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18029, 'And they called the name of the city Dan, after the name of Dan their father, who was born to Israel. However, the name of the city formerly was Laish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18030, 'Then the children of Dan set up for themselves the carved image; and Jonathan the son of Gershom, the son of Manasseh, and his sons were priests to the tribe of Dan until the day of the captivity of the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 18031, 'So they set up for themselves Micah&rsquo;s carved image which he made, all the time that the house of God was in Shiloh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19001, 'And it came to pass in those days, when there was no king in Israel, that there was a certain Levite staying in the remote mountains of Ephraim. He took for himself a concubine from Bethlehem in Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19002, 'But his concubine played the harlot against him, and went away from him to her father&rsquo;s house at Bethlehem in Judah, and was there four whole months. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19003, 'Then her husband arose and went after her, to speak kindly to her and bring her back, having his servant and a couple of donkeys with him. So she brought him into her father&rsquo;s house; and when the father of the young woman saw him, he was glad to meet him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19004, 'Now his father-in-law, the young woman&rsquo;s father, detained him; and he stayed with him three days. So they ate and drank and lodged there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19005, 'Then it came to pass on the fourth day that they arose early in the morning, and he stood to depart; but the young woman&rsquo;s father said to his son-in-law, &ldquo;Refresh your heart with a morsel of bread, and afterward go your way.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19006, 'So they sat down, and the two of them ate and drank together. Then the young woman&rsquo;s father said to the man, &ldquo;Please be content to stay all night, and let your heart be merry.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19007, 'And when the man stood to depart, his father-in-law urged him; so he lodged there again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19008, 'Then he arose early in the morning on the fifth day to depart, but the young woman&rsquo;s father said, &ldquo;Please refresh your heart.&rdquo; So they delayed until afternoon; and both of them ate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19009, 'And when the man stood to depart &ndash; he and his concubine and his servant &ndash; his father-in-law, the young woman&rsquo;s father, said to him, &ldquo;Look, the day is now drawing toward evening; please spend the night. See, the day is coming to an end; lodge here, that your heart may be merry. Tomorrow go your way early, so that you may get home.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19010, 'However, the man was not willing to spend that night; so he rose and departed, and came to opposite Jebus (that is, Jerusalem). With him were the two saddled donkeys; his concubine was also with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19011, 'They were near Jebus, and the day was far spent; and the servant said to his master, &ldquo;Come, please, and let us turn aside into this city of the Jebusites and lodge in it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19012, 'But his master said to him, &ldquo;We will not turn aside here into a city of foreigners, who are not of the children of Israel; we will go on to Gibeah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19013, 'So he said to his servant, &ldquo;Come, let us draw near to one of these places, and spend the night in Gibeah or in Ramah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19014, 'And they passed by and went their way; and the sun went down on them near Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19015, 'They turned aside there to go in to lodge in Gibeah. And when he went in, he sat down in the open square of the city, for no one would take them into his house to spend the night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19016, 'Just then an old man came in from his work in the field at evening, who also was from the mountains of Ephraim; he was staying in Gibeah, whereas the men of the place were Benjamites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19017, 'And when he raised his eyes, he saw the traveler in the open square of the city; and the old man said, &ldquo;Where are you going, and where do you come from?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19018, 'So he said to him, &ldquo;We are passing from Bethlehem in Judah toward the remote mountains of Ephraim; I am from there. I went to Bethlehem in Judah; now I am going to the house of the Lord. But there is no one who will take me into his house, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19019, 'although we have both straw and fodder for our donkeys, and bread and wine for myself, for your female servant, and for the young man who is with your servant; there is no lack of anything.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19020, 'And the old man said, &ldquo;Peace be with you! However, let all your needs be my responsibility; only do not spend the night in the open square.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19021, 'So he brought him into his house, and gave fodder to the donkeys. And they washed their feet, and ate and drank. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19022, 'As they were enjoying themselves, suddenly certain men of the city, perverted men, surrounded the house and beat on the door. They spoke to the master of the house, the old man, saying, &ldquo;Bring out the man who came to your house, that we may know him carnally!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19023, 'But the man, the master of the house, went out to them and said to them, &ldquo;No, my brethren! I beg you, do not act so wickedly! Seeing this man has come into my house, do not commit this outrage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19024, 'Look, here is my virgin daughter and the man&rsquo;s concubine; let me bring them out now. Humble them, and do with them as you please; but to this man do not do such a vile thing!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19025, 'But the men would not heed him. So the man took his concubine and brought her out to them. And they knew her and abused her all night until morning; and when the day began to break, they let her go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19026, 'Then the woman came as the day was dawning, and fell down at the door of the man&rsquo;s house where her master was, till it was light. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19027, 'When her master arose in the morning, and opened the doors of the house and went out to go his way, there was his concubine, fallen at the door of the house with her hands on the threshold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19028, 'And he said to her, &ldquo;Get up and let us be going.&rdquo; But there was no answer. So the man lifted her onto the donkey; and the man got up and went to his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19029, 'When he entered his house he took a knife, laid hold of his concubine, and divided her into twelve pieces, limb by limb, and sent her throughout all the territory of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 19030, 'And so it was that all who saw it said, &ldquo;No such deed has been done or seen from the day that the children of Israel came up from the land of Egypt until this day. Consider it, confer, and speak up!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20001, 'So all the children of Israel came out, from Dan to Beersheba, as well as from the land of Gilead, and the congregation gathered together as one man before the Lord at Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20002, 'And the leaders of all the people, all the tribes of Israel, presented themselves in the assembly of the people of God, four hundred thousand foot soldiers who drew the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20003, '(Now the children of Benjamin heard that the children of Israel had gone up to Mizpah.) Then the children of Israel said, &ldquo;Tell us, how did this wicked deed happen?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20004, 'So the Levite, the husband of the woman who was murdered, answered and said, &ldquo;My concubine and I went into Gibeah, which belongs to Benjamin, to spend the night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20005, 'And the men of Gibeah rose against me, and surrounded the house at night because of me. They intended to kill me, but instead they ravished my concubine so that she died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20006, 'So I took hold of my concubine, cut her in pieces, and sent her throughout all the territory of the inheritance of Israel, because they committed lewdness and outrage in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20007, 'Look! All of you are children of Israel; give your advice and counsel here and now!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20008, 'So all the people arose as one man, saying, &ldquo;None of us will go to his tent, nor will any turn back to his house; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20009, 'but now this is the thing which we will do to Gibeah: We will go up against it by lot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20010, 'We will take ten men out of every hundred throughout all the tribes of Israel, a hundred out of every thousand, and a thousand out of every ten thousand, to make provisions for the people, that when they come to Gibeah in Benjamin, they may repay all the vileness that they have done in Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20011, 'So all the men of Israel were gathered against the city, united together as one man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20012, 'Then the tribes of Israel sent men through all the tribe of Benjamin, saying, &ldquo;What is this wickedness that has occurred among you? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20013, 'Now therefore, deliver up the men, the perverted men who are in Gibeah, that we may put them to death and remove the evil from Israel!&rdquo; But the children of Benjamin would not listen to the voice of their brethren, the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20014, 'Instead, the children of Benjamin gathered together from their cities to Gibeah, to go to battle against the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20015, 'And from their cities at that time the children of Benjamin numbered twenty-six thousand men who drew the sword, besides the inhabitants of Gibeah, who numbered seven hundred select men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20016, 'Among all this people were seven hundred select men who were left-handed; every one could sling a stone at a hair&rsquo;s breadth and not miss. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20017, 'Now besides Benjamin, the men of Israel numbered four hundred thousand men who drew the sword; all of these were men of war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20018, 'Then the children of Israel arose and went up to the house of God to inquire of God. They said, &ldquo;Which of us shall go up first to battle against the children of Benjamin?&rdquo; The Lord said, &ldquo;Judah first!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20019, 'So the children of Israel rose in the morning and encamped against Gibeah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20020, 'And the men of Israel went out to battle against Benjamin, and the men of Israel put themselves in battle array to fight against them at Gibeah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20021, 'Then the children of Benjamin came out of Gibeah, and on that day cut down to the ground twenty-two thousand men of the Israelites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20022, 'And the people, that is, the men of Israel, encouraged themselves and again formed the battle line at the place where they had put themselves in array on the first day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20023, 'Then the children of Israel went up and wept before the Lord until evening, and asked counsel of the Lord, saying, &ldquo;Shall I again draw near for battle against the children of my brother Benjamin?&rdquo; And the Lord said, &ldquo;Go up against him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20024, 'So the children of Israel approached the children of Benjamin on the second day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20025, 'And Benjamin went out against them from Gibeah on the second day, and cut down to the ground eighteen thousand more of the children of Israel; all these drew the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20026, 'Then all the children of Israel, that is, all the people, went up and came to the house of God and wept. They sat there before the Lord and fasted that day until evening; and they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20027, 'So the children of Israel inquired of the Lord (the ark of the covenant of God was there in those days, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20028, 'and Phinehas the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron, stood before it in those days), saying, &ldquo;Shall I yet again go out to battle against the children of my brother Benjamin, or shall I cease?&rdquo; And the Lord said, &ldquo;Go up, for tomorrow I will deliver them into your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20029, 'Then Israel set men in ambush all around Gibeah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20030, 'And the children of Israel went up against the children of Benjamin on the third day, and put themselves in battle array against Gibeah as at the other times. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20031, 'So the children of Benjamin went out against the people, and were drawn away from the city. They began to strike down and kill some of the people, as at the other times, in the highways (one of which goes up to Bethel and the other to Gibeah) and in the field, about thirty men of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20032, 'And the children of Benjamin said, &ldquo;They are defeated before us, as at first.&rdquo; But the children of Israel said, &ldquo;Let us flee and draw them away from the city to the highways.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20033, 'So all the men of Israel rose from their place and put themselves in battle array at Baal Tamar. Then Israel&rsquo;s men in ambush burst forth from their position in the plain of Geba. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20034, 'And ten thousand select men from all Israel came against Gibeah, and the battle was fierce. But the Benjamites did not know that disaster was upon them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20035, 'The Lord defeated Benjamin before Israel. And the children of Israel destroyed that day twenty-five thousand one hundred Benjamites; all these drew the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20036, 'So the children of Benjamin saw that they were defeated. The men of Israel had given ground to the Benjamites, because they relied on the men in ambush whom they had set against Gibeah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20037, 'And the men in ambush quickly rushed upon Gibeah; the men in ambush spread out and struck the whole city with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20038, 'Now the appointed signal between the men of Israel and the men in ambush was that they would make a great cloud of smoke rise up from the city, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20039, 'whereupon the men of Israel would turn in battle. Now Benjamin had begun to strike and kill about thirty of the men of Israel. For they said, &ldquo;Surely they are defeated before us, as in the first battle.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20040, 'But when the cloud began to rise from the city in a column of smoke, the Benjamites looked behind them, and there was the whole city going up in smoke to heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20041, 'And when the men of Israel turned back, the men of Benjamin panicked, for they saw that disaster had come upon them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20042, 'Therefore they turned their backs before the men of Israel in the direction of the wilderness; but the battle overtook them, and whoever came out of the cities they destroyed in their midst. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20043, 'They surrounded the Benjamites, chased them, and easily trampled them down as far as the front of Gibeah toward the east. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20044, 'And eighteen thousand men of Benjamin fell; all these were men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20045, 'Then they turned and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon; and they cut down five thousand of them on the highways. Then they pursued them relentlessly up to Gidom, and killed two thousand of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20046, 'So all who fell of Benjamin that day were twenty-five thousand men who drew the sword; all these were men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20047, 'But six hundred men turned and fled toward the wilderness to the rock of Rimmon, and they stayed at the rock of Rimmon for four months. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 20048, 'And the men of Israel turned back against the children of Benjamin, and struck them down with the edge of the sword &ndash; from every city, men and beasts, all who were found. They also set fire to all the cities they came to. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21001, 'Now the men of Israel had sworn an oath at Mizpah, saying, &ldquo;None of us shall give his daughter to Benjamin as a wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21002, 'Then the people came to the house of God, and remained there before God till evening. They lifted up their voices and wept bitterly, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21003, 'and said, &ldquo;O Lord God of Israel, why has this come to pass in Israel, that today there should be one tribe missing in Israel?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21004, 'So it was, on the next morning, that the people rose early and built an altar there, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21005, 'The children of Israel said, &ldquo;Who is there among all the tribes of Israel who did not come up with the assembly to the Lord?&rdquo; For they had made a great oath concerning anyone who had not come up to the Lord at Mizpah, saying, &ldquo;He shall surely be put to death.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21006, 'And the children of Israel grieved for Benjamin their brother, and said, &ldquo;One tribe is cut off from Israel today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21007, 'What shall we do for wives for those who remain, seeing we have sworn by the Lord that we will not give them our daughters as wives?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21008, 'And they said, &ldquo;What one is there from the tribes of Israel who did not come up to Mizpah to the Lord?&rdquo; And, in fact, no one had come to the camp from Jabesh Gilead to the assembly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21009, 'For when the people were counted, indeed, not one of the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead was there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21010, 'So the congregation sent out there twelve thousand of their most valiant men, and commanded them, saying, &ldquo;Go and strike the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead with the edge of the sword, including the women and children. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21011, 'And this is the thing that you shall do: You shall utterly destroy every male, and every woman who has known a man intimately.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21012, 'So they found among the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead four hundred young virgins who had not known a man intimately; and they brought them to the camp at Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21013, 'Then the whole congregation sent word to the children of Benjamin who were at the rock of Rimmon, and announced peace to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21014, 'So Benjamin came back at that time, and they gave them the women whom they had saved alive of the women of Jabesh Gilead; and yet they had not found enough for them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21015, 'And the people grieved for Benjamin, because the Lord had made a void in the tribes of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21016, 'Then the elders of the congregation said, &ldquo;What shall we do for wives for those who remain, since the women of Benjamin have been destroyed?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21017, 'And they said, &ldquo;There must be an inheritance for the survivors of Benjamin, that a tribe may not be destroyed from Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21018, 'However, we cannot give them wives from our daughters, for the children of Israel have sworn an oath, saying, &lsquo;Cursed be the one who gives a wife to Benjamin.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21019, 'Then they said, &ldquo;In fact, there is a yearly feast of the Lord in Shiloh, which is north of Bethel, on the east side of the highway that goes up from Bethel to Shechem, and south of Lebonah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21020, 'Therefore they instructed the children of Benjamin, saying, &ldquo;Go, lie in wait in the vineyards, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21021, 'and watch; and just when the daughters of Shiloh come out to perform their dances, then come out from the vineyards, and every man catch a wife for himself from the daughters of Shiloh; then go to the land of Benjamin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21022, 'Then it shall be, when their fathers or their brothers come to us to complain, that we will say to them, &lsquo;Be kind to them for our sakes, because we did not take a wife for any of them in the war; for it is not as though you have given the women to them at this time, making yourselves guilty of your oath.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21023, 'And the children of Benjamin did so; they took enough wives for their number from those who danced, whom they caught. Then they went and returned to their inheritance, and they rebuilt the cities and dwelt in them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21024, 'So the children of Israel departed from there at that time, every man to his tribe and family; they went out from there, every man to his inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Judg', 21025, 'In those days there was no king in Israel; everyone did what was right in his own eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1001, 'Now it came to pass, in the days when the judges ruled, that there was a famine in the land. And a certain man of Bethlehem, Judah, went to dwell in the country of Moab, he and his wife and his two sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1002, 'The name of the man was Elimelech, the name of his wife was Naomi, and the names of his two sons were Mahlon and Chilion &ndash; Ephrathites of Bethlehem, Judah. And they went to the country of Moab and remained there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1003, 'Then Elimelech, Naomi&rsquo;s husband, died; and she was left, and her two sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1004, 'Now they took wives of the women of Moab: the name of the one was Orpah, and the name of the other Ruth. And they dwelt there about ten years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1005, 'Then both Mahlon and Chilion also died; so the woman survived her two sons and her husband. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1006, 'Then she arose with her daughters-in-law that she might return from the country of Moab, for she had heard in the country of Moab that the Lord had visited His people by giving them bread. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1007, 'Therefore she went out from the place where she was, and her two daughters-in-law with her; and they went on the way to return to the land of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1008, 'And Naomi said to her two daughters-in-law, &ldquo;Go, return each to her mother&rsquo;s house. The Lord deal kindly with you, as you have dealt with the dead and with me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1009, 'The Lord grant that you may find rest, each in the house of her husband.&rdquo; Then she kissed them, and they lifted up their voices and wept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1010, 'And they said to her, &ldquo;Surely we will return with you to your people.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1011, 'But Naomi said, &ldquo;Turn back, my daughters; why will you go with me? Are there still sons in my womb, that they may be your husbands? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1012, 'Turn back, my daughters, go &ndash; for I am too old to have a husband. If I should say I have hope, if I should have a husband tonight and should also bear sons, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1013, 'would you wait for them till they were grown? Would you restrain yourselves from having husbands? No, my daughters; for it grieves me very much for your sakes that the hand of the Lord has gone out against me!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1014, 'Then they lifted up their voices and wept again; and Orpah kissed her mother-in-law, but Ruth clung to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1015, 'And she said, &ldquo;Look, your sister-in-law has gone back to her people and to her gods; return after your sister-in-law.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1016, 'But Ruth said: &ldquo;Entreat me not to leave you, Or to turn back from following after you; For wherever you go, I will go; And wherever you lodge, I will lodge; Your people shall be my people, And your God, my God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1017, 'Where you die, I will die, And there will I be buried. The Lord do so to me, and more also, If anything but death parts you and me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1018, 'When she saw that she was determined to go with her, she stopped speaking to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1019, 'Now the two of them went until they came to Bethlehem. And it happened, when they had come to Bethlehem, that all the city was excited because of them; and the women said, &ldquo;Is this Naomi?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1020, 'But she said to them, &ldquo;Do not call me Naomi; call me Mara, for the Almighty has dealt very bitterly with me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1021, 'I went out full, and the Lord has brought me home again empty. Why do you call me Naomi, since the Lord has testified against me, and the Almighty has afflicted me?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 1022, 'So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabitess her daughter-in-law with her, who returned from the country of Moab. Now they came to Bethlehem at the beginning of barley harvest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2001, 'There was a relative of Naomi&rsquo;s husband, a man of great wealth, of the family of Elimelech. His name was Boaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2002, 'So Ruth the Moabitess said to Naomi, &ldquo;Please let me go to the field, and glean heads of grain after him in whose sight I may find favor.&rdquo; And she said to her, &ldquo;Go, my daughter.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2003, 'Then she left, and went and gleaned in the field after the reapers. And she happened to come to the part of the field belonging to Boaz, who was of the family of Elimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2004, 'Now behold, Boaz came from Bethlehem, and said to the reapers, &ldquo;The Lord be with you!&rdquo; And they answered him, &ldquo;The Lord bless you!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2005, 'Then Boaz said to his servant who was in charge of the reapers, &ldquo;Whose young woman is this?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2006, 'So the servant who was in charge of the reapers answered and said, &ldquo;It is the young Moabite woman who came back with Naomi from the country of Moab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2007, 'And she said, &lsquo;Please let me glean and gather after the reapers among the sheaves.&rsquo; So she came and has continued from morning until now, though she rested a little in the house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2008, 'Then Boaz said to Ruth, &ldquo;You will listen, my daughter, will you not? Do not go to glean in another field, nor go from here, but stay close by my young women. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2009, 'Let your eyes be on the field which they reap, and go after them. Have I not commanded the young men not to touch you? And when you are thirsty, go to the vessels and drink from what the young men have drawn.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2010, 'So she fell on her face, bowed down to the ground, and said to him, &ldquo;Why have I found favor in your eyes, that you should take notice of me, since I am a foreigner?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2011, 'And Boaz answered and said to her, &ldquo;It has been fully reported to me, all that you have done for your mother-in-law since the death of your husband, and how you have left your father and your mother and the land of your birth, and have come to a people whom you did not know before. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2012, 'The Lord repay your work, and a full reward be given you by the Lord God of Israel, under whose wings you have come for refuge.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2013, 'Then she said, &ldquo;Let me find favor in your sight, my lord; for you have comforted me, and have spoken kindly to your maidservant, though I am not like one of your maidservants.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2014, 'Now Boaz said to her at mealtime, &ldquo;Come here, and eat of the bread, and dip your piece of bread in the vinegar.&rdquo; So she sat beside the reapers, and he passed parched grain to her; and she ate and was satisfied, and kept some back. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2015, 'And when she rose up to glean, Boaz commanded his young men, saying, &ldquo;Let her glean even among the sheaves, and do not reproach her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2016, 'Also let grain from the bundles fall purposely for her; leave it that she may glean, and do not rebuke her.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2017, 'So she gleaned in the field until evening, and beat out what she had gleaned, and it was about an ephah of barley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2018, 'Then she took it up and went into the city, and her mother-in-law saw what she had gleaned. So she brought out and gave to her what she had kept back after she had been satisfied. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2019, 'And her mother-in-law said to her, &ldquo;Where have you gleaned today? And where did you work? Blessed be the one who took notice of you.&rdquo; So she told her mother-in-law with whom she had worked, and said, &ldquo;The man&rsquo;s name with whom I worked today is Boaz.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2020, 'Then Naomi said to her daughter-in-law, &ldquo;Blessed be he of the Lord, who has not forsaken His kindness to the living and the dead!&rdquo; And Naomi said to her, &ldquo;This man is a relation of ours, one of our close relatives.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2021, 'Ruth the Moabitess said, &ldquo;He also said to me, &lsquo;You shall stay close by my young men until they have finished all my harvest.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2022, 'And Naomi said to Ruth her daughter-in-law, &ldquo;It is good, my daughter, that you go out with his young women, and that people do not meet you in any other field.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 2023, 'So she stayed close by the young women of Boaz, to glean until the end of barley harvest and wheat harvest; and she dwelt with her mother-in-law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3001, 'Then Naomi her mother-in-law said to her, &ldquo;My daughter, shall I not seek security for you, that it may be well with you? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3002, 'Now Boaz, whose young women you were with, is he not our relative? In fact, he is winnowing barley tonight at the threshing floor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3003, 'Therefore wash yourself and anoint yourself, put on your best garment and go down to the threshing floor; but do not make yourself known to the man until he has finished eating and drinking. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3004, 'Then it shall be, when he lies down, that you shall notice the place where he lies; and you shall go in, uncover his feet, and lie down; and he will tell you what you should do.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3005, 'And she said to her, &ldquo;All that you say to me I will do.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3006, 'So she went down to the threshing floor and did according to all that her mother-in-law instructed her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3007, 'And after Boaz had eaten and drunk, and his heart was cheerful, he went to lie down at the end of the heap of grain; and she came softly, uncovered his feet, and lay down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3008, 'Now it happened at midnight that the man was startled, and turned himself; and there, a woman was lying at his feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3009, 'And he said, &ldquo;Who are you?&rdquo; So she answered, &ldquo;I am Ruth, your maidservant. Take your maidservant under your wing, for you are a close relative.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3010, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Blessed are you of the Lord, my daughter! For you have shown more kindness at the end than at the beginning, in that you did not go after young men, whether poor or rich. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3011, 'And now, my daughter, do not fear. I will do for you all that you request, for all the people of my town know that you are a virtuous woman. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3012, 'Now it is true that I am a close relative; however, there is a relative closer than I. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3013, 'Stay this night, and in the morning it shall be that if he will perform the duty of a close relative for you &ndash; good; let him do it. But if he does not want to perform the duty for you, then I will perform the duty for you, as the Lord lives! Lie down until morning.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3014, 'So she lay at his feet until morning, and she arose before one could recognize another. Then he said, &ldquo;Do not let it be known that the woman came to the threshing floor.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3015, 'Also he said, &ldquo;Bring the shawl that is on you and hold it.&rdquo; And when she held it, he measured six ephahs of barley, and laid it on her. Then she went into the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3016, 'So when she came to her mother-in-law, she said, &ldquo;Is that you, my daughter?&rdquo; Then she told her all that the man had done for her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3017, 'And she said, &ldquo;These six ephahs of barley he gave me; for he said to me, &lsquo;Do not go empty-handed to your mother-in-law.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 3018, 'Then she said, &ldquo;Sit still, my daughter, until you know how the matter will turn out; for the man will not rest until he has concluded the matter this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4001, 'Now Boaz went up to the gate and sat down there; and behold, the close relative of whom Boaz had spoken came by. So Boaz said, &ldquo;Come aside, friend,* sit down here.&rdquo; So he came aside and sat down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4002, 'And he took ten men of the elders of the city, and said, &ldquo;Sit down here.&rdquo; So they sat down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4003, 'Then he said to the close relative, &ldquo;Naomi, who has come back from the country of Moab, sold the piece of land which belonged to our brother Elimelech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4004, 'And I thought to inform you, saying, &lsquo;Buy it back in the presence of the inhabitants and the elders of my people. If you will redeem it, redeem it; but if you will not redeem it, then tell me, that I may know; for there is no one but you to redeem it, and I am next after you.&rsquo; &ldquo; And he said, &ldquo;I will redeem it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4005, 'Then Boaz said, &ldquo;On the day you buy the field from the hand of Naomi, you must also buy it from Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of the dead, to perpetuate the name of the dead through his inheritance.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4006, 'And the close relative said, &ldquo;I cannot redeem it for myself, lest I ruin my own inheritance. You redeem my right of redemption for yourself, for I cannot redeem it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4007, 'Now this was the custom in former times in Israel concerning redeeming and exchanging, to confirm anything: one man took off his sandal and gave it to the other, and this was a confirmation in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4008, 'Therefore the close relative said to Boaz, &ldquo;Buy it for yourself.&rdquo; So he took off his sandal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4009, 'And Boaz said to the elders and all the people, &ldquo;You are witnesses this day that I have bought all that was Elimelech&rsquo;s, and all that was Chilion&rsquo;s and Mahlon&rsquo;s, from the hand of Naomi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4010, 'Moreover, Ruth the Moabitess, the widow of Mahlon, I have acquired as my wife, to perpetuate the name of the dead through his inheritance, that the name of the dead may not be cut off from among his brethren and from his position at the gate. You are witnesses this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4011, 'And all the people who were at the gate, and the elders, said, &ldquo;We are witnesses. The Lord make the woman who is coming to your house like Rachel and Leah, the two who built the house of Israel; and may you prosper in Ephrathah and be famous in Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4012, 'May your house be like the house of Perez, whom Tamar bore to Judah, because of the offspring which the Lord will give you from this young woman.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4013, 'So Boaz took Ruth and she became his wife; and when he went in to her, the Lord gave her conception, and she bore a son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4014, 'Then the women said to Naomi, &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord, who has not left you this day without a close relative; and may his name be famous in Israel! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4015, 'And may he be to you a restorer of life and a nourisher of your old age; for your daughter-in-law, who loves you, who is better to you than seven sons, has borne him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4016, 'Then Naomi took the child and laid him on her bosom, and became a nurse to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4017, 'Also the neighbor women gave him a name, saying, &ldquo;There is a son born to Naomi.&rdquo; And they called his name Obed. He is the father of Jesse, the father of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4018, 'Now this is the genealogy of Perez: Perez begot Hezron; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4019, 'Hezron begot Ram, and Ram begot Amminadab; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4020, 'Amminadab begot Nahshon, and Nahshon begot Salmon; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4021, 'Salmon begot Boaz, and Boaz begot Obed; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ruth', 4022, 'Obed begot Jesse, and Jesse begot David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1001, 'Now there was a certain man of Ramathaim Zophim, of the mountains of Ephraim, and his name was Elkanah the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1002, 'And he had two wives: the name of one was Hannah, and the name of the other Peninnah. Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1003, 'This man went up from his city yearly to worship and sacrifice to the Lord of hosts in Shiloh. Also the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, the priests of the Lord, were there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1004, 'And whenever the time came for Elkanah to make an offering, he would give portions to Peninnah his wife and to all her sons and daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1005, 'But to Hannah he would give a double portion, for he loved Hannah, although the Lord had closed her womb. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1006, 'And her rival also provoked her severely, to make her miserable, because the Lord had closed her womb. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1007, 'So it was, year by year, when she went up to the house of the Lord, that she provoked her; therefore she wept and did not eat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1008, 'Then Elkanah her husband said to her, &ldquo;Hannah, why do you weep? Why do you not eat? And why is your heart grieved? Am I not better to you than ten sons?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1009, 'So Hannah arose after they had finished eating and drinking in Shiloh. Now Eli the priest was sitting on the seat by the doorpost of the tabernacle of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1010, 'And she was in bitterness of soul, and prayed to the Lord and wept in anguish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1011, 'Then she made a vow and said, &ldquo;O Lord of hosts, if You will indeed look on the affliction of Your maidservant and remember me, and not forget Your maidservant, but will give Your maidservant a male child, then I will give him to the Lord all the days of his life, and no razor shall come upon his head.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1012, 'And it happened, as she continued praying before the Lord, that Eli watched her mouth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1013, 'Now Hannah spoke in her heart; only her lips moved, but her voice was not heard. Therefore Eli thought she was drunk. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1014, 'So Eli said to her, &ldquo;How long will you be drunk? Put your wine away from you!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1015, 'And Hannah answered and said, &ldquo;No, my lord, I am a woman of sorrowful spirit. I have drunk neither wine nor intoxicating drink, but have poured out my soul before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1016, 'Do not consider your maidservant a wicked woman, for out of the abundance of my complaint and grief I have spoken until now.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1017, 'Then Eli answered and said, &ldquo;Go in peace, and the God of Israel grant your petition which you have asked of Him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1018, 'And she said, &ldquo;Let your maidservant find favor in your sight.&rdquo; So the woman went her way and ate, and her face was no longer sad. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1019, 'Then they rose early in the morning and worshiped before the Lord, and returned and came to their house at Ramah. And Elkanah knew Hannah his wife, and the Lord remembered her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1020, 'So it came to pass in the process of time that Hannah conceived and bore a son, and called his name Samuel, saying, &ldquo;Because I have asked for him from the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1021, 'Now the man Elkanah and all his house went up to offer to the Lord the yearly sacrifice and his vow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1022, 'But Hannah did not go up, for she said to her husband, &ldquo;Not until the child is weaned; then I will take him, that he may appear before the Lord and remain there forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1023, 'And Elkanah her husband said to her, &ldquo;Do what seems best to you; wait until you have weaned him. Only let the Lord establish His word.&rdquo; So the woman stayed and nursed her son until she had weaned him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1024, 'Now when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three bulls, one ephah of flour, and a skin of wine, and brought him to the house of the Lord in Shiloh. And the child was young. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1025, 'Then they slaughtered a bull, and brought the child to Eli. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1026, 'And she said, &ldquo;O my lord! As your soul lives, my lord, I am the woman who stood by you here, praying to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1027, 'For this child I prayed, and the Lord has granted me my petition which I asked of Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 1028, 'Therefore I also have lent him to the Lord; as long as he lives he shall be lent to the Lord.&rdquo; So they worshiped the Lord there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2001, 'And Hannah prayed and said: &ldquo;My heart rejoices in the Lord; My horn* is exalted in the Lord. I smile at my enemies, Because I rejoice in Your salvation. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2002, 'No one is holy like the Lord, For there is none besides You, Nor is there any rock like our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2003, 'Talk no more so very proudly; Let no arrogance come from your mouth, For the Lord is the God of knowledge; And by Him actions are weighed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2004, 'The bows of the mighty men are broken, And those who stumbled are girded with strength. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2005, 'Those who were full have hired themselves out for bread, And the hungry have ceased to hunger. Even the barren has borne seven, And she who has many children has become feeble. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2006, 'The Lord kills and makes alive; He brings down to the grave and brings up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2007, 'The Lord makes poor and makes rich; He brings low and lifts up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2008, 'He raises the poor from the dust And lifts the beggar from the ash heap, To set them among princes And make them inherit the throne of glory. &ldquo;For the pillars of the earth are the Lord&rsquo;s, And He has set the world upon them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2009, 'He will guard the feet of His saints, But the wicked shall be silent in darkness. &ldquo;For by strength no man shall prevail. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2010, 'The adversaries of the Lord shall be broken in pieces; From heaven He will thunder against them. The Lord will judge the ends of the earth. &ldquo;He will give strength to His king, And exalt the horn of His anointed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2011, 'Then Elkanah went to his house at Ramah. But the child ministered to the Lord before Eli the priest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2012, 'Now the sons of Eli were corrupt; they did not know the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2013, 'And the priests&rsquo; custom with the people was that when any man offered a sacrifice, the priest&rsquo;s servant would come with a three-pronged fleshhook in his hand while the meat was boiling. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2014, 'Then he would thrust it into the pan, or kettle, or caldron, or pot; and the priest would take for himself all that the fleshhook brought up. So they did in Shiloh to all the Israelites who came there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2015, 'Also, before they burned the fat, the priest&rsquo;s servant would come and say to the man who sacrificed, &ldquo;Give meat for roasting to the priest, for he will not take boiled meat from you, but raw.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2016, 'And if the man said to him, &ldquo;They should really burn the fat first; then you may take as much as your heart desires,&rdquo; he would then answer him, &ldquo;No, but you must give it now; and if not, I will take it by force.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2017, 'Therefore the sin of the young men was very great before the Lord, for men abhorred the offering of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2018, 'But Samuel ministered before the Lord, even as a child, wearing a linen ephod. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2019, 'Moreover his mother used to make him a little robe, and bring it to him year by year when she came up with her husband to offer the yearly sacrifice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2020, 'And Eli would bless Elkanah and his wife, and say, &ldquo;The Lord give you descendants from this woman for the loan that was given to the Lord.&rdquo; Then they would go to their own home. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2021, 'And the Lord visited Hannah, so that she conceived and bore three sons and two daughters. Meanwhile the child Samuel grew before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2022, 'Now Eli was very old; and he heard everything his sons did to all Israel, and how they lay with the women who assembled at the door of the tabernacle of meeting. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2023, 'So he said to them, &ldquo;Why do you do such things? For I hear of your evil dealings from all the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2024, 'No, my sons! For it is not a good report that I hear. You make the Lord&rsquo;s people transgress. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2025, 'If one man sins against another, God will judge him. But if a man sins against the Lord, who will intercede for him?&rdquo; Nevertheless they did not heed the voice of their father, because the Lord desired to kill them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2026, 'And the child Samuel grew in stature, and in favor both with the Lord and men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2027, 'Then a man of God came to Eli and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Did I not clearly reveal Myself to the house of your father when they were in Egypt in Pharaoh&rsquo;s house? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2028, 'Did I not choose him out of all the tribes of Israel to be My priest, to offer upon My altar, to burn incense, and to wear an ephod before Me? And did I not give to the house of your father all the offerings of the children of Israel made by fire? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2029, 'Why do you kick at My sacrifice and My offering which I have commanded in My dwelling place, and honor your sons more than Me, to make yourselves fat with the best of all the offerings of Israel My people?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2030, 'Therefore the Lord God of Israel says: &lsquo;I said indeed that your house and the house of your father would walk before Me forever.&rsquo; But now the Lord says: &lsquo;Far be it from Me; for those who honor Me I will honor, and those who despise Me shall be lightly esteemed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2031, 'Behold, the days are coming that I will cut off your arm and the arm of your father&rsquo;s house, so that there will not be an old man in your house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2032, 'And you will see an enemy in My dwelling place, despite all the good which God does for Israel. And there shall not be an old man in your house forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2033, 'But any of your men whom I do not cut off from My altar shall consume your eyes and grieve your heart. And all the descendants of your house shall die in the flower of their age. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2034, 'Now this shall be a sign to you that will come upon your two sons, on Hophni and Phinehas: in one day they shall die, both of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2035, 'Then I will raise up for Myself a faithful priest who shall do according to what is in My heart and in My mind. I will build him a sure house, and he shall walk before My anointed forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 2036, 'And it shall come to pass that everyone who is left in your house will come and bow down to him for a piece of silver and a morsel of bread, and say, &ldquo;Please, put me in one of the priestly positions, that I may eat a piece of bread.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3001, 'Then the boy Samuel ministered to the Lord before Eli. And the word of the Lord was rare in those days; there was no widespread revelation. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3002, 'And it came to pass at that time, while Eli was lying down in his place, and when his eyes had begun to grow so dim that he could not see, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3003, 'and before the lamp of God went out in the tabernacle of the Lord where the ark of God was, and while Samuel was lying down, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3004, 'that the Lord called Samuel. And he answered, &ldquo;Here I am!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3005, 'So he ran to Eli and said, &ldquo;Here I am, for you called me.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;I did not call; lie down again.&rdquo; And he went and lay down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3006, 'Then the Lord called yet again, &ldquo;Samuel!&rdquo; So Samuel arose and went to Eli, and said, &ldquo;Here I am, for you called me.&rdquo; He answered, &ldquo;I did not call, my son; lie down again.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3007, '(Now Samuel did not yet know the Lord, nor was the word of the Lord yet revealed to him.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3008, 'And the Lord called Samuel again the third time. Then he arose and went to Eli, and said, &ldquo;Here I am, for you did call me.&rdquo; Then Eli perceived that the Lord had called the boy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3009, 'Therefore Eli said to Samuel, &ldquo;Go, lie down; and it shall be, if He calls you, that you must say, &lsquo;Speak, Lord, for Your servant hears.&rsquo; &ldquo; So Samuel went and lay down in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3010, 'Now the Lord came and stood and called as at other times, &ldquo;Samuel! Samuel!&rdquo; And Samuel answered, &ldquo;Speak, for Your servant hears.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3011, 'Then the Lord said to Samuel: &ldquo;Behold, I will do something in Israel at which both ears of everyone who hears it will tingle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3012, 'In that day I will perform against Eli all that I have spoken concerning his house, from beginning to end. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3013, 'For I have told him that I will judge his house forever for the iniquity which he knows, because his sons made themselves vile, and he did not restrain them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3014, 'And therefore I have sworn to the house of Eli that the iniquity of Eli&rsquo;s house shall not be atoned for by sacrifice or offering forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3015, 'So Samuel lay down until morning, and opened the doors of the house of the Lord. And Samuel was afraid to tell Eli the vision. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3016, 'Then Eli called Samuel and said, &ldquo;Samuel, my son!&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;Here I am.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3017, 'And he said, &ldquo;What is the word that the Lord spoke to you? Please do not hide it from me. God do so to you, and more also, if you hide anything from me of all the things that He said to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3018, 'Then Samuel told him everything, and hid nothing from him. And he said, &ldquo;It is the Lord. Let Him do what seems good to Him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3019, 'So Samuel grew, and the Lord was with him and let none of his words fall to the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3020, 'And all Israel from Dan to Beersheba knew that Samuel had been established as a prophet of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 3021, 'Then the Lord appeared again in Shiloh. For the Lord revealed Himself to Samuel in Shiloh by the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4001, 'And the word of Samuel came to all Israel.*Now Israel went out to battle against the Philistines, and encamped beside Ebenezer; and the Philistines encamped in Aphek. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4002, 'Then the Philistines put themselves in battle array against Israel. And when they joined battle, Israel was defeated by the Philistines, who killed about four thousand men of the army in the field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4003, 'And when the people had come into the camp, the elders of Israel said, &ldquo;Why has the Lord defeated us today before the Philistines? Let us bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord from Shiloh to us, that when it comes among us it may save us from the hand of our enemies.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4004, 'So the people sent to Shiloh, that they might bring from there the ark of the covenant of the Lord of hosts, who dwells between the cherubim. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, were there with the ark of the covenant of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4005, 'And when the ark of the covenant of the Lord came into the camp, all Israel shouted so loudly that the earth shook. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4006, 'Now when the Philistines heard the noise of the shout, they said, &ldquo;What does the sound of this great shout in the camp of the Hebrews mean?&rdquo; Then they understood that the ark of the Lord had come into the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4007, 'So the Philistines were afraid, for they said, &ldquo;God has come into the camp!&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;Woe to us! For such a thing has never happened before. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4008, 'Woe to us! Who will deliver us from the hand of these mighty gods? These are the gods who struck the Egyptians with all the plagues in the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4009, 'Be strong and conduct yourselves like men, you Philistines, that you do not become servants of the Hebrews, as they have been to you. Conduct yourselves like men, and fight!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4010, 'So the Philistines fought, and Israel was defeated, and every man fled to his tent. There was a very great slaughter, and there fell of Israel thirty thousand foot soldiers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4011, 'Also the ark of God was captured; and the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4012, 'Then a man of Benjamin ran from the battle line the same day, and came to Shiloh with his clothes torn and dirt on his head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4013, 'Now when he came, there was Eli, sitting on a seat by the wayside watching, for his heart trembled for the ark of God. And when the man came into the city and told it, all the city cried out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4014, 'When Eli heard the noise of the outcry, he said, &ldquo;What does the sound of this tumult mean?&rdquo; And the man came quickly and told Eli. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4015, 'Eli was ninety-eight years old, and his eyes were so dim that he could not see. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4016, 'Then the man said to Eli, &ldquo;I am he who came from the battle. And I fled today from the battle line.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;What happened, my son?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4017, 'So the messenger answered and said, &ldquo;Israel has fled before the Philistines, and there has been a great slaughter among the people. Also your two sons, Hophni and Phinehas, are dead; and the ark of God has been captured.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4018, 'Then it happened, when he made mention of the ark of God, that Eli fell off the seat backward by the side of the gate; and his neck was broken and he died, for the man was old and heavy. And he had judged Israel forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4019, 'Now his daughter-in-law, Phinehas&rsquo; wife, was with child, due to be delivered; and when she heard the news that the ark of God was captured, and that her father-in-law and her husband were dead, she bowed herself and gave birth, for her labor pains came upon her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4020, 'And about the time of her death the women who stood by her said to her, &ldquo;Do not fear, for you have borne a son.&rdquo; But she did not answer, nor did she regard it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4021, 'Then she named the child Ichabod, saying, &ldquo;The glory has departed from Israel!&rdquo; because the ark of God had been captured and because of her father-in-law and her husband. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 4022, 'And she said, &ldquo;The glory has departed from Israel, for the ark of God has been captured.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5001, 'Then the Philistines took the ark of God and brought it from Ebenezer to Ashdod. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5002, 'When the Philistines took the ark of God, they brought it into the temple of Dagon and set it by Dagon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5003, 'And when the people of Ashdod arose early in the morning, there was Dagon, fallen on its face to the earth before the ark of the Lord. So they took Dagon and set it in its place again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5004, 'And when they arose early the next morning, there was Dagon, fallen on its face to the ground before the ark of the Lord. The head of Dagon and both the palms of its hands were broken off on the threshold; only Dagon&rsquo;s torso was left of it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5005, 'Therefore neither the priests of Dagon nor any who come into Dagon&rsquo;s house tread on the threshold of Dagon in Ashdod to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5006, 'But the hand of the Lord was heavy on the people of Ashdod, and He ravaged them and struck them with tumors, both Ashdod and its territory. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5007, 'And when the men of Ashdod saw how it was, they said, &ldquo;The ark of the God of Israel must not remain with us, for His hand is harsh toward us and Dagon our god.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5008, 'Therefore they sent and gathered to themselves all the lords of the Philistines, and said, &ldquo;What shall we do with the ark of the God of Israel?&rdquo; And they answered, &ldquo;Let the ark of the God of Israel be carried away to Gath.&rdquo; So they carried the ark of the God of Israel away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5009, 'So it was, after they had carried it away, that the hand of the Lord was against the city with a very great destruction; and He struck the men of the city, both small and great, and tumors broke out on them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5010, 'Therefore they sent the ark of God to Ekron. So it was, as the ark of God came to Ekron, that the Ekronites cried out, saying, &ldquo;They have brought the ark of the God of Israel to us, to kill us and our people!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5011, 'So they sent and gathered together all the lords of the Philistines, and said, &ldquo;Send away the ark of the God of Israel, and let it go back to its own place, so that it does not kill us and our people.&rdquo; For there was a deadly destruction throughout all the city; the hand of God was very heavy there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 5012, 'And the men who did not die were stricken with the tumors, and the cry of the city went up to heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6001, 'Now the ark of the Lord was in the country of the Philistines seven months. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6002, 'And the Philistines called for the priests and the diviners, saying, &ldquo;What shall we do with the ark of the Lord? Tell us how we should send it to its place.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6003, 'So they said, &ldquo;If you send away the ark of the God of Israel, do not send it empty; but by all means return it to Him with a trespass offering. Then you will be healed, and it will be known to you why His hand is not removed from you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6004, 'Then they said, &ldquo;What is the trespass offering which we shall return to Him?&rdquo; They answered, &ldquo;Five golden tumors and five golden rats, according to the number of the lords of the Philistines. For the same plague was on all of you and on your lords. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6005, 'Therefore you shall make images of your tumors and images of your rats that ravage the land, and you shall give glory to the God of Israel; perhaps He will lighten His hand from you, from your gods, and from your land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6006, 'Why then do you harden your hearts as the Egyptians and Pharaoh hardened their hearts? When He did mighty things among them, did they not let the people go, that they might depart? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6007, 'Now therefore, make a new cart, take two milk cows which have never been yoked, and hitch the cows to the cart; and take their calves home, away from them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6008, 'Then take the ark of the Lord and set it on the cart; and put the articles of gold which you are returning to Him as a trespass offering in a chest by its side. Then send it away, and let it go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6009, 'And watch: if it goes up the road to its own territory, to Beth Shemesh, then He has done us this great evil. But if not, then we shall know that it is not His hand that struck us &ndash; it happened to us by chance.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6010, 'Then the men did so; they took two milk cows and hitched them to the cart, and shut up their calves at home. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6011, 'And they set the ark of the Lord on the cart, and the chest with the gold rats and the images of their tumors. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6012, 'Then the cows headed straight for the road to Beth Shemesh, and went along the highway, lowing as they went, and did not turn aside to the right hand or the left. And the lords of the Philistines went after them to the border of Beth Shemesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6013, 'Now the people of Beth Shemesh were reaping their wheat harvest in the valley; and they lifted their eyes and saw the ark, and rejoiced to see it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6014, 'Then the cart came into the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh, and stood there; a large stone was there. So they split the wood of the cart and offered the cows as a burnt offering to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6015, 'The Levites took down the ark of the Lord and the chest that was with it, in which were the articles of gold, and put them on the large stone. Then the men of Beth Shemesh offered burnt offerings and made sacrifices the same day to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6016, 'So when the five lords of the Philistines had seen it, they returned to Ekron the same day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6017, 'These are the golden tumors which the Philistines returned as a trespass offering to the Lord: one for Ashdod, one for Gaza, one for Ashkelon, one for Gath, one for Ekron; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6018, 'and the golden rats, according to the number of all the cities of the Philistines belonging to the five lords, both fortified cities and country villages, even as far as the large stone of Abel on which they set the ark of the Lord, which stone remains to this day in the field of Joshua of Beth Shemesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6019, 'Then He struck the men of Beth Shemesh, because they had looked into the ark of the Lord. He struck fifty thousand and seventy men of the people, and the people lamented because the Lord had struck the people with a great slaughter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6020, 'And the men of Beth Shemesh said, &ldquo;Who is able to stand before this holy Lord God? And to whom shall it go up from us?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 6021, 'So they sent messengers to the inhabitants of Kirjath Jearim, saying, &ldquo;The Philistines have brought back the ark of the Lord; come down and take it up with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7001, 'Then the men of Kirjath Jearim came and took the ark of the Lord, and brought it into the house of Abinadab on the hill, and consecrated Eleazar his son to keep the ark of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7002, 'So it was that the ark remained in Kirjath Jearim a long time; it was there twenty years. And all the house of Israel lamented after the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7003, 'Then Samuel spoke to all the house of Israel, saying, &ldquo;If you return to the Lord with all your hearts, then put away the foreign gods and the Ashtoreths from among you, and prepare your hearts for the Lord, and serve Him only; and He will deliver you from the hand of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7004, 'So the children of Israel put away the Baals and the Ashtoreths, and served the Lord only. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7005, 'And Samuel said, &ldquo;Gather all Israel to Mizpah, and I will pray to the Lord for you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7006, 'So they gathered together at Mizpah, drew water, and poured it out before the Lord. And they fasted that day, and said there, &ldquo;We have sinned against the Lord.&rdquo; And Samuel judged the children of Israel at Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7007, 'Now when the Philistines heard that the children of Israel had gathered together at Mizpah, the lords of the Philistines went up against Israel. And when the children of Israel heard of it, they were afraid of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7008, 'So the children of Israel said to Samuel, &ldquo;Do not cease to cry out to the Lord our God for us, that He may save us from the hand of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7009, 'And Samuel took a suckling lamb and offered it as a whole burnt offering to the Lord. Then Samuel cried out to the Lord for Israel, and the Lord answered him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7010, 'Now as Samuel was offering up the burnt offering, the Philistines drew near to battle against Israel. But the Lord thundered with a loud thunder upon the Philistines that day, and so confused them that they were overcome before Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7011, 'And the men of Israel went out of Mizpah and pursued the Philistines, and drove them back as far as below Beth Car. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7012, 'Then Samuel took a stone and set it up between Mizpah and Shen, and called its name Ebenezer, saying, &ldquo;Thus far the Lord has helped us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7013, 'So the Philistines were subdued, and they did not come anymore into the territory of Israel. And the hand of the Lord was against the Philistines all the days of Samuel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7014, 'Then the cities which the Philistines had taken from Israel were restored to Israel, from Ekron to Gath; and Israel recovered its territory from the hands of the Philistines. Also there was peace between Israel and the Amorites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7015, 'And Samuel judged Israel all the days of his life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7016, 'He went from year to year on a circuit to Bethel, Gilgal, and Mizpah, and judged Israel in all those places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 7017, 'But he always returned to Ramah, for his home was there. There he judged Israel, and there he built an altar to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8001, 'Now it came to pass when Samuel was old that he made his sons judges over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8002, 'The name of his firstborn was Joel, and the name of his second, Abijah; they were judges in Beersheba. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8003, 'But his sons did not walk in his ways; they turned aside after dishonest gain, took bribes, and perverted justice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8004, 'Then all the elders of Israel gathered together and came to Samuel at Ramah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8005, 'and said to him, &ldquo;Look, you are old, and your sons do not walk in your ways. Now make us a king to judge us like all the nations.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8006, 'But the thing displeased Samuel when they said, &ldquo;Give us a king to judge us.&rdquo; So Samuel prayed to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8007, 'And the Lord said to Samuel, &ldquo;Heed the voice of the people in all that they say to you; for they have not rejected you, but they have rejected Me, that I should not reign over them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8008, 'According to all the works which they have done since the day that I brought them up out of Egypt, even to this day &ndash; with which they have forsaken Me and served other gods &ndash; so they are doing to you also. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8009, 'Now therefore, heed their voice. However, you shall solemnly forewarn them, and show them the behavior of the king who will reign over them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8010, 'So Samuel told all the words of the Lord to the people who asked him for a king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8011, 'And he said, &ldquo;This will be the behavior of the king who will reign over you: He will take your sons and appoint them for his own chariots and to be his horsemen, and some will run before his chariots. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8012, 'He will appoint captains over his thousands and captains over his fifties, will set some to plow his ground and reap his harvest, and some to make his weapons of war and equipment for his chariots. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8013, 'He will take your daughters to be perfumers, cooks, and bakers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8014, 'And he will take the best of your fields, your vineyards, and your olive groves, and give them to his servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8015, 'He will take a tenth of your grain and your vintage, and give it to his officers and servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8016, 'And he will take your male servants, your female servants, your finest young men, and your donkeys, and put them to his work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8017, 'He will take a tenth of your sheep. And you will be his servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8018, 'And you will cry out in that day because of your king whom you have chosen for yourselves, and the Lord will not hear you in that day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8019, 'Nevertheless the people refused to obey the voice of Samuel; and they said, &ldquo;No, but we will have a king over us, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8020, 'that we also may be like all the nations, and that our king may judge us and go out before us and fight our battles.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8021, 'And Samuel heard all the words of the people, and he repeated them in the hearing of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 8022, 'So the Lord said to Samuel, &ldquo;Heed their voice, and make them a king.&rdquo; And Samuel said to the men of Israel, &ldquo;Every man go to his city.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9001, 'There was a man of Benjamin whose name was Kish the son of Abiel, the son of Zeror, the son of Bechorath, the son of Aphiah, a Benjamite, a mighty man of power. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9002, 'And he had a choice and handsome son whose name was Saul. There was not a more handsome person than he among the children of Israel. From his shoulders upward he was taller than any of the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9003, 'Now the donkeys of Kish, Saul&rsquo;s father, were lost. And Kish said to his son Saul, &ldquo;Please, take one of the servants with you, and arise, go and look for the donkeys.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9004, 'So he passed through the mountains of Ephraim and through the land of Shalisha, but they did not find them. Then they passed through the land of Shaalim, and they were not there. Then he passed through the land of the Benjamites, but they did not find them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9005, 'When they had come to the land of Zuph, Saul said to his servant who was with him, &ldquo;Come, let us return, lest my father cease caring about the donkeys and become worried about us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9006, 'And he said to him, &ldquo;Look now, there is in this city a man of God, and he is an honorable man; all that he says surely comes to pass. So let us go there; perhaps he can show us the way that we should go.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9007, 'Then Saul said to his servant, &ldquo;But look, if we go, what shall we bring the man? For the bread in our vessels is all gone, and there is no present to bring to the man of God. What do we have?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9008, 'And the servant answered Saul again and said, &ldquo;Look, I have here at hand one fourth of a shekel of silver. I will give that to the man of God, to tell us our way.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9009, '(Formerly in Israel, when a man went to inquire of God, he spoke thus: &ldquo;Come, let us go to the seer&rdquo;; for he who is now called a prophet was formerly called a seer.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9010, 'Then Saul said to his servant, &ldquo;Well said; come, let us go.&rdquo; So they went to the city where the man of God was. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9011, 'As they went up the hill to the city, they met some young women going out to draw water, and said to them, &ldquo;Is the seer here?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9012, 'And they answered them and said, &ldquo;Yes, there he is, just ahead of you. Hurry now; for today he came to this city, because there is a sacrifice of the people today on the high place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9013, 'As soon as you come into the city, you will surely find him before he goes up to the high place to eat. For the people will not eat until he comes, because he must bless the sacrifice; afterward those who are invited will eat. Now therefore, go up, for about this time you will find him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9014, 'So they went up to the city. As they were coming into the city, there was Samuel, coming out toward them on his way up to the high place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9015, 'Now the Lord had told Samuel in his ear the day before Saul came, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9016, 'Tomorrow about this time I will send you a man from the land of Benjamin, and you shall anoint him commander over My people Israel, that he may save My people from the hand of the Philistines; for I have looked upon My people, because their cry has come to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9017, 'And when Samuel saw Saul, the Lord said to him, &ldquo;There he is, the man of whom I spoke to you. This one shall reign over My people.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9018, 'Then Saul drew near to Samuel in the gate, and said, &ldquo;Please tell me, where is the seer&rsquo;s house?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9019, 'And Samuel answered Saul and said, &ldquo;I am the seer. Go up before me to the high place, for you shall eat with me today; and tomorrow I will let you go and will tell you all that is in your heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9020, 'But as for your donkeys that were lost three days ago, do not be anxious about them, for they have been found. And on whom is all the desire of Israel? Is it not on you and on all your father&rsquo;s house?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9021, 'And Saul answered and said, &ldquo;Am I not a Benjamite, of the smallest of the tribes of Israel, and my family the least of all the families of the tribe of Benjamin? Why then do you speak like this to me?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9022, 'Now Samuel took Saul and his servant and brought them into the hall, and had them sit in the place of honor among those who were invited; there were about thirty persons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9023, 'And Samuel said to the cook, &ldquo;Bring the portion which I gave you, of which I said to you, &lsquo;Set it apart.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9024, 'So the cook took up the thigh with its upper part and set it before Saul. And Samuel said, &ldquo;Here it is, what was kept back. It was set apart for you. Eat; for until this time it has been kept for you, since I said I invited the people.&rdquo; So Saul ate with Samuel that day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9025, 'When they had come down from the high place into the city, Samuel spoke with Saul on the top of the house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9026, 'They arose early; and it was about the dawning of the day that Samuel called to Saul on the top of the house, saying, &ldquo;Get up, that I may send you on your way.&rdquo; And Saul arose, and both of them went outside, he and Samuel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 9027, 'As they were going down to the outskirts of the city, Samuel said to Saul, &ldquo;Tell the servant to go on ahead of us.&rdquo; And he went on. &ldquo;But you stand here awhile, that I may announce to you the word of God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10001, 'Then Samuel took a flask of oil and poured it on his head, and kissed him and said: &ldquo;Is it not because the Lord has anointed you commander over His inheritance?* ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10002, 'When you have departed from me today, you will find two men by Rachel&rsquo;s tomb in the territory of Benjamin at Zelzah; and they will say to you, &lsquo;The donkeys which you went to look for have been found. And now your father has ceased caring about the donkeys and is worrying about you, saying, &ldquo;What shall I do about my son?&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10003, 'Then you shall go on forward from there and come to the terebinth tree of Tabor. There three men going up to God at Bethel will meet you, one carrying three young goats, another carrying three loaves of bread, and another carrying a skin of wine. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10004, 'And they will greet you and give you two loaves of bread, which you shall receive from their hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10005, 'After that you shall come to the hill of God where the Philistine garrison is. And it will happen, when you have come there to the city, that you will meet a group of prophets coming down from the high place with a stringed instrument, a tambourine, a flute, and a harp before them; and they will be prophesying. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10006, 'Then the Spirit of the Lord will come upon you, and you will prophesy with them and be turned into another man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10007, 'And let it be, when these signs come to you, that you do as the occasion demands; for God is with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10008, 'You shall go down before me to Gilgal; and surely I will come down to you to offer burnt offerings and make sacrifices of peace offerings. Seven days you shall wait, till I come to you and show you what you should do.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10009, 'So it was, when he had turned his back to go from Samuel, that God gave him another heart; and all those signs came to pass that day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10010, 'When they came there to the hill, there was a group of prophets to meet him; then the Spirit of God came upon him, and he prophesied among them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10011, 'And it happened, when all who knew him formerly saw that he indeed prophesied among the prophets, that the people said to one another, &ldquo;What is this that has come upon the son of Kish? Is Saul also among the prophets?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10012, 'Then a man from there answered and said, &ldquo;But who is their father?&rdquo; Therefore it became a proverb: &ldquo;Is Saul also among the prophets?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10013, 'And when he had finished prophesying, he went to the high place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10014, 'Then Saul&rsquo;s uncle said to him and his servant, &ldquo;Where did you go?&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;To look for the donkeys. When we saw that they were nowhere to be found, we went to Samuel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10015, 'And Saul&rsquo;s uncle said, &ldquo;Tell me, please, what Samuel said to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10016, 'So Saul said to his uncle, &ldquo;He told us plainly that the donkeys had been found.&rdquo; But about the matter of the kingdom, he did not tell him what Samuel had said. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10017, 'Then Samuel called the people together to the Lord at Mizpah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10018, 'and said to the children of Israel, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;I brought up Israel out of Egypt, and delivered you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of all kingdoms and from those who oppressed you.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10019, 'But you have today rejected your God, who Himself saved you from all your adversities and your tribulations; and you have said to Him, &lsquo;No, set a king over us!&rsquo; Now therefore, present yourselves before the Lord by your tribes and by your clans.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10020, 'And when Samuel had caused all the tribes of Israel to come near, the tribe of Benjamin was chosen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10021, 'When he had caused the tribe of Benjamin to come near by their families, the family of Matri was chosen. And Saul the son of Kish was chosen. But when they sought him, he could not be found. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10022, 'Therefore they inquired of the Lord further, &ldquo;Has the man come here yet?&rdquo; And the Lord answered, &ldquo;There he is, hidden among the equipment.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10023, 'So they ran and brought him from there; and when he stood among the people, he was taller than any of the people from his shoulders upward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10024, 'And Samuel said to all the people, &ldquo;Do you see him whom the Lord has chosen, that there is no one like him among all the people?&rdquo; So all the people shouted and said, &ldquo;Long live the king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10025, 'Then Samuel explained to the people the behavior of royalty, and wrote it in a book and laid it up before the Lord. And Samuel sent all the people away, every man to his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10026, 'And Saul also went home to Gibeah; and valiant men went with him, whose hearts God had touched. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 10027, 'But some rebels said, &ldquo;How can this man save us?&rdquo; So they despised him, and brought him no presents. But he held his peace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11001, 'Then Nahash the Ammonite came up and encamped against Jabesh Gilead; and all the men of Jabesh said to Nahash, &ldquo;Make a covenant with us, and we will serve you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11002, 'And Nahash the Ammonite answered them, &ldquo;On this condition I will make a covenant with you, that I may put out all your right eyes, and bring reproach on all Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11003, 'Then the elders of Jabesh said to him, &ldquo;Hold off for seven days, that we may send messengers to all the territory of Israel. And then, if there is no one to save us, we will come out to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11004, 'So the messengers came to Gibeah of Saul and told the news in the hearing of the people. And all the people lifted up their voices and wept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11005, 'Now there was Saul, coming behind the herd from the field; and Saul said, &ldquo;What troubles the people, that they weep?&rdquo; And they told him the words of the men of Jabesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11006, 'Then the Spirit of God came upon Saul when he heard this news, and his anger was greatly aroused. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11007, 'So he took a yoke of oxen and cut them in pieces, and sent them throughout all the territory of Israel by the hands of messengers, saying, &ldquo;Whoever does not go out with Saul and Samuel to battle, so it shall be done to his oxen.&rdquo; And the fear of the Lord fell on the people, and they came out with one consent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11008, 'When he numbered them in Bezek, the children of Israel were three hundred thousand, and the men of Judah thirty thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11009, 'And they said to the messengers who came, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to the men of Jabesh Gilead: &lsquo;Tomorrow, by the time the sun is hot, you shall have help.&rsquo; &ldquo; Then the messengers came and reported it to the men of Jabesh, and they were glad. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11010, 'Therefore the men of Jabesh said, &ldquo;Tomorrow we will come out to you, and you may do with us whatever seems good to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11011, 'So it was, on the next day, that Saul put the people in three companies; and they came into the midst of the camp in the morning watch, and killed Ammonites until the heat of the day. And it happened that those who survived were scattered, so that no two of them were left together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11012, 'Then the people said to Samuel, &ldquo;Who is he who said, &lsquo;Shall Saul reign over us?&rsquo; Bring the men, that we may put them to death.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11013, 'But Saul said, &ldquo;Not a man shall be put to death this day, for today the Lord has accomplished salvation in Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11014, 'Then Samuel said to the people, &ldquo;Come, let us go to Gilgal and renew the kingdom there.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 11015, 'So all the people went to Gilgal, and there they made Saul king before the Lord in Gilgal. There they made sacrifices of peace offerings before the Lord, and there Saul and all the men of Israel rejoiced greatly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12001, 'Now Samuel said to all Israel: &ldquo;Indeed I have heeded your voice in all that you said to me, and have made a king over you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12002, 'And now here is the king, walking before you; and I am old and grayheaded, and look, my sons are with you. I have walked before you from my childhood to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12003, 'Here I am. Witness against me before the Lord and before His anointed: Whose ox have I taken, or whose donkey have I taken, or whom have I cheated? Whom have I oppressed, or from whose hand have I received any bribe with which to blind my eyes? I will restore it to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12004, 'And they said, &ldquo;You have not cheated us or oppressed us, nor have you taken anything from any man&rsquo;s hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12005, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;The Lord is witness against you, and His anointed is witness this day, that you have not found anything in my hand.&rdquo; And they answered, &ldquo;He is witness.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12006, 'Then Samuel said to the people, &ldquo;It is the Lord who raised up Moses and Aaron, and who brought your fathers up from the land of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12007, 'Now therefore, stand still, that I may reason with you before the Lord concerning all the righteous acts of the Lord which He did to you and your fathers: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12008, 'When Jacob had gone into Egypt, and your fathers cried out to the Lord, then the Lord sent Moses and Aaron, who brought your fathers out of Egypt and made them dwell in this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12009, 'And when they forgot the Lord their God, He sold them into the hand of Sisera, commander of the army of Hazor, into the hand of the Philistines, and into the hand of the king of Moab; and they fought against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12010, 'Then they cried out to the Lord, and said, &lsquo;We have sinned, because we have forsaken the Lord and served the Baals and Ashtoreths; but now deliver us from the hand of our enemies, and we will serve You.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12011, 'And the Lord sent Jerubbaal, Bedan, Jephthah, and Samuel, and delivered you out of the hand of your enemies on every side; and you dwelt in safety. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12012, 'And when you saw that Nahash king of the Ammonites came against you, you said to me, &lsquo;No, but a king shall reign over us,&rsquo; when the Lord your God was your king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12013, 'Now therefore, here is the king whom you have chosen and whom you have desired. And take note, the Lord has set a king over you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12014, 'If you fear the Lord and serve Him and obey His voice, and do not rebel against the commandment of the Lord, then both you and the king who reigns over you will continue following the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12015, 'However, if you do not obey the voice of the Lord, but rebel against the commandment of the Lord, then the hand of the Lord will be against you, as it was against your fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12016, 'Now therefore, stand and see this great thing which the Lord will do before your eyes: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12017, 'Is today not the wheat harvest? I will call to the Lord, and He will send thunder and rain, that you may perceive and see that your wickedness is great, which you have done in the sight of the Lord, in asking a king for yourselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12018, 'So Samuel called to the Lord, and the Lord sent thunder and rain that day; and all the people greatly feared the Lord and Samuel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12019, 'And all the people said to Samuel, &ldquo;Pray for your servants to the Lord your God, that we may not die; for we have added to all our sins the evil of asking a king for ourselves.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12020, 'Then Samuel said to the people, &ldquo;Do not fear. You have done all this wickedness; yet do not turn aside from following the Lord, but serve the Lord with all your heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12021, 'And do not turn aside; for then you would go after empty things which cannot profit or deliver, for they are nothing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12022, 'For the Lord will not forsake His people, for His great name&rsquo;s sake, because it has pleased the Lord to make you His people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12023, 'Moreover, as for me, far be it from me that I should sin against the Lord in ceasing to pray for you; but I will teach you the good and the right way. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12024, 'Only fear the Lord, and serve Him in truth with all your heart; for consider what great things He has done for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 12025, 'But if you still do wickedly, you shall be swept away, both you and your king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13001, 'Saul reigned one year; and when he had reigned two years over Israel,* ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13002, 'Saul chose for himself three thousand men of Israel. Two thousand were with Saul in Michmash and in the mountains of Bethel, and a thousand were with Jonathan in Gibeah of Benjamin. The rest of the people he sent away, every man to his tent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13003, 'And Jonathan attacked the garrison of the Philistines that was in Geba, and the Philistines heard of it. Then Saul blew the trumpet throughout all the land, saying, &ldquo;Let the Hebrews hear!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13004, 'Now all Israel heard it said that Saul had attacked a garrison of the Philistines, and that Israel had also become an abomination to the Philistines. And the people were called together to Saul at Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13005, 'Then the Philistines gathered together to fight with Israel, thirty thousand chariots and six thousand horsemen, and people as the sand which is on the seashore in multitude. And they came up and encamped in Michmash, to the east of Beth Aven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13006, 'When the men of Israel saw that they were in danger (for the people were distressed), then the people hid in caves, in thickets, in rocks, in holes, and in pits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13007, 'And some of the Hebrews crossed over the Jordan to the land of Gad and Gilead. As for Saul, he was still in Gilgal, and all the people followed him trembling. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13008, 'Then he waited seven days, according to the time set by Samuel. But Samuel did not come to Gilgal; and the people were scattered from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13009, 'So Saul said, &ldquo;Bring a burnt offering and peace offerings here to me.&rdquo; And he offered the burnt offering. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13010, 'Now it happened, as soon as he had finished presenting the burnt offering, that Samuel came; and Saul went out to meet him, that he might greet him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13011, 'And Samuel said, &ldquo;What have you done?&rdquo; And Saul said, &ldquo;When I saw that the people were scattered from me, and that you did not come within the days appointed, and that the Philistines gathered together at Michmash, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13012, 'then I said, &lsquo;The Philistines will now come down on me at Gilgal, and I have not made supplication to the Lord.&rsquo; Therefore I felt compelled, and offered a burnt offering.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13013, 'And Samuel said to Saul, &ldquo;You have done foolishly. You have not kept the commandment of the Lord your God, which He commanded you. For now the Lord would have established your kingdom over Israel forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13014, 'But now your kingdom shall not continue. The Lord has sought for Himself a man after His own heart, and the Lord has commanded him to be commander over His people, because you have not kept what the Lord commanded you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13015, 'Then Samuel arose and went up from Gilgal to Gibeah of Benjamin. And Saul numbered the people present with him, about six hundred men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13016, 'Saul, Jonathan his son, and the people present with them remained in Gibeah of Benjamin. But the Philistines encamped in Michmash. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13017, 'Then raiders came out of the camp of the Philistines in three companies. One company turned to the road to Ophrah, to the land of Shual, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13018, 'another company turned to the road to Beth Horon, and another company turned to the road of the border that overlooks the Valley of Zeboim toward the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13019, 'Now there was no blacksmith to be found throughout all the land of Israel, for the Philistines said, &ldquo;Lest the Hebrews make swords or spears.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13020, 'But all the Israelites would go down to the Philistines to sharpen each man&rsquo;s plowshare, his mattock, his ax, and his sickle; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13021, 'and the charge for a sharpening was a pim for the plowshares, the mattocks, the forks, and the axes, and to set the points of the goads. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13022, 'So it came about, on the day of battle, that there was neither sword nor spear found in the hand of any of the people who were with Saul and Jonathan. But they were found with Saul and Jonathan his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 13023, 'And the garrison of the Philistines went out to the pass of Michmash. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14001, 'Now it happened one day that Jonathan the son of Saul said to the young man who bore his armor, &ldquo;Come, let us go over to the Philistines&rsquo; garrison that is on the other side.&rdquo; But he did not tell his father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14002, 'And Saul was sitting in the outskirts of Gibeah under a pomegranate tree which is in Migron. The people who were with him were about six hundred men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14003, 'Ahijah the son of Ahitub, Ichabod&rsquo;s brother, the son of Phinehas, the son of Eli, the Lord&rsquo;s priest in Shiloh, was wearing an ephod. But the people did not know that Jonathan had gone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14004, 'Between the passes, by which Jonathan sought to go over to the Philistines&rsquo; garrison, there was a sharp rock on one side and a sharp rock on the other side. And the name of one was Bozez, and the name of the other Seneh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14005, 'The front of one faced northward opposite Michmash, and the other southward opposite Gibeah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14006, 'Then Jonathan said to the young man who bore his armor, &ldquo;Come, let us go over to the garrison of these uncircumcised; it may be that the Lord will work for us. For nothing restrains the Lord from saving by many or by few.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14007, 'So his armorbearer said to him, &ldquo;Do all that is in your heart. Go then; here I am with you, according to your heart.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14008, 'Then Jonathan said, &ldquo;Very well, let us cross over to these men, and we will show ourselves to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14009, 'If they say thus to us, &lsquo;Wait until we come to you,&rsquo; then we will stand still in our place and not go up to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14010, 'But if they say thus, &lsquo;Come up to us,&rsquo; then we will go up. For the Lord has delivered them into our hand, and this will be a sign to us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14011, 'So both of them showed themselves to the garrison of the Philistines. And the Philistines said, &ldquo;Look, the Hebrews are coming out of the holes where they have hidden.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14012, 'Then the men of the garrison called to Jonathan and his armorbearer, and said, &ldquo;Come up to us, and we will show you something.&rdquo; Jonathan said to his armorbearer, &ldquo;Come up after me, for the Lord has delivered them into the hand of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14013, 'And Jonathan climbed up on his hands and knees with his armorbearer after him; and they fell before Jonathan. And as he came after him, his armorbearer killed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14014, 'That first slaughter which Jonathan and his armorbearer made was about twenty men within about half an acre of land.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14015, 'And there was trembling in the camp, in the field, and among all the people. The garrison and the raiders also trembled; and the earth quaked, so that it was a very great trembling. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14016, 'Now the watchmen of Saul in Gibeah of Benjamin looked, and there was the multitude, melting away; and they went here and there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14017, 'Then Saul said to the people who were with him, &ldquo;Now call the roll and see who has gone from us.&rdquo; And when they had called the roll, surprisingly, Jonathan and his armorbearer were not there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14018, 'And Saul said to Ahijah, &ldquo;Bring the ark of God here&rdquo; (for at that time the ark of God was with the children of Israel). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14019, 'Now it happened, while Saul talked to the priest, that the noise which was in the camp of the Philistines continued to increase; so Saul said to the priest, &ldquo;Withdraw your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14020, 'Then Saul and all the people who were with him assembled, and they went to the battle; and indeed every man&rsquo;s sword was against his neighbor, and there was very great confusion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14021, 'Moreover the Hebrews who were with the Philistines before that time, who went up with them into the camp from the surrounding country, they also joined the Israelites who were with Saul and Jonathan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14022, 'Likewise all the men of Israel who had hidden in the mountains of Ephraim, when they heard that the Philistines fled, they also followed hard after them in the battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14023, 'So the Lord saved Israel that day, and the battle shifted to Beth Aven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14024, 'And the men of Israel were distressed that day, for Saul had placed the people under oath, saying, &ldquo;Cursed is the man who eats any food until evening, before I have taken vengeance on my enemies.&rdquo; So none of the people tasted food. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14025, 'Now all the people of the land came to a forest; and there was honey on the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14026, 'And when the people had come into the woods, there was the honey, dripping; but no one put his hand to his mouth, for the people feared the oath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14027, 'But Jonathan had not heard his father charge the people with the oath; therefore he stretched out the end of the rod that was in his hand and dipped it in a honeycomb, and put his hand to his mouth; and his countenance brightened. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14028, 'Then one of the people said, &ldquo;Your father strictly charged the people with an oath, saying, &lsquo;Cursed is the man who eats food this day.&rsquo; &ldquo; And the people were faint. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14029, 'But Jonathan said, &ldquo;My father has troubled the land. Look now, how my countenance has brightened because I tasted a little of this honey. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14030, 'How much better if the people had eaten freely today of the spoil of their enemies which they found! For now would there not have been a much greater slaughter among the Philistines?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14031, 'Now they had driven back the Philistines that day from Michmash to Aijalon. So the people were very faint. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14032, 'And the people rushed on the spoil, and took sheep, oxen, and calves, and slaughtered them on the ground; and the people ate them with the blood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14033, 'Then they told Saul, saying, &ldquo;Look, the people are sinning against the Lord by eating with the blood!&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;You have dealt treacherously; roll a large stone to me this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14034, 'And Saul said, &ldquo;Disperse yourselves among the people, and say to them, &lsquo;Bring me here every man&rsquo;s ox and every man&rsquo;s sheep, slaughter them here, and eat; and do not sin against the Lord by eating with the blood.&rsquo; &ldquo; So every one of the people brought his ox with him that night, and slaughtered it there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14035, 'Then Saul built an altar to the Lord. This was the first altar that he built to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14036, 'Now Saul said, &ldquo;Let us go down after the Philistines by night, and plunder them until the morning light; and let us not leave a man of them.&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;Do whatever seems good to you.&rdquo; Then the priest said, &ldquo;Let us draw near to God here.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14037, 'So Saul asked counsel of God, &ldquo;Shall I go down after the Philistines? Will You deliver them into the hand of Israel?&rdquo; But He did not answer him that day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14038, 'And Saul said, &ldquo;Come over here, all you chiefs of the people, and know and see what this sin was today. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14039, 'For as the Lord lives, who saves Israel, though it be in Jonathan my son, he shall surely die.&rdquo; But not a man among all the people answered him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14040, 'Then he said to all Israel, &ldquo;You be on one side, and my son Jonathan and I will be on the other side.&rdquo; And the people said to Saul, &ldquo;Do what seems good to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14041, 'Therefore Saul said to the Lord God of Israel, &ldquo;Give a perfect lot.&rdquo; So Saul and Jonathan were taken, but the people escaped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14042, 'And Saul said, &ldquo;Cast lots between my son Jonathan and me.&rdquo; So Jonathan was taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14043, 'Then Saul said to Jonathan, &ldquo;Tell me what you have done.&rdquo; And Jonathan told him, and said, &ldquo;I only tasted a little honey with the end of the rod that was in my hand. So now I must die!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14044, 'And Saul answered, &ldquo;God do so and more also; for you shall surely die, Jonathan.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14045, 'But the people said to Saul, &ldquo;Shall Jonathan die, who has accomplished this great deliverance in Israel? Certainly not! As the Lord lives, not one hair of his head shall fall to the ground, for he has worked with God this day.&rdquo; So the people rescued Jonathan, and he did not die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14046, 'Then Saul returned from pursuing the Philistines, and the Philistines went to their own place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14047, 'So Saul established his sovereignty over Israel, and fought against all his enemies on every side, against Moab, against the people of Ammon, against Edom, against the kings of Zobah, and against the Philistines. Wherever he turned, he harassed them.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14048, 'And he gathered an army and attacked the Amalekites, and delivered Israel from the hands of those who plundered them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14049, 'The sons of Saul were Jonathan, Jishui and Malchishua. And the names of his two daughters were these: the name of the firstborn Merab, and the name of the younger Michal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14050, 'The name of Saul&rsquo;s wife was Ahinoam the daughter of Ahimaaz. And the name of the commander of his army was Abner the son of Ner, Saul&rsquo;s uncle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14051, 'Kish was the father of Saul, and Ner the father of Abner was the son of Abiel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 14052, 'Now there was fierce war with the Philistines all the days of Saul. And when Saul saw any strong man or any valiant man, he took him for himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15001, 'Samuel also said to Saul, &ldquo;The Lord sent me to anoint you king over His people, over Israel. Now therefore, heed the voice of the words of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15002, 'Thus says the Lord of hosts: &lsquo;I will punish Amalek for what he did to Israel, how he ambushed him on the way when he came up from Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15003, 'Now go and attack Amalek, and utterly destroy all that they have, and do not spare them. But kill both man and woman, infant and nursing child, ox and sheep, camel and donkey.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15004, 'So Saul gathered the people together and numbered them in Telaim, two hundred thousand foot soldiers and ten thousand men of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15005, 'And Saul came to a city of Amalek, and lay in wait in the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15006, 'Then Saul said to the Kenites, &ldquo;Go, depart, get down from among the Amalekites, lest I destroy you with them. For you showed kindness to all the children of Israel when they came up out of Egypt.&rdquo; So the Kenites departed from among the Amalekites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15007, 'And Saul attacked the Amalekites, from Havilah all the way to Shur, which is east of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15008, 'He also took Agag king of the Amalekites alive, and utterly destroyed all the people with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15009, 'But Saul and the people spared Agag and the best of the sheep, the oxen, the fatlings, the lambs, and all that was good, and were unwilling to utterly destroy them. But everything despised and worthless, that they utterly destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15010, 'Now the word of the Lord came to Samuel, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15011, 'I greatly regret that I have set up Saul as king, for he has turned back from following Me, and has not performed My commandments. And it grieved Samuel, and he cried out to the Lord all night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15012, 'So when Samuel rose early in the morning to meet Saul, it was told Samuel, saying, &ldquo;Saul went to Carmel, and indeed, he set up a monument for himself; and he has gone on around, passed by, and gone down to Gilgal.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15013, 'Then Samuel went to Saul, and Saul said to him, &ldquo;Blessed are you of the Lord! I have performed the commandment of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15014, 'But Samuel said, &ldquo;What then is this bleating of the sheep in my ears, and the lowing of the oxen which I hear?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15015, 'And Saul said, &ldquo;They have brought them from the Amalekites; for the people spared the best of the sheep and the oxen, to sacrifice to the Lord your God; and the rest we have utterly destroyed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15016, 'Then Samuel said to Saul, &ldquo;Be quiet! And I will tell you what the Lord said to me last night.&rdquo; And he said to him, &ldquo;Speak on.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15017, 'So Samuel said, &ldquo;When you were little in your own eyes, were you not head of the tribes of Israel? And did not the Lord anoint you king over Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15018, 'Now the Lord sent you on a mission, and said, &lsquo;Go, and utterly destroy the sinners, the Amalekites, and fight against them until they are consumed.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15019, 'Why then did you not obey the voice of the Lord? Why did you swoop down on the spoil, and do evil in the sight of the Lord?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15020, 'And Saul said to Samuel, &ldquo;But I have obeyed the voice of the Lord, and gone on the mission on which the Lord sent me, and brought back Agag king of Amalek; I have utterly destroyed the Amalekites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15021, 'But the people took of the plunder, sheep and oxen, the best of the things which should have been utterly destroyed, to sacrifice to the Lord your God in Gilgal.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15022, 'So Samuel said: &ldquo;Has the Lord as great delight in burnt offerings and sacrifices, As in obeying the voice of the Lord? Behold, to obey is better than sacrifice, And to heed than the fat of rams. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15023, 'For rebellion is as the sin of witchcraft, And stubbornness is as iniquity and idolatry. Because you have rejected the word of the Lord, He also has rejected you from being king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15024, 'Then Saul said to Samuel, &ldquo;I have sinned, for I have transgressed the commandment of the Lord and your words, because I feared the people and obeyed their voice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15025, 'Now therefore, please pardon my sin, and return with me, that I may worship the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15026, 'But Samuel said to Saul, &ldquo;I will not return with you, for you have rejected the word of the Lord, and the Lord has rejected you from being king over Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15027, 'And as Samuel turned around to go away, Saul seized the edge of his robe, and it tore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15028, 'So Samuel said to him, &ldquo;The Lord has torn the kingdom of Israel from you today, and has given it to a neighbor of yours, who is better than you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15029, 'And also the Strength of Israel will not lie nor relent. For He is not a man, that He should relent.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15030, 'Then he said, &ldquo;I have sinned; yet honor me now, please, before the elders of my people and before Israel, and return with me, that I may worship the Lord your God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15031, 'So Samuel turned back after Saul, and Saul worshiped the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15032, 'Then Samuel said, &ldquo;Bring Agag king of the Amalekites here to me.&rdquo; So Agag came to him cautiously. And Agag said, &ldquo;Surely the bitterness of death is past.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15033, 'But Samuel said, &ldquo;As your sword has made women childless, so shall your mother be childless among women.&rdquo; And Samuel hacked Agag in pieces before the Lord in Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15034, 'Then Samuel went to Ramah, and Saul went up to his house at Gibeah of Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 15035, 'And Samuel went no more to see Saul until the day of his death. Nevertheless Samuel mourned for Saul, and the Lord regretted that He had made Saul king over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16001, 'Now the Lord said to Samuel, &ldquo;How long will you mourn for Saul, seeing I have rejected him from reigning over Israel? Fill your horn with oil, and go; I am sending you to Jesse the Bethlehemite. For I have provided Myself a king among his sons.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16002, 'And Samuel said, &ldquo;How can I go? If Saul hears it, he will kill me.&rdquo; And the Lord said, &ldquo;Take a heifer with you, and say, &lsquo;I have come to sacrifice to the Lord.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16003, 'Then invite Jesse to the sacrifice, and I will show you what you shall do; you shall anoint for Me the one I name to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16004, 'So Samuel did what the Lord said, and went to Bethlehem. And the elders of the town trembled at his coming, and said, &ldquo;Do you come peaceably?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16005, 'And he said, &ldquo;Peaceably; I have come to sacrifice to the Lord. Sanctify yourselves, and come with me to the sacrifice.&rdquo; Then he consecrated Jesse and his sons, and invited them to the sacrifice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16006, 'So it was, when they came, that he looked at Eliab and said, &ldquo;Surely the Lord&rsquo;s anointed is before Him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16007, 'But the Lord said to Samuel, &ldquo;Do not look at his appearance or at the height of his stature, because I have refused him. For the Lord does not see as man sees; for man looks at the outward appearance, but the Lord looks at the heart.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16008, 'So Jesse called Abinadab, and made him pass before Samuel. And he said, &ldquo;Neither has the Lord chosen this one.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16009, 'Then Jesse made Shammah pass by. And he said, &ldquo;Neither has the Lord chosen this one.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16010, 'Thus Jesse made seven of his sons pass before Samuel. And Samuel said to Jesse, &ldquo;The Lord has not chosen these.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16011, 'And Samuel said to Jesse, &ldquo;Are all the young men here?&rdquo; Then he said, &ldquo;There remains yet the youngest, and there he is, keeping the sheep.&rdquo; And Samuel said to Jesse, &ldquo;Send and bring him. For we will not sit down till he comes here.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16012, 'So he sent and brought him in. Now he was ruddy, with bright eyes, and good-looking. And the Lord said, &ldquo;Arise, anoint him; for this is the one!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16013, 'Then Samuel took the horn of oil and anointed him in the midst of his brothers; and the Spirit of the Lord came upon David from that day forward. So Samuel arose and went to Ramah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16014, 'But the Spirit of the Lord departed from Saul, and a distressing spirit from the Lord troubled him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16015, 'And Saul&rsquo;s servants said to him, &ldquo;Surely, a distressing spirit from God is troubling you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16016, 'Let our master now command your servants, who are before you, to seek out a man who is a skillful player on the harp; and it shall be that he will play it with his hand when the distressing spirit from God is upon you, and you shall be well.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16017, 'So Saul said to his servants, &ldquo;Provide me now a man who can play well, and bring him to me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16018, 'Then one of the servants answered and said, &ldquo;Look, I have seen a son of Jesse the Bethlehemite, who is skillful in playing, a mighty man of valor, a man of war, prudent in speech, and a handsome person; and the Lord is with him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16019, 'Therefore Saul sent messengers to Jesse, and said, &ldquo;Send me your son David, who is with the sheep.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16020, 'And Jesse took a donkey loaded with bread, a skin of wine, and a young goat, and sent them by his son David to Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16021, 'So David came to Saul and stood before him. And he loved him greatly, and he became his armorbearer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16022, 'Then Saul sent to Jesse, saying, &ldquo;Please let David stand before me, for he has found favor in my sight.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 16023, 'And so it was, whenever the spirit from God was upon Saul, that David would take a harp and play it with his hand. Then Saul would become refreshed and well, and the distressing spirit would depart from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17001, 'Now the Philistines gathered their armies together to battle, and were gathered together at Sochoh, which belongs to Judah; they encamped between Sochoh and Azekah, in Ephes Dammim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17002, 'And Saul and the men of Israel were gathered together, and they encamped in the Valley of Elah, and drew up in battle array against the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17003, 'The Philistines stood on a mountain on one side, and Israel stood on a mountain on the other side, with a valley between them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17004, 'And a champion went out from the camp of the Philistines, named Goliath, from Gath, whose height was six cubits and a span. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17005, 'He had a bronze helmet on his head, and he was armed with a coat of mail, and the weight of the coat was five thousand shekels of bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17006, 'And he had bronze armor on his legs and a bronze javelin between his shoulders. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17007, 'Now the staff of his spear was like a weaver&rsquo;s beam, and his iron spearhead weighed six hundred shekels; and a shield-bearer went before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17008, 'Then he stood and cried out to the armies of Israel, and said to them, &ldquo;Why have you come out to line up for battle? Am I not a Philistine, and you the servants of Saul? Choose a man for yourselves, and let him come down to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17009, 'If he is able to fight with me and kill me, then we will be your servants. But if I prevail against him and kill him, then you shall be our servants and serve us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17010, 'And the Philistine said, &ldquo;I defy the armies of Israel this day; give me a man, that we may fight together.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17011, 'When Saul and all Israel heard these words of the Philistine, they were dismayed and greatly afraid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17012, 'Now David was the son of that Ephrathite of Bethlehem Judah, whose name was Jesse, and who had eight sons. And the man was old, advanced in years, in the days of Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17013, 'The three oldest sons of Jesse had gone to follow Saul to the battle. The names of his three sons who went to the battle were Eliab the firstborn, next to him Abinadab, and the third Shammah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17014, 'David was the youngest. And the three oldest followed Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17015, 'But David occasionally went and returned from Saul to feed his father&rsquo;s sheep at Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17016, 'And the Philistine drew near and presented himself forty days, morning and evening. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17017, 'Then Jesse said to his son David, &ldquo;Take now for your brothers an ephah of this dried grain and these ten loaves, and run to your brothers at the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17018, 'And carry these ten cheeses to the captain of their thousand, and see how your brothers fare, and bring back news of them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17019, 'Now Saul and they and all the men of Israel were in the Valley of Elah, fighting with the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17020, 'So David rose early in the morning, left the sheep with a keeper, and took the things and went as Jesse had commanded him. And he came to the camp as the army was going out to the fight and shouting for the battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17021, 'For Israel and the Philistines had drawn up in battle array, army against army. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17022, 'And David left his supplies in the hand of the supply keeper, ran to the army, and came and greeted his brothers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17023, 'Then as he talked with them, there was the champion, the Philistine of Gath, Goliath by name, coming up from the armies of the Philistines; and he spoke according to the same words. So David heard them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17024, 'And all the men of Israel, when they saw the man, fled from him and were dreadfully afraid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17025, 'So the men of Israel said, &ldquo;Have you seen this man who has come up? Surely he has come up to defy Israel; and it shall be that the man who kills him the king will enrich with great riches, will give him his daughter, and give his father&rsquo;s house exemption from taxes in Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17026, 'Then David spoke to the men who stood by him, saying, &ldquo;What shall be done for the man who kills this Philistine and takes away the reproach from Israel? For who is this uncircumcised Philistine, that he should defy the armies of the living God?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17027, 'And the people answered him in this manner, saying, &ldquo;So shall it be done for the man who kills him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17028, 'Now Eliab his oldest brother heard when he spoke to the men; and Eliab&rsquo;s anger was aroused against David, and he said, &ldquo;Why did you come down here? And with whom have you left those few sheep in the wilderness? I know your pride and the insolence of your heart, for you have come down to see the battle.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17029, 'And David said, &ldquo;What have I done now? Is there not a cause?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17030, 'Then he turned from him toward another and said the same thing; and these people answered him as the first ones did. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17031, 'Now when the words which David spoke were heard, they reported them to Saul; and he sent for him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17032, 'Then David said to Saul, &ldquo;Let no man&rsquo;s heart fail because of him; your servant will go and fight with this Philistine.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17033, 'And Saul said to David, &ldquo;You are not able to go against this Philistine to fight with him; for you are a youth, and he a man of war from his youth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17034, 'But David said to Saul, &ldquo;Your servant used to keep his father&rsquo;s sheep, and when a lion or a bear came and took a lamb out of the flock, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17035, 'I went out after it and struck it, and delivered the lamb from its mouth; and when it arose against me, I caught it by its beard, and struck and killed it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17036, 'Your servant has killed both lion and bear; and this uncircumcised Philistine will be like one of them, seeing he has defied the armies of the living God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17037, 'Moreover David said, &ldquo;The Lord, who delivered me from the paw of the lion and from the paw of the bear, He will deliver me from the hand of this Philistine.&rdquo; And Saul said to David, &ldquo;Go, and the Lord be with you!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17038, 'So Saul clothed David with his armor, and he put a bronze helmet on his head; he also clothed him with a coat of mail. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17039, 'David fastened his sword to his armor and tried to walk, for he had not tested them. And David said to Saul, &ldquo;I cannot walk with these, for I have not tested them.&rdquo; So David took them off. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17040, 'Then he took his staff in his hand; and he chose for himself five smooth stones from the brook, and put them in a shepherd&rsquo;s bag, in a pouch which he had, and his sling was in his hand. And he drew near to the Philistine. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17041, 'So the Philistine came, and began drawing near to David, and the man who bore the shield went before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17042, 'And when the Philistine looked about and saw David, he disdained him; for he was only a youth, ruddy and good-looking. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17043, 'So the Philistine said to David, &ldquo;Am I a dog, that you come to me with sticks?&rdquo; And the Philistine cursed David by his gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17044, 'And the Philistine said to David, &ldquo;Come to me, and I will give your flesh to the birds of the air and the beasts of the field!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17045, 'Then David said to the Philistine, &ldquo;You come to me with a sword, with a spear, and with a javelin. But I come to you in the name of the Lord of hosts, the God of the armies of Israel, whom you have defied. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17046, 'This day the Lord will deliver you into my hand, and I will strike you and take your head from you. And this day I will give the carcasses of the camp of the Philistines to the birds of the air and the wild beasts of the earth, that all the earth may know that there is a God in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17047, 'Then all this assembly shall know that the Lord does not save with sword and spear; for the battle is the Lord&rsquo;s, and He will give you into our hands.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17048, 'So it was, when the Philistine arose and came and drew near to meet David, that David hastened and ran toward the army to meet the Philistine. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17049, 'Then David put his hand in his bag and took out a stone; and he slung it and struck the Philistine in his forehead, so that the stone sank into his forehead, and he fell on his face to the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17050, 'So David prevailed over the Philistine with a sling and a stone, and struck the Philistine and killed him. But there was no sword in the hand of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17051, 'Therefore David ran and stood over the Philistine, took his sword and drew it out of its sheath and killed him, and cut off his head with it. And when the Philistines saw that their champion was dead, they fled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17052, 'Now the men of Israel and Judah arose and shouted, and pursued the Philistines as far as the entrance of the valley and to the gates of Ekron. And the wounded of the Philistines fell along the road to Shaaraim, even as far as Gath and Ekron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17053, 'Then the children of Israel returned from chasing the Philistines, and they plundered their tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17054, 'And David took the head of the Philistine and brought it to Jerusalem, but he put his armor in his tent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17055, 'When Saul saw David going out against the Philistine, he said to Abner, the commander of the army, &ldquo;Abner, whose son is this youth?&rdquo; And Abner said, &ldquo;As your soul lives, O king, I do not know.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17056, 'So the king said, &ldquo;Inquire whose son this young man is.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17057, 'Then, as David returned from the slaughter of the Philistine, Abner took him and brought him before Saul with the head of the Philistine in his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 17058, 'And Saul said to him, &ldquo;Whose son are you, young man?&rdquo; So David answered, &ldquo;I am the son of your servant Jesse the Bethlehemite.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18001, 'Now when he had finished speaking to Saul, the soul of Jonathan was knit to the soul of David, and Jonathan loved him as his own soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18002, 'Saul took him that day, and would not let him go home to his father&rsquo;s house anymore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18003, 'Then Jonathan and David made a covenant, because he loved him as his own soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18004, 'And Jonathan took off the robe that was on him and gave it to David, with his armor, even to his sword and his bow and his belt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18005, 'So David went out wherever Saul sent him, and behaved wisely. And Saul set him over the men of war, and he was accepted in the sight of all the people and also in the sight of Saul&rsquo;s servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18006, 'Now it had happened as they were coming home, when David was returning from the slaughter of the Philistine, that the women had come out of all the cities of Israel, singing and dancing, to meet King Saul, with tambourines, with joy, and with musical instruments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18007, 'So the women sang as they danced, and said: &ldquo;Saul has slain his thousands, And David his ten thousands.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18008, 'Then Saul was very angry, and the saying displeased him; and he said, &ldquo;They have ascribed to David ten thousands, and to me they have ascribed only thousands. Now what more can he have but the kingdom?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18009, 'So Saul eyed David from that day forward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18010, 'And it happened on the next day that the distressing spirit from God came upon Saul, and he prophesied inside the house. So David played music with his hand, as at other times; but there was a spear in Saul&rsquo;s hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18011, 'And Saul cast the spear, for he said, &ldquo;I will pin David to the wall!&rdquo; But David escaped his presence twice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18012, 'Now Saul was afraid of David, because the Lord was with him, but had departed from Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18013, 'Therefore Saul removed him from his presence, and made him his captain over a thousand; and he went out and came in before the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18014, 'And David behaved wisely in all his ways, and the Lord was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18015, 'Therefore, when Saul saw that he behaved very wisely, he was afraid of him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18016, 'But all Israel and Judah loved David, because he went out and came in before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18017, 'Then Saul said to David, &ldquo;Here is my older daughter Merab; I will give her to you as a wife. Only be valiant for me, and fight the Lord&rsquo;s battles.&rdquo; For Saul thought, &ldquo;Let my hand not be against him, but let the hand of the Philistines be against him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18018, 'So David said to Saul, &ldquo;Who am I, and what is my life or my father&rsquo;s family in Israel, that I should be son-in-law to the king?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18019, 'But it happened at the time when Merab, Saul&rsquo;s daughter, should have been given to David, that she was given to Adriel the Meholathite as a wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18020, 'Now Michal, Saul&rsquo;s daughter, loved David. And they told Saul, and the thing pleased him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18021, 'So Saul said, &ldquo;I will give her to him, that she may be a snare to him, and that the hand of the Philistines may be against him.&rdquo; Therefore Saul said to David a second time, &ldquo;You shall be my son-in-law today.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18022, 'And Saul commanded his servants, &ldquo;Communicate with David secretly, and say, &lsquo;Look, the king has delight in you, and all his servants love you. Now therefore, become the king&rsquo;s son-in-law.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18023, 'So Saul&rsquo;s servants spoke those words in the hearing of David. And David said, &ldquo;Does it seem to you a light thing to be a king&rsquo;s son-in-law, seeing I am a poor and lightly esteemed man?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18024, 'And the servants of Saul told him, saying, &ldquo;In this manner David spoke.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18025, 'Then Saul said, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to David: &lsquo;The king does not desire any dowry but one hundred foreskins of the Philistines, to take vengeance on the king&rsquo;s enemies.&rsquo; &ldquo; But Saul thought to make David fall by the hand of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18026, 'So when his servants told David these words, it pleased David well to become the king&rsquo;s son-in-law. Now the days had not expired; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18027, 'therefore David arose and went, he and his men, and killed two hundred men of the Philistines. And David brought their foreskins, and they gave them in full count to the king, that he might become the king&rsquo;s son-in-law. Then Saul gave him Michal his daughter as a wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18028, 'Thus Saul saw and knew that the Lord was with David, and that Michal, Saul&rsquo;s daughter, loved him; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18029, 'and Saul was still more afraid of David. So Saul became David&rsquo;s enemy continually. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 18030, 'Then the princes of the Philistines went out to war. And so it was, whenever they went out, that David behaved more wisely than all the servants of Saul, so that his name became highly esteemed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19001, 'Now Saul spoke to Jonathan his son and to all his servants, that they should kill David; but Jonathan, Saul&rsquo;s son, delighted greatly in David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19002, 'So Jonathan told David, saying, &ldquo;My father Saul seeks to kill you. Therefore please be on your guard until morning, and stay in a secret place and hide. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19003, 'And I will go out and stand beside my father in the field where you are, and I will speak with my father about you. Then what I observe, I will tell you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19004, 'Thus Jonathan spoke well of David to Saul his father, and said to him, &ldquo;Let not the king sin against his servant, against David, because he has not sinned against you, and because his works have been very good toward you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19005, 'For he took his life in his hands and killed the Philistine, and the Lord brought about a great deliverance for all Israel. You saw it and rejoiced. Why then will you sin against innocent blood, to kill David without a cause?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19006, 'So Saul heeded the voice of Jonathan, and Saul swore, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, he shall not be killed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19007, 'Then Jonathan called David, and Jonathan told him all these things. So Jonathan brought David to Saul, and he was in his presence as in times past. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19008, 'And there was war again; and David went out and fought with the Philistines, and struck them with a mighty blow, and they fled from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19009, 'Now the distressing spirit from the Lord came upon Saul as he sat in his house with his spear in his hand. And David was playing music with his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19010, 'Then Saul sought to pin David to the wall with the spear, but he slipped away from Saul&rsquo;s presence; and he drove the spear into the wall. So David fled and escaped that night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19011, 'Saul also sent messengers to David&rsquo;s house to watch him and to kill him in the morning. And Michal, David&rsquo;s wife, told him, saying, &ldquo;If you do not save your life tonight, tomorrow you will be killed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19012, 'So Michal let David down through a window. And he went and fled and escaped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19013, 'And Michal took an image and laid it in the bed, put a cover of goats&rsquo; hair for his head, and covered it with clothes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19014, 'So when Saul sent messengers to take David, she said, &ldquo;He is sick.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19015, 'Then Saul sent the messengers back to see David, saying, &ldquo;Bring him up to me in the bed, that I may kill him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19016, 'And when the messengers had come in, there was the image in the bed, with a cover of goats&rsquo; hair for his head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19017, 'Then Saul said to Michal, &ldquo;Why have you deceived me like this, and sent my enemy away, so that he has escaped?&rdquo; And Michal answered Saul, &ldquo;He said to me, &lsquo;Let me go! Why should I kill you?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19018, 'So David fled and escaped, and went to Samuel at Ramah, and told him all that Saul had done to him. And he and Samuel went and stayed in Naioth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19019, 'Now it was told Saul, saying, &ldquo;Take note, David is at Naioth in Ramah!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19020, 'Then Saul sent messengers to take David. And when they saw the group of prophets prophesying, and Samuel standing as leader over them, the Spirit of God came upon the messengers of Saul, and they also prophesied. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19021, 'And when Saul was told, he sent other messengers, and they prophesied likewise. Then Saul sent messengers again the third time, and they prophesied also. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19022, 'Then he also went to Ramah, and came to the great well that is at Sechu. So he asked, and said, &ldquo;Where are Samuel and David?&rdquo; And someone said, &ldquo;Indeed they are at Naioth in Ramah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19023, 'So he went there to Naioth in Ramah. Then the Spirit of God was upon him also, and he went on and prophesied until he came to Naioth in Ramah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 19024, 'And he also stripped off his clothes and prophesied before Samuel in like manner, and lay down naked all that day and all that night. Therefore they say, &ldquo;Is Saul also among the prophets?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20001, 'Then David fled from Naioth in Ramah, and went and said to Jonathan, &ldquo;What have I done? What is my iniquity, and what is my sin before your father, that he seeks my life?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20002, 'So Jonathan said to him, &ldquo;By no means! You shall not die! Indeed, my father will do nothing either great or small without first telling me. And why should my father hide this thing from me? It is not so!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20003, 'Then David took an oath again, and said, &ldquo;Your father certainly knows that I have found favor in your eyes, and he has said, &lsquo;Do not let Jonathan know this, lest he be grieved.&rsquo; But truly, as the Lord lives and as your soul lives, there is but a step between me and death.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20004, 'So Jonathan said to David, &ldquo;Whatever you yourself desire, I will do it for you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20005, 'And David said to Jonathan, &ldquo;Indeed tomorrow is the New Moon, and I should not fail to sit with the king to eat. But let me go, that I may hide in the field until the third day at evening. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20006, 'If your father misses me at all, then say, &lsquo;David earnestly asked permission of me that he might run over to Bethlehem, his city, for there is a yearly sacrifice there for all the family.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20007, 'If he says thus: &lsquo;It is well,&rsquo; your servant will be safe. But if he is very angry, then be sure that evil is determined by him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20008, 'Therefore you shall deal kindly with your servant, for you have brought your servant into a covenant of the Lord with you. Nevertheless, if there is iniquity in me, kill me yourself, for why should you bring me to your father?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20009, 'But Jonathan said, &ldquo;Far be it from you! For if I knew certainly that evil was determined by my father to come upon you, then would I not tell you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20010, 'Then David said to Jonathan, &ldquo;Who will tell me, or what if your father answers you roughly?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20011, 'And Jonathan said to David, &ldquo;Come, and let us go out into the field.&rdquo; So both of them went out into the field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20012, 'Then Jonathan said to David: &ldquo;The Lord God of Israel is witness! When I have sounded out my father sometime tomorrow, or the third day, and indeed there is good toward David, and I do not send to you and tell you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20013, 'may the Lord do so and much more to Jonathan. But if it pleases my father to do you evil, then I will report it to you and send you away, that you may go in safety. And the Lord be with you as He has been with my father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20014, 'And you shall not only show me the kindness of the Lord while I still live, that I may not die; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20015, 'but you shall not cut off your kindness from my house forever, no, not when the Lord has cut off every one of the enemies of David from the face of the earth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20016, 'So Jonathan made a covenant with the house of David, saying, &ldquo;Let the Lord require it at the hand of David&rsquo;s enemies.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20017, 'Now Jonathan again caused David to vow, because he loved him; for he loved him as he loved his own soul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20018, 'Then Jonathan said to David, &ldquo;Tomorrow is the New Moon; and you will be missed, because your seat will be empty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20019, 'And when you have stayed three days, go down quickly and come to the place where you hid on the day of the deed; and remain by the stone Ezel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20020, 'Then I will shoot three arrows to the side, as though I shot at a target; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20021, 'and there I will send a lad, saying, &lsquo;Go, find the arrows.&rsquo; If I expressly say to him, &lsquo;Look, the arrows are on this side of you; get them and come&rsquo; &ndash; then, as the Lord lives, there is safety for you and no harm. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20022, 'But if I say thus to the young man, &lsquo;Look, the arrows are beyond you&rsquo; &ndash; go your way, for the Lord has sent you away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20023, 'And as for the matter which you and I have spoken of, indeed the Lord be between you and me forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20024, 'Then David hid in the field. And when the New Moon had come, the king sat down to eat the feast. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20025, 'Now the king sat on his seat, as at other times, on a seat by the wall. And Jonathan arose, and Abner sat by Saul&rsquo;s side, but David&rsquo;s place was empty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20026, 'Nevertheless Saul did not say anything that day, for he thought, &ldquo;Something has happened to him; he is unclean, surely he is unclean.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20027, 'And it happened the next day, the second day of the month, that David&rsquo;s place was empty. And Saul said to Jonathan his son, &ldquo;Why has the son of Jesse not come to eat, either yesterday or today?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20028, 'So Jonathan answered Saul, &ldquo;David earnestly asked permission of me to go to Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20029, 'And he said, &lsquo;Please let me go, for our family has a sacrifice in the city, and my brother has commanded me to be there. And now, if I have found favor in your eyes, please let me get away and see my brothers.&rsquo; Therefore he has not come to the king&rsquo;s table.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20030, 'Then Saul&rsquo;s anger was aroused against Jonathan, and he said to him, &ldquo;You son of a perverse, rebellious woman! Do I not know that you have chosen the son of Jesse to your own shame and to the shame of your mother&rsquo;s nakedness? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20031, 'For as long as the son of Jesse lives on the earth, you shall not be established, nor your kingdom. Now therefore, send and bring him to me, for he shall surely die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20032, 'And Jonathan answered Saul his father, and said to him, &ldquo;Why should he be killed? What has he done?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20033, 'Then Saul cast a spear at him to kill him, by which Jonathan knew that it was determined by his father to kill David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20034, 'So Jonathan arose from the table in fierce anger, and ate no food the second day of the month, for he was grieved for David, because his father had treated him shamefully. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20035, 'And so it was, in the morning, that Jonathan went out into the field at the time appointed with David, and a little lad was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20036, 'Then he said to his lad, &ldquo;Now run, find the arrows which I shoot.&rdquo; As the lad ran, he shot an arrow beyond him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20037, 'When the lad had come to the place where the arrow was which Jonathan had shot, Jonathan cried out after the lad and said, &ldquo;Is not the arrow beyond you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20038, 'And Jonathan cried out after the lad, &ldquo;Make haste, hurry, do not delay!&rdquo; So Jonathan&rsquo;s lad gathered up the arrows and came back to his master. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20039, 'But the lad did not know anything. Only Jonathan and David knew of the matter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20040, 'Then Jonathan gave his weapons to his lad, and said to him, &ldquo;Go, carry them to the city.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20041, 'As soon as the lad had gone, David arose from a place toward the south, fell on his face to the ground, and bowed down three times. And they kissed one another; and they wept together, but David more so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 20042, 'Then Jonathan said to David, &ldquo;Go in peace, since we have both sworn in the name of the Lord, saying, &lsquo;May the Lord be between you and me, and between your descendants and my descendants, forever.&rsquo; &ldquo; So he arose and departed, and Jonathan went into the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21001, 'Now David came to Nob, to Ahimelech the priest. And Ahimelech was afraid when he met David, and said to him, &ldquo;Why are you alone, and no one is with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21002, 'So David said to Ahimelech the priest, &ldquo;The king has ordered me on some business, and said to me, &lsquo;Do not let anyone know anything about the business on which I send you, or what I have commanded you.&rsquo; And I have directed my young men to such and such a place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21003, 'Now therefore, what have you on hand? Give me five loaves of bread in my hand, or whatever can be found.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21004, 'And the priest answered David and said, &ldquo;There is no common bread on hand; but there is holy bread, if the young men have at least kept themselves from women.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21005, 'Then David answered the priest, and said to him, &ldquo;Truly, women have been kept from us about three days since I came out. And the vessels of the young men are holy, and the bread is in effect common, even though it was sanctified in the vessel this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21006, 'So the priest gave him holy bread; for there was no bread there but the showbread which had been taken from before the Lord, in order to put hot bread in its place on the day when it was taken away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21007, 'Now a certain man of the servants of Saul was there that day, detained before the Lord. And his name was Doeg, an Edomite, the chief of the herdsmen who belonged to Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21008, 'And David said to Ahimelech, &ldquo;Is there not here on hand a spear or a sword? For I have brought neither my sword nor my weapons with me, because the king&rsquo;s business required haste.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21009, 'So the priest said, &ldquo;The sword of Goliath the Philistine, whom you killed in the Valley of Elah, there it is, wrapped in a cloth behind the ephod. If you will take that, take it. For there is no other except that one here.&rdquo; And David said, &ldquo;There is none like it; give it to me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21010, 'Then David arose and fled that day from before Saul, and went to Achish the king of Gath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21011, 'And the servants of Achish said to him, &ldquo;Is this not David the king of the land? Did they not sing of him to one another in dances, saying: &lsquo;Saul has slain his thousands, And David his ten thousands&rsquo;?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21012, 'Now David took these words to heart, and was very much afraid of Achish the king of Gath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21013, 'So he changed his behavior before them, feigned madness in their hands, scratched on the doors of the gate, and let his saliva fall down on his beard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21014, 'Then Achish said to his servants, &ldquo;Look, you see the man is insane. Why have you brought him to me? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 21015, 'Have I need of madmen, that you have brought this fellow to play the madman in my presence? Shall this fellow come into my house?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22001, 'David therefore departed from there and escaped to the cave of Adullam. And when his brothers and all his father&rsquo;s house heard it, they went down there to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22002, 'And everyone who was in distress, everyone who was in debt, and everyone who was discontented gathered to him. So he became captain over them. And there were about four hundred men with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22003, 'Then David went from there to Mizpah of Moab; and he said to the king of Moab, &ldquo;Please let my father and mother come here with you, till I know what God will do for me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22004, 'So he brought them before the king of Moab, and they dwelt with him all the time that David was in the stronghold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22005, 'Now the prophet Gad said to David, &ldquo;Do not stay in the stronghold; depart, and go to the land of Judah.&rdquo; So David departed and went into the forest of Hereth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22006, 'When Saul heard that David and the men who were with him had been discovered &ndash; now Saul was staying in Gibeah under a tamarisk tree in Ramah, with his spear in his hand, and all his servants standing about him &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22007, 'then Saul said to his servants who stood about him, &ldquo;Hear now, you Benjamites! Will the son of Jesse give every one of you fields and vineyards, and make you all captains of thousands and captains of hundreds? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22008, 'All of you have conspired against me, and there is no one who reveals to me that my son has made a covenant with the son of Jesse; and there is not one of you who is sorry for me or reveals to me that my son has stirred up my servant against me, to lie in wait, as it is this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22009, 'Then answered Doeg the Edomite, who was set over the servants of Saul, and said, &ldquo;I saw the son of Jesse going to Nob, to Ahimelech the son of Ahitub. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22010, 'And he inquired of the Lord for him, gave him provisions, and gave him the sword of Goliath the Philistine.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22011, 'So the king sent to call Ahimelech the priest, the son of Ahitub, and all his father&rsquo;s house, the priests who were in Nob. And they all came to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22012, 'And Saul said, &ldquo;Hear now, son of Ahitub!&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;Here I am, my lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22013, 'Then Saul said to him, &ldquo;Why have you conspired against me, you and the son of Jesse, in that you have given him bread and a sword, and have inquired of God for him, that he should rise against me, to lie in wait, as it is this day?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22014, 'So Ahimelech answered the king and said, &ldquo;And who among all your servants is as faithful as David, who is the king&rsquo;s son-in-law, who goes at your bidding, and is honorable in your house? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22015, 'Did I then begin to inquire of God for him? Far be it from me! Let not the king impute anything to his servant, or to any in the house of my father. For your servant knew nothing of all this, little or much.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22016, 'And the king said, &ldquo;You shall surely die, Ahimelech, you and all your father&rsquo;s house!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22017, 'Then the king said to the guards who stood about him, &ldquo;Turn and kill the priests of the Lord, because their hand also is with David, and because they knew when he fled and did not tell it to me.&rdquo; But the servants of the king would not lift their hands to strike the priests of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22018, 'And the king said to Doeg, &ldquo;You turn and kill the priests!&rdquo; So Doeg the Edomite turned and struck the priests, and killed on that day eighty-five men who wore a linen ephod. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22019, 'Also Nob, the city of the priests, he struck with the edge of the sword, both men and women, children and nursing infants, oxen and donkeys and sheep &ndash; with the edge of the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22020, 'Now one of the sons of Ahimelech the son of Ahitub, named Abiathar, escaped and fled after David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22021, 'And Abiathar told David that Saul had killed the Lord&rsquo;s priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22022, 'So David said to Abiathar, &ldquo;I knew that day, when Doeg the Edomite was there, that he would surely tell Saul. I have caused the death of all the persons of your father&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 22023, 'Stay with me; do not fear. For he who seeks my life seeks your life, but with me you shall be safe.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23001, 'Then they told David, saying, &ldquo;Look, the Philistines are fighting against Keilah, and they are robbing the threshing floors.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23002, 'Therefore David inquired of the Lord, saying, &ldquo;Shall I go and attack these Philistines?&rdquo; And the Lord said to David, &ldquo;Go and attack the Philistines, and save Keilah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23003, 'But David&rsquo;s men said to him, &ldquo;Look, we are afraid here in Judah. How much more then if we go to Keilah against the armies of the Philistines?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23004, 'Then David inquired of the Lord once again. And the Lord answered him and said, &ldquo;Arise, go down to Keilah. For I will deliver the Philistines into your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23005, 'And David and his men went to Keilah and fought with the Philistines, struck them with a mighty blow, and took away their livestock. So David saved the inhabitants of Keilah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23006, 'Now it happened, when Abiathar the son of Ahimelech fled to David at Keilah, that he went down with an ephod in his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23007, 'And Saul was told that David had gone to Keilah. So Saul said, &ldquo;God has delivered him into my hand, for he has shut himself in by entering a town that has gates and bars.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23008, 'Then Saul called all the people together for war, to go down to Keilah to besiege David and his men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23009, 'When David knew that Saul plotted evil against him, he said to Abiathar the priest, &ldquo;Bring the ephod here.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23010, 'Then David said, &ldquo;O Lord God of Israel, Your servant has certainly heard that Saul seeks to come to Keilah to destroy the city for my sake. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23011, 'Will the men of Keilah deliver me into his hand? Will Saul come down, as Your servant has heard? O Lord God of Israel, I pray, tell Your servant.&rdquo; And the Lord said, &ldquo;He will come down.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23012, 'Then David said, &ldquo;Will the men of Keilah deliver me and my men into the hand of Saul?&rdquo; And the Lord said, &ldquo;They will deliver you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23013, 'So David and his men, about six hundred, arose and departed from Keilah and went wherever they could go. Then it was told Saul that David had escaped from Keilah; so he halted the expedition. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23014, 'And David stayed in strongholds in the wilderness, and remained in the mountains in the Wilderness of Ziph. Saul sought him every day, but God did not deliver him into his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23015, 'So David saw that Saul had come out to seek his life. And David was in the Wilderness of Ziph in a forest.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23016, 'Then Jonathan, Saul&rsquo;s son, arose and went to David in the woods and strengthened his hand in God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23017, 'And he said to him, &ldquo;Do not fear, for the hand of Saul my father shall not find you. You shall be king over Israel, and I shall be next to you. Even my father Saul knows that.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23018, 'So the two of them made a covenant before the Lord. And David stayed in the woods, and Jonathan went to his own house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23019, 'Then the Ziphites came up to Saul at Gibeah, saying, &ldquo;Is David not hiding with us in strongholds in the woods, in the hill of Hachilah, which is on the south of Jeshimon? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23020, 'Now therefore, O king, come down according to all the desire of your soul to come down; and our part shall be to deliver him into the king&rsquo;s hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23021, 'And Saul said, &ldquo;Blessed are you of the Lord, for you have compassion on me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23022, 'Please go and find out for sure, and see the place where his hideout is, and who has seen him there. For I am told he is very crafty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23023, 'See therefore, and take knowledge of all the lurking places where he hides; and come back to me with certainty, and I will go with you. And it shall be, if he is in the land, that I will search for him throughout all the clans of Judah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23024, 'So they arose and went to Ziph before Saul. But David and his men were in the Wilderness of Maon, in the plain on the south of Jeshimon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23025, 'When Saul and his men went to seek him, they told David. Therefore he went down to the rock, and stayed in the Wilderness of Maon. And when Saul heard that, he pursued David in the Wilderness of Maon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23026, 'Then Saul went on one side of the mountain, and David and his men on the other side of the mountain. So David made haste to get away from Saul, for Saul and his men were encircling David and his men to take them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23027, 'But a messenger came to Saul, saying, &ldquo;Hasten and come, for the Philistines have invaded the land!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23028, 'Therefore Saul returned from pursuing David, and went against the Philistines; so they called that place the Rock of Escape.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 23029, 'Then David went up from there and dwelt in strongholds at En Gedi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24001, 'Now it happened, when Saul had returned from following the Philistines, that it was told him, saying, &ldquo;Take note! David is in the Wilderness of En Gedi.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24002, 'Then Saul took three thousand chosen men from all Israel, and went to seek David and his men on the Rocks of the Wild Goats. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24003, 'So he came to the sheepfolds by the road, where there was a cave; and Saul went in to attend to his needs. (David and his men were staying in the recesses of the cave.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24004, 'Then the men of David said to him, &ldquo;This is the day of which the Lord said to you, &lsquo;Behold, I will deliver your enemy into your hand, that you may do to him as it seems good to you.&rsquo; &ldquo; And David arose and secretly cut off a corner of Saul&rsquo;s robe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24005, 'Now it happened afterward that David&rsquo;s heart troubled him because he had cut Saul&rsquo;s robe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24006, 'And he said to his men, &ldquo;The Lord forbid that I should do this thing to my master, the Lord&rsquo;s anointed, to stretch out my hand against him, seeing he is the anointed of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24007, 'So David restrained his servants with these words, and did not allow them to rise against Saul. And Saul got up from the cave and went on his way. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24008, 'David also arose afterward, went out of the cave, and called out to Saul, saying, &ldquo;My lord the king!&rdquo; And when Saul looked behind him, David stooped with his face to the earth, and bowed down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24009, 'And David said to Saul: &ldquo;Why do you listen to the words of men who say, &lsquo;Indeed David seeks your harm&rsquo;? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24010, 'Look, this day your eyes have seen that the Lord delivered you today into my hand in the cave, and someone urged me to kill you. But my eye spared you, and I said, &lsquo;I will not stretch out my hand against my lord, for he is the Lord&rsquo;s anointed.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24011, 'Moreover, my father, see! Yes, see the corner of your robe in my hand! For in that I cut off the corner of your robe, and did not kill you, know and see that there is neither evil nor rebellion in my hand, and I have not sinned against you. Yet you hunt my life to take it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24012, 'Let the Lord judge between you and me, and let the Lord avenge me on you. But my hand shall not be against you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24013, 'As the proverb of the ancients says, &lsquo;Wickedness proceeds from the wicked.&rsquo; But my hand shall not be against you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24014, 'After whom has the king of Israel come out? Whom do you pursue? A dead dog? A flea? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24015, 'Therefore let the Lord be judge, and judge between you and me, and see and plead my case, and deliver me out of your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24016, 'So it was, when David had finished speaking these words to Saul, that Saul said, &ldquo;Is this your voice, my son David?&rdquo; And Saul lifted up his voice and wept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24017, 'Then he said to David: &ldquo;You are more righteous than I; for you have rewarded me with good, whereas I have rewarded you with evil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24018, 'And you have shown this day how you have dealt well with me; for when the Lord delivered me into your hand, you did not kill me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24019, 'For if a man finds his enemy, will he let him get away safely? Therefore may the Lord reward you with good for what you have done to me this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24020, 'And now I know indeed that you shall surely be king, and that the kingdom of Israel shall be established in your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24021, 'Therefore swear now to me by the Lord that you will not cut off my descendants after me, and that you will not destroy my name from my father&rsquo;s house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 24022, 'So David swore to Saul. And Saul went home, but David and his men went up to the stronghold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25001, 'Then Samuel died; and the Israelites gathered together and lamented for him, and buried him at his home in Ramah. And David arose and went down to the Wilderness of Paran.* ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25002, 'Now there was a man in Maon whose business was in Carmel, and the man was very rich. He had three thousand sheep and a thousand goats. And he was shearing his sheep in Carmel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25003, 'The name of the man was Nabal, and the name of his wife Abigail. And she was a woman of good understanding and beautiful appearance; but the man was harsh and evil in his doings. And he was of the house of Caleb. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25004, 'When David heard in the wilderness that Nabal was shearing his sheep, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25005, 'David sent ten young men; and David said to the young men, &ldquo;Go up to Carmel, go to Nabal, and greet him in my name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25006, 'And thus you shall say to him who lives in prosperity: &lsquo;Peace be to you, peace to your house, and peace to all that you have! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25007, 'Now I have heard that you have shearers. Your shepherds were with us, and we did not hurt them, nor was there anything missing from them all the while they were in Carmel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25008, 'Ask your young men, and they will tell you. Therefore let my young men find favor in your eyes, for we come on a feast day. Please give whatever comes to your hand to your servants and to your son David.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25009, 'So when David&rsquo;s young men came, they spoke to Nabal according to all these words in the name of David, and waited. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25010, 'Then Nabal answered David&rsquo;s servants, and said, &ldquo;Who is David, and who is the son of Jesse? There are many servants nowadays who break away each one from his master. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25011, 'Shall I then take my bread and my water and my meat that I have killed for my shearers, and give it to men when I do not know where they are from?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25012, 'So David&rsquo;s young men turned on their heels and went back; and they came and told him all these words. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25013, 'Then David said to his men, &ldquo;Every man gird on his sword.&rdquo; So every man girded on his sword, and David also girded on his sword. And about four hundred men went with David, and two hundred stayed with the supplies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25014, 'Now one of the young men told Abigail, Nabal&rsquo;s wife, saying, &ldquo;Look, David sent messengers from the wilderness to greet our master; and he reviled them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25015, 'But the men were very good to us, and we were not hurt, nor did we miss anything as long as we accompanied them, when we were in the fields. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25016, 'They were a wall to us both by night and day, all the time we were with them keeping the sheep. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25017, 'Now therefore, know and consider what you will do, for harm is determined against our master and against all his household. For he is such a scoundrel that one cannot speak to him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25018, 'Then Abigail made haste and took two hundred loaves of bread, two skins of wine, five sheep already dressed, five seahs of roasted grain, one hundred clusters of raisins, and two hundred cakes of figs, and loaded them on donkeys. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25019, 'And she said to her servants, &ldquo;Go on before me; see, I am coming after you.&rdquo; But she did not tell her husband Nabal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25020, 'So it was, as she rode on the donkey, that she went down under cover of the hill; and there were David and his men, coming down toward her, and she met them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25021, 'Now David had said, &ldquo;Surely in vain I have protected all that this fellow has in the wilderness, so that nothing was missed of all that belongs to him. And he has repaid me evil for good. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25022, 'May God do so, and more also, to the enemies of David, if I leave one male of all who belong to him by morning light.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25023, 'Now when Abigail saw David, she hastened to dismount from the donkey, fell on her face before David, and bowed down to the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25024, 'So she fell at his feet and said: &ldquo;On me, my lord, on me let this iniquity be! And please let your maidservant speak in your ears, and hear the words of your maidservant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25025, 'Please, let not my lord regard this scoundrel Nabal. For as his name is, so is he: Nabal is his name, and folly is with him. But I, your maidservant, did not see the young men of my lord whom you sent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25026, 'Now therefore, my lord, as the Lord lives and as your soul lives, since the Lord has held you back from coming to bloodshed and from avenging yourself with your own hand, now then, let your enemies and those who seek harm for my lord be as Nabal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25027, 'And now this present which your maidservant has brought to my lord, let it be given to the young men who follow my lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25028, 'Please forgive the trespass of your maidservant. For the Lord will certainly make for my lord an enduring house, because my lord fights the battles of the Lord, and evil is not found in you throughout your days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25029, 'Yet a man has risen to pursue you and seek your life, but the life of my lord shall be bound in the bundle of the living with the Lord your God; and the lives of your enemies He shall sling out, as from the pocket of a sling. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25030, 'And it shall come to pass, when the Lord has done for my lord according to all the good that He has spoken concerning you, and has appointed you ruler over Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25031, 'that this will be no grief to you, nor offense of heart to my lord, either that you have shed blood without cause, or that my lord has avenged himself. But when the Lord has dealt well with my lord, then remember your maidservant.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25032, 'Then David said to Abigail: &ldquo;Blessed is the Lord God of Israel, who sent you this day to meet me! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25033, 'And blessed is your advice and blessed are you, because you have kept me this day from coming to bloodshed and from avenging myself with my own hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25034, 'For indeed, as the Lord God of Israel lives, who has kept me back from hurting you, unless you had hastened and come to meet me, surely by morning light no males would have been left to Nabal!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25035, 'So David received from her hand what she had brought him, and said to her, &ldquo;Go up in peace to your house. See, I have heeded your voice and respected your person.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25036, 'Now Abigail went to Nabal, and there he was, holding a feast in his house, like the feast of a king. And Nabal&rsquo;s heart was merry within him, for he was very drunk; therefore she told him nothing, little or much, until morning light. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25037, 'So it was, in the morning, when the wine had gone from Nabal, and his wife had told him these things, that his heart died within him, and he became like a stone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25038, 'Then it came about, after about ten days, that the Lord struck Nabal, and he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25039, 'So when David heard that Nabal was dead, he said, &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord, who has pleaded the cause of my reproach from the hand of Nabal, and has kept His servant from evil! For the Lord has returned the wickedness of Nabal on his own head.&rdquo; And David sent and proposed to Abigail, to take her as his wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25040, 'When the servants of David had come to Abigail at Carmel, they spoke to her saying, &ldquo;David sent us to you, to ask you to become his wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25041, 'Then she arose, bowed her face to the earth, and said, &ldquo;Here is your maidservant, a servant to wash the feet of the servants of my lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25042, 'So Abigail rose in haste and rode on a donkey, attended by five of her maidens; and she followed the messengers of David, and became his wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25043, 'David also took Ahinoam of Jezreel, and so both of them were his wives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 25044, 'But Saul had given Michal his daughter, David&rsquo;s wife, to Palti the son of Laish, who was from Gallim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26001, 'Now the Ziphites came to Saul at Gibeah, saying, &ldquo;Is David not hiding in the hill of Hachilah, opposite Jeshimon?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26002, 'Then Saul arose and went down to the Wilderness of Ziph, having three thousand chosen men of Israel with him, to seek David in the Wilderness of Ziph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26003, 'And Saul encamped in the hill of Hachilah, which is opposite Jeshimon, by the road. But David stayed in the wilderness, and he saw that Saul came after him into the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26004, 'David therefore sent out spies, and understood that Saul had indeed come. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26005, 'So David arose and came to the place where Saul had encamped. And David saw the place where Saul lay, and Abner the son of Ner, the commander of his army. Now Saul lay within the camp, with the people encamped all around him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26006, 'Then David answered, and said to Ahimelech the Hittite and to Abishai the son of Zeruiah, brother of Joab, saying, &ldquo;Who will go down with me to Saul in the camp?&rdquo; And Abishai said, &ldquo;I will go down with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26007, 'So David and Abishai came to the people by night; and there Saul lay sleeping within the camp, with his spear stuck in the ground by his head. And Abner and the people lay all around him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26008, 'Then Abishai said to David, &ldquo;God has delivered your enemy into your hand this day. Now therefore, please, let me strike him at once with the spear, right to the earth; and I will not have to strike him a second time!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26009, 'And David said to Abishai, &ldquo;Do not destroy him; for who can stretch out his hand against the Lord&rsquo;s anointed, and be guiltless?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26010, 'David said furthermore, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, the Lord shall strike him, or his day shall come to die, or he shall go out to battle and perish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26011, 'The Lord forbid that I should stretch out my hand against the Lord&rsquo;s anointed. But please, take now the spear and the jug of water that are by his head, and let us go.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26012, 'So David took the spear and the jug of water by Saul&rsquo;s head, and they got away; and no man saw it or knew it or awoke. For they were all asleep, because a deep sleep from the Lord had fallen on them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26013, 'Now David went over to the other side, and stood on the top of a hill afar off, a great distance being between them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26014, 'And David called out to the people and to Abner the son of Ner, saying, &ldquo;Do you not answer, Abner?&rdquo; Then Abner answered and said, &ldquo;Who are you, calling out to the king?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26015, 'So David said to Abner, &ldquo;Are you not a man? And who is like you in Israel? Why then have you not guarded your lord the king? For one of the people came in to destroy your lord the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26016, 'This thing that you have done is not good. As the Lord lives, you deserve to die, because you have not guarded your master, the Lord&rsquo;s anointed. And now see where the king&rsquo;s spear is, and the jug of water that was by his head.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26017, 'Then Saul knew David&rsquo;s voice, and said, &ldquo;Is that your voice, my son David?&rdquo; And David said, &ldquo;It is my voice, my lord, O king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26018, 'And he said, &ldquo;Why does my lord thus pursue his servant? For what have I done, or what evil is in my hand? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26019, 'Now therefore, please, let my lord the king hear the words of his servant: If the Lord has stirred you up against me, let Him accept an offering. But if it is the children of men, may they be cursed before the Lord, for they have driven me out this day from sharing in the inheritance of the Lord, saying, &lsquo;Go, serve other gods.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26020, 'So now, do not let my blood fall to the earth before the face of the Lord. For the king of Israel has come out to seek a flea, as when one hunts a partridge in the mountains.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26021, 'Then Saul said, &ldquo;I have sinned. Return, my son David. For I will harm you no more, because my life was precious in your eyes this day. Indeed I have played the fool and erred exceedingly.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26022, 'And David answered and said, &ldquo;Here is the king&rsquo;s spear. Let one of the young men come over and get it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26023, 'May the Lord repay every man for his righteousness and his faithfulness; for the Lord delivered you into my hand today, but I would not stretch out my hand against the Lord&rsquo;s anointed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26024, 'And indeed, as your life was valued much this day in my eyes, so let my life be valued much in the eyes of the Lord, and let Him deliver me out of all tribulation.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 26025, 'Then Saul said to David, &ldquo;May you be blessed, my son David! You shall both do great things and also still prevail.&rdquo; So David went on his way, and Saul returned to his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27001, 'And David said in his heart, &ldquo;Now I shall perish someday by the hand of Saul. There is nothing better for me than that I should speedily escape to the land of the Philistines; and Saul will despair of me, to seek me anymore in any part of Israel. So I shall escape out of his hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27002, 'Then David arose and went over with the six hundred men who were with him to Achish the son of Maoch, king of Gath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27003, 'So David dwelt with Achish at Gath, he and his men, each man with his household, and David with his two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the Carmelitess, Nabal&rsquo;s widow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27004, 'And it was told Saul that David had fled to Gath; so he sought him no more. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27005, 'Then David said to Achish, &ldquo;If I have now found favor in your eyes, let them give me a place in some town in the country, that I may dwell there. For why should your servant dwell in the royal city with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27006, 'So Achish gave him Ziklag that day. Therefore Ziklag has belonged to the kings of Judah to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27007, 'Now the time that David dwelt in the country of the Philistines was one full year and four months. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27008, 'And David and his men went up and raided the Geshurites, the Girzites, and the Amalekites. For those nations were the inhabitants of the land from of old, as you go to Shur, even as far as the land of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27009, 'Whenever David attacked the land, he left neither man nor woman alive, but took away the sheep, the oxen, the donkeys, the camels, and the apparel, and returned and came to Achish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27010, 'Then Achish would say, &ldquo;Where have you made a raid today?&rdquo; And David would say, &ldquo;Against the southern area of Judah, or against the southern area of the Jerahmeelites, or against the southern area of the Kenites.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27011, 'David would save neither man nor woman alive, to bring news to Gath, saying, &ldquo;Lest they should inform on us, saying, &lsquo;Thus David did.&rsquo; &ldquo; And thus was his behavior all the time he dwelt in the country of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 27012, 'So Achish believed David, saying, &ldquo;He has made his people Israel utterly abhor him; therefore he will be my servant forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28001, 'Now it happened in those days that the Philistines gathered their armies together for war, to fight with Israel. And Achish said to David, &ldquo;You assuredly know that you will go out with me to battle, you and your men.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28002, 'And David said to Achish, &ldquo;Surely you know what your servant can do.&rdquo; And Achish said to David, &ldquo;Therefore I will make you one of my chief guardians forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28003, 'Now Samuel had died, and all Israel had lamented for him and buried him in Ramah, in his own city. And Saul had put the mediums and the spiritists out of the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28004, 'Then the Philistines gathered together, and came and encamped at Shunem. So Saul gathered all Israel together, and they encamped at Gilboa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28005, 'When Saul saw the army of the Philistines, he was afraid, and his heart trembled greatly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28006, 'And when Saul inquired of the Lord, the Lord did not answer him, either by dreams or by Urim or by the prophets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28007, 'Then Saul said to his servants, &ldquo;Find me a woman who is a medium, that I may go to her and inquire of her.&rdquo; And his servants said to him, &ldquo;In fact, there is a woman who is a medium at En Dor.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28008, 'So Saul disguised himself and put on other clothes, and he went, and two men with him; and they came to the woman by night. And he said, &ldquo;Please conduct a seance for me, and bring up for me the one I shall name to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28009, 'Then the woman said to him, &ldquo;Look, you know what Saul has done, how he has cut off the mediums and the spiritists from the land. Why then do you lay a snare for my life, to cause me to die?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28010, 'And Saul swore to her by the Lord, saying, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, no punishment shall come upon you for this thing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28011, 'Then the woman said, &ldquo;Whom shall I bring up for you?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Bring up Samuel for me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28012, 'When the woman saw Samuel, she cried out with a loud voice. And the woman spoke to Saul, saying, &ldquo;Why have you deceived me? For you are Saul!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28013, 'And the king said to her, &ldquo;Do not be afraid. What did you see?&rdquo; And the woman said to Saul, &ldquo;I saw a spirit ascending out of the earth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28014, 'So he said to her, &ldquo;What is his form?&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;An old man is coming up, and he is covered with a mantle.&rdquo; And Saul perceived that it was Samuel, and he stooped with his face to the ground and bowed down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28015, 'Now Samuel said to Saul, &ldquo;Why have you disturbed me by bringing me up?&rdquo; And Saul answered, &ldquo;I am deeply distressed; for the Philistines make war against me, and God has departed from me and does not answer me anymore, neither by prophets nor by dreams. Therefore I have called you, that you may reveal to me what I should do.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28016, 'Then Samuel said: &ldquo;Why then do you ask me, seeing the Lord has departed from you and has become your enemy? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28017, 'And the Lord has done for Himself as He spoke by me. For the Lord has torn the kingdom out of your hand and given it to your neighbor, David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28018, 'Because you did not obey the voice of the Lord nor execute His fierce wrath upon Amalek, therefore the Lord has done this thing to you this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28019, 'Moreover the Lord will also deliver Israel with you into the hand of the Philistines. And tomorrow you and your sons will be with me. The Lord will also deliver the army of Israel into the hand of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28020, 'Then immediately Saul fell full length on the ground, and was dreadfully afraid because of the words of Samuel. And there was no strength in him, for he had eaten no food all day or all night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28021, 'And the woman came to Saul and saw that he was severely troubled, and said to him, &ldquo;Look, your maidservant has obeyed your voice, and I have put my life in my hands and heeded the words which you spoke to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28022, 'Now therefore, please, heed also the voice of your maidservant, and let me set a piece of bread before you; and eat, that you may have strength when you go on your way.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28023, 'But he refused and said, &ldquo;I will not eat.&rdquo; So his servants, together with the woman, urged him; and he heeded their voice. Then he arose from the ground and sat on the bed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28024, 'Now the woman had a fatted calf in the house, and she hastened to kill it. And she took flour and kneaded it, and baked unleavened bread from it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 28025, 'So she brought it before Saul and his servants, and they ate. Then they rose and went away that night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29001, 'Then the Philistines gathered together all their armies at Aphek, and the Israelites encamped by a fountain which is in Jezreel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29002, 'And the lords of the Philistines passed in review by hundreds and by thousands, but David and his men passed in review at the rear with Achish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29003, 'Then the princes of the Philistines said, &ldquo;What are these Hebrews doing here?&rdquo; And Achish said to the princes of the Philistines, &ldquo;Is this not David, the servant of Saul king of Israel, who has been with me these days, or these years? And to this day I have found no fault in him since he defected to me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29004, 'But the princes of the Philistines were angry with him; so the princes of the Philistines said to him, &ldquo;Make this fellow return, that he may go back to the place which you have appointed for him, and do not let him go down with us to battle, lest in the battle he become our adversary. For with what could he reconcile himself to his master, if not with the heads of these men? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29005, 'Is this not David, of whom they sang to one another in dances, saying: &lsquo;Saul has slain his thousands, And David his ten thousands&rsquo;?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29006, 'Then Achish called David and said to him, &ldquo;Surely, as the Lord lives, you have been upright, and your going out and your coming in with me in the army is good in my sight. For to this day I have not found evil in you since the day of your coming to me. Nevertheless the lords do not favor you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29007, 'Therefore return now, and go in peace, that you may not displease the lords of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29008, 'So David said to Achish, &ldquo;But what have I done? And to this day what have you found in your servant as long as I have been with you, that I may not go and fight against the enemies of my lord the king?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29009, 'Then Achish answered and said to David, &ldquo;I know that you are as good in my sight as an angel of God; nevertheless the princes of the Philistines have said, &lsquo;He shall not go up with us to the battle.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29010, 'Now therefore, rise early in the morning with your master&rsquo;s servants who have come with you. And as soon as you are up early in the morning and have light, depart.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 29011, 'So David and his men rose early to depart in the morning, to return to the land of the Philistines. And the Philistines went up to Jezreel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30001, 'Now it happened, when David and his men came to Ziklag, on the third day, that the Amalekites had invaded the South and Ziklag, attacked Ziklag and burned it with fire, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30002, 'and had taken captive the women and those who were there, from small to great; they did not kill anyone, but carried them away and went their way. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30003, 'So David and his men came to the city, and there it was, burned with fire; and their wives, their sons, and their daughters had been taken captive. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30004, 'Then David and the people who were with him lifted up their voices and wept, until they had no more power to weep. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30005, 'And David&rsquo;s two wives, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite, had been taken captive. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30006, 'Now David was greatly distressed, for the people spoke of stoning him, because the soul of all the people was grieved, every man for his sons and his daughters. But David strengthened himself in the Lord his God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30007, 'Then David said to Abiathar the priest, Ahimelech&rsquo;s son, &ldquo;Please bring the ephod here to me.&rdquo; And Abiathar brought the ephod to David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30008, 'So David inquired of the Lord, saying, &ldquo;Shall I pursue this troop? Shall I overtake them?&rdquo; And He answered him, &ldquo;Pursue, for you shall surely overtake them and without fail recover all.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30009, 'So David went, he and the six hundred men who were with him, and came to the Brook Besor, where those stayed who were left behind. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30010, 'But David pursued, he and four hundred men; for two hundred stayed behind, who were so weary that they could not cross the Brook Besor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30011, 'Then they found an Egyptian in the field, and brought him to David; and they gave him bread and he ate, and they let him drink water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30012, 'And they gave him a piece of a cake of figs and two clusters of raisins. So when he had eaten, his strength came back to him; for he had eaten no bread nor drunk water for three days and three nights. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30013, 'Then David said to him, &ldquo;To whom do you belong, and where are you from?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;I am a young man from Egypt, servant of an Amalekite; and my master left me behind, because three days ago I fell sick. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30014, 'We made an invasion of the southern area of the Cherethites, in the territory which belongs to Judah, and of the southern area of Caleb; and we burned Ziklag with fire.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30015, 'And David said to him, &ldquo;Can you take me down to this troop?&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Swear to me by God that you will neither kill me nor deliver me into the hands of my master, and I will take you down to this troop.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30016, 'And when he had brought him down, there they were, spread out over all the land, eating and drinking and dancing, because of all the great spoil which they had taken from the land of the Philistines and from the land of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30017, 'Then David attacked them from twilight until the evening of the next day. Not a man of them escaped, except four hundred young men who rode on camels and fled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30018, 'So David recovered all that the Amalekites had carried away, and David rescued his two wives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30019, 'And nothing of theirs was lacking, either small or great, sons or daughters, spoil or anything which they had taken from them; David recovered all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30020, 'Then David took all the flocks and herds they had driven before those other livestock, and said, &ldquo;This is David&rsquo;s spoil.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30021, 'Now David came to the two hundred men who had been so weary that they could not follow David, whom they also had made to stay at the Brook Besor. So they went out to meet David and to meet the people who were with him. And when David came near the people, he greeted them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30022, 'Then all the wicked and worthless men of those who went with David answered and said, &ldquo;Because they did not go with us, we will not give them any of the spoil that we have recovered, except for every man&rsquo;s wife and children, that they may lead them away and depart.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30023, 'But David said, &ldquo;My brethren, you shall not do so with what the Lord has given us, who has preserved us and delivered into our hand the troop that came against us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30024, 'For who will heed you in this matter? But as his part is who goes down to the battle, so shall his part be who stays by the supplies; they shall share alike.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30025, 'So it was, from that day forward; he made it a statute and an ordinance for Israel to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30026, 'Now when David came to Ziklag, he sent some of the spoil to the elders of Judah, to his friends, saying, &ldquo;Here is a present for you from the spoil of the enemies of the Lord&rdquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30027, 'to those who were in Bethel, those who were in Ramoth of the South, those who were in Jattir, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30028, 'those who were in Aroer, those who were in Siphmoth, those who were in Eshtemoa, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30029, 'those who were in Rachal, those who were in the cities of the Jerahmeelites, those who were in the cities of the Kenites, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30030, 'those who were in Hormah, those who were in Chorashan, those who were in Athach, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 30031, 'those who were in Hebron, and to all the places where David himself and his men were accustomed to rove. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31001, 'Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel fled from before the Philistines, and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31002, 'Then the Philistines followed hard after Saul and his sons. And the Philistines killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malchishua, Saul&rsquo;s sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31003, 'The battle became fierce against Saul. The archers hit him, and he was severely wounded by the archers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31004, 'Then Saul said to his armorbearer, &ldquo;Draw your sword, and thrust me through with it, lest these uncircumcised men come and thrust me through and abuse me.&rdquo; But his armorbearer would not, for he was greatly afraid. Therefore Saul took a sword and fell on it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31005, 'And when his armorbearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on his sword, and died with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31006, 'So Saul, his three sons, his armorbearer, and all his men died together that same day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31007, 'And when the men of Israel who were on the other side of the valley, and those who were on the other side of the Jordan, saw that the men of Israel had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they forsook the cities and fled; and the Philistines came and dwelt in them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31008, 'So it happened the next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, that they found Saul and his three sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31009, 'And they cut off his head and stripped off his armor, and sent word throughout the land of the Philistines, to proclaim it in the temple of their idols and among the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31010, 'Then they put his armor in the temple of the Ashtoreths, and they fastened his body to the wall of Beth Shan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31011, 'Now when the inhabitants of Jabesh Gilead heard what the Philistines had done to Saul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31012, 'all the valiant men arose and traveled all night, and took the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons from the wall of Beth Shan; and they came to Jabesh and burned them there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Kg', 31013, 'Then they took their bones and buried them under the tamarisk tree at Jabesh, and fasted seven days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1001, 'Now it came to pass after the death of Saul, when David had returned from the slaughter of the Amalekites, and David had stayed two days in Ziklag, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1002, 'on the third day, behold, it happened that a man came from Saul&rsquo;s camp with his clothes torn and dust on his head. So it was, when he came to David, that he fell to the ground and prostrated himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1003, 'And David said to him, &ldquo;Where have you come from?&rdquo; So he said to him, &ldquo;I have escaped from the camp of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1004, 'Then David said to him, &ldquo;How did the matter go? Please tell me.&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;The people have fled from the battle, many of the people are fallen and dead, and Saul and Jonathan his son are dead also.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1005, 'So David said to the young man who told him, &ldquo;How do you know that Saul and Jonathan his son are dead?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1006, 'Then the young man who told him said, &ldquo;As I happened by chance to be on Mount Gilboa, there was Saul, leaning on his spear; and indeed the chariots and horsemen followed hard after him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1007, 'Now when he looked behind him, he saw me and called to me. And I answered, &lsquo;Here I am.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1008, 'And he said to me, &lsquo;Who are you?&rsquo; So I answered him, &lsquo;I am an Amalekite.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1009, 'He said to me again, &lsquo;Please stand over me and kill me, for anguish has come upon me, but my life still remains in me.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1010, 'So I stood over him and killed him, because I was sure that he could not live after he had fallen. And I took the crown that was on his head and the bracelet that was on his arm, and have brought them here to my lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1011, 'Therefore David took hold of his own clothes and tore them, and so did all the men who were with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1012, 'And they mourned and wept and fasted until evening for Saul and for Jonathan his son, for the people of the Lord and for the house of Israel, because they had fallen by the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1013, 'Then David said to the young man who told him, &ldquo;Where are you from?&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;I am the son of an alien, an Amalekite.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1014, 'So David said to him, &ldquo;How was it you were not afraid to put forth your hand to destroy the Lord&rsquo;s anointed?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1015, 'Then David called one of the young men and said, &ldquo;Go near, and execute him!&rdquo; And he struck him so that he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1016, 'So David said to him, &ldquo;Your blood is on your own head, for your own mouth has testified against you, saying, &lsquo;I have killed the Lord&rsquo;s anointed.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1017, 'Then David lamented with this lamentation over Saul and over Jonathan his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1018, 'and he told them to teach the children of Judah the Song of the Bow; indeed it is written in the Book of Jasher: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1019, 'The beauty of Israel is slain on your high places! How the mighty have fallen! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1020, 'Tell it not in Gath, Proclaim it not in the streets of Ashkelon &ndash; Lest the daughters of the Philistines rejoice, Lest the daughters of the uncircumcised triumph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1021, 'O mountains of Gilboa, Let there be no dew nor rain upon you, Nor fields of offerings. For the shield of the mighty is cast away there! The shield of Saul, not anointed with oil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1022, 'From the blood of the slain, From the fat of the mighty, The bow of Jonathan did not turn back, And the sword of Saul did not return empty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1023, 'Saul and Jonathan were beloved and pleasant in their lives, And in their death they were not divided; They were swifter than eagles, They were stronger than lions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1024, 'O daughters of Israel, weep over Saul, Who clothed you in scarlet, with luxury; Who put ornaments of gold on your apparel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1025, 'How the mighty have fallen in the midst of the battle! Jonathan was slain in your high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1026, 'I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan; You have been very pleasant to me; Your love to me was wonderful, Surpassing the love of women. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 1027, 'How the mighty have fallen, And the weapons of war perished! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2001, 'It happened after this that David inquired of the Lord, saying, Shall I go up to any of the cities of Judah? And the Lord said to him, Go up. David said, Where shall I go up? And He said, To Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2002, 'So David went up there, and his two wives also, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess, and Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2003, 'And David brought up the men who were with him, every man with his household. So they dwelt in the cities of Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2004, 'Then the men of Judah came, and there they anointed David king over the house of Judah. And they told David, saying, The men of Jabesh Gilead were the ones who buried Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2005, 'So David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh Gilead, and said to them, You are blessed of the Lord, for you have shown this kindness to your lord, to Saul, and have buried him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2006, 'And now may the Lord show kindness and truth to you. I also will repay you this kindness, because you have done this thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2007, 'Now therefore, let your hands be strengthened, and be valiant; for your master Saul is dead, and also the house of Judah has anointed me king over them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2008, 'But Abner the son of Ner, commander of Saul&rsquo;s army, took Ishbosheth the son of Saul and brought him over to Mahanaim; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2009, 'and he made him king over Gilead, over the Ashurites, over Jezreel, over Ephraim, over Benjamin, and over all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2010, 'Ishbosheth, Saul&rsquo;s son, was forty years old when he began to reign over Israel, and he reigned two years. Only the house of Judah followed David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2011, 'And the time that David was king in Hebron over the house of Judah was seven years and six months. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2012, 'Now Abner the son of Ner, and the servants of Ishbosheth the son of Saul, went out from Mahanaim to Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2013, 'And Joab the son of Zeruiah, and the servants of David, went out and met them by the pool of Gibeon. So they sat down, one on one side of the pool and the other on the other side of the pool. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2014, 'Then Abner said to Joab, &ldquo;Let the young men now arise and compete before us.&rdquo; And Joab said, &ldquo;Let them arise.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2015, 'So they arose and went over by number, twelve from Benjamin, followers of Ishbosheth the son of Saul, and twelve from the servants of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2016, 'And each one grasped his opponent by the head and thrust his sword in his opponent&rsquo;s side; so they fell down together. Therefore that place was called the Field of Sharp Swords, which is in Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2017, 'So there was a very fierce battle that day, and Abner and the men of Israel were beaten before the servants of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2018, 'Now the three sons of Zeruiah were there: Joab and Abishai and Asahel. And Asahel was as fleet of foot as a wild gazelle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2019, 'So Asahel pursued Abner, and in going he did not turn to the right hand or to the left from following Abner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2020, 'Then Abner looked behind him and said, &ldquo;Are you Asahel?&rdquo; He answered, &ldquo;I am.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2021, 'And Abner said to him, &ldquo;Turn aside to your right hand or to your left, and lay hold on one of the young men and take his armor for yourself.&rdquo; But Asahel would not turn aside from following him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2022, 'So Abner said again to Asahel, &ldquo;Turn aside from following me. Why should I strike you to the ground? How then could I face your brother Joab?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2023, 'However, he refused to turn aside. Therefore Abner struck him in the stomach with the blunt end of the spear, so that the spear came out of his back; and he fell down there and died on the spot. So it was that as many as came to the place where Asahel fell down and died, stood still. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2024, 'Joab and Abishai also pursued Abner. And the sun was going down when they came to the hill of Ammah, which is before Giah by the road to the Wilderness of Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2025, 'Now the children of Benjamin gathered together behind Abner and became a unit, and took their stand on top of a hill. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2026, 'Then Abner called to Joab and said, &ldquo;Shall the sword devour forever? Do you not know that it will be bitter in the latter end? How long will it be then until you tell the people to return from pursuing their brethren?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2027, 'And Joab said, &ldquo;As God lives, unless you had spoken, surely then by morning all the people would have given up pursuing their brethren.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2028, 'So Joab blew a trumpet; and all the people stood still and did not pursue Israel anymore, nor did they fight anymore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2029, 'Then Abner and his men went on all that night through the plain, crossed over the Jordan, and went through all Bithron; and they came to Mahanaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2030, 'So Joab returned from pursuing Abner. And when he had gathered all the people together, there were missing of David&rsquo;s servants nineteen men and Asahel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2031, 'But the servants of David had struck down, of Benjamin and Abner&rsquo;s men, three hundred and sixty men who died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 2032, 'Then they took up Asahel and buried him in his father&rsquo;s tomb, which was in Bethlehem. And Joab and his men went all night, and they came to Hebron at daybreak. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3001, 'Now there was a long war between the house of Saul and the house of David. But David grew stronger and stronger, and the house of Saul grew weaker and weaker. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3002, 'Sons were born to David in Hebron: His firstborn was Amnon by Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3003, 'his second, Chileab, by Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite; the third, Absalom the son of Maacah, the daughter of Talmai, king of Geshur; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3004, 'the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith; the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3005, 'and the sixth, Ithream, by David&rsquo;s wife Eglah. These were born to David in Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3006, 'Now it was so, while there was war between the house of Saul and the house of David, that Abner was strengthening his hold on the house of Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3007, 'And Saul had a concubine, whose name was Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah. So Ishbosheth said to Abner, &ldquo;Why have you gone in to my father&rsquo;s concubine?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3008, 'Then Abner became very angry at the words of Ishbosheth, and said, &ldquo;Am I a dog&rsquo;s head that belongs to Judah? Today I show loyalty to the house of Saul your father, to his brothers, and to his friends, and have not delivered you into the hand of David; and you charge me today with a fault concerning this woman? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3009, 'May God do so to Abner, and more also, if I do not do for David as the Lord has sworn to him &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3010, 'to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul, and set up the throne of David over Israel and over Judah, from Dan to Beersheba.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3011, 'And he could not answer Abner another word, because he feared him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3012, 'Then Abner sent messengers on his behalf to David, saying, &ldquo;Whose is the land?&rdquo; saying also, &ldquo;Make your covenant with me, and indeed my hand shall be with you to bring all Israel to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3013, 'And David said, &ldquo;Good, I will make a covenant with you. But one thing I require of you: you shall not see my face unless you first bring Michal, Saul&rsquo;s daughter, when you come to see my face.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3014, 'So David sent messengers to Ishbosheth, Saul&rsquo;s son, saying, &ldquo;Give me my wife Michal, whom I betrothed to myself for a hundred foreskins of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3015, 'And Ishbosheth sent and took her from her husband, from Paltiel the son of Laish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3016, 'Then her husband went along with her to Bahurim, weeping behind her. So Abner said to him, &ldquo;Go, return!&rdquo; And he returned. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3017, 'Now Abner had communicated with the elders of Israel, saying, &ldquo;In time past you were seeking for David to be king over you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3018, 'Now then, do it! For the Lord has spoken of David, saying, &lsquo;By the hand of My servant David, I will save My people Israel from the hand of the Philistines and the hand of all their enemies.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3019, 'And Abner also spoke in the hearing of Benjamin. Then Abner also went to speak in the hearing of David in Hebron all that seemed good to Israel and the whole house of Benjamin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3020, 'So Abner and twenty men with him came to David at Hebron. And David made a feast for Abner and the men who were with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3021, 'Then Abner said to David, &ldquo;I will arise and go, and gather all Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant with you, and that you may reign over all that your heart desires.&rdquo; So David sent Abner away, and he went in peace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3022, 'At that moment the servants of David and Joab came from a raid and brought much spoil with them. But Abner was not with David in Hebron, for he had sent him away, and he had gone in peace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3023, 'When Joab and all the troops that were with him had come, they told Joab, saying, &ldquo;Abner the son of Ner came to the king, and he sent him away, and he has gone in peace.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3024, 'Then Joab came to the king and said, &ldquo;What have you done? Look, Abner came to you; why is it that you sent him away, and he has already gone? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3025, 'Surely you realize that Abner the son of Ner came to deceive you, to know your going out and your coming in, and to know all that you are doing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3026, 'And when Joab had gone from David&rsquo;s presence, he sent messengers after Abner, who brought him back from the well of Sirah. But David did not know it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3027, 'Now when Abner had returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside in the gate to speak with him privately, and there stabbed him in the stomach, so that he died for the blood of Asahel his brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3028, 'Afterward, when David heard it, he said, &ldquo;My kingdom and I are guiltless before the Lord forever of the blood of Abner the son of Ner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3029, 'Let it rest on the head of Joab and on all his father&rsquo;s house; and let there never fail to be in the house of Joab one who has a discharge or is a leper, who leans on a staff or falls by the sword, or who lacks bread.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3030, 'So Joab and Abishai his brother killed Abner, because he had killed their brother Asahel at Gibeon in the battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3031, 'Then David said to Joab and to all the people who were with him, &ldquo;Tear your clothes, gird yourselves with sackcloth, and mourn for Abner.&rdquo; And King David followed the coffin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3032, 'So they buried Abner in Hebron; and the king lifted up his voice and wept at the grave of Abner, and all the people wept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3033, 'And the king sang a lament over Abner and said: &ldquo;Should Abner die as a fool dies? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3034, 'Your hands were not bound Nor your feet put into fetters; As a man falls before wicked men, so you fell.&rdquo; Then all the people wept over him again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3035, 'And when all the people came to persuade David to eat food while it was still day, David took an oath, saying, &ldquo;God do so to me, and more also, if I taste bread or anything else till the sun goes down!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3036, 'Now all the people took note of it, and it pleased them, since whatever the king did pleased all the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3037, 'For all the people and all Israel understood that day that it had not been the king&rsquo;s intent to kill Abner the son of Ner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3038, 'Then the king said to his servants, &ldquo;Do you not know that a prince and a great man has fallen this day in Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 3039, 'And I am weak today, though anointed king; and these men, the sons of Zeruiah, are too harsh for me. The Lord shall repay the evildoer according to his wickedness.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4001, 'When Saul&rsquo;s son* heard that Abner had died in Hebron, he lost heart, and all Israel was troubled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4002, 'Now Saul&rsquo;s son had two men who were captains of troops. The name of one was Baanah and the name of the other Rechab, the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, of the children of Benjamin. (For Beeroth also was part of Benjamin, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4003, 'because the Beerothites fled to Gittaim and have been sojourners there until this day.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4004, 'Jonathan, Saul&rsquo;s son, had a son who was lame in his feet. He was five years old when the news about Saul and Jonathan came from Jezreel; and his nurse took him up and fled. And it happened, as she made haste to flee, that he fell and became lame. His name was Mephibosheth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4005, 'Then the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, set out and came at about the heat of the day to the house of Ishbosheth, who was lying on his bed at noon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4006, 'And they came there, all the way into the house, as though to get wheat, and they stabbed him in the stomach. Then Rechab and Baanah his brother escaped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4007, 'For when they came into the house, he was lying on his bed in his bedroom; then they struck him and killed him, beheaded him and took his head, and were all night escaping through the plain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4008, 'And they brought the head of Ishbosheth to David at Hebron, and said to the king, &ldquo;Here is the head of Ishbosheth, the son of Saul your enemy, who sought your life; and the Lord has avenged my lord the king this day of Saul and his descendants.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4009, 'But David answered Rechab and Baanah his brother, the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, and said to them, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, who has redeemed my life from all adversity, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4010, 'when someone told me, saying, &lsquo;Look, Saul is dead,&rsquo; thinking to have brought good news, I arrested him and had him executed in Ziklag &ndash; the one who thought I would give him a reward for his news. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4011, 'How much more, when wicked men have killed a righteous person in his own house on his bed? Therefore, shall I not now require his blood at your hand and remove you from the earth?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 4012, 'So David commanded his young men, and they executed them, cut off their hands and feet, and hanged them by the pool in Hebron. But they took the head of Ishbosheth and buried it in the tomb of Abner in Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5001, 'Then all the tribes of Israel came to David at Hebron and spoke, saying, &ldquo;Indeed we are your bone and your flesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5002, 'Also, in time past, when Saul was king over us, you were the one who led Israel out and brought them in; and the Lord said to you, &lsquo;You shall shepherd My people Israel, and be ruler over Israel.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5003, 'Therefore all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and King David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the Lord. And they anointed David king over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5004, 'David was thirty years old when he began to reign, and he reigned forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5005, 'In Hebron he reigned over Judah seven years and six months, and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years over all Israel and Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5006, 'And the king and his men went to Jerusalem against the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, who spoke to David, saying, &ldquo;You shall not come in here; but the blind and the lame will repel you,&rdquo; thinking, &ldquo;David cannot come in here.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5007, 'Nevertheless David took the stronghold of Zion (that is, the City of David). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5008, 'Now David said on that day, &ldquo;Whoever climbs up by way of the water shaft and defeats the Jebusites (the lame and the blind, who are hated by David&rsquo;s soul), he shall be chief and captain.&rdquo; Therefore they say, &ldquo;The blind and the lame shall not come into the house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5009, 'Then David dwelt in the stronghold, and called it the City of David. And David built all around from the Millo and inward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5010, 'So David went on and became great, and the Lord God of hosts was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5011, 'Then Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, and carpenters and masons. And they built David a house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5012, 'So David knew that the Lord had established him as king over Israel, and that He had exalted His kingdom for the sake of His people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5013, 'And David took more concubines and wives from Jerusalem, after he had come from Hebron. Also more sons and daughters were born to David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5014, 'Now these are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5015, 'Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5016, 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5017, 'Now when the Philistines heard that they had anointed David king over Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. And David heard of it and went down to the stronghold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5018, 'The Philistines also went and deployed themselves in the Valley of Rephaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5019, 'So David inquired of the Lord, saying, &ldquo;Shall I go up against the Philistines? Will You deliver them into my hand?&rdquo; And the Lord said to David, &ldquo;Go up, for I will doubtless deliver the Philistines into your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5020, 'So David went to Baal Perazim, and David defeated them there; and he said, &ldquo;The Lord has broken through my enemies before me, like a breakthrough of water.&rdquo; Therefore he called the name of that place Baal Perazim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5021, 'And they left their images there, and David and his men carried them away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5022, 'Then the Philistines went up once again and deployed themselves in the Valley of Rephaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5023, 'Therefore David inquired of the Lord, and He said, &ldquo;You shall not go up; circle around behind them, and come upon them in front of the mulberry trees. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5024, 'And it shall be, when you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the mulberry trees, then you shall advance quickly. For then the Lord will go out before you to strike the camp of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 5025, 'And David did so, as the Lord commanded him; and he drove back the Philistines from Geba as far as Gezer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6001, 'Again David gathered all the choice men of Israel, thirty thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6002, 'And David arose and went with all the people who were with him from Baale Judah to bring up from there the ark of God, whose name is called by the Name, the Lord of Hosts, who dwells between the cherubim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6003, 'So they set the ark of God on a new cart, and brought it out of the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill; and Uzzah and Ahio, the sons of Abinadab, drove the new cart.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6004, 'And they brought it out of the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill, accompanying the ark of God; and Ahio went before the ark. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6005, 'Then David and all the house of Israel played music before the Lord on all kinds of instruments of fir wood, on harps, on stringed instruments, on tambourines, on sistrums, and on cymbals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6006, 'And when they came to Nachon&rsquo;s threshing floor, Uzzah put out his hand to the ark of God and took hold of it, for the oxen stumbled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6007, 'Then the anger of the Lord was aroused against Uzzah, and God struck him there for his error; and he died there by the ark of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6008, 'And David became angry because of the Lord&rsquo;s outbreak against Uzzah; and he called the name of the place Perez Uzzah to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6009, 'David was afraid of the Lord that day; and he said, &ldquo;How can the ark of the Lord come to me?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6010, 'So David would not move the ark of the Lord with him into the City of David; but David took it aside into the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6011, 'The ark of the Lord remained in the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite three months. And the Lord blessed Obed-Edom and all his household. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6012, 'Now it was told King David, saying, &ldquo;The Lord has blessed the house of Obed-Edom and all that belongs to him, because of the ark of God.&rdquo; So David went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obed-Edom to the City of David with gladness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6013, 'And so it was, when those bearing the ark of the Lord had gone six paces, that he sacrificed oxen and fatted sheep. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6014, 'Then David danced before the Lord with all his might; and David was wearing a linen ephod. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6015, 'So David and all the house of Israel brought up the ark of the Lord with shouting and with the sound of the trumpet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6016, 'Now as the ark of the Lord came into the City of David, Michal, Saul&rsquo;s daughter, looked through a window and saw King David leaping and whirling before the Lord; and she despised him in her heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6017, 'So they brought the ark of the Lord, and set it in its place in the midst of the tabernacle that David had erected for it. Then David offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6018, 'And when David had finished offering burnt offerings and peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the Lord of hosts. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6019, 'Then he distributed among all the people, among the whole multitude of Israel, both the women and the men, to everyone a loaf of bread, a piece of meat, and a cake of raisins. So all the people departed, everyone to his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6020, 'Then David returned to bless his household. And Michal the daughter of Saul came out to meet David, and said, &ldquo;How glorious was the king of Israel today, uncovering himself today in the eyes of the maids of his servants, as one of the base fellows shamelessly uncovers himself!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6021, 'So David said to Michal, &ldquo;It was before the Lord, who chose me instead of your father and all his house, to appoint me ruler over the people of the Lord, over Israel. Therefore I will play music before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6022, 'And I will be even more undignified than this, and will be humble in my own sight. But as for the maidservants of whom you have spoken, by them I will be held in honor.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 6023, 'Therefore Michal the daughter of Saul had no children to the day of her death. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7001, 'Now it came to pass when the king was dwelling in his house, and the Lord had given him rest from all his enemies all around, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7002, 'that the king said to Nathan the prophet, &ldquo;See now, I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of God dwells inside tent curtains.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7003, 'Then Nathan said to the king, &ldquo;Go, do all that is in your heart, for the Lord is with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7004, 'But it happened that night that the word of the Lord came to Nathan, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7005, 'Go and tell My servant David, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: Would you build a house for Me to dwell in? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7006, 'For I have not dwelt in a house since the time that I brought the children of Israel up from Egypt, even to this day, but have moved about in a tent and in a tabernacle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7007, 'Wherever I have moved about with all the children of Israel, have I ever spoken a word to anyone from the tribes of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd My people Israel, saying, &lsquo;Why have you not built Me a house of cedar?&rsquo; &ldquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7008, 'Now therefore, thus shall you say to My servant David, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord of hosts: &ldquo;I took you from the sheepfold, from following the sheep, to be ruler over My people, over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7009, 'And I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off all your enemies from before you, and have made you a great name, like the name of the great men who are on the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7010, 'Moreover I will appoint a place for My people Israel, and will plant them, that they may dwell in a place of their own and move no more; nor shall the sons of wickedness oppress them anymore, as previously, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7011, 'since the time that I commanded judges to be over My people Israel, and have caused you to rest from all your enemies. Also the Lord tells you that He will make you a house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7012, 'When your days are fulfilled and you rest with your fathers, I will set up your seed after you, who will come from your body, and I will establish his kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7013, 'He shall build a house for My name, and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7014, 'I will be his Father, and he shall be My son. If he commits iniquity, I will chasten him with the rod of men and with the blows of the sons of men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7015, 'But My mercy shall not depart from him, as I took it from Saul, whom I removed from before you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7016, 'And your house and your kingdom shall be established forever before you. Your throne shall be established forever. &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7017, 'According to all these words and according to all this vision, so Nathan spoke to David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7018, 'Then King David went in and sat before the Lord; and he said: Who am I, O Lord God? And what is my house, that You have brought me this far? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7019, 'And yet this was a small thing in Your sight, O Lord God; and You have also spoken of Your servant&rsquo;s house for a great while to come. Is this the manner of man, O Lord God? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7020, 'Now what more can David say to You? For You, Lord God, know Your servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7021, 'For Your word&rsquo;s sake, and according to Your own heart, You have done all these great things, to make Your servant know them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7022, 'Therefore You are great, O Lord God. For there is none like You, nor is there any God besides You, according to all that we have heard with our ears. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7023, 'And who is like Your people, like Israel, the one nation on the earth whom God went to redeem for Himself as a people, to make for Himself a name &ndash; and to do for Yourself great and awesome deeds for Your land &ndash; before Your people whom You redeemed for Yourself from Egypt, the nations, and their gods? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7024, 'For You have made Your people Israel Your very own people forever; and You, Lord, have become their God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7025, 'Now, O Lord God, the word which You have spoken concerning Your servant and concerning his house, establish it forever and do as You have said. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7026, 'So let Your name be magnified forever, saying, &lsquo;The Lord of hosts is the God over Israel.&rsquo; And let the house of Your servant David be established before You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7027, 'For You, O Lord of hosts, God of Israel, have revealed this to Your servant, saying, &lsquo;I will build you a house.&rsquo; Therefore Your servant has found it in his heart to pray this prayer to You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7028, 'And now, O Lord God, You are God, and Your words are true, and You have promised this goodness to Your servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 7029, 'Now therefore, let it please You to bless the house of Your servant, that it may continue forever before You; for You, O Lord God, have spoken it, and with Your blessing let the house of Your servant be blessed forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8001, 'After this it came to pass that David attacked the Philistines and subdued them. And David took Metheg Ammah from the hand of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8002, 'Then he defeated Moab. Forcing them down to the ground, he measured them off with a line. With two lines he measured off those to be put to death, and with one full line those to be kept alive. So the Moabites became David&rsquo;s servants, and brought tribute. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8003, 'David also defeated Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah, as he went to recover his territory at the River Euphrates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8004, 'David took from him one thousand chariots, seven hundred horsemen, and twenty thousand foot soldiers. Also David hamstrung all the chariot horses, except that he spared enough of them for one hundred chariots. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8005, 'When the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah, David killed twenty-two thousand of the Syrians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8006, 'Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians became David&rsquo;s servants, and brought tribute. The Lord preserved David wherever he went. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8007, 'And David took the shields of gold that had belonged to the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8008, 'Also from Betah and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, King David took a large amount of bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8009, 'When Toi king of Hamath heard that David had defeated all the army of Hadadezer, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8010, 'then Toi sent Joram his son to King David, to greet him and bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him (for Hadadezer had been at war with Toi); and Joram brought with him articles of silver, articles of gold, and articles of bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8011, 'King David also dedicated these to the Lord, along with the silver and gold that he had dedicated from all the nations which he had subdued &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8012, 'from Syria, from Moab, from the people of Ammon, from the Philistines, from Amalek, and from the spoil of Hadadezer the son of Rehob, king of Zobah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8013, 'And David made himself a name when he returned from killing eighteen thousand Syrians in the Valley of Salt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8014, 'He also put garrisons in Edom; throughout all Edom he put garrisons, and all the Edomites became David&rsquo;s servants. And the Lord preserved David wherever he went. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8015, 'So David reigned over all Israel; and David administered judgment and justice to all his people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8016, 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8017, 'Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar were the priests; Seraiah was the scribe; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 8018, 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over both the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and David&rsquo;s sons were chief ministers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9001, 'And there was a servant of the house of Saul whose name was Ziba. So when they had called him to David, the king said to him, &ldquo;Are you Ziba?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;At your service!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9002, 'Then the king said, &ldquo;Is there not still someone of the house of Saul, to whom I may show the kindness of God?&rdquo; And Ziba said to the king, &ldquo;There is still a son of Jonathan who is lame in his feet.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9003, 'So the king said to him, &ldquo;Where is he?&rdquo; And Ziba said to the king, &ldquo;Indeed he is in the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, in Lo Debar.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9004, 'Then King David sent and brought him out of the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, from Lo Debar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9005, 'Now when Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, had come to David, he fell on his face and prostrated himself. Then David said, &ldquo;Mephibosheth?&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;Here is your servant!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9006, 'So David said to him, &ldquo;Do not fear, for I will surely show you kindness for Jonathan your father&rsquo;s sake, and will restore to you all the land of Saul your grandfather; and you shall eat bread at my table continually.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9007, 'Then he bowed himself, and said, &ldquo;What is your servant, that you should look upon such a dead dog as I?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9008, 'And the king called to Ziba, Saul&rsquo;s servant, and said to him, &ldquo;I have given to your master&rsquo;s son all that belonged to Saul and to all his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9009, 'You therefore, and your sons and your servants, shall work the land for him, and you shall bring in the harvest, that your master&rsquo;s son may have food to eat. But Mephibosheth your master&rsquo;s son shall eat bread at my table always.&rdquo; Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9010, 'Then Ziba said to the king, &ldquo;According to all that my lord the king has commanded his servant, so will your servant do.&rdquo; &ldquo;As for Mephibosheth,&rdquo; said the king, &ldquo;he shall eat at my table like one of the king&rsquo;s sons.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9011, 'Mephibosheth had a young son whose name was Micha. And all who dwelt in the house of Ziba were servants of Mephibosheth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 9012, 'So Mephibosheth dwelt in Jerusalem, for he ate continually at the king&rsquo;s table. And he was lame in both his feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10001, 'It happened after this that the king of the people of Ammon died, and Hanun his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10002, 'Then David said, &ldquo;I will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash, as his father showed kindness to me.&rdquo; So David sent by the hand of his servants to comfort him concerning his father. And David&rsquo;s servants came into the land of the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10003, 'And the princes of the people of Ammon said to Hanun their lord, &ldquo;Do you think that David really honors your father because he has sent comforters to you? Has David not rather sent his servants to you to search the city, to spy it out, and to overthrow it?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10004, 'Therefore Hanun took David&rsquo;s servants, shaved off half of their beards, cut off their garments in the middle, at their buttocks, and sent them away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10005, 'When they told David, he sent to meet them, because the men were greatly ashamed. And the king said, &ldquo;Wait at Jericho until your beards have grown, and then return.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10006, 'When the people of Ammon saw that they had made themselves repulsive to David, the people of Ammon sent and hired the Syrians of Beth Rehob and the Syrians of Zoba, twenty thousand foot soldiers; and from the king of Maacah one thousand men, and from Ish-Tob twelve thousand men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10007, 'Now when David heard of it, he sent Joab and all the army of the mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10008, 'Then the people of Ammon came out and put themselves in battle array at the entrance of the gate. And the Syrians of Zoba, Beth Rehob, Ish-Tob, and Maacah were by themselves in the field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10009, 'When Joab saw that the battle line was against him before and behind, he chose some of Israel&rsquo;s best and put them in battle array against the Syrians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10010, 'And the rest of the people he put under the command of Abishai his brother, that he might set them in battle array against the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10011, 'Then he said, &ldquo;If the Syrians are too strong for me, then you shall help me; but if the people of Ammon are too strong for you, then I will come and help you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10012, 'Be of good courage, and let us be strong for our people and for the cities of our God. And may the Lord do what is good in His sight.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10013, 'So Joab and the people who were with him drew near for the battle against the Syrians, and they fled before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10014, 'When the people of Ammon saw that the Syrians were fleeing, they also fled before Abishai, and entered the city. So Joab returned from the people of Ammon and went to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10015, 'When the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they gathered together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10016, 'Then Hadadezer sent and brought out the Syrians who were beyond the River, and they came to Helam. And Shobach the commander of Hadadezer&rsquo;s army went before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10017, 'When it was told David, he gathered all Israel, crossed over the Jordan, and came to Helam. And the Syrians set themselves in battle array against David and fought with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10018, 'Then the Syrians fled before Israel; and David killed seven hundred charioteers and forty thousand horsemen of the Syrians, and struck Shobach the commander of their army, who died there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 10019, 'And when all the kings who were servants to Hadadezer saw that they were defeated by Israel, they made peace with Israel and served them. So the Syrians were afraid to help the people of Ammon anymore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11001, 'It happened in the spring of the year, at the time when kings go out to battle, that David sent Joab and his servants with him, and all Israel; and they destroyed the people of Ammon and besieged Rabbah. But David remained at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11002, 'Then it happened one evening that David arose from his bed and walked on the roof of the king&rsquo;s house. And from the roof he saw a woman bathing, and the woman was very beautiful to behold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11003, 'So David sent and inquired about the woman. And someone said, &ldquo;Is this not Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, the wife of Uriah the Hittite?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11004, 'Then David sent messengers, and took her; and she came to him, and he lay with her, for she was cleansed from her impurity; and she returned to her house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11005, 'And the woman conceived; so she sent and told David, and said, &ldquo;I am with child.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11006, 'Then David sent to Joab, saying, &ldquo;Send me Uriah the Hittite.&rdquo; And Joab sent Uriah to David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11007, 'When Uriah had come to him, David asked how Joab was doing, and how the people were doing, and how the war prospered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11008, 'And David said to Uriah, &ldquo;Go down to your house and wash your feet.&rdquo; So Uriah departed from the king&rsquo;s house, and a gift of food from the king followed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11009, 'But Uriah slept at the door of the king&rsquo;s house with all the servants of his lord, and did not go down to his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11010, 'So when they told David, saying, &ldquo;Uriah did not go down to his house,&rdquo; David said to Uriah, &ldquo;Did you not come from a journey? Why did you not go down to your house?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11011, 'And Uriah said to David, &ldquo;The ark and Israel and Judah are dwelling in tents, and my lord Joab and the servants of my lord are encamped in the open fields. Shall I then go to my house to eat and drink, and to lie with my wife? As you live, and as your soul lives, I will not do this thing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11012, 'Then David said to Uriah, &ldquo;Wait here today also, and tomorrow I will let you depart.&rdquo; So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and the next. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11013, 'Now when David called him, he ate and drank before him; and he made him drunk. And at evening he went out to lie on his bed with the servants of his lord, but he did not go down to his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11014, 'In the morning it happened that David wrote a letter to Joab and sent it by the hand of Uriah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11015, 'And he wrote in the letter, saying, &ldquo;Set Uriah in the forefront of the hottest battle, and retreat from him, that he may be struck down and die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11016, 'So it was, while Joab besieged the city, that he assigned Uriah to a place where he knew there were valiant men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11017, 'Then the men of the city came out and fought with Joab. And some of the people of the servants of David fell; and Uriah the Hittite died also. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11018, 'Then Joab sent and told David all the things concerning the war, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11019, 'and charged the messenger, saying, &ldquo;When you have finished telling the matters of the war to the king, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11020, 'if it happens that the king&rsquo;s wrath rises, and he says to you: &lsquo;Why did you approach so near to the city when you fought? Did you not know that they would shoot from the wall? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11021, 'Who struck Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth? Was it not a woman who cast a piece of a millstone on him from the wall, so that he died in Thebez? Why did you go near the wall?&rsquo; &ndash; then you shall say, &lsquo;Your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11022, 'So the messenger went, and came and told David all that Joab had sent by him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11023, 'And the messenger said to David, &ldquo;Surely the men prevailed against us and came out to us in the field; then we drove them back as far as the entrance of the gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11024, 'The archers shot from the wall at your servants; and some of the king&rsquo;s servants are dead, and your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11025, 'Then David said to the messenger, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to Joab: &lsquo;Do not let this thing displease you, for the sword devours one as well as another. Strengthen your attack against the city, and overthrow it.&rsquo; So encourage him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11026, 'When the wife of Uriah heard that Uriah her husband was dead, she mourned for her husband. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 11027, 'And when her mourning was over, David sent and brought her to his house, and she became his wife and bore him a son. But the thing that David had done displeased the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12001, 'Then the Lord sent Nathan to David. And he came to him, and said to him: &ldquo;There were two men in one city, one rich and the other poor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12002, 'The rich man had exceedingly many flocks and herds. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12003, 'But the poor man had nothing, except one little ewe lamb which he had bought and nourished; and it grew up together with him and with his children. It ate of his own food and drank from his own cup and lay in his bosom; and it was like a daughter to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12004, 'And a traveler came to the rich man, who refused to take from his own flock and from his own herd to prepare one for the wayfaring man who had come to him; but he took the poor man&rsquo;s lamb and prepared it for the man who had come to him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12005, 'So David&rsquo;s anger was greatly aroused against the man, and he said to Nathan, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, the man who has done this shall surely die! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12006, 'And he shall restore fourfold for the lamb, because he did this thing and because he had no pity.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12007, 'Then Nathan said to David, &ldquo;You are the man! Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;I anointed you king over Israel, and I delivered you from the hand of Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12008, 'I gave you your master&rsquo;s house and your master&rsquo;s wives into your keeping, and gave you the house of Israel and Judah. And if that had been too little, I also would have given you much more! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12009, 'Why have you despised the commandment of the Lord, to do evil in His sight? You have killed Uriah the Hittite with the sword; you have taken his wife to be your wife, and have killed him with the sword of the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12010, 'Now therefore, the sword shall never depart from your house, because you have despised Me, and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your wife.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12011, 'Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Behold, I will raise up adversity against you from your own house; and I will take your wives before your eyes and give them to your neighbor, and he shall lie with your wives in the sight of this sun. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12012, 'For you did it secretly, but I will do this thing before all Israel, before the sun.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12013, 'So David said to Nathan, &ldquo;I have sinned against the Lord.&rdquo; And Nathan said to David, &ldquo;The Lord also has put away your sin; you shall not die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12014, 'However, because by this deed you have given great occasion to the enemies of the Lord to blaspheme, the child also who is born to you shall surely die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12015, 'Then Nathan departed to his house.And the Lord struck the child that Uriah&rsquo;s wife bore to David, and it became ill. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12016, 'David therefore pleaded with God for the child, and David fasted and went in and lay all night on the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12017, 'So the elders of his house arose and went to him, to raise him up from the ground. But he would not, nor did he eat food with them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12018, 'Then on the seventh day it came to pass that the child died. And the servants of David were afraid to tell him that the child was dead. For they said, &ldquo;Indeed, while the child was alive, we spoke to him, and he would not heed our voice. How can we tell him that the child is dead? He may do some harm!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12019, 'When David saw that his servants were whispering, David perceived that the child was dead. Therefore David said to his servants, &ldquo;Is the child dead?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;He is dead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12020, 'So David arose from the ground, washed and anointed himself, and changed his clothes; and he went into the house of the Lord and worshiped. Then he went to his own house; and when he requested, they set food before him, and he ate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12021, 'Then his servants said to him, &ldquo;What is this that you have done? You fasted and wept for the child while he was alive, but when the child died, you arose and ate food.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12022, 'And he said, &ldquo;While the child was alive, I fasted and wept; for I said, &lsquo;Who can tell whether the Lord will be gracious to me, that the child may live?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12023, 'But now he is dead; why should I fast? Can I bring him back again? I shall go to him, but he shall not return to me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12024, 'Then David comforted Bathsheba his wife, and went in to her and lay with her. So she bore a son, and he called his name Solomon. Now the Lord loved him, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12025, 'and He sent word by the hand of Nathan the prophet: So he called his name Jedidiah, because of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12026, 'Now Joab fought against Rabbah of the people of Ammon, and took the royal city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12027, 'And Joab sent messengers to David, and said, &ldquo;I have fought against Rabbah, and I have taken the city&rsquo;s water supply. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12028, 'Now therefore, gather the rest of the people together and encamp against the city and take it, lest I take the city and it be called after my name.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12029, 'So David gathered all the people together and went to Rabbah, fought against it, and took it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12030, 'Then he took their king&rsquo;s crown from his head. Its weight was a talent of gold, with precious stones. And it was set on David&rsquo;s head. Also he brought out the spoil of the city in great abundance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 12031, 'And he brought out the people who were in it, and put them to work with saws and iron picks and iron axes, and made them cross over to the brick works. So he did to all the cities of the people of Ammon. Then David and all the people returned to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13001, 'After this Absalom the son of David had a lovely sister, whose name was Tamar; and Amnon the son of David loved her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13002, 'Amnon was so distressed over his sister Tamar that he became sick; for she was a virgin. And it was improper for Amnon to do anything to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13003, 'But Amnon had a friend whose name was Jonadab the son of Shimeah, David&rsquo;s brother. Now Jonadab was a very crafty man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13004, 'And he said to him, &ldquo;Why are you, the king&rsquo;s son, becoming thinner day after day? Will you not tell me?&rdquo; Amnon said to him, &ldquo;I love Tamar, my brother Absalom&rsquo;s sister.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13005, 'So Jonadab said to him, &ldquo;Lie down on your bed and pretend to be ill. And when your father comes to see you, say to him, &lsquo;Please let my sister Tamar come and give me food, and prepare the food in my sight, that I may see it and eat it from her hand.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13006, 'Then Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill; and when the king came to see him, Amnon said to the king, &ldquo;Please let Tamar my sister come and make a couple of cakes for me in my sight, that I may eat from her hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13007, 'And David sent home to Tamar, saying, &ldquo;Now go to your brother Amnon&rsquo;s house, and prepare food for him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13008, 'So Tamar went to her brother Amnon&rsquo;s house; and he was lying down. Then she took flour and kneaded it, made cakes in his sight, and baked the cakes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13009, 'And she took the pan and placed them out before him, but he refused to eat. Then Amnon said, &ldquo;Have everyone go out from me.&rdquo; And they all went out from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13010, 'Then Amnon said to Tamar, &ldquo;Bring the food into the bedroom, that I may eat from your hand.&rdquo; And Tamar took the cakes which she had made, and brought them to Amnon her brother in the bedroom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13011, 'Now when she had brought them to him to eat, he took hold of her and said to her, &ldquo;Come, lie with me, my sister.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13012, 'And she answered him, &ldquo;No, my brother, do not force me, for no such thing should be done in Israel. Do not do this disgraceful thing! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13013, 'And I, where could I take my shame? And as for you, you would be like one of the fools in Israel. Now therefore, please speak to the king; for he will not withhold me from you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13014, 'However, he would not heed her voice; and being stronger than she, he forced her and lay with her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13015, 'Then Amnon hated her exceedingly, so that the hatred with which he hated her was greater than the love with which he had loved her. And Amnon said to her, &ldquo;Arise, be gone!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13016, 'So she said to him, &ldquo;No, indeed! This evil of sending me away is worse than the other that you did to me.&rdquo; But he would not listen to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13017, 'Then he called his servant who attended him, and said, &ldquo;Here! Put this woman out, away from me, and bolt the door behind her.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13018, 'Now she had on a robe of many colors, for the king&rsquo;s virgin daughters wore such apparel. And his servant put her out and bolted the door behind her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13019, 'Then Tamar put ashes on her head, and tore her robe of many colors that was on her, and laid her hand on her head and went away crying bitterly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13020, 'And Absalom her brother said to her, &ldquo;Has Amnon your brother been with you? But now hold your peace, my sister. He is your brother; do not take this thing to heart.&rdquo; So Tamar remained desolate in her brother Absalom&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13021, 'But when King David heard of all these things, he was very angry. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13022, 'And Absalom spoke to his brother Amnon neither good nor bad. For Absalom hated Amnon, because he had forced his sister Tamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13023, 'And it came to pass, after two full years, that Absalom had sheepshearers in Baal Hazor, which is near Ephraim; so Absalom invited all the king&rsquo;s sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13024, 'Then Absalom came to the king and said, &ldquo;Kindly note, your servant has sheepshearers; please, let the king and his servants go with your servant.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13025, 'But the king said to Absalom, &ldquo;No, my son, let us not all go now, lest we be a burden to you.&rdquo; Then he urged him, but he would not go; and he blessed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13026, 'Then Absalom said, &ldquo;If not, please let my brother Amnon go with us.&rdquo; And the king said to him, &ldquo;Why should he go with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13027, 'But Absalom urged him; so he let Amnon and all the king&rsquo;s sons go with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13028, 'Now Absalom had commanded his servants, saying, &ldquo;Watch now, when Amnon&rsquo;s heart is merry with wine, and when I say to you, &lsquo;Strike Amnon!&rsquo; then kill him. Do not be afraid. Have I not commanded you? Be courageous and valiant.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13029, 'So the servants of Absalom did to Amnon as Absalom had commanded. Then all the king&rsquo;s sons arose, and each one got on his mule and fled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13030, 'And it came to pass, while they were on the way, that news came to David, saying, &ldquo;Absalom has killed all the king&rsquo;s sons, and not one of them is left!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13031, 'So the king arose and tore his garments and lay on the ground, and all his servants stood by with their clothes torn. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13032, 'Then Jonadab the son of Shimeah, David&rsquo;s brother, answered and said, &ldquo;Let not my lord suppose they have killed all the young men, the king&rsquo;s sons, for only Amnon is dead. For by the command of Absalom this has been determined from the day that he forced his sister Tamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13033, 'Now therefore, let not my lord the king take the thing to his heart, to think that all the king&rsquo;s sons are dead. For only Amnon is dead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13034, 'Then Absalom fled. And the young man who was keeping watch lifted his eyes and looked, and there, many people were coming from the road on the hillside behind him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13035, 'And Jonadab said to the king, &ldquo;Look, the king&rsquo;s sons are coming; as your servant said, so it is.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13036, 'So it was, as soon as he had finished speaking, that the king&rsquo;s sons indeed came, and they lifted up their voice and wept. Also the king and all his servants wept very bitterly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13037, 'But Absalom fled and went to Talmai the son of Ammihud, king of Geshur. And David mourned for his son every day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13038, 'So Absalom fled and went to Geshur, and was there three years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 13039, 'And King David longed to go to Absalom. For he had been comforted concerning Amnon, because he was dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14001, 'So Joab the son of Zeruiah perceived that the king&rsquo;s heart was concerned about Absalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14002, 'And Joab sent to Tekoa and brought from there a wise woman, and said to her, &ldquo;Please pretend to be a mourner, and put on mourning apparel; do not anoint yourself with oil, but act like a woman who has been mourning a long time for the dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14003, 'Go to the king and speak to him in this manner.&rdquo; So Joab put the words in her mouth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14004, 'And when the woman of Tekoa spoke to the king, she fell on her face to the ground and prostrated herself, and said, &ldquo;Help, O king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14005, 'Then the king said to her, &ldquo;What troubles you?&rdquo; And she answered, &ldquo;Indeed I am a widow, my husband is dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14006, 'Now your maidservant had two sons; and the two fought with each other in the field, and there was no one to part them, but the one struck the other and killed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14007, 'And now the whole family has risen up against your maidservant, and they said, &lsquo;Deliver him who struck his brother, that we may execute him for the life of his brother whom he killed; and we will destroy the heir also.&rsquo; So they would extinguish my ember that is left, and leave to my husband neither name nor remnant on the earth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14008, 'Then the king said to the woman, &ldquo;Go to your house, and I will give orders concerning you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14009, 'And the woman of Tekoa said to the king, &ldquo;My lord, O king, let the iniquity be on me and on my father&rsquo;s house, and the king and his throne be guiltless.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14010, 'So the king said, &ldquo;Whoever says anything to you, bring him to me, and he shall not touch you anymore.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14011, 'Then she said, &ldquo;Please let the king remember the Lord your God, and do not permit the avenger of blood to destroy anymore, lest they destroy my son.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, not one hair of your son shall fall to the ground.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14012, 'Therefore the woman said, &ldquo;Please, let your maidservant speak another word to my lord the king.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Say on.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14013, 'So the woman said: &ldquo;Why then have you schemed such a thing against the people of God? For the king speaks this thing as one who is guilty, in that the king does not bring his banished one home again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14014, 'For we will surely die and become like water spilled on the ground, which cannot be gathered up again. Yet God does not take away a life; but He devises means, so that His banished ones are not expelled from Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14015, 'Now therefore, I have come to speak of this thing to my lord the king because the people have made me afraid. And your maidservant said, &lsquo;I will now speak to the king; it may be that the king will perform the request of his maidservant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14016, 'For the king will hear and deliver his maidservant from the hand of the man who would destroy me and my son together from the inheritance of God.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14017, 'Your maidservant said, &lsquo;The word of my lord the king will now be comforting; for as the angel of God, so is my lord the king in discerning good and evil. And may the Lord your God be with you.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14018, 'Then the king answered and said to the woman, &ldquo;Please do not hide from me anything that I ask you.&rdquo; And the woman said, &ldquo;Please, let my lord the king speak.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14019, 'So the king said, &ldquo;Is the hand of Joab with you in all this?&rdquo; And the woman answered and said, &ldquo;As you live, my lord the king, no one can turn to the right hand or to the left from anything that my lord the king has spoken. For your servant Joab commanded me, and he put all these words in the mouth of your maidservant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14020, 'To bring about this change of affairs your servant Joab has done this thing; but my lord is wise, according to the wisdom of the angel of God, to know everything that is in the earth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14021, 'And the king said to Joab, &ldquo;All right, I have granted this thing. Go therefore, bring back the young man Absalom.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14022, 'Then Joab fell to the ground on his face and bowed himself, and thanked the king. And Joab said, &ldquo;Today your servant knows that I have found favor in your sight, my lord, O king, in that the king has fulfilled the request of his servant.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14023, 'So Joab arose and went to Geshur, and brought Absalom to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14024, 'And the king said, &ldquo;Let him return to his own house, but do not let him see my face.&rdquo; So Absalom returned to his own house, but did not see the king&rsquo;s face. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14025, 'Now in all Israel there was no one who was praised as much as Absalom for his good looks. From the sole of his foot to the crown of his head there was no blemish in him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14026, 'And when he cut the hair of his head &ndash; at the end of every year he cut it because it was heavy on him &ndash; when he cut it, he weighed the hair of his head at two hundred shekels according to the king&rsquo;s standard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14027, 'To Absalom were born three sons, and one daughter whose name was Tamar. She was a woman of beautiful appearance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14028, 'And Absalom dwelt two full years in Jerusalem, but did not see the king&rsquo;s face. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14029, 'Therefore Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but he would not come to him. And when he sent again the second time, he would not come. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14030, 'So he said to his servants, &ldquo;See, Joab&rsquo;s field is near mine, and he has barley there; go and set it on fire.&rdquo; And Absalom&rsquo;s servants set the field on fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14031, 'Then Joab arose and came to Absalom&rsquo;s house, and said to him, &ldquo;Why have your servants set my field on fire?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14032, 'And Absalom answered Joab, &ldquo;Look, I sent to you, saying, &lsquo;Come here, so that I may send you to the king, to say, &ldquo;Why have I come from Geshur? It would be better for me to be there still.&rdquo; &lsquo; Now therefore, let me see the king&rsquo;s face; but if there is iniquity in me, let him execute me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 14033, 'So Joab went to the king and told him. And when he had called for Absalom, he came to the king and bowed himself on his face to the ground before the king. Then the king kissed Absalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15001, 'After this it happened that Absalom provided himself with chariots and horses, and fifty men to run before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15002, 'Now Absalom would rise early and stand beside the way to the gate. So it was, whenever anyone who had a lawsuit came to the king for a decision, that Absalom would call to him and say, &ldquo;What city are you from?&rdquo; And he would say, &ldquo;Your servant is from such and such a tribe of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15003, 'Then Absalom would say to him, &ldquo;Look, your case is good and right; but there is no deputy of the king to hear you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15004, 'Moreover Absalom would say, &ldquo;Oh, that I were made judge in the land, and everyone who has any suit or cause would come to me; then I would give him justice.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15005, 'And so it was, whenever anyone came near to bow down to him, that he would put out his hand and take him and kiss him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15006, 'In this manner Absalom acted toward all Israel who came to the king for judgment. So Absalom stole the hearts of the men of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15007, 'Now it came to pass after forty years that Absalom said to the king, &ldquo;Please, let me go to Hebron and pay the vow which I made to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15008, 'For your servant took a vow while I dwelt at Geshur in Syria, saying, &lsquo;If the Lord indeed brings me back to Jerusalem, then I will serve the Lord.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15009, 'And the king said to him, &ldquo;Go in peace.&rdquo; So he arose and went to Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15010, 'Then Absalom sent spies throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, &ldquo;As soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then you shall say, &lsquo;Absalom reigns in Hebron!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15011, 'And with Absalom went two hundred men invited from Jerusalem, and they went along innocently and did not know anything. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15012, 'Then Absalom sent for Ahithophel the Gilonite, David&rsquo;s counselor, from his city &ndash; from Giloh &ndash; while he offered sacrifices. And the conspiracy grew strong, for the people with Absalom continually increased in number. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15013, 'Now a messenger came to David, saying, &ldquo;The hearts of the men of Israel are with Absalom.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15014, 'So David said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem, &ldquo;Arise, and let us flee; or we shall not escape from Absalom. Make haste to depart, lest he overtake us suddenly and bring disaster upon us, and strike the city with the edge of the sword.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15015, 'And the king&rsquo;s servants said to the king, &ldquo;We are your servants, ready to do whatever my lord the king commands.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15016, 'Then the king went out with all his household after him. But the king left ten women, concubines, to keep the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15017, 'And the king went out with all the people after him, and stopped at the outskirts. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15018, 'Then all his servants passed before him; and all the Cherethites, all the Pelethites, and all the Gittites, six hundred men who had followed him from Gath, passed before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15019, 'Then the king said to Ittai the Gittite, &ldquo;Why are you also going with us? Return and remain with the king. For you are a foreigner and also an exile from your own place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15020, 'In fact, you came only yesterday. Should I make you wander up and down with us today, since I go I know not where? Return, and take your brethren back. Mercy and truth be with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15021, 'And Ittai answered the king and said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, and as my lord the king lives, surely in whatever place my lord the king shall be, whether in death or life, even there also your servant will be.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15022, 'So David said to Ittai, &ldquo;Go, and cross over.&rdquo; Then Ittai the Gittite and all his men and all the little ones who were with him crossed over. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15023, 'And all the country wept with a loud voice, and all the people crossed over. The king himself also crossed over the Brook Kidron, and all the people crossed over toward the way of the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15024, 'There was Zadok also, and all the Levites with him, bearing the ark of the covenant of God. And they set down the ark of God, and Abiathar went up until all the people had finished crossing over from the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15025, 'Then the king said to Zadok, &ldquo;Carry the ark of God back into the city. If I find favor in the eyes of the Lord, He will bring me back and show me both it and His dwelling place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15026, 'But if He says thus: &lsquo;I have no delight in you,&rsquo; here I am, let Him do to me as seems good to Him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15027, 'The king also said to Zadok the priest, &ldquo;Are you not a seer? Return to the city in peace, and your two sons with you, Ahimaaz your son, and Jonathan the son of Abiathar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15028, 'See, I will wait in the plains of the wilderness until word comes from you to inform me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15029, 'Therefore Zadok and Abiathar carried the ark of God back to Jerusalem. And they remained there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15030, 'So David went up by the Ascent of the Mount of Olives, and wept as he went up; and he had his head covered and went barefoot. And all the people who were with him covered their heads and went up, weeping as they went up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15031, 'Then someone told David, saying, &ldquo;Ahithophel is among the conspirators with Absalom.&rdquo; And David said, &ldquo;O Lord, I pray, turn the counsel of Ahithophel into foolishness!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15032, 'Now it happened when David had come to the top of the mountain, where he worshiped God &ndash; there was Hushai the Archite coming to meet him with his robe torn and dust on his head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15033, 'David said to him, &ldquo;If you go on with me, then you will become a burden to me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15034, 'But if you return to the city, and say to Absalom, &lsquo;I will be your servant, O king; as I was your father&rsquo;s servant previously, so I will now also be your servant,&rsquo; then you may defeat the counsel of Ahithophel for me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15035, 'And do you not have Zadok and Abiathar the priests with you there? Therefore it will be that whatever you hear from the king&rsquo;s house, you shall tell to Zadok and Abiathar the priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15036, 'Indeed they have there with them their two sons, Ahimaaz, Zadok&rsquo;s son, and Jonathan, Abiathar&rsquo;s son; and by them you shall send me everything you hear.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 15037, 'So Hushai, David&rsquo;s friend, went into the city. And Absalom came into Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16001, 'When David was a little past the top of the mountain, there was Ziba the servant of Mephibosheth, who met him with a couple of saddled donkeys, and on them two hundred loaves of bread, one hundred clusters of raisins, one hundred summer fruits, and a skin of wine. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16002, 'And the king said to Ziba, &ldquo;What do you mean to do with these?&rdquo; So Ziba said, &ldquo;The donkeys are for the king&rsquo;s household to ride on, the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat, and the wine for those who are faint in the wilderness to drink.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16003, 'Then the king said, &ldquo;And where is your master&rsquo;s son?&rdquo; And Ziba said to the king, &ldquo;Indeed he is staying in Jerusalem, for he said, &lsquo;Today the house of Israel will restore the kingdom of my father to me.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16004, 'So the king said to Ziba, &ldquo;Here, all that belongs to Mephibosheth is yours.&rdquo; And Ziba said, &ldquo;I humbly bow before you, that I may find favor in your sight, my lord, O king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16005, 'Now when King David came to Bahurim, there was a man from the family of the house of Saul, whose name was Shimei the son of Gera, coming from there. He came out, cursing continuously as he came. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16006, 'And he threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David. And all the people and all the mighty men were on his right hand and on his left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16007, 'Also Shimei said thus when he cursed: &ldquo;Come out! Come out! You bloodthirsty man, you rogue! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16008, 'The Lord has brought upon you all the blood of the house of Saul, in whose place you have reigned; and the Lord has delivered the kingdom into the hand of Absalom your son. So now you are caught in your own evil, because you are a bloodthirsty man!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16009, 'Then Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, &ldquo;Why should this dead dog curse my lord the king? Please, let me go over and take off his head!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16010, 'But the king said, &ldquo;What have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah? So let him curse, because the Lord has said to him, &lsquo;Curse David.&rsquo; Who then shall say, &lsquo;Why have you done so?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16011, 'And David said to Abishai and all his servants, &ldquo;See how my son who came from my own body seeks my life. How much more now may this Benjamite? Let him alone, and let him curse; for so the Lord has ordered him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16012, 'It may be that the Lord will look on my affliction, and that the Lord will repay me with good for his cursing this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16013, 'And as David and his men went along the road, Shimei went along the hillside opposite him and cursed as he went, threw stones at him and kicked up dust. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16014, 'Now the king and all the people who were with him became weary; so they refreshed themselves there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16015, 'Meanwhile Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, came to Jerusalem; and Ahithophel was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16016, 'And so it was, when Hushai the Archite, David&rsquo;s friend, came to Absalom, that Hushai said to Absalom, &ldquo;Long live the king! Long live the king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16017, 'So Absalom said to Hushai, &ldquo;Is this your loyalty to your friend? Why did you not go with your friend?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16018, 'And Hushai said to Absalom, &ldquo;No, but whom the Lord and this people and all the men of Israel choose, his I will be, and with him I will remain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16019, 'Furthermore, whom should I serve? Should I not serve in the presence of his son? As I have served in your father&rsquo;s presence, so will I be in your presence.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16020, 'Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, &ldquo;Give counsel as to what we should do.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16021, 'And Ahithophel said to Absalom, &ldquo;Go in to your father&rsquo;s concubines, whom he has left to keep the house; and all Israel will hear that you are abhorred by your father. Then the hands of all who are with you will be strong.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16022, 'So they pitched a tent for Absalom on the top of the house, and Absalom went in to his father&rsquo;s concubines in the sight of all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 16023, 'Now the advice of Ahithophel, which he gave in those days, was as if one had inquired at the oracle of God. So was all the advice of Ahithophel both with David and with Absalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17001, 'Moreover Ahithophel said to Absalom, &ldquo;Now let me choose twelve thousand men, and I will arise and pursue David tonight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17002, 'I will come upon him while he is weary and weak, and make him afraid. And all the people who are with him will flee, and I will strike only the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17003, 'Then I will bring back all the people to you. When all return except the man whom you seek, all the people will be at peace.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17004, 'And the saying pleased Absalom and all the elders of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17005, 'Then Absalom said, &ldquo;Now call Hushai the Archite also, and let us hear what he says too.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17006, 'And when Hushai came to Absalom, Absalom spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;Ahithophel has spoken in this manner. Shall we do as he says? If not, speak up.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17007, 'So Hushai said to Absalom: &ldquo;The advice that Ahithophel has given is not good at this time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17008, 'For,&rdquo; said Hushai, &ldquo;you know your father and his men, that they are mighty men, and they are enraged in their minds, like a bear robbed of her cubs in the field; and your father is a man of war, and will not camp with the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17009, 'Surely by now he is hidden in some pit, or in some other place. And it will be, when some of them are overthrown at the first, that whoever hears it will say, &lsquo;There is a slaughter among the people who follow Absalom.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17010, 'And even he who is valiant, whose heart is like the heart of a lion, will melt completely. For all Israel knows that your father is a mighty man, and those who are with him are valiant men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17011, 'Therefore I advise that all Israel be fully gathered to you, from Dan to Beersheba, like the sand that is by the sea for multitude, and that you go to battle in person. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17012, 'So we will come upon him in some place where he may be found, and we will fall on him as the dew falls on the ground. And of him and all the men who are with him there shall not be left so much as one. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17013, 'Moreover, if he has withdrawn into a city, then all Israel shall bring ropes to that city; and we will pull it into the river, until there is not one small stone found there.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17014, 'So Absalom and all the men of Israel said, &ldquo;The advice of Hushai the Archite is better than the advice of Ahithophel.&rdquo; For the Lord had purposed to defeat the good advice of Ahithophel, to the intent that the Lord might bring disaster on Absalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17015, 'Then Hushai said to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, &ldquo;Thus and so Ahithophel advised Absalom and the elders of Israel, and thus and so I have advised. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17016, 'Now therefore, send quickly and tell David, saying, &lsquo;Do not spend this night in the plains of the wilderness, but speedily cross over, lest the king and all the people who are with him be swallowed up.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17017, 'Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz stayed at En Rogel, for they dared not be seen coming into the city; so a female servant would come and tell them, and they would go and tell King David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17018, 'Nevertheless a lad saw them, and told Absalom. But both of them went away quickly and came to a man&rsquo;s house in Bahurim, who had a well in his court; and they went down into it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17019, 'Then the woman took and spread a covering over the well&rsquo;s mouth, and spread ground grain on it; and the thing was not known. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17020, 'And when Absalom&rsquo;s servants came to the woman at the house, they said, &ldquo;Where are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?&rdquo; So the woman said to them, &ldquo;They have gone over the water brook.&rdquo; And when they had searched and could not find them, they returned to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17021, 'Now it came to pass, after they had departed, that they came up out of the well and went and told King David, and said to David, &ldquo;Arise and cross over the water quickly. For thus has Ahithophel advised against you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17022, 'So David and all the people who were with him arose and crossed over the Jordan. By morning light not one of them was left who had not gone over the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17023, 'Now when Ahithophel saw that his advice was not followed, he saddled a donkey, and arose and went home to his house, to his city. Then he put his household in order, and hanged himself, and died; and he was buried in his father&rsquo;s tomb. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17024, 'Then David went to Mahanaim. And Absalom crossed over the Jordan, he and all the men of Israel with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17025, 'And Absalom made Amasa captain of the army instead of Joab. This Amasa was the son of a man whose name was Jithra, an Israelite, who had gone in to Abigail the daughter of Nahash, sister of Zeruiah, Joab&rsquo;s mother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17026, 'So Israel and Absalom encamped in the land of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17027, 'Now it happened, when David had come to Mahanaim, that Shobi the son of Nahash from Rabbah of the people of Ammon, Machir the son of Ammiel from Lo Debar, and Barzillai the Gileadite from Rogelim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17028, 'brought beds and basins, earthen vessels and wheat, barley and flour, parched grain and beans, lentils and parched seeds, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 17029, 'honey and curds, sheep and cheese of the herd, for David and the people who were with him to eat. For they said, &ldquo;The people are hungry and weary and thirsty in the wilderness.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18001, 'And David numbered the people who were with him, and set captains of thousands and captains of hundreds over them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18002, 'Then David sent out one third of the people under the hand of Joab, one third under the hand of Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab&rsquo;s brother, and one third under the hand of Ittai the Gittite. And the king said to the people, &ldquo;I also will surely go out with you myself.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18003, 'But the people answered, &ldquo;You shall not go out! For if we flee away, they will not care about us; nor if half of us die, will they care about us. But you are worth ten thousand of us now. For you are now more help to us in the city.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18004, 'Then the king said to them, &ldquo;Whatever seems best to you I will do.&rdquo; So the king stood beside the gate, and all the people went out by hundreds and by thousands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18005, 'Now the king had commanded Joab, Abishai, and Ittai, saying, &ldquo;Deal gently for my sake with the young man Absalom.&rdquo; And all the people heard when the king gave all the captains orders concerning Absalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18006, 'So the people went out into the field of battle against Israel. And the battle was in the woods of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18007, 'The people of Israel were overthrown there before the servants of David, and a great slaughter of twenty thousand took place there that day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18008, 'For the battle there was scattered over the face of the whole countryside, and the woods devoured more people that day than the sword devoured. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18009, 'Then Absalom met the servants of David. Absalom rode on a mule. The mule went under the thick boughs of a great terebinth tree, and his head caught in the terebinth; so he was left hanging between heaven and earth. And the mule which was under him went on. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18010, 'Now a certain man saw it and told Joab, and said, &ldquo;I just saw Absalom hanging in a terebinth tree!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18011, 'So Joab said to the man who told him, &ldquo;You just saw him! And why did you not strike him there to the ground? I would have given you ten shekels of silver and a belt.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18012, 'But the man said to Joab, &ldquo;Though I were to receive a thousand shekels of silver in my hand, I would not raise my hand against the king&rsquo;s son. For in our hearing the king commanded you and Abishai and Ittai, saying, &lsquo;Beware lest anyone touch the young man Absalom!&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18013, 'Otherwise I would have dealt falsely against my own life. For there is nothing hidden from the king, and you yourself would have set yourself against me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18014, 'Then Joab said, &ldquo;I cannot linger with you.&rdquo; And he took three spears in his hand and thrust them through Absalom&rsquo;s heart, while he was still alive in the midst of the terebinth tree. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18015, 'And ten young men who bore Joab&rsquo;s armor surrounded Absalom, and struck and killed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18016, 'So Joab blew the trumpet, and the people returned from pursuing Israel. For Joab held back the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18017, 'And they took Absalom and cast him into a large pit in the woods, and laid a very large heap of stones over him. Then all Israel fled, everyone to his tent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18018, 'Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and set up a pillar for himself, which is in the King&rsquo;s Valley. For he said, &ldquo;I have no son to keep my name in remembrance.&rdquo; He called the pillar after his own name. And to this day it is called Absalom&rsquo;s Monument. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18019, 'Then Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, &ldquo;Let me run now and take the news to the king, how the Lord has avenged him of his enemies.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18020, 'And Joab said to him, &ldquo;You shall not take the news this day, for you shall take the news another day. But today you shall take no news, because the king&rsquo;s son is dead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18021, 'Then Joab said to the Cushite, &ldquo;Go, tell the king what you have seen.&rdquo; So the Cushite bowed himself to Joab and ran. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18022, 'And Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said again to Joab, &ldquo;But whatever happens, please let me also run after the Cushite.&rdquo; So Joab said, &ldquo;Why will you run, my son, since you have no news ready?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18023, 'But whatever happens, he said, let me run. So he said to him, Run. Then Ahimaaz ran by way of the plain, and outran the Cushite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18024, 'Now David was sitting between the two gates. And the watchman went up to the roof over the gate, to the wall, lifted his eyes and looked, and there was a man, running alone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18025, 'Then the watchman cried out and told the king. And the king said, &ldquo;If he is alone, there is news in his mouth.&rdquo; And he came rapidly and drew near. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18026, 'Then the watchman saw another man running, and the watchman called to the gatekeeper and said, &ldquo;There is another man, running alone!&rdquo; And the king said, &ldquo;He also brings news.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18027, 'So the watchman said, &ldquo;I think the running of the first is like the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zadok.&rdquo; And the king said, &ldquo;He is a good man, and comes with good news.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18028, 'And Ahimaaz called out and said to the king, &ldquo;All is well!&rdquo; Then he bowed down with his face to the earth before the king, and said, &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord your God, who has delivered up the men who raised their hand against my lord the king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18029, 'The king said, &ldquo;Is the young man Absalom safe?&rdquo; Ahimaaz answered, &ldquo;When Joab sent the king&rsquo;s servant and me your servant, I saw a great tumult, but I did not know what it was about.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18030, 'And the king said, &ldquo;Turn aside and stand here.&rdquo; So he turned aside and stood still. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18031, 'Just then the Cushite came, and the Cushite said, &ldquo;There is good news, my lord the king! For the Lord has avenged you this day of all those who rose against you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18032, 'And the king said to the Cushite, &ldquo;Is the young man Absalom safe?&rdquo; So the Cushite answered, &ldquo;May the enemies of my lord the king, and all who rise against you to do harm, be like that young man!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 18033, 'Then the king was deeply moved, and went up to the chamber over the gate, and wept. And as he went, he said thus: &ldquo;O my son Absalom &ndash; my son, my son Absalom &ndash; if only I had died in your place! O Absalom my son, my son!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19001, 'And Joab was told, &ldquo;Behold, the king is weeping and mourning for Absalom.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19002, 'So the victory that day was turned into mourning for all the people. For the people heard it said that day, &ldquo;The king is grieved for his son.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19003, 'And the people stole back into the city that day, as people who are ashamed steal away when they flee in battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19004, 'But the king covered his face, and the king cried out with a loud voice, &ldquo;O my son Absalom! O Absalom, my son, my son!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19005, 'Then Joab came into the house to the king, and said, &ldquo;Today you have disgraced all your servants who today have saved your life, the lives of your sons and daughters, the lives of your wives and the lives of your concubines, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19006, 'in that you love your enemies and hate your friends. For you have declared today that you regard neither princes nor servants; for today I perceive that if Absalom had lived and all of us had died today, then it would have pleased you well. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19007, 'Now therefore, arise, go out and speak comfort to your servants. For I swear by the Lord, if you do not go out, not one will stay with you this night. And that will be worse for you than all the evil that has befallen you from your youth until now.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19008, 'Then the king arose and sat in the gate. And they told all the people, saying, &ldquo;There is the king, sitting in the gate.&rdquo; So all the people came before the king. For everyone of Israel had fled to his tent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19009, 'Now all the people were in a dispute throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, &ldquo;The king saved us from the hand of our enemies, he delivered us from the hand of the Philistines, and now he has fled from the land because of Absalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19010, 'But Absalom, whom we anointed over us, has died in battle. Now therefore, why do you say nothing about bringing back the king?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19011, 'So King David sent to Zadok and Abiathar the priests, saying, &ldquo;Speak to the elders of Judah, saying, &lsquo;Why are you the last to bring the king back to his house, since the words of all Israel have come to the king, to his very house? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19012, 'You are my brethren, you are my bone and my flesh. Why then are you the last to bring back the king?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19013, 'And say to Amasa, &lsquo;Are you not my bone and my flesh? God do so to me, and more also, if you are not commander of the army before me continually in place of Joab.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19014, 'So he swayed the hearts of all the men of Judah, just as the heart of one man, so that they sent this word to the king: &ldquo;Return, you and all your servants!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19015, 'Then the king returned and came to the Jordan. And Judah came to Gilgal, to go to meet the king, to escort the king across the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19016, 'And Shimei the son of Gera, a Benjamite, who was from Bahurim, hastened and came down with the men of Judah to meet King David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19017, 'There were a thousand men of Benjamin with him, and Ziba the servant of the house of Saul, and his fifteen sons and his twenty servants with him; and they went over the Jordan before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19018, 'Then a ferryboat went across to carry over the king&rsquo;s household, and to do what he thought good.Now Shimei the son of Gera fell down before the king when he had crossed the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19019, 'Then he said to the king, &ldquo;Do not let my lord impute iniquity to me, or remember what wrong your servant did on the day that my lord the king left Jerusalem, that the king should take it to heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19020, 'For I, your servant, know that I have sinned. Therefore here I am, the first to come today of all the house of Joseph to go down to meet my lord the king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19021, 'But Abishai the son of Zeruiah answered and said, &ldquo;Shall not Shimei be put to death for this, because he cursed the Lord&rsquo;s anointed?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19022, 'And David said, &ldquo;What have I to do with you, you sons of Zeruiah, that you should be adversaries to me today? Shall any man be put to death today in Israel? For do I not know that today I am king over Israel?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19023, 'Therefore the king said to Shimei, &ldquo;You shall not die.&rdquo; And the king swore to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19024, 'Now Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king. And he had not cared for his feet, nor trimmed his mustache, nor washed his clothes, from the day the king departed until the day he returned in peace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19025, 'So it was, when he had come to Jerusalem to meet the king, that the king said to him, &ldquo;Why did you not go with me, Mephibosheth?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19026, 'And he answered, &ldquo;My lord, O king, my servant deceived me. For your servant said, &lsquo;I will saddle a donkey for myself, that I may ride on it and go to the king,&rsquo; because your servant is lame. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19027, 'And he has slandered your servant to my lord the king, but my lord the king is like the angel of God. Therefore do what is good in your eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19028, 'For all my father&rsquo;s house were but dead men before my lord the king. Yet you set your servant among those who eat at your own table. Therefore what right have I still to cry out anymore to the king?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19029, 'So the king said to him, &ldquo;Why do you speak anymore of your matters? I have said, &lsquo;You and Ziba divide the land.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19030, 'Then Mephibosheth said to the king, &ldquo;Rather, let him take it all, inasmuch as my lord the king has come back in peace to his own house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19031, 'And Barzillai the Gileadite came down from Rogelim and went across the Jordan with the king, to escort him across the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19032, 'Now Barzillai was a very aged man, eighty years old. And he had provided the king with supplies while he stayed at Mahanaim, for he was a very rich man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19033, 'And the king said to Barzillai, &ldquo;Come across with me, and I will provide for you while you are with me in Jerusalem.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19034, 'But Barzillai said to the king, &ldquo;How long have I to live, that I should go up with the king to Jerusalem? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19035, 'I am today eighty years old. Can I discern between the good and bad? Can your servant taste what I eat or what I drink? Can I hear any longer the voice of singing men and singing women? Why then should your servant be a further burden to my lord the king? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19036, 'Your servant will go a little way across the Jordan with the king. And why should the king repay me with such a reward? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19037, 'Please let your servant turn back again, that I may die in my own city, near the grave of my father and mother. But here is your servant Chimham; let him cross over with my lord the king, and do for him what seems good to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19038, 'And the king answered, &ldquo;Chimham shall cross over with me, and I will do for him what seems good to you. Now whatever you request of me, I will do for you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19039, 'Then all the people went over the Jordan. And when the king had crossed over, the king kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and he returned to his own place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19040, 'Now the king went on to Gilgal, and Chimham went on with him. And all the people of Judah escorted the king, and also half the people of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19041, 'Just then all the men of Israel came to the king, and said to the king, &ldquo;Why have our brethren, the men of Judah, stolen you away and brought the king, his household, and all David&rsquo;s men with him across the Jordan?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19042, 'So all the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, &ldquo;Because the king is a close relative of ours. Why then are you angry over this matter? Have we ever eaten at the king&rsquo;s expense? Or has he given us any gift?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 19043, 'And the men of Israel answered the men of Judah, and said, &ldquo;We have ten shares in the king; therefore we also have more right to David than you. Why then do you despise us &ndash; were we not the first to advise bringing back our king?&rdquo; Yet the words of the men of Judah were fiercer than the words of the men of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20001, 'And there happened to be there a rebel,* whose name was Sheba the son of Bichri, a Benjamite. And he blew a trumpet, and said: &ldquo;We have no share in David, Nor do we have inheritance in the son of Jesse; Every man to his tents, O Israel!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20002, 'So every man of Israel deserted David, and followed Sheba the son of Bichri. But the men of Judah, from the Jordan as far as Jerusalem, remained loyal to their king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20003, 'Now David came to his house at Jerusalem. And the king took the ten women, his concubines whom he had left to keep the house, and put them in seclusion and supported them, but did not go in to them. So they were shut up to the day of their death, living in widowhood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20004, 'And the king said to Amasa, &ldquo;Assemble the men of Judah for me within three days, and be present here yourself.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20005, 'So Amasa went to assemble the men of Judah. But he delayed longer than the set time which David had appointed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20006, 'And David said to Abishai, &ldquo;Now Sheba the son of Bichri will do us more harm than Absalom. Take your lord&rsquo;s servants and pursue him, lest he find for himself fortified cities, and escape us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20007, 'So Joab&rsquo;s men, with the Cherethites, the Pelethites, and all the mighty men, went out after him. And they went out of Jerusalem to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20008, 'When they were at the large stone which is in Gibeon, Amasa came before them. Now Joab was dressed in battle armor; on it was a belt with a sword fastened in its sheath at his hips; and as he was going forward, it fell out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20009, 'Then Joab said to Amasa, &ldquo;Are you in health, my brother?&rdquo; And Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand to kiss him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20010, 'But Amasa did not notice the sword that was in Joab&rsquo;s hand. And he struck him with it in the stomach, and his entrails poured out on the ground; and he did not strike him again. Thus he died. Then Joab and Abishai his brother pursued Sheba the son of Bichri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20011, 'Meanwhile one of Joab&rsquo;s men stood near Amasa, and said, &ldquo;Whoever favors Joab and whoever is for David &ndash; follow Joab!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20012, 'But Amasa wallowed in his blood in the middle of the highway. And when the man saw that all the people stood still, he moved Amasa from the highway to the field and threw a garment over him, when he saw that everyone who came upon him halted. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20013, 'When he was removed from the highway, all the people went on after Joab to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20014, 'And he went through all the tribes of Israel to Abel and Beth Maachah and all the Berites. So they were gathered together and also went after Sheba.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20015, 'Then they came and besieged him in Abel of Beth Maachah; and they cast up a siege mound against the city, and it stood by the rampart. And all the people who were with Joab battered the wall to throw it down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20016, 'Then a wise woman cried out from the city, &ldquo;Hear, Hear! Please say to Joab, &lsquo;Come nearby, that I may speak with you.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20017, 'When he had come near to her, the woman said, &ldquo;Are you Joab?&rdquo; He answered, &ldquo;I am.&rdquo; Then she said to him, &ldquo;Hear the words of your maidservant.&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;I am listening.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20018, 'So she spoke, saying, &ldquo;They used to talk in former times, saying, &lsquo;They shall surely seek guidance at Abel,&rsquo; and so they would end disputes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20019, 'I am among the peaceable and faithful in Israel. You seek to destroy a city and a mother in Israel. Why would you swallow up the inheritance of the Lord?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20020, 'And Joab answered and said, &ldquo;Far be it, far be it from me, that I should swallow up or destroy! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20021, 'That is not so. But a man from the mountains of Ephraim, Sheba the son of Bichri by name, has raised his hand against the king, against David. Deliver him only, and I will depart from the city.&rdquo; So the woman said to Joab, &ldquo;Watch, his head will be thrown to you over the wall.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20022, 'Then the woman in her wisdom went to all the people. And they cut off the head of Sheba the son of Bichri, and threw it out to Joab. Then he blew a trumpet, and they withdrew from the city, every man to his tent. So Joab returned to the king at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20023, 'And Joab was over all the army of Israel; Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20024, 'Adoram was in charge of revenue; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20025, 'Sheva was scribe; Zadok and Abiathar were the priests; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 20026, 'and Ira the Jairite was a chief minister under David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21001, 'Now there was a famine in the days of David for three years, year after year; and David inquired of the Lord. And the Lord answered, &ldquo;It is because of Saul and his bloodthirsty house, because he killed the Gibeonites.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21002, 'So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them. Now the Gibeonites were not of the children of Israel, but of the remnant of the Amorites; the children of Israel had sworn protection to them, but Saul had sought to kill them in his zeal for the children of Israel and Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21003, 'Therefore David said to the Gibeonites, &ldquo;What shall I do for you? And with what shall I make atonement, that you may bless the inheritance of the Lord?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21004, 'And the Gibeonites said to him, &ldquo;We will have no silver or gold from Saul or from his house, nor shall you kill any man in Israel for us.&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Whatever you say, I will do for you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21005, 'Then they answered the king, &ldquo;As for the man who consumed us and plotted against us, that we should be destroyed from remaining in any of the territories of Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21006, 'let seven men of his descendants be delivered to us, and we will hang them before the Lord in Gibeah of Saul, whom the Lord chose.&rdquo; And the king said, &ldquo;I will give them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21007, 'But the king spared Mephibosheth the son of Jonathan, the son of Saul, because of the Lord&rsquo;s oath that was between them, between David and Jonathan the son of Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21008, 'So the king took Armoni and Mephibosheth, the two sons of Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, whom she bore to Saul; and the five sons of Michal the daughter of Saul, whom she brought up for Adriel the son of Barzillai the Meholathite; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21009, 'and he delivered them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they hanged them on the hill before the Lord. So they fell, all seven together, and were put to death in the days of harvest, in the first days, in the beginning of barley harvest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21010, 'Now Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it for herself on the rock, from the beginning of harvest until the late rains poured on them from heaven. And she did not allow the birds of the air to rest on them by day nor the beasts of the field by night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21011, 'And David was told what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine of Saul, had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21012, 'Then David went and took the bones of Saul, and the bones of Jonathan his son, from the men of Jabesh Gilead who had stolen them from the street of Beth Shan, where the Philistines had hung them up, after the Philistines had struck down Saul in Gilboa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21013, 'So he brought up the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his son from there; and they gathered the bones of those who had been hanged. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21014, 'They buried the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son in the country of Benjamin in Zelah, in the tomb of Kish his father. So they performed all that the king commanded. And after that God heeded the prayer for the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21015, 'When the Philistines were at war again with Israel, David and his servants with him went down and fought against the Philistines; and David grew faint. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21016, 'Then Ishbi-Benob, who was one of the sons of the giant, the weight of whose bronze spear was three hundred shekels, who was bearing a new sword, thought he could kill David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21017, 'But Abishai the son of Zeruiah came to his aid, and struck the Philistine and killed him. Then the men of David swore to him, saying, &ldquo;You shall go out no more with us to battle, lest you quench the lamp of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21018, 'Now it happened afterward that there was again a battle with the Philistines at Gob. Then Sibbechai the Hushathite killed Saph, who was one of the sons of the giant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21019, 'Again there was war at Gob with the Philistines, where Elhanan the son of Jaare-Oregim the Bethlehemite killed the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver&rsquo;s beam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21020, 'Yet again there was war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature, who had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in number; and he also was born to the giant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21021, 'So when he defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea, David&rsquo;s brother, killed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 21022, 'These four were born to the giant in Gath, and fell by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22001, 'Then David spoke to the Lord the words of this song, on the day when the Lord had delivered him from the hand of all his enemies, and from the hand of Saul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22002, 'And he said: &ldquo;The Lord is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22003, 'The God of my strength, in whom I will trust; My shield and the horn of my salvation, My stronghold and my refuge; My Savior, You save me from violence. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22004, 'I will call upon the Lord, who is worthy to be praised; So shall I be saved from my enemies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22005, 'When the waves of death surrounded me, The floods of ungodliness made me afraid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22006, 'The sorrows of Sheol surrounded me; The snares of death confronted me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22007, 'In my distress I called upon the Lord, And cried out to my God; He heard my voice from His temple, And my cry entered His ears. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22008, 'Then the earth shook and trembled; The foundations of heaven quaked and were shaken, Because He was angry. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22009, 'Smoke went up from His nostrils, And devouring fire from His mouth; Coals were kindled by it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22010, 'He bowed the heavens also, and came down With darkness under His feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22011, 'He rode upon a cherub, and flew; And He was seen upon the wings of the wind. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22012, 'He made darkness canopies around Him, Dark waters and thick clouds of the skies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22013, 'From the brightness before Him Coals of fire were kindled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22014, 'The Lord thundered from heaven, And the Most High uttered His voice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22015, 'He sent out arrows and scattered them; Lightning bolts, and He vanquished them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22016, 'Then the channels of the sea were seen, The foundations of the world were uncovered, At the rebuke of the Lord, At the blast of the breath of His nostrils. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22017, 'He sent from above, He took me, He drew me out of many waters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22018, 'He delivered me from my strong enemy, From those who hated me; For they were too strong for me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22019, 'They confronted me in the day of my calamity, But the Lord was my support. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22020, 'He also brought me out into a broad place; He delivered me because He delighted in me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22021, 'The Lord rewarded me according to my righteousness; According to the cleanness of my hands He has recompensed me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22022, 'For I have kept the ways of the Lord, And have not wickedly departed from my God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22023, 'For all His judgments were before me; And as for His statutes, I did not depart from them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22024, 'I was also blameless before Him, And I kept myself from my iniquity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22025, 'Therefore the Lord has recompensed me according to my righteousness, According to my cleanness in His eyes.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22026, 'With the merciful You will show Yourself merciful; With a blameless man You will show Yourself blameless; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22027, 'With the pure You will show Yourself pure; And with the devious You will show Yourself shrewd. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22028, 'You will save the humble people; But Your eyes are on the haughty, that You may bring them down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22029, 'For You are my lamp, O Lord; The Lord shall enlighten my darkness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22030, 'For by You I can run against a troop; By my God I can leap over a wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22031, 'As for God, His way is perfect; The word of the Lord is proven; He is a shield to all who trust in Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22032, 'For who is God, except the Lord? And who is a rock, except our God? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22033, 'God is my strength and power, And He makes my way perfect. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22034, 'He makes my feet like the feet of deer, And sets me on my high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22035, 'He teaches my hands to make war, So that my arms can bend a bow of bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22036, 'You have also given me the shield of Your salvation; Your gentleness has made me great. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22037, 'You enlarged my path under me; So my feet did not slip. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22038, 'I have pursued my enemies and destroyed them; Neither did I turn back again till they were destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22039, 'And I have destroyed them and wounded them, So that they could not rise; They have fallen under my feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22040, 'For You have armed me with strength for the battle; You have subdued under me those who rose against me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22041, 'You have also given me the necks of my enemies, So that I destroyed those who hated me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22042, 'They looked, but there was none to save; Even to the Lord, but He did not answer them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22043, 'Then I beat them as fine as the dust of the earth; I trod them like dirt in the streets, And I spread them out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22044, 'You have also delivered me from the strivings of my people; You have kept me as the head of the nations. A people I have not known shall serve me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22045, 'The foreigners submit to me; As soon as they hear, they obey me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22046, 'The foreigners fade away, And come frightened from their hideouts. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22047, 'The Lord lives! Blessed be my Rock! Let God be exalted, The Rock of my salvation! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22048, 'It is God who avenges me, And subdues the peoples under me; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22049, 'He delivers me from my enemies. You also lift me up above those who rise against me; You have delivered me from the violent man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22050, 'Therefore I will give thanks to You, O Lord, among the Gentiles, And sing praises to Your name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 22051, 'He is the tower of salvation to His king, And shows mercy to His anointed, To David and his descendants forevermore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23001, 'Now these are the last words of David. Thus says David the son of Jesse; Thus says the man raised up on high, The anointed of the God of Jacob, And the sweet psalmist of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23002, 'The Spirit of the Lord spoke by me, And His word was on my tongue. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23003, 'The God of Israel said, The Rock of Israel spoke to me: &lsquo;He who rules over men must be just, Ruling in the fear of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23004, 'And he shall be like the light of the morning when the sun rises, A morning without clouds, Like the tender grass springing out of the earth, By clear shining after rain.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23005, 'Although my house is not so with God, Yet He has made with me an everlasting covenant, Ordered in all things and secure. For this is all my salvation and all my desire; Will He not make it increase? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23006, 'But the sons of rebellion shall all be as thorns thrust away, Because they cannot be taken with hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23007, 'But the man who touches them Must be armed with iron and the shaft of a spear, And they shall be utterly burned with fire in their place.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23008, 'These are the names of the mighty men whom David had: Josheb-Basshebeth the Tachmonite, chief among the captains. He was called Adino the Eznite, because he had killed eight hundred men at one time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23009, 'And after him was Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite, one of the three mighty men with David when they defied the Philistines who were gathered there for battle, and the men of Israel had retreated. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23010, 'He arose and attacked the Philistines until his hand was weary, and his hand stuck to the sword. The Lord brought about a great victory that day; and the people returned after him only to plunder. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23011, 'And after him was Shammah the son of Agee the Hararite. The Philistines had gathered together into a troop where there was a piece of ground full of lentils. Then the people fled from the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23012, 'But he stationed himself in the middle of the field, defended it, and killed the Philistines. And the Lord brought about a great victory. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23013, 'Then three of the thirty chief men went down at harvest time and came to David at the cave of Adullam. And the troop of Philistines encamped in the Valley of Rephaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23014, 'David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines was then in Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23015, 'And David said with longing, &ldquo;Oh, that someone would give me a drink of the water from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23016, 'So the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines, drew water from the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate, and took it and brought it to David. Nevertheless he would not drink it, but poured it out to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23017, 'And he said, &ldquo;Far be it from me, O Lord, that I should do this! Is this not the blood of the men who went in jeopardy of their lives?&rdquo; Therefore he would not drink it. These things were done by the three mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23018, 'Now Abishai the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was chief of another three. He lifted his spear against three hundred men, killed them, and won a name among these three. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23019, 'Was he not the most honored of three? Therefore he became their captain. However, he did not attain to the first three. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23020, 'Benaiah was the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man from Kabzeel, who had done many deeds. He had killed two lion-like heroes of Moab. He also had gone down and killed a lion in the midst of a pit on a snowy day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23021, 'And he killed an Egyptian, a spectacular man. The Egyptian had a spear in his hand; so he went down to him with a staff, wrested the spear out of the Egyptian&rsquo;s hand, and killed him with his own spear. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23022, 'These things Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did, and won a name among three mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23023, 'He was more honored than the thirty, but he did not attain to the first three. And David appointed him over his guard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23024, 'Asahel the brother of Joab was one of the thirty; Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23025, 'Shammah the Harodite, Elika the Harodite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23026, 'Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23027, 'Abiezer the Anathothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23028, 'Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the Netophathite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23029, 'Heleb the son of Baanah (the Netophathite), Ittai the son of Ribai from Gibeah of the children of Benjamin, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23030, 'Benaiah a Pirathonite, Hiddai from the brooks of Gaash, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23031, 'Abi-Albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the Barhumite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23032, 'Eliahba the Shaalbonite (of the sons of Jashen), Jonathan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23033, 'Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Hararite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23034, 'Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai, the son of the Maachathite, Eliam the son of Ahithophel the Gilonite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23035, 'Hezrai the Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23036, 'Igal the son of Nathan of Zobah, Bani the Gadite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23037, 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Beerothite (armorbearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23038, 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 23039, 'and Uriah the Hittite: thirty-seven in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24001, 'Again the anger of the Lord was aroused against Israel, and He moved David against them to say, &ldquo;Go, number Israel and Judah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24002, 'So the king said to Joab the commander of the army who was with him, &ldquo;Now go throughout all the tribes of Israel, from Dan to Beersheba, and count the people, that I may know the number of the people.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24003, 'And Joab said to the king, &ldquo;Now may the Lord your God add to the people a hundred times more than there are, and may the eyes of my lord the king see it. But why does my lord the king desire this thing?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24004, 'Nevertheless the king&rsquo;s word prevailed against Joab and against the captains of the army. Therefore Joab and the captains of the army went out from the presence of the king to count the people of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24005, 'And they crossed over the Jordan and camped in Aroer, on the right side of the town which is in the midst of the ravine of Gad, and toward Jazer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24006, 'Then they came to Gilead and to the land of Tahtim Hodshi; they came to Dan Jaan and around to Sidon; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Kg', 24007, 'and they came to the stronghold of Tyre and to all the cities of the Hivites and the Canaanites. Then they went out to South Judah as far as Beersheba. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1001, 'Now King David was old, advanced in years; and they put covers on him, but he could not get warm. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1002, 'Therefore his servants said to him, &ldquo;Let a young woman, a virgin, be sought for our lord the king, and let her stand before the king, and let her care for him; and let her lie in your bosom, that our lord the king may be warm.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1003, 'So they sought for a lovely young woman throughout all the territory of Israel, and found Abishag the Shunammite, and brought her to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1004, 'The young woman was very lovely; and she cared for the king, and served him; but the king did not know her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1005, 'Then Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, &ldquo;I will be king&rdquo;; and he prepared for himself chariots and horsemen, and fifty men to run before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1006, '(And his father had not rebuked him at any time by saying, &ldquo;Why have you done so?&rdquo; He was also very good-looking. His mother had borne him after Absalom.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1007, 'Then he conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah and with Abiathar the priest, and they followed and helped Adonijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1008, 'But Zadok the priest, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, Nathan the prophet, Shimei, Rei, and the mighty men who belonged to David were not with Adonijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1009, 'And Adonijah sacrificed sheep and oxen and fattened cattle by the stone of Zoheleth, which is by En Rogel; he also invited all his brothers, the king&rsquo;s sons, and all the men of Judah, the king&rsquo;s servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1010, 'But he did not invite Nathan the prophet, Benaiah, the mighty men, or Solomon his brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1011, 'So Nathan spoke to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, saying, &ldquo;Have you not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king, and David our lord does not know it? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1012, 'Come, please, let me now give you advice, that you may save your own life and the life of your son Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1013, 'Go immediately to King David and say to him, &lsquo;Did you not, my lord, O king, swear to your maidservant, saying, &ldquo;Assuredly your son Solomon shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne&rdquo;? Why then has Adonijah become king?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1014, 'Then, while you are still talking there with the king, I also will come in after you and confirm your words.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1015, 'So Bathsheba went into the chamber to the king. (Now the king was very old, and Abishag the Shunammite was serving the king.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1016, 'And Bathsheba bowed and did homage to the king. Then the king said, &ldquo;What is your wish?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1017, 'Then she said to him, &ldquo;My lord, you swore by the Lord your God to your maidservant, saying, &lsquo;Assuredly Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1018, 'So now, look! Adonijah has become king; and now, my lord the king, you do not know about it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1019, 'He has sacrificed oxen and fattened cattle and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the sons of the king, Abiathar the priest, and Joab the commander of the army; but Solomon your servant he has not invited. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1020, 'And as for you, my lord, O king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, that you should tell them who will sit on the throne of my lord the king after him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1021, 'Otherwise it will happen, when my lord the king rests with his fathers, that I and my son Solomon will be counted as offenders.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1022, 'And just then, while she was still talking with the king, Nathan the prophet also came in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1023, 'So they told the king, saying, &ldquo;Here is Nathan the prophet.&rdquo; And when he came in before the king, he bowed down before the king with his face to the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1024, 'And Nathan said, &ldquo;My lord, O king, have you said, &lsquo;Adonijah shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne&rsquo;? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1025, 'For he has gone down today, and has sacrificed oxen and fattened cattle and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the king&rsquo;s sons, and the commanders of the army, and Abiathar the priest; and look! They are eating and drinking before him; and they say, &lsquo;Long live King Adonijah!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1026, 'But he has not invited me &ndash; me your servant &ndash; nor Zadok the priest, nor Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, nor your servant Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1027, 'Has this thing been done by my lord the king, and you have not told your servant who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1028, 'Then King David answered and said, &ldquo;Call Bathsheba to me.&rdquo; So she came into the king&rsquo;s presence and stood before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1029, 'And the king took an oath and said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, who has redeemed my life from every distress, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1030, 'just as I swore to you by the Lord God of Israel, saying, &lsquo;Assuredly Solomon your son shall be king after me, and he shall sit on my throne in my place,&rsquo; so I certainly will do this day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1031, 'Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the earth, and paid homage to the king, and said, &ldquo;Let my lord King David live forever!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1032, 'And King David said, &ldquo;Call to me Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada.&rdquo; So they came before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1033, 'The king also said to them, &ldquo;Take with you the servants of your lord, and have Solomon my son ride on my own mule, and take him down to Gihon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1034, 'There let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet anoint him king over Israel; and blow the horn, and say, &lsquo;Long live King Solomon!&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1035, 'Then you shall come up after him, and he shall come and sit on my throne, and he shall be king in my place. For I have appointed him to be ruler over Israel and Judah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1036, 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king and said, &ldquo;Amen! May the Lord God of my lord the king say so too. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1037, 'As the Lord has been with my lord the king, even so may He be with Solomon, and make his throne greater than the throne of my lord King David.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1038, 'So Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the Cherethites, and the Pelethites went down and had Solomon ride on King David&rsquo;s mule, and took him to Gihon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1039, 'Then Zadok the priest took a horn of oil from the tabernacle and anointed Solomon. And they blew the horn, and all the people said, &ldquo;Long live King Solomon!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1040, 'And all the people went up after him; and the people played the flutes and rejoiced with great joy, so that the earth seemed to split with their sound. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1041, 'Now Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they finished eating. And when Joab heard the sound of the horn, he said, &ldquo;Why is the city in such a noisy uproar?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1042, 'While he was still speaking, there came Jonathan, the son of Abiathar the priest. And Adonijah said to him, &ldquo;Come in, for you are a prominent man, and bring good news.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1043, 'Then Jonathan answered and said to Adonijah, &ldquo;No! Our lord King David has made Solomon king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1044, 'The king has sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the Cherethites, and the Pelethites; and they have made him ride on the king&rsquo;s mule. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1045, 'So Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king at Gihon; and they have gone up from there rejoicing, so that the city is in an uproar. This is the noise that you have heard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1046, 'Also Solomon sits on the throne of the kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1047, 'And moreover the king&rsquo;s servants have gone to bless our lord King David, saying, &lsquo;May God make the name of Solomon better than your name, and may He make his throne greater than your throne.&rsquo; Then the king bowed himself on the bed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1048, 'Also the king said thus, &lsquo;Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, who has given one to sit on my throne this day, while my eyes see it!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1049, 'So all the guests who were with Adonijah were afraid, and arose, and each one went his way. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1050, 'Now Adonijah was afraid of Solomon; so he arose, and went and took hold of the horns of the altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1051, 'And it was told Solomon, saying, &ldquo;Indeed Adonijah is afraid of King Solomon; for look, he has taken hold of the horns of the altar, saying, &lsquo;Let King Solomon swear to me today that he will not put his servant to death with the sword.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1052, 'Then Solomon said, &ldquo;If he proves himself a worthy man, not one hair of him shall fall to the earth; but if wickedness is found in him, he shall die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 1053, 'So King Solomon sent them to bring him down from the altar. And he came and fell down before King Solomon; and Solomon said to him, &ldquo;Go to your house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2001, 'Now the days of David drew near that he should die, and he charged Solomon his son, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2002, 'I go the way of all the earth; be strong, therefore, and prove yourself a man. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2003, 'And keep the charge of the Lord your God: to walk in His ways, to keep His statutes, His commandments, His judgments, and His testimonies, as it is written in the Law of Moses, that you may prosper in all that you do and wherever you turn; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2004, 'that the Lord may fulfill His word which He spoke concerning me, saying, &lsquo;If your sons take heed to their way, to walk before Me in truth with all their heart and with all their soul,&rsquo; He said, &lsquo;you shall not lack a man on the throne of Israel.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2005, 'Moreover you know also what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to me, and what he did to the two commanders of the armies of Israel, to Abner the son of Ner and Amasa the son of Jether, whom he killed. And he shed the blood of war in peacetime, and put the blood of war on his belt that was around his waist, and on his sandals that were on his feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2006, 'Therefore do according to your wisdom, and do not let his gray hair go down to the grave in peace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2007, 'But show kindness to the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let them be among those who eat at your table, for so they came to me when I fled from Absalom your brother. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2008, 'And see, you have with you Shimei the son of Gera, a Benjamite from Bahurim, who cursed me with a malicious curse in the day when I went to Mahanaim. But he came down to meet me at the Jordan, and I swore to him by the Lord, saying, &lsquo;I will not put you to death with the sword.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2009, 'Now therefore, do not hold him guiltless, for you are a wise man and know what you ought to do to him; but bring his gray hair down to the grave with blood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2010, 'So David rested with his fathers, and was buried in the City of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2011, 'The period that David reigned over Israel was forty years; seven years he reigned in Hebron, and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2012, 'Then Solomon sat on the throne of his father David; and his kingdom was firmly established. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2013, 'Now Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon. So she said, &ldquo;Do you come peaceably?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Peaceably.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2014, 'Moreover he said, &ldquo;I have something to say to you.&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;Say it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2015, 'Then he said, &ldquo;You know that the kingdom was mine, and all Israel had set their expectations on me, that I should reign. However, the kingdom has been turned over, and has become my brother&rsquo;s; for it was his from the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2016, 'Now I ask one petition of you; do not deny me.&rdquo; And she said to him, &ldquo;Say it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2017, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Please speak to King Solomon, for he will not refuse you, that he may give me Abishag the Shunammite as wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2018, 'So Bathsheba said, &ldquo;Very well, I will speak for you to the king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2019, 'Bathsheba therefore went to King Solomon, to speak to him for Adonijah. And the king rose up to meet her and bowed down to her, and sat down on his throne and had a throne set for the king&rsquo;s mother; so she sat at his right hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2020, 'Then she said, &ldquo;I desire one small petition of you; do not refuse me.&rdquo; And the king said to her, &ldquo;Ask it, my mother, for I will not refuse you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2021, 'So she said, &ldquo;Let Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah your brother as wife.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2022, 'And King Solomon answered and said to his mother, &ldquo;Now why do you ask Abishag the Shunammite for Adonijah? Ask for him the kingdom also &ndash; for he is my older brother &ndash; for him, and for Abiathar the priest, and for Joab the son of Zeruiah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2023, 'Then King Solomon swore by the Lord, saying, &ldquo;May God do so to me, and more also, if Adonijah has not spoken this word against his own life! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2024, 'Now therefore, as the Lord lives, who has confirmed me and set me on the throne of David my father, and who has established a house for me, as He promised, Adonijah shall be put to death today!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2025, 'So King Solomon sent by the hand of Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; and he struck him down, and he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2026, 'And to Abiathar the priest the king said, &ldquo;Go to Anathoth, to your own fields, for you are deserving of death; but I will not put you to death at this time, because you carried the ark of the Lord God before my father David, and because you were afflicted every time my father was afflicted.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2027, 'So Solomon removed Abiathar from being priest to the Lord, that he might fulfill the word of the Lord which He spoke concerning the house of Eli at Shiloh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2028, 'Then news came to Joab, for Joab had defected to Adonijah, though he had not defected to Absalom. So Joab fled to the tabernacle of the Lord, and took hold of the horns of the altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2029, 'And King Solomon was told, &ldquo;Joab has fled to the tabernacle of the Lord; there he is, by the altar.&rdquo; Then Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, saying, &ldquo;Go, strike him down.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2030, 'So Benaiah went to the tabernacle of the Lord, and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the king, &lsquo;Come out!&rsquo; &ldquo; And he said, &ldquo;No, but I will die here.&rdquo; And Benaiah brought back word to the king, saying, &ldquo;Thus said Joab, and thus he answered me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2031, 'Then the king said to him, &ldquo;Do as he has said, and strike him down and bury him, that you may take away from me and from the house of my father the innocent blood which Joab shed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2032, 'So the Lord will return his blood on his head, because he struck down two men more righteous and better than he, and killed them with the sword &ndash; Abner the son of Ner, the commander of the army of Israel, and Amasa the son of Jether, the commander of the army of Judah &ndash; though my father David did not know it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2033, 'Their blood shall therefore return upon the head of Joab and upon the head of his descendants forever. But upon David and his descendants, upon his house and his throne, there shall be peace forever from the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2034, 'So Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up and struck and killed him; and he was buried in his own house in the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2035, 'The king put Benaiah the son of Jehoiada in his place over the army, and the king put Zadok the priest in the place of Abiathar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2036, 'Then the king sent and called for Shimei, and said to him, &ldquo;Build yourself a house in Jerusalem and dwell there, and do not go out from there anywhere. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2037, 'For it shall be, on the day you go out and cross the Brook Kidron, know for certain you shall surely die; your blood shall be on your own head.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2038, 'And Shimei said to the king, &ldquo;The saying is good. As my lord the king has said, so your servant will do.&rdquo; So Shimei dwelt in Jerusalem many days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2039, 'Now it happened at the end of three years, that two slaves of Shimei ran away to Achish the son of Maachah, king of Gath. And they told Shimei, saying, &ldquo;Look, your slaves are in Gath!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2040, 'So Shimei arose, saddled his donkey, and went to Achish at Gath to seek his slaves. And Shimei went and brought his slaves from Gath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2041, 'And Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to Gath and had come back. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2042, 'Then the king sent and called for Shimei, and said to him, &ldquo;Did I not make you swear by the Lord, and warn you, saying, &lsquo;Know for certain that on the day you go out and travel anywhere, you shall surely die&rsquo;? And you said to me, &lsquo;The word I have heard is good.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2043, 'Why then have you not kept the oath of the Lord and the commandment that I gave you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2044, 'The king said moreover to Shimei, &ldquo;You know, as your heart acknowledges, all the wickedness that you did to my father David; therefore the Lord will return your wickedness on your own head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2045, 'But King Solomon shall be blessed, and the throne of David shall be established before the Lord forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 2046, 'So the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada; and he went out and struck him down, and he died. Thus the kingdom was established in the hand of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3001, 'Now Solomon made a treaty with Pharaoh king of Egypt, and married Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter; then he brought her to the City of David until he had finished building his own house, and the house of the Lord, and the wall all around Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3002, 'Meanwhile the people sacrificed at the high places, because there was no house built for the name of the Lord until those days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3003, 'And Solomon loved the Lord, walking in the statutes of his father David, except that he sacrificed and burned incense at the high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3004, 'Now the king went to Gibeon to sacrifice there, for that was the great high place: Solomon offered a thousand burnt offerings on that altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3005, 'At Gibeon the Lord appeared to Solomon in a dream by night; and God said, &ldquo;Ask! What shall I give you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3006, 'And Solomon said: &ldquo;You have shown great mercy to Your servant David my father, because he walked before You in truth, in righteousness, and in uprightness of heart with You; You have continued this great kindness for him, and You have given him a son to sit on his throne, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3007, 'Now, O Lord my God, You have made Your servant king instead of my father David, but I am a little child; I do not know how to go out or come in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3008, 'And Your servant is in the midst of Your people whom You have chosen, a great people, too numerous to be numbered or counted. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3009, 'Therefore give to Your servant an understanding heart to judge Your people, that I may discern between good and evil. For who is able to judge this great people of Yours?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3010, 'The speech pleased the Lord, that Solomon had asked this thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3011, 'Then God said to him: &ldquo;Because you have asked this thing, and have not asked long life for yourself, nor have asked riches for yourself, nor have asked the life of your enemies, but have asked for yourself understanding to discern justice, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3012, 'behold, I have done according to your words; see, I have given you a wise and understanding heart, so that there has not been anyone like you before you, nor shall any like you arise after you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3013, 'And I have also given you what you have not asked: both riches and honor, so that there shall not be anyone like you among the kings all your days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3014, 'So if you walk in My ways, to keep My statutes and My commandments, as your father David walked, then I will lengthen your days.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3015, 'Then Solomon awoke; and indeed it had been a dream. And he came to Jerusalem and stood before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, offered up burnt offerings, offered peace offerings, and made a feast for all his servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3016, 'Now two women who were harlots came to the king, and stood before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3017, 'And one woman said, &ldquo;O my lord, this woman and I dwell in the same house; and I gave birth while she was in the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3018, 'Then it happened, the third day after I had given birth, that this woman also gave birth. And we were together; no one was with us in the house, except the two of us in the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3019, 'And this woman&rsquo;s son died in the night, because she lay on him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3020, 'So she arose in the middle of the night and took my son from my side, while your maidservant slept, and laid him in her bosom, and laid her dead child in my bosom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3021, 'And when I rose in the morning to nurse my son, there he was, dead. But when I had examined him in the morning, indeed, he was not my son whom I had borne.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3022, 'Then the other woman said, &ldquo;No! But the living one is my son, and the dead one is your son.&rdquo; And the first woman said, &ldquo;No! But the dead one is your son, and the living one is my son.&rdquo; Thus they spoke before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3023, 'And the king said, &ldquo;The one says, &lsquo;This is my son, who lives, and your son is the dead one&rsquo;; and the other says, &lsquo;No! But your son is the dead one, and my son is the living one.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3024, 'Then the king said, &ldquo;Bring me a sword.&rdquo; So they brought a sword before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3025, 'And the king said, &ldquo;Divide the living child in two, and give half to one, and half to the other.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3026, 'Then the woman whose son was living spoke to the king, for she yearned with compassion for her son; and she said, &ldquo;O my lord, give her the living child, and by no means kill him!&rdquo; But the other said, &ldquo;Let him be neither mine nor yours, but divide him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3027, 'So the king answered and said, &ldquo;Give the first woman the living child, and by no means kill him; she is his mother.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 3028, 'And all Israel heard of the judgment which the king had rendered; and they feared the king, for they saw that the wisdom of God was in him to administer justice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4001, 'So King Solomon was king over all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4002, 'And these were his officials: Azariah the son of Zadok, the priest; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4003, 'Elihoreph and Ahijah, the sons of Shisha, scribes; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud, the recorder; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4004, 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, over the army; Zadok and Abiathar, the priests; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4005, 'Azariah the son of Nathan, over the officers; Zabud the son of Nathan, a priest and the king&rsquo;s friend; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4006, 'Ahishar, over the household; and Adoniram the son of Abda, over the labor force. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4007, 'And Solomon had twelve governors over all Israel, who provided food for the king and his household; each one made provision for one month of the year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4008, 'These are their names: Ben-Hur, in the mountains of Ephraim; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4009, 'Ben-Deker, in Makaz, Shaalbim, Beth Shemesh, and Elon Beth Hanan; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4010, 'Ben-Hesed, in Arubboth; to him belonged Sochoh and all the land of Hepher; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4011, 'Ben-Abinadab, in all the regions of Dor; he had Taphath the daughter of Solomon as wife; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4012, 'Baana the son of Ahilud, in Taanach, Megiddo, and all Beth Shean, which is beside Zaretan below Jezreel, from Beth Shean to Abel Meholah, as far as the other side of Jokneam; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4013, 'Ben-Geber, in Ramoth Gilead; to him belonged the towns of Jair the son of Manasseh, in Gilead; to him also belonged the region of Argob in Bashan &ndash; sixty large cities with walls and bronze gate-bars; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4014, 'Ahinadab the son of Iddo, in Mahanaim; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4015, 'Ahimaaz, in Naphtali; he also took Basemath the daughter of Solomon as wife; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4016, 'Baanah the son of Hushai, in Asher and Aloth; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4017, 'Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4018, 'Shimei the son of Elah, in Benjamin; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4019, 'Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, in the country of Sihon king of the Amorites, and of Og king of Bashan. He was the only governor who was in the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4020, 'Judah and Israel were as numerous as the sand by the sea in multitude, eating and drinking and rejoicing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4021, 'So Solomon reigned over all kingdoms from the River to the land of the Philistines, as far as the border of Egypt. They brought tribute and served Solomon all the days of his life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4022, 'Now Solomon&rsquo;s provision for one day was thirty kors of fine flour, sixty kors of meal, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4023, 'ten fatted oxen, twenty oxen from the pastures, and one hundred sheep, besides deer, gazelles, roebucks, and fatted fowl. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4024, 'For he had dominion over all the region on this side of the River from Tiphsah even to Gaza, namely over all the kings on this side of the River; and he had peace on every side all around him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4025, 'And Judah and Israel dwelt safely, each man under his vine and his fig tree, from Dan as far as Beersheba, all the days of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4026, 'Solomon had forty thousand stalls of horses for his chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4027, 'And these governors, each man in his month, provided food for King Solomon and for all who came to King Solomon&rsquo;s table. There was no lack in their supply. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4028, 'They also brought barley and straw to the proper place, for the horses and steeds, each man according to his charge. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4029, 'And God gave Solomon wisdom and exceedingly great understanding, and largeness of heart like the sand on the seashore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4030, 'Thus Solomon&rsquo;s wisdom excelled the wisdom of all the men of the East and all the wisdom of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4031, 'For he was wiser than all men &ndash; than Ethan the Ezrahite, and Heman, Chalcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol; and his fame was in all the surrounding nations. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4032, 'He spoke three thousand proverbs, and his songs were one thousand and five. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4033, 'Also he spoke of trees, from the cedar tree of Lebanon even to the hyssop that springs out of the wall; he spoke also of animals, of birds, of creeping things, and of fish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 4034, 'And men of all nations, from all the kings of the earth who had heard of his wisdom, came to hear the wisdom of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5001, 'Now Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon, because he heard that they had anointed him king in place of his father, for Hiram had always loved David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5002, 'Then Solomon sent to Hiram, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5003, 'You know how my father David could not build a house for the name of the Lord his God because of the wars which were fought against him on every side, until the Lord put his foes under the soles of his feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5004, 'But now the Lord my God has given me rest on every side; there is neither adversary nor evil occurrence. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5005, 'And behold, I propose to build a house for the name of the Lord my God, as the Lord spoke to my father David, saying, &ldquo;Your son, whom I will set on your throne in your place, he shall build the house for My name.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5006, 'Now therefore, command that they cut down cedars for me from Lebanon; and my servants will be with your servants, and I will pay you wages for your servants according to whatever you say. For you know there is none among us who has skill to cut timber like the Sidonians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5007, 'So it was, when Hiram heard the words of Solomon, that he rejoiced greatly and said, Blessed be the Lord this day, for He has given David a wise son over this great people! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5008, 'Then Hiram sent to Solomon, saying: I have considered the message which you sent me, and I will do all you desire concerning the cedar and cypress logs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5009, 'My servants shall bring them down from Lebanon to the sea; I will float them in rafts by sea to the place you indicate to me, and will have them broken apart there; then you can take them away. And you shall fulfill my desire by giving food for my household. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5010, 'Then Hiram gave Solomon cedar and cypress logs according to all his desire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5011, 'And Solomon gave Hiram twenty thousand kors of wheat as food for his household, and twenty kors of pressed oil. Thus Solomon gave to Hiram year by year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5012, 'So the Lord gave Solomon wisdom, as He had promised him; and there was peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made a treaty together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5013, 'Then King Solomon raised up a labor force out of all Israel; and the labor force was thirty thousand men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5014, 'And he sent them to Lebanon, ten thousand a month in shifts: they were one month in Lebanon and two months at home; Adoniram was in charge of the labor force. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5015, 'Solomon had seventy thousand who carried burdens, and eighty thousand who quarried stone in the mountains, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5016, 'besides three thousand three hundred from the chiefs of Solomon&rsquo;s deputies, who supervised the people who labored in the work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5017, 'And the king commanded them to quarry large stones, costly stones, and hewn stones, to lay the foundation of the temple.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 5018, 'So Solomon&rsquo;s builders, Hiram&rsquo;s builders, and the Gebalites quarried them; and they prepared timber and stones to build the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6001, 'And it came to pass in the four hundred and eightieth* year after the children of Israel had come out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon&rsquo;s reign over Israel, in the month of Ziv, which is the second month, that he began to build the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6002, 'Now the house which King Solomon built for the Lord, its length was sixty cubits, its width twenty, and its height thirty cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6003, 'The vestibule in front of the sanctuary of the house was twenty cubits long across the width of the house, and the width of the vestibule extended ten cubits from the front of the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6004, 'And he made for the house windows with beveled frames. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6005, 'Against the wall of the temple he built chambers all around, against the walls of the temple, all around the sanctuary and the inner sanctuary. Thus he made side chambers all around it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6006, 'The lowest chamber was five cubits wide, the middle was six cubits wide, and the third was seven cubits wide; for he made narrow ledges around the outside of the temple, so that the support beams would not be fastened into the walls of the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6007, 'And the temple, when it was being built, was built with stone finished at the quarry, so that no hammer or chisel or any iron tool was heard in the temple while it was being built. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6008, 'The doorway for the middle story was on the right side of the temple. They went up by stairs to the middle story, and from the middle to the third. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6009, 'So he built the temple and finished it, and he paneled the temple with beams and boards of cedar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6010, 'And he built side chambers against the entire temple, each five cubits high; they were attached to the temple with cedar beams. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6011, 'Then the word of the Lord came to Solomon, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6012, 'Concerning this temple which you are building, if you walk in My statutes, execute My judgments, keep all My commandments, and walk in them, then I will perform My word with you, which I spoke to your father David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6013, 'And I will dwell among the children of Israel, and will not forsake My people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6014, 'So Solomon built the temple and finished it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6015, 'And he built the inside walls of the temple with cedar boards; from the floor of the temple to the ceiling he paneled the inside with wood; and he covered the floor of the temple with planks of cypress. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6016, 'Then he built the twenty-cubit room at the rear of the temple, from floor to ceiling, with cedar boards; he built it inside as the inner sanctuary, as the Most Holy Place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6017, 'And in front of it the temple sanctuary was forty cubits long. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6018, 'The inside of the temple was cedar, carved with ornamental buds and open flowers. All was cedar; there was no stone to be seen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6019, 'And he prepared the inner sanctuary inside the temple, to set the ark of the covenant of the Lord there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6020, 'The inner sanctuary was twenty cubits long, twenty cubits wide, and twenty cubits high. He overlaid it with pure gold, and overlaid the altar of cedar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6021, 'So Solomon overlaid the inside of the temple with pure gold. He stretched gold chains across the front of the inner sanctuary, and overlaid it with gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6022, 'The whole temple he overlaid with gold, until he had finished all the temple; also he overlaid with gold the entire altar that was by the inner sanctuary. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6023, 'Inside the inner sanctuary he made two cherubim of olive wood, each ten cubits high. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6024, 'One wing of the cherub was five cubits, and the other wing of the cherub five cubits: ten cubits from the tip of one wing to the tip of the other. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6025, 'And the other cherub was ten cubits; both cherubim were of the same size and shape. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6026, 'The height of one cherub was ten cubits, and so was the other cherub. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6027, 'Then he set the cherubim inside the inner room; and they stretched out the wings of the cherubim so that the wing of the one touched one wall, and the wing of the other cherub touched the other wall. And their wings touched each other in the middle of the room. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6028, 'Also he overlaid the cherubim with gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6029, 'Then he carved all the walls of the temple all around, both the inner and outer sanctuaries, with carved figures of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6030, 'And the floor of the temple he overlaid with gold, both the inner and outer sanctuaries. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6031, 'For the entrance of the inner sanctuary he made doors of olive wood; the lintel and doorposts were one-fifth of the wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6032, 'The two doors were of olive wood; and he carved on them figures of cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers, and overlaid them with gold; and he spread gold on the cherubim and on the palm trees. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6033, 'So for the door of the sanctuary he also made doorposts of olive wood, one-fourth of the wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6034, 'And the two doors were of cypress wood; two panels comprised one folding door, and two panels comprised the other folding door. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6035, 'Then he carved cherubim, palm trees, and open flowers on them, and overlaid them with gold applied evenly on the carved work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6036, 'And he built the inner court with three rows of hewn stone and a row of cedar beams. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6037, 'In the fourth year the foundation of the house of the Lord was laid, in the month of Ziv. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 6038, 'And in the eleventh year, in the month of Bul, which is the eighth month, the house was finished in all its details and according to all its plans. So he was seven years in building it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7001, 'But Solomon took thirteen years to build his own house; so he finished all his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7002, 'He also built the House of the Forest of Lebanon; its length was one hundred cubits, its width fifty cubits, and its height thirty cubits, with four rows of cedar pillars, and cedar beams on the pillars. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7003, 'And it was paneled with cedar above the beams that were on forty-five pillars, fifteen to a row. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7004, 'There were windows with beveled frames in three rows, and window was opposite window in three tiers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7005, 'And all the doorways and doorposts had rectangular frames; and window was opposite window in three tiers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7006, 'He also made the Hall of Pillars: its length was fifty cubits, and its width thirty cubits; and in front of them was a portico with pillars, and a canopy was in front of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7007, 'Then he made a hall for the throne, the Hall of Judgment, where he might judge; and it was paneled with cedar from floor to ceiling.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7008, 'And the house where he dwelt had another court inside the hall, of like workmanship. Solomon also made a house like this hall for Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter, whom he had taken as wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7009, 'All these were of costly stones cut to size, trimmed with saws, inside and out, from the foundation to the eaves, and also on the outside to the great court. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7010, 'The foundation was of costly stones, large stones, some ten cubits and some eight cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7011, 'And above were costly stones, hewn to size, and cedar wood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7012, 'The great court was enclosed with three rows of hewn stones and a row of cedar beams. So were the inner court of the house of the Lord and the vestibule of the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7013, 'Now King Solomon sent and brought Huram from Tyre. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7014, 'He was the son of a widow from the tribe of Naphtali, and his father was a man of Tyre, a bronze worker; he was filled with wisdom and understanding and skill in working with all kinds of bronze work. So he came to King Solomon and did all his work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7015, 'And he cast two pillars of bronze, each one eighteen cubits high, and a line of twelve cubits measured the circumference of each. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7016, 'Then he made two capitals of cast bronze, to set on the tops of the pillars. The height of one capital was five cubits, and the height of the other capital was five cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7017, 'He made a lattice network, with wreaths of chainwork, for the capitals which were on top of the pillars: seven chains for one capital and seven for the other capital. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7018, 'So he made the pillars, and two rows of pomegranates above the network all around to cover the capitals that were on top; and thus he did for the other capital. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7019, 'The capitals which were on top of the pillars in the hall were in the shape of lilies, four cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7020, 'The capitals on the two pillars also had pomegranates above, by the convex surface which was next to the network; and there were two hundred such pomegranates in rows on each of the capitals all around. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7021, 'Then he set up the pillars by the vestibule of the temple; he set up the pillar on the right and called its name Jachin, and he set up the pillar on the left and called its name Boaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7022, 'The tops of the pillars were in the shape of lilies. So the work of the pillars was finished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7023, 'And he made the Sea of cast bronze, ten cubits from one brim to the other; it was completely round. Its height was five cubits, and a line of thirty cubits measured its circumference. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7024, 'Below its brim were ornamental buds encircling it all around, ten to a cubit, all the way around the Sea. The ornamental buds were cast in two rows when it was cast. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7025, 'It stood on twelve oxen: three looking toward the north, three looking toward the west, three looking toward the south, and three looking toward the east; the Sea was set upon them, and all their back parts pointed inward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7026, 'It was a handbreadth thick; and its brim was shaped like the brim of a cup, like a lily blossom. It contained two thousand baths. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7027, 'He also made ten carts of bronze; four cubits was the length of each cart, four cubits its width, and three cubits its height. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7028, 'And this was the design of the carts: They had panels, and the panels were between frames; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7029, 'on the panels that were between the frames were lions, oxen, and cherubim. And on the frames was a pedestal on top. Below the lions and oxen were wreaths of plaited work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7030, 'Every cart had four bronze wheels and axles of bronze, and its four feet had supports. Under the laver were supports of cast bronze beside each wreath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7031, 'Its opening inside the crown at the top was one cubit in diameter; and the opening was round, shaped like a pedestal, one and a half cubits in outside diameter; and also on the opening were engravings, but the panels were square, not round. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7032, 'Under the panels were the four wheels, and the axles of the wheels were joined to the cart. The height of a wheel was one and a half cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 7033, 'The workmanship of the wheels was like the workmanship of a chariot wheel; their axle pins, their rims, their spokes, and their hubs were all of cast bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8001, 'Now Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of the tribes, the chief fathers of the children of Israel, to King Solomon in Jerusalem, that they might bring up the ark of the covenant of the Lord from the City of David, which is Zion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8002, 'Therefore all the men of Israel assembled with King Solomon at the feast in the month of Ethanim, which is the seventh month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8003, 'So all the elders of Israel came, and the priests took up the ark. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8004, 'Then they brought up the ark of the Lord, the tabernacle of meeting, and all the holy furnishings that were in the tabernacle. The priests and the Levites brought them up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8005, 'Also King Solomon, and all the congregation of Israel who were assembled with him, were with him before the ark, sacrificing sheep and oxen that could not be counted or numbered for multitude. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8006, 'Then the priests brought in the ark of the covenant of the Lord to its place, into the inner sanctuary of the temple, to the Most Holy Place, under the wings of the cherubim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8007, 'For the cherubim spread their two wings over the place of the ark, and the cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8008, 'The poles extended so that the ends of the poles could be seen from the holy place, in front of the inner sanctuary; but they could not be seen from outside. And they are there to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8009, 'Nothing was in the ark except the two tablets of stone which Moses put there at Horeb, when the Lord made a covenant with the children of Israel, when they came out of the land of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8010, 'And it came to pass, when the priests came out of the holy place, that the cloud filled the house of the Lord, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8011, 'so that the priests could not continue ministering because of the cloud; for the glory of the Lord filled the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8012, 'Then Solomon spoke: &ldquo;The Lord said He would dwell in the dark cloud. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8013, 'I have surely built You an exalted house, And a place for You to dwell in forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8014, 'Then the king turned around and blessed the whole assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel was standing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8015, 'And he said: &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, who spoke with His mouth to my father David, and with His hand has fulfilled it, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8016, '&rsquo;Since the day that I brought My people Israel out of Egypt, I have chosen no city from any tribe of Israel in which to build a house, that My name might be there; but I chose David to be over My people Israel.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8017, 'Now it was in the heart of my father David to build a temple for the name of the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8018, 'But the Lord said to my father David, &lsquo;Whereas it was in your heart to build a temple for My name, you did well that it was in your heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8019, 'Nevertheless you shall not build the temple, but your son who will come from your body, he shall build the temple for My name.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8020, 'So the Lord has fulfilled His word which He spoke; and I have filled the position of my father David, and sit on the throne of Israel, as the Lord promised; and I have built a temple for the name of the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8021, 'And there I have made a place for the ark, in which is the covenant of the Lord which He made with our fathers, when He brought them out of the land of Egypt.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8022, 'Then *Solomon stood before the altar of the Lord in the presence of all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands toward heaven; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8023, 'and he said: &ldquo;Lord God of Israel, there is no God in heaven above or on earth below like You, who keep Your covenant and mercy with Your servants who walk before You with all their hearts.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8024, 'You have kept what You promised Your servant David my father; You have both spoken with Your mouth and fulfilled it with Your hand, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8025, 'Therefore, Lord God of Israel, now keep what You promised Your servant David my father, saying, &lsquo;You shall not fail to have a man sit before Me on the throne of Israel, only if your sons take heed to their way, that they walk before Me as you have walked before Me.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8026, 'And now I pray, O God of Israel, let Your word come true, which You have spoken to Your servant David my father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8027, 'But will God indeed dwell on the earth? Behold, heaven and the heaven of heavens cannot contain You. How much less this temple which I have built! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8028, 'Yet regard the prayer of Your servant and his supplication, O Lord my God, and listen to the cry and the prayer which Your servant is praying before You today: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8029, 'that Your eyes may be open toward this temple night and day, toward the place of which You said, &lsquo;My name shall be there,&rsquo; that You may hear the prayer which Your servant makes toward this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8030, 'And may You hear the supplication of Your servant and of Your people Israel, when they pray toward this place. Hear in heaven Your dwelling place; and when You hear, forgive.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8031, 'When anyone sins against his neighbor, and is forced to take an oath, and comes and takes an oath before Your altar in this temple, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8032, 'then hear in heaven, and act, and judge Your servants, condemning the wicked, bringing his way on his head, and justifying the righteous by giving him according to his righteousness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8033, 'When Your people Israel are defeated before an enemy because they have sinned against You, and when they turn back to You and confess Your name, and pray and make supplication to You in this temple, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8034, 'then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of Your people Israel, and bring them back to the land which You gave to their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8035, 'When the heavens are shut up and there is no rain because they have sinned against You, when they pray toward this place and confess Your name, and turn from their sin because You afflict them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8036, 'then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of Your servants, Your people Israel, that You may teach them the good way in which they should walk; and send rain on Your land which You have given to Your people as an inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8037, 'When there is famine in the land, pestilence or blight or mildew, locusts or grasshoppers; when their enemy besieges them in the land of their cities; whatever plague or whatever sickness there is; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8038, 'whatever prayer, whatever supplication is made by anyone, or by all Your people Israel, when each one knows the plague of his own heart, and spreads out his hands toward this temple: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8039, 'then hear in heaven Your dwelling place, and forgive, and act, and give to everyone according to all his ways, whose heart You know (for You alone know the hearts of all the sons of men), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8040, 'that they may fear You all the days that they live in the land which You gave to our fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8041, 'Moreover, concerning a foreigner, who is not of Your people Israel, but has come from a far country for Your name&rsquo;s sake ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8042, '(for they will hear of Your great name and Your strong hand and Your outstretched arm), when he comes and prays toward this temple, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8043, 'hear in heaven Your dwelling place, and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to You, that all peoples of the earth may know Your name and fear You, as do Your people Israel, and that they may know that this temple which I have built is called by Your name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8044, 'When Your people go out to battle against their enemy, wherever You send them, and when they pray to the Lord toward the city which You have chosen and the temple which I have built for Your name, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8045, 'then hear in heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8046, 'When they sin against You (for there is no one who does not sin), and You become angry with them and deliver them to the enemy, and they take them captive to the land of the enemy, far or near; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8047, 'yet when they come to themselves in the land where they were carried captive, and repent, and make supplication to You in the land of those who took them captive, saying, &lsquo;We have sinned and done wrong, we have committed wickedness&rsquo;; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8048, 'and when they return to You with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their enemies who led them away captive, and pray to You toward their land which You gave to their fathers, the city which You have chosen and the temple which I have built for Your name: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8049, 'then hear in heaven Your dwelling place their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8050, 'and forgive Your people who have sinned against You, and all their transgressions which they have transgressed against You; and grant them compassion before those who took them captive, that they may have compassion on them ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8051, '(for they are Your people and Your inheritance, whom You brought out of Egypt, out of the iron furnace), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8052, 'that Your eyes may be open to the supplication of Your servant and the supplication of Your people Israel, to listen to them whenever they call to You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8053, 'For You separated them from among all the peoples of the earth to be Your inheritance, as You spoke by Your servant Moses, when You brought our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8054, 'And so it was, when Solomon had finished praying all this prayer and supplication to the Lord, that he arose from before the altar of the Lord, from kneeling on his knees with his hands spread up to heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8055, 'Then he stood and blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8056, 'Blessed be the Lord, who has given rest to His people Israel, according to all that He promised. There has not failed one word of all His good promise, which He promised through His servant Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8057, 'May the Lord our God be with us, as He was with our fathers. May He not leave us nor forsake us, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8058, 'that He may incline our hearts to Himself, to walk in all His ways, and to keep His commandments and His statutes and His judgments, which He commanded our fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8059, 'And may these words of mine, with which I have made supplication before the Lord, be near the Lord our God day and night, that He may maintain the cause of His servant and the cause of His people Israel, as each day may require, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8060, 'that all the peoples of the earth may know that the Lord is God; there is no other. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8061, 'Let your heart therefore be loyal to the Lord our God, to walk in His statutes and keep His commandments, as at this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8062, 'Then the king and all Israel with him offered sacrifices before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8063, 'And Solomon offered a sacrifice of peace offerings, which he offered to the Lord, twenty-two thousand bulls and one hundred and twenty thousand sheep. So the king and all the children of Israel dedicated the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8064, 'On the same day the king consecrated the middle of the court that was in front of the house of the Lord; for there he offered burnt offerings, grain offerings, and the fat of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar that was before the Lord was too small to receive the burnt offerings, the grain offerings, and the fat of the peace offerings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8065, 'At that time Solomon held a feast, and all Israel with him, a great assembly from the entrance of Hamath to the Brook of Egypt, before the Lord our God, seven days and seven more days &ndash; fourteen days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 8066, 'On the eighth day he sent the people away; and they blessed the king, and went to their tents joyful and glad of heart for all the good that the Lord had done for His servant David, and for Israel His people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9001, 'And it came to pass, when Solomon had finished building the house of the Lord and the king&rsquo;s house, and all Solomon&rsquo;s desire which he wanted to do, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9002, 'that the Lord appeared to Solomon the second time, as He had appeared to him at Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9003, 'And the Lord said to him: &ldquo;I have heard your prayer and your supplication that you have made before Me; I have consecrated this house which you have built to put My name there forever, and My eyes and My heart will be there perpetually. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9004, 'Now if you walk before Me as your father David walked, in integrity of heart and in uprightness, to do according to all that I have commanded you, and if you keep My statutes and My judgments, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9005, 'then I will establish the throne of your kingdom over Israel forever, as I promised David your father, saying, &lsquo;You shall not fail to have a man on the throne of Israel.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9006, 'But if you or your sons at all turn from following Me, and do not keep My commandments and My statutes which I have set before you, but go and serve other gods and worship them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9007, 'then I will cut off Israel from the land which I have given them; and this house which I have consecrated for My name I will cast out of My sight. Israel will be a proverb and a byword among all peoples. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9008, 'And as for this house, which is exalted, everyone who passes by it will be astonished and will hiss, and say, &lsquo;Why has the Lord done thus to this land and to this house?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9009, 'Then they will answer, &lsquo;Because they forsook the Lord their God, who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt, and have embraced other gods, and worshiped them and served them; therefore the Lord has brought all this calamity on them.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9010, 'Now it happened at the end of twenty years, when Solomon had built the two houses, the house of the Lord and the king&rsquo;s house ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9011, '(Hiram the king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with cedar and cypress and gold, as much as he desired), that King Solomon then gave Hiram twenty cities in the land of Galilee. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9012, 'Then Hiram went from Tyre to see the cities which Solomon had given him, but they did not please him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9013, 'So he said, &ldquo;What kind of cities are these which you have given me, my brother?&rdquo; And he called them the land of Cabul, as they are to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9014, 'Then Hiram sent the king one hundred and twenty talents of gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9015, 'And this is the reason for the labor force which King Solomon raised: to build the house of the Lord, his own house, the Millo, the wall of Jerusalem, Hazor, Megiddo, and Gezer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9016, '(Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up and taken Gezer and burned it with fire, had killed the Canaanites who dwelt in the city, and had given it as a dowry to his daughter, Solomon&rsquo;s wife.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9017, 'And Solomon built Gezer, Lower Beth Horon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9018, 'Baalath, and Tadmor in the wilderness, in the land of Judah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9019, 'all the storage cities that Solomon had, cities for his chariots and cities for his cavalry, and whatever Solomon desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9020, 'All the people who were left of the Amorites, Hittites, Perizzites, Hivites, and Jebusites, who were not of the children of Israel &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9021, 'that is, their descendants who were left in the land after them, whom the children of Israel had not been able to destroy completely &ndash; from these Solomon raised forced labor, as it is to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9022, 'But of the children of Israel Solomon made no forced laborers, because they were men of war and his servants: his officers, his captains, commanders of his chariots, and his cavalry. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9023, 'Others were chiefs of the officials who were over Solomon&rsquo;s work: five hundred and fifty, who ruled over the people who did the work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9024, 'But Pharaoh&rsquo;s daughter came up from the City of David to her house which Solomon had built for her. Then he built the Millo. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9025, 'Now three times a year Solomon offered burnt offerings and peace offerings on the altar which he had built for the Lord, and he burned incense with them on the altar that was before the Lord. So he finished the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9026, 'King Solomon also built a fleet of ships at Ezion Geber, which is near Elath on the shore of the Red Sea, in the land of Edom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9027, 'Then Hiram sent his servants with the fleet, seamen who knew the sea, to work with the servants of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 9028, 'And they went to Ophir, and acquired four hundred and twenty talents of gold from there, and brought it to King Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10001, 'Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning the name of the Lord, she came to test him with hard questions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10002, 'She came to Jerusalem with a very great retinue, with camels that bore spices, very much gold, and precious stones; and when she came to Solomon, she spoke with him about all that was in her heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10003, 'So Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing so difficult for the king that he could not explain it to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10004, 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen all the wisdom of Solomon, the house that he had built, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10005, 'the food on his table, the seating of his servants, the service of his waiters and their apparel, his cupbearers, and his entryway by which he went up to the house of the Lord, there was no more spirit in her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10006, 'Then she said to the king: &ldquo;It was a true report which I heard in my own land about your words and your wisdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10007, 'However I did not believe the words until I came and saw with my own eyes; and indeed the half was not told me. Your wisdom and prosperity exceed the fame of which I heard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10008, 'Happy are your men and happy are these your servants, who stand continually before you and hear your wisdom! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10009, 'Blessed be the Lord your God, who delighted in you, setting you on the throne of Israel! Because the Lord has loved Israel forever, therefore He made you king, to do justice and righteousness.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10010, 'Then she gave the king one hundred and twenty talents of gold, spices in great quantity, and precious stones. There never again came such abundance of spices as the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10011, 'Also, the ships of Hiram, which brought gold from Ophir, brought great quantities of almug wood and precious stones from Ophir. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10012, 'And the king made steps of the almug wood for the house of the Lord and for the king&rsquo;s house, also harps and stringed instruments for singers. There never again came such almug wood, nor has the like been seen to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10013, 'Now King Solomon gave the queen of Sheba all she desired, whatever she asked, besides what Solomon had given her according to the royal generosity. So she turned and went to her own country, she and her servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10014, 'The weight of gold that came to Solomon yearly was six hundred and sixty-six talents of gold, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10015, 'besides that from the traveling merchants, from the income of traders, from all the kings of Arabia, and from the governors of the country. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10016, 'And King Solomon made two hundred large shields of hammered gold; six hundred shekels of gold went into each shield. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10017, 'He also made three hundred shields of hammered gold; three minas of gold went into each shield. The king put them in the House of the Forest of Lebanon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10018, 'Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with pure gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10019, 'The throne had six steps, and the top of the throne was round at the back; there were armrests on either side of the place of the seat, and two lions stood beside the armrests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10020, 'Twelve lions stood there, one on each side of the six steps; nothing like this had been made for any other kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10021, 'All King Solomon&rsquo;s drinking vessels were gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were pure gold. Not one was silver, for this was accounted as nothing in the days of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10022, 'For the king had merchant ships at sea with the fleet of Hiram. Once every three years the merchant ships came bringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and monkeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10023, 'So King Solomon surpassed all the kings of the earth in riches and wisdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10024, 'Now all the earth sought the presence of Solomon to hear his wisdom, which God had put in his heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10025, 'Each man brought his present: articles of silver and gold, garments, armor, spices, horses, and mules, at a set rate year by year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10026, 'And Solomon gathered chariots and horsemen; he had one thousand four hundred chariots and twelve thousand horsemen, whom he stationed in the chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10027, 'The king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stones, and he made cedar trees as abundant as the sycamores which are in the lowland. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10028, 'Also Solomon had horses imported from Egypt and Keveh; the king&rsquo;s merchants bought them in Keveh at the current price. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 10029, 'Now a chariot that was imported from Egypt cost six hundred shekels of silver, and a horse one hundred and fifty; and thus, through their agents, they exported them to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Syria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11001, 'But King Solomon loved many foreign women, as well as the daughter of Pharaoh: women of the Moabites, Ammonites, Edomites, Sidonians, and Hittites &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11002, 'from the nations of whom the Lord had said to the children of Israel, &ldquo;You shall not intermarry with them, nor they with you. Surely they will turn away your hearts after their gods.&rdquo; Solomon clung to these in love. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11003, 'And he had seven hundred wives, princesses, and three hundred concubines; and his wives turned away his heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11004, 'For it was so, when Solomon was old, that his wives turned his heart after other gods; and his heart was not loyal to the Lord his God, as was the heart of his father David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11005, 'For Solomon went after Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, and after Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11006, 'Solomon did evil in the sight of the Lord, and did not fully follow the Lord, as did his father David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11007, 'Then Solomon built a high place for Chemosh the abomination of Moab, on the hill that is east of Jerusalem, and for Molech the abomination of the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11008, 'And he did likewise for all his foreign wives, who burned incense and sacrificed to their gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11009, 'So the Lord became angry with Solomon, because his heart had turned from the Lord God of Israel, who had appeared to him twice, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11010, 'and had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go after other gods; but he did not keep what the Lord had commanded. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11011, 'Therefore the Lord said to Solomon, &ldquo;Because you have done this, and have not kept My covenant and My statutes, which I have commanded you, I will surely tear the kingdom away from you and give it to your servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11012, 'Nevertheless I will not do it in your days, for the sake of your father David; I will tear it out of the hand of your son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11013, 'However I will not tear away the whole kingdom; I will give one tribe to your son for the sake of my servant David, and for the sake of Jerusalem which I have chosen.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11014, 'Now the Lord raised up an adversary against Solomon, Hadad the Edomite; he was a descendant of the king in Edom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11015, 'For it happened, when David was in Edom, and Joab the commander of the army had gone up to bury the slain, after he had killed every male in Edom ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11016, '(because for six months Joab remained there with all Israel, until he had cut down every male in Edom), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11017, 'that Hadad fled to go to Egypt, he and certain Edomites of his father&rsquo;s servants with him. Hadad was still a little child. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11018, 'Then they arose from Midian and came to Paran; and they took men with them from Paran and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who gave him a house, apportioned food for him, and gave him land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11019, 'And Hadad found great favor in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he gave him as wife the sister of his own wife, that is, the sister of Queen Tahpenes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11020, 'Then the sister of Tahpenes bore him Genubath his son, whom Tahpenes weaned in Pharaoh&rsquo;s house. And Genubath was in Pharaoh&rsquo;s household among the sons of Pharaoh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11021, 'So when Hadad heard in Egypt that David rested with his fathers, and that Joab the commander of the army was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, &ldquo;Let me depart, that I may go to my own country.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11022, 'Then Pharaoh said to him, &ldquo;But what have you lacked with me, that suddenly you seek to go to your own country?&rdquo; So he answered, &ldquo;Nothing, but do let me go anyway.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11023, 'And God raised up another adversary against him, Rezon the son of Eliadah, who had fled from his lord, Hadadezer king of Zobah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11024, 'So he gathered men to him and became captain over a band of raiders, when David killed those of Zobah. And they went to Damascus and dwelt there, and reigned in Damascus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11025, 'He was an adversary of Israel all the days of Solomon (besides the trouble that Hadad caused); and he abhorred Israel, and reigned over Syria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11026, 'Then Solomon&rsquo;s servant, Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephraimite from Zereda, whose mother&rsquo;s name was Zeruah, a widow, also rebelled against the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11027, 'And this is what caused him to rebel against the king: Solomon had built the Millo and repaired the damages to the City of David his father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11028, 'The man Jeroboam was a mighty man of valor; and Solomon, seeing that the young man was industrious, made him the officer over all the labor force of the house of Joseph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11029, 'Now it happened at that time, when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem, that the prophet Ahijah the Shilonite met him on the way; and he had clothed himself with a new garment, and the two were alone in the field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11030, 'Then Ahijah took hold of the new garment that was on him, and tore it into twelve pieces. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11031, 'And he said to Jeroboam, &ldquo;Take for yourself ten pieces, for thus says the Lord, the God of Israel: &lsquo;Behold, I will tear the kingdom out of the hand of Solomon and will give ten tribes to you ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11032, '(but he shall have one tribe for the sake of My servant David, and for the sake of Jerusalem, the city which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11033, 'because they have forsaken Me, and worshiped Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of the Moabites, and Milcom the god of the people of Ammon, and have not walked in My ways to do what is right in My eyes and keep My statutes and My judgments, as did his father David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11034, 'However I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand, because I have made him ruler all the days of his life for the sake of My servant David, whom I chose because he kept My commandments and My statutes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11035, 'But I will take the kingdom out of his son&rsquo;s hand and give it to you &ndash; ten tribes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11036, 'And to his son I will give one tribe, that My servant David may always have a lamp before Me in Jerusalem, the city which I have chosen for Myself, to put My name there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11037, 'So I will take you, and you shall reign over all your heart desires, and you shall be king over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11038, 'Then it shall be, if you heed all that I command you, walk in My ways, and do what is right in My sight, to keep My statutes and My commandments, as My servant David did, then I will be with you and build for you an enduring house, as I built for David, and will give Israel to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11039, 'And I will afflict the descendants of David because of this, but not forever.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11040, 'Solomon therefore sought to kill Jeroboam. But Jeroboam arose and fled to Egypt, to Shishak king of Egypt, and was in Egypt until the death of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11041, 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, all that he did, and his wisdom, are they not written in the book of the acts of Solomon? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11042, 'And the period that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 11043, 'Then Solomon rested with his fathers, and was buried in the City of David his father. And Rehoboam his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12001, 'And Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had gone to Shechem to make him king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12002, 'So it happened, when Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard it (he was still in Egypt, for he had fled from the presence of King Solomon and had been dwelling in Egypt), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12003, 'that they sent and called him. Then Jeroboam and the whole assembly of Israel came and spoke to Rehoboam, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12004, 'Your father made our yoke heavy; now therefore, lighten the burdensome service of your father, and his heavy yoke which he put on us, and we will serve you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12005, 'So he said to them, &ldquo;Depart for three days, then come back to me.&rdquo; And the people departed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12006, 'Then King Rehoboam consulted the elders who stood before his father Solomon while he still lived, and he said, &ldquo;How do you advise me to answer these people?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12007, 'And they spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;If you will be a servant to these people today, and serve them, and answer them, and speak good words to them, then they will be your servants forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12008, 'But he rejected the advice which the elders had given him, and consulted the young men who had grown up with him, who stood before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12009, 'And he said to them, &ldquo;What advice do you give? How should we answer this people who have spoken to me, saying, &lsquo;Lighten the yoke which your father put on us&rsquo;?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12010, 'Then the young men who had grown up with him spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;Thus you should speak to this people who have spoken to you, saying, &lsquo;Your father made our yoke heavy, but you make it lighter on us&rsquo; &ndash; thus you shall say to them: &lsquo;My little finger shall be thicker than my father&rsquo;s waist! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12011, 'And now, whereas my father put a heavy yoke on you, I will add to your yoke; my father chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scourges!&rsquo; &ldquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12012, 'So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as the king had directed, saying, &ldquo;Come back to me the third day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12013, 'Then the king answered the people roughly, and rejected the advice which the elders had given him; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12014, 'and he spoke to them according to the advice of the young men, saying, &ldquo;My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to your yoke; my father chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scourges!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12015, 'So the king did not listen to the people; for the turn of events was from the Lord, that He might fulfill His word, which the Lord had spoken by Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12016, 'Now when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the people answered the king, saying: &ldquo;What share have we in David? We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse. To your tents, O Israel! Now, see to your own house, O David!&rdquo; So Israel departed to their tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12017, 'But Rehoboam reigned over the children of Israel who dwelt in the cities of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12018, 'Then King Rehoboam sent Adoram, who was in charge of the revenue; but all Israel stoned him with stones, and he died. Therefore King Rehoboam mounted his chariot in haste to flee to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12019, 'So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12020, 'Now it came to pass when all Israel heard that Jeroboam had come back, they sent for him and called him to the congregation, and made him king over all Israel. There was none who followed the house of David, but the tribe of Judah only. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12021, 'And when Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house of Judah with the tribe of Benjamin, one hundred and eighty thousand chosen men who were warriors, to fight against the house of Israel, that he might restore the kingdom to Rehoboam the son of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12022, 'But the word of God came to Shemaiah the man of God, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12023, 'Speak to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, to all the house of Judah and Benjamin, and to the rest of the people, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12024, '&rsquo;Thus says the Lord: You shall not go up nor fight against your brethren the children of Israel. Let every man return to his house, for this thing is from Me. &lsquo; Therefore they obeyed the word of the Lord, and turned back, according to the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12025, 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem in the mountains of Ephraim, and dwelt there. Also he went out from there and built Penuel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12026, 'And Jeroboam said in his heart, &ldquo;Now the kingdom may return to the house of David: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12027, 'If these people go up to offer sacrifices in the house of the Lord at Jerusalem, then the heart of this people will turn back to their lord, Rehoboam king of Judah, and they will kill me and go back to Rehoboam king of Judah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12028, 'Therefore the king asked advice, made two calves of gold, and said to the people, &ldquo;It is too much for you to go up to Jerusalem. Here are your gods, O Israel, which brought you up from the land of Egypt!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12029, 'And he set up one in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12030, 'Now this thing became a sin, for the people went to worship before the one as far as Dan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12031, 'He made shrines on the high places, and made priests from every class of people, who were not of the sons of Levi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12032, 'Jeroboam ordained a feast on the fifteenth day of the eighth month, like the feast that was in Judah, and offered sacrifices on the altar. So he did at Bethel, sacrificing to the calves that he had made. And at Bethel he installed the priests of the high places which he had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 12033, 'So he made offerings on the altar which he had made at Bethel on the fifteenth day of the eighth month, in the month which he had devised in his own heart. And he ordained a feast for the children of Israel, and offered sacrifices on the altar and burned incense. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13001, 'And behold, a man of God went from Judah to Bethel by the word of the Lord, and Jeroboam stood by the altar to burn incense. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13002, 'Then he cried out against the altar by the word of the Lord, and said, &ldquo;O altar, altar! Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Behold, a child, Josiah by name, shall be born to the house of David; and on you he shall sacrifice the priests of the high places who burn incense on you, and men&rsquo;s bones shall be burned on you.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13003, 'And he gave a sign the same day, saying, &ldquo;This is the sign which the Lord has spoken: Surely the altar shall split apart, and the ashes on it shall be poured out.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13004, 'So it came to pass when King Jeroboam heard the saying of the man of God, who cried out against the altar in Bethel, that he stretched out his hand from the altar, saying, &ldquo;Arrest him!&rdquo; Then his hand, which he stretched out toward him, withered, so that he could not pull it back to himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13005, 'The altar also was split apart, and the ashes poured out from the altar, according to the sign which the man of God had given by the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13006, 'Then the king answered and said to the man of God, &ldquo;Please entreat the favor of the Lord your God, and pray for me, that my hand may be restored to me.&rdquo; So the man of God entreated the Lord, and the king&rsquo;s hand was restored to him, and became as before. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13007, 'Then the king said to the man of God, &ldquo;Come home with me and refresh yourself, and I will give you a reward.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13008, 'But the man of God said to the king, &ldquo;If you were to give me half your house, I would not go in with you; nor would I eat bread nor drink water in this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13009, 'For so it was commanded me by the word of the Lord, saying, &lsquo;You shall not eat bread, nor drink water, nor return by the same way you came.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13010, 'So he went another way and did not return by the way he came to Bethel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13011, 'Now an old prophet dwelt in Bethel, and his sons came and told him all the works that the man of God had done that day in Bethel; they also told their father the words which he had spoken to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13012, 'And their father said to them, &ldquo;Which way did he go?&rdquo; For his sons had seen which way the man of God went who came from Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13013, 'Then he said to his sons, &ldquo;Saddle the donkey for me.&rdquo; So they saddled the donkey for him; and he rode on it, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13014, 'and went after the man of God, and found him sitting under an oak. Then he said to him, &ldquo;Are you the man of God who came from Judah?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;I am.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13015, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Come home with me and eat bread.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13016, 'And he said, &ldquo;I cannot return with you nor go in with you; neither can I eat bread nor drink water with you in this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13017, 'For I have been told by the word of the Lord, &lsquo;You shall not eat bread nor drink water there, nor return by going the way you came.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13018, 'He said to him, &ldquo;I too am a prophet as you are, and an angel spoke to me by the word of the Lord, saying, &lsquo;Bring him back with you to your house, that he may eat bread and drink water.&rsquo; &ldquo; (He was lying to him.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13019, 'So he went back with him, and ate bread in his house, and drank water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13020, 'Now it happened, as they sat at the table, that the word of the Lord came to the prophet who had brought him back; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13021, 'and he cried out to the man of God who came from Judah, saying, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Because you have disobeyed the word of the Lord, and have not kept the commandment which the Lord your God commanded you, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13022, 'but you came back, ate bread, and drank water in the place of which the Lord said to you, &ldquo;Eat no bread and drink no water,&rdquo; your corpse shall not come to the tomb of your fathers.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13023, 'So it was, after he had eaten bread and after he had drunk, that he saddled the donkey for him, the prophet whom he had brought back. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13024, 'When he was gone, a lion met him on the road and killed him. And his corpse was thrown on the road, and the donkey stood by it. The lion also stood by the corpse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13025, 'And there, men passed by and saw the corpse thrown on the road, and the lion standing by the corpse. Then they went and told it in the city where the old prophet dwelt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13026, 'Now when the prophet who had brought him back from the way heard it, he said, &ldquo;It is the man of God who was disobedient to the word of the Lord. Therefore the Lord has delivered him to the lion, which has torn him and killed him, according to the word of the Lord which He spoke to him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13027, 'And he spoke to his sons, saying, &ldquo;Saddle the donkey for me.&rdquo; So they saddled it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13028, 'Then he went and found his corpse thrown on the road, and the donkey and the lion standing by the corpse. The lion had not eaten the corpse nor torn the donkey. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13029, 'And the prophet took up the corpse of the man of God, laid it on the donkey, and brought it back. So the old prophet came to the city to mourn, and to bury him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13030, 'Then he laid the corpse in his own tomb; and they mourned over him, saying, &ldquo;Alas, my brother!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13031, 'So it was, after he had buried him, that he spoke to his sons, saying, &ldquo;When I am dead, then bury me in the tomb where the man of God is buried; lay my bones beside his bones. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13032, 'For the saying which he cried out by the word of the Lord against the altar in Bethel, and against all the shrines on the high places which are in the cities of Samaria, will surely come to pass.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13033, 'After this event Jeroboam did not turn from his evil way, but again he made priests from every class of people for the high places; whoever wished, he consecrated him, and he became one of the priests of the high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 13034, 'And this thing was the sin of the house of Jeroboam, so as to exterminate and destroy it from the face of the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14001, 'At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam became sick. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14002, 'And Jeroboam said to his wife, &ldquo;Please arise, and disguise yourself, that they may not recognize you as the wife of Jeroboam, and go to Shiloh. Indeed, Ahijah the prophet is there, who told me that I would be king over this people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14003, 'Also take with you ten loaves, some cakes, and a jar of honey, and go to him; he will tell you what will become of the child.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14004, 'And Jeroboam&rsquo;s wife did so; she arose and went to Shiloh, and came to the house of Ahijah. But Ahijah could not see, for his eyes were glazed by reason of his age. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14005, 'Now the Lord had said to Ahijah, &ldquo;Here is the wife of Jeroboam, coming to ask you something about her son, for he is sick. Thus and thus you shall say to her; for it will be, when she comes in, that she will pretend to be another woman.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14006, 'And so it was, when Ahijah heard the sound of her footsteps as she came through the door, he said, &ldquo;Come in, wife of Jeroboam. Why do you pretend to be another person? For I have been sent to you with bad news. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14007, 'Go, tell Jeroboam, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &ldquo;Because I exalted you from among the people, and made you ruler over My people Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14008, 'and tore the kingdom away from the house of David, and gave it to you; and yet you have not been as My servant David, who kept My commandments and who followed Me with all his heart, to do only what was right in My eyes; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14009, 'but you have done more evil than all who were before you, for you have gone and made for yourself other gods and molded images to provoke Me to anger, and have cast Me behind your back &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14010, 'therefore behold! I will bring disaster on the house of Jeroboam, and will cut off from Jeroboam every male in Israel, bond and free; I will take away the remnant of the house of Jeroboam, as one takes away refuse until it is all gone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14011, 'The dogs shall eat whoever belongs to Jeroboam and dies in the city, and the birds of the air shall eat whoever dies in the field; for the Lord has spoken!&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14012, 'Arise therefore, go to your own house. When your feet enter the city, the child shall die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14013, 'And all Israel shall mourn for him and bury him, for he is the only one of Jeroboam who shall come to the grave, because in him there is found something good toward the Lord God of Israel in the house of Jeroboam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14014, 'Moreover the Lord will raise up for Himself a king over Israel who shall cut off the house of Jeroboam; this is the day. What? Even now! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14015, 'For the Lord will strike Israel, as a reed is shaken in the water. He will uproot Israel from this good land which He gave to their fathers, and will scatter them beyond the River, because they have made their wooden images, provoking the Lord to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14016, 'And He will give Israel up because of the sins of Jeroboam, who sinned and who made Israel sin.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 14017, 'Then Jeroboam&rsquo;s wife arose and departed, and came to Tirzah. When she came to the threshold of the house, the child died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15001, 'In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam the son of Nebat, Abijam became king over Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15002, 'He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Maachah the granddaughter of Abishalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15003, 'And he walked in all the sins of his father, which he had done before him; his heart was not loyal to the Lord his God, as was the heart of his father David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15004, 'Nevertheless for David&rsquo;s sake the Lord his God gave him a lamp in Jerusalem, by setting up his son after him and by establishing Jerusalem; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15005, 'because David did what was right in the eyes of the Lord, and had not turned aside from anything that He commanded him all the days of his life, except in the matter of Uriah the Hittite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15006, 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his life. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15007, 'Now the rest of the acts of Abijam, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? And there was war between Abijam and Jeroboam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15008, 'So Abijam rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the City of David. Then Asa his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15009, 'In the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa became king over Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15010, 'And he reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem. His grandmother&rsquo;s name was Maachah the granddaughter of Abishalom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15011, 'Asa did what was right in the eyes of the Lord, as did his father David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15012, 'And he banished the perverted persons from the land, and removed all the idols that his fathers had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15013, 'Also he removed Maachah his grandmother from being queen mother, because she had made an obscene image of Asherah. And Asa cut down her obscene image and burned it by the Brook Kidron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15014, 'But the high places were not removed. Nevertheless Asa&rsquo;s heart was loyal to the Lord all his days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15015, 'He also brought into the house of the Lord the things which his father had dedicated, and the things which he himself had dedicated: silver and gold and utensils. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15016, 'Now there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15017, 'And Baasha king of Israel came up against Judah, and built Ramah, that he might let none go out or come in to Asa king of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15018, 'Then Asa took all the silver and gold that was left in the treasuries of the house of the Lord and the treasuries of the king&rsquo;s house, and delivered them into the hand of his servants. And King Asa sent them to Ben-Hadad the son of Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, king of Syria, who dwelt in Damascus, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15019, 'Let there be a treaty between you and me, as there was between my father and your father. See, I have sent you a present of silver and gold. Come and break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, so that he will withdraw from me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15020, 'So Ben-Hadad heeded King Asa, and sent the captains of his armies against the cities of Israel. He attacked Ijon, Dan, Abel Beth Maachah, and all Chinneroth, with all the land of Naphtali. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15021, 'Now it happened, when Baasha heard it, that he stopped building Ramah, and remained in Tirzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15022, 'Then King Asa made a proclamation throughout all Judah; none was exempted. And they took away the stones and timber of Ramah, which Baasha had used for building; and with them King Asa built Geba of Benjamin, and Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15023, 'The rest of all the acts of Asa, all his might, all that he did, and the cities which he built, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? But in the time of his old age he was diseased in his feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15024, 'So Asa rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the City of David his father. Then Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15025, 'Now Nadab the son of Jeroboam became king over Israel in the second year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15026, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin by which he had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15027, 'Then Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house of Issachar, conspired against him. And Baasha killed him at Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines, while Nadab and all Israel laid siege to Gibbethon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15028, 'Baasha killed him in the third year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15029, 'And it was so, when he became king, that he killed all the house of Jeroboam. He did not leave to Jeroboam anyone that breathed, until he had destroyed him, according to the word of the Lord which He had spoken by His servant Ahijah the Shilonite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15030, 'because of the sins of Jeroboam, which he had sinned and by which he had made Israel sin, because of his provocation with which he had provoked the Lord God of Israel to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15031, 'Now the rest of the acts of Nadab, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15032, 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15033, 'In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah became king over all Israel in Tirzah, and reigned twenty-four years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 15034, 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord, and walked in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin by which he had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16001, 'Then the word of the Lord came to Jehu the son of Hanani, against Baasha, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16002, 'Inasmuch as I lifted you out of the dust and made you ruler over My people Israel, and you have walked in the way of Jeroboam, and have made My people Israel sin, to provoke Me to anger with their sins, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16003, 'surely I will take away the posterity of Baasha and the posterity of his house, and I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16004, 'The dogs shall eat whoever belongs to Baasha and dies in the city, and the birds of the air shall eat whoever dies in the fields. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16005, 'Now the rest of the acts of Baasha, what he did, and his might, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16006, 'So Baasha rested with his fathers and was buried in Tirzah. Then Elah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16007, 'And also the word of the Lord came by the prophet Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha and his house, because of all the evil that he did in the sight of the Lord in provoking Him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house of Jeroboam, and because he killed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16008, 'In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha became king over Israel, and reigned two years in Tirzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16009, 'Now his servant Zimri, commander of half his chariots, conspired against him as he was in Tirzah drinking himself drunk in the house of Arza, steward of his house in Tirzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16010, 'And Zimri went in and struck him and killed him in the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16011, 'Then it came to pass, when he began to reign, as soon as he was seated on his throne, that he killed all the household of Baasha; he did not leave him one male, neither of his relatives nor of his friends. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16012, 'Thus Zimri destroyed all the household of Baasha, according to the word of the Lord, which He spoke against Baasha by Jehu the prophet, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16013, 'for all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son, by which they had sinned and by which they had made Israel sin, in provoking the Lord God of Israel to anger with their idols. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16014, 'Now the rest of the acts of Elah, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16015, 'In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri had reigned in Tirzah seven days. And the people were encamped against Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16016, 'Now the people who were encamped heard it said, &ldquo;Zimri has conspired and also has killed the king.&rdquo; So all Israel made Omri, the commander of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16017, 'Then Omri and all Israel with him went up from Gibbethon, and they besieged Tirzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16018, 'And it happened, when Zimri saw that the city was taken, that he went into the citadel of the king&rsquo;s house and burned the king&rsquo;s house down upon himself with fire, and died, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16019, 'because of the sins which he had committed in doing evil in the sight of the Lord, in walking in the way of Jeroboam, and in his sin which he had committed to make Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16020, 'Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and the treason he committed, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16021, 'Then the people of Israel were divided into two parts: half of the people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king, and half followed Omri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16022, 'But the people who followed Omri prevailed over the people who followed Tibni the son of Ginath. So Tibni died and Omri reigned. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16023, 'In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri became king over Israel, and reigned twelve years. Six years he reigned in Tirzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16024, 'And he bought the hill of Samaria from Shemer for two talents of silver; then he built on the hill, and called the name of the city which he built, Samaria, after the name of Shemer, owner of the hill. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16025, 'Omri did evil in the eyes of the Lord, and did worse than all who were before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16026, 'For he walked in all the ways of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and in his sin by which he had made Israel sin, provoking the Lord God of Israel to anger with their idols. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16027, 'Now the rest of the acts of Omri which he did, and the might that he showed, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16028, 'So Omri rested with his fathers and was buried in Samaria. Then Ahab his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16029, 'In the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, Ahab the son of Omri became king over Israel; and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over Israel in Samaria twenty-two years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16030, 'Now Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the Lord, more than all who were before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16031, 'And it came to pass, as though it had been a trivial thing for him to walk in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, that he took as wife Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal, king of the Sidonians; and he went and served Baal and worshiped him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16032, 'Then he set up an altar for Baal in the temple of Baal, which he had built in Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16033, 'And Ahab made a wooden image. Ahab did more to provoke the Lord God of Israel to anger than all the kings of Israel who were before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 16034, 'In his days Hiel of Bethel built Jericho. He laid its foundation with Abiram his firstborn, and with his youngest son Segub he set up its gates, according to the word of the Lord, which He had spoken through Joshua the son of Nun. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17001, 'And Elijah the Tishbite, of the inhabitants of Gilead, said to Ahab, &ldquo;As the Lord God of Israel lives, before whom I stand, there shall not be dew nor rain these years, except at my word.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17002, 'Then the word of the Lord came to him, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17003, 'Get away from here and turn eastward, and hide by the Brook Cherith, which flows into the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17004, 'And it will be that you shall drink from the brook, and I have commanded the ravens to feed you there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17005, 'So he went and did according to the word of the Lord, for he went and stayed by the Brook Cherith, which flows into the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17006, 'The ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning, and bread and meat in the evening; and he drank from the brook. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17007, 'And it happened after a while that the brook dried up, because there had been no rain in the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17008, 'Then the word of the Lord came to him,* saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17009, 'Arise, go to Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and dwell there. See, I have commanded a widow there to provide for you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17010, 'So he arose and went to Zarephath. And when he came to the gate of the city, indeed a widow was there gathering sticks. And he called to her and said, &ldquo;Please bring me a little water in a cup, that I may drink.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17011, 'And as she was going to get it, he called to her and said, &ldquo;Please bring me a morsel of bread in your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17012, 'So she said, &ldquo;As the Lord your God lives, I do not have bread, only a handful of flour in a bin, and a little oil in a jar; and see, I am gathering a couple of sticks that I may go in and prepare it for myself and my son, that we may eat it, and die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17013, 'And Elijah said to her, &ldquo;Do not fear; go and do as you have said, but make me a small cake from it first, and bring it to me; and afterward make some for yourself and your son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17014, 'For thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;The bin of flour shall not be used up, nor shall the jar of oil run dry, until the day the Lord sends rain on the earth.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17015, 'So she went away and did according to the word of Elijah; and she and he and her household ate for many days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17016, 'The bin of flour was not used up, nor did the jar of oil run dry, according to the word of the Lord which He spoke by Elijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17017, 'Now it happened after these things that the son of the woman who owned the house became sick. And his sickness was so serious that there was no breath left in him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17018, 'So she said to Elijah, &ldquo;What have I to do with you, O man of God? Have you come to me to bring my sin to remembrance, and to kill my son?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17019, 'And he said to her, &ldquo;Give me your son.&rdquo; So he took him out of her arms and carried him to the upper room where he was staying, and laid him on his own bed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17020, 'Then he cried out to the Lord and said, &ldquo;O Lord my God, have You also brought tragedy on the widow with whom I lodge, by killing her son?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17021, 'And he stretched himself out on the child three times, and cried out to the Lord and said, &ldquo;O Lord my God, I pray, let this child&rsquo;s soul come back to him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17022, 'Then the Lord heard the voice of Elijah; and the soul of the child came back to him, and he revived. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17023, 'And Elijah took the child and brought him down from the upper room into the house, and gave him to his mother. And Elijah said, &ldquo;See, your son lives!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 17024, 'Then the woman said to Elijah, &ldquo;Now by this I know that you are a man of God, and that the word of the Lord in your mouth is the truth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18001, 'And it came to pass after many days that the word of the Lord came to Elijah, in the third year, saying, &ldquo;Go, present yourself to Ahab, and I will send rain on the earth.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18002, 'So Elijah went to present himself to Ahab; and there was a severe famine in Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18003, 'And Ahab had called Obadiah, who was in charge of his house. (Now Obadiah feared the Lord greatly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18004, 'For so it was, while Jezebel massacred the prophets of the Lord, that Obadiah had taken one hundred prophets and hidden them, fifty to a cave, and had fed them with bread and water.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18005, 'And Ahab had said to Obadiah, &ldquo;Go into the land to all the springs of water and to all the brooks; perhaps we may find grass to keep the horses and mules alive, so that we will not have to kill any livestock.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18006, 'So they divided the land between them to explore it; Ahab went one way by himself, and Obadiah went another way by himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18007, 'Now as Obadiah was on his way, suddenly Elijah met him; and he recognized him, and fell on his face, and said, &ldquo;Is that you, my lord Elijah?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18008, 'And he answered him, &ldquo;It is I. Go, tell your master, &lsquo;Elijah is here.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18009, 'So he said, &ldquo;How have I sinned, that you are delivering your servant into the hand of Ahab, to kill me? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18010, 'As the Lord your God lives, there is no nation or kingdom where my master has not sent someone to hunt for you; and when they said, &lsquo;He is not here,&rsquo; he took an oath from the kingdom or nation that they could not find you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18011, 'And now you say, &lsquo;Go, tell your master, &ldquo;Elijah is here&rdquo; &lsquo;! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18012, 'And it shall come to pass, as soon as I am gone from you, that the Spirit of the Lord will carry you to a place I do not know; so when I go and tell Ahab, and he cannot find you, he will kill me. But I your servant have feared the Lord from my youth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18013, 'Was it not reported to my lord what I did when Jezebel killed the prophets of the Lord, how I hid one hundred men of the Lord&rsquo;s prophets, fifty to a cave, and fed them with bread and water? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18014, 'And now you say, &lsquo;Go, tell your master, &ldquo;Elijah is here.&rdquo; &lsquo; He will kill me!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18015, 'Then Elijah said, &ldquo;As the Lord of hosts lives, before whom I stand, I will surely present myself to him today.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18016, 'So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and told him; and Ahab went to meet Elijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18017, 'Then it happened, when Ahab saw Elijah, that Ahab said to him, &ldquo;Is that you, O troubler of Israel?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18018, 'And he answered, &ldquo;I have not troubled Israel, but you and your father&rsquo;s house have, in that you have forsaken the commandments of the Lord and have followed the Baals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18019, 'Now therefore, send and gather all Israel to me on Mount Carmel, the four hundred and fifty prophets of Baal, and the four hundred prophets of Asherah, who eat at Jezebel&rsquo;s table.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18020, 'So Ahab sent for all the children of Israel, and gathered the prophets together on Mount Carmel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18021, 'And Elijah came to all the people, and said, &ldquo;How long will you falter between two opinions? If the Lord is God, follow Him; but if Baal, follow him.&rdquo; But the people answered him not a word. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18022, 'Then Elijah said to the people, &ldquo;I alone am left a prophet of the Lord; but Baal&rsquo;s prophets are four hundred and fifty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18023, 'Therefore let them give us two bulls; and let them choose one bull for themselves, cut it in pieces, and lay it on the wood, but put no fire under it; and I will prepare the other bull, and lay it on the wood, but put no fire under it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18024, 'Then you call on the name of your gods, and I will call on the name of the Lord; and the God who answers by fire, He is God.&rdquo; So all the people answered and said, &ldquo;It is well spoken.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18025, 'Now Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, &ldquo;Choose one bull for yourselves and prepare it first, for you are many; and call on the name of your god, but put no fire under it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18026, 'So they took the bull which was given them, and they prepared it, and called on the name of Baal from morning even till noon, saying, &ldquo;O Baal, hear us!&rdquo; But there was no voice; no one answered. Then they leaped about the altar which they had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18027, 'And so it was, at noon, that Elijah mocked them and said, &ldquo;Cry aloud, for he is a god; either he is meditating, or he is busy, or he is on a journey, or perhaps he is sleeping and must be awakened.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18028, 'So they cried aloud, and cut themselves, as was their custom, with knives and lances, until the blood gushed out on them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18029, 'And when midday was past, they prophesied until the time of the offering of the evening sacrifice. But there was no voice; no one answered, no one paid attention. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18030, 'Then *Elijah said to all the people, &ldquo;Come near to me.&rdquo; So all the people came near to him. And he repaired the altar of the Lord that was broken down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18031, 'And Elijah took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes of the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of the Lord had come, saying, &ldquo;Israel shall be your name.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18032, 'Then with the stones he built an altar in the name of the Lord; and he made a trench around the altar large enough to hold two seahs of seed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18033, 'And he put the wood in order, cut the bull in pieces, and laid it on the wood, and said, &ldquo;Fill four waterpots with water, and pour it on the burnt sacrifice and on the wood.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18034, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Do it a second time,&rdquo; and they did it a second time; and he said, &ldquo;Do it a third time,&rdquo; and they did it a third time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18035, 'So the water ran all around the altar; and he also filled the trench with water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18036, 'And it came to pass, at the time of the offering of the evening sacrifice, that Elijah the prophet came near and said, &ldquo;Lord God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, let it be known this day that You are God in Israel and I am Your servant, and that I have done all these things at Your word. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18037, 'Hear me, O Lord, hear me, that this people may know that You are the Lord God, and that You have turned their hearts back to You again.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18038, 'Then the fire of the Lord fell and consumed the burnt sacrifice, and the wood and the stones and the dust, and it licked up the water that was in the trench. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18039, 'Now when all the people saw it, they fell on their faces; and they said, &ldquo;The Lord, He is God! The Lord, He is God!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18040, 'And Elijah said to them, &ldquo;Seize the prophets of Baal! Do not let one of them escape!&rdquo; So they seized them; and Elijah brought them down to the Brook Kishon and executed them there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18041, 'Then Elijah said to Ahab, &ldquo;Go up, eat and drink; for there is the sound of abundance of rain.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18042, 'So Ahab went up to eat and drink. And Elijah went up to the top of Carmel; then he bowed down on the ground, and put his face between his knees, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18043, 'and said to his servant, &ldquo;Go up now, look toward the sea.&rdquo; So he went up and looked, and said, &ldquo;There is nothing.&rdquo; And seven times he said, &ldquo;Go again.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18044, 'Then it came to pass the seventh time, that he said, &ldquo;There is a cloud, as small as a man&rsquo;s hand, rising out of the sea!&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Go up, say to Ahab, &lsquo;Prepare your chariot, and go down before the rain stops you.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18045, 'Now it happened in the meantime that the sky became black with clouds and wind, and there was a heavy rain. So Ahab rode away and went to Jezreel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 18046, 'Then the hand of the Lord came upon Elijah; and he girded up his loins and ran ahead of Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19001, 'And Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, also how he had executed all the prophets with the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19002, 'Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, &ldquo;So let the gods do to me, and more also, if I do not make your life as the life of one of them by tomorrow about this time.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19003, 'And when he saw that, he arose and ran for his life, and went to Beersheba, which belongs to Judah, and left his servant there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19004, 'But he himself went a day&rsquo;s journey into the wilderness, and came and sat down under a broom tree. And he prayed that he might die, and said, &ldquo;It is enough! Now, Lord, take my life, for I am no better than my fathers!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19005, 'Then as he lay and slept under a broom tree, suddenly an angel touched him, and said to him, &ldquo;Arise and eat.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19006, 'Then he looked, and there by his head was a cake baked on coals, and a jar of water. So he ate and drank, and lay down again. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19007, 'And the angel of the Lord came back the second time, and touched him, and said, &ldquo;Arise and eat, because the journey is too great for you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19008, 'So he arose, and ate and drank; and he went in the strength of that food forty days and forty nights as far as Horeb, the mountain of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19009, 'And there he went into a cave, and spent the night in that place; and behold, the word of the Lord came to him, and He said to him, &ldquo;What are you doing here, Elijah?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19010, 'So he said, &ldquo;I have been very zealous for the Lord God of hosts; for the children of Israel have forsaken Your covenant, torn down Your altars, and killed Your prophets with the sword. I alone am left; and they seek to take my life.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19011, 'Then He said, &ldquo;Go out, and stand on the mountain before the Lord.&rdquo; And behold, the Lord passed by, and a great and strong wind tore into the mountains and broke the rocks in pieces before the Lord, but the Lord was not in the wind; and after the wind an earthquake, but the Lord was not in the earthquake; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19012, 'and after the earthquake a fire, but the Lord was not in the fire; and after the fire a still small voice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19013, 'So it was, when Elijah heard it, that he wrapped his face in his mantle and went out and stood in the entrance of the cave. Suddenly a voice came to him, and said, &ldquo;What are you doing here, Elijah?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19014, 'And he said, &ldquo;I have been very zealous for the Lord God of hosts; because the children of Israel have forsaken Your covenant, torn down Your altars, and killed Your prophets with the sword. I alone am left; and they seek to take my life.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19015, 'Then the Lord said to him: &ldquo;Go, return on your way to the Wilderness of Damascus; and when you arrive, anoint Hazael as king over Syria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19016, 'Also you shall anoint Jehu the son of Nimshi as king over Israel. And Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel Meholah you shall anoint as prophet in your place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19017, 'It shall be that whoever escapes the sword of Hazael, Jehu will kill; and whoever escapes the sword of Jehu, Elisha will kill. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19018, 'Yet I have reserved seven thousand in Israel, all whose knees have not bowed to Baal, and every mouth that has not kissed him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19019, 'So he departed from there, and found Elisha the son of Shaphat, who was plowing with twelve yoke of oxen before him, and he was with the twelfth. Then Elijah passed by him and threw his mantle on him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19020, 'And he left the oxen and ran after Elijah, and said, &ldquo;Please let me kiss my father and my mother, and then I will follow you.&rdquo; And he said to him, &ldquo;Go back again, for what have I done to you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 19021, 'So Elisha turned back from him, and took a yoke of oxen and slaughtered them and boiled their flesh, using the oxen&rsquo;s equipment, and gave it to the people, and they ate. Then he arose and followed Elijah, and became his servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20001, 'Now Ben-Hadad the king of Syria gathered all his forces together; thirty-two kings were with him, with horses and chariots. And he went up and besieged Samaria, and made war against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20002, 'Then he sent messengers into the city to Ahab king of Israel, and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says Ben-Hadad: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20003, '&rsquo;Your silver and your gold are mine; your loveliest wives and children are mine.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20004, 'And the king of Israel answered and said, &ldquo;My lord, O king, just as you say, I and all that I have are yours.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20005, 'Then the messengers came back and said, &ldquo;Thus speaks Ben-Hadad, saying, &lsquo;Indeed I have sent to you, saying, &ldquo;You shall deliver to me your silver and your gold, your wives and your children&rdquo;; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20006, 'but I will send my servants to you tomorrow about this time, and they shall search your house and the houses of your servants. And it shall be, that whatever is pleasant in your eyes, they will put it in their hands and take it.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20007, 'So the king of Israel called all the elders of the land, and said, &ldquo;Notice, please, and see how this man seeks trouble, for he sent to me for my wives, my children, my silver, and my gold; and I did not deny him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20008, 'And all the elders and all the people said to him, &ldquo;Do not listen or consent.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20009, 'Therefore he said to the messengers of Ben-Hadad, &ldquo;Tell my lord the king, &lsquo;All that you sent for to your servant the first time I will do, but this thing I cannot do.&rsquo; &ldquo; And the messengers departed and brought back word to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20010, 'Then Ben-Hadad sent to him and said, &ldquo;The gods do so to me, and more also, if enough dust is left of Samaria for a handful for each of the people who follow me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20011, 'So the king of Israel answered and said, &ldquo;Tell him, &lsquo;Let not the one who puts on his armor boast like the one who takes it off.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20012, 'And it happened when Ben-Hadad heard this message, as he and the kings were drinking at the command post, that he said to his servants, &ldquo;Get ready.&rdquo; And they got ready to attack the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20013, 'Suddenly a prophet approached Ahab king of Israel, saying, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Have you seen all this great multitude? Behold, I will deliver it into your hand today, and you shall know that I am the Lord.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20014, 'So Ahab said, &ldquo;By whom?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;By the young leaders of the provinces.&rsquo; &ldquo; Then he said, &ldquo;Who will set the battle in order?&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;You.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20015, 'Then he mustered the young leaders of the provinces, and there were two hundred and thirty-two; and after them he mustered all the people, all the children of Israel &ndash; seven thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20016, 'So they went out at noon. Meanwhile Ben-Hadad and the thirty-two kings helping him were getting drunk at the command post. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20017, 'The young leaders of the provinces went out first. And Ben-Hadad sent out a patrol, and they told him, saying, &ldquo;Men are coming out of Samaria!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20018, 'So he said, &ldquo;If they have come out for peace, take them alive; and if they have come out for war, take them alive.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20019, 'Then these young leaders of the provinces went out of the city with the army which followed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20020, 'And each one killed his man; so the Syrians fled, and Israel pursued them; and Ben-Hadad the king of Syria escaped on a horse with the cavalry. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20021, 'Then the king of Israel went out and attacked the horses and chariots, and killed the Syrians with a great slaughter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20022, 'And the prophet came to the king of Israel and said to him, &ldquo;Go, strengthen yourself; take note, and see what you should do, for in the spring of the year the king of Syria will come up against you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20023, 'Then the servants of the king of Syria said to him, &ldquo;Their gods are gods of the hills. Therefore they were stronger than we; but if we fight against them in the plain, surely we will be stronger than they. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20024, 'So do this thing: Dismiss the kings, each from his position, and put captains in their places; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20025, 'and you shall muster an army like the army that you have lost, horse for horse and chariot for chariot. Then we will fight against them in the plain; surely we will be stronger than they.&rdquo; And he listened to their voice and did so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20026, 'So it was, in the spring of the year, that Ben-Hadad mustered the Syrians and went up to Aphek to fight against Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20027, 'And the children of Israel were mustered and given provisions, and they went against them. Now the children of Israel encamped before them like two little flocks of goats, while the Syrians filled the countryside. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20028, 'Then a man of God came and spoke to the king of Israel, and said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Because the Syrians have said, &ldquo;The Lord is God of the hills, but He is not God of the valleys,&rdquo; therefore I will deliver all this great multitude into your hand, and you shall know that I am the Lord.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20029, 'And they encamped opposite each other for seven days. So it was that on the seventh day the battle was joined; and the children of Israel killed one hundred thousand foot soldiers of the Syrians in one day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20030, 'But the rest fled to Aphek, into the city; then a wall fell on twenty-seven thousand of the men who were left. And Ben-Hadad fled and went into the city, into an inner chamber. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20031, 'Then his servants said to him, &ldquo;Look now, we have heard that the kings of the house of Israel are merciful kings. Please, let us put sackcloth around our waists and ropes around our heads, and go out to the king of Israel; perhaps he will spare your life.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20032, 'So they wore sackcloth around their waists and put ropes around their heads, and came to the king of Israel and said, &ldquo;Your servant Ben-Hadad says, &lsquo;Please let me live.&rsquo; &ldquo; And he said, &ldquo;Is he still alive? He is my brother.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20033, 'Now the men were watching closely to see whether any sign of mercy would come from him; and they quickly grasped at this word and said, &ldquo;Your brother Ben-Hadad.&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Go, bring him.&rdquo; Then Ben-Hadad came out to him; and he had him come up into the chariot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20034, 'So Ben-Hadad said to him, &ldquo;The cities which my father took from your father I will restore; and you may set up marketplaces for yourself in Damascus, as my father did in Samaria.&rdquo; Then Ahab said, &ldquo;I will send you away with this treaty.&rdquo; So he made a treaty with him and sent him away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20035, 'Now a certain man of the sons of the prophets said to his neighbor by the word of the Lord, &ldquo;Strike me, please.&rdquo; And the man refused to strike him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20036, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Because you have not obeyed the voice of the Lord, surely, as soon as you depart from me, a lion shall kill you.&rdquo; And as soon as he left him, a lion found him and killed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20037, 'And he found another man, and said, &ldquo;Strike me, please.&rdquo; So the man struck him, inflicting a wound. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20038, 'Then the prophet departed and waited for the king by the road, and disguised himself with a bandage over his eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20039, 'Now as the king passed by, he cried out to the king and said, &ldquo;Your servant went out into the midst of the battle; and there, a man came over and brought a man to me, and said, &lsquo;Guard this man; if by any means he is missing, your life shall be for his life, or else you shall pay a talent of silver.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20040, 'While your servant was busy here and there, he was gone.&rdquo; Then the king of Israel said to him, &ldquo;So shall your judgment be; you yourself have decided it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20041, 'And he hastened to take the bandage away from his eyes; and the king of Israel recognized him as one of the prophets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20042, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Because you have let slip out of your hand a man whom I appointed to utter destruction, therefore your life shall go for his life, and your people for his people.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 20043, 'So the king of Israel went to his house sullen and displeased, and came to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21001, 'And it came to pass after these things that Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard which was in Jezreel, next to the palace of Ahab king of Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21002, 'So Ahab spoke to Naboth, saying, &ldquo;Give me your vineyard, that I may have it for a vegetable garden, because it is near, next to my house; and for it I will give you a vineyard better than it. Or, if it seems good to you, I will give you its worth in money.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21003, 'But Naboth said to Ahab, &ldquo;The Lord forbid that I should give the inheritance of my fathers to you!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21004, 'So Ahab went into his house sullen and displeased because of the word which Naboth the Jezreelite had spoken to him; for he had said, &ldquo;I will not give you the inheritance of my fathers.&rdquo; And he lay down on his bed, and turned away his face, and would eat no food. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21005, 'But Jezebel his wife came to him, and said to him, &ldquo;Why is your spirit so sullen that you eat no food?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21006, 'He said to her, &ldquo;Because I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite, and said to him, &lsquo;Give me your vineyard for money; or else, if it pleases you, I will give you another vineyard for it.&rsquo; And he answered, &lsquo;I will not give you my vineyard.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21007, 'Then Jezebel his wife said to him, &ldquo;You now exercise authority over Israel! Arise, eat food, and let your heart be cheerful; I will give you the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21008, 'And she wrote letters in Ahab&rsquo;s name, sealed them with his seal, and sent the letters to the elders and the nobles who were dwelling in the city with Naboth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21009, 'She wrote in the letters, saying, Proclaim a fast, and seat Naboth with high honor among the people; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21010, 'and seat two men, scoundrels, before him to bear witness against him, saying, &ldquo;You have blasphemed God and the king.&rdquo; Then take him out, and stone him, that he may die. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21011, 'So the men of his city, the elders and nobles who were inhabitants of his city, did as Jezebel had sent to them, as it was written in the letters which she had sent to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21012, 'They proclaimed a fast, and seated Naboth with high honor among the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21013, 'And two men, scoundrels, came in and sat before him; and the scoundrels witnessed against him, against Naboth, in the presence of the people, saying, &ldquo;Naboth has blasphemed God and the king!&rdquo; Then they took him outside the city and stoned him with stones, so that he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21014, 'Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, &ldquo;Naboth has been stoned and is dead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21015, 'And it came to pass, when Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned and was dead, that Jezebel said to Ahab, &ldquo;Arise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, which he refused to give you for money; for Naboth is not alive, but dead.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21016, 'So it was, when Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, that Ahab got up and went down to take possession of the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21017, 'Then the word of the Lord came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21018, 'Arise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who lives in Samaria. There he is, in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has gone down to take possession of it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21019, 'You shall speak to him, saying, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: Have you murdered and also taken possession? &lsquo; And you shall speak to him, saying, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: In the place where dogs licked the blood of Naboth, dogs shall lick your blood, even yours. &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21020, 'So Ahab said to Elijah, &ldquo;Have you found me, O my enemy?&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;I have found you, because you have sold yourself to do evil in the sight of the Lord: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21021, '&rsquo;Behold, I will bring calamity on you. I will take away your posterity, and will cut off from Ahab every male in Israel, both bond and free. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21022, 'I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, because of the provocation with which you have provoked Me to anger, and made Israel sin.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21023, 'And concerning Jezebel the Lord also spoke, saying, &lsquo;The dogs shall eat Jezebel by the wall of Jezreel.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21024, 'The dogs shall eat whoever belongs to Ahab and dies in the city, and the birds of the air shall eat whoever dies in the field.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21025, 'But there was no one like Ahab who sold himself to do wickedness in the sight of the Lord, because Jezebel his wife stirred him up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21026, 'And he behaved very abominably in following idols, according to all that the Amorites had done, whom the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21027, 'So it was, when Ahab heard those words, that he tore his clothes and put sackcloth on his body, and fasted and lay in sackcloth, and went about mourning. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21028, 'And the word of the Lord came to Elijah the Tishbite, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 21029, 'See how Ahab has humbled himself before Me? Because he has humbled himself before Me, I will not bring the calamity in his days. In the days of his son I will bring the calamity on his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22001, 'Now three years passed without war between Syria and Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22002, 'Then it came to pass, in the third year, that Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went down to visit the king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22003, 'And the king of Israel said to his servants, &ldquo;Do you know that Ramoth in Gilead is ours, but we hesitate to take it out of the hand of the king of Syria?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22004, 'So he said to Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;Will you go with me to fight at Ramoth Gilead?&rdquo; Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, &ldquo;I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22005, 'Also Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, &ldquo;Please inquire for the word of the Lord today.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22006, 'Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four hundred men, and said to them, &ldquo;Shall I go against Ramoth Gilead to fight, or shall I refrain?&rdquo; So they said, &ldquo;Go up, for the Lord will deliver it into the hand of the king.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22007, 'And Jehoshaphat said, &ldquo;Is there not still a prophet of the Lord here, that we may inquire of Him?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22008, 'So the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;There is still one man, Micaiah the son of Imlah, by whom we may inquire of the Lord; but I hate him, because he does not prophesy good concerning me, but evil.&rdquo; And Jehoshaphat said, &ldquo;Let not the king say such things!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22009, 'Then the king of Israel called an officer and said, &ldquo;Bring Micaiah the son of Imlah quickly!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22010, 'The king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah, having put on their robes, sat each on his throne, at a threshing floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets prophesied before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22011, 'Now Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah had made horns of iron for himself; and he said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;With these you shall gore the Syrians until they are destroyed.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22012, 'And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, &ldquo;Go up to Ramoth Gilead and prosper, for the Lord will deliver it into the king&rsquo;s hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22013, 'Then the messenger who had gone to call Micaiah spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;Now listen, the words of the prophets with one accord encourage the king. Please, let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak encouragement.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22014, 'And Micaiah said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, whatever the Lord says to me, that I will speak.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22015, 'Then he came to the king; and the king said to him, &ldquo;Micaiah, shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall we refrain?&rdquo; And he answered him, &ldquo;Go and prosper, for the Lord will deliver it into the hand of the king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22016, 'So the king said to him, &ldquo;How many times shall I make you swear that you tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the Lord?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22017, 'Then he said, &ldquo;I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, as sheep that have no shepherd. And the Lord said, &lsquo;These have no master. Let each return to his house in peace.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22018, 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;Did I not tell you he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '3Kg', 22019, 'Then Micaiah said, &ldquo;Therefore hear the word of the Lord: I saw the Lord sitting on His throne, and all the host of heaven standing by, on His right hand and on His left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1001, 'Moab rebelled against Israel after the death of Ahab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1002, 'Now Ahaziah fell through the lattice of his upper room in Samaria, and was injured; so he sent messengers and said to them, &ldquo;Go, inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron, whether I shall recover from this injury.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1003, 'But the angel of the Lord said to Elijah the Tishbite, &ldquo;Arise, go up to meet the messengers of the king of Samaria, and say to them, &lsquo;Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are going to inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1004, 'Now therefore, thus says the Lord: &lsquo;You shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.&rsquo; &ldquo; So Elijah departed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1005, 'And when the messengers returned to him, he said to them, &ldquo;Why have you come back?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1006, 'So they said to him, &ldquo;A man came up to meet us, and said to us, &lsquo;Go, return to the king who sent you, and say to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Is it because there is no God in Israel that you are sending to inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron? Therefore you shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.&rsquo; &ldquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1007, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;What kind of man was it who came up to meet you and told you these words?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1008, 'So they answered him, &ldquo;A hairy man wearing a leather belt around his waist.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;It is Elijah the Tishbite.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1009, 'Then the king sent to him a captain of fifty with his fifty men. So he went up to him; and there he was, sitting on the top of a hill. And he spoke to him: &ldquo;Man of God, the king has said, &lsquo;Come down!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1010, 'So Elijah answered and said to the captain of fifty, &ldquo;If I am a man of God, then let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty men.&rdquo; And fire came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1011, 'Then he sent to him another captain of fifty with his fifty men. And he answered and said to him: &ldquo;Man of God, thus has the king said, &lsquo;Come down quickly!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1012, 'So Elijah answered and said to them, &ldquo;If I am a man of God, let fire come down from heaven and consume you and your fifty men.&rdquo; And the fire of God came down from heaven and consumed him and his fifty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1013, 'Again, he sent a third captain of fifty with his fifty men. And the third captain of fifty went up, and came and fell on his knees before Elijah, and pleaded with him, and said to him: &ldquo;Man of God, please let my life and the life of these fifty servants of yours be precious in your sight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1014, 'Look, fire has come down from heaven and burned up the first two captains of fifties with their fifties. But let my life now be precious in your sight.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1015, 'And the angel of the Lord said to Elijah, &ldquo;Go down with him; do not be afraid of him.&rdquo; So he arose and went down with him to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1016, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Because you have sent messengers to inquire of Baal-Zebub, the god of Ekron, is it because there is no God in Israel to inquire of His word? Therefore you shall not come down from the bed to which you have gone up, but you shall surely die.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1017, 'So Ahaziah died according to the word of the Lord which Elijah had spoken. Because he had no son, Jehoram became king in his place, in the second year of Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat, king of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 1018, 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahaziah which he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2001, 'And it came to pass, when the Lord was about to take up Elijah into heaven by a whirlwind, that Elijah went with Elisha from Gilgal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2002, 'Then Elijah said to Elisha, &ldquo;Stay here, please, for the Lord has sent me on to Bethel.&rdquo; But Elisha said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, and as your soul lives, I will not leave you!&rdquo; So they went down to Bethel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2003, 'Now the sons of the prophets who were at Bethel came out to Elisha, and said to him, &ldquo;Do you know that the Lord will take away your master from over you today?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Yes, I know; keep silent!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2004, 'Then Elijah said to him, &ldquo;Elisha, stay here, please, for the Lord has sent me on to Jericho.&rdquo; But he said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, and as your soul lives, I will not leave you!&rdquo; So they came to Jericho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2005, 'Now the sons of the prophets who were at Jericho came to Elisha and said to him, &ldquo;Do you know that the Lord will take away your master from over you today?&rdquo; So he answered, &ldquo;Yes, I know; keep silent!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2006, 'Then Elijah said to him,* &ldquo;Stay here, please, for the Lord has sent me on to the Jordan.&rdquo; But he said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, and as your soul lives, I will not leave you!&rdquo; So the two of them went on. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2007, 'And fifty men of the sons of the prophets went and stood facing them at a distance, while the two of them stood by the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2008, 'Now Elijah took his mantle, rolled it up, and struck the water; and it was divided this way and that, so that the two of them crossed over on dry ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2009, 'And so it was, when they had crossed over, that Elijah said to Elisha, &ldquo;Ask! What may I do for you, before I am taken away from you?&rdquo; Elisha said, &ldquo;Please let a double portion of your spirit be upon me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2010, 'So he said, You have asked a hard thing. Nevertheless, if you see me when I am taken from you, it shall be so for you; but if not, it shall not be so.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2011, 'Then it happened, as they continued on and talked, that suddenly a chariot of fire appeared with horses of fire, and separated the two of them; and Elijah went up by a whirlwind into heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2012, 'And Elisha saw it, and he cried out, &ldquo;My father, my father, the chariot of Israel and its horsemen!&rdquo; So he saw him no more. And he took hold of his own clothes and tore them into two pieces. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2013, 'He also took up the mantle of Elijah that had fallen from him, and went back and stood by the bank of the Jordan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2014, 'Then he took the mantle of Elijah that had fallen from him, and struck the water, and said, &ldquo;Where is the Lord God of Elijah?&rdquo; And when he also had struck the water, it was divided this way and that; and Elisha crossed over.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2015, 'Now when the sons of the prophets who were from Jericho saw him, they said, &ldquo;The spirit of Elijah rests on Elisha.&rdquo; And they came to meet him, and bowed to the ground before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2016, 'Then they said to him, &ldquo;Look now, there are fifty strong men with your servants. Please let them go and search for your master, lest perhaps the Spirit of the Lord has taken him up and cast him upon some mountain or into some valley.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;You shall not send anyone.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2017, 'But when they urged him till he was ashamed, he said, &ldquo;Send them!&rdquo; Therefore they sent fifty men, and they searched for three days but did not find him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2018, 'And when they came back to him, for he had stayed in Jericho, he said to them, &ldquo;Did I not say to you, &lsquo;Do not go&rsquo;?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2019, 'Then the* men of the city said to Elisha, &ldquo;Please notice, the situation of this city is pleasant, as my lord sees; but the water is bad, and the ground barren.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2020, 'And he said, &ldquo;Bring me a new bowl, and put salt in it.&rdquo; So they brought it to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2021, 'Then he went out to the source of the water, and cast in the salt there, and said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;I have healed this water; from it there shall be no more death or barrenness.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2022, 'So the water remains healed to this day, according to the word of Elisha which he spoke.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2023, 'Then he went up from there to Bethel; and as he was going up the road, some youths came from the city and mocked him, and said to him, &ldquo;Go up, you baldhead! Go up, you baldhead!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2024, 'So he turned around and looked at them, and pronounced a curse on them in the name of the Lord. And two female bears came out of the woods and mauled forty-two of the youths. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 2025, 'Then he went from there to Mount Carmel, and from there he returned to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3001, 'Now Jehoram the son of Ahab became king over Israel at Samaria in the eighteenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and reigned twelve years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3002, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, but not like his father and mother; for he put away the sacred pillar of Baal that his father had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3003, 'Nevertheless he persisted in the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin; he did not depart from them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3004, 'Now Mesha king of Moab was a sheepbreeder, and he regularly paid the king of Israel one hundred thousand lambs and the wool of one hundred thousand rams. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3005, 'But it happened, when Ahab died, that the king of Moab rebelled against the king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3006, 'So King Jehoram went out of Samaria at that time and mustered all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3007, 'Then he went and sent to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, saying, &ldquo;The king of Moab has rebelled against me. Will you go with me to fight against Moab?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;I will go up; I am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3008, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Which way shall we go up?&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;By way of the Wilderness of Edom.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3009, 'So the king of Israel went with the king of Judah and the king of Edom, and they marched on that roundabout route seven days; and there was no water for the army, nor for the animals that followed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3010, 'And the king of Israel said, &ldquo;Alas! For the Lord has called these three kings together to deliver them into the hand of Moab.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3011, 'But Jehoshaphat said, &ldquo;Is there no prophet of the Lord here, that we may inquire of the Lord by him?&rdquo; So one of the servants of the king of Israel answered and said, &ldquo;Elisha the son of Shaphat is here, who poured water on the hands of Elijah.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3012, 'And Jehoshaphat said, &ldquo;The word of the Lord is with him.&rdquo; So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat and the king of Edom went down to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3013, 'Then Elisha said to the king of Israel, &ldquo;What have I to do with you? Go to the prophets of your father and the prophets of your mother.&rdquo; But the king of Israel said to him, &ldquo;No, for the Lord has called these three kings together to deliver them into the hand of Moab.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3014, 'And Elisha said, &ldquo;As the Lord of hosts lives, before whom I stand, surely were it not that I regard the presence of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, I would not look at you, nor see you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3015, 'But now bring me a musician.&rdquo; Then it happened, when the musician played, that the hand of the Lord came upon him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3016, 'And he said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Make this valley full of ditches.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3017, 'For thus says the Lord: &lsquo;You shall not see wind, nor shall you see rain; yet that valley shall be filled with water, so that you, your cattle, and your animals may drink.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3018, 'And this is a simple matter in the sight of the Lord; He will also deliver the Moabites into your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3019, 'Also you shall attack every fortified city and every choice city, and shall cut down every good tree, and stop up every spring of water, and ruin every good piece of land with stones.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3020, 'Now it happened in the morning, when the grain offering was offered, that suddenly water came by way of Edom, and the land was filled with water. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3021, 'And when all the Moabites heard that the kings had come up to fight against them, all who were able to bear arms and older were gathered; and they stood at the border. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3022, 'Then they rose up early in the morning, and the sun was shining on the water; and the Moabites saw the water on the other side as red as blood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3023, 'And they said, &ldquo;This is blood; the kings have surely struck swords and have killed one another; now therefore, Moab, to the spoil!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3024, 'So when they came to the camp of Israel, Israel rose up and attacked the Moabites, so that they fled before them; and they entered their land, killing the Moabites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3025, 'Then they destroyed the cities, and each man threw a stone on every good piece of land and filled it; and they stopped up all the springs of water and cut down all the good trees. But they left the stones of Kir Haraseth intact. However the slingers surrounded and attacked it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3026, 'And when the king of Moab saw that the battle was too fierce for him, he took with him seven hundred men who drew swords, to break through to the king of Edom, but they could not. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 3027, 'Then he took his eldest son who would have reigned in his place, and offered him as a burnt offering upon the wall; and there was great indignation against Israel. So they departed from him and returned to their own land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4001, 'A certain woman of the wives of the sons of the prophets cried out to Elisha, saying, &ldquo;Your servant my husband is dead, and you know that your servant feared the Lord. And the creditor is coming to take my two sons to be his slaves.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4002, 'So Elisha said to her, &ldquo;What shall I do for you? Tell me, what do you have in the house?&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;Your maidservant has nothing in the house but a jar of oil.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4003, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Go, borrow vessels from everywhere, from all your neighbors &ndash; empty vessels; do not gather just a few. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4004, 'And when you have come in, you shall shut the door behind you and your sons; then pour it into all those vessels, and set aside the full ones.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4005, 'So she went from him and shut the door behind her and her sons, who brought the vessels to her; and she poured it out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4006, 'Now it came to pass, when the vessels were full, that she said to her son, &ldquo;Bring me another vessel.&rdquo; And he said to her, &ldquo;There is not another vessel.&rdquo; So the oil ceased. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4007, 'Then she came and told the man of God. And he said, &ldquo;Go, sell the oil and pay your debt; and you and your sons live on the rest.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4008, 'Now it* happened one day that Elisha went to Shunem, where there was a notable woman, and she persuaded him to eat some food. So it was, as often as he passed by, he would turn in there to eat some food. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4009, 'And she said to her husband, &ldquo;Look now, I know that this is a holy man of God, who passes by us regularly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4010, 'Please, let us make a small upper room on the wall; and let us put a bed for him there, and a table and a chair and a lampstand; so it will be, whenever he comes to us, he can turn in there.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4011, 'And it happened one day that he came there, and he turned in to the upper room and lay down there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4012, 'Then he said to Gehazi his servant, &ldquo;Call this Shunammite woman.&rdquo; When he had called her, she stood before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4013, 'And he said to him, &ldquo;Say now to her, &lsquo;Look, you have been concerned for us with all this care. What can I do for you? Do you want me to speak on your behalf to the king or to the commander of the army?&rsquo; &ldquo; She answered, &ldquo;I dwell among my own people.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4014, 'So he said, &ldquo;What then is to be done for her?&rdquo; And Gehazi answered, &ldquo;Actually, she has no son, and her husband is old.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4015, 'So he said, &ldquo;Call her.&rdquo; When he had called her, she stood in the doorway. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4016, 'Then he said, &ldquo;About this time next year you shall embrace a son.&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;No, my lord. Man of God, do not lie to your maidservant!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4017, 'But the woman conceived, and bore a son when the appointed time had come, of which Elisha had told her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4018, 'And the child grew. Now it happened one day that he went out to his father, to the reapers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4019, 'And he said to his father, &ldquo;My head, my head!&rdquo; So he said to a servant, &ldquo;Carry him to his mother.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4020, 'When he had taken him and brought him to his mother, he sat on her knees till noon, and then died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4021, 'And she went up and laid him on the bed of the man of God, shut the door upon him, and went out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4022, 'Then she called to her husband, and said, &ldquo;Please send me one of the young men and one of the donkeys, that I may run to the man of God and come back.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4023, 'So he said, &ldquo;Why are you going to him today? It is neither the New Moon nor the Sabbath.&rdquo; And she said, &ldquo;It is well.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4024, 'Then she saddled a donkey, and said to her servant, &ldquo;Drive, and go forward; do not slacken the pace for me unless I tell you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4025, 'And so she departed, and went to the man of God at Mount Carmel.So it was, when the man of God saw her afar off, that he said to his servant Gehazi, &ldquo;Look, the Shunammite woman!. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4026, 'Please run now to meet her, and say to her, &lsquo;Is it well with you? Is it well with your husband? Is it well with the child?&rsquo; &ldquo; And she answered, &ldquo;It is well.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4027, 'Now when she came to the man of God at the hill, she caught him by the feet, but Gehazi came near to push her away. But the man of God said, &ldquo;Let her alone; for her soul is in deep distress, and the Lord has hidden it from me, and has not told me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4028, 'So she said, &ldquo;Did I ask a son of my lord? Did I not say, &lsquo;Do not deceive me&rsquo;?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4029, 'Then he said to Gehazi, &ldquo;Get yourself ready, and take my staff in your hand, and be on your way. If you meet anyone, do not greet him; and if anyone greets you, do not answer him; but lay my staff on the face of the child.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4030, 'And the mother of the child said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, and as your soul lives, I will not leave you.&rdquo; So he arose and followed her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4031, 'Now Gehazi went on ahead of them, and laid the staff on the face of the child; but there was neither voice nor hearing. Therefore he went back to meet him, and told him, saying, &ldquo;The child has not awakened.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4032, 'When Elisha came into the house, there was the child, lying dead on his bed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4033, 'He went in therefore, shut the door behind the two of them, and prayed to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4034, 'And he went up and lay on the child, and put his mouth on his mouth, his eyes on his eyes, and his hands on his hands; and he stretched himself out on the child, and the flesh of the child became warm. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4035, 'He returned and walked back and forth in the house, and again went up and stretched himself out on him; then the child sneezed seven times, and the child opened his eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4036, 'And he called Gehazi and said, &ldquo;Call this Shunammite woman.&rdquo; So he called her. And when she came in to him, he said, &ldquo;Pick up your son.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4037, 'So she went in, fell at his feet, and bowed to the ground; then she picked up her son and went out. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4038, 'And Elisha returned to Gilgal, and there was a famine in the land. Now the sons of the prophets were sitting before him; and he said to his servant, &ldquo;Put on the large pot, and boil stew for the sons of the prophets.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4039, 'So one went out into the field to gather herbs, and found a wild vine, and gathered from it a lapful of wild gourds, and came and sliced them into the pot of stew, though they did not know what they were. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4040, 'Then they served it to the men to eat. Now it happened, as they were eating the stew, that they cried out and said, &ldquo;Man of God, there is death in the pot!&rdquo; And they could not eat it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4041, 'So he said, &ldquo;Then bring some flour.&rdquo; And he put it into the pot, and said, &ldquo;Serve it to the people, that they may eat.&rdquo; And there was nothing harmful in the pot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4042, 'Then a man came from Baal Shalisha, and brought the man of God bread of the firstfruits, twenty loaves of barley bread, and newly ripened grain in his knapsack. And he said, &ldquo;Give it to the people, that they may eat.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4043, 'But his servant said, &ldquo;What? Shall I set this before one hundred men?&rdquo; He said again, &ldquo;Give it to the people, that they may eat; for thus says the Lord: &lsquo;They shall eat and have some left over.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 4044, 'So he set it before them; and they ate and had some left over, according to the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5001, 'Now Naaman, commander of the army of the king of Syria, was a great and honorable man in the eyes of his master, because by him the Lord had given victory to Syria. He was also a mighty man of valor, but a leper. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5002, 'And the Syrians had gone out on raids, and had brought back captive a young girl from the land of Israel. She waited on Naaman&rsquo;s wife. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5003, 'Then she said to her mistress, &ldquo;If only my master were with the prophet who is in Samaria! For he would heal him of his leprosy.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5004, 'And Naaman went in and told his master, saying, &ldquo;Thus and thus said the girl who is from the land of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5005, 'Then the king of Syria said, &ldquo;Go now, and I will send a letter to the king of Israel.&rdquo; So he departed and took with him ten talents of silver, six thousand shekels of gold, and ten changes of clothing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5006, 'Then he brought the letter to the king of Israel, which said, Now be advised, when this letter comes to you, that I have sent Naaman my servant to you, that you may heal him of his leprosy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5007, 'And it happened, when the king of Israel read the letter, that he tore his clothes and said, &ldquo;Am I God, to kill and make alive, that this man sends a man to me to heal him of his leprosy? Therefore please consider, and see how he seeks a quarrel with me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5008, 'So it was, when Elisha the man of God heard that the king of Israel had torn his clothes, that he sent to the king, saying, &ldquo;Why have you torn your clothes? Please let him come to me, and he shall know that there is a prophet in Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5009, 'Then Naaman went* with his horses and chariots, and he stood at the door of Elisha&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5010, 'And Elisha sent a messenger to him, saying, &ldquo;Go and wash in the Jordan seven times, and your flesh shall be restored to you, and you shall be clean.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5011, 'But Naaman became furious, and went away and said, &ldquo;Indeed, I said to myself, &lsquo;He will surely come out to me, and stand and call on the name of the Lord his God, and wave his hand over the place, and heal the leprosy.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5012, 'Are not the Abanah and the Pharpar, the rivers of Damascus, better than all the waters of Israel? Could I not wash in them and be clean?&rdquo; So he turned and went away in a rage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5013, 'And his servants came near and spoke to him, and said, &ldquo;My father, if the prophet had told you to do something great, would you not have done it? How much more then, when he says to you, &lsquo;Wash, and be clean&rsquo;?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5014, 'So he went down and dipped seven times in the Jordan, according to the saying of the man of God; and his flesh was restored like the flesh of a little child, and he was clean.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5015, 'And he returned to the man of God, he and all his aides, and came and stood before him; and he said, &ldquo;Indeed, now I know that there is no God in all the earth, except in Israel; now therefore, please take a gift from your servant.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5016, 'But he said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, before whom I stand, I will receive nothing.&rdquo; And he urged him to take it, but he refused. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5017, 'So Naaman said, &ldquo;Then, if not, please let your servant be given two mule-loads of earth; for your servant will no longer offer either burnt offering or sacrifice to other gods, but to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5018, 'Yet in this thing may the Lord pardon your servant: when my master goes into the temple of Rimmon to worship there, and he leans on my hand, and I bow down in the temple of Rimmon &ndash; when I bow down in the temple of Rimmon, may the Lord please pardon your servant in this thing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5019, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Go in peace.&rdquo; So he departed from him a short distance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5020, 'But Gehazi, the servant of Elisha the man of God, said, &ldquo;Look, my master has spared Naaman this Syrian, while not receiving from his hands what he brought; but as the Lord lives, I will run after him and take something from him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5021, 'So Gehazi pursued Naaman. When Naaman saw him running after him, he got down from the chariot to meet him, and said, &ldquo;Is all well?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5022, 'And he said, &ldquo;All is well. My master has sent me, saying, &lsquo;Indeed, just now two young men of the sons of the prophets have come to me from the mountains of Ephraim. Please give them a talent of silver and two changes of garments.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5023, 'So Naaman said, &ldquo;Please, take two talents.&rdquo; And he urged him, and bound two talents of silver in two bags, with two changes of garments, and handed them to two of his servants; and they carried them on ahead of him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5024, 'When he came to the citadel, he took them from their hand, and stored them away in the house; then he let the men go, and they departed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5025, 'Now he went in and stood before his master. Elisha said to him, &ldquo;Where did you go, Gehazi?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Your servant did not go anywhere.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5026, 'Then he said to him, &ldquo;Did not my heart go with you when the man turned back from his chariot to meet you? Is it time to receive money and to receive clothing, olive groves and vineyards, sheep and oxen, male and female servants? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 5027, 'Therefore the leprosy of Naaman shall cling to you and your descendants forever.&rdquo; And he went out from his presence leprous, as white as snow. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6001, 'And the sons of the prophets said to Elisha, &ldquo;See now, the place where we dwell with you is too small for us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6002, 'Please, let us go to the Jordan, and let every man take a beam from there, and let us make there a place where we may dwell.&rdquo; So he answered, &ldquo;Go.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6003, 'Then one said, &ldquo;Please consent to go with your servants.&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;I will go.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6004, 'So he went with them. And when they came to the Jordan, they cut down trees. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6005, 'But as one was cutting down a tree, the iron ax head fell into the water; and he cried out and said, &ldquo;Alas, master! For it was borrowed.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6006, 'So the man of God said, &ldquo;Where did it fall?&rdquo; And he showed him the place. So he cut off a stick, and threw it in there; and he made the iron float. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6007, 'Therefore he said, &ldquo;Pick it up for yourself.&rdquo; So he reached out his hand and took it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6008, 'Now the king of Syria was making war against Israel; and he consulted with his servants, saying, &ldquo;My camp will be in such and such a place.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6009, 'And the man of God sent to the king of Israel, saying, &ldquo;Beware that you do not pass this place, for the Syrians are coming down there.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6010, 'Then the king of Israel sent someone to the place of which the man of God had told him. Thus he warned him, and he was watchful there, not just once or twice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6011, 'Therefore the heart of the king of Syria was greatly troubled by this thing; and he called his servants and said to them, &ldquo;Will you not show me which of us is for the king of Israel?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6012, 'And one of his servants said, &ldquo;None, my lord, O king; but Elisha, the prophet who is in Israel, tells the king of Israel the words that you speak in your bedroom.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6013, 'So he said, &ldquo;Go and see where he is, that I may send and get him.&rdquo; And it was told him, saying, &ldquo;Surely he is in Dothan.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6014, 'Therefore he sent horses and chariots and a great army there, and they came by night and surrounded the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6015, 'And when the servant of the man of God arose early and went out, there was an army, surrounding the city with horses and chariots. And his servant said to him, &ldquo;Alas, my master! What shall we do?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6016, 'So he answered, &ldquo;Do not fear, for those who are with us are more than those who are with them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6017, 'And Elisha prayed, and said, &ldquo;Lord, I pray, open his eyes that he may see.&rdquo; Then the Lord opened the eyes of the young man, and he saw. And behold, the mountain was full of horses and chariots of fire all around Elisha. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6018, 'So when the Syrians came down to him, Elisha prayed to the Lord, and said, &ldquo;Strike this people, I pray, with blindness.&rdquo; And He struck them with blindness according to the word of Elisha. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6019, 'Now Elisha said to them, &ldquo;This is not the way, nor is this the city. Follow me, and I will bring you to the man whom you seek.&rdquo; But he led them to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6020, 'So it was, when they had come to Samaria, that Elisha said, &ldquo;Lord, open the eyes of these men, that they may see.&rdquo; And the Lord opened their eyes, and they saw; and there they were, inside Samaria! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6021, 'Now when the king of Israel saw them, he said to Elisha, &ldquo;My father, shall I kill them? Shall I kill them?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6022, 'But he answered, &ldquo;You shall not kill them. Would you kill those whom you have taken captive with your sword and your bow? Set food and water before them, that they may eat and drink and go to their master.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6023, 'Then he prepared a great feast for them; and after they ate and drank, he sent them away and they went to their master. So the bands of Syrian raiders came no more into the land of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6024, 'And it happened after this that Ben-Hadad king of Syria gathered all his army, and went up and besieged Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6025, 'And there was a great famine in Samaria; and indeed they besieged it until a donkey&rsquo;s head was sold for eighty shekels of silver, and one-fourth of a kab of dove droppings for five shekels of silver. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6026, 'Then, as the king of Israel was passing by on the wall, a woman cried out to him, saying, &ldquo;Help, my lord, O king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6027, 'And he said, &ldquo;If the Lord does not help you, where can I find help for you? From the threshing floor or from the winepress?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6028, 'Then the king said to her, &ldquo;What is troubling you?&rdquo; And she answered, &ldquo;This woman said to me, &lsquo;Give your son, that we may eat him today, and we will eat my son tomorrow.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6029, 'So we boiled my son, and ate him. And I said to her on the next day, &lsquo;Give your son, that we may eat him&rsquo;; but she has hidden her son.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6030, 'Now it happened, when the king heard the words of the woman, that he tore his clothes; and as he passed by on the wall, the people looked, and there underneath he had sackcloth on his body. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6031, 'Then he said, &ldquo;God do so to me and more also, if the head of Elisha the son of Shaphat remains on him today.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6032, 'But Elisha was sitting in his house, and the elders were sitting with him. And the king sent a man ahead of him, but before the messenger came to him, he said to the elders, &ldquo;Do you see how this son of a murderer has sent someone to take away my head? Look, when the messenger comes, shut the door, and hold him fast at the door. Is not the sound of his master&rsquo;s feet behind him?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 6033, 'And while he was still talking with them, there was the messenger, coming down to him; and then the king said, &ldquo;Surely this calamity is from the Lord; why should I wait for the Lord any longer?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7001, 'Then Elisha said, &ldquo;Hear the word of the Lord. Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Tomorrow about this time a seah of fine flour shall be sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a shekel, at the gate of Samaria.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7002, 'So an officer on whose hand the king leaned answered the man of God and said, &ldquo;Look, if the Lord would make windows in heaven, could this thing be?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;In fact, you shall see it with your eyes, but you shall not eat of it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7003, 'Now there were four leprous men at the entrance of the gate; and they said to one another, &ldquo;Why are we sitting here until we die? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7004, 'If we say, &lsquo;We will enter the city,&rsquo; the famine is in the city, and we shall die there. And if we sit here, we die also. Now therefore, come, let us surrender to the army of the Syrians. If they keep us alive, we shall live; and if they kill us, we shall only die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7005, 'And they rose at twilight to go to the camp of the Syrians; and when they had come to the outskirts of the Syrian camp, to their surprise no one was there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7006, 'For the Lord had caused the army of the Syrians to hear the noise of chariots and the noise of horses &ndash; the noise of a great army; so they said to one another, &ldquo;Look, the king of Israel has hired against us the kings of the Hittites and the kings of the Egyptians to attack us!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7007, 'Therefore they arose and fled at twilight, and left the camp intact &ndash; their tents, their horses, and their donkeys &ndash; and they fled for their lives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7008, 'And when these lepers came to the outskirts of the camp, they went into one tent and ate and drank, and carried from it silver and gold and clothing, and went and hid them; then they came back and entered another tent, and carried some from there also, and went and hid it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7009, 'Then they said to one another, &ldquo;We are not doing right. This day is a day of good news, and we remain silent. If we wait until morning light, some punishment will come upon us. Now therefore, come, let us go and tell the king&rsquo;s household.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7010, 'So they went and called to the gatekeepers of the city, and told them, saying, &ldquo;We went to the Syrian camp, and surprisingly no one was there, not a human sound &ndash; only horses and donkeys tied, and the tents intact.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7011, 'And the gatekeepers called out, and they told it to the king&rsquo;s household inside. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7012, 'So the king arose in the night and said to his servants, &ldquo;Let me now tell you what the Syrians have done to us. They know that we are hungry; therefore they have gone out of the camp to hide themselves in the field, saying, &lsquo;When they come out of the city, we shall catch them alive, and get into the city.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7013, 'And one of his servants answered and said, &ldquo;Please, let several men take five of the remaining horses which are left in the city. Look, they may either become like all the multitude of Israel that are left in it; or indeed, I say, they may become like all the multitude of Israel left from those who are consumed; so let us send them and see.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7014, 'Therefore they took two chariots with horses; and the king sent them in the direction of the Syrian army, saying, &ldquo;Go and see.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7015, 'And they went after them to the Jordan; and indeed all the road was full of garments and weapons which the Syrians had thrown away in their haste. So the messengers returned and told the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7016, 'Then the people went out and plundered the tents of the Syrians. So a seah of fine flour was sold for a shekel, and two seahs of barley for a shekel, according to the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7017, 'Now the king had appointed the officer on whose hand he leaned to have charge of the gate. But the people trampled him in the gate, and he died, just as the man of God had said, who spoke when the king came down to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7018, 'So it happened just as the man of God had spoken to the king, saying, &ldquo;Two seahs of barley for a shekel, and a seah of fine flour for a shekel, shall be sold tomorrow about this time in the gate of Samaria.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7019, 'Then that officer had answered the man of God, and said, &ldquo;Now look, if the Lord would make windows in heaven, could such a thing be?&rdquo; And he had said, &ldquo;In fact, you shall see it with your eyes, but you shall not eat of it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 7020, 'And so it happened to him, for the people trampled him in the gate, and he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8001, 'Then Elisha spoke to the woman whose son he had restored to life, saying, &ldquo;Arise and go, you and your household, and stay wherever you can; for the Lord has called for a famine, and furthermore, it will come upon the land for seven years.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8002, 'So the woman arose and did according to the saying of the man of God, and she went with her household and dwelt in the land of the Philistines seven years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8003, 'It came to pass, at the end of seven years, that the woman returned from the land of the Philistines; and she went to make an appeal to the king for her house and for her land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8004, 'Then the king talked with Gehazi, the servant of the man of God, saying, &ldquo;Tell me, please, all the great things Elisha has done.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8005, 'Now it happened, as he was telling the king how he had restored the dead to life, that there was the woman whose son he had restored to life, appealing to the king for her house and for her land. And Gehazi said, &ldquo;My lord, O king, this is the woman, and this is her son whom Elisha restored to life.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8006, 'And when the king asked the woman, she told him. So the king appointed a certain officer for her, saying, &ldquo;Restore all that was hers, and all the proceeds of the field from the day that she left the land until now.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8007, 'Then Elisha went to Damascus, and Ben-Hadad king of Syria was sick; and it was told him, saying, &ldquo;The man of God has come here.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8008, 'And the king said to Hazael, &ldquo;Take a present in your hand, and go to meet the man of God, and inquire of the Lord by him, saying, &lsquo;Shall I recover from this disease?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8009, 'So Hazael went to meet him and took a present with him, of every good thing of Damascus, forty camel-loads; and he came and stood before him, and said, &ldquo;Your son Ben-Hadad king of Syria has sent me to you, saying, &lsquo;Shall I recover from this disease?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8010, 'And Elisha said to him, &ldquo;Go, say to him, &lsquo;You shall certainly recover.&rsquo; However the Lord has shown me that he will really die.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8011, 'Then he set his countenance in a stare until he was ashamed; and the man of God wept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8012, 'And Hazael said, &ldquo;Why is my lord weeping?&rdquo; He answered, &ldquo;Because I know the evil that you will do to the children of Israel: Their strongholds you will set on fire, and their young men you will kill with the sword; and you will dash their children, and rip open their women with child.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8013, 'So Hazael said, &ldquo;But what is your servant &ndash; a dog, that he should do this gross thing?&rdquo; And Elisha answered, &ldquo;The Lord has shown me that you will become king over Syria.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8014, 'Then he departed from Elisha, and came to his master, who said to him, &ldquo;What did Elisha say to you?&rdquo; And he answered, &ldquo;He told me you would surely recover.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8015, 'But it happened on the next day that he took a thick cloth and dipped it in water, and spread it over his face so that he died; and Hazael reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8016, 'Now in the fifth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Jehoshaphat having been king of Judah, Jehoram the son of Jehoshaphat began to reign as king of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8017, 'He was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8018, 'And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house of Ahab had done, for the daughter of Ahab was his wife; and he did evil in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8019, 'Yet the Lord would not destroy Judah, for the sake of his servant David, as He promised him to give a lamp to him and his sons forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8020, 'In his days Edom revolted against Judah&rsquo;s authority, and made a king over themselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8021, 'So Joram went to Zair, and all his chariots with him. Then he rose by night and attacked the Edomites who had surrounded him and the captains of the chariots; and the troops fled to their tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8022, 'Thus Edom has been in revolt against Judah&rsquo;s authority to this day. And Libnah revolted at that time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8023, 'Now the rest of the acts of Joram, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8024, 'So Joram rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the City of David. Then Ahaziah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8025, 'In the twelfth year of Joram the son of Ahab, king of Israel, Ahaziah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, began to reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8026, 'Ahaziah was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Athaliah the granddaughter of Omri, king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8027, 'And he walked in the way of the house of Ahab, and did evil in the sight of the Lord, like the house of Ahab, for he was the son-in-law of the house of Ahab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8028, 'Now he went with Joram the son of Ahab to war against Hazael king of Syria at Ramoth Gilead; and the Syrians wounded Joram. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 8029, 'Then King Joram went back to Jezreel to recover from the wounds which the Syrians had inflicted on him at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of Syria. And Ahaziah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, went down to see Joram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9001, 'And Elisha the prophet called one of the sons of the prophets, and said to him, &ldquo;Get yourself ready, take this flask of oil in your hand, and go to Ramoth Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9002, 'Now when you arrive at that place, look there for Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi, and go in and make him rise up from among his associates, and take him to an inner room. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9003, 'Then take the flask of oil, and pour it on his head, and say, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;I have anointed you king over Israel.&rdquo; &lsquo; Then open the door and flee, and do not delay.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9004, 'So the young man, the servant of the prophet, went to Ramoth Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9005, 'And when he arrived, there were the captains of the army sitting; and he said, &ldquo;I have a message for you, Commander.&rdquo; Jehu said, &ldquo;For which one of us?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;For you, Commander.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9006, 'Then he arose and went into the house. And he poured the oil on his head, and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;I have anointed you king over the people of the Lord, over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9007, 'You shall strike down the house of Ahab your master, that I may avenge the blood of My servants the prophets, and the blood of all the servants of the Lord, at the hand of Jezebel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9008, 'For the whole house of Ahab shall perish; and I will cut off from Ahab all the males in Israel, both bond and free. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9009, 'So I will make the house of Ahab like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9010, 'The dogs shall eat Jezebel on the plot of ground at Jezreel, and there shall be none to bury her.&rsquo; &ldquo; And he opened the door and fled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9011, 'Then Jehu came out to the servants of his master, and one said to him, &ldquo;Is all well? Why did this madman come to you?&rdquo; And he said to them, &ldquo;You know the man and his babble.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9012, 'And they said, &ldquo;A lie! Tell us now.&rdquo; So he said, &ldquo;Thus and thus he spoke to me, saying, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;I have anointed you king over Israel.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9013, 'Then each man hastened to take his garment and put it under him on the top of the steps; and they blew trumpets, saying, &ldquo;Jehu is king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9014, 'So Jehu the son of Jehoshaphat, the son of Nimshi, conspired against Joram. (Now Joram had been defending Ramoth Gilead, he and all Israel, against Hazael king of Syria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9015, 'But King Joram had returned to Jezreel to recover from the wounds which the Syrians had inflicted on him when he fought with Hazael king of Syria.) And Jehu said, &ldquo;If you are so minded, let no one leave or escape from the city to go and tell it in Jezreel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9016, 'So Jehu rode in a chariot and went to Jezreel, for Joram was laid up there; and Ahaziah king of Judah had come down to see Joram. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9017, 'Now a watchman stood on the tower in Jezreel, and he saw the company of Jehu as he came, and said, &ldquo;I see a company of men.&rdquo; And Joram said, &ldquo;Get a horseman and send him to meet them, and let him say, &lsquo;Is it peace?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9018, 'So the horseman went to meet him, and said, &ldquo;Thus says the king: &lsquo;Is it peace?&rsquo; &ldquo; And Jehu said, &ldquo;What have you to do with peace? Turn around and follow me.&rdquo; So the watchman reported, saying, &ldquo;The messenger went to them, but is not coming back.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9019, 'Then he sent out a second horseman who came to them, and said, &ldquo;Thus says the king: &lsquo;Is it peace?&rsquo; &ldquo; And Jehu answered, &ldquo;What have you to do with peace? Turn around and follow me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9020, 'So the watchman reported, saying, &ldquo;He went up to them and is not coming back; and the driving is like the driving of Jehu the son of Nimshi, for he drives furiously!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9021, 'Then Joram said, &ldquo;Make ready.&rdquo; And his chariot was made ready. Then Joram king of Israel and Ahaziah king of Judah went out, each in his chariot; and they went out to meet Jehu, and met him on the property of Naboth the Jezreelite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9022, 'Now it happened, when Joram saw Jehu, that he said, &ldquo;Is it peace, Jehu?&rdquo; So he answered, &ldquo;What peace, as long as the harlotries of your mother Jezebel and her witchcraft are so many?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9023, 'Then Joram turned around and fled, and said to Ahaziah, &ldquo;Treachery, Ahaziah!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9024, 'Now Jehu drew his bow with full strength and shot Jehoram between his arms; and the arrow came out at his heart, and he sank down in his chariot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9025, 'Then Jehu said to Bidkar his captain, &ldquo;Pick him up, and throw him into the tract of the field of Naboth the Jezreelite; for remember, when you and I were riding together behind Ahab his father, that the Lord laid this burden upon him: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9026, '&rsquo;Surely I saw yesterday the blood of Naboth and the blood of his sons,&rsquo; says the Lord, &lsquo;and I will repay you in this plot,&rsquo; says the Lord. Now therefore, take and throw him on the plot of ground, according to the word of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9027, 'But when Ahaziah king of Judah saw this, he fled by the road to Beth Haggan. So Jehu pursued him, and said, &ldquo;Shoot him also in the chariot.&rdquo; And they shot him at the Ascent of Gur, which is by Ibleam. Then he fled to Megiddo, and died there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9028, 'And his servants carried him in the chariot to Jerusalem, and buried him in his tomb with his fathers in the City of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9029, 'In the eleventh year of Joram the son of Ahab, Ahaziah had become king over Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9030, 'Now when Jehu had come to Jezreel, Jezebel heard of it; and she put paint on her eyes and adorned her head, and looked through a window. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9031, 'Then, as Jehu entered at the gate, she said, &ldquo;Is it peace, Zimri, murderer of your master?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9032, 'And he looked up at the window, and said, &ldquo;Who is on my side? Who?&rdquo; So two or three eunuchs looked out at him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9033, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Throw her down.&rdquo; So they threw her down, and some of her blood spattered on the wall and on the horses; and he trampled her underfoot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9034, 'And when he had gone in, he ate and drank. Then he said, &ldquo;Go now, see to this accursed woman, and bury her, for she was a king&rsquo;s daughter.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9035, 'So they went to bury her, but they found no more of her than the skull and the feet and the palms of her hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9036, 'Therefore they came back and told him. And he said, &ldquo;This is the word of the Lord, which He spoke by His servant Elijah the Tishbite, saying, &lsquo;On the plot of ground at Jezreel dogs shall eat the flesh of Jezebel;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 9037, 'and the corpse of Jezebel shall be as refuse on the surface of the field, in the plot at Jezreel, so that they shall not say, &ldquo;Here lies Jezebel.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10001, 'Now Ahab had seventy sons in Samaria. And Jehu wrote and sent letters to Samaria, to the rulers of Jezreel,* to the elders, and to those who reared Ahab&rsquo;s sons, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10002, 'Now as soon as this letter comes to you, since your master&rsquo;s sons are with you, and you have chariots and horses, a fortified city also, and weapons, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10003, 'choose the best qualified of your master&rsquo;s sons, set him on his father&rsquo;s throne, and fight for your master&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10004, 'But they were exceedingly afraid, and said, &ldquo;Look, two kings could not stand up to him; how then can we stand?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10005, 'And he who was in charge of the house, and he who was in charge of the city, the elders also, and those who reared the sons, sent to Jehu, saying, &ldquo;We are your servants, we will do all you tell us; but we will not make anyone king. Do what is good in your sight.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10006, 'Then he wrote a second letter to them, saying: If you are for me and will obey my voice, take the heads of the men, your master&rsquo;s sons, and come to me at Jezreel by this time tomorrow. Now the king&rsquo;s sons, seventy persons, were with the great men of the city, who were rearing them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10007, 'So it was, when the letter came to them, that they took the king&rsquo;s sons and slaughtered seventy persons, put their heads in baskets and sent them to him at Jezreel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10008, 'Then a messenger came and told him, saying, &ldquo;They have brought the heads of the king&rsquo;s sons.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Lay them in two heaps at the entrance of the gate until morning.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10009, 'So it was, in the morning, that he went out and stood, and said to all the people, &ldquo;You are righteous. Indeed I conspired against my master and killed him; but who killed all these? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10010, 'Know now that nothing shall fall to the earth of the word of the Lord which the Lord spoke concerning the house of Ahab; for the Lord has done what He spoke by His servant Elijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10011, 'So Jehu killed all who remained of the house of Ahab in Jezreel, and all his great men and his close acquaintances and his priests, until he left him none remaining. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10012, 'And he arose and departed and went to Samaria. On the way, at Beth Eked of the Shepherds, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10013, 'Jehu met with the brothers of Ahaziah king of Judah, and said, &ldquo;Who are you?&rdquo; So they answered, &ldquo;We are the brothers of Ahaziah; we have come down to greet the sons of the king and the sons of the queen mother.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10014, 'And he said, &ldquo;Take them alive!&rdquo; So they took them alive, and killed them at the well of Beth Eked, forty-two men; and he left none of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10015, 'Now when he departed from there, he met Jehonadab the son of Rechab, coming to meet him; and he greeted him and said to him, &ldquo;Is your heart right, as my heart is toward your heart?&rdquo; And Jehonadab answered, &ldquo;It is.&rdquo; Jehu said, &ldquo;If it is, give me your hand.&rdquo; So he gave him his hand, and he took him up to him into the chariot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10016, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Come with me, and see my zeal for the Lord.&rdquo; So they had him ride in his chariot. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10017, 'And when he came to Samaria, he killed all who remained to Ahab in Samaria, till he had destroyed them, according to the word of the Lord which He spoke to Elijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10018, 'Then Jehu gathered all the people together, and said to them, &ldquo;Ahab served Baal a little, Jehu will serve him much. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10019, 'Now therefore, call to me all the prophets of Baal, all his servants, and all his priests. Let no one be missing, for I have a great sacrifice for Baal. Whoever is missing shall not live.&rdquo; But Jehu acted deceptively, with the intent of destroying the worshipers of Baal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10020, 'And Jehu said, &ldquo;Proclaim a solemn assembly for Baal.&rdquo; So they proclaimed it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10021, 'Then Jehu sent throughout all Israel; and all the worshipers of Baal came, so that there was not a man left who did not come. So they came into the temple of Baal, and the temple of Baal was full from one end to the other. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10022, 'And he said to the one in charge of the wardrobe, &ldquo;Bring out vestments for all the worshipers of Baal.&rdquo; So he brought out vestments for them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10023, 'Then Jehu and Jehonadab the son of Rechab went into the temple of Baal, and said to the worshipers of Baal, &ldquo;Search and see that no servants of the Lord are here with you, but only the worshipers of Baal.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10024, 'So they went in to offer sacrifices and burnt offerings. Now Jehu had appointed for himself eighty men on the outside, and had said, &ldquo;If any of the men whom I have brought into your hands escapes, whoever lets him escape, it shall be his life for the life of the other.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10025, 'Now it happened, as soon as he had made an end of offering the burnt offering, that Jehu said to the guard and to the captains, &ldquo;Go in and kill them; let no one come out!&rdquo; And they killed them with the edge of the sword; then the guards and the officers threw them out, and went into the inner room of the temple of Baal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10026, 'And they brought the sacred pillars out of the temple of Baal and burned them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10027, 'Then they broke down the sacred pillar of Baal, and tore down the temple of Baal and made it a refuse dump to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10028, 'Thus Jehu destroyed Baal from Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10029, 'However Jehu did not turn away from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin, that is, from the golden calves that were at Bethel and Dan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10030, 'And the Lord said to Jehu, &ldquo;Because you have done well in doing what is right in My sight, and have done to the house of Ahab all that was in My heart, your sons shall sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10031, 'But Jehu took no heed to walk in the law of the Lord God of Israel with all his heart; for he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam, who had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10032, 'In those days the Lord began to cut off parts of Israel; and Hazael conquered them in all the territory of Israel ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10033, 'from the Jordan eastward: all the land of Gilead &ndash; Gad, Reuben, and Manasseh &ndash; from Aroer, which is by the River Arnon, including Gilead and Bashan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10034, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehu, all that he did, and all his might, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10035, 'So Jehu rested with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria. Then Jehoahaz his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 10036, 'And the period that Jehu reigned over Israel in Samaria was twenty-eight years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11001, 'When Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal heirs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11002, 'But Jehosheba, the daughter of King Joram, sister of Ahaziah, took Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stole him away from among the king&rsquo;s sons who were being murdered; and they hid him and his nurse in the bedroom, from Athaliah, so that he was not killed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11003, 'So he was hidden with her in the house of the Lord for six years, while Athaliah reigned over the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11004, 'In the seventh year Jehoiada sent and brought the captains of hundreds &ndash; of the bodyguards and the escorts &ndash; and brought them into the house of the Lord to him. And he made a covenant with them and took an oath from them in the house of the Lord, and showed them the king&rsquo;s son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11005, 'Then he commanded them, saying, &ldquo;This is what you shall do: One-third of you who come on duty on the Sabbath shall be keeping watch over the king&rsquo;s house, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11006, 'one-third shall be at the gate of Sur, and one-third at the gate behind the escorts. You shall keep the watch of the house, lest it be broken down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11007, 'The two contingents of you who go off duty on the Sabbath shall keep the watch of the house of the Lord for the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11008, 'But you shall surround the king on all sides, every man with his weapons in his hand; and whoever comes within range, let him be put to death. You are to be with the king as he goes out and as he comes in.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11009, 'So the captains of the hundreds did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded. Each of them took his men who were to be on duty on the Sabbath, with those who were going off duty on the Sabbath, and came to Jehoiada the priest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11010, 'And the priest gave the captains of hundreds the spears and shields which had belonged to King David, that were in the temple of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11011, 'Then the escorts stood, every man with his weapons in his hand, all around the king, from the right side of the temple to the left side of the temple, by the altar and the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11012, 'And he brought out the king&rsquo;s son, put the crown on him, and gave him the Testimony; they made him king and anointed him, and they clapped their hands and said, &ldquo;Long live the king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11013, 'Now when Athaliah heard the noise of the escorts and the people, she came to the people in the temple of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11014, 'When she looked, there was the king standing by a pillar according to custom; and the leaders and the trumpeters were by the king. All the people of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets. So Athaliah tore her clothes and cried out, &ldquo;Treason! Treason!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11015, 'And Jehoiada the priest commanded the captains of the hundreds, the officers of the army, and said to them, &ldquo;Take her outside under guard, and slay with the sword whoever follows her.&rdquo; For the priest had said, &ldquo;Do not let her be killed in the house of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11016, 'So they seized her; and she went by way of the horses&rsquo; entrance into the king&rsquo;s house, and there she was killed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11017, 'Then Jehoiada made a covenant between the Lord, the king, and the people, that they should be the Lord&rsquo;s people, and also between the king and the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11018, 'And all the people of the land went to the temple of Baal, and tore it down. They thoroughly broke in pieces its altars and images, and killed Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars. And the priest appointed officers over the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11019, 'Then he took the captains of hundreds, the bodyguards, the escorts, and all the people of the land; and they brought the king down from the house of the Lord, and went by way of the gate of the escorts to the king&rsquo;s house. Then he sat on the throne of the kings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11020, 'So all the people of the land rejoiced; and the city was quiet, for they had slain Athaliah with the sword in the king&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 11021, 'Jehoash was seven years old when he became king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12001, 'In the seventh year of Jehu, Jehoash* became king, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Zibiah of Beersheba. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12002, 'Jehoash did what was right in the sight of the Lord all the days in which Jehoiada the priest instructed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12003, 'But the high places were not taken away; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12004, 'And Jehoash said to the priests, &ldquo;All the money of the dedicated gifts that are brought into the house of the Lord &ndash; each man&rsquo;s census money, each man&rsquo;s assessment money* &ndash; and all the money that a man purposes in his heart to bring into the house of the Lord, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12005, 'let the priests take it themselves, each from his constituency; and let them repair the damages of the temple, wherever any dilapidation is found.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12006, 'Now it was so, by the twenty-third year of King Jehoash, that the priests had not repaired the damages of the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12007, 'So King Jehoash called Jehoiada the priest and the other priests, and said to them, &ldquo;Why have you not repaired the damages of the temple? Now therefore, do not take more money from your constituency, but deliver it for repairing the damages of the temple.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12008, 'And the priests agreed that they would neither receive more money from the people, nor repair the damages of the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12009, 'Then Jehoiada the priest took a chest, bored a hole in its lid, and set it beside the altar, on the right side as one comes into the house of the Lord; and the priests who kept the door put there all the money brought into the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12010, 'So it was, whenever they saw that there was much money in the chest, that the king&rsquo;s scribe and the high priest came up and put it in bags, and counted the money that was found in the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12011, 'Then they gave the money, which had been apportioned, into the hands of those who did the work, who had the oversight of the house of the Lord; and they paid it out to the carpenters and builders who worked on the house of the Lord, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12012, 'and to masons and stonecutters, and for buying timber and hewn stone, to repair the damage of the house of the Lord, and for all that was paid out to repair the temple. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12013, 'However there were not made for the house of the Lord basins of silver, trimmers, sprinkling-bowls, trumpets, any articles of gold or articles of silver, from the money brought into the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12014, 'But they gave that to the workmen, and they repaired the house of the Lord with it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12015, 'Moreover they did not require an account from the men into whose hand they delivered the money to be paid to workmen, for they dealt faithfully. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12016, 'The money from the trespass offerings and the money from the sin offerings was not brought into the house of the Lord. It belonged to the priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12017, 'Hazael king of Syria went up and fought against Gath, and took it; then Hazael set his face to go up to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12018, 'And Jehoash king of Judah took all the sacred things that his fathers, Jehoshaphat and Jehoram and Ahaziah, kings of Judah, had dedicated, and his own sacred things, and all the gold found in the treasuries of the house of the Lord and in the king&rsquo;s house, and sent them to Hazael king of Syria. Then he went away from Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12019, 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12020, 'And his servants arose and formed a conspiracy, and killed Joash in the house of the Millo, which goes down to Silla. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 12021, 'For Jozachar the son of Shimeath and Jehozabad the son of Shomer, his servants, struck him. So he died, and they buried him with his fathers in the City of David. Then Amaziah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13001, 'In the twenty-third year of Joash* the son of Ahaziah, king of Judah, Jehoahaz the son of Jehu became king over Israel in Samaria, and reigned seventeen years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13002, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, and followed the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. He did not depart from them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13003, 'Then the anger of the Lord was aroused against Israel, and He delivered them into the hand of Hazael king of Syria, and into the hand of Ben-Hadad the son of Hazael, all their days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13004, 'So Jehoahaz pleaded with the Lord, and the Lord listened to him; for He saw the oppression of Israel, because the king of Syria oppressed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13005, 'Then the Lord gave Israel a deliverer, so that they escaped from under the hand of the Syrians; and the children of Israel dwelt in their tents as before. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13006, 'Nevertheless they did not depart from the sins of the house of Jeroboam, who had made Israel sin, but walked in them; and the wooden image also remained in Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13007, 'For He left of the army of Jehoahaz only fifty horsemen, ten chariots, and ten thousand foot soldiers; for the king of Syria had destroyed them and made them like the dust at threshing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13008, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoahaz, all that he did, and his might, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13009, 'So Jehoahaz rested with his fathers, and they buried him in Samaria. Then Joash his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13010, 'In the thirty-seventh year of Joash king of Judah, Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz became king over Israel in Samaria, and reigned sixteen years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13011, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord. He did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, but walked in them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13012, 'Now the rest of the acts of Joash, all that he did, and his might with which he fought against Amaziah king of Judah, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13013, 'So Joash rested with his fathers. Then Jeroboam sat on his throne. And Joash was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13014, 'Elisha had become sick with the illness of which he would die. Then Joash the king of Israel came down to him, and wept over his face, and said, &ldquo;O my father, my father, the chariots of Israel and their horsemen!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13015, 'And Elisha said to him, &ldquo;Take a bow and some arrows.&rdquo; So he took himself a bow and some arrows. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13016, 'Then he said to the king of Israel, &ldquo;Put your hand on the bow.&rdquo; So he put his hand on it, and Elisha put his hands on the king&rsquo;s hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13017, 'And he said, &ldquo;Open the east window&rdquo;; and he opened it. Then Elisha said, &ldquo;Shoot&rdquo;; and he shot. And he said, &ldquo;The arrow of the Lord&rsquo;s deliverance and the arrow of deliverance from Syria; for you must strike the Syrians at Aphek till you have destroyed them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13018, 'Then he said, &ldquo;Take the arrows&rdquo;; so he took them. And he said to the king of Israel, &ldquo;Strike the ground&rdquo;; so he struck three times, and stopped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13019, 'And the man of God was angry with him, and said, &ldquo;You should have struck five or six times; then you would have struck Syria till you had destroyed it! But now you will strike Syria only three times.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13020, 'Then Elisha died, and they buried him. And the raiding bands from Moab invaded the land in the spring of the year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13021, 'So it was, as they were burying a man, that suddenly they spied a band of raiders; and they put the man in the tomb of Elisha; and when the man was let down and touched the bones of Elisha, he revived and stood on his feet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13022, 'And Hazael king of Syria oppressed Israel all the days of Jehoahaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13023, 'But the Lord was gracious to them, had compassion on them, and regarded them, because of His covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and would not yet destroy them or cast them from His presence. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13024, 'Now Hazael king of Syria died. Then Ben-Hadad his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 13025, 'And Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz recaptured from the hand of Ben-Hadad, the son of Hazael, the cities which he had taken out of the hand of Jehoahaz his father by war. Three times Joash defeated him and recaptured the cities of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14001, 'In the second year of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel, Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, became king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14002, 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14003, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, yet not like his father David; he did everything as his father Joash had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14004, 'However the high places were not taken away, and the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14005, 'Now it happened, as soon as the kingdom was established in his hand, that he executed his servants who had murdered his father the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14006, 'But the children of the murderers he did not execute, according to what is written in the Book of the Law of Moses, in which the Lord commanded, saying, &ldquo;Fathers shall not be put to death for their children, nor shall children be put to death for their fathers; but a person shall be put to death for his own sin.&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14007, 'He killed ten thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt, and took Sela by war, and called its name Joktheel to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14008, 'Then Amaziah sent messengers to Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz, the son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, &ldquo;Come, let us face one another in battle.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14009, 'And Jehoash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, &ldquo;The thistle that was in Lebanon sent to the cedar that was in Lebanon, saying, &lsquo;Give your daughter to my son as wife&rsquo;; and a wild beast that was in Lebanon passed by and trampled the thistle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14010, 'You have indeed defeated Edom, and your heart has lifted you up. Glory in that, and stay at home; for why should you meddle with trouble so that you fall &ndash; you and Judah with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14011, 'But Amaziah would not heed. Therefore Jehoash king of Israel went out; so he and Amaziah king of Judah faced one another at Beth Shemesh, which belongs to Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14012, 'And Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his tent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14013, 'Then Jehoash king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Jehoash, the son of Ahaziah, at Beth Shemesh; and he went to Jerusalem, and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim to the Corner Gate &ndash; four hundred cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14014, 'And he took all the gold and silver, all the articles that were found in the house of the Lord and in the treasuries of the king&rsquo;s house, and hostages, and returned to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14015, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoash which he did &ndash; his might, and how he fought with Amaziah king of Judah &ndash; are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14016, 'So Jehoash rested with his fathers, and was buried in Samaria with the kings of Israel. Then Jeroboam his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14017, 'Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after the death of Jehoash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14018, 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14019, 'And they formed a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish; but they sent after him to Lachish and killed him there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14020, 'Then they brought him on horses, and he was buried at Jerusalem with his fathers in the City of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14021, 'And all the people of Judah took Azariah, who was sixteen years old, and made him king instead of his father Amaziah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14022, 'He built Elath and restored it to Judah, after the king rested with his fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14023, 'In the fifteenth year of Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, became king in Samaria, and reigned forty-one years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14024, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart from all the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14025, 'He restored the territory of Israel from the entrance of Hamath to the Sea of the Arabah, according to the word of the Lord God of Israel, which He had spoken through His servant Jonah the son of Amittai, the prophet who was from Gath Hepher. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14026, 'For the Lord saw that the affliction of Israel was very bitter; and whether bond or free, there was no helper for Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14027, 'And the Lord did not say that He would blot out the name of Israel from under heaven; but He saved them by the hand of Jeroboam the son of Joash. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14028, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, and all that he did &ndash; his might, how he made war, and how he recaptured for Israel, from Damascus and Hamath, what had belonged to Judah &ndash; are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 14029, 'So Jeroboam rested with his fathers, the kings of Israel. Then Zechariah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15001, 'In the twenty-seventh year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Azariah the son of Amaziah, king of Judah, became king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15002, 'He was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jecholiah of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15003, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his father Amaziah had done, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15004, 'except that the high places were not removed; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15005, 'Then the Lord struck the king, so that he was a leper until the day of his death; so he dwelt in an isolated house. And Jotham the king&rsquo;s son was over the royal house, judging the people of the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15006, 'Now the rest of the acts of Azariah, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15007, 'So Azariah rested with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers in the City of David. Then Jotham his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15008, 'In the thirty-eighth year of Azariah king of Judah, Zechariah the son of Jeroboam reigned over Israel in Samaria six months. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15009, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, as his fathers had done; he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15010, 'Then Shallum the son of Jabesh conspired against him, and struck and killed him in front of the people; and he reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15011, 'Now the rest of the acts of Zechariah, indeed they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15012, 'This was the word of the Lord which He spoke to Jehu, saying, &ldquo;Your sons shall sit on the throne of Israel to the fourth generation.&rdquo; And so it was. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15013, 'Shallum the son of Jabesh became king in the thirty-ninth year of Uzziah king of Judah; and he reigned a full month in Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15014, 'For Menahem the son of Gadi went up from Tirzah, came to Samaria, and struck Shallum the son of Jabesh in Samaria and killed him; and he reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15015, 'Now the rest of the acts of Shallum, and the conspiracy which he led, indeed they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15016, 'Then from Tirzah, Menahem attacked Tiphsah, all who were there, and its territory. Because they did not surrender, therefore he attacked it. All the women there who were with child he ripped open. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15017, 'In the thirty-ninth year of Azariah king of Judah, Menahem the son of Gadi became king over Israel, and reigned ten years in Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15018, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart all his days from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15019, 'Pul king of Assyria came against the land; and Menahem gave Pul a thousand talents of silver, that his hand might be with him to strengthen the kingdom under his control. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15020, 'And Menahem exacted the money from Israel, from all the very wealthy, from each man fifty shekels of silver, to give to the king of Assyria. So the king of Assyria turned back, and did not stay there in the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15021, 'Now the rest of the acts of Menahem, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15022, 'So Menahem rested with his fathers. Then Pekahiah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15023, 'In the fiftieth year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekahiah the son of Menahem became king over Israel in Samaria, and reigned two years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15024, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15025, 'Then Pekah the son of Remaliah, an officer of his, conspired against him and killed him in Samaria, in the citadel of the king&rsquo;s house, along with Argob and Arieh; and with him were fifty men of Gilead. He killed him and reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15026, 'Now the rest of the acts of Pekahiah, and all that he did, indeed they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15027, 'In the fifty-second year of Azariah king of Judah, Pekah the son of Remaliah became king over Israel in Samaria, and reigned twenty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15028, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord; he did not depart from the sins of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who had made Israel sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15029, 'In the days of Pekah king of Israel, Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria came and took Ijon, Abel Beth Maachah, Janoah, Kedesh, Hazor, Gilead, and Galilee, all the land of Naphtali; and he carried them captive to Assyria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15030, 'Then Hoshea the son of Elah led a conspiracy against Pekah the son of Remaliah, and struck and killed him; so he reigned in his place in the twentieth year of Jotham the son of Uzziah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15031, 'Now the rest of the acts of Pekah, and all that he did, indeed they are written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15032, 'In the second year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel, Jotham the son of Uzziah, king of Judah, began to reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15033, 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jerusha the daughter of Zadok. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15034, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord; he did according to all that his father Uzziah had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15035, 'However the high places were not removed; the people still sacrificed and burned incense on the high places. He built the Upper Gate of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15036, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15037, 'In those days the Lord began to send Rezin king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah against Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 15038, 'So Jotham rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the City of David his father. Then Ahaz his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16001, 'In the seventeenth year of Pekah the son of Remaliah, Ahaz the son of Jotham, king of Judah, began to reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16002, 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem; and he did not do what was right in the sight of the Lord his God, as his father David had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16003, 'But he walked in the way of the kings of Israel; indeed he made his son pass through the fire, according to the abominations of the nations whom the Lord had cast out from before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16004, 'And he sacrificed and burned incense on the high places, on the hills, and under every green tree. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16005, 'Then Rezin king of Syria and Pekah the son of Remaliah, king of Israel, came up to Jerusalem to make war; and they besieged Ahaz but could not overcome him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16006, 'At that time Rezin king of Syria captured Elath for Syria, and drove the men of Judah from Elath. Then the Edomites went to Elath, and dwell there to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16007, 'So Ahaz sent messengers to Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria, saying, &ldquo;I am your servant and your son. Come up and save me from the hand of the king of Syria and from the hand of the king of Israel, who rise up against me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16008, 'And Ahaz took the silver and gold that was found in the house of the Lord, and in the treasuries of the king&rsquo;s house, and sent it as a present to the king of Assyria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16009, 'So the king of Assyria heeded him; for the king of Assyria went up against Damascus and took it, carried its people captive to Kir, and killed Rezin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16010, 'Now King Ahaz went to Damascus to meet Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria, and saw an altar that was at Damascus; and King Ahaz sent to Urijah the priest the design of the altar and its pattern, according to all its workmanship. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16011, 'Then Urijah the priest built an altar according to all that King Ahaz had sent from Damascus. So Urijah the priest made it before King Ahaz came back from Damascus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16012, 'And when the king came back from Damascus, the king saw the altar; and the king approached the altar and made offerings on it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16013, 'So he burned his burnt offering and his grain offering; and he poured his drink offering and sprinkled the blood of his peace offerings on the altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16014, 'He also brought the bronze altar which was before the Lord, from the front of the temple &ndash; from between the new altar and the house of the Lord &ndash; and put it on the north side of the new altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16015, 'Then King Ahaz commanded Urijah the priest, saying, &ldquo;On the great new altar burn the morning burnt offering, the evening grain offering, the king&rsquo;s burnt sacrifice, and his grain offering, with the burnt offering of all the people of the land, their grain offering, and their drink offerings; and sprinkle on it all the blood of the burnt offering and all the blood of the sacrifice. And the bronze altar shall be for me to inquire by.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16016, 'Thus did Urijah the priest, according to all that King Ahaz commanded. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16017, 'And King Ahaz cut off the panels of the carts, and removed the lavers from them; and he took down the Sea from the bronze oxen that were under it, and put it on a pavement of stones. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16018, 'Also he removed the Sabbath pavilion which they had built in the temple, and he removed the king&rsquo;s outer entrance from the house of the Lord, on account of the king of Assyria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16019, 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahaz which he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 16020, 'So Ahaz rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the City of David. Then Hezekiah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17001, 'In the twelfth year of Ahaz king of Judah, Hoshea the son of Elah became king of Israel in Samaria, and he reigned nine years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17002, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, but not as the kings of Israel who were before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17003, 'Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against him; and Hoshea became his vassal, and paid him tribute money. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17004, 'And the king of Assyria uncovered a conspiracy by Hoshea; for he had sent messengers to So, king of Egypt, and brought no tribute to the king of Assyria, as he had done year by year. Therefore the king of Assyria shut him up, and bound him in prison. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17005, 'Now the king of Assyria went throughout all the land, and went up to Samaria and besieged it for three years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17006, 'In the ninth year of Hoshea, the king of Assyria took Samaria and carried Israel away to Assyria, and placed them in Halah and by the Habor, the River of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17007, 'For so it was that the children of Israel had sinned against the Lord their God, who had brought them up out of the land of Egypt, from under the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt; and they had feared other gods, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17008, 'and had walked in the statutes of the nations whom the Lord had cast out from before the children of Israel, and of the kings of Israel, which they had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17009, 'Also the children of Israel secretly did against the Lord their God things that were not right, and they built for themselves high places in all their cities, from watchtower to fortified city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17010, 'They set up for themselves sacred pillars and wooden images on every high hill and under every green tree. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17011, 'There they burned incense on all the high places, like the nations whom the Lord had carried away before them; and they did wicked things to provoke the Lord to anger, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17012, 'for they served idols, of which the Lord had said to them, &ldquo;You shall not do this thing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17013, 'Yet the Lord testified against Israel and against Judah, by all of His prophets, every seer, saying, &ldquo;Turn from your evil ways, and keep My commandments and My statutes, according to all the law which I commanded your fathers, and which I sent to you by My servants the prophets.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17014, 'Nevertheless they would not hear, but stiffened their necks, like the necks of their fathers, who did not believe in the Lord their God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17015, 'And they rejected His statutes and His covenant that He had made with their fathers, and His testimonies which He had testified against them; they followed idols, became idolaters, and went after the nations who were all around them, concerning whom the Lord had charged them that they should not do like them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17016, 'So they left all the commandments of the Lord their God, made for themselves a molded image and two calves, made a wooden image and worshiped all the host of heaven, and served Baal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17017, 'And they caused their sons and daughters to pass through the fire, practiced witchcraft and soothsaying, and sold themselves to do evil in the sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17018, 'Therefore the Lord was very angry with Israel, and removed them from His sight; there was none left but the tribe of Judah alone. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17019, 'Also Judah did not keep the commandments of the Lord their God, but walked in the statutes of Israel which they made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17020, 'And the Lord rejected all the descendants of Israel, afflicted them, and delivered them into the hand of plunderers, until He had cast them from His sight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17021, 'For He tore Israel from the house of David, and they made Jeroboam the son of Nebat king. Then Jeroboam drove Israel from following the Lord, and made them commit a great sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17022, 'For the children of Israel walked in all the sins of Jeroboam which he did; they did not depart from them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17023, 'until the Lord removed Israel out of His sight, as He had said by all His servants the prophets. So Israel was carried away from their own land to Assyria, as it is to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17024, 'Then the king of Assyria brought people from Babylon, Cuthah, Ava, Hamath, and from Sepharvaim, and placed them in the cities of Samaria instead of the children of Israel; and they took possession of Samaria and dwelt in its cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17025, 'And it was so, at the beginning of their dwelling there, that they did not fear the Lord; therefore the Lord sent lions among them, which killed some of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17026, 'So they spoke to the king of Assyria, saying, &ldquo;The nations whom you have removed and placed in the cities of Samaria do not know the rituals of the God of the land; therefore He has sent lions among them, and indeed, they are killing them because they do not know the rituals of the God of the land.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17027, 'Then the king of Assyria commanded, saying, &ldquo;Send there one of the priests whom you brought from there; let him go and dwell there, and let him teach them the rituals of the God of the land.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17028, 'Then one of the priests whom they had carried away from Samaria came and dwelt in Bethel, and taught them how they should fear the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17029, 'However every nation continued to make gods of its own, and put them in the shrines on the high places which the Samaritans had made, every nation in the cities where they dwelt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17030, 'The men of Babylon made Succoth Benoth, the men of Cuth made Nergal, the men of Hamath made Ashima, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17031, 'and the Avites made Nibhaz and Tartak; and the Sepharvites burned their children in fire to Adrammelech and Anammelech, the gods of Sepharvaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17032, 'So they feared the Lord, and from every class they appointed for themselves priests of the high places, who sacrificed for them in the shrines of the high places. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17033, 'They feared the Lord, yet served their own gods &ndash; according to the rituals of the nations from among whom they were carried away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17034, 'To this day they continue practicing the former rituals; they do not fear the Lord, nor do they follow their statutes or their ordinances, or the law and commandment which the Lord had commanded the children of Jacob, whom He named Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17035, 'with whom the Lord had made a covenant and charged them, saying: &ldquo;You shall not fear other gods, nor bow down to them nor serve them nor sacrifice to them; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17036, 'but the Lord, who brought you up from the land of Egypt with great power and an outstretched arm, Him you shall fear, Him you shall worship, and to Him you shall offer sacrifice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17037, 'And the statutes, the ordinances, the law, and the commandment which He wrote for you, you shall be careful to observe forever; you shall not fear other gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17038, 'And the covenant that I have made with you, you shall not forget, nor shall you fear other gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17039, 'But the Lord your God you shall fear; and He will deliver you from the hand of all your enemies.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17040, 'However they did not obey, but they followed their former rituals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 17041, 'So these nations feared the Lord, yet served their carved images; also their children and their children&rsquo;s children have continued doing as their fathers did, even to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18001, 'Now it came to pass in the third year of Hoshea the son of Elah, king of Israel, that Hezekiah the son of Ahaz, king of Judah, began to reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18002, 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Abi the daughter of Zechariah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18003, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his father David had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18004, 'He removed the high places and broke the sacred pillars, cut down the wooden image and broke in pieces the bronze serpent that Moses had made; for until those days the children of Israel burned incense to it, and called it Nehushtan.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18005, 'He trusted in the Lord God of Israel, so that after him was none like him among all the kings of Judah, nor who were before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18006, 'For he held fast to the Lord; he did not depart from following Him, but kept His commandments, which the Lord had commanded Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18007, 'The Lord was with him; he prospered wherever he went. And he rebelled against the king of Assyria and did not serve him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18008, 'He subdued the Philistines, as far as Gaza and its territory, from watchtower to fortified city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18009, 'Now it came to pass in the fourth year of King Hezekiah, which was the seventh year of Hoshea the son of Elah, king of Israel, that Shalmaneser king of Assyria came up against Samaria and besieged it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18010, 'And at the end of three years they took it. In the sixth year of Hezekiah, that is, the ninth year of Hoshea king of Israel, Samaria was taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18011, 'Then the king of Assyria carried Israel away captive to Assyria, and put them in Halah and by the Habor, the River of Gozan, and in the cities of the Medes, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18012, 'because they did not obey the voice of the Lord their God, but transgressed His covenant and all that Moses the servant of the Lord had commanded; and they would neither hear nor do them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18013, 'And in the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and took them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18014, 'Then Hezekiah king of Judah sent to the king of Assyria at Lachish, saying, &ldquo;I have done wrong; turn away from me; whatever you impose on me I will pay.&rdquo; And the king of Assyria assessed Hezekiah king of Judah three hundred talents of silver and thirty talents of gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18015, 'So Hezekiah gave him all the silver that was found in the house of the Lord and in the treasuries of the king&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18016, 'At that time Hezekiah stripped the gold from the doors of the temple of the Lord, and from the pillars which Hezekiah king of Judah had overlaid, and gave it to the king of Assyria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18017, 'Then the king of Assyria sent the Tartan, the Rabsaris, and the Rabshakeh from Lachish, with a great army against Jerusalem, to King Hezekiah. And they went up and came to Jerusalem. When they had come up, they went and stood by the aqueduct from the upper pool, which was on the highway to the Fuller&rsquo;s Field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18018, 'And when they had called to the king, Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came out to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18019, 'Then the Rabshakeh said to them, &ldquo;Say now to Hezekiah, &lsquo;Thus says the great king, the king of Assyria: &ldquo;What confidence is this in which you trust? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18020, 'You speak of having plans and power for war; but they are mere words. And in whom do you trust, that you rebel against me? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18021, 'Now look! You are trusting in the staff of this broken reed, Egypt, on which if a man leans, it will go into his hand and pierce it. So is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all who trust in him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18022, 'But if you say to me, &lsquo;We trust in the Lord our God,&rsquo; is it not He whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah has taken away, and said to Judah and Jerusalem, &lsquo;You shall worship before this altar in Jerusalem&rsquo;?&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18023, 'Now therefore, I urge you, give a pledge to my master the king of Assyria, and I will give you two thousand horses &ndash; if you are able on your part to put riders on them! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18024, 'How then will you repel one captain of the least of my master&rsquo;s servants, and put your trust in Egypt for chariots and horsemen? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18025, 'Have I now come up without the Lord against this place to destroy it? The Lord said to me, &lsquo;Go up against this land, and destroy it.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18026, 'Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, Shebna, and Joah said to the Rabshakeh, &ldquo;Please speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand it; and do not speak to us in Hebrew in the hearing of the people who are on the wall.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18027, 'But the Rabshakeh said to them, &ldquo;Has my master sent me to your master and to you to speak these words, and not to the men who sit on the wall, who will eat and drink their own waste with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18028, 'Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out with a loud voice in Hebrew, and spoke, saying, &ldquo;Hear the word of the great king, the king of Assyria! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18029, 'Thus says the king: &lsquo;Do not let Hezekiah deceive you, for he shall not be able to deliver you from his hand; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18030, 'nor let Hezekiah make you trust in the Lord, saying, &ldquo;The Lord will surely deliver us; this city shall not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.&rdquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18031, 'Do not listen to Hezekiah; for thus says the king of Assyria: &lsquo;Make peace with me by a present and come out to me; and every one of you eat from his own vine and every one from his own fig tree, and every one of you drink the waters of his own cistern; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18032, 'until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards, a land of olive groves and honey, that you may live and not die. But do not listen to Hezekiah, lest he persuade you, saying, &ldquo;The Lord will deliver us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18033, 'Has any of the gods of the nations at all delivered its land from the hand of the king of Assyria? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18034, 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim and Hena and Ivah? Indeed, have they delivered Samaria from my hand? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18035, 'Who among all the gods of the lands have delivered their countries from my hand, that the Lord should deliver Jerusalem from my hand?&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18036, 'But the people held their peace and answered him not a word; for the king&rsquo;s commandment was, &ldquo;Do not answer him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 18037, 'Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recorder, came to Hezekiah with their clothes torn, and told him the words of the Rabshakeh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19001, 'And so it was, when King Hezekiah heard it, that he tore his clothes, covered himself with sackcloth, and went into the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19002, 'Then he sent Eliakim, who was over the household, Shebna the scribe, and the elders of the priests, covered with sackcloth, to Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19003, 'And they said to him, &ldquo;Thus says Hezekiah: &lsquo;This day is a day of trouble, and rebuke, and blasphemy; for the children have come to birth, but there is no strength to bring them forth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19004, 'It may be that the Lord your God will hear all the words of the Rabshakeh, whom his master the king of Assyria has sent to reproach the living God, and will rebuke the words which the Lord your God has heard. Therefore lift up your prayer for the remnant that is left.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19005, 'So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19006, 'And Isaiah said to them, &ldquo;Thus you shall say to your master, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: &ldquo;Do not be afraid of the words which you have heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria have blasphemed Me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19007, 'Surely I will send a spirit upon him, and he shall hear a rumor and return to his own land; and I will cause him to fall by the sword in his own land.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19008, 'Then the Rabshakeh returned and found the king of Assyria warring against Libnah, for he heard that he had departed from Lachish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19009, 'And the king heard concerning Tirhakah king of Ethiopia, &ldquo;Look, he has come out to make war with you.&rdquo; So he again sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19010, 'Thus you shall speak to Hezekiah king of Judah, saying: &lsquo;Do not let your God in whom you trust deceive you, saying, Jerusalem shall not be given into the hand of the king of Assyria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19011, 'Look! You have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands by utterly destroying them; and shall you be delivered? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19012, 'Have the gods of the nations delivered those whom my fathers have destroyed, Gozan and Haran and Rezeph, and the people of Eden who were in Telassar? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19013, 'Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad, and the king of the city of Sepharvaim, Hena, and Ivah?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19014, 'And Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers, and read it; and Hezekiah went up to the house of the Lord, and spread it before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19015, 'Then Hezekiah prayed before the Lord, and said: &ldquo;O Lord God of Israel, the One who dwells between the cherubim, You are God, You alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth. You have made heaven and earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19016, 'Incline Your ear, O Lord, and hear; open Your eyes, O Lord, and see; and hear the words of Sennacherib, which he has sent to reproach the living God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19017, 'Truly, Lord, the kings of Assyria have laid waste the nations and their lands, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19018, 'and have cast their gods into the fire; for they were not gods, but the work of men&rsquo;s hands &ndash; wood and stone. Therefore they destroyed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19019, 'Now therefore, O Lord our God, I pray, save us from his hand, that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that You are the Lord God, You alone.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19020, 'Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;Because you have prayed to Me against Sennacherib king of Assyria, I have heard.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19021, 'This is the word which the Lord has spoken concerning him: &lsquo;The virgin, the daughter of Zion, Has despised you, laughed you to scorn; The daughter of Jerusalem Has shaken her head behind your back! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19022, '&rsquo;Whom have you reproached and blasphemed? Against whom have you raised your voice, And lifted up your eyes on high? Against the Holy One of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19023, 'By your messengers you have reproached the Lord, And said: &ldquo;By the multitude of my chariots I have come up to the height of the mountains, To the limits of Lebanon; I will cut down its tall cedars And its choice cypress trees; I will enter the extremity of its borders, To its fruitful forest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19024, 'I have dug and drunk strange water, And with the soles of my feet I have dried up All the brooks of defense.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19025, '&rsquo;Did you not hear long ago How I made it, From ancient times that I formed it? Now I have brought it to pass, That you should be For crushing fortified cities into heaps of ruins. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19026, 'Therefore their inhabitants had little power; They were dismayed and confounded; They were as the grass of the field And the green herb, As the grass on the housetops And grain blighted before it is grown. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19027, '&rsquo;But I know your dwelling place, Your going out and your coming in, And your rage against Me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19028, 'Because your rage against Me and your tumult Have come up to My ears, Therefore I will put My hook in your nose And My bridle in your lips, And I will turn you back By the way which you came. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19029, '&rsquo;This shall be a sign to you: You shall eat this year such as grows of itself, And in the second year what springs from the same; Also in the third year sow and reap, Plant vineyards and eat the fruit of them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19030, 'And the remnant who have escaped of the house of Judah Shall again take root downward, And bear fruit upward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19031, 'For out of Jerusalem shall go a remnant, And those who escape from Mount Zion. The zeal of the Lord of hosts will do this.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19032, 'Therefore thus says the Lord concerning the king of Assyria: &lsquo;He shall not come into this city, Nor shoot an arrow there, Nor come before it with shield, Nor build a siege mound against it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19033, 'By the way that he came, By the same shall he return; And he shall not come into this city,&rsquo; Says the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19034, '&rsquo;For I will defend this city, to save it For My own sake and for My servant David&rsquo;s sake.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19035, 'And it came to pass on a certain night that the angel of the Lord went out, and killed in the camp of the Assyrians one hundred and eighty-five thousand; and when people arose early in the morning, there were the corpses &ndash; all dead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19036, 'So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and went away, returned home, and remained at Nineveh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 19037, 'Now it came to pass, as he was worshiping in the temple of Nisroch his god, that his sons Adrammelech and Sharezer struck him down with the sword; and they escaped into the land of Ararat. Then Esarhaddon his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20001, 'In those days Hezekiah was sick and near death. And Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, went to him and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Set your house in order, for you shall die, and not live.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20002, 'Then he turned his face toward the wall, and prayed to the Lord, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20003, 'Remember now, O Lord, I pray, how I have walked before You in truth and with a loyal heart, and have done what was good in Your sight. And Hezekiah wept bitterly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20004, 'And it happened, before Isaiah had gone out into the middle court, that the word of the Lord came to him, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20005, 'Return and tell Hezekiah the leader of My people, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord, the God of David your father: I have heard your prayer, I have seen your tears; surely I will heal you. On the third day you shall go up to the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20006, 'And I will add to your days fifteen years. I will deliver you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria; and I will defend this city for My own sake, and for the sake of My servant David.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20007, 'Then Isaiah said, &ldquo;Take a lump of figs.&rdquo; So they took and laid it on the boil, and he recovered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20008, 'And Hezekiah said to Isaiah, &ldquo;What is the sign that the Lord will heal me, and that I shall go up to the house of the Lord the third day?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20009, 'Then Isaiah said, &ldquo;This is the sign to you from the Lord, that the Lord will do the thing which He has spoken: shall the shadow go forward ten degrees or go backward ten degrees?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20010, 'And Hezekiah answered, &ldquo;It is an easy thing for the shadow to go down ten degrees; no, but let the shadow go backward ten degrees.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20011, 'So Isaiah the prophet cried out to the Lord, and He brought the shadow ten degrees backward, by which it had gone down on the sundial of Ahaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20012, 'At that time Berodach-Baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon, sent letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he heard that Hezekiah had been sick. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20013, 'And Hezekiah was attentive to them, and showed them all the house of his treasures &ndash; the silver and gold, the spices and precious ointment, and all his armory &ndash; all that was found among his treasures. There was nothing in his house or in all his dominion that Hezekiah did not show them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20014, 'Then Isaiah the prophet went to King Hezekiah, and said to him, &ldquo;What did these men say, and from where did they come to you?&rdquo; So Hezekiah said, &ldquo;They came from a far country, from Babylon.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20015, 'And he said, &ldquo;What have they seen in your house?&rdquo; So Hezekiah answered, &ldquo;They have seen all that is in my house; there is nothing among my treasures that I have not shown them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20016, 'Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, &ldquo;Hear the word of the Lord: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20017, '&rsquo;Behold, the days are coming when all that is in your house, and what your fathers have accumulated until this day, shall be carried to Babylon; nothing shall be left,&rsquo; says the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20018, '&rsquo;And they shall take away some of your sons who will descend from you, whom you will beget; and they shall be eunuchs in the palace of the king of Babylon.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20019, 'So Hezekiah said to Isaiah, &ldquo;The word of the Lord which you have spoken is good!&rdquo; For he said, &ldquo;Will there not be peace and truth at least in my days?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20020, 'Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah &ndash; all his might, and how he made a pool and a tunnel and brought water into the city &ndash; are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 20021, 'So Hezekiah rested with his fathers. Then Manasseh his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21001, 'Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Hephzibah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21002, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to the abominations of the nations whom the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21003, 'For he rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father had destroyed; he raised up altars for Baal, and made a wooden image, as Ahab king of Israel had done; and he worshiped all the host of heaven and served them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21004, 'He also built altars in the house of the Lord, of which the Lord had said, &ldquo;In Jerusalem I will put My name.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21005, 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21006, 'Also he made his son pass through the fire, practiced soothsaying, used witchcraft, and consulted spiritists and mediums. He did much evil in the sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21007, 'He even set a carved image of Asherah that he had made, in the house of which the Lord had said to David and to Solomon his son, &ldquo;In this house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, I will put My name forever; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21008, 'and I will not make the feet of Israel wander anymore from the land which I gave their fathers &ndash; only if they are careful to do according to all that I have commanded them, and according to all the law that My servant Moses commanded them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21009, 'But they paid no attention, and Manasseh seduced them to do more evil than the nations whom the Lord had destroyed before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21010, 'And the Lord spoke by His servants the prophets, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21011, 'Because Manasseh king of Judah has done these abominations (he has acted more wickedly than all the Amorites who were before him, and has also made Judah sin with his idols), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21012, 'therefore thus says the Lord God of Israel: &lsquo;Behold, I am bringing such calamity upon Jerusalem and Judah, that whoever hears of it, both his ears will tingle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21013, 'And I will stretch over Jerusalem the measuring line of Samaria and the plummet of the house of Ahab; I will wipe Jerusalem as one wipes a dish, wiping it and turning it upside down. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21014, 'So I will forsake the remnant of My inheritance and deliver them into the hand of their enemies; and they shall become victims of plunder to all their enemies, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21015, 'because they have done evil in My sight, and have provoked Me to anger since the day their fathers came out of Egypt, even to this day.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21016, 'Moreover Manasseh shed very much innocent blood, till he had filled Jerusalem from one end to another, besides his sin by which he made Judah sin, in doing evil in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21017, 'Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh &ndash; all that he did, and the sin that he committed &ndash; are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21018, 'So Manasseh rested with his fathers, and was buried in the garden of his own house, in the garden of Uzza. Then his son Amon reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21019, 'Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned two years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Meshullemeth the daughter of Haruz of Jotbah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21020, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, as his father Manasseh had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21021, 'So he walked in all the ways that his father had walked; and he served the idols that his father had served, and worshiped them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21022, 'He forsook the Lord God of his fathers, and did not walk in the way of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21023, 'Then the servants of Amon conspired against him, and killed the king in his own house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21024, 'But the people of the land executed all those who had conspired against King Amon. Then the people of the land made his son Josiah king in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21025, 'Now the rest of the acts of Amon which he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 21026, 'And he was buried in his tomb in the garden of Uzza. Then Josiah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22001, 'Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jedidah the daughter of Adaiah of Bozkath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22002, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, and walked in all the ways of his father David; he did not turn aside to the right hand or to the left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22003, 'Now it came to pass, in the eighteenth year of King Josiah, that the king sent Shaphan the scribe, the son of Azaliah, the son of Meshullam, to the house of the Lord, saying: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22004, 'Go up to Hilkiah the high priest, that he may count the money which has been brought into the house of the Lord, which the doorkeepers have gathered from the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22005, 'And let them deliver it into the hand of those doing the work, who are the overseers in the house of the Lord; let them give it to those who are in the house of the Lord doing the work, to repair the damages of the house &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22006, 'to carpenters and builders and masons &ndash; and to buy timber and hewn stone to repair the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22007, 'However there need be no accounting made with them of the money delivered into their hand, because they deal faithfully. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22008, 'Then Hilkiah the high priest said to Shaphan the scribe, &ldquo;I have found the Book of the Law in the house of the Lord.&rdquo; And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan, and he read it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22009, 'So Shaphan the scribe went to the king, bringing the king word, saying, &ldquo;Your servants have gathered the money that was found in the house, and have delivered it into the hand of those who do the work, who oversee the house of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22010, 'Then Shaphan the scribe showed the king, saying, &ldquo;Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.&rdquo; And Shaphan read it before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22011, 'Now it happened, when the king heard the words of the Book of the Law, that he tore his clothes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22012, 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Achbor the son of Michaiah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah a servant of the king, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22013, 'Go, inquire of the Lord for me, for the people and for all Judah, concerning the words of this book that has been found; for great is the wrath of the Lord that is aroused against us, because our fathers have not obeyed the words of this book, to do according to all that is written concerning us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22014, 'So Hilkiah the priest, Ahikam, Achbor, Shaphan, and Asaiah went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tikvah, the son of Harhas, keeper of the wardrobe. (She dwelt in Jerusalem in the Second Quarter.) And they spoke with her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22015, 'Then she said to them, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel, &lsquo;Tell the man who sent you to Me, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22016, 'Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Behold, I will bring calamity on this place and on its inhabitants &ndash; all the words of the book which the king of Judah has read &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22017, 'because they have forsaken Me and burned incense to other gods, that they might provoke Me to anger with all the works of their hands. Therefore My wrath shall be aroused against this place and shall not be quenched.&rsquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22018, 'But as for the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the Lord, in this manner you shall speak to him, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &ldquo;Concerning the words which you have heard &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22019, 'because your heart was tender, and you humbled yourself before the Lord when you heard what I spoke against this place and against its inhabitants, that they would become a desolation and a curse, and you tore your clothes and wept before Me, I also have heard you,&rdquo; says the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 22020, 'Surely, therefore, I will gather you to your fathers, and you shall be gathered to your grave in peace; and your eyes shall not see all the calamity which I will bring on this place.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; So they brought back word to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23001, 'Now the king sent them to gather all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem to him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23002, 'The king went up to the house of the Lord with all the men of Judah, and with him all the inhabitants of Jerusalem &ndash; the priests and the prophets and all the people, both small and great. And he read in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant which had been found in the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23003, 'Then the king stood by a pillar and made a covenant before the Lord, to follow the Lord and to keep His commandments and His testimonies and His statutes, with all his heart and all his soul, to perform the words of this covenant that were written in this book. And all the people took a stand for the covenant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23004, 'And the king commanded Hilkiah the high priest, the priests of the second order, and the doorkeepers, to bring out of the temple of the Lord all the articles that were made for Baal, for Asherah, and for all the host of heaven; and he burned them outside Jerusalem in the fields of Kidron, and carried their ashes to Bethel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23005, 'Then he removed the idolatrous priests whom the kings of Judah had ordained to burn incense on the high places in the cities of Judah and in the places all around Jerusalem, and those who burned incense to Baal, to the sun, to the moon, to the constellations, and to all the host of heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23006, 'And he brought out the wooden image from the house of the Lord, to the Brook Kidron outside Jerusalem, burned it at the Brook Kidron and ground it to ashes, and threw its ashes on the graves of the common people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23007, 'Then he tore down the ritual booths of the perverted persons that were in the house of the Lord, where the women wove hangings for the wooden image. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23008, 'And he brought all the priests from the cities of Judah, and defiled the high places where the priests had burned incense, from Geba to Beersheba; also he broke down the high places at the gates which were at the entrance of the Gate of Joshua the governor of the city, which were to the left of the city gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23009, 'Nevertheless the priests of the high places did not come up to the altar of the Lord in Jerusalem, but they ate unleavened bread among their brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23010, 'And he defiled Topheth, which is in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, that no man might make his son or his daughter pass through the fire to Molech. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23011, 'Then he removed the horses that the kings of Judah had dedicated to the sun, at the entrance to the house of the Lord, by the chamber of Nathan-Melech, the officer who was in the court; and he burned the chariots of the sun with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23012, 'The altars that were on the roof, the upper chamber of Ahaz, which the kings of Judah had made, and the altars which Manasseh had made in the two courts of the house of the Lord, the king broke down and pulverized there, and threw their dust into the Brook Kidron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23013, 'Then the king defiled the high places that were east of Jerusalem, which were on the south of the Mount of Corruption, which Solomon king of Israel had built for Ashtoreth the abomination of the Sidonians, for Chemosh the abomination of the Moabites, and for Milcom the abomination of the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23014, 'And he broke in pieces the sacred pillars and cut down the wooden images, and filled their places with the bones of men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23015, 'Moreover the altar that was at Bethel, and the high place which Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel sin, had made, both that altar and the high place he broke down; and he burned the high place and crushed it to powder, and burned the wooden image. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23016, 'As Josiah turned, he saw the tombs that were there on the mountain. And he sent and took the bones out of the tombs and burned them on the altar, and defiled it according to the word of the Lord which the man of God proclaimed, who proclaimed these words. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23017, 'Then he said, &ldquo;What gravestone is this that I see?&rdquo; So the men of the city told him, &ldquo;It is the tomb of the man of God who came from Judah and proclaimed these things which you have done against the altar of Bethel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23018, 'And he said, &ldquo;Let him alone; let no one move his bones.&rdquo; So they let his bones alone, with the bones of the prophet who came from Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23019, 'Now Josiah also took away all the shrines of the high places that were in the cities of Samaria, which the kings of Israel had made to provoke the Lord to anger; and he did to them according to all the deeds he had done in Bethel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23020, 'He executed all the priests of the high places who were there, on the altars, and burned men&rsquo;s bones on them; and he returned to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23021, 'Then the king commanded all the people, saying, &ldquo;Keep the Passover to the Lord your God, as it is written in this Book of the Covenant.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23022, 'Such a Passover surely had never been held since the days of the judges who judged Israel, nor in all the days of the kings of Israel and the kings of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23023, 'But in the eighteenth year of King Josiah this Passover was held before the Lord in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23024, 'Moreover Josiah put away those who consulted mediums and spiritists, the household gods and idols, all the abominations that were seen in the land of Judah and in Jerusalem, that he might perform the words of the law which were written in the book that Hilkiah the priest found in the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23025, 'Now before him there was no king like him, who turned to the Lord with all his heart, with all his soul, and with all his might, according to all the Law of Moses; nor after him did any arise like him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23026, 'Nevertheless the Lord did not turn from the fierceness of His great wrath, with which His anger was aroused against Judah, because of all the provocations with which Manasseh had provoked Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23027, 'And the Lord said, &ldquo;I will also remove Judah from My sight, as I have removed Israel, and will cast off this city Jerusalem which I have chosen, and the house of which I said, &lsquo;My name shall be there.&rsquo; &ldquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23028, 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23029, 'In his days Pharaoh Necho king of Egypt went to the aid of the king of Assyria, to the River Euphrates; and King Josiah went against him. And Pharaoh Necho killed him at Megiddo when he confronted him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23030, 'Then his servants moved his body in a chariot from Megiddo, brought him to Jerusalem, and buried him in his own tomb. And the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, anointed him, and made him king in his father&rsquo;s place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23031, 'Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23032, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his fathers had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23033, 'Now Pharaoh Necho put him in prison at Riblah in the land of Hamath, that he might not reign in Jerusalem; and he imposed on the land a tribute of one hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23034, 'Then Pharaoh Necho made Eliakim the son of Josiah king in place of his father Josiah, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. And Pharaoh took Jehoahaz and went to Egypt, and he died there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23035, 'So Jehoiakim gave the silver and gold to Pharaoh; but he taxed the land to give money according to the command of Pharaoh; he exacted the silver and gold from the people of the land, from every one according to his assessment, to give it to Pharaoh Necho. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23036, 'Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Zebudah the daughter of Pedaiah of Rumah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 23037, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his fathers had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24001, 'In his days Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up, and Jehoiakim became his vassal for three years. Then he turned and rebelled against him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24002, 'And the Lord sent against him raiding bands of Chaldeans, bands of Syrians, bands of Moabites, and bands of the people of Ammon; He sent them against Judah to destroy it, according to the word of the Lord which He had spoken by His servants the prophets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24003, 'Surely at the commandment of the Lord this came upon Judah, to remove them from His sight because of the sins of Manasseh, according to all that he had done, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24004, 'and also because of the innocent blood that he had shed; for he had filled Jerusalem with innocent blood, which the Lord would not pardon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24005, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, and all that he did, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Judah? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24006, 'So Jehoiakim rested with his fathers. Then Jehoiachin his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24007, 'And the king of Egypt did not come out of his land anymore, for the king of Babylon had taken all that belonged to the king of Egypt from the Brook of Egypt to the River Euphrates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24008, 'Jehoiachin was eighteen years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months. His mother&rsquo;s name was Nehushta the daughter of Elnathan of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24009, 'And he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his father had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24010, 'At that time the servants of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against Jerusalem, and the city was besieged. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24011, 'And Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came against the city, as his servants were besieging it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24012, 'Then Jehoiachin king of Judah, his mother, his servants, his princes, and his officers went out to the king of Babylon; and the king of Babylon, in the eighth year of his reign, took him prisoner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24013, 'And he carried out from there all the treasures of the house of the Lord and the treasures of the king&rsquo;s house, and he cut in pieces all the articles of gold which Solomon king of Israel had made in the temple of the Lord, as the Lord had said. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24014, 'Also he carried into captivity all Jerusalem: all the captains and all the mighty men of valor, ten thousand captives, and all the craftsmen and smiths. None remained except the poorest people of the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24015, 'And he carried Jehoiachin captive to Babylon. The king&rsquo;s mother, the king&rsquo;s wives, his officers, and the mighty of the land he carried into captivity from Jerusalem to Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24016, 'All the valiant men, seven thousand, and craftsmen and smiths, one thousand, all who were strong and fit for war, these the king of Babylon brought captive to Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24017, 'Then the king of Babylon made Mattaniah, Jehoiachin&rsquo;s uncle, king in his place, and changed his name to Zedekiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24018, 'Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Hamutal the daughter of Jeremiah of Libnah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24019, 'He also did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to all that Jehoiakim had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '4Kg', 24020, 'For because of the anger of the Lord this happened in Jerusalem and Judah, that He finally cast them out from His presence. Then Zedekiah rebelled against the king of Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1001, 'Adam, Seth, Enosh,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1002, 'Cainan, Mahalalel, Jared, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1003, 'Enoch, Methuselah, Lamech, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1004, 'Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1005, 'The sons of Japheth were Gomer, Magog, Madai, Javan, Tubal, Meshech, and Tiras. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1006, 'The sons of Gomer were Ashkenaz, Diphath, and Togarmah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1007, 'The sons of Javan were Elishah, Tarshishah, Kittim, and Rodanim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1008, 'The sons of Ham were Cush, Mizraim, Put, and Canaan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1009, 'The sons of Cush were Seba, Havilah, Sabta, Raama, and Sabtecha. The sons of Raama were Sheba and Dedan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1010, 'Cush begot Nimrod; he began to be a mighty one on the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1011, 'Mizraim begot Ludim, Anamim, Lehabim, Naphtuhim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1012, 'Pathrusim, Casluhim (from whom came the Philistines and the Caphtorim). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1013, 'Canaan begot Sidon, his firstborn, and Heth; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1014, 'the Jebusite, the Amorite, and the Girgashite; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1015, 'the Hivite, the Arkite, and the Sinite; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1016, 'the Arvadite, the Zemarite, and the Hamathite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1017, 'The sons of Shem were Elam, Asshur, Arphaxad, Lud, Aram, Uz, Hul, Gether, and Meshech.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1018, 'Arphaxad begot Shelah, and Shelah begot Eber. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1019, 'To Eber were born two sons: the name of one was Peleg, for in his days the earth was divided; and his brother&rsquo;s name was Joktan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1020, 'Joktan begot Almodad, Sheleph, Hazarmaveth, Jerah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1021, 'Hadoram, Uzal, Diklah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1022, 'Ebal, Abimael, Sheba, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1023, 'Ophir, Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1024, 'Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1025, 'Eber, Peleg, Reu, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1026, 'Serug, Nahor, Terah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1027, 'and Abram, who is Abraham. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1028, 'The sons of Abraham were Isaac and Ishmael. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1029, 'These are their genealogies: The firstborn of Ishmael was Nebajoth; then Kedar, Adbeel, Mibsam, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1030, 'Mishma, Dumah, Massa, Hadad, Tema, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1031, 'Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These were the sons of Ishmael. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1032, 'Now the sons born to Keturah, Abraham&rsquo;s concubine, were Zimran, Jokshan, Medan, Midian, Ishbak, and Shuah. The sons of Jokshan were Sheba and Dedan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1033, 'The sons of Midian were Ephah, Epher, Hanoch, Abida, and Eldaah. All these were the children of Keturah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1034, 'And Abraham begot Isaac. The sons of Isaac were Esau and Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1035, 'The sons of Esau were Eliphaz, Reuel, Jeush, Jaalam, and Korah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1036, 'And the sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zephi, Gatam, and Kenaz; and by Timna, Amalek. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1037, 'The sons of Reuel were Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1038, 'The sons of Seir were Lotan, Shobal, Zibeon, Anah, Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1039, 'And the sons of Lotan were Hori and Homam; Lotan&rsquo;s sister was Timna. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1040, 'The sons of Shobal were Alian, Manahath, Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. The sons of Zibeon were Ajah and Anah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1041, 'The son of Anah was Dishon. The sons of Dishon were Hamran, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1042, 'The sons of Ezer were Bilhan, Zaavan, and Jaakan. The sons of Dishan were Uz and Aran. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1043, 'Now these were the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before a king reigned over the children of Israel: Bela the son of Beor, and the name of his city was Dinhabah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1044, 'And when Bela died, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1045, 'When Jobab died, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1046, 'And when Husham died, Hadad the son of Bedad, who attacked Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his place. The name of his city was Avith. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1047, 'When Hadad died, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1048, 'And when Samlah died, Saul of Rehoboth-by-the-River reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1049, 'When Saul died, Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1050, 'And when Baal-Hanan died, Hadad reigned in his place; and the name of his city was Pai. His wife&rsquo;s name was Mehetabel the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1051, 'Hadad died also. And the chiefs of Edom were Chief Timnah, Chief Aliah, Chief Jetheth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1052, 'Chief Aholibamah, Chief Elah, Chief Pinon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1053, 'Chief Kenaz, Chief Teman, Chief Mibzar, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 1054, 'Chief Magdiel, and Chief Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2001, 'These were the sons of Israel: Reuben, Simeon, Levi, Judah, Issachar, Zebulun, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2002, 'Dan, Joseph, Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2003, 'The sons of Judah were Er, Onan, and Shelah. These three were born to him by the daughter of Shua, the Canaanitess. Er, the firstborn of Judah, was wicked in the sight of the Lord; so He killed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2004, 'And Tamar, his daughter-in-law, bore him Perez and Zerah. All the sons of Judah were five. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2005, 'The sons of Perez were Hezron and Hamul. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2006, 'The sons of Zerah were Zimri, Ethan, Heman, Calcol, and Dara &ndash; five of them in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2007, 'The son of Carmi was Achar, the troubler of Israel, who transgressed in the accursed thing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2008, 'The son of Ethan was Azariah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2009, 'Also the sons of Hezron who were born to him were Jerahmeel, Ram, and Chelubai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2010, 'Ram begot Amminadab, and Amminadab begot Nahshon, leader of the children of Judah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2011, 'Nahshon begot Salma, and Salma begot Boaz; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2012, 'Boaz begot Obed, and Obed begot Jesse; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2013, 'Jesse begot Eliab his firstborn, Abinadab the second, Shimea the third, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2014, 'Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2015, 'Ozem the sixth, and David the seventh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2016, 'Now their sisters were Zeruiah and Abigail. And the sons of Zeruiah were Abishai, Joab, and Asahel &ndash; three. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2017, 'Abigail bore Amasa; and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2018, 'Caleb the son of Hezron had children by Azubah, his wife, and by Jerioth. Now these were her sons: Jesher, Shobab, and Ardon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2019, 'When Azubah died, Caleb took Ephrath as his wife, who bore him Hur. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2020, 'And Hur begot Uri, and Uri begot Bezalel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2021, 'Now afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Gilead, whom he married when he was sixty years old; and she bore him Segub. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2022, 'Segub begot Jair, who had twenty-three cities in the land of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2023, '(Geshur and Syria took from them the towns of Jair, with Kenath and its towns &ndash; sixty towns.) All these belonged to the sons of Machir the father of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2024, 'After Hezron died in Caleb Ephrathah, Hezron&rsquo;s wife Abijah bore him Ashhur the father of Tekoa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2025, 'The sons of Jerahmeel, the firstborn of Hezron, were Ram, the firstborn, and Bunah, Oren, Ozem, and Ahijah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2026, 'Jerahmeel had another wife, whose name was Atarah; she was the mother of Onam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2027, 'The sons of Ram, the firstborn of Jerahmeel, were Maaz, Jamin, and Eker. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2028, 'The sons of Onam were Shammai and Jada. The sons of Shammai were Nadab and Abishur. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2029, 'And the name of the wife of Abishur was Abihail, and she bore him Ahban and Molid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2030, 'The sons of Nadab were Seled and Appaim; Seled died without children. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2031, 'The son of Appaim was Ishi, the son of Ishi was Sheshan, and Sheshan&rsquo;s child was Ahlai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2032, 'The sons of Jada, the brother of Shammai, were Jether and Jonathan; Jether died without children. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2033, 'The sons of Jonathan were Peleth and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2034, 'Now Sheshan had no sons, only daughters. And Sheshan had an Egyptian servant whose name was Jarha. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2035, 'Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant as wife, and she bore him Attai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2036, 'Attai begot Nathan, and Nathan begot Zabad; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2037, 'Zabad begot Ephlal, and Ephlal begot Obed; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2038, 'Obed begot Jehu, and Jehu begot Azariah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2039, 'Azariah begot Helez, and Helez begot Eleasah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2040, 'Eleasah begot Sismai, and Sismai begot Shallum; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2041, 'Shallum begot Jekamiah, and Jekamiah begot Elishama. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2042, 'The descendants of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel were Mesha, his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph, and the sons of Mareshah the father of Hebron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2043, 'The sons of Hebron were Korah, Tappuah, Rekem, and Shema. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2044, 'Shema begot Raham the father of Jorkoam, and Rekem begot Shammai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2045, 'And the son of Shammai was Maon, and Maon was the father of Beth Zur. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2046, 'Ephah, Caleb&rsquo;s concubine, bore Haran, Moza, and Gazez; and Haran begot Gazez. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2047, 'And the sons of Jahdai were Regem, Jotham, Geshan, Pelet, Ephah, and Shaaph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2048, 'Maachah, Caleb&rsquo;s concubine, bore Sheber and Tirhanah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2049, 'She also bore Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbenah and the father of Gibea. And the daughter of Caleb was Achsah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2050, 'These were the descendants of Caleb: The sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, were Shobal the father of Kirjath Jearim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2051, 'Salma the father of Bethlehem, and Hareph the father of Beth Gader. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2052, 'And Shobal the father of Kirjath Jearim had descendants: Haroeh, and half of the families of Manuhoth.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2053, 'The families of Kirjath Jearim were the Ithrites, the Puthites, the Shumathites, and the Mishraites. From these came the Zorathites and the Eshtaolites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2054, 'The sons of Salma were Bethlehem, the Netophathites, Atroth Beth Joab, half of the Manahethites, and the Zorites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 2055, 'And the families of the scribes who dwelt at Jabez were the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, and the Suchathites. These were the Kenites who came from Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3001, 'Now these were the sons of David who were born to him in Hebron: The firstborn was Amnon, by Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second, Daniel,* by Abigail the Carmelitess; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3002, 'the third, Absalom the son of Maacah, the daughter of Talmai, king of Geshur; the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3003, 'the fifth, Shephatiah, by Abital; the sixth, Ithream, by his wife Eglah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3004, 'These six were born to him in Hebron. There he reigned seven years and six months, and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3005, 'And these were born to him in Jerusalem: Shimea, Shobab, Nathan, and Solomon &ndash; four by Bathshua the daughter of Ammiel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3006, 'Also there were Ibhar, Elishama, Eliphelet,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3007, 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3008, 'Elishama, Eliada, and Eliphelet &ndash; nine in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3009, 'These were all the sons of David, besides the sons of the concubines, and Tamar their sister. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3010, 'Solomon&rsquo;s son was Rehoboam; Abijah was his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3011, 'Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3012, 'Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3013, 'Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3014, 'Amon his son, and Josiah his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3015, 'The sons of Josiah were Johanan the firstborn, the second Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, and the fourth Shallum.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3016, 'The sons of Jehoiakim were Jeconiah his son and Zedekiah his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3017, 'And the sons of Jeconiah were Assir, Shealtiel his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3018, 'and Malchiram, Pedaiah, Shenazzar, Jecamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3019, 'The sons of Pedaiah were Zerubbabel and Shimei. The sons of Zerubbabel were Meshullam, Hananiah, Shelomith their sister, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3020, 'and Hashubah, Ohel, Berechiah, Hasadiah, and Jushab-Hesed &ndash; five in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3021, 'The sons of Hananiah were Pelatiah and Jeshaiah, the sons of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, and the sons of Shechaniah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3022, 'The son of Shechaniah was Shemaiah. The sons of Shemaiah were Hattush, Igal, Bariah, Neariah, and Shaphat &ndash; six in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3023, 'The sons of Neariah were Elioenai, Hezekiah, and Azrikam &ndash; three in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 3024, 'The sons of Elioenai were Hodaviah, Eliashib, Pelaiah, Akkub, Johanan, Delaiah, and Anani &ndash; seven in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4001, 'The sons of Judah were Perez, Hezron, Carmi, Hur, and Shobal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4002, 'And Reaiah the son of Shobal begot Jahath, and Jahath begot Ahumai and Lahad. These were the families of the Zorathites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4003, 'These were the sons of the father of Etam: Jezreel, Ishma, and Idbash; and the name of their sister was Hazelelponi; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4004, 'and Penuel was the father of Gedor, and Ezer was the father of Hushah. These were the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah the father of Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4005, 'And Ashhur the father of Tekoa had two wives, Helah and Naarah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4006, 'Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, Hepher, Temeni, and Haahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4007, 'The sons of Helah were Zereth, Zohar, and Ethnan; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4008, 'and Koz begot Anub, Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4009, 'Now Jabez was more honorable than his brothers, and his mother called his name Jabez, saying, &ldquo;Because I bore him in pain.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4010, 'And Jabez called on the God of Israel saying, &ldquo;Oh, that You would bless me indeed, and enlarge my territory, that Your hand would be with me, and that You would keep me from evil, that I may not cause pain!&rdquo; So God granted him what he requested. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4011, 'Chelub the brother of Shuhah begot Mehir, who was the father of Eshton. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4012, 'And Eshton begot Beth-Rapha, Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of Ir-Nahash. These were the men of Rechah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4013, 'The sons of Kenaz were Othniel and Seraiah. The sons of Othniel were Hathath,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4014, 'and Meonothai who begot Ophrah. Seraiah begot Joab the father of Ge Harashim, for they were craftsmen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4015, 'The sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh were Iru, Elah, and Naam. The son of Elah was Kenaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4016, 'The sons of Jehallelel were Ziph, Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4017, 'The sons of Ezrah were Jether, Mered, Epher, and Jalon. And Mered&rsquo;s wife bore Miriam, Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4018, '(His wife Jehudijah* bore Jered the father of Gedor, Heber the father of Sochoh, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah.) And these were the sons of Bithiah the daughter of Pharaoh, whom Mered took. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4019, 'The sons of Hodiah&rsquo;s wife, the sister of Naham, were the fathers of Keilah the Garmite and of Eshtemoa the Maachathite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4020, 'And the sons of Shimon were Amnon, Rinnah, Ben-Hanan, and Tilon. And the sons of Ishi were Zoheth and Ben-Zoheth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4021, 'The sons of Shelah the son of Judah were Er the father of Lecah, Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of the linen workers of the house of Ashbea; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4022, 'also Jokim, the men of Chozeba, and Joash; Saraph, who ruled in Moab, and Jashubi-Lehem. Now the records are ancient. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4023, 'These were the potters and those who dwell at Netaim and Gederah; there they dwelt with the king for his work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4024, 'The sons of Simeon were Nemuel, Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, and Shaul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4025, 'Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, and Mishma his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4026, 'And the sons of Mishma were Hamuel his son, Zacchur his son, and Shimei his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4027, 'Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers did not have many children, nor did any of their families multiply as much as the children of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4028, 'They dwelt at Beersheba, Moladah, Hazar Shual, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4029, 'Bilhah, Ezem, Tolad, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4030, 'Bethuel, Hormah, Ziklag, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4031, 'Beth Marcaboth, Hazar Susim, Beth Biri, and at Shaaraim. These were their cities until the reign of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4032, 'And their villages were Etam, Ain, Rimmon, Tochen, and Ashan &ndash; five cities &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4033, 'and all the villages that were around these cities as far as Baal. These were their dwelling places, and they maintained their genealogy: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4034, 'Meshobab, Jamlech, and Joshah the son of Amaziah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4035, 'Joel, and Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4036, 'Elioenai, Jaakobah, Jeshohaiah, Asaiah, Adiel, Jesimiel, and Benaiah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4037, 'Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4038, 'these mentioned by name were leaders in their families, and their father&rsquo;s house increased greatly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4039, 'So they went to the entrance of Gedor, as far as the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4040, 'And they found rich, good pasture, and the land was broad, quiet, and peaceful; for some Hamites formerly lived there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4041, 'These recorded by name came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah; and they attacked their tents and the Meunites who were found there, and utterly destroyed them, as it is to this day. So they dwelt in their place, because there was pasture for their flocks there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4042, 'Now some of them, five hundred men of the sons of Simeon, went to Mount Seir, having as their captains Pelatiah, Neariah, Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 4043, 'And they defeated the rest of the Amalekites who had escaped. They have dwelt there to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5001, 'Now the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel &ndash; he was indeed the firstborn, but because he defiled his father&rsquo;s bed, his birthright was given to the sons of Joseph, the son of Israel, so that the genealogy is not listed according to the birthright; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5002, 'yet Judah prevailed over his brothers, and from him came a ruler, although the birthright was Joseph&rsquo;s &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5003, 'the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel were Hanoch, Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5004, 'The sons of Joel were Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5005, 'Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5006, 'and Beerah his son, whom Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria carried into captivity. He was leader of the Reubenites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5007, 'And his brethren by their families, when the genealogy of their generations was registered: the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5008, 'and Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who dwelt in Aroer, as far as Nebo and Baal Meon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5009, 'Eastward they settled as far as the entrance of the wilderness this side of the River Euphrates, because their cattle had multiplied in the land of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5010, 'Now in the days of Saul they made war with the Hagrites, who fell by their hand; and they dwelt in their tents throughout the entire area east of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5011, 'And the children of Gad dwelt next to them in the land of Bashan as far as Salcah: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5012, 'Joel was the chief, Shapham the next, then Jaanai and Shaphat in Bashan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5013, 'and their brethren of their father&rsquo;s house: Michael, Meshullam, Sheba, Jorai, Jachan, Zia, and Eber &ndash; seven in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5014, 'These were the children of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5015, 'Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, was chief of their father&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5016, 'And the Gadites dwelt in Gilead, in Bashan and in its villages, and in all the common-lands of Sharon within their borders. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5017, 'All these were registered by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5018, 'The sons of Reuben, the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh had forty-four thousand seven hundred and sixty valiant men, men able to bear shield and sword, to shoot with the bow, and skillful in war, who went to war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5019, 'They made war with the Hagrites, Jetur, Naphish, and Nodab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5020, 'And they were helped against them, and the Hagrites were delivered into their hand, and all who were with them, for they cried out to God in the battle. He heeded their prayer, because they put their trust in Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5021, 'Then they took away their livestock &ndash; fifty thousand of their camels, two hundred and fifty thousand of their sheep, and two thousand of their donkeys &ndash; also one hundred thousand of their men; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5022, 'for many fell dead, because the war was God&rsquo;s. And they dwelt in their place until the captivity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5023, 'So the children of the half-tribe of Manasseh dwelt in the land. Their numbers increased from Bashan to Baal Hermon, that is, to Senir, or Mount Hermon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5024, 'These were the heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses: Epher, Ishi, Eliel, Azriel, Jeremiah, Hodaviah, and Jahdiel. They were mighty men of valor, famous men, and heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5025, 'And they were unfaithful to the God of their fathers, and played the harlot after the gods of the peoples of the land, whom God had destroyed before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 5026, 'So the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, that is, Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria. He carried the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh into captivity. He took them to Halah, Habor, Hara, and the river of Gozan to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6001, 'The sons of Levi were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6002, 'The sons of Kohath were Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6003, 'The children of Amram were Aaron, Moses, and Miriam. And the sons of Aaron were Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6004, 'Eleazar begot Phinehas, and Phinehas begot Abishua; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6005, 'Abishua begot Bukki, and Bukki begot Uzzi; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6006, 'Uzzi begot Zerahiah, and Zerahiah begot Meraioth; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6007, 'Meraioth begot Amariah, and Amariah begot Ahitub; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6008, 'Ahitub begot Zadok, and Zadok begot Ahimaaz; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6009, 'Ahimaaz begot Azariah, and Azariah begot Johanan; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6010, 'Johanan begot Azariah (it was he who ministered as priest in the temple that Solomon built in Jerusalem); ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6011, 'Azariah begot Amariah, and Amariah begot Ahitub; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6012, 'Ahitub begot Zadok, and Zadok begot Shallum; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6013, 'Shallum begot Hilkiah, and Hilkiah begot Azariah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6014, 'Azariah begot Seraiah, and Seraiah begot Jehozadak. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6015, 'Jehozadak went into captivity when the Lord carried Judah and Jerusalem into captivity by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6016, 'The sons of Levi were Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6017, 'These are the names of the sons of Gershon: Libni and Shimei. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6018, 'The sons of Kohath were Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6019, 'The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi. Now these are the families of the Levites according to their fathers: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6020, 'Of Gershon were Libni his son, Jahath his son, Zimmah his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6021, 'Joah his son, Iddo his son, Zerah his son, and Jeatherai his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6022, 'The sons of Kohath were Amminadab his son, Korah his son, Assir his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6023, 'Elkanah his son, Ebiasaph his son, Assir his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6024, 'Tahath his son, Uriel his son, Uzziah his son, and Shaul his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6025, 'The sons of Elkanah were Amasai and Ahimoth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6026, 'As for Elkanah, the sons of Elkanah were Zophai his son, Nahath his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6027, 'Eliab his son, Jeroham his son, and Elkanah his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6028, 'The sons of Samuel were Joel the firstborn, and Abijah the second.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6029, 'The sons of Merari were Mahli, Libni his son, Shimei his son, Uzzah his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6030, 'Shimea his son, Haggiah his son, and Asaiah his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6031, 'Now these are the men whom David appointed over the service of song in the house of the Lord, after the ark came to rest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6032, 'They were ministering with music before the dwelling place of the tabernacle of meeting, until Solomon had built the house of the Lord in Jerusalem, and they served in their office according to their order. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6033, 'And these are the ones who ministered with their sons: Of the sons of the Kohathites were Heman the singer, the son of Joel, the son of Samuel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6034, 'the son of Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Eliel, the son of Toah,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6035, 'the son of Zuph, the son of Elkanah, the son of Mahath, the son of Amasai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6036, 'the son of Elkanah, the son of Joel, the son of Azariah, the son of Zephaniah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6037, 'the son of Tahath, the son of Assir, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6038, 'the son of Izhar, the son of Kohath, the son of Levi, the son of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6039, 'And his brother Asaph, who stood at his right hand, was Asaph the son of Berachiah, the son of Shimea, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6040, 'the son of Michael, the son of Baaseiah, the son of Malchijah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6041, 'the son of Ethni, the son of Zerah, the son of Adaiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6042, 'the son of Ethan, the son of Zimmah, the son of Shimei, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6043, 'the son of Jahath, the son of Gershon, the son of Levi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6044, 'Their brethren, the sons of Merari, on the left hand, were Ethan the son of Kishi, the son of Abdi, the son of Malluch, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6045, 'the son of Hashabiah, the son of Amaziah, the son of Hilkiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6046, 'the son of Amzi, the son of Bani, the son of Shamer, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6047, 'the son of Mahli, the son of Mushi, the son of Merari, the son of Levi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 6048, 'And their brethren, the Levites, were appointed to every kind of service of the tabernacle of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7001, 'The sons of Issachar were Tola, Puah,* Jashub, and Shimron &ndash; four in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7002, 'The sons of Tola were Uzzi, Rephaiah, Jeriel, Jahmai, Jibsam, and Shemuel, heads of their father&rsquo;s house. The sons of Tola were mighty men of valor in their generations; their number in the days of David was twenty-two thousand six hundred. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7003, 'The son of Uzzi was Izrahiah, and the sons of Izrahiah were Michael, Obadiah, Joel, and Ishiah. All five of them were chief men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7004, 'And with them, by their generations, according to their fathers&rsquo; houses, were thirty-six thousand troops ready for war; for they had many wives and sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7005, 'Now their brethren among all the families of Issachar were mighty men of valor, listed by their genealogies, eighty-seven thousand in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7006, 'The sons of Benjamin were Bela, Becher, and Jediael &ndash; three in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7007, 'The sons of Bela were Ezbon, Uzzi, Uzziel, Jerimoth, and Iri &ndash; five in all. They were heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, and they were listed by their genealogies, twenty-two thousand and thirty-four mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7008, 'The sons of Becher were Zemirah, Joash, Eliezer, Elioenai, Omri, Jerimoth, Abijah, Anathoth, and Alemeth. All these are the sons of Becher. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7009, 'And they were recorded by genealogy according to their generations, heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, twenty thousand two hundred mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7010, 'The son of Jediael was Bilhan, and the sons of Bilhan were Jeush, Benjamin, Ehud, Chenaanah, Zethan, Tharshish, and Ahishahar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7011, 'All these sons of Jediael were heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses; there were seventeen thousand two hundred mighty men of valor fit to go out for war and battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7012, 'Shuppim and Huppim were the sons of Ir, and Hushim was the son of Aher. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7013, 'The sons of Naphtali were Jahziel, Guni, Jezer, and Shallum, the sons of Bilhah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7014, 'The descendants of Manasseh: his Syrian concubine bore him Machir the father of Gilead, the father of Asriel.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7015, 'Machir took as his wife the sister of Huppim and Shuppim, whose name was Maachah. The name of Gilead&rsquo;s grandson was Zelophehad, but Zelophehad begot only daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7016, '(Maachah the wife of Machir bore a son, and she called his name Peresh. The name of his brother was Sheresh, and his sons were Ulam and Rakem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7017, 'The son of Ulam was Bedan.) These were the descendants of Gilead the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7018, 'His sister Hammoleketh bore Ishhod, Abiezer, and Mahlah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7019, 'And the sons of Shemida were Ahian, Shechem, Likhi, and Aniam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7020, 'The sons of Ephraim were Shuthelah, Bered his son, Tahath his son, Eladah his son, Tahath his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7021, 'Zabad his son, Shuthelah his son, and Ezer and Elead. The men of Gath who were born in that land killed them because they came down to take away their cattle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7022, 'Then Ephraim their father mourned many days, and his brethren came to comfort him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7023, 'And when he went in to his wife, she conceived and bore a son; and he called his name Beriah, because tragedy had come upon his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7024, 'Now his daughter was Sheerah, who built Lower and Upper Beth Horon and Uzzen Sheerah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7025, 'and Rephah was his son, as well as Resheph, and Telah his son, Tahan his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7026, 'Laadan his son, Ammihud his son, Elishama his son, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7027, 'Nun his son, and Joshua his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7028, 'Now their possessions and dwelling places were Bethel and its towns: to the east Naaran, to the west Gezer and its towns, and Shechem and its towns, as far as Ayyah and its towns; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7029, 'and by the borders of the children of Manasseh were Beth Shean and its towns, Taanach and its towns, Megiddo and its towns, Dor and its towns. In these dwelt the children of Joseph, the son of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7030, 'The sons of Asher were Imnah, Ishvah, Ishvi, Beriah, and their sister Serah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7031, 'The sons of Beriah were Heber and Malchiel, who was the father of Birzaith.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7032, 'And Heber begot Japhlet, Shomer, Hotham, and their sister Shua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7033, 'The sons of Japhlet were Pasach, Bimhal, and Ashvath. These were the children of Japhlet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7034, 'The sons of Shemer were Ahi, Rohgah, Jehubbah, and Aram. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7035, 'And the sons of his brother Helem were Zophah, Imna, Shelesh, and Amal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7036, 'The sons of Zophah were Suah, Harnepher, Shual, Beri, Imrah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7037, 'Bezer, Hod, Shamma, Shilshah, Jithran, and Beera. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7038, 'The sons of Jether were Jephunneh, Pispah, and Ara. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7039, 'The sons of Ulla were Arah, Haniel, and Rizia. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 7040, 'All these were the children of Asher, heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, choice men, mighty men of valor, chief leaders. And they were recorded by genealogies among the army fit for battle; their number was twenty-six thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8001, 'Now Benjamin begot Bela his firstborn, Ashbel the second, Aharah* the third, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8002, 'Nohah the fourth, and Rapha the fifth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8003, 'The sons of Bela were Addar*, Gera, Abihud, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8004, 'Abishua, Naaman, Ahoah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8005, 'Gera, Shephuphan, and Huram. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8006, 'These are the sons of Ehud, who were the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the inhabitants of Geba, and who forced them to move to Manahath: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8007, 'Naaman, Ahijah, and Gera who forced them to move. He begot Uzza and Ahihud. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8008, 'And Shaharaim had children in the country of Moab, after he had sent away Hushim and Baara his wives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8009, 'By Hodesh his wife he begot Jobab, Zibia, Mesha, Malcam, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8010, 'Jeuz, Sachiah, and Mirmah. These were his sons, heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8011, 'And by Hushim he begot Abitub and Elpaal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8012, 'The sons of Elpaal were Eber, Misham, and Shemed, who built Ono and Lod with its towns; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8013, 'and Beriah and Shema, who were heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses of the inhabitants of Aijalon, who drove out the inhabitants of Gath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8014, 'Ahio, Shashak, Jeremoth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8015, 'Zebadiah, Arad, Eder, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8016, 'Michael, Ispah, and Joha were the sons of Beriah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8017, 'Zebadiah, Meshullam, Hizki, Heber, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8018, 'Ishmerai, Jizliah, and Jobab were the sons of Elpaal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8019, 'Jakim, Zichri, Zabdi, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8020, 'Elienai, Zillethai, Eliel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8021, 'Adaiah, Beraiah, and Shimrath were the sons of Shimei. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8022, 'Ishpan, Eber, Eliel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8023, 'Abdon, Zichri, Hanan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8024, 'Hananiah, Elam, Antothijah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8025, 'Iphdeiah, and Penuel were the sons of Shashak. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8026, 'Shamsherai, Shehariah, Athaliah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8027, 'Jaareshiah, Elijah, and Zichri were the sons of Jeroham. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8028, 'These were heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses by their generations, chief men. These dwelt in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8029, 'Now the father of Gibeon, whose wife&rsquo;s name was Maacah, dwelt at Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8030, 'And his firstborn son was Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Nadab, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8031, 'Gedor, Ahio, Zecher, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8032, 'and Mikloth, who begot Shimeah. They also dwelt alongside their relatives in Jerusalem, with their brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8033, 'Ner begot Kish, Kish begot Saul, and Saul begot Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab, and Esh-Baal.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8034, 'The son of Jonathan was Merib-Baal, and Merib-Baal begot Micah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8035, 'The sons of Micah were Pithon, Melech, Tarea, and Ahaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8036, 'And Ahaz begot Jehoaddah; Jehoaddah begot Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri begot Moza. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8037, 'Moza begot Binea, Raphah his son, Eleasah his son, and Azel his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8038, 'Azel had six sons whose names were these: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan. All these were the sons of Azel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8039, 'And the sons of Eshek his brother were Ulam his firstborn, Jeush the second, and Eliphelet the third. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 8040, 'The sons of Ulam were mighty men of valor &ndash; archers. They had many sons and grandsons, one hundred and fifty in all. These were all sons of Benjamin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9001, 'So all Israel was recorded by genealogies, and indeed, they were inscribed in the book of the kings of Israel. But Judah was carried away captive to Babylon because of their unfaithfulness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9002, 'And the first inhabitants who dwelt in their possessions in their cities were Israelites, priests, Levites, and the Nethinim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9003, 'Now in Jerusalem the children of Judah dwelt, and some of the children of Benjamin, and of the children of Ephraim and Manasseh: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9004, 'Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, of the descendants of Perez, the son of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9005, 'Of the Shilonites: Asaiah the firstborn and his sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9006, 'Of the sons of Zerah: Jeuel, and their brethren &ndash; six hundred and ninety. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9007, 'Of the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of Hodaviah, the son of Hassenuah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9008, 'Ibneiah the son of Jeroham; Elah the son of Uzzi, the son of Michri; Meshullam the son of Shephatiah, the son of Reuel, the son of Ibnijah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9009, 'and their brethren, according to their generations &ndash; nine hundred and fifty-six. All these men were heads of a father&rsquo;s house in their fathers&rsquo; houses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9010, 'Of the priests: Jedaiah, Jehoiarib, and Jachin; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9011, 'Azariah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, the officer over the house of God; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9012, 'Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pashur, the son of Malchijah; Maasai the son of Adiel, the son of Jahzerah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Meshillemith, the son of Immer; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9013, 'and their brethren, heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses &ndash; one thousand seven hundred and sixty. They were very able men for the work of the service of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9014, 'Of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, of the sons of Merari; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9015, 'Bakbakkar, Heresh, Galal, and Mattaniah the son of Micah, the son of Zichri, the son of Asaph; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9016, 'Obadiah the son of Shemaiah, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun; and Berechiah the son of Asa, the son of Elkanah, who lived in the villages of the Netophathites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9017, 'And the gatekeepers were Shallum, Akkub, Talmon, Ahiman, and their brethren. Shallum was the chief. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9018, 'Until then they had been gatekeepers for the camps of the children of Levi at the King&rsquo;s Gate on the east. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9019, 'Shallum the son of Kore, the son of Ebiasaph, the son of Korah, and his brethren, from his father&rsquo;s house, the Korahites, were in charge of the work of the service, gatekeepers of the tabernacle. Their fathers had been keepers of the entrance to the camp of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9020, 'And Phinehas the son of Eleazar had been the officer over them in time past; the Lord was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9021, 'Zechariah the son of Meshelemiah was keeper of the door of the tabernacle of meeting. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9022, 'All those chosen as gatekeepers were two hundred and twelve. They were recorded by their genealogy, in their villages. David and Samuel the seer had appointed them to their trusted office. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9023, 'So they and their children were in charge of the gates of the house of the Lord, the house of the tabernacle, by assignment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9024, 'The gatekeepers were assigned to the four directions: the east, west, north, and south. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9025, 'And their brethren in their villages had to come with them from time to time for seven days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9026, 'For in this trusted office were four chief gatekeepers; they were Levites. And they had charge over the chambers and treasuries of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9027, 'And they lodged all around the house of God because they had the responsibility, and they were in charge of opening it every morning. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9028, 'Now some of them were in charge of the serving vessels, for they brought them in and took them out by count. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9029, 'Some of them were appointed over the furnishings and over all the implements of the sanctuary, and over the fine flour and the wine and the oil and the incense and the spices. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9030, 'And some of the sons of the priests made the ointment of the spices. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9031, 'Mattithiah of the Levites, the firstborn of Shallum the Korahite, had the trusted office over the things that were baked in the pans. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9032, 'And some of their brethren of the sons of the Kohathites were in charge of preparing the showbread for every Sabbath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9033, 'These are the singers, heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the Levites, who lodged in the chambers, and were free from other duties; for they were employed in that work day and night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9034, 'These heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the Levites were heads throughout their generations. They dwelt at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9035, 'Jeiel the father of Gibeon, whose wife&rsquo;s name was Maacah, dwelt at Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9036, 'His firstborn son was Abdon, then Zur, Kish, Baal, Ner, Nadab, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9037, 'Gedor, Ahio, Zechariah, and Mikloth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9038, 'And Mikloth begot Shimeam. They also dwelt alongside their relatives in Jerusalem, with their brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9039, 'Ner begot Kish, Kish begot Saul, and Saul begot Jonathan, Malchishua, Abinadab, and Esh-Baal. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9040, 'The son of Jonathan was Merib-Baal, and Merib-Baal begot Micah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9041, 'The sons of Micah were Pithon, Melech, Tahrea, and Ahaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9042, 'And Ahaz begot Jarah; Jarah begot Alemeth, Azmaveth, and Zimri; and Zimri begot Moza; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9043, 'Moza begot Binea, Rephaiah his son, Eleasah his son, and Azel his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 9044, 'And Azel had six sons whose names were these: Azrikam, Bocheru, Ishmael, Sheariah, Obadiah, and Hanan; these were the sons of Azel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10001, 'Now the Philistines fought against Israel; and the men of Israel fled from before the Philistines, and fell slain on Mount Gilboa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10002, 'Then the Philistines followed hard after Saul and his sons. And the Philistines killed Jonathan, Abinadab, and Malchishua, Saul&rsquo;s sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10003, 'The battle became fierce against Saul. The archers hit him, and he was wounded by the archers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10004, 'Then Saul said to his armorbearer, &ldquo;Draw your sword, and thrust me through with it, lest these uncircumcised men come and abuse me.&rdquo; But his armorbearer would not, for he was greatly afraid. Therefore Saul took a sword and fell on it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10005, 'And when his armorbearer saw that Saul was dead, he also fell on his sword and died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10006, 'So Saul and his three sons died, and all his house died together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10007, 'And when all the men of Israel who were in the valley saw that they had fled and that Saul and his sons were dead, they forsook their cities and fled; then the Philistines came and dwelt in them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10008, 'So it happened the next day, when the Philistines came to strip the slain, that they found Saul and his sons fallen on Mount Gilboa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10009, 'And they stripped him and took his head and his armor, and sent word throughout the land of the Philistines to proclaim the news in the temple of their idols and among the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10010, 'Then they put his armor in the temple of their gods, and fastened his head in the temple of Dagon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10011, 'And when all Jabesh Gilead heard all that the Philistines had done to Saul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10012, 'all the valiant men arose and took the body of Saul and the bodies of his sons; and they brought them to Jabesh, and buried their bones under the tamarisk tree at Jabesh, and fasted seven days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10013, 'So Saul died for his unfaithfulness which he had committed against the Lord, because he did not keep the word of the Lord, and also because he consulted a medium for guidance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 10014, 'But he did not inquire of the Lord; therefore He killed him, and turned the kingdom over to David the son of Jesse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11001, 'Then all Israel came together to David at Hebron, saying, &ldquo;Indeed we are your bone and your flesh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11002, 'Also, in time past, even when Saul was king, you were the one who led Israel out and brought them in; and the Lord your God said to you, &lsquo;You shall shepherd My people Israel, and be ruler over My people Israel.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11003, 'Therefore all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and David made a covenant with them at Hebron before the Lord. Then they anointed David king over Israel, according to the word of the Lord by Samuel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11004, 'And David and all Israel went to Jerusalem, which is Jebus, where the Jebusites were, the inhabitants of the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11005, 'Then the inhabitants of Jebus said to David, &ldquo;You shall not come in here!&rdquo; Nevertheless David took the stronghold of Zion (that is, the City of David). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11006, 'Now David said, &ldquo;Whoever attacks the Jebusites first shall be chief and captain.&rdquo; And Joab the son of Zeruiah went up first, and became chief. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11007, 'Then David dwelt in the stronghold; therefore they called it the City of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11008, 'And he built the city around it, from the Millo to the surrounding area. Joab repaired the rest of the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11009, 'Then David went on and became great, and the Lord of hosts was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11010, 'Now these were the heads of the mighty men whom David had, who strengthened themselves with him in his kingdom, with all Israel, to make him king, according to the word of the Lord concerning Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11011, 'And this is the number of the mighty men whom David had: Jashobeam the son of a Hachmonite, chief of the captains; he had lifted up his spear against three hundred, killed by him at one time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11012, 'After him was Eleazar the son of Dodo, the Ahohite, who was one of the three mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11013, 'He was with David at Pasdammim. Now there the Philistines were gathered for battle, and there was a piece of ground full of barley. And the people fled from the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11014, 'But they stationed themselves in the middle of that field, defended it, and killed the Philistines. So the Lord brought about a great victory. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11015, 'Now three of the thirty chief men went down to the rock to David, into the cave of Adullam; and the army of the Philistines encamped in the Valley of Rephaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11016, 'David was then in the stronghold, and the garrison of the Philistines was then in Bethlehem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11017, 'And David said with longing, &ldquo;Oh, that someone would give me a drink of water from the well of Bethlehem, which is by the gate!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11018, 'So the three broke through the camp of the Philistines, drew water from the well of Bethlehem that was by the gate, and took it and brought it to David. Nevertheless David would not drink it, but poured it out to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11019, 'And he said, &ldquo;Far be it from me, O my God, that I should do this! Shall I drink the blood of these men who have put their lives in jeopardy? For at the risk of their lives they brought it.&rdquo; Therefore he would not drink it. These things were done by the three mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11020, 'Abishai the brother of Joab was chief of another three. He had lifted up his spear against three hundred men, killed them, and won a name among these three. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11021, 'Of the three he was more honored than the other two men. Therefore he became their captain. However he did not attain to the first three. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11022, 'Benaiah was the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man from Kabzeel, who had done many deeds. He had killed two lion-like heroes of Moab. He also had gone down and killed a lion in the midst of a pit on a snowy day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11023, 'And he killed an Egyptian, a man of great height, five cubits tall. In the Egyptian&rsquo;s hand there was a spear like a weaver&rsquo;s beam; and he went down to him with a staff, wrested the spear out of the Egyptian&rsquo;s hand, and killed him with his own spear. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11024, 'These things Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did, and won a name among three mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11025, 'Indeed he was more honored than the thirty, but he did not attain to the first three. And David appointed him over his guard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11026, 'Also the mighty warriors were Asahel the brother of Joab, Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11027, 'Shammoth the Harorite, Helez the Pelonite,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11028, 'Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite, Abiezer the Anathothite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11029, 'Sibbechai the Hushathite, Ilai the Ahohite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11030, 'Maharai the Netophathite, Heled the son of Baanah the Netophathite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11031, 'Ithai the son of Ribai of Gibeah, of the sons of Benjamin, Benaiah the Pirathonite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11032, 'Hurai of the brooks of Gaash, Abiel the Arbathite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11033, 'Azmaveth the Baharumite, Eliahba the Shaalbonite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11034, 'the sons of Hashem the Gizonite, Jonathan the son of Shageh the Hararite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11035, 'Ahiam the son of Sacar the Hararite, Eliphal the son of Ur, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11036, 'Hepher the Mecherathite, Ahijah the Pelonite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11037, 'Hezro the Carmelite, Naarai the son of Ezbai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11038, 'Joel the brother of Nathan, Mibhar the son of Hagri, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11039, 'Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the Berothite (the armorbearer of Joab the son of Zeruiah), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11040, 'Ira the Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11041, 'Uriah the Hittite, Zabad the son of Ahlai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11042, 'Adina the son of Shiza the Reubenite (a chief of the Reubenites) and thirty with him, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11043, 'Hanan the son of Maachah, Joshaphat the Mithnite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11044, 'Uzzia the Ashterathite, Shama and Jeiel the sons of Hotham the Aroerite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11045, 'Jediael the son of Shimri, and Joha his brother, the Tizite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11046, 'Eliel the Mahavite, Jeribai and Joshaviah the sons of Elnaam, Ithmah the Moabite, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 11047, 'Eliel, Obed, and Jaasiel the Mezobaite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12001, 'Now these were the men who came to David at Ziklag while he was still a fugitive from Saul the son of Kish; and they were among the mighty men, helpers in the war, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12002, 'armed with bows, using both the right hand and the left in hurling stones and shooting arrows with the bow. They were of Benjamin, Saul&rsquo;s brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12003, 'The chief was Ahiezer, then Joash, the sons of Shemaah the Gibeathite; Jeziel and Pelet the sons of Azmaveth; Berachah, and Jehu the Anathothite; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12004, 'Ishmaiah the Gibeonite, a mighty man among the thirty, and over the thirty; Jeremiah, Jahaziel, Johanan, and Jozabad the Gederathite; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12005, 'Eluzai, Jerimoth, Bealiah, Shemariah, and Shephatiah the Haruphite; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12006, 'Elkanah, Jisshiah, Azarel, Joezer, and Jashobeam, the Korahites; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12007, 'and Joelah and Zebadiah the sons of Jeroham of Gedor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12008, 'Some Gadites joined David at the stronghold in the wilderness, mighty men of valor, men trained for battle, who could handle shield and spear, whose faces were like the faces of lions, and were as swift as gazelles on the mountains: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12009, 'Ezer the first, Obadiah the second, Eliab the third, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12010, 'Mishmannah the fourth, Jeremiah the fifth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12011, 'Attai the sixth, Eliel the seventh, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12012, 'Johanan the eighth, Elzabad the ninth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12013, 'Jeremiah the tenth, and Machbanai the eleventh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12014, 'These were from the sons of Gad, captains of the army; the least was over a hundred, and the greatest was over a thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12015, 'These are the ones who crossed the Jordan in the first month, when it had overflowed all its banks; and they put to flight all those in the valleys, to the east and to the west. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12016, 'Then some of the sons of Benjamin and Judah came to David at the stronghold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12017, 'And David went out to meet them, and answered and said to them, &ldquo;If you have come peaceably to me to help me, my heart will be united with you; but if to betray me to my enemies, since there is no wrong in my hands, may the God of our fathers look and bring judgment.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12018, 'Then the Spirit came upon Amasai, chief of the captains, and he said: &ldquo;We are yours, O David; We are on your side, O son of Jesse! Peace, peace to you, And peace to your helpers! For your God helps you.&rdquo; So David received them, and made them captains of the troop. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12019, 'And some from Manasseh defected to David when he was going with the Philistines to battle against Saul; but they did not help them, for the lords of the Philistines sent him away by agreement, saying, &ldquo;He may defect to his master Saul and endanger our heads.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12020, 'When he went to Ziklag, those of Manasseh who defected to him were Adnah, Jozabad, Jediael, Michael, Jozabad, Elihu, and Zillethai, captains of the thousands who were from Manasseh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12021, 'And they helped David against the bands of raiders, for they were all mighty men of valor, and they were captains in the army. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12022, 'For at that time they came to David day by day to help him, until it was a great army, like the army of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12023, 'Now these were the numbers of the divisions that were equipped for war, and came to David at Hebron to turn over the kingdom of Saul to him, according to the word of the Lord: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12024, 'of the sons of Judah bearing shield and spear, six thousand eight hundred armed for war; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12025, 'of the sons of Simeon, mighty men of valor fit for war, seven thousand one hundred; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12026, 'of the sons of Levi four thousand six hundred; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12027, 'Jehoiada, the leader of the Aaronites, and with him three thousand seven hundred; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12028, 'Zadok, a young man, a valiant warrior, and from his father&rsquo;s house twenty-two captains; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12029, 'of the sons of Benjamin, relatives of Saul, three thousand (until then the greatest part of them had remained loyal to the house of Saul); ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12030, 'of the sons of Ephraim twenty thousand eight hundred, mighty men of valor, famous men throughout their father&rsquo;s house; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12031, 'of the half-tribe of Manasseh eighteen thousand, who were designated by name to come and make David king; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12032, 'of the sons of Issachar who had understanding of the times, to know what Israel ought to do, their chiefs were two hundred; and all their brethren were at their command; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12033, 'of Zebulun there were fifty thousand who went out to battle, expert in war with all weapons of war, stouthearted men who could keep ranks; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12034, 'of Naphtali one thousand captains, and with them thirty-seven thousand with shield and spear; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12035, 'of the Danites who could keep battle formation, twenty-eight thousand six hundred; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12036, 'of Asher, those who could go out to war, able to keep battle formation, forty thousand; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12037, 'of the Reubenites and the Gadites and the half-tribe of Manasseh, from the other side of the Jordan, one hundred and twenty thousand armed for battle with every kind of weapon of war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12038, 'All these men of war, who could keep ranks, came to Hebron with a loyal heart, to make David king over all Israel; and all the rest of Israel were of one mind to make David king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12039, 'And they were there with David three days, eating and drinking, for their brethren had prepared for them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 12040, 'Moreover those who were near to them, from as far away as Issachar and Zebulun and Naphtali, were bringing food on donkeys and camels, on mules and oxen &ndash; provisions of flour and cakes of figs and cakes of raisins, wine and oil and oxen and sheep abundantly, for there was joy in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13001, 'Then David consulted with the captains of thousands and hundreds, and with every leader. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13002, 'And David said to all the assembly of Israel, &ldquo;If it seems good to you, and if it is of the Lord our God, let us send out to our brethren everywhere who are left in all the land of Israel, and with them to the priests and Levites who are in their cities and their common-lands, that they may gather together to us; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13003, 'and let us bring the ark of our God back to us, for we have not inquired at it since the days of Saul.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13004, 'Then all the assembly said that they would do so, for the thing was right in the eyes of all the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13005, 'So David gathered all Israel together, from Shihor in Egypt to as far as the entrance of Hamath, to bring the ark of God from Kirjath Jearim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13006, 'And David and all Israel went up to Baalah, to Kirjath Jearim, which belonged to Judah, to bring up from there the ark of God the Lord, who dwells between the cherubim, where His name is proclaimed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13007, 'So they carried the ark of God on a new cart from the house of Abinadab, and Uzza and Ahio drove the cart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13008, 'Then David and all Israel played music before God with all their might, with singing, on harps, on stringed instruments, on tambourines, on cymbals, and with trumpets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13009, 'And when they came to Chidon&rsquo;s threshing floor, Uzza put out his hand to hold the ark, for the oxen stumbled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13010, 'Then the anger of the Lord was aroused against Uzza, and He struck him because he put his hand to the ark; and he died there before God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13011, 'And David became angry because of the Lord&rsquo;s outbreak against Uzza; therefore that place is called Perez Uzza to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13012, 'David was afraid of God that day, saying, &ldquo;How can I bring the ark of God to me?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13013, 'So David would not move the ark with him into the City of David, but took it aside into the house of Obed-Edom the Gittite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 13014, 'The ark of God remained with the family of Obed-Edom in his house three months. And the Lord blessed the house of Obed-Edom and all that he had. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14001, 'Now Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David, and cedar trees, with masons and carpenters, to build him a house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14002, 'So David knew that the Lord had established him as king over Israel, for his kingdom was highly exalted for the sake of His people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14003, 'Then David took more wives in Jerusalem, and David begot more sons and daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14004, 'And these are the names of his children whom he had in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14005, 'Ibhar, Elishua, Elpelet,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14006, 'Nogah, Nepheg, Japhia, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14007, 'Elishama, Beeliada, and Eliphelet. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14008, 'Now when the Philistines heard that David had been anointed king over all Israel, all the Philistines went up to search for David. And David heard of it and went out against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14009, 'Then the Philistines went and made a raid on the Valley of Rephaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14010, 'And David inquired of God, saying, &ldquo;Shall I go up against the Philistines? Will You deliver them into my hand?&rdquo; And the Lord said to him, &ldquo;Go up, for I will deliver them into your hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14011, 'So they went up to Baal Perazim, and David defeated them there. Then David said, &ldquo;God has broken through my enemies by my hand like a breakthrough of water.&rdquo; Therefore they called the name of that place Baal Perazim.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14012, 'And when they left their gods there, David gave a commandment, and they were burned with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14013, 'Then the Philistines once again made a raid on the valley. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14014, 'Therefore David inquired again of God, and God said to him, &ldquo;You shall not go up after them; circle around them, and come upon them in front of the mulberry trees. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14015, 'And it shall be, when you hear a sound of marching in the tops of the mulberry trees, then you shall go out to battle, for God has gone out before you to strike the camp of the Philistines.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14016, 'So David did as God commanded him, and they drove back the army of the Philistines from Gibeon as far as Gezer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 14017, 'Then the fame of David went out into all lands, and the Lord brought the fear of him upon all nations. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15001, 'David built houses for himself in the City of David; and he prepared a place for the ark of God, and pitched a tent for it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15002, 'Then David said, &ldquo;No one may carry the ark of God but the Levites, for the Lord has chosen them to carry the ark of God and to minister before Him forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15003, 'And David gathered all Israel together at Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the Lord to its place, which he had prepared for it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15004, 'Then David assembled the children of Aaron and the Levites: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15005, 'of the sons of Kohath, Uriel the chief, and one hundred and twenty of his brethren; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15006, 'of the sons of Merari, Asaiah the chief, and two hundred and twenty of his brethren; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15007, 'of the sons of Gershom, Joel the chief, and one hundred and thirty of his brethren; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15008, 'of the sons of Elizaphan, Shemaiah the chief, and two hundred of his brethren; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15009, 'of the sons of Hebron, Eliel the chief, and eighty of his brethren; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15010, 'of the sons of Uzziel, Amminadab the chief, and one hundred and twelve of his brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15011, 'And David called for Zadok and Abiathar the priests, and for the Levites: for Uriel, Asaiah, Joel, Shemaiah, Eliel, and Amminadab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15012, 'He said to them, &ldquo;You are the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the Levites; sanctify yourselves, you and your brethren, that you may bring up the ark of the Lord God of Israel to the place I have prepared for it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15013, 'For because you did not do it the first time, the Lord our God broke out against us, because we did not consult Him about the proper order.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15014, 'So the priests and the Levites sanctified themselves to bring up the ark of the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15015, 'And the children of the Levites bore the ark of God on their shoulders, by its poles, as Moses had commanded according to the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15016, 'Then David spoke to the leaders of the Levites to appoint their brethren to be the singers accompanied by instruments of music, stringed instruments, harps, and cymbals, by raising the voice with resounding joy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15017, 'So the Levites appointed Heman the son of Joel; and of his brethren, Asaph the son of Berechiah; and of their brethren, the sons of Merari, Ethan the son of Kushaiah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15018, 'and with them their brethren of the second rank: Zechariah, Ben, Jaaziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattithiah, Elipheleh, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom, and Jeiel, the gatekeepers; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15019, 'the singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, were to sound the cymbals of bronze; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15020, 'Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and Benaiah, with strings according to Alamoth; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15021, 'Mattithiah, Elipheleh, Mikneiah, Obed-Edom, Jeiel, and Azaziah, to direct with harps on the Sheminith; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15022, 'Chenaniah, leader of the Levites, was instructor in charge of the music, because he was skillful; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15023, 'Berechiah and Elkanah were doorkeepers for the ark; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15024, 'Shebaniah, Joshaphat, Nethanel, Amasai, Zechariah, Benaiah, and Eliezer, the priests, were to blow the trumpets before the ark of God; and Obed-Edom and Jehiah, doorkeepers for the ark. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15025, 'So David, the elders of Israel, and the captains over thousands went to bring up the ark of the covenant of the Lord from the house of Obed-Edom with joy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15026, 'And so it was, when God helped the Levites who bore the ark of the covenant of the Lord, that they offered seven bulls and seven rams. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15027, 'David was clothed with a robe of fine linen, as were all the Levites who bore the ark, the singers, and Chenaniah the music master with the singers. David also wore a linen ephod. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15028, 'Thus all Israel brought up the ark of the covenant of the Lord with shouting and with the sound of the horn, with trumpets and with cymbals, making music with stringed instruments and harps. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 15029, 'And it happened, as the ark of the covenant of the Lord came to the City of David, that Michal, Saul&rsquo;s daughter, looked through a window and saw King David whirling and playing music; and she despised him in her heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16001, 'So they brought the ark of God, and set it in the midst of the tabernacle that David had erected for it. Then they offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16002, 'And when David had finished offering the burnt offerings and the peace offerings, he blessed the people in the name of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16003, 'Then he distributed to everyone of Israel, both man and woman, to everyone a loaf of bread, a piece of meat, and a cake of raisins. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16004, 'And he appointed some of the Levites to minister before the ark of the Lord, to commemorate, to thank, and to praise the Lord God of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16005, 'Asaph the chief, and next to him Zechariah, then Jeiel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Mattithiah, Eliab, Benaiah, and Obed-Edom: Jeiel with stringed instruments and harps, but Asaph made music with cymbals; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16006, 'Benaiah and Jahaziel the priests regularly blew the trumpets before the ark of the covenant of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16007, 'On that day David first delivered this psalm into the hand of Asaph and his brethren, to thank the Lord: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16008, 'Oh, give thanks to the Lord! Call upon His name; Make known His deeds among the peoples! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16009, 'Sing to Him, sing psalms to Him; Talk of all His wondrous works! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16010, 'Glory in His holy name; Let the hearts of those rejoice who seek the Lord! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16011, 'Seek the Lord and His strength; Seek His face evermore! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16012, 'Remember His marvelous works which He has done, His wonders, and the judgments of His mouth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16013, 'O seed of Israel His servant, You children of Jacob, His chosen ones! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16014, 'He is the Lord our God; His judgments are in all the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16015, 'Remember His covenant forever, The word which He commanded, for a thousand generations, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16016, 'The covenant which He made with Abraham, And His oath to Isaac, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16017, 'And confirmed it to Jacob for a statute, To Israel for an everlasting covenant, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16018, 'Saying, &ldquo;To you I will give the land of Canaan As the allotment of your inheritance,&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16019, 'When you were few in number, Indeed very few, and strangers in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16020, 'When they went from one nation to another, And from one kingdom to another people, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16021, 'He permitted no man to do them wrong; Yes, He rebuked kings for their sakes, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16022, 'Saying, &ldquo;Do not touch My anointed ones, And do My prophets no harm.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16023, 'Sing to the Lord, all the earth; Proclaim the good news of His salvation from day to day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16024, 'Declare His glory among the nations, His wonders among all peoples. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16025, 'For the Lord is great and greatly to be praised; He is also to be feared above all gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16026, 'For all the gods of the peoples are idols, But the Lord made the heavens. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16027, 'Honor and majesty are before Him; Strength and gladness are in His place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16028, 'Give to the Lord, O families of the peoples, Give to the Lord glory and strength. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16029, 'Give to the Lord the glory due His name; Bring an offering, and come before Him. Oh, worship the Lord in the beauty of holiness! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16030, 'Tremble before Him, all the earth. The world also is firmly established, It shall not be moved. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16031, 'Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad; And let them say among the nations, &ldquo;The Lord reigns.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16032, 'Let the sea roar, and all its fullness; Let the field rejoice, and all that is in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16033, 'Then the trees of the woods shall rejoice before the Lord, For He is coming to judge the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16034, 'Oh, give thanks to the Lord, for He is good! For His mercy endures forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16035, 'And say, &ldquo;Save us, O God of our salvation; Gather us together, and deliver us from the Gentiles, To give thanks to Your holy name, To triumph in Your praise.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16036, 'Blessed be the Lord God of Israel From everlasting to everlasting! And all the people said, &ldquo;Amen!&rdquo; and praised the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16037, 'So he left Asaph and his brothers there before the ark of the covenant of the Lord to minister before the ark regularly, as every day&rsquo;s work required; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16038, 'and Obed-Edom with his sixty-eight brethren, including Obed-Edom the son of Jeduthun, and Hosah, to be gatekeepers; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16039, 'and Zadok the priest and his brethren the priests, before the tabernacle of the Lord at the high place that was at Gibeon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16040, 'to offer burnt offerings to the Lord on the altar of burnt offering regularly morning and evening, and to do according to all that is written in the Law of the Lord which He commanded Israel; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16041, 'and with them Heman and Jeduthun and the rest who were chosen, who were designated by name, to give thanks to the Lord, because His mercy endures forever; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16042, 'and with them Heman and Jeduthun, to sound aloud with trumpets and cymbals and the musical instruments of God. Now the sons of Jeduthun were gatekeepers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 16043, 'Then all the people departed, every man to his house; and David returned to bless his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17001, 'Now it came to pass, when David was dwelling in his house, that David said to Nathan the prophet, &ldquo;See now, I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of the covenant of the Lord is under tent curtains.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17002, 'Then Nathan said to David, &ldquo;Do all that is in your heart, for God is with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17003, 'But it happened that night that the word of God came to Nathan, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17004, 'Go and tell My servant David, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: You shall not build Me a house to dwell in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17005, 'For I have not dwelt in a house since the time that I brought up Israel, even to this day, but have gone from tent to tent, and from one tabernacle to another. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17006, 'Wherever I have moved about with all Israel, have I ever spoken a word to any of the judges of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd My people, saying, &lsquo;Why have you not built Me a house of cedar?&rsquo; &ldquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17007, 'Now therefore, thus shall you say to My servant David, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord of hosts: &ldquo;I took you from the sheepfold, from following the sheep, to be ruler over My people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17008, 'And I have been with you wherever you have gone, and have cut off all your enemies from before you, and have made you a name like the name of the great men who are on the earth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17009, 'Moreover I will appoint a place for My people Israel, and will plant them, that they may dwell in a place of their own and move no more; nor shall the sons of wickedness oppress them anymore, as previously, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17010, 'since the time that I commanded judges to be over My people Israel. Also I will subdue all your enemies. Furthermore I tell you that the Lord will build you a house.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17011, 'And it shall be, when your days are fulfilled, when you must go to be with your fathers, that I will set up your seed after you, who will be of your sons; and I will establish his kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17012, 'He shall build Me a house, and I will establish his throne forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17013, 'I will be his Father, and he shall be My son; and I will not take My mercy away from him, as I took it from him who was before you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17014, 'And I will establish him in My house and in My kingdom forever; and his throne shall be established forever.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17015, 'According to all these words and according to all this vision, so Nathan spoke to David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17016, 'Then King David went in and sat before the Lord; and he said: &ldquo;Who am I, O Lord God? And what is my house, that You have brought me this far? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17017, 'And yet this was a small thing in Your sight, O God; and You have also spoken of Your servant&rsquo;s house for a great while to come, and have regarded me according to the rank of a man of high degree, O Lord God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17018, 'What more can David say to You for the honor of Your servant? For You know Your servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17019, 'O Lord, for Your servant&rsquo;s sake, and according to Your own heart, You have done all this greatness, in making known all these great things. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17020, 'O Lord, there is none like You, nor is there any God besides You, according to all that we have heard with our ears. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17021, 'And who is like Your people Israel, the one nation on the earth whom God went to redeem for Himself as a people &ndash; to make for Yourself a name by great and awesome deeds, by driving out nations from before Your people whom You redeemed from Egypt? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17022, 'For You have made Your people Israel Your very own people forever; and You, Lord, have become their God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17023, 'And now, O Lord, the word which You have spoken concerning Your servant and concerning his house, let it be established forever, and do as You have said. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17024, 'So let it be established, that Your name may be magnified forever, saying, &lsquo;The Lord of hosts, the God of Israel, is Israel&rsquo;s God.&rsquo; And let the house of Your servant David be established before You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17025, 'For You, O my God, have revealed to Your servant that You will build him a house. Therefore Your servant has found it in his heart to pray before You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17026, 'And now, Lord, You are God, and have promised this goodness to Your servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 17027, 'Now You have been pleased to bless the house of Your servant, that it may continue before You forever; for You have blessed it, O Lord, and it shall be blessed forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18001, 'After this it came to pass that David attacked the Philistines, subdued them, and took Gath and its towns from the hand of the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18002, 'Then he defeated Moab, and the Moabites became David&rsquo;s servants, and brought tribute. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18003, 'And David defeated Hadadezer king of Zobah as far as Hamath, as he went to establish his power by the River Euphrates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18004, 'David took from him one thousand chariots, seven thousand horsemen, and twenty thousand foot soldiers. And David also hamstrung all the chariot horses, except that he spared enough of them for one hundred chariots. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18005, 'When the Syrians of Damascus came to help Hadadezer king of Zobah, David killed twenty-two thousand of the Syrians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18006, 'Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus; and the Syrians became David&rsquo;s servants, and brought tribute. So the Lord preserved David wherever he went. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18007, 'And David took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18008, 'Also from Tibhath and from Chun, cities of Hadadezer, David brought a large amount of bronze, with which Solomon made the bronze Sea, the pillars, and the articles of bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18009, 'Now when Tou king of Hamath heard that David had defeated all the army of Hadadezer king of Zobah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18010, 'he sent Hadoram his son to King David, to greet him and bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him (for Hadadezer had been at war with Tou); and Hadoram brought with him all kinds of articles of gold, silver, and bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18011, 'King David also dedicated these to the Lord, along with the silver and gold that he had brought from all these nations &ndash; from Edom, from Moab, from the people of Ammon, from the Philistines, and from Amalek. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18012, 'Moreover Abishai the son of Zeruiah killed eighteen thousand Edomites in the Valley of Salt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18013, 'He also put garrisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became David&rsquo;s servants. And the Lord preserved David wherever he went. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18014, 'So David reigned over all Israel, and administered judgment and justice to all his people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18015, 'Joab the son of Zeruiah was over the army; Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was recorder; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18016, 'Zadok the son of Ahitub and Abimelech the son of Abiathar were the priests; Shavsha was the scribe; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 18017, 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites; and David&rsquo;s sons were chief ministers at the king&rsquo;s side. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19001, 'It happened after this that Nahash the king of the people of Ammon died, and his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19002, 'Then David said, &ldquo;I will show kindness to Hanun the son of Nahash, because his father showed kindness to me.&rdquo; So David sent messengers to comfort him concerning his father. And David&rsquo;s servants came to Hanun in the land of the people of Ammon to comfort him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19003, 'And the princes of the people of Ammon said to Hanun, &ldquo;Do you think that David really honors your father because he has sent comforters to you? Did his servants not come to you to search and to overthrow and to spy out the land?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19004, 'Therefore Hanun took David&rsquo;s servants, shaved them, and cut off their garments in the middle, at their buttocks, and sent them away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19005, 'Then some went and told David about the men; and he sent to meet them, because the men were greatly ashamed. And the king said, &ldquo;Wait at Jericho until your beards have grown, and then return.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19006, 'When the people of Ammon saw that they had made themselves repulsive to David, Hanun and the people of Ammon sent a thousand talents of silver to hire for themselves chariots and horsemen from Mesopotamia, from Syrian Maachah, and from Zobah.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19007, 'So they hired for themselves thirty-two thousand chariots, with the king of Maachah and his people, who came and encamped before Medeba. Also the people of Ammon gathered together from their cities, and came to battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19008, 'Now when David heard of it, he sent Joab and all the army of the mighty men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19009, 'Then the people of Ammon came out and put themselves in battle array before the gate of the city, and the kings who had come were by themselves in the field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19010, 'When Joab saw that the battle line was against him before and behind, he chose some of Israel&rsquo;s best and put them in battle array against the Syrians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19011, 'And the rest of the people he put under the command of Abishai his brother, and they set themselves in battle array against the people of Ammon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19012, 'Then he said, &ldquo;If the Syrians are too strong for me, then you shall help me; but if the people of Ammon are too strong for you, then I will help you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19013, 'Be of good courage, and let us be strong for our people and for the cities of our God. And may the Lord do what is good in His sight.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19014, 'So Joab and the people who were with him drew near for the battle against the Syrians, and they fled before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19015, 'When the people of Ammon saw that the Syrians were fleeing, they also fled before Abishai his brother, and entered the city. So Joab went to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19016, 'Now when the Syrians saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they sent messengers and brought the Syrians who were beyond the River, and Shophach the commander of Hadadezer&rsquo;s army went before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19017, 'When it was told David, he gathered all Israel, crossed over the Jordan and came upon them, and set up in battle array against them. So when David had set up in battle array against the Syrians, they fought with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19018, 'Then the Syrians fled before Israel; and David killed seven thousand charioteers and forty thousand foot soldiers of the Syrians, and killed Shophach the commander of the army. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 19019, 'And when the servants of Hadadezer saw that they were defeated by Israel, they made peace with David and became his servants. So the Syrians were not willing to help the people of Ammon anymore. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20001, 'It happened in the spring of the year, at the time kings go out to battle, that Joab led out the armed forces and ravaged the country of the people of Ammon, and came and besieged Rabbah. But David stayed at Jerusalem. And Joab defeated Rabbah and overthrew it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20002, 'Then David took their king&rsquo;s crown from his head, and found it to weigh a talent of gold, and there were precious stones in it. And it was set on David&rsquo;s head. Also he brought out the spoil of the city in great abundance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20003, 'And he brought out the people who were in it, and put them to work with saws, with iron picks, and with axes. So David did to all the cities of the people of Ammon. Then David and all the people returned to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20004, 'Now it happened afterward that war broke out at Gezer with the Philistines, at which time Sibbechai the Hushathite killed Sippai, who was one of the sons of the giant. And they were subdued. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20005, 'Again there was war with the Philistines, and Elhanan the son of Jair killed Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver&rsquo;s beam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20006, 'Yet again there was war at Gath, where there was a man of great stature, with twenty-four fingers and toes, six on each hand and six on each foot; and he also was born to the giant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20007, 'So when he defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimea, David&rsquo;s brother, killed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 20008, 'These were born to the giant in Gath, and they fell by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21001, 'Now Satan stood up against Israel, and moved David to number Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21002, 'So David said to Joab and to the leaders of the people, &ldquo;Go, number Israel from Beersheba to Dan, and bring the number of them to me that I may know it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21003, 'And Joab answered, &ldquo;May the Lord make His people a hundred times more than they are. But, my lord the king, are they not all my lord&rsquo;s servants? Why then does my lord require this thing? Why should he be a cause of guilt in Israel?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21004, 'Nevertheless the king&rsquo;s word prevailed against Joab. Therefore Joab departed and went throughout all Israel and came to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21005, 'Then Joab gave the sum of the number of the people to David. All Israel had one million one hundred thousand men who drew the sword, and Judah had four hundred and seventy thousand men who drew the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21006, 'But he did not count Levi and Benjamin among them, for the king&rsquo;s word was abominable to Joab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21007, 'And God was displeased with this thing; therefore He struck Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21008, 'So David said to God, &ldquo;I have sinned greatly, because I have done this thing; but now, I pray, take away the iniquity of Your servant, for I have done very foolishly.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21009, 'And the Lord spoke to Gad, David&rsquo;s seer, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21010, 'Go and tell David, saying, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord: I offer you three things; choose one of them for yourself, that I may do it to you. &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21011, 'So Gad came to David and said to him, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Choose for yourself, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21012, 'either three years of famine, or three months to be defeated by your foes with the sword of your enemies overtaking you, or else for three days the sword of the Lord &ndash; the plague in the land, with the angel of the Lord destroying throughout all the territory of Israel.&rsquo; Now consider what answer I should take back to Him who sent me.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21013, 'And David said to Gad, &ldquo;I am in great distress. Please let me fall into the hand of the Lord, for His mercies are very great; but do not let me fall into the hand of man.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21014, 'So the Lord sent a plague upon Israel, and seventy thousand men of Israel fell. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21015, 'And God sent an angel to Jerusalem to destroy it. As he was destroying, the Lord looked and relented of the disaster, and said to the angel who was destroying, &ldquo;It is enough; now restrain your hand.&rdquo; And the angel of the Lord stood by the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21016, 'Then David lifted his eyes and saw the angel of the Lord standing between earth and heaven, having in his hand a drawn sword stretched out over Jerusalem. So David and the elders, clothed in sackcloth, fell on their faces. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21017, 'And David said to God, &ldquo;Was it not I who commanded the people to be numbered? I am the one who has sinned and done evil indeed; but these sheep, what have they done? Let Your hand, I pray, O Lord my God, be against me and my father&rsquo;s house, but not against Your people that they should be plagued.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21018, 'Therefore, the angel of the Lord commanded Gad to say to David that David should go and erect an altar to the Lord on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21019, 'So David went up at the word of Gad, which he had spoken in the name of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21020, 'Now Ornan turned and saw the angel; and his four sons who were with him hid themselves, but Ornan continued threshing wheat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21021, 'Then David came to Ornan, and Ornan looked and saw David. And he went out from the threshing floor, and bowed before David with his face to the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21022, 'Then David said to Ornan, &ldquo;Grant me the place of this threshing floor, that I may build an altar on it to the Lord. You shall grant it to me at the full price, that the plague may be withdrawn from the people.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21023, 'And Ornan said to David, &ldquo;Take it to yourself, and let my lord the king do what is good in his eyes. Look, I also give you the oxen for burnt offerings, the threshing implements for wood, and the wheat for the grain offering; I give it all.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21024, 'Then King David said to Ornan, &ldquo;No, but I will surely buy it for the full price, for I will not take what is yours for the Lord, nor offer burnt offerings with that which costs me nothing.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21025, 'So David gave Ornan six hundred shekels of gold by weight for the place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21026, 'And David built there an altar to the Lord, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings, and called on the Lord; and He answered him from heaven by fire on the altar of burnt offering. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21027, 'So the Lord commanded the angel, and he returned his sword to its sheath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21028, 'At that time, when David saw that the Lord had answered him on the threshing floor of Ornan the Jebusite, he sacrificed there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21029, 'For the tabernacle of the Lord and the altar of the burnt offering, which Moses had made in the wilderness, were at that time at the high place in Gibeon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 21030, 'But David could not go before it to inquire of God, for he was afraid of the sword of the angel of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22001, 'Then David said, &ldquo;This is the house of the Lord God, and this is the altar of burnt offering for Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22002, 'So David commanded to gather the aliens who were in the land of Israel; and he appointed masons to cut hewn stones to build the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22003, 'And David prepared iron in abundance for the nails of the doors of the gates and for the joints, and bronze in abundance beyond measure, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22004, 'and cedar trees in abundance; for the Sidonians and those from Tyre brought much cedar wood to David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22005, 'Now David said, &ldquo;Solomon my son is young and inexperienced, and the house to be built for the Lord must be exceedingly magnificent, famous and glorious throughout all countries. I will now make preparation for it.&rdquo; So David made abundant preparations before his death. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22006, 'Then he called for his son Solomon, and charged him to build a house for the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22007, 'And David said to Solomon: &ldquo;My son, as for me, it was in my mind to build a house to the name of the Lord my God; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22008, 'but the word of the Lord came to me, saying, &lsquo;You have shed much blood and have made great wars; you shall not build a house for My name, because you have shed much blood on the earth in My sight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22009, 'Behold, a son shall be born to you, who shall be a man of rest; and I will give him rest from all his enemies all around. His name shall be Solomon, for I will give peace and quietness to Israel in his days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22010, 'He shall build a house for My name, and he shall be My son, and I will be his Father; and I will establish the throne of his kingdom over Israel forever.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22011, 'Now, my son, may the Lord be with you; and may you prosper, and build the house of the Lord your God, as He has said to you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22012, 'Only may the Lord give you wisdom and understanding, and give you charge concerning Israel, that you may keep the law of the Lord your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22013, 'Then you will prosper, if you take care to fulfill the statutes and judgments with which the Lord charged Moses concerning Israel. Be strong and of good courage; do not fear nor be dismayed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22014, 'Indeed I have taken much trouble to prepare for the house of the Lord one hundred thousand talents of gold and one million talents of silver, and bronze and iron beyond measure, for it is so abundant. I have prepared timber and stone also, and you may add to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22015, 'Moreover there are workmen with you in abundance: woodsmen and stonecutters, and all types of skillful men for every kind of work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22016, 'Of gold and silver and bronze and iron there is no limit. Arise and begin working, and the Lord be with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22017, 'David also commanded all the leaders of Israel to help Solomon his son, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22018, 'Is not the Lord your God with you? And has He not given you rest on every side? For He has given the inhabitants of the land into my hand, and the land is subdued before the Lord and before His people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 22019, 'Now set your heart and your soul to seek the Lord your God. Therefore arise and build the sanctuary of the Lord God, to bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord and the holy articles of God into the house that is to be built for the name of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23001, 'So when David was old and full of days, he made his son Solomon king over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23002, 'And he gathered together all the leaders of Israel, with the priests and the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23003, 'Now the Levites were numbered from the age of thirty years and above; and the number of individual males was thirty-eight thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23004, 'Of these, twenty-four thousand were to look after the work of the house of the Lord, six thousand were officers and judges, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23005, 'four thousand were gatekeepers, and four thousand praised the Lord with musical instruments, &ldquo;which I made,&rdquo; said David, &ldquo;for giving praise.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23006, 'Also David separated them into divisions among the sons of Levi: Gershon, Kohath, and Merari. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23007, 'Of the Gershonites: Laadan and Shimei. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23008, 'The sons of Laadan: the first Jehiel, then Zetham and Joel &ndash; three in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23009, 'The sons of Shimei: Shelomith, Haziel, and Haran &ndash; three in all. These were the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of Laadan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23010, 'And the sons of Shimei: Jahath, Zina, Jeush, and Beriah. These were the four sons of Shimei. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23011, 'Jahath was the first and Zizah the second. But Jeush and Beriah did not have many sons; therefore they were assigned as one father&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23012, 'The sons of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel &ndash; four in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23013, 'The sons of Amram: Aaron and Moses; and Aaron was set apart, he and his sons forever, that he should sanctify the most holy things, to burn incense before the Lord, to minister to Him, and to give the blessing in His name forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23014, 'Now the sons of Moses the man of God were reckoned to the tribe of Levi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23015, 'The sons of Moses were Gershon and Eliezer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23016, 'Of the sons of Gershon, Shebuel was the first. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23017, 'Of the descendants of Eliezer, Rehabiah was the first. And Eliezer had no other sons, but the sons of Rehabiah were very many. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23018, 'Of the sons of Izhar, Shelomith was the first. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23019, 'Of the sons of Hebron, Jeriah was the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23020, 'Of the sons of Uzziel, Michah was the first and Jesshiah the second. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23021, 'The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi. The sons of Mahli were Eleazar and Kish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23022, 'And Eleazar died, and had no sons, but only daughters; and their brethren, the sons of Kish, took them as wives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23023, 'The sons of Mushi were Mahli, Eder, and Jeremoth &ndash; three in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23024, 'These were the sons of Levi by their fathers&rsquo; houses &ndash; the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses as they were counted individually by the number of their names, who did the work for the service of the house of the Lord, from the age of twenty years and above. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23025, 'For David said, &ldquo;The Lord God of Israel has given rest to His people, that they may dwell in Jerusalem forever&rdquo;; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23026, 'and also to the Levites, &ldquo;They shall no longer carry the tabernacle, or any of the articles for its service.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23027, 'For by the last words of David the Levites were numbered from twenty years old and above; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23028, 'because their duty was to help the sons of Aaron in the service of the house of the Lord, in the courts and in the chambers, in the purifying of all holy things and the work of the service of the house of God, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23029, 'both with the showbread and the fine flour for the grain offering, with the unleavened cakes and what is baked in the pan, with what is mixed and with all kinds of measures and sizes; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23030, 'to stand every morning to thank and praise the Lord, and likewise at evening; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23031, 'and at every presentation of a burnt offering to the Lord on the Sabbaths and on the New Moons and on the set feasts, by number according to the ordinance governing them, regularly before the Lord; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 23032, 'and that they should attend to the needs of the tabernacle of meeting, the needs of the holy place, and the needs of the sons of Aaron their brethren in the work of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24001, 'Now these are the divisions of the sons of Aaron. The sons of Aaron were Nadab, Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24002, 'And Nadab and Abihu died before their father, and had no children; therefore Eleazar and Ithamar ministered as priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24003, 'Then David with Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, divided them according to the schedule of their service. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24004, 'There were more leaders found of the sons of Eleazar than of the sons of Ithamar, and thus they were divided. Among the sons of Eleazar were sixteen heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, and eight heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses among the sons of Ithamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24005, 'Thus they were divided by lot, one group as another, for there were officials of the sanctuary and officials of the house of God, from the sons of Eleazar and from the sons of Ithamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24006, 'And the scribe, Shemaiah the son of Nethanel, one of the Levites, wrote them down before the king, the leaders, Zadok the priest, Ahimelech the son of Abiathar, and the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the priests and Levites, one father&rsquo;s house taken for Eleazar and one for Ithamar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24007, 'Now the first lot fell to Jehoiarib, the second to Jedaiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24008, 'the third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24009, 'the fifth to Malchijah, the sixth to Mijamin, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24010, 'the seventh to Hakkoz, the eighth to Abijah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24011, 'the ninth to Jeshua, the tenth to Shecaniah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24012, 'the eleventh to Eliashib, the twelfth to Jakim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24013, 'the thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Jeshebeab, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24014, 'the fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24015, 'the seventeenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Happizzez, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24016, 'the nineteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Jehezekel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24017, 'the twenty-first to Jachin, the twenty-second to Gamul, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24018, 'the twenty-third to Delaiah, the twenty-fourth to Maaziah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24019, 'This was the schedule of their service for coming into the house of the Lord according to their ordinance by the hand of Aaron their father, as the Lord God of Israel had commanded him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24020, 'And the rest of the sons of Levi: of the sons of Amram, Shubael; of the sons of Shubael, Jehdeiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24021, 'Concerning Rehabiah, of the sons of Rehabiah, the first was Isshiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24022, 'Of the Izharites, Shelomoth; of the sons of Shelomoth, Jahath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24023, 'Of the sons of Hebron, Jeriah was the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24024, 'Of the sons of Uzziel, Michah; of the sons of Michah, Shamir. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24025, 'The brother of Michah, Isshiah; of the sons of Isshiah, Zechariah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24026, 'The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi; the son of Jaaziah, Beno. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24027, 'The sons of Merari by Jaaziah were Beno, Shoham, Zaccur, and Ibri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24028, 'Of Mahli: Eleazar, who had no sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24029, 'Of Kish: the son of Kish, Jerahmeel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24030, 'Also the sons of Mushi were Mahli, Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the sons of the Levites according to their fathers&rsquo; houses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 24031, 'These also cast lots just as their brothers the sons of Aaron did, in the presence of King David, Zadok, Ahimelech, and the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the priests and Levites. The chief fathers did just as their younger brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25001, 'Moreover David and the captains of the army separated for the service some of the sons of Asaph, of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who should prophesy with harps, stringed instruments, and cymbals. And the number of the skilled men performing their service was: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25002, 'Of the sons of Asaph: Zaccur, Joseph, Nethaniah, and Asharelah; the sons of Asaph were under the direction of Asaph, who prophesied according to the order of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25003, 'Of Jeduthun, the sons of Jeduthun: Gedaliah, Zeri, Jeshaiah, Shimei, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the direction of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied with a harp to give thanks and to praise the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25004, 'Of Heman, the sons of Heman: Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel, Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, Romamti-Ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25005, 'All these were the sons of Heman the king&rsquo;s seer in the words of God, to exalt his horn. For God gave Heman fourteen sons and three daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25006, 'All these were under the direction of their father for the music in the house of the Lord, with cymbals, stringed instruments, and harps, for the service of the house of God. Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman were under the authority of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25007, 'So the number of them, with their brethren who were instructed in the songs of the Lord, all who were skillful, was two hundred and eighty-eight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25008, 'And they cast lots for their duty, the small as well as the great, the teacher with the student. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25009, 'Now the first lot for Asaph came out for Joseph; the second for Gedaliah, him with his brethren and sons, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25010, 'the third for Zaccur, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25011, 'the fourth for Jizri, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25012, 'the fifth for Nethaniah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25013, 'the sixth for Bukkiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25014, 'the seventh for Jesharelah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25015, 'the eighth for Jeshaiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25016, 'the ninth for Mattaniah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25017, 'the tenth for Shimei, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25018, 'the eleventh for Azarel, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25019, 'the twelfth for Hashabiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25020, 'the thirteenth for Shubael, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25021, 'the fourteenth for Mattithiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25022, 'the fifteenth for Jeremoth, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25023, 'the sixteenth for Hananiah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25024, 'the seventeenth for Joshbekashah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25025, 'the eighteenth for Hanani, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25026, 'the nineteenth for Mallothi, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25027, 'the twentieth for Eliathah, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25028, 'the twenty-first for Hothir, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25029, 'the twenty-second for Giddalti, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25030, 'the twenty-third for Mahazioth, his sons and his brethren, twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 25031, 'the twenty-fourth for Romamti-Ezer, his sons and his brethren, twelve. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26001, 'Concerning the divisions of the gatekeepers: of the Korahites, Meshelemiah the son of Kore, of the sons of Asaph. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26002, 'And the sons of Meshelemiah were Zechariah the firstborn, Jediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Jathniel the fourth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26003, 'Elam the fifth, Jehohanan the sixth, Eliehoenai the seventh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26004, 'Moreover the sons of Obed-Edom were Shemaiah the firstborn, Jehozabad the second, Joah the third, Sacar the fourth, Nethanel the fifth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26005, 'Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seventh, Peulthai the eighth; for God blessed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26006, 'Also to Shemaiah his son were sons born who governed their fathers&rsquo; houses, because they were men of great ability. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26007, 'The sons of Shemaiah were Othni, Rephael, Obed, and Elzabad, whose brothers Elihu and Semachiah were able men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26008, 'All these were of the sons of Obed-Edom, they and their sons and their brethren, able men with strength for the work: sixty-two of Obed-Edom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26009, 'And Meshelemiah had sons and brethren, eighteen able men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26010, 'Also Hosah, of the children of Merari, had sons: Shimri the first (for though he was not the firstborn, his father made him the first), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26011, 'Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the third, Zechariah the fourth; all the sons and brethren of Hosah were thirteen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26012, 'Among these were the divisions of the gatekeepers, among the chief men, having duties just like their brethren, to serve in the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26013, 'And they cast lots for each gate, the small as well as the great, according to their father&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26014, 'The lot for the East Gate fell to Shelemiah. Then they cast lots for his son Zechariah, a wise counselor, and his lot came out for the North Gate; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26015, 'to Obed-Edom the South Gate, and to his sons the storehouse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26016, 'To Shuppim and Hosah the lot came out for the West Gate, with the Shallecheth Gate on the ascending highway &ndash; watchman opposite watchman. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26017, 'On the east were six Levites, on the north four each day, on the south four each day, and for the storehouse two by two. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26018, 'As for the Parbar on the west, there were four on the highway and two at the Parbar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26019, 'These were the divisions of the gatekeepers among the sons of Korah and among the sons of Merari. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26020, 'Of the Levites, Ahijah was over the treasuries of the house of God and over the treasuries of the dedicated things. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26021, 'The sons of Laadan, the descendants of the Gershonites of Laadan, heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, of Laadan the Gershonite: Jehieli. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26022, 'The sons of Jehieli, Zetham and Joel his brother, were over the treasuries of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26023, 'Of the Amramites, the Izharites, the Hebronites, and the Uzzielites: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26024, 'Shebuel the son of Gershom, the son of Moses, was overseer of the treasuries. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26025, 'And his brethren by Eliezer were Rehabiah his son, Jeshaiah his son, Joram his son, Zichri his son, and Shelomith his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26026, 'This Shelomith and his brethren were over all the treasuries of the dedicated things which King David and the heads of fathers&rsquo; houses, the captains over thousands and hundreds, and the captains of the army, had dedicated. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26027, 'Some of the spoils won in battles they dedicated to maintain the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26028, 'And all that Samuel the seer, Saul the son of Kish, Abner the son of Ner, and Joab the son of Zeruiah had dedicated, every dedicated thing, was under the hand of Shelomith and his brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26029, 'Of the Izharites, Chenaniah and his sons performed duties as officials and judges over Israel outside Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26030, 'Of the Hebronites, Hashabiah and his brethren, one thousand seven hundred able men, had the oversight of Israel on the west side of the Jordan for all the business of the Lord, and in the service of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26031, 'Among the Hebronites, Jerijah was head of the Hebronites according to his genealogy of the fathers. In the fortieth year of the reign of David they were sought, and there were found among them capable men at Jazer of Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 26032, 'And his brethren were two thousand seven hundred able men, heads of fathers&rsquo; houses, whom King David made officials over the Reubenites, the Gadites, and the half-tribe of Manasseh, for every matter pertaining to God and the affairs of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27001, 'And the children of Israel, according to their number, the heads of fathers&rsquo; houses, the captains of thousands and hundreds and their officers, served the king in every matter of the military divisions. These divisions came in and went out month by month throughout all the months of the year, each division having twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27002, 'Over the first division for the first month was Jashobeam the son of Zabdiel, and in his division were twenty-four thousand; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27003, 'he was of the children of Perez, and the chief of all the captains of the army for the first month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27004, 'Over the division of the second month was Dodai an Ahohite, and of his division Mikloth also was the leader; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27005, 'The third captain of the army for the third month was Benaiah, the son of Jehoiada the priest, who was chief; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27006, 'This was the Benaiah who was mighty among the thirty, and was over the thirty; in his division was Ammizabad his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27007, 'The fourth captain for the fourth month was Asahel the brother of Joab, and Zebadiah his son after him; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27008, 'The fifth captain for the fifth month was Shamhuth the Izrahite; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27009, 'The sixth captain for the sixth month was Ira the son of Ikkesh the Tekoite; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27010, 'The seventh captain for the seventh month was Helez the Pelonite, of the children of Ephraim; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27011, 'The eighth captain for the eighth month was Sibbechai the Hushathite, of the Zarhites; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27012, 'The ninth captain for the ninth month was Abiezer the Anathothite, of the Benjamites; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27013, 'The tenth captain for the tenth month was Maharai the Netophathite, of the Zarhites; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27014, 'The eleventh captain for the eleventh month was Benaiah the Pirathonite, of the children of Ephraim; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27015, 'The twelfth captain for the twelfth month was Heldai the Netophathite, of Othniel; in his division were twenty-four thousand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27016, 'Furthermore, over the tribes of Israel: the officer over the Reubenites was Eliezer the son of Zichri; over the Simeonites, Shephatiah the son of Maachah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27017, 'over the Levites, Hashabiah the son of Kemuel; over the Aaronites, Zadok; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27018, 'over Judah, Elihu, one of David&rsquo;s brothers; over Issachar, Omri the son of Michael; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27019, 'over Zebulun, Ishmaiah the son of Obadiah; over Naphtali, Jerimoth the son of Azriel; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27020, 'over the children of Ephraim, Hoshea the son of Azaziah; over the half-tribe of Manasseh, Joel the son of Pedaiah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27021, 'over the half-tribe of Manasseh in Gilead, Iddo the son of Zechariah; over Benjamin, Jaasiel the son of Abner; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27022, 'over Dan, Azarel the son of Jeroham. These were the leaders of the tribes of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27023, 'But David did not take the number of those twenty years old and under, because the Lord had said He would multiply Israel like the stars of the heavens. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27024, 'Joab the son of Zeruiah began a census, but he did not finish, for wrath came upon Israel because of this census; nor was the number recorded in the account of the chronicles of King David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27025, 'And Azmaveth the son of Adiel was over the king&rsquo;s treasuries; and Jehonathan the son of Uzziah was over the storehouses in the field, in the cities, in the villages, and in the fortresses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27026, 'Ezri the son of Chelub was over those who did the work of the field for tilling the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27027, 'And Shimei the Ramathite was over the vineyards, and Zabdi the Shiphmite was over the produce of the vineyards for the supply of wine. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27028, 'Baal-Hanan the Gederite was over the olive trees and the sycamore trees that were in the lowlands, and Joash was over the store of oil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27029, 'And Shitrai the Sharonite was over the herds that fed in Sharon, and Shaphat the son of Adlai was over the herds that were in the valleys. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27030, 'Obil the Ishmaelite was over the camels, Jehdeiah the Meronothite was over the donkeys, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27031, 'and Jaziz the Hagrite was over the flocks. All these were the officials over King David&rsquo;s property. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27032, 'Also Jehonathan, David&rsquo;s uncle, was a counselor, a wise man, and a scribe; and Jehiel the son of Hachmoni was with the king&rsquo;s sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27033, 'Ahithophel was the king&rsquo;s counselor, and Hushai the Archite was the king&rsquo;s companion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 27034, 'After Ahithophel was Jehoiada the son of Benaiah, then Abiathar. And the general of the king&rsquo;s army was Joab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28001, 'Now David assembled at Jerusalem all the leaders of Israel: the officers of the tribes and the captains of the divisions who served the king, the captains over thousands and captains over hundreds, and the stewards over all the substance and possessions of the king and of his sons, with the officials, the valiant men, and all the mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28002, 'Then King David rose to his feet and said, &ldquo;Hear me, my brethren and my people: I had it in my heart to build a house of rest for the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and for the footstool of our God, and had made preparations to build it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28003, 'But God said to me, &lsquo;You shall not build a house for My name, because you have been a man of war and have shed blood.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28004, 'However the Lord God of Israel chose me above all the house of my father to be king over Israel forever, for He has chosen Judah to be the ruler; and of the house of Judah, the house of my father, and among the sons of my father, He was pleased with me to make me king over all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28005, 'And of all my sons (for the Lord has given me many sons) He has chosen my son Solomon to sit on the throne of the kingdom of the Lord over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28006, 'Now He said to me, &lsquo;It is your son Solomon who shall build My house and My courts; for I have chosen him to be My son, and I will be his Father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28007, 'Moreover I will establish his kingdom forever, if he is steadfast to observe My commandments and My judgments, as it is this day.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28008, 'Now therefore, in the sight of all Israel, the assembly of the Lord, and in the hearing of our God, be careful to seek out all the commandments of the Lord your God, that you may possess this good land, and leave it as an inheritance for your children after you forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28009, 'As for you, my son Solomon, know the God of your father, and serve Him with a loyal heart and with a willing mind; for the Lord searches all hearts and understands all the intent of the thoughts. If you seek Him, He will be found by you; but if you forsake Him, He will cast you off forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28010, 'Consider now, for the Lord has chosen you to build a house for the sanctuary; be strong, and do it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28011, 'Then David gave his son Solomon the plans for the vestibule, its houses, its treasuries, its upper chambers, its inner chambers, and the place of the mercy seat; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28012, 'and the plans for all that he had by the Spirit, of the courts of the house of the Lord, of all the chambers all around, of the treasuries of the house of God, and of the treasuries for the dedicated things; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28013, 'also for the division of the priests and the Levites, for all the work of the service of the house of the Lord, and for all the articles of service in the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28014, 'He gave gold by weight for things of gold, for all articles used in every kind of service; also silver for all articles of silver by weight, for all articles used in every kind of service; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28015, 'the weight for the lampstands of gold, and their lamps of gold, by weight for each lampstand and its lamps; for the lampstands of silver by weight, for the lampstand and its lamps, according to the use of each lampstand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28016, 'And by weight he gave gold for the tables of the showbread, for each table, and silver for the tables of silver; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28017, 'also pure gold for the forks, the basins, the pitchers of pure gold, and the golden bowls &ndash; he gave gold by weight for every bowl; and for the silver bowls, silver by weight for every bowl; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28018, 'and refined gold by weight for the altar of incense, and for the construction of the chariot, that is, the gold cherubim that spread their wings and overshadowed the ark of the covenant of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28019, 'All this, said David, the Lord made me understand in writing, by His hand upon me, all the works of these plans. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28020, 'And David said to his son Solomon, &ldquo;Be strong and of good courage, and do it; do not fear nor be dismayed, for the Lord God &ndash; my God &ndash; will be with you. He will not leave you nor forsake you, until you have finished all the work for the service of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 28021, 'Here are the divisions of the priests and the Levites for all the service of the house of God; and every willing craftsman will be with you for all manner of workmanship, for every kind of service; also the leaders and all the people will be completely at your command.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29001, 'Furthermore King David said to all the assembly: &ldquo;My son Solomon, whom alone God has chosen, is young and inexperienced; and the work is great, because the temple* is not for man but for the Lord God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29002, 'Now for the house of my God I have prepared with all my might: gold for things to be made of gold, silver for things of silver, bronze for things of bronze, iron for things of iron, wood for things of wood, onyx stones, stones to be set, glistening stones of various colors, all kinds of precious stones, and marble slabs in abundance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29003, 'Moreover, because I have set my affection on the house of my God, I have given to the house of my God, over and above all that I have prepared for the holy house, my own special treasure of gold and silver: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29004, 'three thousand talents of gold, of the gold of Ophir, and seven thousand talents of refined silver, to overlay the walls of the houses; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29005, 'the gold for things of gold and the silver for things of silver, and for all kinds of work to be done by the hands of craftsmen. Who then is willing to consecrate himself this day to the Lord?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29006, 'Then the leaders of the fathers&rsquo; houses, leaders of the tribes of Israel, the captains of thousands and of hundreds, with the officers over the king&rsquo;s work, offered willingly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29007, 'They gave for the work of the house of God five thousand talents and ten thousand darics of gold, ten thousand talents of silver, eighteen thousand talents of bronze, and one hundred thousand talents of iron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29008, 'And whoever had precious stones gave them to the treasury of the house of the Lord, into the hand of Jehiel the Gershonite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29009, 'Then the people rejoiced, for they had offered willingly, because with a loyal heart they had offered willingly to the Lord; and King David also rejoiced greatly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29010, 'Therefore David blessed the Lord before all the assembly; and David said: &ldquo;Blessed are You, Lord God of Israel, our Father, forever and ever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29011, 'Yours, O Lord, is the greatness, The power and the glory, The victory and the majesty; For all that is in heaven and in earth is Yours; Yours is the kingdom, O Lord, And You are exalted as head over all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29012, 'Both riches and honor come from You, And You reign over all. In Your hand is power and might; In Your hand it is to make great And to give strength to all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29013, 'Now therefore, our God, We thank You And praise Your glorious name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29014, 'But who am I, and who are my people, That we should be able to offer so willingly as this? For all things come from You, And of Your own we have given You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29015, 'For we are aliens and pilgrims before You, As were all our fathers; Our days on earth are as a shadow, And without hope. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29016, 'O Lord our God, all this abundance that we have prepared to build You a house for Your holy name is from Your hand, and is all Your own. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29017, 'I know also, my God, that You test the heart and have pleasure in uprightness. As for me, in the uprightness of my heart I have willingly offered all these things; and now with joy I have seen Your people, who are present here to offer willingly to You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29018, 'O Lord God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, our fathers, keep this forever in the intent of the thoughts of the heart of Your people, and fix their heart toward You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29019, 'And give my son Solomon a loyal heart to keep Your commandments and Your testimonies and Your statutes, to do all these things, and to build the temple for which I have made provision.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29020, 'Then David said to all the assembly, &ldquo;Now bless the Lord your God.&rdquo; So all the assembly blessed the Lord God of their fathers, and bowed their heads and prostrated themselves before the Lord and the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29021, 'And they made sacrifices to the Lord and offered burnt offerings to the Lord on the next day: a thousand bulls, a thousand rams, a thousand lambs, with their drink offerings, and sacrifices in abundance for all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29022, 'So they ate and drank before the Lord with great gladness on that day. And they made Solomon the son of David king the second time, and anointed him before the Lord to be the leader, and Zadok to be priest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29023, 'Then Solomon sat on the throne of the Lord as king instead of David his father, and prospered; and all Israel obeyed him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29024, 'All the leaders and the mighty men, and also all the sons of King David, submitted themselves to King Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29025, 'So the Lord exalted Solomon exceedingly in the sight of all Israel, and bestowed on him such royal majesty as had not been on any king before him in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29026, 'Thus David the son of Jesse reigned over all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29027, 'And the period that he reigned over Israel was forty years; seven years he reigned in Hebron, and thirty-three years he reigned in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29028, 'So he died in a good old age, full of days and riches and honor; and Solomon his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29029, 'Now the acts of King David, first and last, indeed they are written in the book of Samuel the seer, in the book of Nathan the prophet, and in the book of Gad the seer, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '1Chr', 29030, 'with all his reign and his might, and the events that happened to him, to Israel, and to all the kingdoms of the lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1001, 'Now Solomon the son of David was strengthened in his kingdom, and the Lord his God was with him and exalted him exceedingly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1002, 'And Solomon spoke to all Israel, to the captains of thousands and of hundreds, to the judges, and to every leader in all Israel, the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1003, 'Then Solomon, and all the assembly with him, went to the high place that was at Gibeon; for the tabernacle of meeting with God was there, which Moses the servant of the Lord had made in the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1004, 'But David had brought up the ark of God from Kirjath Jearim to the place David had prepared for it, for he had pitched a tent for it at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1005, 'Now the bronze altar that Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, had made, he put before the tabernacle of the Lord; Solomon and the assembly sought Him there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1006, 'And Solomon went up there to the bronze altar before the Lord, which was at the tabernacle of meeting, and offered a thousand burnt offerings on it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1007, 'On that night God appeared to Solomon, and said to him, &ldquo;Ask! What shall I give you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1008, 'And Solomon said to God: &ldquo;You have shown great mercy to David my father, and have made me king in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1009, 'Now, O Lord God, let Your promise to David my father be established, for You have made me king over a people like the dust of the earth in multitude. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1010, 'Now give me wisdom and knowledge, that I may go out and come in before this people; for who can judge this great people of Yours?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1011, 'And God said to Solomon: &ldquo;Because this was in your heart, and you have not asked riches or wealth or honor or the life of your enemies, nor have you asked long life &ndash; but have asked wisdom and knowledge for yourself, that you may judge My people over whom I have made you king &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1012, 'wisdom and knowledge are granted to you; and I will give you riches and wealth and honor, such as none of the kings have had who were before you, nor shall any after you have the like.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1013, 'So Solomon came to Jerusalem from the high place that was at Gibeon, from before the tabernacle of meeting, and reigned over Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1014, 'And Solomon gathered chariots and horsemen; he had one thousand four hundred chariots and twelve thousand horsemen, whom he stationed in the chariot cities and with the king in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1015, 'Also the king made silver and gold as common in Jerusalem as stones, and he made cedars as abundant as the sycamores which are in the lowland. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1016, 'And Solomon had horses imported from Egypt and Keveh; the king&rsquo;s merchants bought them in Keveh at the current price. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 1017, 'They also acquired and imported from Egypt a chariot for six hundred shekels of silver, and a horse for one hundred and fifty; thus, through their agents, they exported them to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Syria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2001, 'Then Solomon determined to build a temple for the name of the Lord, and a royal house for himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2002, 'Solomon selected seventy thousand men to bear burdens, eighty thousand to quarry stone in the mountains, and three thousand six hundred to oversee them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2003, 'Then Solomon sent to Hiram king of Tyre, saying: As you have dealt with David my father, and sent him cedars to build himself a house to dwell in, so deal with me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2004, 'Behold, I am building a temple for the name of the Lord my God, to dedicate it to Him, to burn before Him sweet incense, for the continual showbread, for the burnt offerings morning and evening, on the Sabbaths, on the New Moons, and on the set feasts of the Lord our God. This is an ordinance forever to Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2005, 'And the temple which I build will be great, for our God is greater than all gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2006, 'But who is able to build Him a temple, since heaven and the heaven of heavens cannot contain Him? Who am I then, that I should build Him a temple, except to burn sacrifice before Him? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2007, 'Therefore send me at once a man skillful to work in gold and silver, in bronze and iron, in purple and crimson and blue, who has skill to engrave with the skillful men who are with me in Judah and Jerusalem, whom David my father provided. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2008, 'Also send me cedar and cypress and algum logs from Lebanon, for I know that your servants have skill to cut timber in Lebanon; and indeed my servants will be with your servants, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2009, 'to prepare timber for me in abundance, for the temple which I am about to build shall be great and wonderful. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2010, 'And indeed I will give to your servants, the woodsmen who cut timber, twenty thousand kors of ground wheat, twenty thousand kors of barley, twenty thousand baths of wine, and twenty thousand baths of oil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2011, 'Then Hiram king of Tyre answered in writing, which he sent to Solomon: Because the Lord loves His people, He has made you king over them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2012, 'Hiram also said: Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, who made heaven and earth, for He has given King David a wise son, endowed with prudence and understanding, who will build a temple for the Lord and a royal house for himself! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2013, 'And now I have sent a skillful man, endowed with understanding, Huram my master craftsman ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2014, '(the son of a woman of the daughters of Dan, and his father was a man of Tyre), skilled to work in gold and silver, bronze and iron, stone and wood, purple and blue, fine linen and crimson, and to make any engraving and to accomplish any plan which may be given to him, with your skillful men and with the skillful men of my lord David your father. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2015, 'Now therefore, the wheat, the barley, the oil, and the wine which my lord has spoken of, let him send to his servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2016, 'And we will cut wood from Lebanon, as much as you need; we will bring it to you in rafts by sea to Joppa, and you will carry it up to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2017, 'Then Solomon numbered all the aliens who were in the land of Israel, after the census in which David his father had numbered them; and there were found to be one hundred and fifty-three thousand six hundred. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 2018, 'And he made seventy thousand of them bearers of burdens, eighty thousand stonecutters in the mountain, and three thousand six hundred overseers to make the people work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3001, 'Now Solomon began to build the house of the Lord at Jerusalem on Mount Moriah, where the Lord* had appeared to his father David, at the place that David had prepared on the threshing floor of Ornan+ the Jebusite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3002, 'And he began to build on the second day of the second month in the fourth year of his reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3003, 'This is the foundation which Solomon laid for building the house of God: The length was sixty cubits (by cubits according to the former measure) and the width twenty cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3004, 'And the vestibule that was in front of the sanctuary was twenty cubits long across the width of the house, and the height was one hundred and twenty. He overlaid the inside with pure gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3005, 'The larger room he paneled with cypress which he overlaid with fine gold, and he carved palm trees and chainwork on it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3006, 'And he decorated the house with precious stones for beauty, and the gold was gold from Parvaim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3007, 'He also overlaid the house &ndash; the beams and doorposts, its walls and doors &ndash; with gold; and he carved cherubim on the walls. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3008, 'And he made the Most Holy Place. Its length was according to the width of the house, twenty cubits, and its width twenty cubits. He overlaid it with six hundred talents of fine gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3009, 'The weight of the nails was fifty shekels of gold; and he overlaid the upper area with gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3010, 'In the Most Holy Place he made two cherubim, fashioned by carving, and overlaid them with gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3011, 'The wings of the cherubim were twenty cubits in overall length: one wing of the one cherub was five cubits, touching the wall of the room, and the other wing was five cubits, touching the wing of the other cherub; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3012, 'one wing of the other cherub was five cubits, touching the wall of the room, and the other wing also was five cubits, touching the wing of the other cherub. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3013, 'The wings of these cherubim spanned twenty cubits overall. They stood on their feet, and they faced inward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3014, 'And he made the veil of blue, purple, crimson, and fine linen, and wove cherubim into it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3015, 'Also he made in front of the temple two pillars thirty-five cubits high, and the capital that was on the top of each of them was five cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3016, 'He made wreaths of chainwork, as in the inner sanctuary, and put them on top of the pillars; and he made one hundred pomegranates, and put them on the wreaths of chainwork. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 3017, 'Then he set up the pillars before the temple, one on the right hand and the other on the left; he called the name of the one on the right hand Jachin, and the name of the one on the left Boaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4001, 'Moreover he made a bronze altar: twenty cubits was its length, twenty cubits its width, and ten cubits its height. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4002, 'Then he made the Sea of cast bronze, ten cubits from one brim to the other; it was completely round. Its height was five cubits, and a line of thirty cubits measured its circumference. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4003, 'And under it was the likeness of oxen encircling it all around, ten to a cubit, all the way around the Sea. The oxen were cast in two rows, when it was cast. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4004, 'It stood on twelve oxen: three looking toward the north, three looking toward the west, three looking toward the south, and three looking toward the east; the Sea was set upon them, and all their back parts pointed inward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4005, 'It was a handbreadth thick; and its brim was shaped like the brim of a cup, like a lily blossom. It contained three thousand baths. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4006, 'He also made ten lavers, and put five on the right side and five on the left, to wash in them; such things as they offered for the burnt offering they would wash in them, but the Sea was for the priests to wash in. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4007, 'And he made ten lampstands of gold according to their design, and set them in the temple, five on the right side and five on the left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4008, 'He also made ten tables, and placed them in the temple, five on the right side and five on the left. And he made one hundred bowls of gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4009, 'Furthermore he made the court of the priests, and the great court and doors for the court; and he overlaid these doors with bronze. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4010, 'He set the Sea on the right side, toward the southeast. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4011, 'Then Huram made the pots and the shovels and the bowls. So Huram finished doing the work that he was to do for King Solomon for the house of God: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4012, 'the two pillars and the bowl-shaped capitals that were on top of the two pillars; the two networks covering the two bowl-shaped capitals which were on top of the pillars; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4013, 'four hundred pomegranates for the two networks (two rows of pomegranates for each network, to cover the two bowl-shaped capitals that were on the pillars); ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4014, 'he also made carts and the lavers on the carts; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4015, 'one Sea and twelve oxen under it; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4016, 'also the pots, the shovels, the forks &ndash; and all their articles Huram his master craftsman made of burnished bronze for King Solomon for the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4017, 'In the plain of Jordan the king had them cast in clay molds, between Succoth and Zeredah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4018, 'And Solomon had all these articles made in such great abundance that the weight of the bronze was not determined. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4019, 'Thus Solomon had all the furnishings made for the house of God: the altar of gold and the tables on which was the showbread; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4020, 'the lampstands with their lamps of pure gold, to burn in the prescribed manner in front of the inner sanctuary, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4021, 'with the flowers and the lamps and the wick-trimmers of gold, of purest gold; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 4022, 'the trimmers, the bowls, the ladles, and the censers of pure gold. As for the entry of the sanctuary, its inner doors to the Most Holy Place, and the doors of the main hall of the temple, were gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5001, 'So all the work that Solomon had done for the house of the Lord was finished; and Solomon brought in the things which his father David had dedicated: the silver and the gold and all the furnishings. And he put them in the treasuries of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5002, 'Now Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads of the tribes, the chief fathers of the children of Israel, in Jerusalem, that they might bring the ark of the covenant of the Lord up from the City of David, which is Zion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5003, 'Therefore all the men of Israel assembled with the king at the feast, which was in the seventh month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5004, 'So all the elders of Israel came, and the Levites took up the ark. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5005, 'Then they brought up the ark, the tabernacle of meeting, and all the holy furnishings that were in the tabernacle. The priests and the Levites brought them up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5006, 'Also King Solomon, and all the congregation of Israel who were assembled with him before the ark, were sacrificing sheep and oxen that could not be counted or numbered for multitude. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5007, 'Then the priests brought in the ark of the covenant of the Lord to its place, into the inner sanctuary of the temple, to the Most Holy Place, under the wings of the cherubim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5008, 'For the cherubim spread their wings over the place of the ark, and the cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5009, 'And the poles extended so that the ends of the poles of the ark could be seen from the holy place, in front of the inner sanctuary; but they could not be seen from outside. And they are there to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5010, 'Nothing was in the ark except the two tablets which Moses put there at Horeb, when the Lord made a covenant with the children of Israel, when they had come out of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5011, 'And it came to pass when the priests came out of the Most Holy Place (for all the priests who were present had sanctified themselves, without keeping to their divisions), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5012, 'and the Levites who were the singers, all those of Asaph and Heman and Jeduthun, with their sons and their brethren, stood at the east end of the altar, clothed in white linen, having cymbals, stringed instruments and harps, and with them one hundred and twenty priests sounding with trumpets &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5013, 'indeed it came to pass, when the trumpeters and singers were as one, to make one sound to be heard in praising and thanking the Lord, and when they lifted up their voice with the trumpets and cymbals and instruments of music, and praised the Lord, saying: &ldquo;For He is good, For His mercy endures forever,&rdquo; that the house, the house of the Lord, was filled with a cloud, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 5014, 'so that the priests could not continue ministering because of the cloud; for the glory of the Lord filled the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6001, 'Then Solomon spoke: &ldquo;The Lord said He would dwell in the dark cloud. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6002, 'I have surely built You an exalted house, And a place for You to dwell in forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6003, 'Then the king turned around and blessed the whole assembly of Israel, while all the assembly of Israel was standing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6004, 'And he said: &ldquo;Blessed be the Lord God of Israel, who has fulfilled with His hands what He spoke with His mouth to my father David, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6005, '&rsquo;Since the day that I brought My people out of the land of Egypt, I have chosen no city from any tribe of Israel in which to build a house, that My name might be there, nor did I choose any man to be a ruler over My people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6006, 'Yet I have chosen Jerusalem, that My name may be there; and I have chosen David to be over My people Israel.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6007, 'Now it was in the heart of my father David to build a temple for the name of the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6008, 'But the Lord said to my father David, &lsquo;Whereas it was in your heart to build a temple for My name, you did well in that it was in your heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6009, 'Nevertheless you shall not build the temple, but your son who will come from your body, he shall build the temple for My name.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6010, 'So the Lord has fulfilled His word which He spoke, and I have filled the position of my father David, and sit on the throne of Israel, as the Lord promised; and I have built the temple for the name of the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6011, 'And there I have put the ark, in which is the covenant of the Lord which He made with the children of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6012, 'Then Solomon stood before the altar of the Lord in the presence of all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6013, '(for Solomon had made a bronze platform five cubits long, five cubits wide, and three cubits high, and had set it in the midst of the court; and he stood on it, knelt down on his knees before all the assembly of Israel, and spread out his hands toward heaven); ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6014, 'and he said: &ldquo;Lord God of Israel, there is no God in heaven or on earth like You, who keep Your covenant and mercy with Your servants who walk before You with all their hearts. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6015, 'You have kept what You promised Your servant David my father; You have both spoken with Your mouth and fulfilled it with Your hand, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6016, 'Therefore, Lord God of Israel, now keep what You promised Your servant David my father, saying, &lsquo;You shall not fail to have a man sit before Me on the throne of Israel, only if your sons take heed to their way, that they walk in My law as you have walked before Me.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6017, 'And now, O Lord God of Israel, let Your word come true, which You have spoken to Your servant David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6018, 'But will God indeed dwell with men on the earth? Behold, heaven and the heaven of heavens cannot contain You. How much less this temple which I have built! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6019, 'Yet regard the prayer of Your servant and his supplication, O Lord my God, and listen to the cry and the prayer which Your servant is praying before You: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6020, 'that Your eyes may be open toward this temple day and night, toward the place where You said You would put Your name, that You may hear the prayer which Your servant prays toward this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6021, 'And may You hear the supplications of Your servant and of Your people Israel, when they pray toward this place. Hear from heaven Your dwelling place, and when You hear, forgive. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6022, 'If anyone sins against his neighbor, and is forced to take an oath, and comes and takes an oath before Your altar in this temple, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6023, 'then hear from heaven, and act, and judge Your servants, bringing retribution on the wicked by bringing his way on his own head, and justifying the righteous by giving him according to his righteousness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6024, 'Or if Your people Israel are defeated before an enemy because they have sinned against You, and return and confess Your name, and pray and make supplication before You in this temple, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6025, 'then hear from heaven and forgive the sin of Your people Israel, and bring them back to the land which You gave to them and their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6026, 'When the heavens are shut up and there is no rain because they have sinned against You, when they pray toward this place and confess Your name, and turn from their sin because You afflict them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6027, 'then hear in heaven, and forgive the sin of Your servants, Your people Israel, that You may teach them the good way in which they should walk; and send rain on Your land which You have given to Your people as an inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6028, 'When there is famine in the land, pestilence or blight or mildew, locusts or grasshoppers; when their enemies besiege them in the land of their cities; whatever plague or whatever sickness there is; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6029, 'whatever prayer, whatever supplication is made by anyone, or by all Your people Israel, when each one knows his own burden and his own grief, and spreads out his hands to this temple: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6030, 'then hear from heaven Your dwelling place, and forgive, and give to everyone according to all his ways, whose heart You know (for You alone know the hearts of the sons of men), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6031, 'that they may fear You, to walk in Your ways as long as they live in the land which You gave to our fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6032, 'Moreover, concerning a foreigner, who is not of Your people Israel, but who comes from a far country for the sake of Your great name and Your mighty hand and Your outstretched arm, when they come and pray in this temple; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6033, 'then hear from heaven Your dwelling place, and do according to all for which the foreigner calls to You, that all peoples of the earth may know Your name and fear You, as do Your people Israel, and that they may know that this temple which I have built is called by Your name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6034, 'When Your people go out to battle against their enemies, wherever You send them, and when they pray to You toward this city which You have chosen and the temple which I have built for Your name, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6035, 'then hear from heaven their prayer and their supplication, and maintain their cause. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6036, 'When they sin against You (for there is no one who does not sin), and You become angry with them and deliver them to the enemy, and they take them captive to a land far or near; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6037, 'yet when they come to themselves in the land where they were carried captive, and repent, and make supplication to You in the land of their captivity, saying, &lsquo;We have sinned, we have done wrong, and have committed wickedness&rsquo;; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6038, 'and when they return to You with all their heart and with all their soul in the land of their captivity, where they have been carried captive, and pray toward their land which You gave to their fathers, the city which You have chosen, and toward the temple which I have built for Your name: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6039, 'then hear from heaven Your dwelling place their prayer and their supplications, and maintain their cause, and forgive Your people who have sinned against You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6040, 'Now, my God, I pray, let Your eyes be open and let Your ears be attentive to the prayer made in this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6041, 'Now therefore, Arise, O Lord God, to Your resting place, You and the ark of Your strength. Let Your priests, O Lord God, be clothed with salvation, And let Your saints rejoice in goodness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 6042, 'O Lord God, do not turn away the face of Your Anointed; Remember the mercies of Your servant David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7001, 'When Solomon had finished praying, fire came down from heaven and consumed the burnt offering and the sacrifices; and the glory of the Lord filled the temple.* ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7002, 'And the priests could not enter the house of the Lord, because the glory of the Lord had filled the Lord&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7003, 'When all the children of Israel saw how the fire came down, and the glory of the Lord on the temple, they bowed their faces to the ground on the pavement, and worshiped and praised the Lord, saying: For He is good, For His mercy endures forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7004, 'Then the king and all the people offered sacrifices before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7005, 'King Solomon offered a sacrifice of twenty-two thousand bulls and one hundred and twenty thousand sheep. So the king and all the people dedicated the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7006, 'And the priests attended to their services; the Levites also with instruments of the music of the Lord, which King David had made to praise the Lord, saying, For His mercy endures forever, whenever David offered praise by their ministry. The priests sounded trumpets opposite them, while all Israel stood. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7007, 'Furthermore Solomon consecrated the middle of the court that was in front of the house of the Lord; for there he offered burnt offerings and the fat of the peace offerings, because the bronze altar which Solomon had made was not able to receive the burnt offerings, the grain offerings, and the fat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7008, 'At that time Solomon kept the feast seven days, and all Israel with him, a very great assembly from the entrance of Hamath to the Brook of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7009, 'And on the eighth day they held a sacred assembly, for they observed the dedication of the altar seven days, and the feast seven days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7010, 'On the twenty-third day of the seventh month he sent the people away to their tents, joyful and glad of heart for the good that the Lord had done for David, for Solomon, and for His people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7011, 'Thus Solomon finished the house of the Lord and the king&rsquo;s house; and Solomon successfully accomplished all that came into his heart to make in the house of the Lord and in his own house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7012, 'Then the Lord appeared to Solomon by night, and said to him: I have heard your prayer, and have chosen this place for Myself as a house of sacrifice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7013, 'When I shut up heaven and there is no rain, or command the locusts to devour the land, or send pestilence among My people, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7014, 'if My people who are called by My name will humble themselves, and pray and seek My face, and turn from their wicked ways, then I will hear from heaven, and will forgive their sin and heal their land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7015, 'Now My eyes will be open and My ears attentive to prayer made in this place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7016, 'For now I have chosen and sanctified this house, that My name may be there forever; and My eyes and My heart will be there perpetually. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7017, 'As for you, if you walk before Me as your father David walked, and do according to all that I have commanded you, and if you keep My statutes and My judgments, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7018, 'then I will establish the throne of your kingdom, as I covenanted with David your father, saying, &lsquo;You shall not fail to have a man as ruler in Israel.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7019, 'But if you turn away and forsake My statutes and My commandments which I have set before you, and go and serve other gods, and worship them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7020, 'then I will uproot them from My land which I have given them; and this house which I have sanctified for My name I will cast out of My sight, and will make it a proverb and a byword among all peoples. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7021, 'And as for this house, which is exalted, everyone who passes by it will be astonished and say, &lsquo;Why has the Lord done thus to this land and this house?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 7022, 'Then they will answer, &lsquo;Because they forsook the Lord God of their fathers, who brought them out of the land of Egypt, and embraced other gods, and worshiped them and served them; therefore He has brought all this calamity on them.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8001, 'It came to pass at the end of twenty years, in which Solomon had built the house of the Lord and his own house, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8002, 'that the cities which Hiram had given to Solomon, Solomon built them; and he settled the children of Israel there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8003, 'And Solomon went to Hamath Zobah and seized it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8004, 'He also built Tadmor in the wilderness, and all the storage cities which he built in Hamath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8005, 'He built Upper Beth Horon and Lower Beth Horon, fortified cities with walls, gates, and bars, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8006, 'also Baalath and all the storage cities that Solomon had, and all the chariot cities and the cities of the cavalry, and all that Solomon desired to build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8007, 'All the people who were left of the Hittites, Amorites, Perizzites, Hivites, and Jebusites, who were not of Israel &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8008, 'that is, their descendants who were left in the land after them, whom the children of Israel did not destroy &ndash; from these Solomon raised forced labor, as it is to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8009, 'But Solomon did not make the children of Israel servants for his work. Some were men of war, captains of his officers, captains of his chariots, and his cavalry. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8010, 'And others were chiefs of the officials of King Solomon: two hundred and fifty, who ruled over the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8011, 'Now Solomon brought the daughter of Pharaoh up from the City of David to the house he had built for her, for he said, &ldquo;My wife shall not dwell in the house of David king of Israel, because the places to which the ark of the Lord has come are holy.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8012, 'Then Solomon offered burnt offerings to the Lord on the altar of the Lord which he had built before the vestibule, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8013, 'according to the daily rate, offering according to the commandment of Moses, for the Sabbaths, the New Moons, and the three appointed yearly feasts &ndash; the Feast of Unleavened Bread, the Feast of Weeks, and the Feast of Tabernacles. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8014, 'And, according to the order of David his father, he appointed the divisions of the priests for their service, the Levites for their duties (to praise and serve before the priests) as the duty of each day required, and the gatekeepers by their divisions at each gate; for so David the man of God had commanded. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8015, 'They did not depart from the command of the king to the priests and Levites concerning any matter or concerning the treasuries. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8016, 'Now all the work of Solomon was well-ordered from the day of the foundation of the house of the Lord until it was finished. So the house of the Lord was completed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8017, 'Then Solomon went to Ezion Geber and Elath on the seacoast, in the land of Edom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 8018, 'And Hiram sent him ships by the hand of his servants, and servants who knew the sea. They went with the servants of Solomon to Ophir, and acquired four hundred and fifty talents of gold from there, and brought it to King Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9001, 'Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon, she came to Jerusalem to test Solomon with hard questions, having a very great retinue, camels that bore spices, gold in abundance, and precious stones; and when she came to Solomon, she spoke with him about all that was in her heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9002, 'So Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing so difficult for Solomon that he could not explain it to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9003, 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen the wisdom of Solomon, the house that he had built, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9004, 'the food on his table, the seating of his servants, the service of his waiters and their apparel, his cupbearers and their apparel, and his entryway by which he went up to the house of the Lord, there was no more spirit in her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9005, 'Then she said to the king: &ldquo;It was a true report which I heard in my own land about your words and your wisdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9006, 'However I did not believe their words until I came and saw with my own eyes; and indeed the half of the greatness of your wisdom was not told me. You exceed the fame of which I heard. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9007, 'Happy are your men and happy are these your servants, who stand continually before you and hear your wisdom! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9008, 'Blessed be the Lord your God, who delighted in you, setting you on His throne to be king for the Lord your God! Because your God has loved Israel, to establish them forever, therefore He made you king over them, to do justice and righteousness.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9009, 'And she gave the king one hundred and twenty talents of gold, spices in great abundance, and precious stones; there never were any spices such as those the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9010, 'Also, the servants of Hiram and the servants of Solomon, who brought gold from Ophir, brought algum wood and precious stones. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9011, 'And the king made walkways of the algum wood for the house of the Lord and for the king&rsquo;s house, also harps and stringed instruments for singers; and there were none such as these seen before in the land of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9012, 'Now King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all she desired, whatever she asked, much more than she had brought to the king. So she turned and went to her own country, she and her servants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9013, 'The weight of gold that came to Solomon yearly was six hundred and sixty-six talents of gold, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9014, 'besides what the traveling merchants and traders brought. And all the kings of Arabia and governors of the country brought gold and silver to Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9015, 'And King Solomon made two hundred large shields of hammered gold; six hundred shekels of hammered gold went into each shield. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9016, 'He also made three hundred shields of hammered gold; three hundred shekels of gold went into each shield. The king put them in the House of the Forest of Lebanon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9017, 'Moreover the king made a great throne of ivory, and overlaid it with pure gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9018, 'The throne had six steps, with a footstool of gold, which were fastened to the throne; there were armrests on either side of the place of the seat, and two lions stood beside the armrests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9019, 'Twelve lions stood there, one on each side of the six steps; nothing like this had been made for any other kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9020, 'All King Solomon&rsquo;s drinking vessels were gold, and all the vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were pure gold. Not one was silver, for this was accounted as nothing in the days of Solomon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9021, 'For the king&rsquo;s ships went to Tarshish with the servants of Hiram. Once every three years the merchant ships came, bringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and monkeys.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9022, 'So King Solomon surpassed all the kings of the earth in riches and wisdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9023, 'And all the kings of the earth sought the presence of Solomon to hear his wisdom, which God had put in his heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9024, 'Each man brought his present: articles of silver and gold, garments, armor, spices, horses, and mules, at a set rate year by year. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9025, 'Solomon had four thousand stalls for horses and chariots, and twelve thousand horsemen whom he stationed in the chariot cities and with the king at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9026, 'So he reigned over all the kings from the River to the land of the Philistines, as far as the border of Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9027, 'The king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stones, and he made cedar trees as abundant as the sycamores which are in the lowland. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9028, 'And they brought horses to Solomon from Egypt and from all lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9029, 'Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, first and last, are they not written in the book of Nathan the prophet, in the prophecy of Ahijah the Shilonite, and in the visions of Iddo the seer concerning Jeroboam the son of Nebat? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9030, 'Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel forty years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 9031, 'Then Solomon rested with his fathers, and was buried in the City of David his father. And Rehoboam his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10001, 'And Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had gone to Shechem to make him king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10002, 'So it happened, when Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard it (he was in Egypt, where he had fled from the presence of King Solomon), that Jeroboam returned from Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10003, 'Then they sent for him and called him. And Jeroboam and all Israel came and spoke to Rehoboam, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10004, 'Your father made our yoke heavy; now therefore, lighten the burdensome service of your father and his heavy yoke which he put on us, and we will serve you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10005, 'So he said to them, &ldquo;Come back to me after three days.&rdquo; And the people departed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10006, 'Then King Rehoboam consulted the elders who stood before his father Solomon while he still lived, saying, &ldquo;How do you advise me to answer these people?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10007, 'And they spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;If you are kind to these people, and please them, and speak good words to them, they will be your servants forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10008, 'But he rejected the advice which the elders had given him, and consulted the young men who had grown up with him, who stood before him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10009, 'And he said to them, &ldquo;What advice do you give? How should we answer this people who have spoken to me, saying, &lsquo;Lighten the yoke which your father put on us&rsquo;?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10010, 'Then the young men who had grown up with him spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;Thus you should speak to the people who have spoken to you, saying, &lsquo;Your father made our yoke heavy, but you make it lighter on us&rsquo; &ndash; thus you shall say to them: &lsquo;My little finger shall be thicker than my father&rsquo;s waist! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10011, 'And now, whereas my father put a heavy yoke on you, I will add to your yoke; my father chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scourges!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10012, 'So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam on the third day, as the king had directed, saying, &ldquo;Come back to me the third day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10013, 'Then the king answered them roughly. King Rehoboam rejected the advice of the elders, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10014, 'and he spoke to them according to the advice of the young men, saying, &ldquo;My father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to it; my father chastised you with whips, but I will chastise you with scourges!&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10015, 'So the king did not listen to the people; for the turn of events was from God, that the Lord might fulfill His word, which He had spoken by the hand of Ahijah the Shilonite to Jeroboam the son of Nebat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10016, 'Now when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the people answered the king, saying: &ldquo;What share have we in David? We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse. Every man to your tents, O Israel! Now see to your own house, O David!&rdquo; So all Israel departed to their tents. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10017, 'But Rehoboam reigned over the children of Israel who dwelt in the cities of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10018, 'Then King Rehoboam sent Hadoram, who was in charge of revenue; but the children of Israel stoned him with stones, and he died. Therefore King Rehoboam mounted his chariot in haste to flee to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 10019, 'So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11001, 'Now when Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled from the house of Judah and Benjamin one hundred and eighty thousand chosen men who were warriors, to fight against Israel, that he might restore the kingdom to Rehoboam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11002, 'But the word of the Lord came to Shemaiah the man of God, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11003, 'Speak to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all Israel in Judah and Benjamin, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11004, '&rsquo;Thus says the Lord: You shall not go up or fight against your brethren! Let every man return to his house, for this thing is from Me. &lsquo; Therefore they obeyed the words of the Lord, and turned back from attacking Jeroboam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11005, 'So Rehoboam dwelt in Jerusalem, and built cities for defense in Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11006, 'And he built Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11007, 'Beth Zur, Sochoh, Adullam, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11008, 'Gath, Mareshah, Ziph, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11009, 'Adoraim, Lachish, Azekah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11010, 'Zorah, Aijalon, and Hebron, which are in Judah and Benjamin, fortified cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11011, 'And he fortified the strongholds, and put captains in them, and stores of food, oil, and wine. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11012, 'Also in every city he put shields and spears, and made them very strong, having Judah and Benjamin on his side. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11013, 'And from all their territories the priests and the Levites who were in all Israel took their stand with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11014, 'For the Levites left their common-lands and their possessions and came to Judah and Jerusalem, for Jeroboam and his sons had rejected them from serving as priests to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11015, 'Then he appointed for himself priests for the high places, for the demons, and the calf idols which he had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11016, 'And after the Levites left, those from all the tribes of Israel, such as set their heart to seek the Lord God of Israel, came to Jerusalem to sacrifice to the Lord God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11017, 'So they strengthened the kingdom of Judah, and made Rehoboam the son of Solomon strong for three years, because they walked in the way of David and Solomon for three years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11018, 'Then Rehoboam took for himself as wife Mahalath the daughter of Jerimoth the son of David, and of Abihail the daughter of Eliah the son of Jesse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11019, 'And she bore him children: Jeush, Shamariah, and Zaham. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11020, 'After her he took Maacah the granddaughter of Absalom; and she bore him Abijah, Attai, Ziza, and Shelomith. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11021, 'Now Rehoboam loved Maachah the granddaughter of Absalom more than all his wives and his concubines; for he took eighteen wives and sixty concubines, and begot twenty-eight sons and sixty daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11022, 'And Rehoboam appointed Abijah the son of Maachah as chief, to be leader among his brothers; for he intended to make him king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 11023, 'He dealt wisely, and dispersed some of his sons throughout all the territories of Judah and Benjamin, to every fortified city; and he gave them provisions in abundance. He also sought many wives for them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12001, 'Now it came to pass, when Rehoboam had established the kingdom and had strengthened himself, that he forsook the law of the Lord, and all Israel along with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12002, 'And it happened in the fifth year of King Rehoboam, that Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, because they had transgressed against the Lord, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12003, 'with twelve hundred chariots, sixty thousand horsemen, and people without number who came with him out of Egypt &ndash; the Lubim and the Sukkiim and the Ethiopians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12004, 'And he took the fortified cities of Judah and came to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12005, 'Then Shemaiah the prophet came to Rehoboam and the leaders of Judah, who were gathered together in Jerusalem because of Shishak, and said to them, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;You have forsaken Me, and therefore I also have left you in the hand of Shishak.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12006, 'So the leaders of Israel and the king humbled themselves; and they said, &ldquo;The Lord is righteous.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12007, 'Now when the Lord saw that they humbled themselves, the word of the Lord came to Shemaiah, saying, &ldquo;They have humbled themselves; therefore I will not destroy them, but I will grant them some deliverance. My wrath shall not be poured out on Jerusalem by the hand of Shishak. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12008, 'Nevertheless they will be his servants, that they may distinguish My service from the service of the kingdoms of the nations.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12009, 'So Shishak king of Egypt came up against Jerusalem, and took away the treasures of the house of the Lord and the treasures of the king&rsquo;s house; he took everything. He also carried away the gold shields which Solomon had made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12010, 'Then King Rehoboam made bronze shields in their place, and committed them to the hands of the captains of the guard, who guarded the doorway of the king&rsquo;s house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12011, 'And whenever the king entered the house of the Lord, the guard would go and bring them out; then they would take them back into the guardroom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12012, 'When he humbled himself, the wrath of the Lord turned from him, so as not to destroy him completely; and things also went well in Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12013, 'Thus Rehoboam strengthened himself in Jerusalem and reigned. Now Rehoboam was forty-one years old when he became king; and he reigned seventeen years in Jerusalem, the city which the Lord had chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, to put His name there. His mother&rsquo;s name was Naamah, an Ammonitess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12014, 'And he did evil, because he did not prepare his heart to seek the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12015, 'The acts of Rehoboam, first and last, are they not written in the book of Shemaiah the prophet, and of Iddo the seer concerning genealogies? And there were wars between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all their days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 12016, 'So Rehoboam rested with his fathers, and was buried in the City of David. Then Abijah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13001, 'In the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam, Abijah became king over Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13002, 'He reigned three years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Michaiah the daughter of Uriel of Gibeah. And there was war between Abijah and Jeroboam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13003, 'Abijah set the battle in order with an army of valiant warriors, four hundred thousand choice men. Jeroboam also drew up in battle formation against him with eight hundred thousand choice men, mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13004, 'Then Abijah stood on Mount Zemaraim, which is in the mountains of Ephraim, and said, &ldquo;Hear me, Jeroboam and all Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13005, 'Should you not know that the Lord God of Israel gave the dominion over Israel to David forever, to him and his sons, by a covenant of salt? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13006, 'Yet Jeroboam the son of Nebat, the servant of Solomon the son of David, rose up and rebelled against his lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13007, 'Then worthless rogues gathered to him, and strengthened themselves against Rehoboam the son of Solomon, when Rehoboam was young and inexperienced and could not withstand them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13008, 'And now you think to withstand the kingdom of the Lord, which is in the hand of the sons of David; and you are a great multitude, and with you are the gold calves which Jeroboam made for you as gods. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13009, 'Have you not cast out the priests of the Lord, the sons of Aaron, and the Levites, and made for yourselves priests, like the peoples of other lands, so that whoever comes to consecrate himself with a young bull and seven rams may be a priest of things that are not gods? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13010, 'But as for us, the Lord is our God, and we have not forsaken Him; and the priests who minister to the Lord are the sons of Aaron, and the Levites attend to their duties. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13011, 'And they burn to the Lord every morning and every evening burnt sacrifices and sweet incense; they also set the showbread in order on the pure gold table, and the lampstand of gold with its lamps to burn every evening; for we keep the command of the Lord our God, but you have forsaken Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13012, 'Now look, God Himself is with us as our head, and His priests with sounding trumpets to sound the alarm against you. O children of Israel, do not fight against the Lord God of your fathers, for you shall not prosper!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13013, 'But Jeroboam caused an ambush to go around behind them; so they were in front of Judah, and the ambush was behind them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13014, 'And when Judah looked around, to their surprise the battle line was at both front and rear; and they cried out to the Lord, and the priests sounded the trumpets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13015, 'Then the men of Judah gave a shout; and as the men of Judah shouted, it happened that God struck Jeroboam and all Israel before Abijah and Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13016, 'And the children of Israel fled before Judah, and God delivered them into their hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13017, 'Then Abijah and his people struck them with a great slaughter; so five hundred thousand choice men of Israel fell slain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13018, 'Thus the children of Israel were subdued at that time; and the children of Judah prevailed, because they relied on the Lord God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13019, 'And Abijah pursued Jeroboam and took cities from him: Bethel with its villages, Jeshanah with its villages, and Ephrain with its villages. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13020, 'So Jeroboam did not recover strength again in the days of Abijah; and the Lord struck him, and he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13021, 'But Abijah grew mighty, married fourteen wives, and begot twenty-two sons and sixteen daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 13022, 'Now the rest of the acts of Abijah, his ways, and his sayings are written in the annals of the prophet Iddo. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14001, 'So Abijah rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the City of David. Then Asa his son reigned in his place. In his days the land was quiet for ten years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14002, 'Asa did what was good and right in the eyes of the Lord his God, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14003, 'for he removed the altars of the foreign gods and the high places, and broke down the sacred pillars and cut down the wooden images. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14004, 'He commanded Judah to seek the Lord God of their fathers, and to observe the law and the commandment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14005, 'He also removed the high places and the incense altars from all the cities of Judah, and the kingdom was quiet under him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14006, 'And he built fortified cities in Judah, for the land had rest; he had no war in those years, because the Lord had given him rest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14007, 'Therefore he said to Judah, &ldquo;Let us build these cities and make walls around them, and towers, gates, and bars, while the land is yet before us, because we have sought the Lord our God; we have sought Him, and He has given us rest on every side.&rdquo; So they built and prospered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14008, 'And Asa had an army of three hundred thousand from Judah who carried shields and spears, and from Benjamin two hundred and eighty thousand men who carried shields and drew bows; all these were mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14009, 'Then Zerah the Ethiopian came out against them with an army of a million men and three hundred chariots, and he came to Mareshah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14010, 'So Asa went out against him, and they set the troops in battle array in the Valley of Zephathah at Mareshah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14011, 'And Asa cried out to the Lord his God, and said, &ldquo;Lord, it is nothing for You to help, whether with many or with those who have no power; help us, O Lord our God, for we rest on You, and in Your name we go against this multitude. O Lord, You are our God; do not let man prevail against You!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14012, 'So the Lord struck the Ethiopians before Asa and Judah, and the Ethiopians fled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14013, 'And Asa and the people who were with him pursued them to Gerar. So the Ethiopians were overthrown, and they could not recover, for they were broken before the Lord and His army. And they carried away very much spoil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14014, 'Then they defeated all the cities around Gerar, for the fear of the Lord came upon them; and they plundered all the cities, for there was exceedingly much spoil in them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 14015, 'They also attacked the livestock enclosures, and carried off sheep and camels in abundance, and returned to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15001, 'Now the Spirit of God came upon Azariah the son of Oded. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15002, 'And he went out to meet Asa, and said to him: &ldquo;Hear me, Asa, and all Judah and Benjamin. The Lord is with you while you are with Him. If you seek Him, He will be found by you; but if you forsake Him, He will forsake you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15003, 'For a long time Israel has been without the true God, without a teaching priest, and without law; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15004, 'but when in their trouble they turned to the Lord God of Israel, and sought Him, He was found by them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15005, 'And in those times there was no peace to the one who went out, nor to the one who came in, but great turmoil was on all the inhabitants of the lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15006, 'So nation was destroyed by nation, and city by city, for God troubled them with every adversity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15007, 'But you, be strong and do not let your hands be weak, for your work shall be rewarded!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15008, 'And when Asa heard these words and the prophecy of Oded the prophet, he took courage, and removed the abominable idols from all the land of Judah and Benjamin and from the cities which he had taken in the mountains of Ephraim; and he restored the altar of the Lord that was before the vestibule of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15009, 'Then he gathered all Judah and Benjamin, and those who dwelt with them from Ephraim, Manasseh, and Simeon, for they came over to him in great numbers from Israel when they saw that the Lord his God was with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15010, 'So they gathered together at Jerusalem in the third month, in the fifteenth year of the reign of Asa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15011, 'And they offered to the Lord at that time seven hundred bulls and seven thousand sheep from the spoil they had brought. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15012, 'Then they entered into a covenant to seek the Lord God of their fathers with all their heart and with all their soul; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15013, 'and whoever would not seek the Lord God of Israel was to be put to death, whether small or great, whether man or woman. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15014, 'Then they took an oath before the Lord with a loud voice, with shouting and trumpets and rams&rsquo; horns. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15015, 'And all Judah rejoiced at the oath, for they had sworn with all their heart and sought Him with all their soul; and He was found by them, and the Lord gave them rest all around. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15016, 'Also he removed Maachah, the mother of Asa the king, from being queen mother, because she had made an obscene image of Asherah; and Asa cut down her obscene image, then crushed and burned it by the Brook Kidron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15017, 'But the high places were not removed from Israel. Nevertheless the heart of Asa was loyal all his days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15018, 'He also brought into the house of God the things that his father had dedicated and that he himself had dedicated: silver and gold and utensils. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 15019, 'And there was no war until the thirty-fifth year of the reign of Asa. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16001, 'In the thirty-sixth year of the reign of Asa, Baasha king of Israel came up against Judah and built Ramah, that he might let none go out or come in to Asa king of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16002, 'Then Asa brought silver and gold from the treasuries of the house of the Lord and of the king&rsquo;s house, and sent to Ben-Hadad king of Syria, who dwelt in Damascus, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16003, 'Let there be a treaty between you and me, as there was between my father and your father. Here, I have sent you silver and gold; come, break your treaty with Baasha king of Israel, so that he will withdraw from me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16004, 'So Ben-Hadad heeded King Asa, and sent the captains of his armies against the cities of Israel. They attacked Ijon, Dan, Abel Maim, and all the storage cities of Naphtali. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16005, 'Now it happened, when Baasha heard it, that he stopped building Ramah and ceased his work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16006, 'Then King Asa took all Judah, and they carried away the stones and timber of Ramah, which Baasha had used for building; and with them he built Geba and Mizpah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16007, 'And at that time Hanani the seer came to Asa king of Judah, and said to him: &ldquo;Because you have relied on the king of Syria, and have not relied on the Lord your God, therefore the army of the king of Syria has escaped from your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16008, 'Were the Ethiopians and the Lubim not a huge army with very many chariots and horsemen? Yet, because you relied on the Lord, He delivered them into your hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16009, 'For the eyes of the Lord run to and fro throughout the whole earth, to show Himself strong on behalf of those whose heart is loyal to Him. In this you have done foolishly; therefore from now on you shall have wars.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16010, 'Then Asa was angry with the seer, and put him in prison, for he was enraged at him because of this. And Asa oppressed some of the people at that time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16011, 'Note that the acts of Asa, first and last, are indeed written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16012, 'And in the thirty-ninth year of his reign, Asa became diseased in his feet, and his malady was severe; yet in his disease he did not seek the Lord, but the physicians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16013, 'So Asa rested with his fathers; he died in the forty-first year of his reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 16014, 'They buried him in his own tomb, which he had made for himself in the City of David; and they laid him in the bed which was filled with spices and various ingredients prepared in a mixture of ointments. They made a very great burning for him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17001, 'Then Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place, and strengthened himself against Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17002, 'And he placed troops in all the fortified cities of Judah, and set garrisons in the land of Judah and in the cities of Ephraim which Asa his father had taken. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17003, 'Now the Lord was with Jehoshaphat, because he walked in the former ways of his father David; he did not seek the Baals, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17004, 'but sought the God of his father, and walked in His commandments and not according to the acts of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17005, 'Therefore the Lord established the kingdom in his hand; and all Judah gave presents to Jehoshaphat, and he had riches and honor in abundance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17006, 'And his heart took delight in the ways of the Lord; moreover he removed the high places and wooden images from Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17007, 'Also in the third year of his reign he sent his leaders, Ben-Hail, Obadiah, Zechariah, Nethanel, and Michaiah, to teach in the cities of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17008, 'And with them he sent Levites: Shemaiah, Nethaniah, Zebadiah, Asahel, Shemiramoth, Jehonathan, Adonijah, Tobijah, and Tobadonijah &ndash; the Levites; and with them Elishama and Jehoram, the priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17009, 'So they taught in Judah, and had the Book of the Law of the Lord with them; they went throughout all the cities of Judah and taught the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17010, 'And the fear of the Lord fell on all the kingdoms of the lands that were around Judah, so that they did not make war against Jehoshaphat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17011, 'Also some of the Philistines brought Jehoshaphat presents and silver as tribute; and the Arabians brought him flocks, seven thousand seven hundred rams and seven thousand seven hundred male goats. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17012, 'So Jehoshaphat became increasingly powerful, and he built fortresses and storage cities in Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17013, 'He had much property in the cities of Judah; and the men of war, mighty men of valor, were in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17014, 'These are their numbers, according to their fathers&rsquo; houses. Of Judah, the captains of thousands: Adnah the captain, and with him three hundred thousand mighty men of valor; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17015, 'and next to him was Jehohanan the captain, and with him two hundred and eighty thousand; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17016, 'and next to him was Amasiah the son of Zichri, who willingly offered himself to the Lord, and with him two hundred thousand mighty men of valor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17017, 'Of Benjamin: Eliada a mighty man of valor, and with him two hundred thousand men armed with bow and shield; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17018, 'and next to him was Jehozabad, and with him one hundred and eighty thousand prepared for war. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 17019, 'These served the king, besides those the king put in the fortified cities throughout all Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18001, 'Jehoshaphat had riches and honor in abundance; and by marriage he allied himself with Ahab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18002, 'After some years he went down to visit Ahab in Samaria; and Ahab killed sheep and oxen in abundance for him and the people who were with him, and persuaded him to go up with him to Ramoth Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18003, 'So Ahab king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat king of Judah, &ldquo;Will you go with me against Ramoth Gilead?&rdquo; And he answered him, &ldquo;I am as you are, and my people as your people; we will be with you in the war.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18004, 'And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, &ldquo;Please inquire for the word of the Lord today.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18005, 'Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, four hundred men, and said to them, &ldquo;Shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall I refrain?&rdquo; And they said, &ldquo;Go up, for God will deliver it into the king&rsquo;s hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18006, 'But Jehoshaphat said, &ldquo;Is there not still a prophet of the Lord here, that we may inquire of Him?&rdquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18007, 'So the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;There is still one man by whom we may inquire of the Lord; but I hate him, because he never prophesies good concerning me, but always evil. He is Micaiah the son of Imla.&rdquo; And Jehoshaphat said, &ldquo;Let not the king say such things!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18008, 'Then the king of Israel called one of his officers and said, &ldquo;Bring Micaiah the son of Imla quickly!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18009, 'The king of Israel and Jehoshaphat king of Judah, clothed in their robes, sat each on his throne; and they sat at a threshing floor at the entrance of the gate of Samaria; and all the prophets prophesied before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18010, 'Now Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah had made horns of iron for himself; and he said, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;With these you shall gore the Syrians until they are destroyed.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18011, 'And all the prophets prophesied so, saying, &ldquo;Go up to Ramoth Gilead and prosper, for the Lord will deliver it into the king&rsquo;s hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18012, 'Then the messenger who had gone to call Micaiah spoke to him, saying, &ldquo;Now listen, the words of the prophets with one accord encourage the king. Therefore please let your word be like the word of one of them, and speak encouragement.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18013, 'And Micaiah said, &ldquo;As the Lord lives, whatever my God says, that I will speak.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18014, 'Then he came to the king; and the king said to him, &ldquo;Micaiah, shall we go to war against Ramoth Gilead, or shall I refrain?&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Go and prosper, and they shall be delivered into your hand!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18015, 'So the king said to him, &ldquo;How many times shall I make you swear that you tell me nothing but the truth in the name of the Lord?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18016, 'Then he said, &ldquo;I saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, as sheep that have no shepherd. And the Lord said, &lsquo;These have no master. Let each return to his house in peace.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18017, 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;Did I not tell you he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18018, 'Then Micaiah said, &ldquo;Therefore hear the word of the Lord: I saw the Lord sitting on His throne, and all the host of heaven standing on His right hand and His left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18019, 'And the Lord said, &lsquo;Who will persuade Ahab king of Israel to go up, that he may fall at Ramoth Gilead?&rsquo; So one spoke in this manner, and another spoke in that manner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18020, 'Then a spirit came forward and stood before the Lord, and said, &lsquo;I will persuade him.&rsquo; The Lord said to him, &lsquo;In what way?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18021, 'So he said, &lsquo;I will go out and be a lying spirit in the mouth of all his prophets.&rsquo; And the Lord said, &lsquo;You shall persuade him and also prevail; go out and do so.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18022, 'Therefore look! The Lord has put a lying spirit in the mouth of these prophets of yours, and the Lord has declared disaster against you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18023, 'Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah went near and struck Micaiah on the cheek, and said, &ldquo;Which way did the spirit from the Lord go from me to speak to you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18024, 'And Micaiah said, &ldquo;Indeed you shall see on that day when you go into an inner chamber to hide!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18025, 'Then the king of Israel said, &ldquo;Take Micaiah, and return him to Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king&rsquo;s son; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18026, 'and say, &lsquo;Thus says the king: &ldquo;Put this fellow in prison, and feed him with bread of affliction and water of affliction until I return in peace.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18027, 'Then Micaiah said, &ldquo;If you ever return in peace, the Lord has not spoken by me.&rdquo; And he said, &ldquo;Take heed, all you people!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18028, 'So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to Ramoth Gilead. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18029, 'And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;I will disguise myself and go into battle; but you put on your robes.&rdquo; So the king of Israel disguised himself, and they went into battle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18030, 'Now the king of Syria had commanded the captains of the chariots who were with him, saying, &ldquo;Fight with no one small or great, but only with the king of Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18031, 'So it was, when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, that they said, &ldquo;It is the king of Israel!&rdquo; Therefore they surrounded him to attack; but Jehoshaphat cried out, and the Lord helped him, and God diverted them from him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18032, 'For so it was, when the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king of Israel, that they turned back from pursuing him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18033, 'Now a certain man drew a bow at random, and struck the king of Israel between the joints of his armor. So he said to the driver of his chariot, &ldquo;Turn around and take me out of the battle, for I am wounded.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 18034, 'The battle increased that day, and the king of Israel propped himself up in his chariot facing the Syrians until evening; and about the time of sunset he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19001, 'Then Jehoshaphat the king of Judah returned safely to his house in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19002, 'And Jehu the son of Hanani the seer went out to meet him, and said to King Jehoshaphat, &ldquo;Should you help the wicked and love those who hate the Lord? Therefore the wrath of the Lord is upon you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19003, 'Nevertheless good things are found in you, in that you have removed the wooden images from the land, and have prepared your heart to seek God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19004, 'So Jehoshaphat dwelt at Jerusalem; and he went out again among the people from Beersheba to the mountains of Ephraim, and brought them back to the Lord God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19005, 'Then he set judges in the land throughout all the fortified cities of Judah, city by city, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19006, 'and said to the judges, &ldquo;Take heed to what you are doing, for you do not judge for man but for the Lord, who is with you in the judgment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19007, 'Now therefore, let the fear of the Lord be upon you; take care and do it, for there is no iniquity with the Lord our God, no partiality, nor taking of bribes.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19008, 'Moreover in Jerusalem, for the judgment of the Lord and for controversies, Jehoshaphat appointed some of the Levites and priests, and some of the chief fathers of Israel, when they returned to Jerusalem.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19009, 'And he commanded them, saying, &ldquo;Thus you shall act in the fear of the Lord, faithfully and with a loyal heart: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19010, 'Whatever case comes to you from your brethren who dwell in their cities, whether of bloodshed or offenses against law or commandment, against statutes or ordinances, you shall warn them, lest they trespass against the Lord and wrath come upon you and your brethren. Do this, and you will not be guilty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 19011, 'And take notice: Amariah the chief priest is over you in all matters of the Lord; and Zebadiah the son of Ishmael, the ruler of the house of Judah, for all the king&rsquo;s matters; also the Levites will be officials before you. Behave courageously, and the Lord will be with the good.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20001, 'It happened after this that the people of Moab with the people of Ammon, and others with them besides the Ammonites,* came to battle against Jehoshaphat. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20002, 'Then some came and told Jehoshaphat, saying, &ldquo;A great multitude is coming against you from beyond the sea, from Syria; and they are in Hazazon Tamar&rdquo; (which is En Gedi). ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20003, 'And Jehoshaphat feared, and set himself to seek the Lord, and proclaimed a fast throughout all Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20004, 'So Judah gathered together to ask help from the Lord; and from all the cities of Judah they came to seek the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20005, 'Then Jehoshaphat stood in the assembly of Judah and Jerusalem, in the house of the Lord, before the new court, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20006, 'and said: &ldquo;O Lord God of our fathers, are You not God in heaven, and do You not rule over all the kingdoms of the nations, and in Your hand is there not power and might, so that no one is able to withstand You? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20007, 'Are You not our God, who drove out the inhabitants of this land before Your people Israel, and gave it to the descendants of Abraham Your friend forever? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20008, 'And they dwell in it, and have built You a sanctuary in it for Your name, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20009, '&rsquo;If disaster comes upon us &ndash; sword, judgment, pestilence, or famine &ndash; we will stand before this temple and in Your presence (for Your name is in this temple), and cry out to You in our affliction, and You will hear and save.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20010, 'And now, here are the people of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir &ndash; whom You would not let Israel invade when they came out of the land of Egypt, but they turned from them and did not destroy them &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20011, 'here they are, rewarding us by coming to throw us out of Your possession which You have given us to inherit. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20012, 'O our God, will You not judge them? For we have no power against this great multitude that is coming against us; nor do we know what to do, but our eyes are upon You.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20013, 'Now all Judah, with their little ones, their wives, and their children, stood before the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20014, 'Then the Spirit of the Lord came upon Jahaziel the son of Zechariah, the son of Benaiah, the son of Jeiel, the son of Mattaniah, a Levite of the sons of Asaph, in the midst of the assembly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20015, 'And he said, &ldquo;Listen, all you of Judah and you inhabitants of Jerusalem, and you, King Jehoshaphat! Thus says the Lord to you: &lsquo;Do not be afraid nor dismayed because of this great multitude, for the battle is not yours, but God&rsquo;s. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20016, 'Tomorrow go down against them. They will surely come up by the Ascent of Ziz, and you will find them at the end of the brook before the Wilderness of Jeruel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20017, 'You will not need to fight in this battle. Position yourselves, stand still and see the salvation of the Lord, who is with you, O Judah and Jerusalem!&rsquo; Do not fear or be dismayed; tomorrow go out against them, for the Lord is with you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20018, 'And Jehoshaphat bowed his head with his face to the ground, and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem bowed before the Lord, worshiping the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20019, 'Then the Levites of the children of the Kohathites and of the children of the Korahites stood up to praise the Lord God of Israel with voices loud and high. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20020, 'So they rose early in the morning and went out into the Wilderness of Tekoa; and as they went out, Jehoshaphat stood and said, &ldquo;Hear me, O Judah and you inhabitants of Jerusalem: Believe in the Lord your God, and you shall be established; believe His prophets, and you shall prosper.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20021, 'And when he had consulted with the people, he appointed those who should sing to the Lord, and who should praise the beauty of holiness, as they went out before the army and were saying: &ldquo;Praise the Lord, For His mercy endures forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20022, 'Now when they began to sing and to praise, the Lord set ambushes against the people of Ammon, Moab, and Mount Seir, who had come against Judah; and they were defeated. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20023, 'For the people of Ammon and Moab stood up against the inhabitants of Mount Seir to utterly kill and destroy them. And when they had made an end of the inhabitants of Seir, they helped to destroy one another. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20024, 'So when Judah came to a place overlooking the wilderness, they looked toward the multitude; and there were their dead bodies, fallen on the earth. No one had escaped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20025, 'When Jehoshaphat and his people came to take away their spoil, they found among them an abundance of valuables on the dead bodies, and precious jewelry, which they stripped off for themselves, more than they could carry away; and they were three days gathering the spoil because there was so much. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20026, 'And on the fourth day they assembled in the Valley of Berachah, for there they blessed the Lord; therefore the name of that place was called The Valley of Berachah until this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20027, 'Then they returned, every man of Judah and Jerusalem, with Jehoshaphat in front of them, to go back to Jerusalem with joy, for the Lord had made them rejoice over their enemies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20028, 'So they came to Jerusalem, with stringed instruments and harps and trumpets, to the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20029, 'And the fear of God was on all the kingdoms of those countries when they heard that the Lord had fought against the enemies of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20030, 'Then the realm of Jehoshaphat was quiet, for his God gave him rest all around. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20031, 'So Jehoshaphat was king over Judah. He was thirty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Azubah the daughter of Shilhi. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20032, 'And he walked in the way of his father Asa, and did not turn aside from it, doing what was right in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20033, 'Nevertheless the high places were not taken away, for as yet the people had not directed their hearts to the God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20034, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, first and last, indeed they are written in the book of Jehu the son of Hanani, which is mentioned in the book of the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20035, 'After this Jehoshaphat king of Judah allied himself with Ahaziah king of Israel, who acted very wickedly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20036, 'And he allied himself with him to make ships to go to Tarshish, and they made the ships in Ezion Geber. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 20037, 'But Eliezer the son of Dodavah of Mareshah prophesied against Jehoshaphat, saying, &ldquo;Because you have allied yourself with Ahaziah, the Lord has destroyed your works.&rdquo; Then the ships were wrecked, so that they were not able to go to Tarshish. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21001, 'And Jehoshaphat rested with his fathers, and was buried with his fathers in the City of David. Then Jehoram his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21002, 'He had brothers, the sons of Jehoshaphat: Azariah, Jehiel, Zechariah, Azaryahu, Michael, and Shephatiah; all these were the sons of Jehoshaphat king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21003, 'Their father gave them great gifts of silver and gold and precious things, with fortified cities in Judah; but he gave the kingdom to Jehoram, because he was the firstborn. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21004, 'Now when Jehoram was established over the kingdom of his father, he strengthened himself and killed all his brothers with the sword, and also others of the princes of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21005, 'Jehoram was thirty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned eight years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21006, 'And he walked in the way of the kings of Israel, just as the house of Ahab had done, for he had the daughter of Ahab as a wife; and he did evil in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21007, 'Yet the Lord would not destroy the house of David, because of the covenant that He had made with David, and since He had promised to give a lamp to him and to his sons forever. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21008, 'In his days the Edomites revolted against Judah&rsquo;s authority, and made a king over themselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21009, 'So Jehoram went out with his officers, and all his chariots with him. And he rose by night and attacked the Edomites who had surrounded him and the captains of the chariots. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21010, 'Thus Edom has been in revolt against Judah&rsquo;s authority to this day. At that time Libnah revolted against his rule, because he had forsaken the Lord God of his fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21011, 'Moreover he made high places in the mountains of Judah, and caused the inhabitants of Jerusalem to commit harlotry, and led Judah astray. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21012, 'And a letter came to him from Elijah the prophet, saying, Thus says the Lord God of your father David: Because you have not walked in the ways of Jehoshaphat your father, or in the ways of Asa king of Judah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21013, 'but have walked in the way of the kings of Israel, and have made Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to play the harlot like the harlotry of the house of Ahab, and also have killed your brothers, those of your father&rsquo;s household, who were better than yourself, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21014, 'behold, the Lord will strike your people with a serious affliction &ndash; your children, your wives, and all your possessions; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21015, 'and you will become very sick with a disease of your intestines, until your intestines come out by reason of the sickness, day by day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21016, 'Moreover the Lord stirred up against Jehoram the spirit of the Philistines and the Arabians who were near the Ethiopians. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21017, 'And they came up into Judah and invaded it, and carried away all the possessions that were found in the king&rsquo;s house, and also his sons and his wives, so that there was not a son left to him except Jehoahaz, the youngest of his sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21018, 'After all this the Lord struck him in his intestines with an incurable disease. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21019, 'Then it happened in the course of time, after the end of two years, that his intestines came out because of his sickness; so he died in severe pain. And his people made no burning for him, like the burning for his fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 21020, 'He was thirty-two years old when he became king. He reigned in Jerusalem eight years and, to no one&rsquo;s sorrow, departed. However they buried him in the City of David, but not in the tombs of the kings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22001, 'Then the inhabitants of Jerusalem made Ahaziah his youngest son king in his place, for the raiders who came with the Arabians into the camp had killed all the older sons. So Ahaziah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, reigned. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22002, 'Ahaziah was forty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned one year in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Athaliah the granddaughter of Omri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22003, 'He also walked in the ways of the house of Ahab, for his mother advised him to do wickedly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22004, 'Therefore he did evil in the sight of the Lord, like the house of Ahab; for they were his counselors after the death of his father, to his destruction. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22005, 'He also followed their advice, and went with Jehoram the son of Ahab king of Israel to war against Hazael king of Syria at Ramoth Gilead; and the Syrians wounded Joram. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22006, 'Then he returned to Jezreel to recover from the wounds which he had received at Ramah, when he fought against Hazael king of Syria. And Azariah the son of Jehoram, king of Judah, went down to see Jehoram the son of Ahab in Jezreel, because he was sick. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22007, 'His going to Joram was God&rsquo;s occasion for Ahaziah&rsquo;s downfall; for when he arrived, he went out with Jehoram against Jehu the son of Nimshi, whom the Lord had anointed to cut off the house of Ahab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22008, 'And it happened, when Jehu was executing judgment on the house of Ahab, and found the princes of Judah and the sons of Ahaziah&rsquo;s brothers who served Ahaziah, that he killed them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22009, 'Then he searched for Ahaziah; and they caught him (he was hiding in Samaria), and brought him to Jehu. When they had killed him, they buried him, &ldquo;because,&rdquo; they said, &ldquo;he is the son of Jehoshaphat, who sought the Lord with all his heart.&rdquo; So the house of Ahaziah had no one to assume power over the kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22010, 'Now when Athaliah the mother of Ahaziah saw that her son was dead, she arose and destroyed all the royal heirs of the house of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22011, 'But Jehoshabeath, the daughter of the king, took Joash the son of Ahaziah, and stole him away from among the king&rsquo;s sons who were being murdered, and put him and his nurse in a bedroom. So Jehoshabeath, the daughter of King Jehoram, the wife of Jehoiada the priest (for she was the sister of Ahaziah), hid him from Athaliah so that she did not kill him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 22012, 'And he was hidden with them in the house of God for six years, while Athaliah reigned over the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23001, 'In the seventh year Jehoiada strengthened himself, and made a covenant with the captains of hundreds: Azariah the son of Jeroham, Ishmael the son of Jehohanan, Azariah the son of Obed, Maaseiah the son of Adaiah, and Elishaphat the son of Zichri. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23002, 'And they went throughout Judah and gathered the Levites from all the cities of Judah, and the chief fathers of Israel, and they came to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23003, 'Then all the assembly made a covenant with the king in the house of God. And he said to them, &ldquo;Behold, the king&rsquo;s son shall reign, as the Lord has said of the sons of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23004, 'This is what you shall do: One-third of you entering on the Sabbath, of the priests and the Levites, shall be keeping watch over the doors; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23005, 'one-third shall be at the king&rsquo;s house; and one-third at the Gate of the Foundation. All the people shall be in the courts of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23006, 'But let no one come into the house of the Lord except the priests and those of the Levites who serve. They may go in, for they are holy; but all the people shall keep the watch of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23007, 'And the Levites shall surround the king on all sides, every man with his weapons in his hand; and whoever comes into the house, let him be put to death. You are to be with the king when he comes in and when he goes out.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23008, 'So the Levites and all Judah did according to all that Jehoiada the priest commanded. And each man took his men who were to be on duty on the Sabbath, with those who were going off duty on the Sabbath; for Jehoiada the priest had not dismissed the divisions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23009, 'And Jehoiada the priest gave to the captains of hundreds the spears and the large and small shields which had belonged to King David, that were in the temple of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23010, 'Then he set all the people, every man with his weapon in his hand, from the right side of the temple to the left side of the temple, along by the altar and by the temple, all around the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23011, 'And they brought out the king&rsquo;s son, put the crown on him, gave him the Testimony, and made him king. Then Jehoiada and his sons anointed him, and said, &ldquo;Long live the king!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23012, 'Now when Athaliah heard the noise of the people running and praising the king, she came to the people in the temple of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23013, 'When she looked, there was the king standing by his pillar at the entrance; and the leaders and the trumpeters were by the king. All the people of the land were rejoicing and blowing trumpets, also the singers with musical instruments, and those who led in praise. So Athaliah tore her clothes and said, &ldquo;Treason! Treason!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23014, 'And Jehoiada the priest brought out the captains of hundreds who were set over the army, and said to them, &ldquo;Take her outside under guard, and slay with the sword whoever follows her.&rdquo; For the priest had said, &ldquo;Do not kill her in the house of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23015, 'So they seized her; and she went by way of the entrance of the Horse Gate into the king&rsquo;s house, and they killed her there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23016, 'Then Jehoiada made a covenant between himself, the people, and the king, that they should be the Lord&rsquo;s people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23017, 'And all the people went to the temple of Baal, and tore it down. They broke in pieces its altars and images, and killed Mattan the priest of Baal before the altars. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23018, 'Also Jehoiada appointed the oversight of the house of the Lord to the hand of the priests, the Levites, whom David had assigned in the house of the Lord, to offer the burnt offerings of the Lord, as it is written in the Law of Moses, with rejoicing and with singing, as it was established by David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23019, 'And he set the gatekeepers at the gates of the house of the Lord, so that no one who was in any way unclean should enter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23020, 'Then he took the captains of hundreds, the nobles, the governors of the people, and all the people of the land, and brought the king down from the house of the Lord; and they went through the Upper Gate to the king&rsquo;s house, and set the king on the throne of the kingdom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 23021, 'So all the people of the land rejoiced; and the city was quiet, for they had slain Athaliah with the sword. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24001, 'Joash was seven years old when he became king, and he reigned forty years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Zibiah of Beersheba. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24002, 'Joash did what was right in the sight of the Lord all the days of Jehoiada the priest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24003, 'And Jehoiada took two wives for him, and he had sons and daughters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24004, 'Now it happened after this that Joash set his heart on repairing the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24005, 'Then he gathered the priests and the Levites, and said to them, &ldquo;Go out to the cities of Judah, and gather from all Israel money to repair the house of your God from year to year, and see that you do it quickly.&rdquo; However the Levites did not do it quickly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24006, 'So the king called Jehoiada the chief priest, and said to him, &ldquo;Why have you not required the Levites to bring in from Judah and from Jerusalem the collection, according to the commandment of Moses the servant of the Lord and of the assembly of Israel, for the tabernacle of witness?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24007, 'For the sons of Athaliah, that wicked woman, had broken into the house of God, and had also presented all the dedicated things of the house of the Lord to the Baals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24008, 'Then at the king&rsquo;s command they made a chest, and set it outside at the gate of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24009, 'And they made a proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem to bring to the Lord the collection that Moses the servant of God had imposed on Israel in the wilderness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24010, 'Then all the leaders and all the people rejoiced, brought their contributions, and put them into the chest until all had given. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24011, 'So it was, at that time, when the chest was brought to the king&rsquo;s official by the hand of the Levites, and when they saw that there was much money, that the king&rsquo;s scribe and the high priest&rsquo;s officer came and emptied the chest, and took it and returned it to its place. Thus they did day by day, and gathered money in abundance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24012, 'The king and Jehoiada gave it to those who did the work of the service of the house of the Lord; and they hired masons and carpenters to repair the house of the Lord, and also those who worked in iron and bronze to restore the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24013, 'So the workmen labored, and the work was completed by them; they restored the house of God to its original condition and reinforced it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24014, 'When they had finished, they brought the rest of the money before the king and Jehoiada; they made from it articles for the house of the Lord, articles for serving and offering, spoons and vessels of gold and silver. And they offered burnt offerings in the house of the Lord continually all the days of Jehoiada. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24015, 'But Jehoiada grew old and was full of days, and he died; he was one hundred and thirty years old when he died. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24016, 'And they buried him in the City of David among the kings, because he had done good in Israel, both toward God and His house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24017, 'Now after the death of Jehoiada the leaders of Judah came and bowed down to the king. And the king listened to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24018, 'Therefore they left the house of the Lord God of their fathers, and served wooden images and idols; and wrath came upon Judah and Jerusalem because of their trespass. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24019, 'Yet He sent prophets to them, to bring them back to the Lord; and they testified against them, but they would not listen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24020, 'Then the Spirit of God came upon Zechariah the son of Jehoiada the priest, who stood above the people, and said to them, &ldquo;Thus says God: &lsquo;Why do you transgress the commandments of the Lord, so that you cannot prosper? Because you have forsaken the Lord, He also has forsaken you.&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24021, 'So they conspired against him, and at the command of the king they stoned him with stones in the court of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24022, 'Thus Joash the king did not remember the kindness which Jehoiada his father had done to him, but killed his son; and as he died, he said, &ldquo;The Lord look on it, and repay!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24023, 'So it happened in the spring of the year that the army of Syria came up against him; and they came to Judah and Jerusalem, and destroyed all the leaders of the people from among the people, and sent all their spoil to the king of Damascus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24024, 'For the army of the Syrians came with a small company of men; but the Lord delivered a very great army into their hand, because they had forsaken the Lord God of their fathers. So they executed judgment against Joash. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24025, 'And when they had withdrawn from him (for they left him severely wounded), his own servants conspired against him because of the blood of the sons of Jehoiada the priest, and killed him on his bed. So he died. And they buried him in the City of David, but they did not bury him in the tombs of the kings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24026, 'These are the ones who conspired against him: Zabad the son of Shimeath the Ammonitess, and Jehozabad the son of Shimrith the Moabitess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 24027, 'Now concerning his sons, and the many oracles about him, and the repairing of the house of God, indeed they are written in the annals of the book of the kings. Then Amaziah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25001, 'Amaziah was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jehoaddan of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25002, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, but not with a loyal heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25003, 'Now it happened, as soon as the kingdom was established for him, that he executed his servants who had murdered his father the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25004, 'However he did not execute their children, but did as it is written in the Law in the Book of Moses, where the Lord commanded, saying, &ldquo;The fathers shall not be put to death for their children, nor shall the children be put to death for their fathers; but a person shall die for his own sin.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25005, 'Moreover Amaziah gathered Judah together and set over them captains of thousands and captains of hundreds, according to their fathers&rsquo; houses, throughout all Judah and Benjamin; and he numbered them from twenty years old and above, and found them to be three hundred thousand choice men, able to go to war, who could handle spear and shield. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25006, 'He also hired one hundred thousand mighty men of valor from Israel for one hundred talents of silver. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25007, 'But a man of God came to him, saying, &ldquo;O king, do not let the army of Israel go with you, for the Lord is not with Israel &ndash; not with any of the children of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25008, 'But if you go, be gone! Be strong in battle! Even so, God shall make you fall before the enemy; for God has power to help and to overthrow.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25009, 'Then Amaziah said to the man of God, &ldquo;But what shall we do about the hundred talents which I have given to the troops of Israel?&rdquo; And the man of God answered, &ldquo;The Lord is able to give you much more than this.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25010, 'So Amaziah discharged the troops that had come to him from Ephraim, to go back home. Therefore their anger was greatly aroused against Judah, and they returned home in great anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25011, 'Then Amaziah strengthened himself, and leading his people, he went to the Valley of Salt and killed ten thousand of the people of Seir. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25012, 'Also the children of Judah took captive ten thousand alive, brought them to the top of the rock, and cast them down from the top of the rock, so that they all were dashed in pieces. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25013, 'But as for the soldiers of the army which Amaziah had discharged, so that they would not go with him to battle, they raided the cities of Judah from Samaria to Beth Horon, killed three thousand in them, and took much spoil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25014, 'Now it was so, after Amaziah came from the slaughter of the Edomites, that he brought the gods of the people of Seir, set them up to be his gods, and bowed down before them and burned incense to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25015, 'Therefore the anger of the Lord was aroused against Amaziah, and He sent him a prophet who said to him, &ldquo;Why have you sought the gods of the people, which could not rescue their own people from your hand?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25016, 'So it was, as he talked with him, that the king said to him, &ldquo;Have we made you the king&rsquo;s counselor? Cease! Why should you be killed?&rdquo; Then the prophet ceased, and said, &ldquo;I know that God has determined to destroy you, because you have done this and have not heeded my advice.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25017, 'Now Amaziah king of Judah asked advice and sent to Joash the son of Jehoahaz, the son of Jehu, king of Israel, saying, &ldquo;Come, let us face one another in battle.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25018, 'And Joash king of Israel sent to Amaziah king of Judah, saying, &ldquo;The thistle that was in Lebanon sent to the cedar that was in Lebanon, saying, &lsquo;Give your daughter to my son as wife&rsquo;; and a wild beast that was in Lebanon passed by and trampled the thistle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25019, 'Indeed you say that you have defeated the Edomites, and your heart is lifted up to boast. Stay at home now; why should you meddle with trouble, that you should fall &ndash; you and Judah with you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25020, 'But Amaziah would not heed, for it came from God, that He might give them into the hand of their enemies, because they sought the gods of Edom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25021, 'So Joash king of Israel went out; and he and Amaziah king of Judah faced one another at Beth Shemesh, which belongs to Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25022, 'And Judah was defeated by Israel, and every man fled to his tent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25023, 'Then Joash the king of Israel captured Amaziah king of Judah, the son of Joash, the son of Jehoahaz, at Beth Shemesh; and he brought him to Jerusalem, and broke down the wall of Jerusalem from the Gate of Ephraim to the Corner Gate &ndash; four hundred cubits. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25024, 'And he took all the gold and silver, all the articles that were found in the house of God with Obed-Edom, the treasures of the king&rsquo;s house, and hostages, and returned to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25025, 'Amaziah the son of Joash, king of Judah, lived fifteen years after the death of Joash the son of Jehoahaz, king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25026, 'Now the rest of the acts of Amaziah, from first to last, indeed are they not written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25027, 'After the time that Amaziah turned away from following the Lord, they made a conspiracy against him in Jerusalem, and he fled to Lachish; but they sent after him to Lachish and killed him there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 25028, 'Then they brought him on horses and buried him with his fathers in the City of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26001, 'Now all the people of Judah took Uzziah,* who was sixteen years old, and made him king instead of his father Amaziah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26002, 'He built Elath and restored it to Judah, after the king rested with his fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26003, 'Uzziah was sixteen years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-two years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jecholiah of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26004, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his father Amaziah had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26005, 'He sought God in the days of Zechariah, who had understanding in the visions of God; and as long as he sought the Lord, God made him prosper. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26006, 'Now he went out and made war against the Philistines, and broke down the wall of Gath, the wall of Jabneh, and the wall of Ashdod; and he built cities around Ashdod and among the Philistines. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26007, 'God helped him against the Philistines, against the Arabians who lived in Gur Baal, and against the Meunites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26008, 'Also the Ammonites brought tribute to Uzziah. His fame spread as far as the entrance of Egypt, for he became exceedingly strong. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26009, 'And Uzziah built towers in Jerusalem at the Corner Gate, at the Valley Gate, and at the corner buttress of the wall; then he fortified them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26010, 'Also he built towers in the desert. He dug many wells, for he had much livestock, both in the lowlands and in the plains; he also had farmers and vinedressers in the mountains and in Carmel, for he loved the soil. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26011, 'Moreover Uzziah had an army of fighting men who went out to war by companies, according to the number on their roll as prepared by Jeiel the scribe and Maaseiah the officer, under the hand of Hananiah, one of the king&rsquo;s captains. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26012, 'The total number of chief officers of the mighty men of valor was two thousand six hundred. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26013, 'And under their authority was an army of three hundred and seven thousand five hundred, that made war with mighty power, to help the king against the enemy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26014, 'Then Uzziah prepared for them, for the entire army, shields, spears, helmets, body armor, bows, and slings to cast stones. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26015, 'And he made devices in Jerusalem, invented by skillful men, to be on the towers and the corners, to shoot arrows and large stones. So his fame spread far and wide, for he was marvelously helped till he became strong. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26016, 'But when he was strong his heart was lifted up, to his destruction, for he transgressed against the Lord his God by entering the temple of the Lord to burn incense on the altar of incense. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26017, 'So Azariah the priest went in after him, and with him were eighty priests of the Lord &ndash; valiant men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26018, 'And they withstood King Uzziah, and said to him, &ldquo;It is not for you, Uzziah, to burn incense to the Lord, but for the priests, the sons of Aaron, who are consecrated to burn incense. Get out of the sanctuary, for you have trespassed! You shall have no honor from the Lord God.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26019, 'Then Uzziah became furious; and he had a censer in his hand to burn incense. And while he was angry with the priests, leprosy broke out on his forehead, before the priests in the house of the Lord, beside the incense altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26020, 'And Azariah the chief priest and all the priests looked at him, and there, on his forehead, he was leprous; so they thrust him out of that place. Indeed he also hurried to get out, because the Lord had struck him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26021, 'King Uzziah was a leper until the day of his death. He dwelt in an isolated house, because he was a leper; for he was cut off from the house of the Lord. Then Jotham his son was over the king&rsquo;s house, judging the people of the land. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26022, 'Now the rest of the acts of Uzziah, from first to last, the prophet Isaiah the son of Amoz wrote. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 26023, 'So Uzziah rested with his fathers, and they buried him with his fathers in the field of burial which belonged to the kings, for they said, &ldquo;He is a leper.&rdquo; Then Jotham his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27001, 'Jotham was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Jerushah* the daughter of Zadok. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27002, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his father Uzziah had done (although he did not enter the temple of the Lord). But still the people acted corruptly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27003, 'He built the Upper Gate of the house of the Lord, and he built extensively on the wall of Ophel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27004, 'Moreover he built cities in the mountains of Judah, and in the forests he built fortresses and towers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27005, 'He also fought with the king of the Ammonites and defeated them. And the people of Ammon gave him in that year one hundred talents of silver, ten thousand kors of wheat, and ten thousand of barley. The people of Ammon paid this to him in the second and third years also. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27006, 'So Jotham became mighty, because he prepared his ways before the Lord his God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27007, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jotham, and all his wars and his ways, indeed they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27008, 'He was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 27009, 'So Jotham rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the City of David. Then Ahaz his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28001, 'Ahaz was twenty years old when he became king, and he reigned sixteen years in Jerusalem; and he did not do what was right in the sight of the Lord, as his father David had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28002, 'For he walked in the ways of the kings of Israel, and made molded images for the Baals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28003, 'He burned incense in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom, and burned his children in the fire, according to the abominations of the nations whom the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28004, 'And he sacrificed and burned incense on the high places, on the hills, and under every green tree. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28005, 'Therefore the Lord his God delivered him into the hand of the king of Syria. They defeated him, and carried away a great multitude of them as captives, and brought them to Damascus. Then he was also delivered into the hand of the king of Israel, who defeated him with a great slaughter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28006, 'For Pekah the son of Remaliah killed one hundred and twenty thousand in Judah in one day, all valiant men, because they had forsaken the Lord God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28007, 'Zichri, a mighty man of Ephraim, killed Maaseiah the king&rsquo;s son, Azrikam the officer over the house, and Elkanah who was second to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28008, 'And the children of Israel carried away captive of their brethren two hundred thousand women, sons, and daughters; and they also took away much spoil from them, and brought the spoil to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28009, 'But a prophet of the Lord was there, whose name was Oded; and he went out before the army that came to Samaria, and said to them: &ldquo;Look, because the Lord God of your fathers was angry with Judah, He has delivered them into your hand; but you have killed them in a rage that reaches up to heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28010, 'And now you propose to force the children of Judah and Jerusalem to be your male and female slaves; but are you not also guilty before the Lord your God? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28011, 'Now hear me, therefore, and return the captives, whom you have taken captive from your brethren, for the fierce wrath of the Lord is upon you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28012, 'Then some of the heads of the children of Ephraim, Azariah the son of Johanan, Berechiah the son of Meshillemoth, Jehizkiah the son of Shallum, and Amasa the son of Hadlai, stood up against those who came from the war, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28013, 'and said to them, &ldquo;You shall not bring the captives here, for we already have offended the Lord. You intend to add to our sins and to our guilt; for our guilt is great, and there is fierce wrath against Israel.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28014, 'So the armed men left the captives and the spoil before the leaders and all the assembly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28015, 'Then the men who were designated by name rose up and took the captives, and from the spoil they clothed all who were naked among them, dressed them and gave them sandals, gave them food and drink, and anointed them; and they let all the feeble ones ride on donkeys. So they brought them to their brethren at Jericho, the city of palm trees. Then they returned to Samaria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28016, 'At the same time King Ahaz sent to the kings of Assyria to help him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28017, 'For again the Edomites had come, attacked Judah, and carried away captives. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28018, 'The Philistines also had invaded the cities of the lowland and of the South of Judah, and had taken Beth Shemesh, Aijalon, Gederoth, Sochoh with its villages, Timnah with its villages, and Gimzo with its villages; and they dwelt there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28019, 'For the Lord brought Judah low because of Ahaz king of Israel, for he had encouraged moral decline in Judah and had been continually unfaithful to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28020, 'Also Tiglath-Pileser king of Assyria came to him and distressed him, and did not assist him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28021, 'For Ahaz took part of the treasures from the house of the Lord, from the house of the king, and from the leaders, and he gave it to the king of Assyria; but he did not help him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28022, 'Now in the time of his distress King Ahaz became increasingly unfaithful to the Lord. This is that King Ahaz. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28023, 'For he sacrificed to the gods of Damascus which had defeated him, saying, &ldquo;Because the gods of the kings of Syria help them, I will sacrifice to them that they may help me.&rdquo; But they were the ruin of him and of all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28024, 'So Ahaz gathered the articles of the house of God, cut in pieces the articles of the house of God, shut up the doors of the house of the Lord, and made for himself altars in every corner of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28025, 'And in every single city of Judah he made high places to burn incense to other gods, and provoked to anger the Lord God of his fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28026, 'Now the rest of his acts and all his ways, from first to last, indeed they are written in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 28027, 'So Ahaz rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the city, in Jerusalem; but they did not bring him into the tombs of the kings of Israel. Then Hezekiah his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29001, 'Hezekiah became king when he was twenty-five years old, and he reigned twenty-nine years in Jerusalem. His mother&rsquo;s name was Abijah* the daughter of Zechariah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29002, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, according to all that his father David had done. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29003, 'In the first year of his reign, in the first month, he opened the doors of the house of the Lord and repaired them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29004, 'Then he brought in the priests and the Levites, and gathered them in the East Square, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29005, 'and said to them: &ldquo;Hear me, Levites! Now sanctify yourselves, sanctify the house of the Lord God of your fathers, and carry out the rubbish from the holy place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29006, 'For our fathers have trespassed and done evil in the eyes of the Lord our God; they have forsaken Him, have turned their faces away from the dwelling place of the Lord, and turned their backs on Him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29007, 'They have also shut up the doors of the vestibule, put out the lamps, and have not burned incense or offered burnt offerings in the holy place to the God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29008, 'Therefore the wrath of the Lord fell upon Judah and Jerusalem, and He has given them up to trouble, to desolation, and to jeering, as you see with your eyes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29009, 'For indeed, because of this our fathers have fallen by the sword; and our sons, our daughters, and our wives are in captivity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29010, 'Now it is in my heart to make a covenant with the Lord God of Israel, that His fierce wrath may turn away from us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29011, 'My sons, do not be negligent now, for the Lord has chosen you to stand before Him, to serve Him, and that you should minister to Him and burn incense.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29012, 'Then these Levites arose: Mahath the son of Amasai and Joel the son of Azariah, of the sons of the Kohathites; of the sons of Merari, Kish the son of Abdi and Azariah the son of Jehallelel; of the Gershonites, Joah the son of Zimmah and Eden the son of Joah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29013, 'of the sons of Elizaphan, Shimri and Jeiel; of the sons of Asaph, Zechariah and Mattaniah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29014, 'of the sons of Heman, Jehiel and Shimei; and of the sons of Jeduthun, Shemaiah and Uzziel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29015, 'And they gathered their brethren, sanctified themselves, and went according to the commandment of the king, at the words of the Lord, to cleanse the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29016, 'Then the priests went into the inner part of the house of the Lord to cleanse it, and brought out all the debris that they found in the temple of the Lord to the court of the house of the Lord. And the Levites took it out and carried it to the Brook Kidron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29017, 'Now they began to sanctify on the first day of the first month, and on the eighth day of the month they came to the vestibule of the Lord. Then they sanctified the house of the Lord in eight days, and on the sixteenth day of the first month they finished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29018, 'Then they went in to King Hezekiah and said, &ldquo;We have cleansed all the house of the Lord, the altar of burnt offerings with all its articles, and the table of the showbread with all its articles. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29019, 'Moreover all the articles which King Ahaz in his reign had cast aside in his transgression we have prepared and sanctified; and there they are, before the altar of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29020, 'Then King Hezekiah rose early, gathered the rulers of the city, and went up to the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29021, 'And they brought seven bulls, seven rams, seven lambs, and seven male goats for a sin offering for the kingdom, for the sanctuary, and for Judah. Then he commanded the priests, the sons of Aaron, to offer them on the altar of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29022, 'So they killed the bulls, and the priests received the blood and sprinkled it on the altar. Likewise they killed the rams and sprinkled the blood on the altar. They also killed the lambs and sprinkled the blood on the altar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29023, 'Then they brought out the male goats for the sin offering before the king and the assembly, and they laid their hands on them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29024, 'And the priests killed them; and they presented their blood on the altar as a sin offering to make an atonement for all Israel, for the king commanded that the burnt offering and the sin offering be made for all Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29025, 'And he stationed the Levites in the house of the Lord with cymbals, with stringed instruments, and with harps, according to the commandment of David, of Gad the king&rsquo;s seer, and of Nathan the prophet; for thus was the commandment of the Lord by his prophets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29026, 'The Levites stood with the instruments of David, and the priests with the trumpets. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29027, 'Then Hezekiah commanded them to offer the burnt offering on the altar. And when the burnt offering began, the song of the Lord also began, with the trumpets and with the instruments of David king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29028, 'So all the assembly worshiped, the singers sang, and the trumpeters sounded; all this continued until the burnt offering was finished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29029, 'And when they had finished offering, the king and all who were present with him bowed and worshiped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29030, 'Moreover King Hezekiah and the leaders commanded the Levites to sing praise to the Lord with the words of David and of Asaph the seer. So they sang praises with gladness, and they bowed their heads and worshiped. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29031, 'Then Hezekiah answered and said, &ldquo;Now that you have consecrated yourselves to the Lord, come near, and bring sacrifices and thank offerings into the house of the Lord.&rdquo; So the assembly brought in sacrifices and thank offerings, and as many as were of a willing heart brought burnt offerings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29032, 'And the number of the burnt offerings which the assembly brought was seventy bulls, one hundred rams, and two hundred lambs; all these were for a burnt offering to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29033, 'The consecrated things were six hundred bulls and three thousand sheep. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29034, 'But the priests were too few, so that they could not skin all the burnt offerings; therefore their brethren the Levites helped them until the work was ended and until the other priests had sanctified themselves, for the Levites were more diligent in sanctifying themselves than the priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29035, 'Also the burnt offerings were in abundance, with the fat of the peace offerings and with the drink offerings for every burnt offering. So the service of the house of the Lord was set in order. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 29036, 'Then Hezekiah and all the people rejoiced that God had prepared the people, since the events took place so suddenly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30001, 'And Hezekiah sent to all Israel and Judah, and also wrote letters to Ephraim and Manasseh, that they should come to the house of the Lord at Jerusalem, to keep the Passover to the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30002, 'For the king and his leaders and all the assembly in Jerusalem had agreed to keep the Passover in the second month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30003, 'For they could not keep it at the regular time, because a sufficient number of priests had not consecrated themselves, nor had the people gathered together at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30004, 'And the matter pleased the king and all the assembly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30005, 'So they resolved to make a proclamation throughout all Israel, from Beersheba to Dan, that they should come to keep the Passover to the Lord God of Israel at Jerusalem, since they had not done it for a long time in the prescribed manner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30006, 'Then the runners went throughout all Israel and Judah with the letters from the king and his leaders, and spoke according to the command of the king: &ldquo;Children of Israel, return to the Lord God of Abraham, Isaac, and Israel; then He will return to the remnant of you who have escaped from the hand of the kings of Assyria. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30007, 'And do not be like your fathers and your brethren, who trespassed against the Lord God of their fathers, so that He gave them up to desolation, as you see. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30008, 'Now do not be stiff-necked, as your fathers were, but yield yourselves to the Lord; and enter His sanctuary, which He has sanctified forever, and serve the Lord your God, that the fierceness of His wrath may turn away from you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30009, 'For if you return to the Lord, your brethren and your children will be treated with compassion by those who lead them captive, so that they may come back to this land; for the Lord your God is gracious and merciful, and will not turn His face from you if you return to Him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30010, 'So the runners passed from city to city through the country of Ephraim and Manasseh, as far as Zebulun; but they laughed at them and mocked them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30011, 'Nevertheless some from Asher, Manasseh, and Zebulun humbled themselves and came to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30012, 'Also the hand of God was on Judah to give them singleness of heart to obey the command of the king and the leaders, at the word of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30013, 'Now many people, a very great assembly, gathered at Jerusalem to keep the Feast of Unleavened Bread in the second month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30014, 'They arose and took away the altars that were in Jerusalem, and they took away all the incense altars and cast them into the Brook Kidron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30015, 'Then they slaughtered the Passover lambs on the fourteenth day of the second month. The priests and the Levites were ashamed, and sanctified themselves, and brought the burnt offerings to the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30016, 'They stood in their place according to their custom, according to the Law of Moses the man of God; the priests sprinkled the blood received from the hand of the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30017, 'For there were many in the assembly who had not sanctified themselves; therefore the Levites had charge of the slaughter of the Passover lambs for everyone who was not clean, to sanctify them to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30018, 'For a multitude of the people, many from Ephraim, Manasseh, Issachar, and Zebulun, had not cleansed themselves, yet they ate the Passover contrary to what was written. But Hezekiah prayed for them, saying, &ldquo;May the good Lord provide atonement for everyone ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30019, 'who prepares his heart to seek God, the Lord God of his fathers, though he is not cleansed according to the purification of the sanctuary.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30020, 'And the Lord listened to Hezekiah and healed the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30021, 'So the children of Israel who were present at Jerusalem kept the Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days with great gladness; and the Levites and the priests praised the Lord day by day, singing to the Lord, accompanied by loud instruments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30022, 'And Hezekiah gave encouragement to all the Levites who taught the good knowledge of the Lord; and they ate throughout the feast seven days, offering peace offerings and making confession to the Lord God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30023, 'Then the whole assembly agreed to keep the feast another seven days, and they kept it another seven days with gladness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30024, 'For Hezekiah king of Judah gave to the assembly a thousand bulls and seven thousand sheep, and the leaders gave to the assembly a thousand bulls and ten thousand sheep; and a great number of priests sanctified themselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30025, 'The whole assembly of Judah rejoiced, also the priests and Levites, all the assembly that came from Israel, the sojourners who came from the land of Israel, and those who dwelt in Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30026, 'So there was great joy in Jerusalem, for since the time of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel, there had been nothing like this in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 30027, 'Then the priests, the Levites, arose and blessed the people, and their voice was heard; and their prayer came up to His holy dwelling place, to heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31001, 'Now when all this was finished, all Israel who were present went out to the cities of Judah and broke the sacred pillars in pieces, cut down the wooden images, and threw down the high places and the altars &ndash; from all Judah, Benjamin, Ephraim, and Manasseh &ndash; until they had utterly destroyed them all. Then all the children of Israel returned to their own cities, every man to his possession. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31002, 'And Hezekiah appointed the divisions of the priests and the Levites according to their divisions, each man according to his service, the priests and Levites for burnt offerings and peace offerings, to serve, to give thanks, and to praise in the gates of the camp of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31003, 'The king also appointed a portion of his possessions for the burnt offerings: for the morning and evening burnt offerings, the burnt offerings for the Sabbaths and the New Moons and the set feasts, as it is written in the Law of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31004, 'Moreover he commanded the people who dwelt in Jerusalem to contribute support for the priests and the Levites, that they might devote themselves to the Law of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31005, 'As soon as the commandment was circulated, the children of Israel brought in abundance the firstfruits of grain and wine, oil and honey, and of all the produce of the field; and they brought in abundantly the tithe of everything. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31006, 'And the children of Israel and Judah, who dwelt in the cities of Judah, brought the tithe of oxen and sheep; also the tithe of holy things which were consecrated to the Lord their God they laid in heaps. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31007, 'In the third month they began laying them in heaps, and they finished in the seventh month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31008, 'And when Hezekiah and the leaders came and saw the heaps, they blessed the Lord and His people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31009, 'Then Hezekiah questioned the priests and the Levites concerning the heaps. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31010, 'And Azariah the chief priest, from the house of Zadok, answered him and said, &ldquo;Since the people began to bring the offerings into the house of the Lord, we have had enough to eat and have plenty left, for the Lord has blessed His people; and what is left is this great abundance.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31011, 'Now Hezekiah commanded them to prepare rooms in the house of the Lord, and they prepared them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31012, 'Then they faithfully brought in the offerings, the tithes, and the dedicated things; Cononiah the Levite had charge of them, and Shimei his brother was the next. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31013, 'Jehiel, Azaziah, Nahath, Asahel, Jerimoth, Jozabad, Eliel, Ismachiah, Mahath, and Benaiah were overseers under the hand of Cononiah and Shimei his brother, at the commandment of Hezekiah the king and Azariah the ruler of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31014, 'Kore the son of Imnah the Levite, the keeper of the East Gate, was over the freewill offerings to God, to distribute the offerings of the Lord and the most holy things. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31015, 'And under him were Eden, Miniamin, Jeshua, Shemaiah, Amariah, and Shecaniah, his faithful assistants in the cities of the priests, to distribute allotments to their brethren by divisions, to the great as well as the small. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31016, 'Besides those males from three years old and up who were written in the genealogy, they distributed to everyone who entered the house of the Lord his daily portion for the work of his service, by his division, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31017, 'and to the priests who were written in the genealogy according to their father&rsquo;s house, and to the Levites from twenty years old and up according to their work, by their divisions, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31018, 'and to all who were written in the genealogy &ndash; their little ones and their wives, their sons and daughters, the whole company of them &ndash; for in their faithfulness they sanctified themselves in holiness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31019, 'Also for the sons of Aaron the priests, who were in the fields of the common-lands of their cities, in every single city, there were men who were designated by name to distribute portions to all the males among the priests and to all who were listed by genealogies among the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31020, 'Thus Hezekiah did throughout all Judah, and he did what was good and right and true before the Lord his God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 31021, 'And in every work that he began in the service of the house of God, in the law and in the commandment, to seek his God, he did it with all his heart. So he prospered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32001, 'After these deeds of faithfulness, Sennacherib king of Assyria came and entered Judah; he encamped against the fortified cities, thinking to win them over to himself. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32002, 'And when Hezekiah saw that Sennacherib had come, and that his purpose was to make war against Jerusalem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32003, 'he consulted with his leaders and commanders stop the water from the springs which were outside the city; and they helped him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32004, 'Thus many people gathered together who stopped all the springs and the brook that ran through the land, saying, &ldquo;Why should the kings of Assyria come and find much water?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32005, 'And he strengthened himself, built up all the wall that was broken, raised it up to the towers, and built another wall outside; also he repaired the Millo in the City of David, and made weapons and shields in abundance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32006, 'Then he set military captains over the people, gathered them together to him in the open square of the city gate, and gave them encouragement, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32007, 'Be strong and courageous; do not be afraid nor dismayed before the king of Assyria, nor before all the multitude that is with him; for there are more with us than with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32008, 'With him is an arm of flesh; but with us is the Lord our God, to help us and to fight our battles. And the people were strengthened by the words of Hezekiah king of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32009, 'After this Sennacherib king of Assyria sent his servants to Jerusalem (but he and all the forces with him laid siege against Lachish), to Hezekiah king of Judah, and to all Judah who were in Jerusalem, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32010, 'Thus says Sennacherib king of Assyria: &lsquo;In what do you trust, that you remain under siege in Jerusalem? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32011, 'Does not Hezekiah persuade you to give yourselves over to die by famine and by thirst, saying, The Lord our God will deliver us from the hand of the king of Assyria? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32012, 'Has not the same Hezekiah taken away His high places and His altars, and commanded Judah and Jerusalem, saying, You shall worship before one altar and burn incense on it? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32013, 'Do you not know what I and my fathers have done to all the peoples of other lands? Were the gods of the nations of those lands in any way able to deliver their lands out of my hand? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32014, 'Who was there among all the gods of those nations that my fathers utterly destroyed that could deliver his people from my hand, that your God should be able to deliver you from my hand? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32015, 'Now therefore, do not let Hezekiah deceive you or persuade you like this, and do not believe him; for no god of any nation or kingdom was able to deliver his people from my hand or the hand of my fathers. How much less will your God deliver you from my hand?&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32016, 'Furthermore, his servants spoke against the Lord God and against His servant Hezekiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32017, 'He also wrote letters to revile the Lord God of Israel, and to speak against Him, saying, &ldquo;As the gods of the nations of other lands have not delivered their people from my hand, so the God of Hezekiah will not deliver His people from my hand.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32018, 'Then they called out with a loud voice in Hebrew to the people of Jerusalem who were on the wall, to frighten them and trouble them, that they might take the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32019, 'And they spoke against the God of Jerusalem, as against the gods of the people of the earth &ndash; the work of men&rsquo;s hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32020, 'Now because of this King Hezekiah and the prophet Isaiah, the son of Amoz, prayed and cried out to heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32021, 'Then the Lord sent an angel who cut down every mighty man of valor, leader, and captain in the camp of the king of Assyria. So he returned shamefaced to his own land. And when he had gone into the temple of his god, some of his own offspring struck him down with the sword there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32022, 'Thus the Lord saved Hezekiah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem from the hand of Sennacherib the king of Assyria, and from the hand of all others, and guided them on every side. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32023, 'And many brought gifts to the Lord at Jerusalem, and presents to Hezekiah king of Judah, so that he was exalted in the sight of all nations thereafter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32024, 'In those days Hezekiah was sick and near death, and he prayed to the Lord; and He spoke to him and gave him a sign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32025, 'But Hezekiah did not repay according to the favor shown him, for his heart was lifted up; therefore wrath was looming over him and over Judah and Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32026, 'Then Hezekiah humbled himself for the pride of his heart, he and the inhabitants of Jerusalem, so that the wrath of the Lord did not come upon them in the days of Hezekiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32027, 'Hezekiah had very great riches and honor. And he made himself treasuries for silver, for gold, for precious stones, for spices, for shields, and for all kinds of desirable items; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32028, 'storehouses for the harvest of grain, wine, and oil; and stalls for all kinds of livestock, and folds for flocks.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32029, 'Moreover he provided cities for himself, and possessions of flocks and herds in abundance; for God had given him very much property. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32030, 'This same Hezekiah also stopped the water outlet of Upper Gihon, and brought the water by tunnel to the west side of the City of David. Hezekiah prospered in all his works. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32031, 'However, regarding the ambassadors of the princes of Babylon, whom they sent to him to inquire about the wonder that was done in the land, God withdrew from him, in order to test him, that He might know all that was in his heart. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32032, 'Now the rest of the acts of Hezekiah, and his goodness, indeed they are written in the vision of Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, and in the book of the kings of Judah and Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 32033, 'So Hezekiah rested with his fathers, and they buried him in the upper tombs of the sons of David; and all Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem honored him at his death. Then Manasseh his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33001, 'Manasseh was twelve years old when he became king, and he reigned fifty-five years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33002, 'But he did evil in the sight of the Lord, according to the abominations of the nations whom the Lord had cast out before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33003, 'For he rebuilt the high places which Hezekiah his father had broken down; he raised up altars for the Baals, and made wooden images; and he worshiped all the host of heaven and served them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33004, 'He also built altars in the house of the Lord, of which the Lord had said, &ldquo;In Jerusalem shall My name be forever.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33005, 'And he built altars for all the host of heaven in the two courts of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33006, 'Also he caused his sons to pass through the fire in the Valley of the Son of Hinnom; he practiced soothsaying, used witchcraft and sorcery, and consulted mediums and spiritists. He did much evil in the sight of the Lord, to provoke Him to anger. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33007, 'He even set a carved image, the idol which he had made, in the house of God, of which God had said to David and to Solomon his son, &ldquo;In this house and in Jerusalem, which I have chosen out of all the tribes of Israel, I will put My name forever; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33008, 'and I will not again remove the foot of Israel from the land which I have appointed for your fathers &ndash; only if they are careful to do all that I have commanded them, according to the whole law and the statutes and the ordinances by the hand of Moses.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33009, 'So Manasseh seduced Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem to do more evil than the nations whom the Lord had destroyed before the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33010, 'And the Lord spoke to Manasseh and his people, but they would not listen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33011, 'Therefore the Lord brought upon them the captains of the army of the king of Assyria, who took Manasseh with hooks, bound him with bronze fetters, and carried him off to Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33012, 'Now when he was in affliction, he implored the Lord his God, and humbled himself greatly before the God of his fathers, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33013, 'and prayed to Him; and He received his entreaty, heard his supplication, and brought him back to Jerusalem into his kingdom. Then Manasseh knew that the Lord was God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33014, 'After this he built a wall outside the City of David on the west side of Gihon, in the valley, as far as the entrance of the Fish Gate; and it enclosed Ophel, and he raised it to a very great height. Then he put military captains in all the fortified cities of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33015, 'He took away the foreign gods and the idol from the house of the Lord, and all the altars that he had built in the mount of the house of the Lord and in Jerusalem; and he cast them out of the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33016, 'He also repaired the altar of the Lord, sacrificed peace offerings and thank offerings on it, and commanded Judah to serve the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33017, 'Nevertheless the people still sacrificed on the high places, but only to the Lord their God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33018, 'Now the rest of the acts of Manasseh, his prayer to his God, and the words of the seers who spoke to him in the name of the Lord God of Israel, indeed they are written in the book of the kings of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33019, 'Also his prayer and how God received his entreaty, and all his sin and trespass, and the sites where he built high places and set up wooden images and carved images, before he was humbled, indeed they are written among the sayings of Hozai.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33020, 'So Manasseh rested with his fathers, and they buried him in his own house. Then his son Amon reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33021, 'Amon was twenty-two years old when he became king, and he reigned two years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33022, 'But he did evil in the sight of the Lord, as his father Manasseh had done; for Amon sacrificed to all the carved images which his father Manasseh had made, and served them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33023, 'And he did not humble himself before the Lord, as his father Manasseh had humbled himself; but Amon trespassed more and more. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33024, 'Then his servants conspired against him, and killed him in his own house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 33025, 'But the people of the land executed all those who had conspired against King Amon. Then the people of the land made his son Josiah king in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34001, 'Josiah was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned thirty-one years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34002, 'And he did what was right in the sight of the Lord, and walked in the ways of his father David; he did not turn aside to the right hand or to the left. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34003, 'For in the eighth year of his reign, while he was still young, he began to seek the God of his father David; and in the twelfth year he began to purge Judah and Jerusalem of the high places, the wooden images, the carved images, and the molded images. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34004, 'They broke down the altars of the Baals in his presence, and the incense altars which were above them he cut down; and the wooden images, the carved images, and the molded images he broke in pieces, and made dust of them and scattered it on the graves of those who had sacrificed to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34005, 'He also burned the bones of the priests on their altars, and cleansed Judah and Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34006, 'And so he did in the cities of Manasseh, Ephraim, and Simeon, as far as Naphtali and all around, with axes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34007, 'When he had broken down the altars and the wooden images, had beaten the carved images into powder, and cut down all the incense altars throughout all the land of Israel, he returned to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34008, 'In the eighteenth year of his reign, when he had purged the land and the temple, he sent Shaphan the son of Azaliah, Maaseiah the governor of the city, and Joah the son of Joahaz the recorder, to repair the house of the Lord his God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34009, 'When they came to Hilkiah the high priest, they delivered the money that was brought into the house of God, which the Levites who kept the doors had gathered from the hand of Manasseh and Ephraim, from all the remnant of Israel, from all Judah and Benjamin, and which they had brought back to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34010, 'Then they put it in the hand of the foremen who had the oversight of the house of the Lord; and they gave it to the workmen who worked in the house of the Lord, to repair and restore the house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34011, 'They gave it to the craftsmen and builders to buy hewn stone and timber for beams, and to floor the houses which the kings of Judah had destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34012, 'And the men did the work faithfully. Their overseers were Jahath and Obadiah the Levites, of the sons of Merari, and Zechariah and Meshullam, of the sons of the Kohathites, to supervise. Others of the Levites, all of whom were skillful with instruments of music, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34013, 'were over the burden bearers and were overseers of all who did work in any kind of service. And some of the Levites were scribes, officers, and gatekeepers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34014, 'Now when they brought out the money that was brought into the house of the Lord, Hilkiah the priest found the Book of the Law of the Lord given by Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34015, 'Then Hilkiah answered and said to Shaphan the scribe, &ldquo;I have found the Book of the Law in the house of the Lord.&rdquo; And Hilkiah gave the book to Shaphan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34016, 'So Shaphan carried the book to the king, bringing the king word, saying, &ldquo;All that was committed to your servants they are doing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34017, 'And they have gathered the money that was found in the house of the Lord, and have delivered it into the hand of the overseers and the workmen.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34018, 'Then Shaphan the scribe told the king, saying, &ldquo;Hilkiah the priest has given me a book.&rdquo; And Shaphan read it before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34019, 'Thus it happened, when the king heard the words of the Law, that he tore his clothes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34020, 'Then the king commanded Hilkiah, Ahikam the son of Shaphan, Abdon the son of Micah, Shaphan the scribe, and Asaiah a servant of the king, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34021, 'Go, inquire of the Lord for me, and for those who are left in Israel and Judah, concerning the words of the book that is found; for great is the wrath of the Lord that is poured out on us, because our fathers have not kept the word of the Lord, to do according to all that is written in this book. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34022, 'So Hilkiah and those the king had appointed went to Huldah the prophetess, the wife of Shallum the son of Tokhath, the son of Hasrah, keeper of the wardrobe. (She dwelt in Jerusalem in the Second Quarter.) And they spoke to her to that effect. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34023, 'Then she answered them, &ldquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel, &lsquo;Tell the man who sent you to Me, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34024, 'Thus says the Lord: &lsquo;Behold, I will bring calamity on this place and on its inhabitants, all the curses that are written in the book which they have read before the king of Judah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34025, 'because they have forsaken Me and burned incense to other gods, that they might provoke Me to anger with all the works of their hands. Therefore My wrath will be poured out on this place, and not be quenched.&rsquo; &lsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34026, 'But as for the king of Judah, who sent you to inquire of the Lord, in this manner you shall speak to him, &lsquo;Thus says the Lord God of Israel: &ldquo;Concerning the words which you have heard &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34027, 'because your heart was tender, and you humbled yourself before God when you heard His words against this place and against its inhabitants, and you humbled yourself before Me, and you tore your clothes and wept before Me, I also have heard you,&rdquo; says the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34028, 'Surely I will gather you to your fathers, and you shall be gathered to your grave in peace; and your eyes shall not see all the calamity which I will bring on this place and its inhabitants.&rdquo; &lsquo; &ldquo; So they brought back word to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34029, 'Then the king sent and gathered all the elders of Judah and Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34030, 'The king went up to the house of the Lord, with all the men of Judah and the inhabitants of Jerusalem &ndash; the priests and the Levites, and all the people, great and small. And he read in their hearing all the words of the Book of the Covenant which had been found in the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34031, 'Then the king stood in his place and made a covenant before the Lord, to follow the Lord, and to keep His commandments and His testimonies and His statutes with all his heart and all his soul, to perform the words of the covenant that were written in this book. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34032, 'And he made all who were present in Jerusalem and Benjamin take a stand. So the inhabitants of Jerusalem did according to the covenant of God, the God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 34033, 'Thus Josiah removed all the abominations from all the country that belonged to the children of Israel, and made all who were present in Israel diligently serve the Lord their God. All his days they did not depart from following the Lord God of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35001, 'Now Josiah kept a Passover to the Lord in Jerusalem, and they slaughtered the Passover lambs on the fourteenth day of the first month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35002, 'And he set the priests in their duties and encouraged them for the service of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35003, 'Then he said to the Levites who taught all Israel, who were holy to the Lord: &ldquo;Put the holy ark in the house which Solomon the son of David, king of Israel, built. It shall no longer be a burden on your shoulders. Now serve the Lord your God and His people Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35004, 'Prepare yourselves according to your fathers&rsquo; houses, according to your divisions, following the written instruction of David king of Israel and the written instruction of Solomon his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35005, 'And stand in the holy place according to the divisions of the fathers&rsquo; houses of your brethren the lay people, and according to the division of the father&rsquo;s house of the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35006, 'So slaughter the Passover offerings, consecrate yourselves, and prepare them for your brethren, that they may do according to the word of the Lord by the hand of Moses.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35007, 'Then Josiah gave the lay people lambs and young goats from the flock, all for Passover offerings for all who were present, to the number of thirty thousand, as well as three thousand cattle; these were from the king&rsquo;s possessions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35008, 'And his leaders gave willingly to the people, to the priests, and to the Levites. Hilkiah, Zechariah, and Jehiel, rulers of the house of God, gave to the priests for the Passover offerings two thousand six hundred from the flock, and three hundred cattle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35009, 'Also Conaniah, his brothers Shemaiah and Nethanel, and Hashabiah and Jeiel and Jozabad, chief of the Levites, gave to the Levites for Passover offerings five thousand from the flock and five hundred cattle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35010, 'So the service was prepared, and the priests stood in their places, and the Levites in their divisions, according to the king&rsquo;s command. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35011, 'And they slaughtered the Passover offerings; and the priests sprinkled the blood with their hands, while the Levites skinned the animals. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35012, 'Then they removed the burnt offerings that they might give them to the divisions of the fathers&rsquo; houses of the lay people, to offer to the Lord, as it is written in the Book of Moses. And so they did with the cattle. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35013, 'Also they roasted the Passover offerings with fire according to the ordinance; but the other holy offerings they boiled in pots, in caldrons, and in pans, and divided them quickly among all the lay people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35014, 'Then afterward they prepared portions for themselves and for the priests, because the priests, the sons of Aaron, were busy in offering burnt offerings and fat until night; therefore the Levites prepared portions for themselves and for the priests, the sons of Aaron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35015, 'And the singers, the sons of Asaph, were in their places, according to the command of David, Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun the king&rsquo;s seer. Also the gatekeepers were at each gate; they did not have to leave their position, because their brethren the Levites prepared portions for them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35016, 'So all the service of the Lord was prepared the same day, to keep the Passover and to offer burnt offerings on the altar of the Lord, according to the command of King Josiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35017, 'And the children of Israel who were present kept the Passover at that time, and the Feast of Unleavened Bread for seven days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35018, 'There had been no Passover kept in Israel like that since the days of Samuel the prophet; and none of the kings of Israel had kept such a Passover as Josiah kept, with the priests and the Levites, all Judah and Israel who were present, and the inhabitants of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35019, 'In the eighteenth year of the reign of Josiah this Passover was kept. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35020, 'After all this, when Josiah had prepared the temple, Necho king of Egypt came up to fight against Carchemish by the Euphrates; and Josiah went out against him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35021, 'But he sent messengers to him, saying, &ldquo;What have I to do with you, king of Judah? I have not come against you this day, but against the house with which I have war; for God commanded me to make haste. Refrain from meddling with God, who is with me, lest He destroy you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35022, 'Nevertheless Josiah would not turn his face from him, but disguised himself so that he might fight with him, and did not heed the words of Necho from the mouth of God. So he came to fight in the Valley of Megiddo. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35023, 'And the archers shot King Josiah; and the king said to his servants, &ldquo;Take me away, for I am severely wounded.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35024, 'His servants therefore took him out of that chariot and put him in the second chariot that he had, and they brought him to Jerusalem. So he died, and was buried in one of the tombs of his fathers. And all Judah and Jerusalem mourned for Josiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35025, 'Jeremiah also lamented for Josiah. And to this day all the singing men and the singing women speak of Josiah in their lamentations. They made it a custom in Israel; and indeed they are written in the Laments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35026, 'Now the rest of the acts of Josiah and his goodness, according to what was written in the Law of the Lord, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 35027, 'and his deeds from first to last, indeed they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36001, 'Then the people of the land took Jehoahaz the son of Josiah, and made him king in his father&rsquo;s place in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36002, 'Jehoahaz was twenty-three years old when he became king, and he reigned three months in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36003, 'Now the king of Egypt deposed him at Jerusalem; and he imposed on the land a tribute of one hundred talents of silver and a talent of gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36004, 'Then the king of Egypt made Jehoahaz&rsquo;s brother Eliakim king over Judah and Jerusalem, and changed his name to Jehoiakim. And Necho took Jehoahaz his brother and carried him off to Egypt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36005, 'Jehoiakim was twenty-five years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. And he did evil in the sight of the Lord his God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36006, 'Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon came up against him, and bound him in bronze fetters to carry him off to Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36007, 'Nebuchadnezzar also carried off some of the articles from the house of the Lord to Babylon, and put them in his temple at Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36008, 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoiakim, the abominations which he did, and what was found against him, indeed they are written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah. Then Jehoiachin his son reigned in his place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36009, 'Jehoiachin was eight years old when he became king, and he reigned in Jerusalem three months and ten days. And he did evil in the sight of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36010, 'At the turn of the year King Nebuchadnezzar summoned him and took him to Babylon, with the costly articles from the house of the Lord, and made Zedekiah, Jehoiakim&rsquo;s brother, king over Judah and Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36011, 'Zedekiah was twenty-one years old when he became king, and he reigned eleven years in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36012, 'He did evil in the sight of the Lord his God, and did not humble himself before Jeremiah the prophet, who spoke from the mouth of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36013, 'And he also rebelled against King Nebuchadnezzar, who had made him swear an oath by God; but he stiffened his neck and hardened his heart against turning to the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36014, 'Moreover all the leaders of the priests and the people transgressed more and more, according to all the abominations of the nations, and defiled the house of the Lord which He had consecrated in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36015, 'And the Lord God of their fathers sent warnings to them by His messengers, rising up early and sending them, because He had compassion on His people and on His dwelling place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36016, 'But they mocked the messengers of God, despised His words, and scoffed at His prophets, until the wrath of the Lord arose against His people, till there was no remedy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36017, 'Therefore He brought against them the king of the Chaldeans, who killed their young men with the sword in the house of their sanctuary, and had no compassion on young man or virgin, on the aged or the weak; He gave them all into his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36018, 'And all the articles from the house of God, great and small, the treasures of the house of the Lord, and the treasures of the king and of his leaders, all these he took to Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36019, 'Then they burned the house of God, broke down the wall of Jerusalem, burned all its palaces with fire, and destroyed all its precious possessions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36020, 'And those who escaped from the sword he carried away to Babylon, where they became servants to him and his sons until the rule of the kingdom of Persia, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36021, 'to fulfill the word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah, until the land had enjoyed her Sabbaths. As long as she lay desolate she kept Sabbath, to fulfill seventy years. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36022, 'Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, that the word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah might be fulfilled, the Lord stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he made a proclamation throughout all his kingdom, and also put it in writing, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, '2Chr', 36023, 'Thus says Cyrus king of Persia: All the kingdoms of the earth the Lord God of heaven has given me. And He has commanded me to build Him a house at Jerusalem which is in Judah. Who is among you of all His people? May the Lord his God be with him, and let him go up! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1001, 'Now in the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, that the word of the Lord by the mouth of Jeremiah might be fulfilled, the Lord stirred up the spirit of Cyrus king of Persia, so that he made a proclamation throughout all his kingdom, and also put it in writing, saying, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1002, 'Thus says Cyrus king of Persia: All the kingdoms of the earth the Lord God of heaven has given me. And He has commanded me to build Him a house at Jerusalem which is in Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1003, 'Who is among you of all His people? May his God be with him, and let him go up to Jerusalem which is in Judah, and build the house of the Lord God of Israel (He is God), which is in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1004, 'And whoever is left in any place where he dwells, let the men of his place help him with silver and gold, with goods and livestock, besides the freewill offerings for the house of God which is in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1005, 'Then the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of Judah and Benjamin, and the priests and the Levites, with all whose spirits God had moved, arose to go up and build the house of the Lord which is in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1006, 'And all those who were around them encouraged them with articles of silver and gold, with goods and livestock, and with precious things, besides all that was willingly offered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1007, 'King Cyrus also brought out the articles of the house of the Lord, which Nebuchadnezzar had taken from Jerusalem and put in the temple of his gods; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1008, 'and Cyrus king of Persia brought them out by the hand of Mithredath the treasurer, and counted them out to Sheshbazzar the prince of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1009, 'This is the number of them: thirty gold platters, one thousand silver platters, twenty-nine knives, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1010, 'thirty gold basins, four hundred and ten silver basins of a similar kind, and one thousand other articles. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 1011, 'All the articles of gold and silver were five thousand four hundred. All these Sheshbazzar took with the captives who were brought from Babylon to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2001, 'Now* these are the people of the province who came back from the captivity, of those who had been carried away, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away to Babylon, and who returned to Jerusalem and Judah, everyone to his own city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2002, 'Those who came with Zerubbabel were Jeshua, Nehemiah, Seraiah, Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum, and Baanah. The number of the men of the people of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2003, 'the people of Parosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2004, 'the people of Shephatiah, three hundred and seventy-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2005, 'the people of Arah, seven hundred and seventy-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2006, 'the people of Pahath-Moab, of the people of Jeshua and Joab, two thousand eight hundred and twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2007, 'the people of Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2008, 'the people of Zattu, nine hundred and forty-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2009, 'the people of Zaccai, seven hundred and sixty; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2010, 'the people of Bani, six hundred and forty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2011, 'the people of Bebai, six hundred and twenty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2012, 'the people of Azgad, one thousand two hundred and twenty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2013, 'the people of Adonikam, six hundred and sixty-six; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2014, 'the people of Bigvai, two thousand and fifty-six; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2015, 'the people of Adin, four hundred and fifty-four; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2016, 'the people of Ater of Hezekiah, ninety-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2017, 'the people of Bezai, three hundred and twenty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2018, 'the people of Jorah, one hundred and twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2019, 'the people of Hashum, two hundred and twenty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2020, 'the people of Gibbar, ninety-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2021, 'the people of Bethlehem, one hundred and twenty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2022, 'the men of Netophah, fifty-six; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2023, 'the men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2024, 'the people of Azmaveth, forty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2025, 'the people of Kirjath Arim, Chephirah, and Beeroth, seven hundred and forty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2026, 'the people of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twenty-one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2027, 'the men of Michmas, one hundred and twenty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2028, 'the men of Bethel and Ai, two hundred and twenty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2029, 'the people of Nebo, fifty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2030, 'the people of Magbish, one hundred and fifty-six; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2031, 'the people of the other Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2032, 'the people of Harim, three hundred and twenty; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2033, 'the people of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, seven hundred and twenty-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2034, 'the people of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2035, 'the people of Senaah, three thousand six hundred and thirty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2036, 'The priests: the sons of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred and seventy-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2037, 'the sons of Immer, one thousand and fifty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2038, 'the sons of Pashhur, one thousand two hundred and forty-seven; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2039, 'the sons of Harim, one thousand and seventeen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2040, 'The Levites: the sons of Jeshua and Kadmiel, of the sons of Hodaviah, seventy-four. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2041, 'The singers: the sons of Asaph, one hundred and twenty-eight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2042, 'The sons of the gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, and the sons of Shobai, one hundred and thirty-nine in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2043, 'The Nethinim: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons of Tabbaoth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2044, 'the sons of Keros, the sons of Siaha, the sons of Padon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2045, 'the sons of Lebanah, the sons of Hagabah, the sons of Akkub, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2046, 'the sons of Hagab, the sons of Shalmai, the sons of Hanan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2047, 'the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar, the sons of Reaiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2048, 'the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda, the sons of Gazzam, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2049, 'the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah, the sons of Besai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2050, 'the sons of Asnah, the sons of Meunim, the sons of Nephusim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2051, 'the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2052, 'the sons of Bazluth, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2053, 'the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Tamah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2054, 'the sons of Neziah, and the sons of Hatipha. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2055, 'The sons of Solomon&rsquo;s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Sophereth, the sons of Peruda, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2056, 'the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2057, 'the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth of Zebaim, and the sons of Ami. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2058, 'All the Nethinim and the children of Solomon&rsquo;s servants were three hundred and ninety-two. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2059, 'And these were the ones who came up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Cherub, Addan, and Immer; but they could not identify their father&rsquo;s house or their genealogy, whether they were of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2060, 'the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, and the sons of Nekoda, six hundred and fifty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2061, 'and of the sons of the priests: the sons of Habaiah, the sons of Koz, and the sons of Barzillai, who took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and was called by their name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2062, 'These sought their listing among those who were registered by genealogy, but they were not found; therefore they were excluded from the priesthood as defiled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2063, 'And the governor said to them that they should not eat of the most holy things till a priest could consult with the Urim and Thummim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2064, 'The whole assembly together was forty-two thousand three hundred and sixty, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2065, 'besides their male and female servants, of whom there were seven thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two hundred men and women singers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2066, 'Their horses were seven hundred and thirty-six, their mules two hundred and forty-five, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2067, 'their camels four hundred and thirty-five, and their donkeys six thousand seven hundred and twenty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2068, 'Some of the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses, when they came to the house of the Lord which is in Jerusalem, offered freely for the house of God, to erect it in its place: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2069, 'According to their ability, they gave to the treasury for the work sixty-one thousand gold drachmas, five thousand minas of silver, and one hundred priestly garments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 2070, 'So the priests and the Levites, some of the people, the singers, the gatekeepers, and the Nethinim, dwelt in their cities, and all Israel in their cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3001, 'And when the seventh month had come, and the children of Israel were in the cities, the people gathered together as one man to Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3002, 'Then Jeshua the son of Jozadak and his brethren the priests, and Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel and his brethren, arose and built the altar of the God of Israel, to offer burnt offerings on it, as it is written in the Law of Moses the man of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3003, 'Though fear had come upon them because of the people of those countries, they set the altar on its bases; and they offered burnt offerings on it to the Lord, both the morning and evening burnt offerings. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3004, 'They also kept the Feast of Tabernacles, as it is written, and offered the daily burnt offerings in the number required by ordinance for each day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3005, 'Afterwards they offered the regular burnt offering, and those for New Moons and for all the appointed feasts of the Lord that were consecrated, and those of everyone who willingly offered a freewill offering to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3006, 'From the first day of the seventh month they began to offer burnt offerings to the Lord, although the foundation of the temple of the Lord had not been laid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3007, 'They also gave money to the masons and the carpenters, and food, drink, and oil to the people of Sidon and Tyre to bring cedar logs from Lebanon to the sea, to Joppa, according to the permission which they had from Cyrus king of Persia. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3008, 'Now in the second month of the second year of their coming to the house of God at Jerusalem, Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and the rest of their brethren the priests and the Levites, and all those who had come out of the captivity to Jerusalem, began work and appointed the Levites from twenty years old and above to oversee the work of the house of the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3009, 'Then Jeshua with his sons and brothers, Kadmiel with his sons, and the sons of Judah, arose as one to oversee those working on the house of God: the sons of Henadad with their sons and their brethren the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3010, 'When the builders laid the foundation of the temple of the Lord, the priests stood in their apparel with trumpets, and the Levites, the sons of Asaph, with cymbals, to praise the Lord, according to the ordinance of David king of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3011, 'And they sang responsively, praising and giving thanks to the Lord: &ldquo;For He is good, For His mercy endures forever toward Israel.&rdquo; Then all the people shouted with a great shout, when they praised the Lord, because the foundation of the house of the Lord was laid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3012, 'But many of the priests and Levites and heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses, old men who had seen the first temple, wept with a loud voice when the foundation of this temple was laid before their eyes. Yet many shouted aloud for joy, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 3013, 'so that the people could not discern the noise of the shout of joy from the noise of the weeping of the people, for the people shouted with a loud shout, and the sound was heard afar off. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4001, 'Now when the adversaries of Judah and Benjamin heard that the descendants of the captivity were building the temple of the Lord God of Israel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4002, 'they came to Zerubbabel and the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses, and said to them, &ldquo;Let us build with you, for we seek your God as you do; and we have sacrificed to Him since the days of Esarhaddon king of Assyria, who brought us here.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4003, 'But Zerubbabel and Jeshua and the rest of the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of Israel said to them, &ldquo;You may do nothing with us to build a house for our God; but we alone will build to the Lord God of Israel, as King Cyrus the king of Persia has commanded us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4004, 'Then the people of the land tried to discourage the people of Judah. They troubled them in building, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4005, 'and hired counselors against them to frustrate their purpose all the days of Cyrus king of Persia, even until the reign of Darius king of Persia. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4006, 'In the reign of Ahasuerus, in the beginning of his reign, they wrote an accusation against the inhabitants of Judah and Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4007, 'In the days of Artaxerxes also, Bishlam, Mithredath, Tabel, and the rest of their companions wrote to Artaxerxes king of Persia; and the letter was written in Aramaic script, and translated into the Aramaic language. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4008, 'Rehum the commander and Shimshai the scribe wrote a letter against Jerusalem to King Artaxerxes in this fashion: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4009, 'From Rehum the commander, Shimshai the scribe, and the rest of their companions &ndash; representatives of the Dinaites, the Apharsathchites, the Tarpelites, the people of Persia and Erech and Babylon and Shushan, the Dehavites, the Elamites, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4010, 'and the rest of the nations whom the great and noble Osnapper took captive and settled in the cities of Samaria and the remainder beyond the River* &ndash; and so forth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4011, '(This is a copy of the letter that they sent him) To King Artaxerxes from your servants, the men of the region beyond the River, and so forth: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4012, 'Let it be known to the king that the Jews who came up from you have come to us at Jerusalem, and are building the rebellious and evil city, and are finishing its walls and repairing the foundations. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4013, 'Let it now be known to the king that, if this city is built and the walls completed, they will not pay tax, tribute, or custom, and the king&rsquo;s treasury will be diminished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4014, 'Now because we receive support from the palace, it was not proper for us to see the king&rsquo;s dishonor; therefore we have sent and informed the king, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4015, 'that search may be made in the book of the records of your fathers. And you will find in the book of the records and know that this city is a rebellious city, harmful to kings and provinces, and that they have incited sedition within the city in former times, for which cause this city was destroyed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4016, 'We inform the king that if this city is rebuilt and its walls are completed, the result will be that you will have no dominion beyond the River. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4017, 'The king sent an answer: To Rehum the commander, to Shimshai the scribe, to the rest of their companions who dwell in Samaria, and to the remainder beyond the River: Peace, and so forth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4018, 'The letter which you sent to us has been clearly read before me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4019, 'And I gave the command, and a search has been made, and it was found that this city in former times has revolted against kings, and rebellion and sedition have been fostered in it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4020, 'There have also been mighty kings over Jerusalem, who have ruled over all the region beyond the River; and tax, tribute, and custom were paid to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4021, 'Now give the command to make these men cease, that this city may not be built until the command is given by me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4022, 'Take heed now that you do not fail to do this. Why should damage increase to the hurt of the kings? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4023, 'Now when the copy of King Artaxerxes&rsquo; letter was read before Rehum, Shimshai the scribe, and their companions, they went up in haste to Jerusalem against the Jews, and by force of arms made them cease. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 4024, 'Thus the work of the house of God which is at Jerusalem ceased, and it was discontinued until the second year of the reign of Darius king of Persia. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5001, 'Then the prophet Haggai and Zechariah the son of Iddo, prophets, prophesied to the Jews who were in Judah and Jerusalem, in the name of the God of Israel, who was over them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5002, 'So Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel and Jeshua the son of Jozadak rose up and began to build the house of God which is in Jerusalem; and the prophets of God were with them, helping them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5003, 'At the same time Tattenai the governor of the region beyond the River and Shethar-Boznai and their companions came to them and spoke thus to them: &ldquo;Who has commanded you to build this temple and finish this wall?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5004, 'Then, accordingly, we told them the names of the men who were constructing this building. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5005, 'But the eye of their God was upon the elders of the Jews, so that they could not make them cease till a report could go to Darius. Then a written answer was returned concerning this matter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5006, 'This is a copy of the letter that Tattenai sent: The governor of the region beyond the River, and Shethar-Boznai, and his companions, the Persians who were in the region beyond the River, to Darius the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5007, '(They sent a letter to him, in which was written thus) To Darius the king: All peace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5008, 'Let it be known to the king that we went into the province of Judea, to the temple of the great God, which is being built with heavy stones, and timber is being laid in the walls; and this work goes on diligently and prospers in their hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5009, 'Then we asked those elders, and spoke thus to them: &ldquo;Who commanded you to build this temple and to finish these walls?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5010, 'We also asked them their names to inform you, that we might write the names of the men who were chief among them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5011, 'And thus they returned us an answer, saying: &ldquo;We are the servants of the God of heaven and earth, and we are rebuilding the temple that was built many years ago, which a great king of Israel built and completed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5012, 'But because our fathers provoked the God of heaven to wrath, He gave them into the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, the Chaldean, who destroyed this temple and carried the people away to Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5013, 'However, in the first year of Cyrus king of Babylon, King Cyrus issued a decree to build this house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5014, 'Also, the gold and silver articles of the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar had taken from the temple that was in Jerusalem and carried into the temple of Babylon &ndash; those King Cyrus took from the temple of Babylon, and they were given to one named Sheshbazzar, whom he had made governor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5015, 'And he said to him, &lsquo;Take these articles; go, carry them to the temple site that is in Jerusalem, and let the house of God be rebuilt on its former site.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5016, 'Then the same Sheshbazzar came and laid the foundation of the house of God which is in Jerusalem; but from that time even until now it has been under construction, and it is not finished.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 5017, 'Now therefore, if it seems good to the king, let a search be made in the king&rsquo;s treasure house, which is there in Babylon, whether it is so that a decree was issued by King Cyrus to build this house of God at Jerusalem, and let the king send us his pleasure concerning this matter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6001, 'Then King Darius issued a decree, and a search was made in the archives,* where the treasures were stored in Babylon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6002, 'And at Achmetha, in the palace that is in the province of Media, a scroll was found, and in it a record was written thus: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6003, 'In the first year of King Cyrus, King Cyrus issued a decree concerning the house of God at Jerusalem: &ldquo;Let the house be rebuilt, the place where they offered sacrifices; and let the foundations of it be firmly laid, its height sixty cubits and its width sixty cubits, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6004, 'with three rows of heavy stones and one row of new timber. Let the expenses be paid from the king&rsquo;s treasury. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6005, 'Also let the gold and silver articles of the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar took from the temple which is in Jerusalem and brought to Babylon, be restored and taken back to the temple which is in Jerusalem, each to its place; and deposit them in the house of God&rdquo; &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6006, 'Now therefore, Tattenai, governor of the region beyond the River, and Shethar-Boznai, and your companions the Persians who are beyond the River, keep yourselves far from there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6007, 'Let the work of this house of God alone; let the governor of the Jews and the elders of the Jews build this house of God on its site. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6008, 'Moreover I issue a decree as to what you shall do for the elders of these Jews, for the building of this house of God: Let the cost be paid at the king&rsquo;s expense from taxes on the region beyond the River; this is to be given immediately to these men, so that they are not hindered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6009, 'And whatever they need &ndash; young bulls, rams, and lambs for the burnt offerings of the God of heaven, wheat, salt, wine, and oil, according to the request of the priests who are in Jerusalem &ndash; let it be given them day by day without fail, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6010, 'that they may offer sacrifices of sweet aroma to the God of heaven, and pray for the life of the king and his sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6011, 'Also I issue a decree that whoever alters this edict, let a timber be pulled from his house and erected, and let him be hanged on it; and let his house be made a refuse heap because of this. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6012, 'And may the God who causes His name to dwell there destroy any king or people who put their hand to alter it, or to destroy this house of God which is in Jerusalem. I Darius issue a decree; let it be done diligently. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6013, 'Then Tattenai, governor of the region beyond the River, Shethar-Boznai, and their companions diligently did according to what King Darius had sent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6014, 'So the elders of the Jews built, and they prospered through the prophesying of Haggai the prophet and Zechariah the son of Iddo. And they built and finished it, according to the commandment of the God of Israel, and according to the command of Cyrus, Darius, and Artaxerxes king of Persia. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6015, 'Now the temple was finished on the third day of the month of Adar, which was in the sixth year of the reign of King Darius. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6016, 'Then the children of Israel, the priests and the Levites and the rest of the descendants of the captivity, celebrated the dedication of this house of God with joy. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6017, 'And they offered sacrifices at the dedication of this house of God, one hundred bulls, two hundred rams, four hundred lambs, and as a sin offering for all Israel twelve male goats, according to the number of the tribes of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6018, 'They assigned the priests to their divisions and the Levites to their divisions, over the service of God in Jerusalem, as it is written in the Book of Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6019, 'And the descendants of the captivity kept the Passover on the fourteenth day of the first month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6020, 'For the priests and the Levites had purified themselves; all of them were ritually clean. And they slaughtered the Passover lambs for all the descendants of the captivity, for their brethren the priests, and for themselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6021, 'Then the children of Israel who had returned from the captivity ate together with all who had separated themselves from the filth of the nations of the land in order to seek the Lord God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 6022, 'And they kept the Feast of Unleavened Bread seven days with joy; for the Lord made them joyful, and turned the heart of the king of Assyria toward them, to strengthen their hands in the work of the house of God, the God of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7001, 'Now after these things, in the reign of Artaxerxes king of Persia, Ezra the son of Seraiah, the son of Azariah, the son of Hilkiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7002, 'the son of Shallum, the son of Zadok, the son of Ahitub, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7003, 'the son of Amariah, the son of Azariah, the son of Meraioth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7004, 'the son of Zerahiah, the son of Uzzi, the son of Bukki, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7005, 'the son of Abishua, the son of Phinehas, the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the chief priest &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7006, 'this Ezra came up from Babylon; and he was a skilled scribe in the Law of Moses, which the Lord God of Israel had given. The king granted him all his request, according to the hand of the Lord his God upon him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7007, 'Some of the children of Israel, the priests, the Levites, the singers, the gatekeepers, and the Nethinim came up to Jerusalem in the seventh year of King Artaxerxes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7008, 'And Ezra came to Jerusalem in the fifth month, which was in the seventh year of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7009, 'On the first day of the first month he began his journey from Babylon, and on the first day of the fifth month he came to Jerusalem, according to the good hand of his God upon him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7010, 'For Ezra had prepared his heart to seek the Law of the Lord, and to do it, and to teach statutes and ordinances in Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7011, 'This is a copy of the letter that King Artaxerxes gave Ezra the priest, the scribe, expert in the words of the commandments of the Lord, and of His statutes to Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7012, 'Artaxerxes, king of kings, To Ezra the priest, a scribe of the Law of the God of heaven: Perfect peace, and so forth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7013, 'I issue a decree that all those of the people of Israel and the priests and Levites in my realm, who volunteer to go up to Jerusalem, may go with you. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7014, 'And whereas you are being sent by the king and his seven counselors to inquire concerning Judah and Jerusalem, with regard to the Law of your God which is in your hand; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7015, 'and whereas you are to carry the silver and gold which the king and his counselors have freely offered to the God of Israel, whose dwelling is in Jerusalem; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7016, 'and whereas all the silver and gold that you may find in all the province of Babylon, along with the freewill offering of the people and the priests, are to be freely offered for the house of their God in Jerusalem &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7017, 'now therefore, be careful to buy with this money bulls, rams, and lambs, with their grain offerings and their drink offerings, and offer them on the altar of the house of your God in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7018, 'And whatever seems good to you and your brethren to do with the rest of the silver and the gold, do it according to the will of your God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7019, 'Also the articles that are given to you for the service of the house of your God, deliver in full before the God of Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7020, 'And whatever more may be needed for the house of your God, which you may have occasion to provide, pay for it from the king&rsquo;s treasury. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7021, 'And I, even I, Artaxerxes the king, issue a decree to all the treasurers who are in the region beyond the River, that whatever Ezra the priest, the scribe of the Law of the God of heaven, may require of you, let it be done diligently, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7022, 'up to one hundred talents of silver, one hundred kors of wheat, one hundred baths of wine, one hundred baths of oil, and salt without prescribed limit. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7023, 'Whatever is commanded by the God of heaven, let it diligently be done for the house of the God of heaven. For why should there be wrath against the realm of the king and his sons? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7024, 'Also we inform you that it shall not be lawful to impose tax, tribute, or custom on any of the priests, Levites, singers, gatekeepers, Nethinim, or servants of this house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7025, 'And you, Ezra, according to your God-given wisdom, set magistrates and judges who may judge all the people who are in the region beyond the River, all such as know the laws of your God; and teach those who do not know them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7026, 'Whoever will not observe the law of your God and the law of the king, let judgment be executed speedily on him, whether it be death, or banishment, or confiscation of goods, or imprisonment. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7027, 'Blessed be the Lord God of our fathers, who has put such a thing as this in the king&rsquo;s heart, to beautify the house of the Lord which is in Jerusalem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 7028, 'and has extended mercy to me before the king and his counselors, and before all the king&rsquo;s mighty princes.So I was encouraged, as the hand of the Lord my God was upon me; and I gathered leading men of Israel to go up with me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8001, 'These are the heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses, and this is the genealogy of those who went up with me from Babylon, in the reign of King Artaxerxes: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8002, 'of the sons of Phinehas, Gershom; of the sons of Ithamar, Daniel; of the sons of David, Hattush; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8003, 'of the sons of Shecaniah, of the sons of Parosh, Zechariah; and registered with him were one hundred and fifty males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8004, 'of the sons of Pahath-Moab, Eliehoenai the son of Zerahiah, and with him two hundred males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8005, 'of the sons of Shechaniah, Ben-Jahaziel, and with him three hundred males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8006, 'of the sons of Adin, Ebed the son of Jonathan, and with him fifty males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8007, 'of the sons of Elam, Jeshaiah the son of Athaliah, and with him seventy males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8008, 'of the sons of Shephatiah, Zebadiah the son of Michael, and with him eighty males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8009, 'of the sons of Joab, Obadiah the son of Jehiel, and with him two hundred and eighteen males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8010, 'of the sons of Shelomith, Ben-Josiphiah, and with him one hundred and sixty males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8011, 'of the sons of Bebai, Zechariah the son of Bebai, and with him twenty-eight males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8012, 'of the sons of Azgad, Johanan the son of Hakkatan, and with him one hundred and ten males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8013, 'of the last sons of Adonikam, whose names are these &ndash; Eliphelet, Jeiel, and Shemaiah &ndash; and with them sixty males; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8014, 'also of the sons of Bigvai, Uthai and Zabbud, and with them seventy males. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8015, 'Now I gathered them by the river that flows to Ahava, and we camped there three days. And I looked among the people and the priests, and found none of the sons of Levi there. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8016, 'Then I sent for Eliezer, Ariel, Shemaiah, Elnathan, Jarib, Elnathan, Nathan, Zechariah, and Meshullam, leaders; also for Joiarib and Elnathan, men of understanding. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8017, 'And I gave them a command for Iddo the chief man at the place Casiphia, and I told them what they should say to Iddo and his brethren the Nethinim at the place Casiphia &ndash; that they should bring us servants for the house of our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8018, 'Then, by the good hand of our God upon us, they brought us a man of understanding, of the sons of Mahli the son of Levi, the son of Israel, namely Sherebiah, with his sons and brothers, eighteen men; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8019, 'and Hashabiah, and with him Jeshaiah of the sons of Merari, his brothers and their sons, twenty men; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8020, 'also of the Nethinim, whom David and the leaders had appointed for the service of the Levites, two hundred and twenty Nethinim. All of them were designated by name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8021, 'Then I proclaimed a fast there at the river of Ahava, that we might humble ourselves before our God, to seek from Him the right way for us and our little ones and all our possessions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8022, 'For I was ashamed to request of the king an escort of soldiers and horsemen to help us against the enemy on the road, because we had spoken to the king, saying, &ldquo;The hand of our God is upon all those for good who seek Him, but His power and His wrath are against all those who forsake Him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8023, 'So we fasted and entreated our God for this, and He answered our prayer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8024, 'And I separated twelve of the leaders of the priests &ndash; Sherebiah, Hashabiah, and ten of their brethren with them &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8025, 'and weighed out to them the silver, the gold, and the articles, the offering for the house of our God which the king and his counselors and his princes, and all Israel who were present, had offered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8026, 'I weighed into their hand six hundred and fifty talents of silver, silver articles weighing one hundred talents, one hundred talents of gold, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8027, 'twenty gold basins worth a thousand drachmas, and two vessels of fine polished bronze, precious as gold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8028, 'And I said to them, &ldquo;You are holy to the Lord; the articles are holy also; and the silver and the gold are a freewill offering to the Lord God of your fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8029, 'Watch and keep them until you weigh them before the leaders of the priests and the Levites and heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of Israel in Jerusalem, in the chambers of the house of the Lord.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8030, 'So the priests and the Levites received the silver and the gold and the articles by weight, to bring them to Jerusalem to the house of our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8031, 'Then we departed from the river of Ahava on the twelfth day of the first month, to go to Jerusalem. And the hand of our God was upon us, and He delivered us from the hand of the enemy and from ambush along the road. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8032, 'So we came to Jerusalem, and stayed there three days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8033, 'Now on the fourth day the silver and the gold and the articles were weighed in the house of our God by the hand of Meremoth the son of Uriah the priest, and with him was Eleazar the son of Phinehas; with them were the Levites, Jozabad the son of Jeshua and Noadiah the son of Binnui, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8034, 'with the number and weight of everything. All the weight was written down at that time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8035, 'The children of those who had been carried away captive, who had come from the captivity, offered burnt offerings to the God of Israel: twelve bulls for all Israel, ninety-six rams, seventy-seven lambs, and twelve male goats as a sin offering. All this was a burnt offering to the Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 8036, 'And they delivered the king&rsquo;s orders to the king&rsquo;s satraps and the governors in the region beyond the River. So they gave support to the people and the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9001, 'When these things were done, the leaders came to me, saying, &ldquo;The people of Israel and the priests and the Levites have not separated themselves from the peoples of the lands, with respect to the abominations of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Jebusites, the Ammonites, the Moabites, the Egyptians, and the Amorites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9002, 'For they have taken some of their daughters as wives for themselves and their sons, so that the holy seed is mixed with the peoples of those lands. Indeed, the hand of the leaders and rulers has been foremost in this trespass.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9003, 'So when I heard this thing, I tore my garment and my robe, and plucked out some of the hair of my head and beard, and sat down astonished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9004, 'Then everyone who trembled at the words of the God of Israel assembled to me, because of the transgression of those who had been carried away captive, and I sat astonished until the evening sacrifice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9005, 'At the evening sacrifice I arose from my fasting; and having torn my garment and my robe, I fell on my knees and spread out my hands to the Lord my God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9006, 'And I said: &ldquo;O my God, I am too ashamed and humiliated to lift up my face to You, my God; for our iniquities have risen higher than our heads, and our guilt has grown up to the heavens. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9007, 'Since the days of our fathers to this day we have been very guilty, and for our iniquities we, our kings, and our priests have been delivered into the hand of the kings of the lands, to the sword, to captivity, to plunder, and to humiliation, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9008, 'And now for a little while grace has been shown from the Lord our God, to leave us a remnant to escape, and to give us a peg in His holy place, that our God may enlighten our eyes and give us a measure of revival in our bondage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9009, 'For we were slaves. Yet our God did not forsake us in our bondage; but He extended mercy to us in the sight of the kings of Persia, to revive us, to repair the house of our God, to rebuild its ruins, and to give us a wall in Judah and Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9010, 'And now, O our God, what shall we say after this? For we have forsaken Your commandments, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9011, 'which You commanded by Your servants the prophets, saying, &lsquo;The land which you are entering to possess is an unclean land, with the uncleanness of the peoples of the lands, with their abominations which have filled it from one end to another with their impurity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9012, 'Now therefore, do not give your daughters as wives for their sons, nor take their daughters to your sons; and never seek their peace or prosperity, that you may be strong and eat the good of the land, and leave it as an inheritance to your children forever.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9013, 'And after all that has come upon us for our evil deeds and for our great guilt, since You our God have punished us less than our iniquities deserve, and have given us such deliverance as this, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9014, 'should we again break Your commandments, and join in marriage with the people committing these abominations? Would You not be angry with us until You had consumed us, so that there would be no remnant or survivor? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 9015, 'O Lord God of Israel, You are righteous, for we are left as a remnant, as it is this day. Here we are before You, in our guilt, though no one can stand before You because of this!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10001, 'Now while Ezra was praying, and while he was confessing, weeping, and bowing down before the house of God, a very large assembly of men, women, and children gathered to him from Israel; for the people wept very bitterly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10002, 'And Shechaniah the son of Jehiel, one of the sons of Elam, spoke up and said to Ezra, &ldquo;We have trespassed against our God, and have taken pagan wives from the peoples of the land; yet now there is hope in Israel in spite of this. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10003, 'Now therefore, let us make a covenant with our God to put away all these wives and those who have been born to them, according to the advice of my master and of those who tremble at the commandment of our God; and let it be done according to the law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10004, 'Arise, for this matter is your responsibility. We also are with you. Be of good courage, and do it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10005, 'Then Ezra arose, and made the leaders of the priests, the Levites, and all Israel swear an oath that they would do according to this word. So they swore an oath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10006, 'Then Ezra rose up from before the house of God, and went into the chamber of Jehohanan the son of Eliashib; and when he came there, he ate no bread and drank no water, for he mourned because of the guilt of those from the captivity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10007, 'And they issued a proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem to all the descendants of the captivity, that they must gather at Jerusalem, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10008, 'and that whoever would not come within three days, according to the instructions of the leaders and elders, all his property would be confiscated, and he himself would be separated from the assembly of those from the captivity. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10009, 'So all the men of Judah and Benjamin gathered at Jerusalem within three days. It was the ninth month, on the twentieth of the month; and all the people sat in the open square of the house of God, trembling because of this matter and because of heavy rain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10010, 'Then Ezra the priest stood up and said to them, &ldquo;You have transgressed and have taken pagan wives, adding to the guilt of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10011, 'Now therefore, make confession to the Lord God of your fathers, and do His will; separate yourselves from the peoples of the land, and from the pagan wives.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10012, 'Then all the assembly answered and said with a loud voice, &ldquo;Yes! As you have said, so we must do. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10013, 'But there are many people; it is the season for heavy rain, and we are not able to stand outside. Nor is this the work of one or two days, for there are many of us who have transgressed in this matter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Ezra', 10014, 'Please, let the leaders of our entire assembly stand; and let all those in our cities who have taken pagan wives come at appointed times, together with the elders and judges of their cities, until the fierce wrath of our God is turned away from us in this matter.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1001, 'The words of Nehemiah the son of Hachaliah. It came to pass in the month of Chislev, in the twentieth year, as I was in Shushan the citadel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1002, 'that Hanani one of my brethren came with men from Judah; and I asked them concerning the Jews who had escaped, who had survived the captivity, and concerning Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1003, 'And they said to me, &ldquo;The survivors who are left from the captivity in the province are there in great distress and reproach. The wall of Jerusalem is also broken down, and its gates are burned with fire.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1004, 'So it was, when I heard these words, that I sat down and wept, and mourned for many days; I was fasting and praying before the God of heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1005, 'And I said: &ldquo;I pray, Lord God of heaven, O great and awesome God, You who keep Your covenant and mercy with those who love You and observe Your commandments, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1006, 'please let Your ear be attentive and Your eyes open, that You may hear the prayer of Your servant which I pray before You now, day and night, for the children of Israel Your servants, and confess the sins of the children of Israel which we have sinned against You. Both my father&rsquo;s house and I have sinned. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1007, 'We have acted very corruptly against You, and have not kept the commandments, the statutes, nor the ordinances which You commanded Your servant Moses. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1008, 'Remember, I pray, the word that You commanded Your servant Moses, saying, &lsquo;If you are unfaithful, I will scatter you among the nations;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1009, 'but if you return to Me, and keep My commandments and do them, though some of you were cast out to the farthest part of the heavens, yet I will gather them from there, and bring them to the place which I have chosen as a dwelling for My name.&rsquo;');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1010, 'Now these are Your servants and Your people, whom You have redeemed by Your great power, and by Your strong hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 1011, 'O Lord, I pray, please let Your ear be attentive to the prayer of Your servant, and to the prayer of Your servants who desire to fear Your name; and let Your servant prosper this day, I pray, and grant him mercy in the sight of this man.&rdquo; For I was the king&rsquo;s cupbearer. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2001, 'And it came to pass in the month of Nisan, in the twentieth year of King Artaxerxes, when wine was before him, that I took the wine and gave it to the king. Now I had never been sad in his presence before. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2002, 'Therefore the king said to me, &ldquo;Why is your face sad, since you are not sick? This is nothing but sorrow of heart.&rdquo; So I became dreadfully afraid, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2003, 'and said to the king, &ldquo;May the king live forever! Why should my face not be sad, when the city, the place of my fathers&rsquo; tombs, lies waste, and its gates are burned with fire?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2004, 'Then the king said to me, &ldquo;What do you request?&rdquo; So I prayed to the God of heaven. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2005, 'And I said to the king, &ldquo;If it pleases the king, and if your servant has found favor in your sight, I ask that you send me to Judah, to the city of my fathers&rsquo; tombs, that I may rebuild it.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2006, 'Then the king said to me (the queen also sitting beside him), &ldquo;How long will your journey be? And when will you return?&rdquo; So it pleased the king to send me; and I set him a time. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2007, 'Furthermore I said to the king, &ldquo;If it pleases the king, let letters be given to me for the governors of the region beyond the River, that they must permit me to pass through till I come to Judah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2008, 'and a letter to Asaph the keeper of the king&rsquo;s forest, that he must give me timber to make beams for the gates of the citadel which pertains to the temple, for the city wall, and for the house that I will occupy.&rdquo; And the king granted them to me according to the good hand of my God upon me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2009, 'Then I went to the governors in the region beyond the River, and gave them the king&rsquo;s letters. Now the king had sent captains of the army and horsemen with me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2010, 'When Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite official heard of it, they were deeply disturbed that a man had come to seek the well-being of the children of Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2011, 'So I came to Jerusalem and was there three days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2012, 'Then I arose in the night, I and a few men with me; I told no one what my God had put in my heart to do at Jerusalem; nor was there any animal with me, except the one on which I rode. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2013, 'And I went out by night through the Valley Gate to the Serpent Well and the Refuse Gate, and viewed the walls of Jerusalem which were broken down and its gates which were burned with fire. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2014, 'Then I went on to the Fountain Gate and to the King&rsquo;s Pool, but there was no room for the animal under me to pass. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2015, 'So I went up in the night by the valley, and viewed the wall; then I turned back and entered by the Valley Gate, and so returned. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2016, 'And the officials did not know where I had gone or what I had done; I had not yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the officials, or the others who did the work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2017, 'Then I said to them, &ldquo;You see the distress that we are in, how Jerusalem lies waste, and its gates are burned with fire. Come and let us build the wall of Jerusalem, that we may no longer be a reproach.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2018, 'And I told them of the hand of my God which had been good upon me, and also of the king&rsquo;s words that he had spoken to me. So they said, &ldquo;Let us rise up and build.&rdquo; Then they set their hands to this good work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2019, 'But when Sanballat the Horonite, Tobiah the Ammonite official, and Geshem the Arab heard of it, they laughed at us and despised us, and said, &ldquo;What is this thing that you are doing? Will you rebel against the king?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 2020, 'So I answered them, and said to them, &ldquo;The God of heaven Himself will prosper us; therefore we His servants will arise and build, but you have no heritage or right or memorial in Jerusalem.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3001, 'Then Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brethren the priests and built the Sheep Gate; they consecrated it and hung its doors. They built as far as the Tower of the Hundred,* and consecrated it, then as far as the Tower of Hananel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3002, 'Next to Eliashib the men of Jericho built. And next to them Zaccur the son of Imri built. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3003, 'Also the sons of Hassenaah built the Fish Gate; they laid its beams and hung its doors with its bolts and bars. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3004, 'And next to them Meremoth the son of Urijah, the son of Koz, made repairs. Next to them Meshullam the son of Berechiah, the son of Meshezabel, made repairs. Next to them Zadok the son of Baana made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3005, 'Next to them the Tekoites made repairs; but their nobles did not put their shoulders to the work of their Lord. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3006, 'Moreover Jehoiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam the son of Besodeiah repaired the Old Gate; they laid its beams and hung its doors, with its bolts and bars. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3007, 'And next to them Melatiah the Gibeonite, Jadon the Meronothite, the men of Gibeon and Mizpah, repaired the residence of the governor of the region beyond the River. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3008, 'Next to him Uzziel the son of Harhaiah, one of the goldsmiths, made repairs. Also next to him Hananiah, one of the perfumers, made repairs; and they fortified Jerusalem as far as the Broad Wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3009, 'And next to them Rephaiah the son of Hur, leader of half the district of Jerusalem, made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3010, 'Next to them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph made repairs in front of his house. And next to him Hattush the son of Hashabniah made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3011, 'Malchijah the son of Harim and Hashub the son of Pahath-Moab repaired another section, as well as the Tower of the Ovens. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3012, 'And next to him was Shallum the son of Hallohesh, leader of half the district of Jerusalem; he and his daughters made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3013, 'Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired the Valley Gate. They built it, hung its doors with its bolts and bars, and repaired a thousand cubits of the wall as far as the Refuse Gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3014, 'Malchijah the son of Rechab, leader of the district of Beth Haccerem, repaired the Refuse Gate; he built it and hung its doors with its bolts and bars. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3015, 'Shallun the son of Col-Hozeh, leader of the district of Mizpah, repaired the Fountain Gate; he built it, covered it, hung its doors with its bolts and bars, and repaired the wall of the Pool of Shelah by the King&rsquo;s Garden, as far as the stairs that go down from the City of David. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3016, 'After him Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, leader of half the district of Beth Zur, made repairs as far as the place in front of the tombs of David, to the man-made pool, and as far as the House of the Mighty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3017, 'After him the Levites, under Rehum the son of Bani, made repairs. Next to him Hashabiah, leader of half the district of Keilah, made repairs for his district. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3018, 'After him their brethren, under Bavai the son of Henadad, leader of the other half of the district of Keilah, made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3019, 'And next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, the leader of Mizpah, repaired another section in front of the Ascent to the Armory at the buttress. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3020, 'After him Baruch the son of Zabbai carefully repaired the other section, from the buttress to the door of the house of Eliashib the high priest. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3021, 'After him Meremoth the son of Urijah, the son of Koz, repaired another section, from the door of the house of Eliashib to the end of the house of Eliashib. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3022, 'And after him the priests, the men of the plain, made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3023, 'After him Benjamin and Hasshub made repairs opposite their house. After them Azariah the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ananiah, made repairs by his house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3024, 'After him Binnui the son of Henadad repaired another section, from the house of Azariah to the buttress, even as far as the corner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3025, 'Palal the son of Uzai made repairs opposite the buttress, and on the tower which projects from the king&rsquo;s upper house that was by the court of the prison. After him Pedaiah the son of Parosh made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3026, 'Moreover the Nethinim who dwelt in Ophel made repairs as far as the place in front of the Water Gate toward the east, and on the projecting tower. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3027, 'After them the Tekoites repaired another section, next to the great projecting tower, and as far as the wall of Ophel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3028, 'Beyond the Horse Gate the priests made repairs, each in front of his own house. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3029, 'After them Zadok the son of Immer made repairs in front of his own house. After him Shemaiah the son of Shechaniah, the keeper of the East Gate, made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3030, 'After him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah, and Hanun, the sixth son of Zalaph, repaired another section. After him Meshullam the son of Berechiah made repairs in front of his dwelling. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3031, 'After him Malchijah, one of the goldsmiths, made repairs as far as the house of the Nethinim and of the merchants, in front of the Miphkad Gate, and as far as the upper room at the corner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 3032, 'And between the upper room at the corner, as far as the Sheep Gate, the goldsmiths and the merchants made repairs. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4001, 'But it so happened, when Sanballat heard that we were rebuilding the wall, that he was furious and very indignant, and mocked the Jews. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4002, 'And he spoke before his brethren and the army of Samaria, and said, &ldquo;What are these feeble Jews doing? Will they fortify themselves? Will they offer sacrifices? Will they complete it in a day? Will they revive the stones from the heaps of rubbish &ndash; stones that are burned?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4003, 'Now Tobiah the Ammonite was beside him, and he said, &ldquo;Whatever they build, if even a fox goes up on it, he will break down their stone wall.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4004, 'Hear, O our God, for we are despised; turn their reproach on their own heads, and give them as plunder to a land of captivity! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4005, 'Do not cover their iniquity, and do not let their sin be blotted out from before You; for they have provoked You to anger before the builders. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4006, 'So we built the wall, and the entire wall was joined together up to half its height, for the people had a mind to work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4007, 'Now it happened, when Sanballat, Tobiah, the Arabs, the Ammonites, and the Ashdodites heard that the walls of Jerusalem were being restored and the gaps were beginning to be closed, that they became very angry, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4008, 'and all of them conspired together to come and attack Jerusalem and create confusion. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4009, 'Nevertheless we made our prayer to our God, and because of them we set a watch against them day and night. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4010, 'Then Judah said, &ldquo;The strength of the laborers is failing, and there is so much rubbish that we are not able to build the wall.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4011, 'And our adversaries said, &ldquo;They will neither know nor see anything, till we come into their midst and kill them and cause the work to cease.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4012, 'So it was, when the Jews who dwelt near them came, that they told us ten times, &ldquo;From whatever place you turn, they will be upon us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4013, 'Therefore I positioned men behind the lower parts of the wall, at the openings; and I set the people according to their families, with their swords, their spears, and their bows. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4014, 'And I looked, and arose and said to the nobles, to the leaders, and to the rest of the people, &ldquo;Do not be afraid of them. Remember the Lord, great and awesome, and fight for your brethren, your sons, your daughters, your wives, and your houses.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4015, 'And it happened, when our enemies heard that it was known to us, and that God had brought their plot to nothing, that all of us returned to the wall, everyone to his work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4016, 'So it was, from that time on, that half of my servants worked at construction, while the other half held the spears, the shields, the bows, and wore armor; and the leaders were behind all the house of Judah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4017, 'Those who built on the wall, and those who carried burdens, loaded themselves so that with one hand they worked at construction, and with the other held a weapon. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4018, 'Every one of the builders had his sword girded at his side as he built. And the one who sounded the trumpet was beside me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4019, 'Then I said to the nobles, the rulers, and the rest of the people, &ldquo;The work is great and extensive, and we are separated far from one another on the wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4020, 'Wherever you hear the sound of the trumpet, rally to us there. Our God will fight for us.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4021, 'So we labored in the work, and half of the men held the spears from daybreak until the stars appeared. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4022, 'At the same time I also said to the people, &ldquo;Let each man and his servant stay at night in Jerusalem, that they may be our guard by night and a working party by day.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 4023, 'So neither I, my brethren, my servants, nor the men of the guard who followed me took off our clothes, except that everyone took them off for washing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5001, 'And there was a great outcry of the people and their wives against their Jewish brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5002, 'For there were those who said, &ldquo;We, our sons, and our daughters are many; therefore let us get grain, that we may eat and live.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5003, 'There were also some who said, &ldquo;We have mortgaged our lands and vineyards and houses, that we might buy grain because of the famine.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5004, 'There were also those who said, &ldquo;We have borrowed money for the king&rsquo;s tax on our lands and vineyards. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5005, 'Yet now our flesh is as the flesh of our brethren, our children as their children; and indeed we are forcing our sons and our daughters to be slaves, and some of our daughters have been brought into slavery. It is not in our power to redeem them, for other men have our lands and vineyards.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5006, 'And I became very angry when I heard their outcry and these words. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5007, 'After serious thought, I rebuked the nobles and rulers, and said to them, &ldquo;Each of you is exacting usury from his brother.&rdquo; So I called a great assembly against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5008, 'And I said to them, &ldquo;According to our ability we have redeemed our Jewish brethren who were sold to the nations. Now indeed, will you even sell your brethren? Or should they be sold to us?&rdquo; Then they were silenced and found nothing to say. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5009, 'Then I said, &ldquo;What you are doing is not good. Should you not walk in the fear of our God because of the reproach of the nations, our enemies? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5010, 'I also, with my brethren and my servants, am lending them money and grain. Please, let us stop this usury! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5011, 'Restore now to them, even this day, their lands, their vineyards, their olive groves, and their houses, also a hundredth of the money and the grain, the new wine and the oil, that you have charged them.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5012, 'So they said, &ldquo;We will restore it, and will require nothing from them; we will do as you say.&rdquo; Then I called the priests, and required an oath from them that they would do according to this promise. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5013, 'Then I shook out the fold of my garment and said, &ldquo;So may God shake out each man from his house, and from his property, who does not perform this promise. Even thus may he be shaken out and emptied.&rdquo; And all the assembly said, &ldquo;Amen!&rdquo; and praised the Lord. Then the people did according to this promise. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5014, 'Moreover, from the time that I was appointed to be their governor in the land of Judah, from the twentieth year until the thirty-second year of King Artaxerxes, twelve years, neither I nor my brothers ate the governor&rsquo;s provisions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5015, 'But the former governors who were before me laid burdens on the people, and took from them bread and wine, besides forty shekels of silver. Yes, even their servants bore rule over the people, but I did not do so, because of the fear of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5016, 'Indeed, I also continued the work on this wall, and we did not buy any land. All my servants were gathered there for the work. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5017, 'And at my table were one hundred and fifty Jews and rulers, besides those who came to us from the nations around us. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5018, 'Now that which was prepared daily was one ox and six choice sheep. Also fowl were prepared for me, and once every ten days an abundance of all kinds of wine. Yet in spite of this I did not demand the governor&rsquo;s provisions, because the bondage was heavy on this people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 5019, 'Remember me, my God, for good, according to all that I have done for this people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6001, 'Now it happened when Sanballat, Tobiah, Geshem the Arab, and the rest of our enemies heard that I had rebuilt the wall, and that there were no breaks left in it (though at that time I had not hung the doors in the gates), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6002, 'that Sanballat and Geshem sent to me, saying, &ldquo;Come, let us meet together among the villages in the plain of Ono.&rdquo; But they thought to do me harm. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6003, 'So I sent messengers to them, saying, &ldquo;I am doing a great work, so that I cannot come down. Why should the work cease while I leave it and go down to you?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6004, 'But they sent me this message four times, and I answered them in the same manner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6005, 'Then Sanballat sent his servant to me as before, the fifth time, with an open letter in his hand. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6006, 'In it was written: It is reported among the nations, and Geshem says, that you and the Jews plan to rebel; therefore, according to these rumors, you are rebuilding the wall, that you may be their king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6007, 'And you have also appointed prophets to proclaim concerning you at Jerusalem, saying, &ldquo;There is a king in Judah!&rdquo; Now these matters will be reported to the king. So come, therefore, and let us consult together. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6008, 'Then I sent to him, saying, &ldquo;No such things as you say are being done, but you invent them in your own heart.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6009, 'For they all were trying to make us afraid, saying, &ldquo;Their hands will be weakened in the work, and it will not be done. &ldquo;Now therefore, O God, strengthen my hands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6010, 'Afterward I came to the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah, the son of Mehetabel, who was a secret informer; and he said, &ldquo;Let us meet together in the house of God, within the temple, and let us close the doors of the temple, for they are coming to kill you; indeed, at night they will come to kill you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6011, 'And I said, &ldquo;Should such a man as I flee? And who is there such as I who would go into the temple to save his life? I will not go in!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6012, 'Then I perceived that God had not sent him at all, but that he pronounced this prophecy against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6013, 'For this reason he was hired, that I should be afraid and act that way and sin, so that they might have cause for an evil report, that they might reproach me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6014, 'My God, remember Tobiah and Sanballat, according to these their works, and the prophetess Noadiah and the rest of the prophets who would have made me afraid. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6015, 'So the wall was finished on the twenty-fifth day of Elul, in fifty-two days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6016, 'And it happened, when all our enemies heard of it, and all the nations around us saw these things, that they were very disheartened in their own eyes; for they perceived that this work was done by our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6017, 'Also in those days the nobles of Judah sent many letters to Tobiah, and the letters of Tobiah came to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6018, 'For many in Judah were pledged to him, because he was the son-in-law of Shechaniah the son of Arah, and his son Jehohanan had married the daughter of Meshullam the son of Berechiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 6019, 'Also they reported his good deeds before me, and reported my words to him. Tobiah sent letters to frighten me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7001, 'Then it was, when the wall was built and I had hung the doors, when the gatekeepers, the singers, and the Levites had been appointed, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7002, 'that I gave the charge of Jerusalem to my brother Hanani, and Hananiah the leader of the citadel, for he was a faithful man and feared God more than many. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7003, 'And I said to them, &ldquo;Do not let the gates of Jerusalem be opened until the sun is hot; and while they stand guard, let them shut and bar the doors; and appoint guards from among the inhabitants of Jerusalem, one at his watch station and another in front of his own house.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7004, 'Now the city was large and spacious, but the people in it were few, and the houses were not rebuilt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7005, 'Then my God put it into my heart to gather the nobles, the rulers, and the people, that they might be registered by genealogy. And I found a register of the genealogy of those who had come up in the first return, and found written in it: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7006, 'These are the people of the province who came back from the captivity, of those who had been carried away, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away, and who returned to Jerusalem and Judah, everyone to his city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7007, 'Those who came with Zerubbabel were Jeshua, Nehemiah, Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, and Baanah. The number of the men of the people of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7008, 'the sons of Parosh, two thousand one hundred and seventy-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7009, 'the sons of Shephatiah, three hundred and seventy-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7010, 'the sons of Arah, six hundred and fifty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7011, 'the sons of Pahath-Moab, of the sons of Jeshua and Joab, two thousand eight hundred and eighteen; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7012, 'the sons of Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7013, 'the sons of Zattu, eight hundred and forty-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7014, 'the sons of Zaccai, seven hundred and sixty; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7015, 'the sons of Binnui, six hundred and forty-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7016, 'the sons of Bebai, six hundred and twenty-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7017, 'the sons of Azgad, two thousand three hundred and twenty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7018, 'the sons of Adonikam, six hundred and sixty-seven; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7019, 'the sons of Bigvai, two thousand and sixty-seven; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7020, 'the sons of Adin, six hundred and fifty-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7021, 'the sons of Ater of Hezekiah, ninety-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7022, 'the sons of Hashum, three hundred and twenty-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7023, 'the sons of Bezai, three hundred and twenty-four; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7024, 'the sons of Hariph, one hundred and twelve; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7025, 'the sons of Gibeon, ninety-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7026, 'the men of Bethlehem and Netophah, one hundred and eighty-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7027, 'the men of Anathoth, one hundred and twenty-eight; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7028, 'the men of Beth Azmaveth, forty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7029, 'the men of Kirjath Jearim, Chephirah, and Beeroth, seven hundred and forty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7030, 'the men of Ramah and Geba, six hundred and twenty-one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7031, 'the men of Michmas, one hundred and twenty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7032, 'the men of Bethel and Ai, one hundred and twenty-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7033, 'the men of the other Nebo, fifty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7034, 'the sons of the other Elam, one thousand two hundred and fifty-four; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7035, 'the sons of Harim, three hundred and twenty; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7036, 'the sons of Jericho, three hundred and forty-five; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7037, 'the sons of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, seven hundred and twenty-one; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7038, 'the sons of Senaah, three thousand nine hundred and thirty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7039, 'The priests: the sons of Jedaiah, of the house of Jeshua, nine hundred and seventy-three; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7040, 'the sons of Immer, one thousand and fifty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7041, 'the sons of Pashhur, one thousand two hundred and forty-seven; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7042, 'the sons of Harim, one thousand and seventeen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7043, 'The Levites: the sons of Jeshua, of Kadmiel, and of the sons of Hodevah, seventy-four. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7044, 'The singers: the sons of Asaph, one hundred and forty-eight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7045, 'The gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, the sons of Shobai, one hundred and thirty-eight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7046, 'The Nethinim: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons of Tabbaoth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7047, 'the sons of Keros, the sons of Sia, the sons of Padon, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7048, 'the sons of Lebana, F31 the sons of Hagaba, F32 the sons of Salmai, F33 ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7049, 'the sons of Hanan, the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7050, 'the sons of Reaiah, the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7051, 'the sons of Gazzam, the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7052, 'the sons of Besai, the sons of Meunim, the sons of Nephishesim, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7053, 'the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7054, 'the sons of Bazlith, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7055, 'the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Tamah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7056, 'the sons of Neziah, and the sons of Hatipha. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7057, 'The sons of Solomon&rsquo;s servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Sophereth, the sons of Perida,');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7058, 'the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7059, 'the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth of Zebaim, and the sons of Amon.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7060, 'All the Nethinim, and the sons of Solomon&rsquo;s servants, were three hundred and ninety-two. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7061, 'And these were the ones who came up from Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Cherub, Addon, and Immer, but they could not identify their father&rsquo;s house nor their lineage, whether they were of Israel: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7062, 'the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, six hundred and forty-two; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7063, 'and of the priests: the sons of Habaiah, the sons of Koz, the sons of Barzillai, who took a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite, and was called by their name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7064, 'These sought their listing among those who were registered by genealogy, but it was not found; therefore they were excluded from the priesthood as defiled. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7065, 'And the governor said to them that they should not eat of the most holy things till a priest could consult with the Urim and Thummim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7066, 'Altogether the whole assembly was forty-two thousand three hundred and sixty, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7067, 'besides their male and female servants, of whom there were seven thousand three hundred and thirty-seven; and they had two hundred and forty-five men and women singers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7068, 'Their horses were seven hundred and thirty-six, their mules two hundred and forty-five, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7069, 'their camels four hundred and thirty-five, and donkeys six thousand seven hundred and twenty. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7070, 'And some of the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses gave to the work. The governor gave to the treasury one thousand gold drachmas, fifty basins, and five hundred and thirty priestly garments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7071, 'Some of the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses gave to the treasury of the work twenty thousand gold drachmas, and two thousand two hundred silver minas. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7072, 'And that which the rest of the people gave was twenty thousand gold drachmas, two thousand silver minas, and sixty-seven priestly garments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 7073, 'So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of the people, the Nethinim, and all Israel dwelt in their cities.When the seventh month came, the children of Israel were in their cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8001, 'Now all the people gathered together as one man in the open square that was in front of the Water Gate; and they told Ezra the scribe to bring the Book of the Law of Moses, which the Lord had commanded Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8002, 'So Ezra the priest brought the Law before the assembly of men and women and all who could hear with understanding on the first day of the seventh month. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8003, 'Then he read from it in the open square that was in front of the Water Gate from morning until midday, before the men and women and those who could understand; and the ears of all the people were attentive to the Book of the Law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8004, 'So Ezra the scribe stood on a platform of wood which they had made for the purpose; and beside him, at his right hand, stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Urijah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah; and at his left hand Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum, Hashbadana, Zechariah, and Meshullam. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8005, 'And Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, for he was standing above all the people; and when he opened it, all the people stood up. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8006, 'And Ezra blessed the Lord, the great God. Then all the people answered, &ldquo;Amen, Amen!&rdquo; while lifting up their hands. And they bowed their heads and worshiped the Lord with their faces to the ground. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8007, 'Also Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodijah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, and the Levites, helped the people to understand the Law; and the people stood in their place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8008, 'So they read distinctly from the book, in the Law of God; and they gave the sense, and helped them to understand the reading. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8009, 'And Nehemiah, who was the governor, Ezra the priest and scribe, and the Levites who taught the people said to all the people, &ldquo;This day is holy to the Lord your God; do not mourn nor weep.&rdquo; For all the people wept, when they heard the words of the Law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8010, 'Then he said to them, &ldquo;Go your way, eat the fat, drink the sweet, and send portions to those for whom nothing is prepared; for this day is holy to our Lord. Do not sorrow, for the joy of the Lord is your strength.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8011, 'So the Levites quieted all the people, saying, &ldquo;Be still, for the day is holy; do not be grieved.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8012, 'And all the people went their way to eat and drink, to send portions and rejoice greatly, because they understood the words that were declared to them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8013, 'Now on the second day the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses of all the people, with the priests and Levites, were gathered to Ezra the scribe, in order to understand the words of the Law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8014, 'And they found written in the Law, which the Lord had commanded by Moses, that the children of Israel should dwell in booths during the feast of the seventh month, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8015, 'and that they should announce and proclaim in all their cities and in Jerusalem, saying, &ldquo;Go out to the mountain, and bring olive branches, branches of oil trees, myrtle branches, palm branches, and branches of leafy trees, to make booths, as it is written.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8016, 'Then the people went out and brought them and made themselves booths, each one on the roof of his house, or in their courtyards or the courts of the house of God, and in the open square of the Water Gate and in the open square of the Gate of Ephraim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8017, 'So the whole assembly of those who had returned from the captivity made booths and sat under the booths; for since the days of Joshua the son of Nun until that day the children of Israel had not done so. And there was very great gladness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 8018, 'Also day by day, from the first day until the last day, he read from the Book of the Law of God. And they kept the feast seven days; and on the eighth day there was a sacred assembly, according to the prescribed manner. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9001, 'Now on the twenty-fourth day of this month the children of Israel were assembled with fasting, in sackcloth, and with dust on their heads.* ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9002, 'Then those of Israelite lineage separated themselves from all foreigners; and they stood and confessed their sins and the iniquities of their fathers. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9003, 'And they stood up in their place and read from the Book of the Law of the Lord their God for one-fourth of the day; and for another fourth they confessed and worshiped the Lord their God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9004, 'Then Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani stood on the stairs of the Levites and cried out with a loud voice to the Lord their God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9005, 'And the Levites, Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabniah, Sherebiah, Hodijah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah, said: &ldquo;Stand up and bless the Lord your God Forever and ever! &ldquo;Blessed be Your glorious name, Which is exalted above all blessing and praise! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9006, 'You alone are the Lord; You have made heaven, The heaven of heavens, with all their host, The earth and everything on it, The seas and all that is in them, And You preserve them all. The host of heaven worships You. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9007, 'You are the Lord God, Who chose Abram, And brought him out of Ur of the Chaldeans, And gave him the name Abraham; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9008, 'You found his heart faithful before You, And made a covenant with him To give the land of the Canaanites, The Hittites, the Amorites, The Perizzites, the Jebusites, And the Girgashites &ndash; To give it to his descendants. You have performed Your words, For You are righteous. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9009, 'You saw the affliction of our fathers in Egypt, And heard their cry by the Red Sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9010, 'You showed signs and wonders against Pharaoh, Against all his servants, And against all the people of his land. For You knew that they acted proudly against them. So You made a name for Yourself, as it is this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9011, 'And You divided the sea before them, So that they went through the midst of the sea on the dry land; And their persecutors You threw into the deep, As a stone into the mighty waters. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9012, 'Moreover You led them by day with a cloudy pillar, And by night with a pillar of fire, To give them light on the road Which they should travel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9013, 'You came down also on Mount Sinai, And spoke with them from heaven, And gave them just ordinances and true laws, Good statutes and commandments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9014, 'You made known to them Your holy Sabbath, And commanded them precepts, statutes and laws, By the hand of Moses Your servant. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9015, 'You gave them bread from heaven for their hunger, And brought them water out of the rock for their thirst, And told them to go in to possess the land Which You had sworn to give them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9016, 'But they and our fathers acted proudly, Hardened their necks, And did not heed Your commandments. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9017, 'They refused to obey, And they were not mindful of Your wonders That You did among them. But they hardened their necks, And in their rebellion They appointed a leader To return to their bondage. But You are God, Ready to pardon, Gracious and merciful, Slow to anger, Abundant in kindness, And did not forsake them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9018, 'Even when they made a molded calf for themselves, And said, &lsquo;This is your god That brought you up out of Egypt,&rsquo; And worked great provocations, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9019, 'Yet in Your manifold mercies You did not forsake them in the wilderness. The pillar of the cloud did not depart from them by day, To lead them on the road; Nor the pillar of fire by night, To show them light, And the way they should go. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9020, 'You also gave Your good Spirit to instruct them, And did not withhold Your manna from their mouth, And gave them water for their thirst. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9021, 'Forty years You sustained them in the wilderness, They lacked nothing; Their clothes did not wear out And their feet did not swell. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9022, 'Moreover You gave them kingdoms and nations, And divided them into districts. F45 So they took possession of the land of Sihon, The land of F46 the king of Heshbon, And the land of Og king of Bashan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9023, 'You also multiplied their children as the stars of heaven, And brought them into the land Which You had told their fathers To go in and possess. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9024, 'So the people went in And possessed the land; You subdued before them the inhabitants of the land, The Canaanites, And gave them into their hands, With their kings And the people of the land, That they might do with them as they wished. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9025, 'And they took strong cities and a rich land, And possessed houses full of all goods, Cisterns already dug, vineyards, olive groves, And fruit trees in abundance. So they ate and were filled and grew fat, And delighted themselves in Your great goodness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9026, 'Nevertheless they were disobedient And rebelled against You, Cast Your law behind their backs And killed Your prophets, who testified against them To turn them to Yourself; And they worked great provocations. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9027, 'Therefore You delivered them into the hand of their enemies, Who oppressed them; And in the time of their trouble, When they cried to You, You heard from heaven; And according to Your abundant mercies You gave them deliverers who saved them From the hand of their enemies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9028, 'But after they had rest, They again did evil before You. Therefore You left them in the hand of their enemies, So that they had dominion over them; Yet when they returned and cried out to You, You heard from heaven; And many times You delivered them according to Your mercies, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9029, 'And testified against them, That You might bring them back to Your law. Yet they acted proudly, And did not heed Your commandments, But sinned against Your judgments, &lsquo;Which if a man does, he shall live by them.&rsquo; And they shrugged their shoulders, Stiffened their necks, And would not hear. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9030, 'Yet for many years You had patience with them, And testified against them by Your Spirit in Your prophets. Yet they would not listen; Therefore You gave them into the hand of the peoples of the lands. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9031, 'Nevertheless in Your great mercy You did not utterly consume them nor forsake them; For You are God, gracious and merciful. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9032, 'Now therefore, our God, The great, the mighty, and awesome God, Who keeps covenant and mercy: Do not let all the trouble seem small before You That has come upon us, Our kings and our princes, Our priests and our prophets, Our fathers and on all Your people, From the days of the kings of Assyria until this day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9033, 'However You are just in all that has befallen us; For You have dealt faithfully, But we have done wickedly. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9034, 'Neither our kings nor our princes, Our priests nor our fathers, Have kept Your law, Nor heeded Your commandments and Your testimonies, With which You testified against them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 9035, 'For they have not served You in their kingdom, Or in the many good things that You gave them, Or in the large and rich land which You set before them; Nor did they turn from their wicked works. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10001, 'Now those who placed their seal on the document were: Nehemiah the governor, the son of Hacaliah, and Zedekiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10002, 'Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10003, 'Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10004, 'Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10005, 'Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10006, 'Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10007, 'Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10008, 'Maaziah, Bilgai, and Shemaiah. These were the priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10009, 'The Levites: Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of Henadad, and Kadmiel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10010, 'Their brethren: Shebaniah, Hodijah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10011, 'Micha, Rehob, Hashabiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10012, 'Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10013, 'Hodijah, Bani, and Beninu. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10014, 'The leaders of the people: Parosh, Pahath-Moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10015, 'Bunni, Azgad, Bebai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10016, 'Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10017, 'Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10018, 'Hodijah, Hashum, Bezai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10019, 'Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10020, 'Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10021, 'Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10022, 'Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10023, 'Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10024, 'Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10025, 'Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10026, 'Ahijah, Hanan, Anan, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10027, 'Malluch, Harim, and Baanah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10028, 'Now the rest of the people &ndash; the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, the Nethinim, and all those who had separated themselves from the peoples of the lands to the Law of God, their wives, their sons, and their daughters, everyone who had knowledge and understanding &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10029, 'these joined with their brethren, their nobles, and entered into a curse and an oath to walk in God&rsquo;s Law, which was given by Moses the servant of God, and to observe and do all the commandments of the Lord our Lord, and His ordinances and His statutes: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10030, 'We would not give our daughters as wives to the peoples of the land, nor take their daughters for our sons; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10031, 'if the peoples of the land brought wares or any grain to sell on the Sabbath day, we would not buy it from them on the Sabbath, or on a holy day; and we would forego the seventh year&rsquo;s produce and the exacting of every debt. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10032, 'Also we made ordinances for ourselves, to exact from ourselves yearly one-third of a shekel for the service of the house of our God: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10033, 'for the showbread, for the regular grain offering, for the regular burnt offering of the Sabbaths, the New Moons, and the set feasts; for the holy things, for the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and all the work of the house of our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10034, 'We cast lots among the priests, the Levites, and the people, for bringing the wood offering into the house of our God, according to our fathers&rsquo; houses, at the appointed times year by year, to burn on the altar of the Lord our God as it is written in the Law. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10035, 'And we made ordinances to bring the firstfruits of our ground and the firstfruits of all fruit of all trees, year by year, to the house of the Lord; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10036, 'to bring the firstborn of our sons and our cattle, as it is written in the Law, and the firstborn of our herds and our flocks, to the house of our God, to the priests who minister in the house of our God; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10037, 'to bring the firstfruits of our dough, our offerings, the fruit from all kinds of trees, the new wine and oil, to the priests, to the storerooms of the house of our God; and to bring the tithes of our land to the Levites, for the Levites should receive the tithes in all our farming communities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10038, 'And the priest, the descendant of Aaron, shall be with the Levites when the Levites receive tithes; and the Levites shall bring up a tenth of the tithes to the house of our God, to the rooms of the storehouse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 10039, 'For the children of Israel and the children of Levi shall bring the offering of the grain, of the new wine and the oil, to the storerooms where the articles of the sanctuary are, where the priests who minister and the gatekeepers and the singers are; and we will not neglect the house of our God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11001, 'Now the leaders of the people dwelt at Jerusalem; the rest of the people cast lots to bring one out of ten to dwell in Jerusalem, the holy city, and nine-tenths were to dwell in other cities. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11002, 'And the people blessed all the men who willingly offered themselves to dwell at Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11003, 'These are the heads of the province who dwelt in Jerusalem. (But in the cities of Judah everyone dwelt in his own possession in their cities &ndash; Israelites, priests, Levites, Nethinim, and descendants of Solomon&rsquo;s servants.) ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11004, 'Also in Jerusalem dwelt some of the children of Judah and of the children of Benjamin.The children of Judah: Athaiah the son of Uzziah, the son of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel, of the children of Perez; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11005, 'and Maaseiah the son of Baruch, the son of Col-Hozeh, the son of Hazaiah, the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, the son of Shiloni. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11006, 'All the sons of Perez who dwelt at Jerusalem were four hundred and sixty-eight valiant men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11007, 'And these are the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ithiel, the son of Jeshaiah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11008, 'and after him Gabbai and Sallai, nine hundred and twenty-eight. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11009, 'Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer, and Judah the son of Senuah was second over the city. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11010, 'Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, and Jachin; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11011, 'Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, was the leader of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11012, 'Their brethren who did the work of the house were eight hundred and twenty-two; and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11013, 'and his brethren, heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses, were two hundred and forty-two; and Amashai the son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of Immer, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11014, 'and their brethren, mighty men of valor, were one hundred and twenty-eight. Their overseer was Zabdiel the son of one of the great men.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11015, 'Also of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11016, 'Shabbethai and Jozabad, of the heads of the Levites, had the oversight of the business outside of the house of God; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11017, 'Mattaniah the son of Micha, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, the leader who began the thanksgiving with prayer; Bakbukiah, the second among his brethren; and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11018, 'All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred and eighty-four. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11019, 'Moreover the gatekeepers, Akkub, Talmon, and their brethren who kept the gates, were one hundred and seventy-two. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11020, 'And the rest of Israel, of the priests and Levites, were in all the cities of Judah, everyone in his inheritance. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11021, 'But the Nethinim dwelt in Ophel. And Ziha and Gishpa were over the Nethinim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11022, 'Also the overseer of the Levites at Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micha, of the sons of Asaph, the singers in charge of the service of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11023, 'For it was the king&rsquo;s command concerning them that a certain portion should be for the singers, a quota day by day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11024, 'Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the children of Zerah the son of Judah, was the king&rsquo;s deputy in all matters concerning the people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11025, 'And as for the villages with their fields, some of the children of Judah dwelt in Kirjath Arba and its villages, Dibon and its villages, Jekabzeel and its villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11026, 'in Jeshua, Moladah, Beth Pelet, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11027, 'Hazar Shual, and Beersheba and its villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11028, 'in Ziklag and Meconah and its villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11029, 'in En Rimmon, Zorah, Jarmuth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11030, 'Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages; in Lachish and its fields; in Azekah and its villages. They dwelt from Beersheba to the Valley of Hinnom. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11031, 'Also the children of Benjamin from Geba dwelt in Michmash, Aija, and Bethel, and their villages; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11032, 'in Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11033, 'in Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11034, 'in Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11035, 'in Lod, Ono, and the Valley of Craftsmen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 11036, 'Some of the Judean divisions of Levites were in Benjamin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12001, 'Now these are the priests and the Levites who came up with Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12002, 'Amariah, Malluch, Hattush, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12003, 'Shechaniah, Rehum, Meremoth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12004, 'Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12005, 'Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12006, 'Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12007, 'Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, and Jedaiah. These were the heads of the priests and their brethren in the days of Jeshua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12008, 'Moreover the Levites were Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah who led the thanksgiving psalms, he and his brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12009, 'Also Bakbukiah and Unni, their brethren, stood across from them in their duties. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12010, 'Jeshua begot Joiakim, Joiakim begot Eliashib, Eliashib begot Joiada, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12011, 'Joiada begot Jonathan, and Jonathan begot Jaddua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12012, 'Now in the days of Joiakim, the priests, the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses were: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12013, 'of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12014, 'of Melichu, F53 Jonathan; of Shebaniah, F54 Joseph; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12015, 'of Harim, F55 Adna; of Meraioth, F56 Helkai; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12016, 'of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12017, 'of Abijah, Zichri; the son of Minjamin; F57 of Moadiah, F58 Piltai; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12018, 'of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12019, 'of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12020, 'of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12021, 'of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; and of Jedaiah, Nethanel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12022, 'During the reign of Darius the Persian, a record was also kept of the Levites and priests who had been heads of their fathers&rsquo; houses in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan, and Jaddua. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12023, 'The sons of Levi, the heads of the fathers&rsquo; houses until the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib, were written in the book of the chronicles. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12024, 'And the heads of the Levites were Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua the son of Kadmiel, with their brothers across from them, to praise and give thanks, group alternating with group, according to the command of David the man of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12025, 'Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were gatekeepers keeping the watch at the storerooms of the gates. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12026, 'These lived in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor, and of Ezra the priest, the scribe. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12027, 'Now at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought out the Levites in all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem to celebrate the dedication with gladness, both with thanksgivings and singing, with cymbals and stringed instruments and harps. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12028, 'And the sons of the singers gathered together from the countryside around Jerusalem, from the villages of the Netophathites, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12029, 'from the house of Gilgal, and from the fields of Geba and Azmaveth; for the singers had built themselves villages all around Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12030, 'Then the priests and Levites purified themselves, and purified the people, the gates, and the wall. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12031, 'So I brought the leaders of Judah up on the wall, and appointed two large thanksgiving choirs. One went to the right hand on the wall toward the Refuse Gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12032, 'After them went Hoshaiah and half of the leaders of Judah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12033, 'and Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12034, 'Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, Jeremiah, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12035, 'and some of the priests&rsquo; sons with trumpets &ndash; Zechariah the son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Michaiah, the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12036, 'and his brethren, Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel, Judah, and Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God. Ezra the scribe went before them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12037, 'By the Fountain Gate, in front of them, they went up the stairs of the City of David, on the stairway of the wall, beyond the house of David, as far as the Water Gate eastward. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12038, 'The other thanksgiving choir went the opposite way, and I was behind them with half of the people on the wall, going past the Tower of the Ovens as far as the Broad Wall, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12039, 'and above the Gate of Ephraim, above the Old Gate, above the Fish Gate, the Tower of Hananel, the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the Sheep Gate; and they stopped by the Gate of the Prison. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12040, 'So the two thanksgiving choirs stood in the house of God, likewise I and the half of the rulers with me; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12041, 'and the priests, Eliakim, Maaseiah, Minjamin, F61 Michaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah, with trumpets; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12042, 'also Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam, and Ezer. The singers sang loudly with Jezrahiah the director. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12043, 'Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced, for God had made them rejoice with great joy; the women and the children also rejoiced, so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard afar off. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12044, 'And at the same time some were appointed over the rooms of the storehouse for the offerings, the firstfruits, and the tithes, to gather into them from the fields of the cities the portions specified by the Law for the priests and Levites; for Judah rejoiced over the priests and Levites who ministered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12045, 'Both the singers and the gatekeepers kept the charge of their God and the charge of the purification, according to the command of David and Solomon his son. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12046, 'For in the days of David and Asaph of old there were chiefs of the singers, and songs of praise and thanksgiving to God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 12047, 'In the days of Zerubbabel and in the days of Nehemiah all Israel gave the portions for the singers and the gatekeepers, a portion for each day. They also consecrated holy things for the Levites, and the Levites consecrated them for the children of Aaron. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13001, 'On that day they read from the Book of Moses in the hearing of the people, and in it was found written that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever come into the assembly of God, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13002, 'because they had not met the children of Israel with bread and water, but hired Balaam against them to curse them. However, our God turned the curse into a blessing. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13003, 'So it was, when they had heard the Law, that they separated all the mixed multitude from Israel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13004, 'Now before this, Eliashib the priest, having authority over the storerooms of the house of our God, was allied with Tobiah. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13005, 'And he had prepared for him a large room, where previously they had stored the grain offerings, the frankincense, the articles, the tithes of grain, the new wine and oil, which were commanded to be given to the Levites and singers and gatekeepers, and the offerings for the priests. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13006, 'But during all this I was not in Jerusalem, for in the thirty-second year of Artaxerxes king of Babylon I had returned to the king. Then after certain days I obtained leave from the king, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13007, 'and I came to Jerusalem and discovered the evil that Eliashib had done for Tobiah, in preparing a room for him in the courts of the house of God. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13008, 'And it grieved me bitterly; therefore I threw all the household goods of Tobiah out of the room. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13009, 'Then I commanded them to cleanse the rooms; and I brought back into them the articles of the house of God, with the grain offering and the frankincense. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13010, 'I also realized that the portions for the Levites had not been given them; for each of the Levites and the singers who did the work had gone back to his field. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13011, 'So I contended with the rulers, and said, Why is the house of God forsaken? And I gathered them together and set them in their place. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13012, 'Then all Judah brought the tithe of the grain and the new wine and the oil to the storehouse. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13013, 'And I appointed as treasurers over the storehouse Shelemiah the priest and Zadok the scribe, and of the Levites, Pedaiah; and next to them was Hanan the son of Zaccur, the son of Mattaniah; for they were considered faithful, and their task was to distribute to their brethren. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13014, 'Remember me, O my God, concerning this, and do not wipe out my good deeds that I have done for the house of my God, and for its services! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13015, 'In those days I saw people in Judah treading wine presses on the Sabbath, and bringing in sheaves, and loading donkeys with wine, grapes, figs, and all kinds of burdens, which they brought into Jerusalem on the Sabbath day. And I warned them about the day on which they were selling provisions. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13016, 'Men of Tyre dwelt there also, who brought in fish and all kinds of goods, and sold them on the Sabbath to the children of Judah, and in Jerusalem. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13017, 'Then I contended with the nobles of Judah, and said to them, What evil thing is this that you do, by which you profane the Sabbath day? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13018, 'Did not your fathers do thus, and did not our God bring all this disaster on us and on this city? Yet you bring added wrath on Israel by profaning the Sabbath.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13019, 'So it was, at the gates of Jerusalem, as it began to be dark before the Sabbath, that I commanded the gates to be shut, and charged that they must not be opened till after the Sabbath. Then I posted some of my servants at the gates, so that no burdens would be brought in on the Sabbath day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13020, 'Now the merchants and sellers of all kinds of wares lodged outside Jerusalem once or twice. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13021, 'Then I warned them, and said to them, &ldquo;Why do you spend the night around the wall? If you do so again, I will lay hands on you!&rdquo; From that time on they came no more on the Sabbath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13022, 'And I commanded the Levites that they should cleanse themselves, and that they should go and guard the gates, to sanctify the Sabbath day. Remember me, O my God, concerning this also, and spare me according to the greatness of Your mercy! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13023, 'In those days I also saw Jews who had married women of Ashdod, Ammon, and Moab. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13024, 'And half of their children spoke the language of Ashdod, and could not speak the language of Judah, but spoke according to the language of one or the other people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13025, 'So I contended with them and cursed them, struck some of them and pulled out their hair, and made them swear by God, saying, &ldquo;You shall not give your daughters as wives to their sons, nor take their daughters for your sons or yourselves. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13026, 'Did not Solomon king of Israel sin by these things? Yet among many nations there was no king like him, who was beloved of his God; and God made him king over all Israel. Nevertheless pagan women caused even him to sin. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13027, 'Should we then hear of your doing all this great evil, transgressing against our God by marrying pagan women?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13028, 'And one of the sons of Joiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest, was a son-in-law of Sanballat the Horonite; therefore I drove him from me. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13029, 'Remember them, O my God, because they have defiled the priesthood and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13030, 'Thus I cleansed them of everything pagan. I also assigned duties to the priests and the Levites, each to his service, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Neh', 13031, 'and to bringing the wood offering and the firstfruits at appointed times.Remember me, O my God, for good! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1001, 'Now it came to pass in the days of Ahasuerus (this was the Ahasuerus who reigned over one hundred and twenty-seven provinces, from India to Ethiopia), ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1002, 'in those days when King Ahasuerus sat on the throne of his kingdom, which was in Shushan the citadel, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1003, 'that in the third year of his reign he made a feast for all his officials and servants &ndash; the powers of Persia and Media, the nobles, and the princes of the provinces being before him &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1004, 'when he showed the riches of his glorious kingdom and the splendor of his excellent majesty for many days, one hundred and eighty days in all. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1005, 'And when these days were completed, the king made a feast lasting seven days for all the people who were present in Shushan the citadel, from great to small, in the court of the garden of the king&rsquo;s palace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1006, 'There were white and blue linen curtains fastened with cords of fine linen and purple on silver rods and marble pillars; and the couches were of gold and silver on a mosaic pavement of alabaster, turquoise, and white and black marble. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1007, 'And they served drinks in golden vessels, each vessel being different from the other, with royal wine in abundance, according to the generosity of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1008, 'In accordance with the law, the drinking was not compulsory; for so the king had ordered all the officers of his household, that they should do according to each man&rsquo;s pleasure. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1009, 'Queen Vashti also made a feast for the women in the royal palace which belonged to King Ahasuerus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1010, 'On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine, he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, Abagtha, Zethar, and Carcas, seven eunuchs who served in the presence of King Ahasuerus, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1011, 'to bring Queen Vashti before the king, wearing her royal crown, in order to show her beauty to the people and the officials, for she was beautiful to behold. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1012, 'But Queen Vashti refused to come at the king&rsquo;s command brought by his eunuchs; therefore the king was furious, and his anger burned within him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1013, 'Then the king said to the wise men who understood the times (for this was the king&rsquo;s manner toward all who knew law and justice, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1014, 'those closest to him being Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media, who had access to the king&rsquo;s presence, and who ranked highest in the kingdom): ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1015, 'What shall we do to Queen Vashti, according to law, because she did not obey the command of King Ahasuerus brought to her by the eunuchs? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1016, 'And Memucan answered before the king and the princes: &ldquo;Queen Vashti has not only wronged the king, but also all the princes, and all the people who are in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1017, 'For the queen&rsquo;s behavior will become known to all women, so that they will despise their husbands in their eyes, when they report, &lsquo;King Ahasuerus commanded Queen Vashti to be brought in before him, but she did not come.&rsquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1018, 'This very day the noble ladies of Persia and Media will say to all the king&rsquo;s officials that they have heard of the behavior of the queen. Thus there will be excessive contempt and wrath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1019, 'If it pleases the king, let a royal decree go out from him, and let it be recorded in the laws of the Persians and the Medes, so that it will not be altered, that Vashti shall come no more before King Ahasuerus; and let the king give her royal position to another who is better than she. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1020, 'When the king&rsquo;s decree which he will make is proclaimed throughout all his empire (for it is great), all wives will honor their husbands, both great and small.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1021, 'And the reply pleased the king and the princes, and the king did according to the word of Memucan. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 1022, 'Then he sent letters to all the king&rsquo;s provinces, to each province in its own script, and to every people in their own language, that each man should be master in his own house, and speak in the language of his own people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2001, 'After these things, when the wrath of King Ahasuerus subsided, he remembered Vashti, what she had done, and what had been decreed against her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2002, 'Then the king&rsquo;s servants who attended him said: &ldquo;Let beautiful young virgins be sought for the king; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2003, 'and let the king appoint officers in all the provinces of his kingdom, that they may gather all the beautiful young virgins to Shushan the citadel, into the women&rsquo;s quarters, under the custody of Hegai the king&rsquo;s eunuch, custodian of the women. And let beauty preparations be given them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2004, 'Then let the young woman who pleases the king be queen instead of Vashti.&rdquo; This thing pleased the king, and he did so. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2005, 'In Shushan the citadel there was a certain Jew whose name was Mordecai the son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish, a Benjamite. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2006, 'Kish F4 had been carried away from Jerusalem with the captives who had been captured with Jeconiah F5 king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2007, 'And Mordecai had brought up Hadassah, that is, Esther, his uncle&rsquo;s daughter, for she had neither father nor mother. The young woman was lovely and beautiful. When her father and mother died, Mordecai took her as his own daughter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2008, 'So it was, when the king&rsquo;s command and decree were heard, and when many young women were gathered at Shushan the citadel, under the custody of Hegai, that Esther also was taken to the king&rsquo;s palace, into the care of Hegai the custodian of the women. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2009, 'Now the young woman pleased him, and she obtained his favor; so he readily gave beauty preparations to her, besides her allowance. Then seven choice maidservants were provided for her from the king&rsquo;s palace, and he moved her and her maidservants to the best place in the house of the women. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2010, 'Esther had not revealed her people or family, for Mordecai had charged her not to reveal it. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2011, 'And every day Mordecai paced in front of the court of the women&rsquo;s quarters, to learn of Esther&rsquo;s welfare and what was happening to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2012, 'Each young woman&rsquo;s turn came to go in to King Ahasuerus after she had completed twelve months&rsquo; preparation, according to the regulations for the women, for thus were the days of their preparation apportioned: six months with oil of myrrh, and six months with perfumes and preparations for beautifying women. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2013, 'Thus prepared, each young woman went to the king, and she was given whatever she desired to take with her from the women&rsquo;s quarters to the king&rsquo;s palace. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2014, 'In the evening she went, and in the morning she returned to the second house of the women, to the custody of Shaashgaz, the king&rsquo;s eunuch who kept the concubines. She would not go in to the king again unless the king delighted in her and called for her by name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2015, 'Now when the turn came for Esther the daughter of Abihail the uncle of Mordecai, who had taken her as his daughter, to go in to the king, she requested nothing but what Hegai the king&rsquo;s eunuch, the custodian of the women, advised. And Esther obtained favor in the sight of all who saw her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2016, 'So Esther was taken to King Ahasuerus, into his royal palace, in the tenth month, which is the month of Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2017, 'The king loved Esther more than all the other women, and she obtained grace and favor in his sight more than all the virgins; so he set the royal crown upon her head and made her queen instead of Vashti. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2018, 'Then the king made a great feast, the Feast of Esther, for all his officials and servants; and he proclaimed a holiday in the provinces and gave gifts according to the generosity of a king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2019, 'When virgins were gathered together a second time, Mordecai sat within the king&rsquo;s gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2020, 'Now Esther had not revealed her family and her people, just as Mordecai had charged her, for Esther obeyed the command of Mordecai as when she was brought up by him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2021, 'In those days, while Mordecai sat within the king&rsquo;s gate, two of the king&rsquo;s eunuchs, Bigthan and Teresh, doorkeepers, became furious and sought to lay hands on King Ahasuerus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2022, 'So the matter became known to Mordecai, who told Queen Esther, and Esther informed the king in Mordecai&rsquo;s name. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 2023, 'And when an inquiry was made into the matter, it was confirmed, and both were hanged on a gallows; and it was written in the book of the chronicles in the presence of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3001, 'After these things King Ahasuerus promoted Haman, the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, and advanced him and set his seat above all the princes who were with him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3002, 'And all the king&rsquo;s servants who were within the king&rsquo;s gate bowed and paid homage to Haman, for so the king had commanded concerning him. But Mordecai would not bow or pay homage. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3003, 'Then the king&rsquo;s servants who were within the king&rsquo;s gate said to Mordecai, &ldquo;Why do you transgress the king&rsquo;s command?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3004, 'Now it happened, when they spoke to him daily and he would not listen to them, that they told it to Haman, to see whether Mordecai&rsquo;s words would stand; for Mordecai had told them that he was a Jew. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3005, 'When Haman saw that Mordecai did not bow or pay him homage, Haman was filled with wrath. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3006, 'But he disdained to lay hands on Mordecai alone, for they had told him of the people of Mordecai. Instead, Haman sought to destroy all the Jews who were throughout the whole kingdom of Ahasuerus &ndash; the people of Mordecai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3007, 'In the first month, which is the month of Nisan, in the twelfth year of King Ahasuerus, they cast Pur (that is, the lot), before Haman to determine the day and the month, F6 until it fell on the twelfth month, F7 which is the month of Adar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3008, 'Then Haman said to King Ahasuerus, &ldquo;There is a certain people scattered and dispersed among the people in all the provinces of your kingdom; their laws are different from all other people&rsquo;s, and they do not keep the king&rsquo;s laws. Therefore it is not fitting for the king to let them remain. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3009, 'If it pleases the king, let a decree be written that they be destroyed, and I will pay ten thousand talents of silver into the hands of those who do the work, to bring it into the king&rsquo;s treasuries.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3010, 'So the king took his signet ring from his hand and gave it to Haman, the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the enemy of the Jews. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3011, 'And the king said to Haman, &ldquo;The money and the people are given to you, to do with them as seems good to you.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3012, 'Then the king&rsquo;s scribes were called on the thirteenth day of the first month, and a decree was written according to all that Haman commanded &ndash; to the king&rsquo;s satraps, to the governors who were over each province, to the officials of all people, to every province according to its script, and to every people in their language. In the name of King Ahasuerus it was written, and sealed with the king&rsquo;s signet ring. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3013, 'And the letters were sent by couriers into all the king&rsquo;s provinces, to destroy, to kill, and to annihilate all the Jews, both young and old, little children and women, in one day, on the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month of Adar, and to plunder their possessions.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3014, 'A copy of the document was to be issued as law in every province, being published for all people, that they should be ready for that day. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 3015, 'The couriers went out, hastened by the king&rsquo;s command; and the decree was proclaimed in Shushan the citadel. So the king and Haman sat down to drink, but the city of Shushan was perplexed. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4001, 'When Mordecai learned all that had happened, he tore his clothes and put on sackcloth and ashes, and went out into the midst of the city. He cried out with a loud and bitter cry. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4002, 'He went as far as the front of the king&rsquo;s gate, for no one might enter the king&rsquo;s gate clothed with sackcloth. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4003, 'And in every province where the king&rsquo;s command and decree arrived, there was great mourning among the Jews, with fasting, weeping, and wailing; and many lay in sackcloth and ashes. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4004, 'So Esther&rsquo;s maids and eunuchs came and told her, and the queen was deeply distressed. Then she sent garments to clothe Mordecai and take his sackcloth away from him, but he would not accept them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4005, 'Then Esther called Hathach, one of the king&rsquo;s eunuchs whom he had appointed to attend her, and she gave him a command concerning Mordecai, to learn what and why this was. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4006, 'So Hathach went out to Mordecai in the city square that was in front of the king&rsquo;s gate. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4007, 'And Mordecai told him all that had happened to him, and the sum of money that Haman had promised to pay into the king&rsquo;s treasuries to destroy the Jews. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4008, 'He also gave him a copy of the written decree for their destruction, which was given at Shushan, that he might show it to Esther and explain it to her, and that he might command her to go in to the king to make supplication to him and plead before him for her people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4009, 'So Hathach returned and told Esther the words of Mordecai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4010, 'Then Esther spoke to Hathach, and gave him a command for Mordecai: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4011, 'All the king&rsquo;s servants and the people of the king&rsquo;s provinces know that any man or woman who goes into the inner court to the king, who has not been called, he has but one law: put all to death, except the one to whom the king holds out the golden scepter, that he may live. Yet I myself have not been called to go in to the king these thirty days. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4012, 'So they told Mordecai Esther&rsquo;s words. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4013, 'And Mordecai told them to answer Esther: &ldquo;Do not think in your heart that you will escape in the king&rsquo;s palace any more than all the other Jews. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4014, 'For if you remain completely silent at this time, relief and deliverance will arise for the Jews from another place, but you and your father&rsquo;s house will perish. Yet who knows whether you have come to the kingdom for such a time as this?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4015, 'Then Esther told them to reply to Mordecai: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4016, 'Go, gather all the Jews who are present in Shushan, and fast for me; neither eat nor drink for three days, night or day. My maids and I will fast likewise. And so I will go to the king, which is against the law; and if I perish, I perish! ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 4017, 'So Mordecai went his way and did according to all that Esther commanded him.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5001, 'Now it happened on the third day that Esther put on her royal robes and stood in the inner court of the king&rsquo;s palace, across from the king&rsquo;s house, while the king sat on his royal throne in the royal house, facing the entrance of the house.* ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5002, 'So it was, when the king saw Queen Esther standing in the court, that she found favor in his sight, and the king held out to Esther the golden scepter that was in his hand. Then Esther went near and touched the top of the scepter. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5003, 'And the king said to her, &ldquo;What do you wish, Queen Esther? What is your request? It shall be given to you &ndash; up to half the kingdom!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5004, 'So Esther answered, &ldquo;If it pleases the king, let the king and Haman come today to the banquet that I have prepared for him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5005, 'Then the king said, &ldquo;Bring Haman quickly, that he may do as Esther has said.&rdquo; So the king and Haman went to the banquet that Esther had prepared. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5006, 'At the banquet of wine the king said to Esther, &ldquo;What is your petition? It shall be granted you. What is your request, up to half the kingdom? It shall be done!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5007, 'Then Esther answered and said, &ldquo;My petition and request is this: ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5008, 'If I have found favor in the sight of the king, and if it pleases the king to grant my petition and fulfill my request, then let the king and Haman come to the banquet which I will prepare for them, and tomorrow I will do as the king has said.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5009, 'So Haman went out that day joyful and with a glad heart; but when Haman saw Mordecai in the king&rsquo;s gate, and that he did not stand or tremble before him, he was filled with indignation against Mordecai. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5010, 'Nevertheless Haman restrained himself and went home, and he sent and called for his friends and his wife Zeresh. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5011, 'Then Haman told them of his great riches, the multitude of his children, everything in which the king had promoted him, and how he had advanced him above the officials and servants of the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5012, 'Moreover Haman said, &ldquo;Besides, Queen Esther invited no one but me to come in with the king to the banquet that she prepared; and tomorrow I am again invited by her, along with the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5013, 'Yet all this avails me nothing, so long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king&rsquo;s gate.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 5014, 'Then his wife Zeresh and all his friends said to him, &ldquo;Let a gallows be made, fifty cubits high, and in the morning suggest to the king that Mordecai be hanged on it; then go merrily with the king to the banquet.&rdquo; And the thing pleased Haman; so he had the gallows made. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6001, 'That night the king could not sleep. So one was commanded to bring the book of the records of the chronicles; and they were read before the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6002, 'And it was found written that Mordecai had told of Bigthana and Teresh, two of the king&rsquo;s eunuchs, the doorkeepers who had sought to lay hands on King Ahasuerus. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6003, 'Then the king said, &ldquo;What honor or dignity has been bestowed on Mordecai for this?&rdquo; And the king&rsquo;s servants who attended him said, &ldquo;Nothing has been done for him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6004, 'So the king said, &ldquo;Who is in the court?&rdquo; Now Haman had just entered the outer court of the king&rsquo;s palace to suggest that the king hang Mordecai on the gallows that he had prepared for him. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6005, 'The king&rsquo;s servants said to him, &ldquo;Haman is there, standing in the court.&rdquo; And the king said, &ldquo;Let him come in.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6006, 'So Haman came in, and the king asked him, &ldquo;What shall be done for the man whom the king delights to honor?&rdquo; Now Haman thought in his heart, &ldquo;Whom would the king delight to honor more than me?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6007, 'And Haman answered the king, &ldquo;For the man whom the king delights to honor, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6008, 'let a royal robe be brought which the king has worn, and a horse on which the king has ridden, which has a royal crest placed on its head. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6009, 'Then let this robe and horse be delivered to the hand of one of the king&rsquo;s most noble princes, that he may array the man whom the king delights to honor. Then parade him on horseback through the city square, and proclaim before him: &lsquo;Thus shall it be done to the man whom the king delights to honor!&rsquo; &ldquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6010, 'Then the king said to Haman, &ldquo;Hurry, take the robe and the horse, as you have suggested, and do so for Mordecai the Jew who sits within the king&rsquo;s gate! Leave nothing undone of all that you have spoken.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6011, 'So Haman took the robe and the horse, arrayed Mordecai and led him on horseback through the city square, and proclaimed before him, &ldquo;Thus shall it be done to the man whom the king delights to honor!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6012, 'Afterward Mordecai went back to the king&rsquo;s gate. But Haman hurried to his house, mourning and with his head covered. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6013, 'When Haman told his wife Zeresh and all his friends everything that had happened to him, his wise men and his wife Zeresh said to him, &ldquo;If Mordecai, before whom you have begun to fall, is of Jewish descent, you will not prevail against him but will surely fall before him.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 6014, 'While they were still talking with him, the king&rsquo;s eunuchs came, and hastened to bring Haman to the banquet which Esther had prepared. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7001, 'So the king and Haman went to dine with Queen Esther. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7002, 'And on the second day, at the banquet of wine, the king again said to Esther, &ldquo;What is your petition, Queen Esther? It shall be granted you. And what is your request, up to half the kingdom? It shall be done!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7003, 'Then Queen Esther answered and said, &ldquo;If I have found favor in your sight, O king, and if it pleases the king, let my life be given me at my petition, and my people at my request. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7004, 'For we have been sold, my people and I, to be destroyed, to be killed, and to be annihilated. Had we been sold as male and female slaves, I would have held my tongue, although the enemy could never compensate for the king&rsquo;s loss.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7005, 'So King Ahasuerus answered and said to Queen Esther, &ldquo;Who is he, and where is he, who would dare presume in his heart to do such a thing?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7006, 'And Esther said, &ldquo;The adversary and enemy is this wicked Haman!&rdquo; So Haman was terrified before the king and queen. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7007, 'Then the king arose in his wrath from the banquet of wine and went into the palace garden; but Haman stood before Queen Esther, pleading for his life, for he saw that evil was determined against him by the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7008, 'When the king returned from the palace garden to the place of the banquet of wine, Haman had fallen across the couch where Esther was. Then the king said, &ldquo;Will he also assault the queen while I am in the house?&rdquo; As the word left the king&rsquo;s mouth, they covered Haman&rsquo;s face. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7009, 'Now Harbonah, one of the eunuchs, said to the king, &ldquo;Look! The gallows, fifty cubits high, which Haman made for Mordecai, who spoke good on the king&rsquo;s behalf, is standing at the house of Haman.&rdquo; Then the king said, &ldquo;Hang him on it!&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 7010, 'So they hanged Haman on the gallows that he had prepared for Mordecai. Then the king&rsquo;s wrath subsided. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8001, 'On that day King Ahasuerus gave Queen Esther the house of Haman, the enemy of the Jews. And Mordecai came before the king, for Esther had told how he was related to her. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8002, 'So the king took off his signet ring, which he had taken from Haman, and gave it to Mordecai; and Esther appointed Mordecai over the house of Haman. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8003, 'Now Esther spoke again to the king, fell down at his feet, and implored him with tears to counteract the evil of Haman the Agagite, and the scheme which he had devised against the Jews. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8004, 'And the king held out the golden scepter toward Esther. So Esther arose and stood before the king, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8005, 'and said, &ldquo;If it pleases the king, and if I have found favor in his sight and the thing seems right to the king and I am pleasing in his eyes, let it be written to revoke the letters devised by Haman, the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, which he wrote to annihilate the Jews who are in all the king&rsquo;s provinces. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8006, 'For how can I endure to see the evil that will come to my people? Or how can I endure to see the destruction of my countrymen?&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8007, 'Then King Ahasuerus said to Queen Esther and Mordecai the Jew, &ldquo;Indeed, I have given Esther the house of Haman, and they have hanged him on the gallows because he tried to lay his hand on the Jews. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8008, 'You yourselves write a decree concerning the Jews, as you please, in the king&rsquo;s name, and seal it with the king&rsquo;s signet ring; for whatever is written in the king&rsquo;s name and sealed with the king&rsquo;s signet ring no one can revoke.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8009, 'So the king&rsquo;s scribes were called at that time, in the third month, which is the month of Sivan, on the twenty-third day; and it was written, according to all that Mordecai commanded, to the Jews, the satraps, the governors, and the princes of the provinces from India to Ethiopia, one hundred and twenty-seven provinces in all, to every province in its own script, to every people in their own language, and to the Jews in their own script and language. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8010, 'And he wrote in the name of King Ahasuerus, sealed it with the king&rsquo;s signet ring, and sent letters by couriers on horseback, riding on royal horses bred from swift steeds.');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8011, 'By these letters the king permitted the Jews who were in every city to gather together and protect their lives &ndash; to destroy, kill, and annihilate all the forces of any people or province that would assault them, both little children and women, and to plunder their possessions, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8012, 'on one day in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus, on the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month of Adar. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8013, 'A copy of the document was to be issued as a decree in every province and published for all people, so that the Jews would be ready on that day to avenge themselves on their enemies. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8014, 'The couriers who rode on royal horses went out, hastened and pressed on by the king&rsquo;s command. And the decree was issued in Shushan the citadel. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8015, 'So Mordecai went out from the presence of the king in royal apparel of blue and white, with a great crown of gold and a garment of fine linen and purple; and the city of Shushan rejoiced and was glad. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8016, 'The Jews had light and gladness, joy and honor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 8017, 'And in every province and city, wherever the king&rsquo;s command and decree came, the Jews had joy and gladness, a feast and a holiday. Then many of the people of the land became Jews, because fear of the Jews fell upon them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9001, 'Now in the twelfth month, that is, the month of Adar, on the thirteenth day, the time came for the king&rsquo;s command and his decree to be executed. On the day that the enemies of the Jews had hoped to overpower them, the opposite occurred, in that the Jews themselves overpowered those who hated them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9002, 'The Jews gathered together in their cities throughout all the provinces of King Ahasuerus to lay hands on those who sought their harm. And no one could withstand them, because fear of them fell upon all people. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9003, 'And all the officials of the provinces, the satraps, the governors, and all those doing the king&rsquo;s work, helped the Jews, because the fear of Mordecai fell upon them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9004, 'For Mordecai was great in the king&rsquo;s palace, and his fame spread throughout all the provinces; for this man Mordecai became increasingly prominent. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9005, 'Thus the Jews defeated all their enemies with the stroke of the sword, with slaughter and destruction, and did what they pleased with those who hated them. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9006, 'And in Shushan the citadel the Jews killed and destroyed five hundred men. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9007, 'Also Parshandatha, Dalphon, Aspatha, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9008, 'Poratha, Adalia, Aridatha, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9009, 'Parmashta, Arisai, Aridai, and Vajezatha &ndash; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9010, 'the ten sons of Haman the son of Hammedatha, the enemy of the Jews &ndash; they killed; but they did not lay a hand on the plunder. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9011, 'On that day the number of those who were killed in Shushan the citadel was brought to the king. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9012, 'And the king said to Queen Esther, &ldquo;The Jews have killed and destroyed five hundred men in Shushan the citadel, and the ten sons of Haman. What have they done in the rest of the king&rsquo;s provinces? Now what is your petition? It shall be granted to you. Or what is your further request? It shall be done.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9013, 'Then Esther said, &ldquo;If it pleases the king, let it be granted to the Jews who are in Shushan to do again tomorrow according to today&rsquo;s decree, and let Haman&rsquo;s ten sons be hanged on the gallows.&rdquo; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9014, 'So the king commanded this to be done; the decree was issued in Shushan, and they hanged Haman&rsquo;s ten sons. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9015, 'And the Jews who were in Shushan gathered together again on the fourteenth day of the month of Adar and killed three hundred men at Shushan; but they did not lay a hand on the plunder. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9016, 'The remainder of the Jews in the king&rsquo;s provinces gathered together and protected their lives, had rest from their enemies, and killed seventy-five thousand of their enemies; but they did not lay a hand on the plunder. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9017, 'This was on the thirteenth day of the month of Adar. And on the fourteenth day of the month they rested and made it a day of feasting and gladness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9018, 'But the Jews who were at Shushan assembled together on the thirteenth day, as well as on the fourteenth; and on the fifteenth of the month they rested, and made it a day of feasting and gladness. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9019, 'Therefore the Jews of the villages who dwelt in the unwalled towns celebrated the fourteenth day of the month of Adar with gladness and feasting, as a holiday, and for sending presents to one another. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9020, 'And Mordecai wrote these things and sent letters to all the Jews, near and far, who were in all the provinces of King Ahasuerus, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9021, 'to establish among them that they should celebrate yearly the fourteenth and fifteenth days of the month of Adar, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9022, 'as the days on which the Jews had rest from their enemies, as the month which was turned from sorrow to joy for them, and from mourning to a holiday; that they should make them days of feasting and joy, of sending presents to one another and gifts to the poor. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9023, 'So the Jews accepted the custom which they had begun, as Mordecai had written to them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9024, 'because Haman, the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the enemy of all the Jews, had plotted against the Jews to annihilate them, and had cast Pur (that is, the lot), to consume them and destroy them; ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9025, 'but when Esther F14 came before the king, he commanded by letter that this F15 wicked plot which Haman had devised against the Jews should return on his own head, and that he and his sons should be hanged on the gallows. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9026, 'So they called these days Purim, after the name Pur. Therefore, because of all the words of this letter, what they had seen concerning this matter, and what had happened to them, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9027, 'the Jews established and imposed it upon themselves and their descendants and all who would join them, that without fail they should celebrate these two days every year, according to the written instructions and according to the prescribed time, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9028, 'that these days should be remembered and kept throughout every generation, every family, every province, and every city, that these days of Purim should not fail to be observed among the Jews, and that the memory of them should not perish among their descendants. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9029, 'Then Queen Esther, the daughter of Abihail, with Mordecai the Jew, wrote with full authority to confirm this second letter about Purim. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9030, 'And Mordecai sent letters to all the Jews, to the one hundred and twenty-seven provinces of the kingdom of Ahasuerus, with words of peace and truth, ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9031, 'to confirm these days of Purim at their appointed time, as Mordecai the Jew and Queen Esther had prescribed for them, and as they had decreed for themselves and their descendants concerning matters of their fasting and lamenting. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 9032, 'So the decree of Esther confirmed these matters of Purim, and it was written in the book. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 10001, 'And King Ahasuerus imposed tribute on the land and on the islands of the sea. ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 10002, 'Now all the acts of his power and his might, and the account of the greatness of Mordecai, to which the king advanced him, are they not written in the book of the chronicles of the kings of Media and Persia? ');
INSERT INTO scriptures VALUES (0, 1, 'Esth', 10003, 'For Mordecai the Jew was second to King Ahasuerus, and was great among the Jews and well received by the multitude of his brethren, seeking the good of his people and speaking peace to all his countrymen. ');
